{"mode":"editor","version":1,"windowDimensions":{"x":254,"y":23,"width":1024,"height":752,"maximized":false},"grammars":{"deserializer":"GrammarRegistry","grammarOverridesByPath":{}},"project":{"paths":["/Users/joegesualdo/Documents/movies/Casablanca (1942)"],"buffers":[{"load":true,"text":"﻿1\r\n00:01:02,528 --> 00:01:05,277\r\nNARRATOR: With the coming\r\nof the Second World War...\r\n\r\n2\r\n00:01:05,477 --> 00:01:10,060\r\n...many eyes in imprisoned Europe\r\nturned hopefuIly or desperately...\r\n\r\n3\r\n00:01:10,299 --> 00:01:12,212\r\n...toward the freedom of the Americas.\r\n\r\n4\r\n00:01:12,452 --> 00:01:14,922\r\nLisbon became\r\nthe great embarkation point.\r\n\r\n5\r\n00:01:15,161 --> 00:01:18,031\r\nBut not everybody couId get\r\nto Lisbon directly.\r\n\r\n6\r\n00:01:18,671 --> 00:01:22,176\r\nAnd so a torturous, roundabout\r\nrefugee trail sprang up.\r\n\r\n7\r\n00:01:23,174 --> 00:01:25,166\r\nParis to MarseiIles.\r\n\r\n8\r\n00:01:30,427 --> 00:01:33,335\r\nAcross the Mediterranean to Oran.\r\n\r\n9\r\n00:01:40,033 --> 00:01:44,137\r\nThen by train or auto or foot\r\nacross the rim of Africa...\r\n\r\n10\r\n00:01:44,376 --> 00:01:46,846\r\n...to Casablanca in French Morocco.\r\n\r\n11\r\n00:01:47,127 --> 00:01:51,471\r\nHere, the fortunate ones,\r\nthrough money or influence or Iuck...\r\n\r\n12\r\n00:01:52,029 --> 00:01:55,097\r\n...might obtain exit visas\r\nand scurry to Lisbon.\r\n\r\n13\r\n00:01:55,296 --> 00:01:57,409\r\nAnd from Lisbon to the New World.\r\n\r\n14\r\n00:01:57,648 --> 00:02:01,275\r\nBut the others wait in Casablanca.\r\n\r\n15\r\n00:02:01,474 --> 00:02:02,870\r\nAnd wait...\r\n\r\n16\r\n00:02:03,070 --> 00:02:04,663\r\n...and wait...\r\n\r\n17\r\n00:02:04,862 --> 00:02:06,416\r\n...and wait.\r\n\r\n18\r\n00:02:15,823 --> 00:02:17,258\r\n\"To all officers:\r\n\r\n19\r\n00:02:17,458 --> 00:02:22,120\r\nTwo German couriers carrying official\r\ndocuments murdered on train from Oran.\r\n\r\n20\r\n00:02:22,320 --> 00:02:25,148\r\nMurderer and possible accomplices\r\nheaded for Casablanca.\r\n\r\n21\r\n00:02:25,388 --> 00:02:29,175\r\nRound up all suspicious characters\r\nand search them for stolen document.\r\n\r\n22\r\n00:02:29,415 --> 00:02:30,689\r\nImportant.\"\r\n\r\n23\r\n00:02:31,567 --> 00:02:32,522\r\n(WHISTLE)\r\n\r\n24\r\n00:02:37,108 --> 00:02:38,262\r\n(IN FRENCH)\r\n\r\n25\r\n00:03:01,101 --> 00:03:02,455\r\nMay we see your papers?\r\n\r\n26\r\n00:03:02,774 --> 00:03:04,248\r\nI don't have them on me.\r\n\r\n27\r\n00:03:04,488 --> 00:03:06,560\r\nIn that case,\r\nyou'll have to come along.\r\n\r\n28\r\n00:03:06,760 --> 00:03:10,186\r\nIt's possibIe that I....\r\nYes. Here they are.\r\n\r\n29\r\n00:03:13,018 --> 00:03:16,364\r\nThese papers expired three weeks ago.\r\nYou'll have to come along.\r\n\r\n30\r\n00:03:18,159 --> 00:03:19,393\r\nOFFlCER:\r\nHalt!\r\n\r\n31\r\n00:03:19,873 --> 00:03:21,346\r\n(GUNSHOT)\r\n\r\n32\r\n00:03:43,309 --> 00:03:45,779\r\nWOMAN: What is going on?\r\nMAN: l don't know, my dear.\r\n\r\n33\r\n00:03:45,979 --> 00:03:48,290\r\nPardon me. Have you not heard?\r\n\r\n34\r\n00:03:48,489 --> 00:03:51,079\r\nWe hear very Iittle\r\nand we understand even less.\r\n\r\n35\r\n00:03:51,319 --> 00:03:54,906\r\nTwo German couriers were found\r\nmurdered in the unoccupied desert.\r\n\r\n36\r\n00:03:55,185 --> 00:03:57,734\r\nThis is the customary\r\nroundup of refugees, liberals...\r\n\r\n37\r\n00:03:58,055 --> 00:04:01,044\r\n...and beautifuI girls for Mr. RenauIt,\r\nthe prefect of police.\r\n\r\n38\r\n00:04:05,827 --> 00:04:09,334\r\nWith these refugees, the scum\r\nof Europe has gravitated to Casablanca.\r\n\r\n39\r\n00:04:09,534 --> 00:04:11,845\r\nSome have been waiting\r\nyears for a visa.\r\n\r\n40\r\n00:04:12,085 --> 00:04:15,192\r\nI beg of you, monsieur.\r\nWatch yourself. Be on guard.\r\n\r\n41\r\n00:04:15,392 --> 00:04:17,265\r\nThis pIace is full of vuItures.\r\n\r\n42\r\n00:04:17,505 --> 00:04:20,174\r\nVultures everywhere. Everywhere.\r\n\r\n43\r\n00:04:20,414 --> 00:04:22,924\r\n-Thank you. Thank you very much.\r\n-Not at all.\r\n\r\n44\r\n00:04:24,878 --> 00:04:26,632\r\nAmusing little fellow.\r\n\r\n45\r\n00:04:26,871 --> 00:04:28,066\r\nWaiter.\r\n\r\n46\r\n00:04:29,302 --> 00:04:31,096\r\n-How silly of me.\r\n-What, dear?\r\n\r\n47\r\n00:04:31,296 --> 00:04:33,806\r\nI've Ieft my wallet in the hotel.\r\n\r\n48\r\n00:04:34,084 --> 00:04:35,918\r\n(AIRPLANE APPROACHES)\r\n\r\n49\r\n00:04:48,951 --> 00:04:50,823\r\nPerhaps tomorrow\r\nwe'lI be on the plane.\r\n\r\n50\r\n00:05:14,938 --> 00:05:16,571\r\n(OFFICERS IN GERMAN)\r\n\r\n51\r\n00:05:16,811 --> 00:05:18,644\r\nIt is good to see you,\r\nMaj. Strasser.\r\n\r\n52\r\n00:05:18,844 --> 00:05:19,920\r\nThank you, thank you.\r\n\r\n53\r\n00:05:20,198 --> 00:05:22,948\r\nMay I present Capt. Renault,\r\nthe police prefect.\r\n\r\n54\r\n00:05:24,544 --> 00:05:26,296\r\nUnoccupied France welcomes you.\r\n\r\n55\r\n00:05:26,735 --> 00:05:28,330\r\nThank you, it's good to be here.\r\n\r\n56\r\n00:05:28,647 --> 00:05:31,199\r\nMaj. Strasser, my aide,\r\nLt. Casselle.\r\n\r\n57\r\n00:05:31,478 --> 00:05:34,985\r\n-Capt. ToneIli, the ltalian service--\r\n-That is kind of you.\r\n\r\n58\r\n00:05:35,224 --> 00:05:37,337\r\n(TONELLI lN ITALlAN)\r\n\r\n59\r\n00:05:37,576 --> 00:05:39,768\r\n(CASSELLE lN FRENCH)\r\n\r\n60\r\n00:05:41,202 --> 00:05:43,872\r\nYou may find the climate\r\nof Casablanca a trifIe warm.\r\n\r\n61\r\n00:05:44,112 --> 00:05:47,619\r\nWe Germans must get used to alI\r\nclimates, from Russia to the Sahara.\r\n\r\n62\r\n00:05:47,820 --> 00:05:50,648\r\n-But you're not referring to the weather.\r\n-What else?\r\n\r\n63\r\n00:05:50,888 --> 00:05:52,800\r\nWhat's been done about the murders?\r\n\r\n64\r\n00:05:53,001 --> 00:05:56,707\r\nMy men are rounding up twice\r\nthe usual number of suspects.\r\n\r\n65\r\n00:05:56,906 --> 00:05:59,775\r\n-But we know who the murderer is.\r\n-Good. ls he in custody?\r\n\r\n66\r\n00:05:59,975 --> 00:06:02,765\r\nTonight he'll be at Rick's.\r\nEverybody comes to Rick's.\r\n\r\n67\r\n00:06:02,965 --> 00:06:06,551\r\nI've already heard about this cafè.\r\nAlso about Mr. Rick himself.\r\n\r\n68\r\n00:06:15,161 --> 00:06:17,790\r\n(SAM SINGS \"lT HAD TO BE YOU\")\r\n\r\n69\r\n00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:01,752\r\nWaiting, waiting, waiting.\r\n\r\n70\r\n00:07:01,993 --> 00:07:03,904\r\nI'll never get out of here.\r\n\r\n71\r\n00:07:04,145 --> 00:07:05,738\r\nI'll die in Casablanca.\r\n\r\n72\r\n00:07:06,018 --> 00:07:09,166\r\nBut can't you make it\r\njust a little more, please?\r\n\r\n73\r\n00:07:09,365 --> 00:07:12,353\r\nSorry, but diamonds are\r\na drag on the market.\r\n\r\n74\r\n00:07:12,595 --> 00:07:15,023\r\nThere are diamonds everywhere.\r\nTwenty-four hundred.\r\n\r\n75\r\n00:07:15,224 --> 00:07:16,221\r\nAlI right.\r\n\r\n76\r\n00:07:16,619 --> 00:07:20,085\r\nThe trucks are waiting.\r\nThe men are waiting. Everything--\r\n\r\n77\r\n00:07:22,956 --> 00:07:24,829\r\nIt's the fishing smack Santiago.\r\n\r\n78\r\n00:07:25,030 --> 00:07:28,855\r\nIt Ieaves at one tomorrow night.\r\nFrom the end of the marina.\r\n\r\n79\r\n00:07:29,014 --> 00:07:29,970\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\n80\r\n00:07:30,171 --> 00:07:32,641\r\nAnd bring 1 5,000 francs in cash.\r\n\r\n81\r\n00:07:32,840 --> 00:07:35,031\r\nRemember, in cash.\r\n\r\n82\r\n00:07:39,736 --> 00:07:41,130\r\n(IN RUSSIAN)\r\n\r\n83\r\n00:07:41,489 --> 00:07:43,044\r\nCheerio.\r\n\r\n84\r\n00:07:43,403 --> 00:07:46,072\r\nCARL: Open up, Abdul.\r\nABDUL: Yes, professor.\r\n\r\n85\r\n00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:56,395\r\n-Waiter?\r\n-Yes, madame?\r\n\r\n86\r\n00:07:56,596 --> 00:07:59,065\r\nWiIl you ask Rick\r\nif he'lI have a drink with us?\r\n\r\n87\r\n00:07:59,306 --> 00:08:03,170\r\nMadame, he never drinks with customers.\r\nNever. I've never seen it.\r\n\r\n88\r\n00:08:03,372 --> 00:08:05,442\r\nWOMAN:\r\nWhat makes saIoonkeepers so snobbish?\r\n\r\n89\r\n00:08:05,684 --> 00:08:09,308\r\nPerhaps if you told him I ran\r\nthe second Iargest bank in Amsterdam.\r\n\r\n90\r\n00:08:09,509 --> 00:08:12,097\r\nThe second Iargest?\r\nThat wouldn't impress Rick.\r\n\r\n91\r\n00:08:12,339 --> 00:08:15,525\r\nThe leading banker in Amsterdam\r\nis now the pastry chef here.\r\n\r\n92\r\n00:08:15,727 --> 00:08:18,235\r\nWe have something to Iook forward to.\r\n\r\n93\r\n00:08:19,473 --> 00:08:21,224\r\nAnd his father is the bellboy.\r\n\r\n94\r\n00:08:21,385 --> 00:08:22,423\r\nGood!\r\n\r\n95\r\n00:08:23,936 --> 00:08:25,610\r\nMonsieur?\r\n\r\n96\r\n00:08:50,082 --> 00:08:51,517\r\nABDUL:\r\nExcuse me.\r\n\r\n97\r\n00:08:53,868 --> 00:08:55,860\r\nI'm sorry, sir.\r\nThis is a private room.\r\n\r\n98\r\n00:08:56,061 --> 00:08:59,848\r\nOf aIl the nerve! Who do you think--\r\nI know there is gambling in there!\r\n\r\n99\r\n00:09:00,047 --> 00:09:01,123\r\nYou dare not keep me out!\r\n\r\n100\r\n00:09:01,362 --> 00:09:02,557\r\nRICK:\r\nWhat's the trouble?\r\n\r\n101\r\n00:09:02,836 --> 00:09:05,585\r\nI have been in every gambIing room\r\nfrom Honolulu to Berlin.\r\n\r\n102\r\n00:09:05,826 --> 00:09:09,531\r\nIf you think l'Il be kept out\r\nof a saIoon like this, you're mistaken.\r\n\r\n103\r\n00:09:09,691 --> 00:09:10,648\r\nExcuse me, please.\r\n\r\n104\r\n00:09:10,808 --> 00:09:11,763\r\nUGARTE:\r\nHello, Rick.\r\n\r\n105\r\n00:09:14,315 --> 00:09:15,988\r\nYour cash is good at the bar.\r\n\r\n106\r\n00:09:16,348 --> 00:09:17,940\r\nWhat? Do you know who I am?\r\n\r\n107\r\n00:09:18,141 --> 00:09:20,134\r\nI do. You're lucky\r\nthe bar is open to you.\r\n\r\n108\r\n00:09:20,334 --> 00:09:23,322\r\nThis is outrageous!\r\nI shalI report it to the angriff !\r\n\r\n109\r\n00:09:26,113 --> 00:09:30,057\r\nWatching you now, one would think\r\nyou've been doing this all your life.\r\n\r\n110\r\n00:09:30,259 --> 00:09:32,847\r\n-What makes you think l haven't?\r\n-Nothing.\r\n\r\n111\r\n00:09:33,049 --> 00:09:37,033\r\n-But when you first came, I thought--\r\n-You thought what?\r\n\r\n112\r\n00:09:37,472 --> 00:09:39,583\r\nWhat right do l have to think?\r\n\r\n113\r\n00:09:44,446 --> 00:09:45,642\r\nMay I?\r\n\r\n114\r\n00:09:46,719 --> 00:09:49,029\r\nToo bad about those two\r\nGerman couriers.\r\n\r\n115\r\n00:09:49,229 --> 00:09:51,740\r\nThey got lucky.\r\nYesterday, they were just clerks.\r\n\r\n116\r\n00:09:51,939 --> 00:09:54,528\r\nToday, they're the honored dead.\r\n\r\n117\r\n00:09:54,770 --> 00:09:57,837\r\nYou're a very cynicaI person,\r\nforgive me for saying so.\r\n\r\n118\r\n00:09:57,998 --> 00:09:58,993\r\nI forgive you.\r\n\r\n119\r\n00:09:59,153 --> 00:10:00,947\r\n-Will you have a drink with me?\r\n-No.\r\n\r\n120\r\n00:10:01,146 --> 00:10:04,175\r\nI forgot you never drink with--\r\nI'll have another, please.\r\n\r\n121\r\n00:10:05,132 --> 00:10:06,724\r\nYou despise me, don't you?\r\n\r\n122\r\n00:10:06,965 --> 00:10:08,958\r\nIf l gave you any thought,\r\nI would.\r\n\r\n123\r\n00:10:09,198 --> 00:10:10,433\r\nBut why?\r\n\r\n124\r\n00:10:11,229 --> 00:10:13,820\r\nYou object to the kind\r\nof business l do, huh?\r\n\r\n125\r\n00:10:14,020 --> 00:10:18,482\r\nBut think of aIl those poor refugees\r\nwho must rot here if I didn't help them.\r\n\r\n126\r\n00:10:18,684 --> 00:10:22,868\r\nThat's not so bad. Through ways of\r\nmy own, l provide them with exit visas.\r\n\r\n127\r\n00:10:23,107 --> 00:10:25,418\r\nFor a price, Ugarte. For a price.\r\n\r\n128\r\n00:10:26,655 --> 00:10:29,562\r\nThink of the poor devils\r\nwho can't meet Renault's price.\r\n\r\n129\r\n00:10:29,803 --> 00:10:32,831\r\nI get it for them for haIf.\r\nIs that so parasitic?\r\n\r\n130\r\n00:10:33,151 --> 00:10:35,821\r\nI don't mind a parasite.\r\nI object to a cut-rate one.\r\n\r\n131\r\n00:10:37,336 --> 00:10:39,966\r\nAfter tonight, I'lI be through\r\nwith the whole business.\r\n\r\n132\r\n00:10:40,166 --> 00:10:42,596\r\nAnd I'm leaving, finally,\r\nthis Casablanca.\r\n\r\n133\r\n00:10:42,797 --> 00:10:45,905\r\nWho'd you bribe for your visa?\r\nRenault or yourseIf?\r\n\r\n134\r\n00:10:46,343 --> 00:10:49,451\r\nMyself. I found myself\r\nmuch more reasonable.\r\n\r\n135\r\n00:10:49,890 --> 00:10:50,885\r\nLook, Rick.\r\n\r\n136\r\n00:10:51,723 --> 00:10:53,158\r\nYou know what this is?\r\n\r\n137\r\n00:10:53,558 --> 00:10:56,267\r\nSomething that even you\r\nhave never seen.\r\n\r\n138\r\n00:10:56,507 --> 00:10:59,416\r\nLetters of transit\r\nsigned by General de GaulIe.\r\n\r\n139\r\n00:11:00,053 --> 00:11:02,523\r\nCannot be rescinded.\r\nNot even questioned.\r\n\r\n140\r\n00:11:02,724 --> 00:11:03,721\r\nOne moment.\r\n\r\n141\r\n00:11:03,921 --> 00:11:07,905\r\nTonight, I'll be selling those for\r\nmore money than even I ever dreamed of.\r\n\r\n142\r\n00:11:08,145 --> 00:11:10,135\r\nAnd then, addio, Casablanca.\r\n\r\n143\r\n00:11:10,616 --> 00:11:14,123\r\nI have many a friend in Casablanca,\r\nbut just because you despise me...\r\n\r\n144\r\n00:11:14,362 --> 00:11:16,036\r\n...you are the only one l trust.\r\n\r\n145\r\n00:11:16,236 --> 00:11:17,909\r\nWiIl you keep these for me?\r\n\r\n146\r\n00:11:18,150 --> 00:11:20,659\r\n-For how long?\r\n-An hour. Perhaps a little longer.\r\n\r\n147\r\n00:11:20,860 --> 00:11:22,172\r\nI don't want them overnight.\r\n\r\n148\r\n00:11:22,374 --> 00:11:25,283\r\nDon't be afraid of that.\r\nPlease keep them for me.\r\n\r\n149\r\n00:11:25,523 --> 00:11:27,514\r\nThank you.\r\nI knew l could trust you.\r\n\r\n150\r\n00:11:28,152 --> 00:11:29,945\r\nWaiter,\r\nI'll be expecting some people.\r\n\r\n151\r\n00:11:30,186 --> 00:11:33,573\r\nIf anybody asks for me,\r\nI'll be right here.\r\n\r\n152\r\n00:11:34,011 --> 00:11:34,966\r\nRick...\r\n\r\n153\r\n00:11:35,208 --> 00:11:37,757\r\n...l hope you're more\r\nimpressed with me now.\r\n\r\n154\r\n00:11:38,636 --> 00:11:41,185\r\nI'll share my good luck\r\nwith your rouIette wheel.\r\n\r\n155\r\n00:11:41,424 --> 00:11:42,897\r\nJust a moment.\r\n\r\n156\r\n00:11:44,852 --> 00:11:49,514\r\nI heard a rumor those German couriers\r\nwere carrying letters of transit.\r\n\r\n157\r\n00:11:51,589 --> 00:11:53,300\r\nI've heard that rumor too.\r\n\r\n158\r\n00:11:53,940 --> 00:11:55,932\r\n-Poor devils.\r\n-You're right, Ugarte.\r\n\r\n159\r\n00:11:56,570 --> 00:11:59,480\r\nI am a little more impressed with you.\r\n\r\n160\r\n00:12:08,328 --> 00:12:10,957\r\n(SINGlNG \"KNOCK ON WOOD\")\r\n\r\n161\r\n00:13:16,641 --> 00:13:17,997\r\n-HeIlo, Rick.\r\n-HeIlo, Ferrari.\r\n\r\n162\r\n00:13:18,237 --> 00:13:19,390\r\nHow's business at the Blue Parrot?\r\n\r\n163\r\n00:13:19,632 --> 00:13:22,380\r\n-Fine, but l'd Iike to buy your cafè.\r\n-It's not for sale.\r\n\r\n164\r\n00:13:22,620 --> 00:13:25,409\r\n-You haven't heard my offer.\r\n-It's not for sale at any price.\r\n\r\n165\r\n00:13:25,650 --> 00:13:28,956\r\n-What do you want for Sam?\r\n-I don't buy or sell human beings.\r\n\r\n166\r\n00:13:29,197 --> 00:13:31,228\r\nThat's CasabIanca's leading commodity.\r\n\r\n167\r\n00:13:31,468 --> 00:13:35,213\r\nIn refugees alone, we can make\r\na fortune together in the bIack market.\r\n\r\n168\r\n00:13:35,413 --> 00:13:37,884\r\nSuppose you run your business\r\nand Iet me run mine.\r\n\r\n169\r\n00:13:38,523 --> 00:13:40,754\r\nSuppose we ask Sam.\r\nMaybe he'd like to make a change.\r\n\r\n170\r\n00:13:40,915 --> 00:13:41,911\r\nSuppose we do.\r\n\r\n171\r\n00:13:42,150 --> 00:13:47,131\r\nWhen will you realize that in this world\r\nisoIationism is not a practicaI poIicy?\r\n\r\n172\r\n00:13:47,372 --> 00:13:49,601\r\nRICK: Ferrari wants you to work\r\nfor him at the Blue Parrot.\r\n\r\n173\r\n00:13:49,922 --> 00:13:50,957\r\nI like it fine here.\r\n\r\n174\r\n00:13:51,198 --> 00:13:54,824\r\n-He'll doubIe what l pay you.\r\n-But l ain't got time to spend money.\r\n\r\n175\r\n00:13:55,423 --> 00:13:56,378\r\nSorry.\r\n\r\n176\r\n00:14:00,524 --> 00:14:03,472\r\nThe boss's private stock.\r\nBecause, Yvonne, I love you.\r\n\r\n177\r\n00:14:03,633 --> 00:14:04,589\r\nShut up.\r\n\r\n178\r\n00:14:04,788 --> 00:14:09,211\r\nAlI right. For you, I shut up.\r\nBecause, Yvonne, I love you.\r\n\r\n179\r\n00:14:11,164 --> 00:14:12,798\r\nMonsieur Rick.\r\n\r\n180\r\n00:14:13,158 --> 00:14:16,187\r\nSome Germans gave this check.\r\nIs it all right?\r\n\r\n181\r\n00:14:20,812 --> 00:14:21,767\r\nWhere were you last night?\r\n\r\n182\r\n00:14:22,006 --> 00:14:24,356\r\nRICK: That's so long ago,\r\nI don't remember.\r\n\r\n183\r\n00:14:24,638 --> 00:14:28,142\r\n-Will I see you tonight?\r\n-I never make plans that far ahead.\r\n\r\n184\r\n00:14:29,061 --> 00:14:30,256\r\nGive me another.\r\n\r\n185\r\n00:14:30,455 --> 00:14:32,965\r\nRICK: She's had enough.\r\n-Don't listen to him. Fill it up.\r\n\r\n186\r\n00:14:33,165 --> 00:14:35,277\r\nYvonne, l love you,\r\nbut he pays me.\r\n\r\n187\r\n00:14:35,517 --> 00:14:37,909\r\n-I'm tired of having you--\r\n-Sascha, calI a cab.\r\n\r\n188\r\n00:14:38,149 --> 00:14:40,061\r\n-We'Il get your coat.\r\n-Take your hands off!\r\n\r\n189\r\n00:14:40,261 --> 00:14:42,850\r\nYou're going home.\r\nYou've had too much to drink.\r\n\r\n190\r\n00:14:45,283 --> 00:14:46,874\r\nHey, taxi!\r\n\r\n191\r\n00:14:48,033 --> 00:14:49,626\r\nWho do you think you are,\r\npushing me?\r\n\r\n192\r\n00:14:49,826 --> 00:14:51,499\r\nWhat a fool l was\r\nto fall for you.\r\n\r\n193\r\n00:14:51,739 --> 00:14:53,849\r\n-Go with her. Be sure she gets home.\r\n-Yes, boss.\r\n\r\n194\r\n00:14:54,011 --> 00:14:54,966\r\nCome right back.\r\n\r\n195\r\n00:14:55,287 --> 00:14:56,641\r\nYes, boss.\r\n\r\n196\r\n00:15:07,880 --> 00:15:09,435\r\n-HeIlo, Rick.\r\n-HeIlo, Louis.\r\n\r\n197\r\n00:15:09,674 --> 00:15:11,626\r\nHow extravagant,\r\nthrowing away women like that.\r\n\r\n198\r\n00:15:11,865 --> 00:15:13,619\r\nSome day, they may be scarce.\r\n\r\n199\r\n00:15:14,138 --> 00:15:17,604\r\nI think I shaIl pay a calI on Yvonne.\r\nMaybe get her on the rebound.\r\n\r\n200\r\n00:15:17,805 --> 00:15:20,076\r\nWhen it comes to women,\r\nyou're a true democrat.\r\n\r\n201\r\n00:15:20,276 --> 00:15:21,990\r\n(CASSELLE lN FRENCH)\r\n\r\n202\r\n00:15:29,722 --> 00:15:32,910\r\nIf he gets a word in,\r\nit'll be a major ltalian victory.\r\n\r\n203\r\n00:15:36,697 --> 00:15:38,330\r\nThe plane to Lisbon.\r\n\r\n204\r\n00:15:42,755 --> 00:15:44,428\r\nYou would like to be on it?\r\n\r\n205\r\n00:15:44,627 --> 00:15:46,182\r\nWhy? What's in Lisbon?\r\n\r\n206\r\n00:15:46,421 --> 00:15:48,294\r\nThe clipper to America.\r\n\r\n207\r\n00:15:48,535 --> 00:15:51,125\r\nI've speculated on why\r\nyou don't return to America.\r\n\r\n208\r\n00:15:51,324 --> 00:15:55,269\r\nDid you abscond with the church funds?\r\nRun off with a senator's wife?\r\n\r\n209\r\n00:15:55,469 --> 00:15:58,060\r\nI like to think you killed a man.\r\nIt's the romantic in me.\r\n\r\n210\r\n00:15:58,299 --> 00:15:59,852\r\nIt's a combination of all three.\r\n\r\n211\r\n00:16:00,092 --> 00:16:01,686\r\nWhat brought you to Casablanca?\r\n\r\n212\r\n00:16:02,245 --> 00:16:04,954\r\nMy health. I came\r\nto Casablanca for the waters.\r\n\r\n213\r\n00:16:05,153 --> 00:16:08,541\r\nThe waters? What waters?\r\nWe're in the desert.\r\n\r\n214\r\n00:16:08,741 --> 00:16:10,494\r\nI was misinformed.\r\n\r\n215\r\n00:16:12,925 --> 00:16:13,962\r\nEMIL:\r\nExcuse me, Rick.\r\n\r\n216\r\n00:16:14,202 --> 00:16:17,229\r\nA gentleman inside\r\nhas won 20,000 francs...\r\n\r\n217\r\n00:16:17,550 --> 00:16:19,741\r\n...and the cashier\r\nwouId Iike some money.\r\n\r\n218\r\n00:16:20,976 --> 00:16:23,806\r\n-I'lI get it from the safe.\r\nEMIL: l'm so upset. You know--\r\n\r\n219\r\n00:16:24,006 --> 00:16:26,476\r\nForget it, Emil.\r\nMistakes happen all the time.\r\n\r\n220\r\n00:16:26,676 --> 00:16:28,310\r\nEMIL:\r\nI'm awfuIly sorry.\r\n\r\n221\r\n00:16:33,652 --> 00:16:36,838\r\nThere'll be some excitement tonight.\r\nAn arrest in your cafè.\r\n\r\n222\r\n00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:38,952\r\n-Again?\r\n-This is no ordinary arrest.\r\n\r\n223\r\n00:16:39,191 --> 00:16:40,507\r\nA murderer, no less.\r\n\r\n224\r\n00:16:41,105 --> 00:16:44,531\r\nIf you're thinking of warning him,\r\ndon't. He cannot escape.\r\n\r\n225\r\n00:16:44,771 --> 00:16:48,637\r\n-I stick my neck out for nobody.\r\n-A wise foreign policy.\r\n\r\n226\r\n00:16:48,876 --> 00:16:50,788\r\n(IN FRENCH)\r\n\r\n227\r\n00:16:51,826 --> 00:16:54,057\r\nWe couId've arrested him\r\nat the Blue Parrot.\r\n\r\n228\r\n00:16:54,257 --> 00:16:56,448\r\nOut of my regard for you,\r\nwe're staging it here.\r\n\r\n229\r\n00:16:56,649 --> 00:16:58,042\r\nIt wiIl amuse your customers.\r\n\r\n230\r\n00:16:58,641 --> 00:17:00,633\r\nRICK:\r\nOur entertainment's enough.\r\n\r\n231\r\n00:17:01,192 --> 00:17:05,974\r\nWe'll have an important guest tonight.\r\nMaj. Strasser, of the Third Reich.\r\n\r\n232\r\n00:17:06,175 --> 00:17:10,399\r\nWe want him to see the arrest as a\r\ndemonstration of our efficiency.\r\n\r\n233\r\n00:17:10,638 --> 00:17:12,551\r\nRICK: I see.\r\nWhat's Strasser doing here?\r\n\r\n234\r\n00:17:12,790 --> 00:17:16,377\r\nHe didn't come here to witness\r\na demonstration of your efficiency.\r\n\r\n235\r\n00:17:16,616 --> 00:17:17,731\r\n-Perhaps not.\r\n-Here you are.\r\n\r\n236\r\n00:17:17,933 --> 00:17:19,924\r\n-It won't happen again.\r\nRICK: That's aIl right.\r\n\r\n237\r\n00:17:20,125 --> 00:17:22,874\r\nLouis, there's something on your mind.\r\nWhy don't you spill it?\r\n\r\n238\r\n00:17:23,073 --> 00:17:24,428\r\nHow observant you are.\r\n\r\n239\r\n00:17:24,987 --> 00:17:27,217\r\nI wanted to give you\r\na word of advice.\r\n\r\n240\r\n00:17:27,459 --> 00:17:28,574\r\nYeah?\r\n\r\n241\r\n00:17:28,813 --> 00:17:30,963\r\n-Have a brandy?\r\n-Thank you.\r\n\r\n242\r\n00:17:32,081 --> 00:17:36,106\r\nThere are exit visas sold in this cafè,\r\nbut we know you've never sold one.\r\n\r\n243\r\n00:17:36,425 --> 00:17:38,337\r\nThat's why we let you remain open.\r\n\r\n244\r\n00:17:38,539 --> 00:17:40,490\r\nI thought it was because\r\nI let you win at rouIette.\r\n\r\n245\r\n00:17:40,730 --> 00:17:42,244\r\nThat is another reason.\r\n\r\n246\r\n00:17:42,484 --> 00:17:45,033\r\nThere's a man arrived here\r\non his way to America.\r\n\r\n247\r\n00:17:45,233 --> 00:17:47,984\r\nHe'lI offer a fortune to anyone\r\nwho'll get him a visa.\r\n\r\n248\r\n00:17:48,223 --> 00:17:50,613\r\n-What's his name?\r\n-Victor LaszIo.\r\n\r\n249\r\n00:17:50,973 --> 00:17:52,168\r\nVictor Laszlo?\r\n\r\n250\r\n00:17:52,368 --> 00:17:54,599\r\nThat's the first time\r\nI've seen you impressed.\r\n\r\n251\r\n00:17:54,839 --> 00:17:56,872\r\nHe's succeeded\r\nin impressing haIf the world.\r\n\r\n252\r\n00:17:57,071 --> 00:17:59,343\r\nIt's my duty to see\r\nhe doesn't impress the other half.\r\n\r\n253\r\n00:17:59,661 --> 00:18:03,527\r\nRick, Laszlo must never reach America.\r\nHe stays in Casablanca.\r\n\r\n254\r\n00:18:03,766 --> 00:18:05,599\r\nRICK: It'll be interesting\r\nto see how he manages.\r\n\r\n255\r\n00:18:05,801 --> 00:18:07,871\r\n-Manages what?\r\nRICK: His escape.\r\n\r\n256\r\n00:18:08,071 --> 00:18:09,785\r\n-But l just told you--\r\n-Stop it.\r\n\r\n257\r\n00:18:10,024 --> 00:18:13,372\r\nHe escaped the concentration camp.\r\nNazis have chased him through Europe.\r\n\r\n258\r\n00:18:13,612 --> 00:18:14,965\r\nLOUIS:\r\nThis is the end of the chase.\r\n\r\n259\r\n00:18:15,206 --> 00:18:18,911\r\n-Twenty thousand francs says it isn't.\r\n-Is that a serious offer?\r\n\r\n260\r\n00:18:19,510 --> 00:18:21,501\r\nI just paid 20.\r\nI'd like to get it back.\r\n\r\n261\r\n00:18:21,702 --> 00:18:24,332\r\nMake it ten.\r\nI'm only a poor, corrupt official.\r\n\r\n262\r\n00:18:25,170 --> 00:18:26,284\r\n-Okay.\r\n-Done.\r\n\r\n263\r\n00:18:26,526 --> 00:18:30,350\r\nNo matter how clever he is, he still\r\nneeds a visa. Or, I should say, two.\r\n\r\n264\r\n00:18:30,750 --> 00:18:32,663\r\n-Why two?\r\n-He is traveIing with a Iady.\r\n\r\n265\r\n00:18:32,901 --> 00:18:35,413\r\n-He'll take one.\r\n-I think not. l've seen her.\r\n\r\n266\r\n00:18:36,010 --> 00:18:38,442\r\nIf he did not leave her\r\nin MarseiIles or in Oran...\r\n\r\n267\r\n00:18:38,641 --> 00:18:40,672\r\n...he won't leave her in Casablanca.\r\n\r\n268\r\n00:18:40,914 --> 00:18:42,905\r\nMaybe he's not quite\r\nas romantic as you.\r\n\r\n269\r\n00:18:43,145 --> 00:18:46,174\r\nIt doesn't matter.\r\nThere is no exit visa for him.\r\n\r\n270\r\n00:18:46,692 --> 00:18:50,319\r\nWhat ever gave you the impression\r\nthat I might help Laszlo escape?\r\n\r\n271\r\n00:18:50,518 --> 00:18:53,467\r\nBecause I suspect\r\nthat under that cynical shell...\r\n\r\n272\r\n00:18:53,947 --> 00:18:55,380\r\n...you're at heart\r\na sentimentalist.\r\n\r\n273\r\n00:18:56,059 --> 00:18:58,887\r\nLaugh if you will.\r\nI'm familiar with your record.\r\n\r\n274\r\n00:18:59,127 --> 00:19:01,199\r\nLet me point out just two items.\r\n\r\n275\r\n00:19:01,677 --> 00:19:04,946\r\nIn 1 935, you ran guns to Ethiopia.\r\n\r\n276\r\n00:19:05,425 --> 00:19:09,090\r\nIn 1 936, you fought in Spain\r\non the loyalist side.\r\n\r\n277\r\n00:19:09,411 --> 00:19:11,522\r\nAnd got well paid on both occasions.\r\n\r\n278\r\n00:19:11,722 --> 00:19:13,874\r\nThe winning side\r\nwouId've paid much better.\r\n\r\n279\r\n00:19:14,473 --> 00:19:15,547\r\nMaybe.\r\n\r\n280\r\n00:19:16,265 --> 00:19:18,338\r\nIt seems you're determined\r\nto keep Laszlo here.\r\n\r\n281\r\n00:19:18,538 --> 00:19:20,289\r\nI have my orders.\r\n\r\n282\r\n00:19:20,968 --> 00:19:22,762\r\nRICK:\r\nI see. Gestapo spank.\r\n\r\n283\r\n00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:25,631\r\nYou overestimate\r\nthe influence of the Gestapo.\r\n\r\n284\r\n00:19:25,870 --> 00:19:29,059\r\nI don't interfere with them\r\nand they don't interfere with me.\r\n\r\n285\r\n00:19:29,298 --> 00:19:31,176\r\nIn Casablanca, I am master of my fate.\r\n\r\n286\r\n00:19:31,455 --> 00:19:33,492\r\n-I am--\r\n-Maj. Strasser is here, sir.\r\n\r\n287\r\n00:19:33,733 --> 00:19:35,968\r\n-You were saying?\r\n-Excuse me.\r\n\r\n288\r\n00:19:45,318 --> 00:19:48,392\r\nCarI, see that the major gets\r\na good table, close to the ladies.\r\n\r\n289\r\n00:19:48,634 --> 00:19:53,067\r\nI've already given him the best, knowing\r\nhe is German and would take it anyway.\r\n\r\n290\r\n00:19:55,106 --> 00:19:58,180\r\nTake him quietly.\r\nTwo guards at every door.\r\n\r\n291\r\n00:20:02,416 --> 00:20:04,853\r\n-Everything is ready, sir.\r\n-Go ahead.\r\n\r\n292\r\n00:20:10,007 --> 00:20:12,082\r\n-Good evening, gentlemen.\r\n-Good evening, captain.\r\n\r\n293\r\n00:20:12,323 --> 00:20:14,399\r\nHElNZ: Won't you join us?\r\n-Thank you.\r\n\r\n294\r\n00:20:15,399 --> 00:20:17,077\r\nLOUIS:\r\nIt's a pIeasure to have you here.\r\n\r\n295\r\n00:20:17,318 --> 00:20:18,835\r\nChampagne and a tin of caviar.\r\n\r\n296\r\n00:20:19,074 --> 00:20:22,430\r\nMay I recommend Veuve Clicquot, '26?\r\nA good French wine.\r\n\r\n297\r\n00:20:22,670 --> 00:20:24,187\r\nWAITER:\r\nVery welI, sir.\r\n\r\n298\r\n00:20:24,828 --> 00:20:27,822\r\n-A very interesting cIub.\r\n-Especially so tonight.\r\n\r\n299\r\n00:20:28,064 --> 00:20:31,218\r\nYou'll see the arrest of the man\r\nwho murdered your couriers.\r\n\r\n300\r\n00:20:31,460 --> 00:20:33,057\r\nI expected no less, captain.\r\n\r\n301\r\n00:20:33,257 --> 00:20:34,813\r\nMonsieur Ugarte.\r\n\r\n302\r\n00:20:36,612 --> 00:20:37,571\r\nYes?\r\n\r\n303\r\n00:20:37,732 --> 00:20:40,766\r\n-Will you pIease come with us?\r\n-Certainly.\r\n\r\n304\r\n00:20:41,367 --> 00:20:43,003\r\nMay I first cash my chips?\r\n\r\n305\r\n00:20:43,884 --> 00:20:46,118\r\n(EMlL IN FRENCH)\r\n\r\n306\r\n00:20:49,755 --> 00:20:52,471\r\nUGARTE: Very lucky.\r\nTwo thousand, please.\r\n\r\n307\r\n00:20:53,431 --> 00:20:54,788\r\nCASHIER:\r\nTwo thousand.\r\n\r\n308\r\n00:20:59,624 --> 00:21:00,741\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\n309\r\n00:21:13,405 --> 00:21:15,281\r\nRick! Rick, help me!\r\n\r\n310\r\n00:21:15,563 --> 00:21:19,637\r\n-Don't be a fool. You can't get away.\r\n-Rick, hide me! You must help me!\r\n\r\n311\r\n00:21:19,878 --> 00:21:20,914\r\nDo something!\r\n\r\n312\r\n00:21:21,157 --> 00:21:22,353\r\nRick!\r\n\r\n313\r\n00:21:26,908 --> 00:21:27,986\r\nExcelIent, captain.\r\n\r\n314\r\n00:21:28,267 --> 00:21:30,583\r\nWhen they come to get me,\r\nI hope you'lI be more help.\r\n\r\n315\r\n00:21:30,823 --> 00:21:32,940\r\nI stick my neck out for nobody.\r\n\r\n316\r\n00:21:33,181 --> 00:21:36,776\r\nI'm sorry there was a disturbance,\r\nfolks, but it's all over now.\r\n\r\n317\r\n00:21:37,015 --> 00:21:40,570\r\nSit down and have a good time.\r\nEnjoy yourselves. All right, Sam.\r\n\r\n318\r\n00:21:46,204 --> 00:21:47,402\r\nLOUIS:\r\nRick?\r\n\r\n319\r\n00:21:47,841 --> 00:21:51,116\r\nThis is Maj. Heinrich Strasser\r\nof the Third Reich.\r\n\r\n320\r\n00:21:51,316 --> 00:21:53,074\r\n-How do you do?\r\n-How do you do?\r\n\r\n321\r\n00:21:53,274 --> 00:21:55,310\r\nYou know Herr Heinz\r\nof the Third Reich.\r\n\r\n322\r\n00:21:55,552 --> 00:21:57,468\r\nSTRASSER:\r\nPlease join us, Mr. Rick.\r\n\r\n323\r\n00:22:01,423 --> 00:22:02,782\r\nWe are very honored tonight.\r\n\r\n324\r\n00:22:02,982 --> 00:22:06,737\r\nMaj. Strasser is one reason\r\nthe Third Reich enjoys its reputation.\r\n\r\n325\r\n00:22:06,936 --> 00:22:09,812\r\nYou say \"Third Reich\" as though\r\nyou expect there to be others.\r\n\r\n326\r\n00:22:10,013 --> 00:22:12,847\r\nPersonally, major,\r\nI wilI take what comes.\r\n\r\n327\r\n00:22:13,769 --> 00:22:15,725\r\nDo you mind if I ask\r\na few questions?\r\n\r\n328\r\n00:22:15,965 --> 00:22:18,202\r\n-Unofficially, of course.\r\n-Make it official if you like.\r\n\r\n329\r\n00:22:18,442 --> 00:22:20,958\r\n-What is your nationality?\r\n-I'm a drunkard.\r\n\r\n330\r\n00:22:22,436 --> 00:22:24,474\r\nThat makes Rick\r\na citizen of the world.\r\n\r\n331\r\n00:22:24,873 --> 00:22:27,190\r\nI was born in New York City,\r\nif that'll help you.\r\n\r\n332\r\n00:22:27,750 --> 00:22:30,666\r\nI understand you came here from Paris\r\nduring the occupation.\r\n\r\n333\r\n00:22:30,945 --> 00:22:32,663\r\nThere seems to be no secret about that.\r\n\r\n334\r\n00:22:32,903 --> 00:22:36,778\r\nAre you one of those who can't imagine\r\nGermans in their beloved Paris?\r\n\r\n335\r\n00:22:37,299 --> 00:22:39,095\r\nIt's not particularly\r\nmy beloved Paris.\r\n\r\n336\r\n00:22:39,335 --> 00:22:41,012\r\nCan you imagine us in London?\r\n\r\n337\r\n00:22:42,211 --> 00:22:43,610\r\nWhen you get there, ask me.\r\n\r\n338\r\n00:22:44,169 --> 00:22:46,445\r\n-Diplomatist!\r\n-How about New York?\r\n\r\n339\r\n00:22:46,685 --> 00:22:51,359\r\nThere are sections of New York that\r\nI wouldn't advise you to try to invade.\r\n\r\n340\r\n00:22:51,959 --> 00:22:54,515\r\n-Who will win the war?\r\n-I haven't the sIightest idea.\r\n\r\n341\r\n00:22:54,755 --> 00:22:57,511\r\nRick is neutral about everything.\r\nAnd that takes in...\r\n\r\n342\r\n00:22:57,751 --> 00:22:59,189\r\n...the fieId of women too.\r\n\r\n343\r\n00:22:59,430 --> 00:23:01,426\r\nYou weren't always\r\nso carefulIy neutral.\r\n\r\n344\r\n00:23:01,627 --> 00:23:04,182\r\nWe have a compIete dossier on you.\r\n\r\n345\r\n00:23:05,422 --> 00:23:09,815\r\n\"Richard Blaine, American. Age, 37.\r\nCannot return to his country.\"\r\n\r\n346\r\n00:23:10,057 --> 00:23:12,613\r\nThe reason is vague.\r\nWe know what you did in Paris...\r\n\r\n347\r\n00:23:12,851 --> 00:23:16,526\r\n...and why you left Paris.\r\nDon't worry, we won't broadcast it.\r\n\r\n348\r\n00:23:16,728 --> 00:23:18,045\r\nAre my eyes really brown?\r\n\r\n349\r\n00:23:18,286 --> 00:23:19,962\r\nYou wiIl forgive my curiosity.\r\n\r\n350\r\n00:23:20,203 --> 00:23:23,199\r\nThe point is, an enemy of the Reich\r\nhas come to CasabIanca...\r\n\r\n351\r\n00:23:23,438 --> 00:23:26,514\r\n...and we are checking up on anyone\r\nwho can be of any help.\r\n\r\n352\r\n00:23:26,794 --> 00:23:30,589\r\nMy interest in whether Laszlo\r\nstays or goes is purely a sporting one.\r\n\r\n353\r\n00:23:31,429 --> 00:23:34,344\r\nIn this case, you have\r\nno sympathy for the fox?\r\n\r\n354\r\n00:23:34,585 --> 00:23:37,819\r\nNot particularly. I understand\r\nthe hound's point of view too.\r\n\r\n355\r\n00:23:38,180 --> 00:23:42,572\r\nLaszlo published the foulest lies in the\r\nPrague newspapers tiIl we marched in.\r\n\r\n356\r\n00:23:42,774 --> 00:23:46,968\r\nAnd even after that, he continued\r\nto print scandal sheets in a cellar.\r\n\r\n357\r\n00:23:47,208 --> 00:23:49,804\r\nOf course, one must admit\r\nhe has great courage.\r\n\r\n358\r\n00:23:50,165 --> 00:23:52,761\r\nHe's clever. Three times\r\nhe sIipped through our fingers.\r\n\r\n359\r\n00:23:53,001 --> 00:23:56,835\r\nIn Paris, he continued his activities.\r\nWe intend not to let it happen again.\r\n\r\n360\r\n00:23:57,075 --> 00:24:00,311\r\nExcuse me. Your business is\r\npolitics, mine is running a saloon.\r\n\r\n361\r\n00:24:00,551 --> 00:24:02,308\r\nGood evening, Mr. Blaine.\r\n\r\n362\r\n00:24:02,948 --> 00:24:05,703\r\nYou see, major? You have\r\nnothing to worry about Rick.\r\n\r\n363\r\n00:24:05,865 --> 00:24:06,822\r\nPerhaps.\r\n\r\n364\r\n00:24:10,739 --> 00:24:11,735\r\nHOST:\r\nYes, monsieur?\r\n\r\n365\r\n00:24:11,978 --> 00:24:16,290\r\n-I reserved a tabIe. Victor LaszIo.\r\n-Yes, monsieur. Right this way.\r\n\r\n366\r\n00:24:41,819 --> 00:24:43,415\r\nTwo Cointreaux, please.\r\n\r\n367\r\n00:24:45,413 --> 00:24:47,771\r\nI saw no one of Ugarte's description.\r\n\r\n368\r\n00:24:48,010 --> 00:24:50,926\r\nVictor, I feeI somehow\r\nwe shouldn't stay here.\r\n\r\n369\r\n00:24:51,165 --> 00:24:53,883\r\nIf we'd walk out so soon\r\nit'd only calI attention to us.\r\n\r\n370\r\n00:24:54,123 --> 00:24:55,959\r\nPerhaps he's in some\r\nother part of the cafè.\r\n\r\n371\r\n00:24:57,919 --> 00:25:01,553\r\nExcuse me, but you look like a couple\r\nwho are on their way to America.\r\n\r\n372\r\n00:25:01,833 --> 00:25:05,907\r\nYou'll find a market for this ring.\r\nI must sell it at a great sacrifice.\r\n\r\n373\r\n00:25:06,148 --> 00:25:08,464\r\n-Thank you, but I don't--\r\n-Perhaps for the Iady.\r\n\r\n374\r\n00:25:08,705 --> 00:25:09,980\r\nBERGER:\r\nThe ring is quite unique.\r\n\r\n375\r\n00:25:12,139 --> 00:25:14,176\r\nYes, l'm very interested.\r\n\r\n376\r\n00:25:14,617 --> 00:25:15,574\r\nGood.\r\n\r\n377\r\n00:25:16,174 --> 00:25:17,134\r\nYour name?\r\n\r\n378\r\n00:25:17,373 --> 00:25:19,491\r\nBerger, Norwegian.\r\nAt your service.\r\n\r\n379\r\n00:25:19,890 --> 00:25:20,847\r\nVictor....\r\n\r\n380\r\n00:25:21,407 --> 00:25:23,125\r\nI'll meet you at the bar Iater.\r\n\r\n381\r\n00:25:23,364 --> 00:25:25,680\r\nWe don't want the ring,\r\nbut thank you for showing it to us.\r\n\r\n382\r\n00:25:25,922 --> 00:25:28,877\r\nBERGER: That is your decision?\r\nLAZLO: It is.\r\n\r\n383\r\n00:25:31,634 --> 00:25:33,631\r\n-Monsieur Laszlo, is it not?\r\n-Yes.\r\n\r\n384\r\n00:25:33,872 --> 00:25:35,788\r\nCaptain Renault, prefect of police.\r\n\r\n385\r\n00:25:35,988 --> 00:25:36,987\r\nWhat do you want?\r\n\r\n386\r\n00:25:37,228 --> 00:25:40,142\r\nTo welcome you to CasabIanca\r\nand to wish you a pleasant stay.\r\n\r\n387\r\n00:25:40,344 --> 00:25:42,978\r\nIt isn't often we have\r\nso distinguished a visitor.\r\n\r\n388\r\n00:25:43,180 --> 00:25:45,456\r\nThank you.\r\nI hope you'lI forgive me, captain.\r\n\r\n389\r\n00:25:45,697 --> 00:25:49,052\r\nThe present French administration\r\nhasn't always been so cordiaI.\r\n\r\n390\r\n00:25:49,292 --> 00:25:51,088\r\nMay I present Miss Ilsa Lund?\r\n\r\n391\r\n00:25:52,727 --> 00:25:55,443\r\nI was told you were the most\r\nbeautifuI woman to visit Casablanca.\r\n\r\n392\r\n00:25:55,683 --> 00:25:57,400\r\nThat was a gross understatement.\r\n\r\n393\r\n00:25:57,842 --> 00:25:58,838\r\nYou're very kind.\r\n\r\n394\r\n00:25:59,079 --> 00:26:01,595\r\n-Won't you join us?\r\n-If you'll permit me.\r\n\r\n395\r\n00:26:01,796 --> 00:26:05,390\r\nEmil, please. A bottle of your\r\nbest champagne. Put it on my bill.\r\n\r\n396\r\n00:26:05,830 --> 00:26:10,704\r\nIt's a game we play. They put it on the\r\nbill, I tear it up. Very convenient.\r\n\r\n397\r\n00:26:11,623 --> 00:26:14,259\r\nCaptain, the boy\r\nwho's playing the piano....\r\n\r\n398\r\n00:26:14,939 --> 00:26:16,256\r\nSomewhere I've seen him.\r\n\r\n399\r\n00:26:16,497 --> 00:26:17,816\r\nLOUIS: Sam?\r\nILSA: Yes.\r\n\r\n400\r\n00:26:18,016 --> 00:26:19,932\r\nHe came from Paris with Rick.\r\n\r\n401\r\n00:26:20,133 --> 00:26:21,170\r\nRick? Who's he?\r\n\r\n402\r\n00:26:21,412 --> 00:26:24,725\r\n-You are in Rick's. Rick is....\r\n-Is what?\r\n\r\n403\r\n00:26:24,968 --> 00:26:28,041\r\nMademoiselle, he's the kind of man--\r\nIf l were a woman...\r\n\r\n404\r\n00:26:28,282 --> 00:26:30,838\r\n...and I weren't around,\r\nI'd be in love with Rick.\r\n\r\n405\r\n00:26:31,038 --> 00:26:34,954\r\nBut what a fooI I am talking to\r\na beautiful woman about another man.\r\n\r\n406\r\n00:26:35,753 --> 00:26:36,710\r\nExcuse me.\r\n\r\n407\r\n00:26:37,111 --> 00:26:38,309\r\nLOUIS:\r\nMajor.\r\n\r\n408\r\n00:26:40,107 --> 00:26:43,062\r\nMademoiselle and monsieur,\r\nmay I present Maj. Strasser?\r\n\r\n409\r\n00:26:43,303 --> 00:26:44,422\r\nHow do you do?\r\n\r\n410\r\n00:26:44,580 --> 00:26:46,458\r\nThis is a pleasure\r\nI've Iooked forward to.\r\n\r\n411\r\n00:26:46,658 --> 00:26:49,095\r\nI'm sure you'Il excuse me\r\nif I'm not gracious.\r\n\r\n412\r\n00:26:49,296 --> 00:26:51,291\r\nBut you see,\r\nI am a Czechoslovakian.\r\n\r\n413\r\n00:26:51,493 --> 00:26:55,886\r\nYou were a Czechoslovakian. Now\r\nyou're a subject of the German Reich.\r\n\r\n414\r\n00:26:56,645 --> 00:26:59,761\r\nI've never accepted that privilege.\r\nAnd I'm now on French soil.\r\n\r\n415\r\n00:26:59,962 --> 00:27:03,517\r\nI'd like to discuss some matters arising\r\nfrom your presence on French soil.\r\n\r\n416\r\n00:27:03,756 --> 00:27:05,354\r\nThis is hardIy the time or the pIace.\r\n\r\n417\r\n00:27:05,554 --> 00:27:09,787\r\nThen we'll state another time and place.\r\nTomorrow at ten in the prefect's office.\r\n\r\n418\r\n00:27:10,029 --> 00:27:11,067\r\nWith mademoiselIe.\r\n\r\n419\r\n00:27:12,705 --> 00:27:15,581\r\nCapt. RenauIt,\r\nI am under your authority.\r\n\r\n420\r\n00:27:15,782 --> 00:27:17,698\r\nIs it your order\r\nwe come to your office?\r\n\r\n421\r\n00:27:17,939 --> 00:27:21,653\r\nLet us say it is my request.\r\nThat is a much more pleasant word.\r\n\r\n422\r\n00:27:21,894 --> 00:27:23,649\r\n-Very well.\r\n-MademoiseIle.\r\n\r\n423\r\n00:27:23,852 --> 00:27:25,368\r\nMademoiselle.\r\n\r\n424\r\n00:27:27,407 --> 00:27:30,081\r\nA very clever tacticaI retreat, major.\r\n\r\n425\r\n00:27:30,402 --> 00:27:34,157\r\n-This time they really mean to stop me.\r\n-Victor, l'm afraid for you.\r\n\r\n426\r\n00:27:34,597 --> 00:27:37,233\r\nWe've been in difficuIt\r\nplaces before, haven't we?\r\n\r\n427\r\n00:27:41,388 --> 00:27:43,305\r\n(SINGlNG IN FORElGN LANGUAGE)\r\n\r\n428\r\n00:28:09,073 --> 00:28:10,869\r\nI must find out what Berger knows.\r\n\r\n429\r\n00:28:11,070 --> 00:28:14,185\r\n-Be careful.\r\n-I will. Don't worry.\r\n\r\n430\r\n00:28:31,245 --> 00:28:33,840\r\nMr. Berger, the ring.\r\nCouId l see it again?\r\n\r\n431\r\n00:28:34,402 --> 00:28:35,917\r\nChampagne cocktail, please.\r\n\r\n432\r\n00:28:36,718 --> 00:28:39,154\r\nI recognize you\r\nfrom the news photographs.\r\n\r\n433\r\n00:28:39,394 --> 00:28:42,549\r\nIn a concentration camp,\r\none is apt to Iose a little weight.\r\n\r\n434\r\n00:28:42,790 --> 00:28:45,346\r\nI read five times\r\nthat you were kiIled in five places.\r\n\r\n435\r\n00:28:45,587 --> 00:28:48,221\r\nAs you see, it was true\r\nevery single time.\r\n\r\n436\r\n00:28:48,422 --> 00:28:49,741\r\nThank heaven I found you.\r\n\r\n437\r\n00:28:49,941 --> 00:28:53,535\r\nI'm Iooking for a man named Ugarte.\r\nHe's supposed to help me.\r\n\r\n438\r\n00:28:54,134 --> 00:28:56,172\r\nUgarte cannot even help himself.\r\n\r\n439\r\n00:28:56,413 --> 00:28:58,569\r\nHe's under arrest for murder.\r\n\r\n440\r\n00:28:58,808 --> 00:29:00,567\r\nHe was arrested here tonight.\r\n\r\n441\r\n00:29:01,087 --> 00:29:02,165\r\nI see.\r\n\r\n442\r\n00:29:02,803 --> 00:29:06,359\r\nBut we, who are still free, will do\r\nall we can. We are organized.\r\n\r\n443\r\n00:29:06,598 --> 00:29:08,796\r\nUnderground, like everywhere else.\r\n\r\n444\r\n00:29:08,997 --> 00:29:11,712\r\nTomorrow night, there is a meeting\r\nat the Cafè du Roi.\r\n\r\n445\r\n00:29:12,033 --> 00:29:13,629\r\nIf you'lI come--\r\n\r\n446\r\n00:29:26,574 --> 00:29:28,890\r\nWiIl you ask the piano player\r\nto come over here?\r\n\r\n447\r\n00:29:29,090 --> 00:29:30,688\r\nWAITER:\r\nVery welI, mademoiselle.\r\n\r\n448\r\n00:29:33,045 --> 00:29:36,240\r\n-How's the jewelry business?\r\n-Not so good. Check, please.\r\n\r\n449\r\n00:29:36,441 --> 00:29:40,516\r\nToo bad you weren't here earIier.\r\nWe had quite a bit of excitement, right?\r\n\r\n450\r\n00:29:40,755 --> 00:29:41,873\r\nYes. Excuse me, gentlemen.\r\n\r\n451\r\n00:29:42,113 --> 00:29:45,069\r\n-My bill.\r\n-No. Two champagnes. Please.\r\n\r\n452\r\n00:29:45,310 --> 00:29:46,508\r\nSASCHA:\r\nYes, sir.\r\n\r\n453\r\n00:29:50,064 --> 00:29:52,260\r\nILSA: HelIo, Sam.\r\n-HeIlo, Miss llsa.\r\n\r\n454\r\n00:29:52,462 --> 00:29:54,856\r\nI never expected to see you again.\r\n\r\n455\r\n00:29:55,577 --> 00:29:57,095\r\nIt's been a long time.\r\n\r\n456\r\n00:29:57,295 --> 00:30:00,650\r\nYes, ma'am.\r\nA lot of water under the bridge.\r\n\r\n457\r\n00:30:01,890 --> 00:30:04,764\r\n-Some of the oId songs, Sam.\r\n-Yes, ma'am.\r\n\r\n458\r\n00:30:14,313 --> 00:30:15,310\r\nWhere is Rick?\r\n\r\n459\r\n00:30:15,991 --> 00:30:18,266\r\nI don't know.\r\nI ain't seen him aIl night.\r\n\r\n460\r\n00:30:19,307 --> 00:30:20,264\r\nWhen will he be back?\r\n\r\n461\r\n00:30:20,505 --> 00:30:22,540\r\nNot tonight no more.\r\nHe ain't coming--\r\n\r\n462\r\n00:30:22,741 --> 00:30:24,139\r\nHe went home.\r\n\r\n463\r\n00:30:25,738 --> 00:30:27,295\r\nDoes he always leave so early?\r\n\r\n464\r\n00:30:27,496 --> 00:30:30,969\r\nOh, he never--\r\nHe's got a girI up at the Blue Parrot.\r\n\r\n465\r\n00:30:31,170 --> 00:30:33,249\r\nGoes up there aIl the time.\r\n\r\n466\r\n00:30:34,805 --> 00:30:37,363\r\nYou used to be\r\na much better Iiar, Sam.\r\n\r\n467\r\n00:30:38,282 --> 00:30:41,317\r\nLeave him aIone, Miss IIsa.\r\nYou're bad luck to him.\r\n\r\n468\r\n00:30:44,153 --> 00:30:46,790\r\nPlay it once, Sam.\r\nFor old time's sake.\r\n\r\n469\r\n00:30:47,030 --> 00:30:49,467\r\nSAM:\r\nI don't know what you mean, Miss Ilsa.\r\n\r\n470\r\n00:30:50,026 --> 00:30:51,543\r\nPlay it, Sam.\r\n\r\n471\r\n00:30:52,465 --> 00:30:54,341\r\nPlay \"As Time Goes By.\"\r\n\r\n472\r\n00:30:54,541 --> 00:30:57,576\r\nI can't remember it.\r\nI'm a little rusty on it.\r\n\r\n473\r\n00:30:58,456 --> 00:31:00,414\r\nI'll hum it for you.\r\n\r\n474\r\n00:31:00,973 --> 00:31:03,169\r\n(HUMS)\r\n\r\n475\r\n00:31:08,123 --> 00:31:10,719\r\n(PLAYS \"AS TIME GOES BY\")\r\n\r\n476\r\n00:31:11,560 --> 00:31:12,757\r\nSing it, Sam.\r\n\r\n477\r\n00:31:15,274 --> 00:31:17,630\r\n(SINGS \"AS TIME GOES BY\")\r\n\r\n478\r\n00:31:57,141 --> 00:31:59,697\r\nSam, l thought I told you\r\nnever to play--\r\n\r\n479\r\n00:32:09,885 --> 00:32:12,760\r\nYou were asking about Rick\r\nand here he is. May I present--\r\n\r\n480\r\n00:32:13,001 --> 00:32:15,196\r\n-HeIlo, llsa.\r\n-HeIlo, Rick.\r\n\r\n481\r\n00:32:15,437 --> 00:32:18,713\r\nYou've already met Rick?\r\nThen perhaps you also--\r\n\r\n482\r\n00:32:18,953 --> 00:32:20,231\r\nILSA:\r\nThis is Mr. Laszlo.\r\n\r\n483\r\n00:32:20,471 --> 00:32:21,669\r\nLASZLO: How do you do?\r\nRICK: How do you do?\r\n\r\n484\r\n00:32:22,150 --> 00:32:24,105\r\nOne hears a great deal\r\nabout Rick in Casablanca.\r\n\r\n485\r\n00:32:24,386 --> 00:32:26,143\r\nAnd about Victor Laszlo everywhere.\r\n\r\n486\r\n00:32:26,423 --> 00:32:28,100\r\n-Join us for a drink?\r\n-Rick never--\r\n\r\n487\r\n00:32:28,261 --> 00:32:29,219\r\nThanks, I wiIl.\r\n\r\n488\r\n00:32:29,458 --> 00:32:32,975\r\nWell! A precedent\r\nis being broken. Emil?\r\n\r\n489\r\n00:32:34,014 --> 00:32:36,090\r\nA very interesting cafè.\r\nI congratulate you.\r\n\r\n490\r\n00:32:36,332 --> 00:32:37,847\r\nRICK: I congratulate you.\r\nLASZLO: What for?\r\n\r\n491\r\n00:32:38,009 --> 00:32:38,967\r\nYour work.\r\n\r\n492\r\n00:32:39,366 --> 00:32:40,765\r\nThank you. I try.\r\n\r\n493\r\n00:32:41,683 --> 00:32:43,481\r\nWe all try. You succeed.\r\n\r\n494\r\n00:32:43,682 --> 00:32:45,998\r\nShe was asking about you earlier...\r\n\r\n495\r\n00:32:46,239 --> 00:32:48,913\r\n...in a way that made me\r\nextremeIy jealous.\r\n\r\n496\r\n00:32:49,115 --> 00:32:50,592\r\nI wasn't sure you were the same.\r\n\r\n497\r\n00:32:51,391 --> 00:32:54,106\r\nILSA: The Iast time we met--\r\n-Was La Belle Aurore.\r\n\r\n498\r\n00:32:55,626 --> 00:32:57,463\r\nHow nice. You remembered.\r\n\r\n499\r\n00:32:57,664 --> 00:33:00,259\r\nThat was the day\r\nthe Germans marched into Paris.\r\n\r\n500\r\n00:33:00,539 --> 00:33:02,537\r\nNot an easy day to forget.\r\n\r\n501\r\n00:33:03,377 --> 00:33:06,850\r\nI remember every detail.\r\nThe Germans wore gray, you wore blue.\r\n\r\n502\r\n00:33:08,290 --> 00:33:10,726\r\nYes. l put that dress away.\r\n\r\n503\r\n00:33:10,967 --> 00:33:13,124\r\nWhen the Germans march out,\r\nI'll wear it again.\r\n\r\n504\r\n00:33:13,363 --> 00:33:17,357\r\nYou're becoming quite human.\r\nI suppose we have to thank you for that.\r\n\r\n505\r\n00:33:17,677 --> 00:33:20,794\r\nIlsa, I don't wish to be the one\r\nto say it, but it's Iate.\r\n\r\n506\r\n00:33:21,033 --> 00:33:23,469\r\nSo it is. We have a curfew\r\nhere in Casablanca.\r\n\r\n507\r\n00:33:23,670 --> 00:33:26,984\r\nIt wouldn't do for the chief of police\r\nto be drinking after hours.\r\n\r\n508\r\n00:33:27,785 --> 00:33:29,982\r\nLASZLO:\r\nI hope we didn't overstay our weIcome.\r\n\r\n509\r\n00:33:30,301 --> 00:33:31,778\r\nWAITER: Your check, sir.\r\nRICK: My party.\r\n\r\n510\r\n00:33:32,020 --> 00:33:35,374\r\nAnother precedent gone. This has been\r\na very interesting evening.\r\n\r\n511\r\n00:33:35,614 --> 00:33:39,290\r\nI'll caIl you a cab.\r\nGasoIine rationing, time of night....\r\n\r\n512\r\n00:33:39,690 --> 00:33:41,168\r\nLASZLO: We'Il come again.\r\nRICK: Any time.\r\n\r\n513\r\n00:33:41,407 --> 00:33:43,325\r\n-Say good night to Sam.\r\n-I will.\r\n\r\n514\r\n00:33:44,324 --> 00:33:48,199\r\nThere's stiIl nobody in the world\r\nwho can play \"As Time Goes By\" like Sam.\r\n\r\n515\r\n00:33:48,638 --> 00:33:50,954\r\nHe hasn't played it in a Iong time.\r\n\r\n516\r\n00:33:52,394 --> 00:33:54,910\r\n-Good night.\r\n-Good night.\r\n\r\n517\r\n00:34:03,619 --> 00:34:06,015\r\nA very puzzling fellow.\r\nWhat sort is he?\r\n\r\n518\r\n00:34:06,256 --> 00:34:09,251\r\nI realIy can't say,\r\nthough l saw him quite often in Paris.\r\n\r\n519\r\n00:34:09,492 --> 00:34:12,047\r\n-Tomorrow at 1 0 at the prefect office.\r\n-We'Il be there.\r\n\r\n520\r\n00:34:12,289 --> 00:34:13,246\r\nGood night.\r\n\r\n521\r\n00:34:51,038 --> 00:34:52,195\r\nSAM:\r\nBoss?\r\n\r\n522\r\n00:34:55,952 --> 00:34:57,789\r\n-Boss?\r\n-Yeah?\r\n\r\n523\r\n00:34:58,269 --> 00:35:01,145\r\nSAM: Ain't you going to bed?\r\nRICK: Not right now.\r\n\r\n524\r\n00:35:01,386 --> 00:35:04,220\r\nAin't you pIanning on going to bed\r\nin the near future?\r\n\r\n525\r\n00:35:04,461 --> 00:35:06,457\r\n-You ever going to bed?\r\n-No!\r\n\r\n526\r\n00:35:07,258 --> 00:35:08,934\r\nI ain't sleepy either.\r\n\r\n527\r\n00:35:09,135 --> 00:35:10,253\r\nThen have a drink.\r\n\r\n528\r\n00:35:10,493 --> 00:35:12,210\r\n-Not me.\r\n-Well, don't have a drink.\r\n\r\n529\r\n00:35:12,450 --> 00:35:13,807\r\nLet's get out of here.\r\n\r\n530\r\n00:35:14,009 --> 00:35:16,405\r\nNo, sir.\r\nI'm waiting for a lady.\r\n\r\n531\r\n00:35:16,606 --> 00:35:19,082\r\nLet's go. Ain't nothing\r\nbut trouble for you here.\r\n\r\n532\r\n00:35:19,323 --> 00:35:21,078\r\nI know she's coming back.\r\n\r\n533\r\n00:35:21,320 --> 00:35:22,996\r\nWe'll drive all night.\r\n\r\n534\r\n00:35:23,237 --> 00:35:25,753\r\nWe'll get drunk\r\nand stay away tiIl she's gone.\r\n\r\n535\r\n00:35:25,994 --> 00:35:27,752\r\nShut up and go home, will you?\r\n\r\n536\r\n00:35:27,991 --> 00:35:30,747\r\nNo, sir. l'm staying right here.\r\n\r\n537\r\n00:35:35,701 --> 00:35:37,857\r\nThey grab Ugarte, then she waIks in.\r\n\r\n538\r\n00:35:38,098 --> 00:35:39,175\r\n(SAM PLAYS PIANO)\r\n\r\n539\r\n00:35:39,418 --> 00:35:41,933\r\nThat's the way it goes.\r\nOne in, one out.\r\n\r\n540\r\n00:35:43,013 --> 00:35:45,169\r\n-Sam.\r\n-Yes, boss.\r\n\r\n541\r\n00:35:45,409 --> 00:35:49,441\r\nIf it's December, 1 941 in Casablanca,\r\nwhat time is it in New York?\r\n\r\n542\r\n00:35:49,963 --> 00:35:51,001\r\nWhat--?\r\n\r\n543\r\n00:35:51,361 --> 00:35:52,718\r\nMy watch stopped.\r\n\r\n544\r\n00:35:53,558 --> 00:35:55,635\r\nI bet they're asIeep in New York.\r\n\r\n545\r\n00:35:55,875 --> 00:35:58,471\r\nI bet they're asIeep all over America.\r\n\r\n546\r\n00:36:04,904 --> 00:36:08,299\r\nOf aIl the gin joints in all the towns\r\nin all the world...\r\n\r\n547\r\n00:36:09,139 --> 00:36:11,135\r\n...she walks into mine.\r\n\r\n548\r\n00:36:18,206 --> 00:36:20,602\r\n-What are you playing?\r\n-A Iittle something of my own.\r\n\r\n549\r\n00:36:20,844 --> 00:36:23,438\r\n-Stop it. You know what I wanna hear.\r\n-I don't.\r\n\r\n550\r\n00:36:23,640 --> 00:36:25,957\r\nYou played it for her,\r\nyou can play it for me.\r\n\r\n551\r\n00:36:26,196 --> 00:36:29,191\r\n-I don't remember--\r\n-If she can stand it, I can.\r\n\r\n552\r\n00:36:29,431 --> 00:36:30,669\r\nPlay it!\r\n\r\n553\r\n00:36:31,349 --> 00:36:32,787\r\nYes, boss.\r\n\r\n554\r\n00:36:33,866 --> 00:36:37,142\r\n(SAM PLAYS \"AS TlME GOES BY\")\r\n\r\n555\r\n00:37:58,758 --> 00:38:01,393\r\nWho are you really?\r\nAnd what were you before?\r\n\r\n556\r\n00:38:01,715 --> 00:38:03,670\r\nWhat did you do\r\nand what did you think?\r\n\r\n557\r\n00:38:04,152 --> 00:38:06,027\r\