--> 00:46:52,851\r\nHow long was it we had, honey?\r\n\r\n652\r\n00:46:53,693 --> 00:46:55,578\r\n-I didn't count the days.\r\n-Well, I did.\r\n\r\n653\r\n00:46:56,219 --> 00:46:57,581\r\nEvery one of them.\r\n\r\n654\r\n00:46:58,223 --> 00:47:00,547\r\nMostly, I remember the Iast one.\r\n\r\n655\r\n00:47:00,989 --> 00:47:04,356\r\nThe \"wow\" finish. A guy standing\r\non a platform in the rain...\r\n\r\n656\r\n00:47:04,558 --> 00:47:08,967\r\n...with a comical Iook on his face\r\nfrom his insides having been kicked out.\r\n\r\n657\r\n00:47:10,491 --> 00:47:12,535\r\nCan l tell you a story, Rick?\r\n\r\n658\r\n00:47:12,737 --> 00:47:14,379\r\nHas it got a \"wow\" finish?\r\n\r\n659\r\n00:47:15,261 --> 00:47:17,225\r\nI don't know the finish yet.\r\n\r\n660\r\n00:47:17,427 --> 00:47:20,472\r\nGo on, tell it. Maybe one wilI\r\ncome to you as you go along.\r\n\r\n661\r\n00:47:23,158 --> 00:47:26,805\r\nIt's about a girl who'd just come\r\nto Paris from her home in Oslo.\r\n\r\n662\r\n00:47:27,007 --> 00:47:28,650\r\nAt the house of some friends...\r\n\r\n663\r\n00:47:28,852 --> 00:47:31,456\r\n...she met a man about whom\r\nshe'd heard her whole life.\r\n\r\n664\r\n00:47:31,698 --> 00:47:34,022\r\nA very great and courageous man.\r\n\r\n665\r\n00:47:35,186 --> 00:47:39,996\r\nHe opened up for her a beautifuI world\r\nfull of knowIedge, thoughts and ideaIs.\r\n\r\n666\r\n00:47:40,198 --> 00:47:43,644\r\nEverything she knew or ever became\r\nwas because of him.\r\n\r\n667\r\n00:47:44,326 --> 00:47:47,653\r\nShe Iooked up to him\r\nand worshiped him...\r\n\r\n668\r\n00:47:47,893 --> 00:47:50,217\r\n...with a feeIing she supposed was love.\r\n\r\n669\r\n00:47:50,700 --> 00:47:52,704\r\nYes, that's very pretty.\r\n\r\n670\r\n00:47:52,905 --> 00:47:56,032\r\nI heard a story once.\r\nI've heard a Iot of stories in my time.\r\n\r\n671\r\n00:47:56,232 --> 00:47:59,079\r\nThey went aIong with\r\nthe sound of a tinny piano...\r\n\r\n672\r\n00:47:59,279 --> 00:48:01,404\r\n...pIaying in the parlor downstairs.\r\n\r\n673\r\n00:48:02,206 --> 00:48:06,695\r\n\"Mister, I met a man once when\r\nI was a kid,\" they'd always begin.\r\n\r\n674\r\n00:48:09,261 --> 00:48:12,507\r\nI guess neither one of our stories\r\nis very funny.\r\n\r\n675\r\n00:48:12,790 --> 00:48:13,750\r\nTell me...\r\n\r\n676\r\n00:48:14,954 --> 00:48:16,876\r\n...who was it you left me for?\r\n\r\n677\r\n00:48:17,079 --> 00:48:19,563\r\nWas it Laszlo, or were there\r\nothers in between...\r\n\r\n678\r\n00:48:20,527 --> 00:48:22,530\r\n...or aren't you the kind that tells?\r\n\r\n679\r\n00:48:46,865 --> 00:48:50,192\r\nSTRASSER: l suspect Ugarte left\r\nthe letters of transit with Mr. Blaine.\r\n\r\n680\r\n00:48:50,433 --> 00:48:52,837\r\nI suggest you search\r\nthe cafè immediately.\r\n\r\n681\r\n00:48:53,037 --> 00:48:55,884\r\nIf Rick has them, he's too smart\r\nto let you find them there.\r\n\r\n682\r\n00:48:56,085 --> 00:48:57,888\r\nYou give him credit\r\nfor too much cIeverness.\r\n\r\n683\r\n00:48:58,089 --> 00:49:00,815\r\nMy impression was that he's just\r\nanother blundering American.\r\n\r\n684\r\n00:49:01,016 --> 00:49:03,060\r\nWe mustn't underestimate\r\nAmerican blundering.\r\n\r\n685\r\n00:49:03,261 --> 00:49:06,428\r\nI was with them when they\r\nblundered into BerIin in 1 91 8.\r\n\r\n686\r\n00:49:07,069 --> 00:49:09,674\r\nAs to LaszIo, we want him watched\r\n24 hours a day.\r\n\r\n687\r\n00:49:09,877 --> 00:49:13,563\r\nLOUIS: It may interest you to know that\r\nat this moment he's on his way here.\r\n\r\n688\r\n00:49:19,056 --> 00:49:20,979\r\nOFFlCER:\r\nThere's nothing we can do.\r\n\r\n689\r\n00:49:22,142 --> 00:49:24,508\r\nI'm delighted to see you both.\r\nDid you rest weIl?\r\n\r\n690\r\n00:49:24,668 --> 00:49:25,629\r\nI slept well.\r\n\r\n691\r\n00:49:25,830 --> 00:49:29,277\r\nThat's strange. Nobody's supposed\r\nto sleep well in CasabIanca.\r\n\r\n692\r\n00:49:29,598 --> 00:49:32,886\r\n-May we proceed with the business?\r\n-With pleasure. Sit down.\r\n\r\n693\r\n00:49:35,373 --> 00:49:38,578\r\nWe won't mince words. You're\r\nan escaped prisoner of the Reich.\r\n\r\n694\r\n00:49:38,779 --> 00:49:41,345\r\nSo far you've been\r\nfortunate enough in eluding us.\r\n\r\n695\r\n00:49:41,586 --> 00:49:43,068\r\nYou have reached Casablanca.\r\n\r\n696\r\n00:49:43,270 --> 00:49:45,875\r\nIt is my duty to see\r\nthat you stay here.\r\n\r\n697\r\n00:49:46,076 --> 00:49:47,999\r\nWhether or not you'll\r\nsucceed is problematic.\r\n\r\n698\r\n00:49:48,201 --> 00:49:50,845\r\nNot at all. Renault's signature\r\nis necessary on every visa.\r\n\r\n699\r\n00:49:51,047 --> 00:49:53,572\r\nIs it possible Herr Laszlo\r\nwill receive a visa?\r\n\r\n700\r\n00:49:53,773 --> 00:49:55,977\r\nI'm afraid not.\r\nMy regrets, monsieur.\r\n\r\n701\r\n00:49:56,179 --> 00:49:58,581\r\nWell, perhaps\r\nI shalI like it in Casablanca.\r\n\r\n702\r\n00:49:58,784 --> 00:50:00,266\r\nSTRASSER:\r\nAnd mademoiselle?\r\n\r\n703\r\n00:50:00,467 --> 00:50:03,955\r\n-You needn't be concerned about me.\r\n-Is that aIl you wish to tell us?\r\n\r\n704\r\n00:50:04,196 --> 00:50:06,921\r\nDon't be in a hurry.\r\nYou have alI the time in the world.\r\n\r\n705\r\n00:50:07,123 --> 00:50:09,565\r\nYou may be in\r\nCasablanca indefinitely.\r\n\r\n706\r\n00:50:10,009 --> 00:50:12,815\r\nOr you may leave for Lisbon tomorrow.\r\nOn one condition.\r\n\r\n707\r\n00:50:12,975 --> 00:50:13,937\r\nAnd that is?\r\n\r\n708\r\n00:50:14,258 --> 00:50:17,423\r\nYou know the leader of the underground\r\nmovement in Paris, in Prague...\r\n\r\n709\r\n00:50:17,665 --> 00:50:21,153\r\n...in BrusseIs, in Amsterdam,\r\nin Oslo, in Belgrade, in Athens....\r\n\r\n710\r\n00:50:21,393 --> 00:50:23,799\r\n-Even BerIin.\r\nSTRASSER: Yes, even in Berlin.\r\n\r\n711\r\n00:50:24,080 --> 00:50:28,329\r\nIf you'lI furnish me with their names\r\nand whereabouts, you'll have your visa.\r\n\r\n712\r\n00:50:28,649 --> 00:50:31,656\r\nLOUIS: And the honor of having\r\nserved the Third Reich.\r\n\r\n713\r\n00:50:31,898 --> 00:50:34,263\r\nI was in a German\r\nconcentration camp for a year.\r\n\r\n714\r\n00:50:34,464 --> 00:50:35,906\r\nThat's honor enough for a lifetime.\r\n\r\n715\r\n00:50:36,428 --> 00:50:37,749\r\nYou'll give us the names?\r\n\r\n716\r\n00:50:39,315 --> 00:50:41,679\r\nIf l didn't give them to you\r\nin a concentration camp...\r\n\r\n717\r\n00:50:41,919 --> 00:50:44,765\r\n...where you had more persuasive\r\nmethods at your disposal...\r\n\r\n718\r\n00:50:45,006 --> 00:50:47,451\r\n...l certainly won't\r\ngive them to you now.\r\n\r\n719\r\n00:50:47,933 --> 00:50:50,137\r\nWhat if you track them down\r\nand kill them?\r\n\r\n720\r\n00:50:50,377 --> 00:50:51,860\r\nWhat if you murdered us alI?\r\n\r\n721\r\n00:50:52,103 --> 00:50:56,110\r\nFrom every corner of Europe, hundreds,\r\nthousands would rise to take our places.\r\n\r\n722\r\n00:50:56,351 --> 00:50:58,515\r\nEven Nazis can't kill that fast.\r\n\r\n723\r\n00:50:58,918 --> 00:51:02,123\r\nYou have a reputation for eloquence,\r\nwhich I can now understand.\r\n\r\n724\r\n00:51:02,325 --> 00:51:03,726\r\nBut you're mistaken.\r\n\r\n725\r\n00:51:03,968 --> 00:51:06,452\r\nYou said enemies of the Reich\r\ncould be replaced.\r\n\r\n726\r\n00:51:06,654 --> 00:51:08,097\r\nThere is one exception.\r\n\r\n727\r\n00:51:08,299 --> 00:51:10,623\r\nNo one could take your place\r\nif anything unfortunate...\r\n\r\n728\r\n00:51:10,864 --> 00:51:13,669\r\n...shouId occur to you\r\nwhile you're trying to escape.\r\n\r\n729\r\n00:51:14,150 --> 00:51:16,154\r\nYou won't dare\r\nto interfere with me here.\r\n\r\n730\r\n00:51:16,396 --> 00:51:17,998\r\nThis is stiIl unoccupied France.\r\n\r\n731\r\n00:51:18,400 --> 00:51:20,925\r\nAny violation of neutraIity\r\nwouId reflect on the captain.\r\n\r\n732\r\n00:51:21,166 --> 00:51:23,771\r\n-Insofar as it is in my power....\r\n-Thank you.\r\n\r\n733\r\n00:51:24,013 --> 00:51:28,141\r\nBy the way, last night you evinced\r\nan interest in Señor Ugarte.\r\n\r\n734\r\n00:51:28,582 --> 00:51:29,544\r\nYes.\r\n\r\n735\r\n00:51:29,786 --> 00:51:31,268\r\nYou have a message for him.\r\n\r\n736\r\n00:51:32,552 --> 00:51:34,717\r\nNothing important.\r\nMay I speak to him now?\r\n\r\n737\r\n00:51:35,439 --> 00:51:38,083\r\nYou would find the conversation\r\na trifle one-sided.\r\n\r\n738\r\n00:51:38,326 --> 00:51:40,048\r\nSeñor Ugarte is dead.\r\n\r\n739\r\n00:51:46,543 --> 00:51:47,784\r\nI'm making the report.\r\n\r\n740\r\n00:51:47,986 --> 00:51:51,032\r\nWe haven't quite decided whether\r\nhe committed suicide...\r\n\r\n741\r\n00:51:51,272 --> 00:51:52,916\r\n...or died trying to escape.\r\n\r\n742\r\n00:51:54,641 --> 00:51:57,246\r\n-Are you finished with us?\r\nSTRASSER: For the time being.\r\n\r\n743\r\n00:51:57,446 --> 00:51:58,608\r\nGood day.\r\n\r\n744\r\n00:52:03,098 --> 00:52:05,544\r\nTheir next step\r\nwill be to the black market.\r\n\r\n745\r\n00:52:05,786 --> 00:52:06,827\r\nOFFlCER:\r\nExcuse me, captain.\r\n\r\n746\r\n00:52:07,029 --> 00:52:09,433\r\nAnother visa\r\nproblem has come up.\r\n\r\n747\r\n00:52:10,315 --> 00:52:11,838\r\nShow her in.\r\n\r\n748\r\n00:52:21,540 --> 00:52:24,265\r\nSorry, we wouldn't be able\r\nto handle the police.\r\n\r\n749\r\n00:52:24,507 --> 00:52:26,911\r\n-This is a job for Señor Ferrari.\r\n-Ferrari?\r\n\r\n750\r\n00:52:27,153 --> 00:52:29,396\r\nIt can be most helpfuI\r\nto know Ferrari.\r\n\r\n751\r\n00:52:29,639 --> 00:52:32,122\r\nHe has a monopoly\r\non the bIack market here.\r\n\r\n752\r\n00:52:32,364 --> 00:52:34,207\r\nYou'll find him at the BIue Parrot.\r\n\r\n753\r\n00:52:34,850 --> 00:52:36,293\r\nMAN: Thanks.\r\n\r\n754\r\n00:52:47,958 --> 00:52:49,401\r\nFERRARl:\r\nDon't be too downhearted.\r\n\r\n755\r\n00:52:49,643 --> 00:52:52,328\r\nPerhaps you can come to terms\r\nwith Capt. RenauIt.\r\n\r\n756\r\n00:52:53,051 --> 00:52:55,173\r\nRICK: Hello, Ferrari.\r\nFERRARl: Good morning, Rick.\r\n\r\n757\r\n00:52:55,416 --> 00:52:57,740\r\nI see the bus is in.\r\nI'll take my shipment.\r\n\r\n758\r\n00:52:57,941 --> 00:53:00,546\r\n-No hurry. Have a drink.\r\n-I never drink in the morning.\r\n\r\n759\r\n00:53:00,747 --> 00:53:03,992\r\nEvery time you send my shipment,\r\nit's always a bit short.\r\n\r\n760\r\n00:53:04,197 --> 00:53:06,157\r\nCarrying charges, my boy.\r\n\r\n761\r\n00:53:06,400 --> 00:53:07,642\r\nHere, sit down.\r\n\r\n762\r\n00:53:07,842 --> 00:53:10,287\r\nThere's something\r\nI want to talk over with you.\r\n\r\n763\r\n00:53:12,413 --> 00:53:14,016\r\nFERRARl:\r\nThe news about Ugarte upsets me.\r\n\r\n764\r\n00:53:14,257 --> 00:53:17,102\r\nYou're a fat hypocrite. You don't feel\r\nany sorrier than I do.\r\n\r\n765\r\n00:53:17,264 --> 00:53:18,226\r\nOf course not.\r\n\r\n766\r\n00:53:18,426 --> 00:53:22,355\r\nWhat upsets me is that he's dead and\r\nno one knows where those letters are.\r\n\r\n767\r\n00:53:22,636 --> 00:53:23,637\r\nPractically no one.\r\n\r\n768\r\n00:53:23,879 --> 00:53:26,242\r\nFERRARl: If I had those letters,\r\nI could make a fortune.\r\n\r\n769\r\n00:53:26,484 --> 00:53:28,447\r\nSo could I,\r\nand l'm a poor businessman.\r\n\r\n770\r\n00:53:28,648 --> 00:53:30,613\r\nI've a proposition\r\nfor whoever has them.\r\n\r\n771\r\n00:53:30,813 --> 00:53:32,216\r\nI'll handle the transaction.\r\n\r\n772\r\n00:53:32,458 --> 00:53:35,223\r\nGet rid of the letters, take\r\nall the risk, for a small fee.\r\n\r\n773\r\n00:53:35,464 --> 00:53:36,866\r\nAnd the carrying charges?\r\n\r\n774\r\n00:53:37,107 --> 00:53:39,833\r\nNaturally, there wilI be\r\na few incidental expenses.\r\n\r\n775\r\n00:53:40,435 --> 00:53:42,640\r\nThat's my proposition\r\nfor whoever has the letters.\r\n\r\n776\r\n00:53:42,841 --> 00:53:44,282\r\nRICK:\r\nI'll tell him when he comes in.\r\n\r\n777\r\n00:53:44,525 --> 00:53:47,169\r\nI'll put my cards out.\r\nI think you know where they are.\r\n\r\n778\r\n00:53:47,370 --> 00:53:50,977\r\nYou're in good company. Renault\r\nand Strasser probably think so too.\r\n\r\n779\r\n00:53:55,950 --> 00:53:58,875\r\nI came over here to give them\r\na chance to ransack my place.\r\n\r\n780\r\n00:53:59,075 --> 00:54:02,242\r\nDon't be a fool. Take me into\r\nyour confidence. You need a partner.\r\n\r\n781\r\n00:54:02,444 --> 00:54:04,608\r\nExcuse me,\r\nI'll be getting back.\r\n\r\n782\r\n00:54:07,735 --> 00:54:11,502\r\nLASZLO: Good morning.\r\n-Ferrari is the fat gent at the tabIe.\r\n\r\n783\r\n00:54:15,713 --> 00:54:18,359\r\nDEALER: You won't find a treasure\r\nlike this in all Morocco.\r\n\r\n784\r\n00:54:18,560 --> 00:54:19,802\r\nOnly 700 francs.\r\n\r\n785\r\n00:54:20,003 --> 00:54:21,726\r\nYou're being cheated.\r\n\r\n786\r\n00:54:21,927 --> 00:54:23,168\r\nIt doesn't matter, thank you.\r\n\r\n787\r\n00:54:23,370 --> 00:54:26,215\r\nFor friends of Rick's\r\nwe have a small discount.\r\n\r\n788\r\n00:54:26,418 --> 00:54:28,983\r\nDid I say 700 francs?\r\nYou can have it for 200.\r\n\r\n789\r\n00:54:29,222 --> 00:54:32,270\r\nI'm sorry I was in no condition\r\nto receive you last night.\r\n\r\n790\r\n00:54:32,471 --> 00:54:33,433\r\nIt doesn't matter.\r\n\r\n791\r\n00:54:33,593 --> 00:54:36,078\r\nSpeciaI friends of Rick's\r\nget a special discount.\r\n\r\n792\r\n00:54:36,279 --> 00:54:37,360\r\nOne hundred francs.\r\n\r\n793\r\n00:54:37,602 --> 00:54:40,608\r\nYour story had me confused,\r\nor maybe it was the bourbon.\r\n\r\n794\r\n00:54:40,849 --> 00:54:42,092\r\nI have some tabIecloths--\r\n\r\n795\r\n00:54:42,332 --> 00:54:44,977\r\nILSA: l'm realIy not interested.\r\nDEALER: Please, one minute.\r\n\r\n796\r\n00:54:45,419 --> 00:54:48,827\r\nDid you come back to teIl me\r\nwhy you ran out on me at the station?\r\n\r\n797\r\n00:54:48,987 --> 00:54:49,948\r\nYes.\r\n\r\n798\r\n00:54:50,149 --> 00:54:52,473\r\nYou can tell me now.\r\nI'm reasonabIy sober.\r\n\r\n799\r\n00:54:52,675 --> 00:54:53,997\r\nI don't think l will.\r\n\r\n800\r\n00:54:54,199 --> 00:54:58,206\r\nWhy not? I got stuck with the\r\nraiIway ticket. I'm entitIed to know.\r\n\r\n801\r\n00:54:58,608 --> 00:55:00,772\r\nLast night I saw\r\nwhat has happened to you.\r\n\r\n802\r\n00:55:01,295 --> 00:55:04,461\r\nThe Rick I knew in Paris,\r\nI could teIl him. He'd understand.\r\n\r\n803\r\n00:55:04,662 --> 00:55:07,187\r\nBut the one who looked at me\r\nwith such hatred....\r\n\r\n804\r\n00:55:08,670 --> 00:55:11,396\r\nI'll be leaving soon and\r\nwe'lI never see each other again.\r\n\r\n805\r\n00:55:12,600 --> 00:55:16,046\r\nWe knew very little about each other\r\nwhen we were in love in Paris.\r\n\r\n806\r\n00:55:16,647 --> 00:55:20,857\r\nIf we Ieave it that way, maybe we'Il\r\nremember those days, and not Casablanca.\r\n\r\n807\r\n00:55:21,740 --> 00:55:22,981\r\nNot last night.\r\n\r\n808\r\n00:55:23,461 --> 00:55:26,503\r\nDid you run out on me because\r\nyou knew what it'd be Iike?\r\n\r\n809\r\n00:55:26,743 --> 00:55:29,505\r\nHiding from the police,\r\nrunning away all the time?\r\n\r\n810\r\n00:55:29,746 --> 00:55:31,307\r\nBelieve that if you want to.\r\n\r\n811\r\n00:55:31,508 --> 00:55:34,109\r\nI'm not running away anymore.\r\nI'm settIed now.\r\n\r\n812\r\n00:55:34,350 --> 00:55:36,111\r\nAbove a saloon, it's true, but....\r\n\r\n813\r\n00:55:36,313 --> 00:55:39,273\r\nWalk up a flight.\r\nI'll be expecting you.\r\n\r\n814\r\n00:55:41,476 --> 00:55:44,077\r\nAlI the same,\r\nsomeday you'll lie to Laszlo.\r\n\r\n815\r\n00:55:44,279 --> 00:55:45,680\r\nYou'll be there.\r\n\r\n816\r\n00:55:47,482 --> 00:55:48,881\r\nNo, Rick.\r\n\r\n817\r\n00:55:49,764 --> 00:55:52,484\r\nNo. You see,\r\nVictor Laszlo is my husband.\r\n\r\n818\r\n00:55:52,966 --> 00:55:56,088\r\nAnd was, even when\r\nI knew you in Paris.\r\n\r\n819\r\n00:56:00,812 --> 00:56:04,895\r\nI was just telling Laszlo that,\r\nunfortunately, l'm not able to help him.\r\n\r\n820\r\n00:56:05,377 --> 00:56:07,098\r\nThe word has gone around.\r\n\r\n821\r\n00:56:07,337 --> 00:56:11,501\r\nAs Ieader of aIl iIlegal activities,\r\nI'm an influential and respected man.\r\n\r\n822\r\n00:56:12,543 --> 00:56:15,142\r\nBut it'd not be worth my Iife\r\nto do anything for Laszlo.\r\n\r\n823\r\n00:56:15,385 --> 00:56:17,144\r\nYou, however, are a different matter.\r\n\r\n824\r\n00:56:17,387 --> 00:56:21,709\r\nSeñor Ferrari thinks it might just be\r\npossibIe to get an exit visa for you.\r\n\r\n825\r\n00:56:22,190 --> 00:56:25,111\r\n-You mean for me to go on alone?\r\nFERRARl: And only alone.\r\n\r\n826\r\n00:56:25,313 --> 00:56:28,273\r\nI'll stay and keep trying.\r\nI'm sure in a Iittle while--\r\n\r\n827\r\n00:56:28,475 --> 00:56:30,116\r\nMight as well be frank.\r\n\r\n828\r\n00:56:30,318 --> 00:56:33,799\r\nIt'd take a miracle to get you out.\r\nThe Germans have outlawed miracles.\r\n\r\n829\r\n00:56:34,161 --> 00:56:36,001\r\nWe're only interested in two visas.\r\n\r\n830\r\n00:56:36,202 --> 00:56:38,483\r\n-Please, llsa, don't be hasty.\r\n-No, Victor.\r\n\r\n831\r\n00:56:38,924 --> 00:56:40,805\r\nYou two wilI want to discuss this.\r\n\r\n832\r\n00:56:41,006 --> 00:56:43,327\r\nExcuse me.\r\nI'll be at the bar.\r\n\r\n833\r\n00:56:46,611 --> 00:56:48,332\r\nNo, I won't let you stay here.\r\n\r\n834\r\n00:56:48,533 --> 00:56:51,694\r\nYou must get to America.\r\nSomehow I'lI get out and join you.\r\n\r\n835\r\n00:56:51,975 --> 00:56:53,695\r\nIf the situation were different...\r\n\r\n836\r\n00:56:53,898 --> 00:56:56,338\r\n...if I had to stay and there was\r\nonly one visa...\r\n\r\n837\r\n00:56:56,538 --> 00:56:57,659\r\n...would you take it?\r\n\r\n838\r\n00:56:58,901 --> 00:56:59,860\r\nYes, l wouId.\r\n\r\n839\r\n00:57:01,023 --> 00:57:02,743\r\nYes, l see.\r\n\r\n840\r\n00:57:03,425 --> 00:57:05,305\r\nWhen I had trouble\r\ngetting out of Lille...\r\n\r\n841\r\n00:57:05,506 --> 00:57:06,946\r\n...why didn't you leave me?\r\n\r\n842\r\n00:57:07,187 --> 00:57:11,310\r\nWhen I was sick in MarseilIes\r\nfor two weeks and you were in danger...\r\n\r\n843\r\n00:57:11,511 --> 00:57:13,032\r\n...why didn't you leave me?\r\n\r\n844\r\n00:57:14,314 --> 00:57:16,675\r\nI meant to.\r\nSomething aIways held me up.\r\n\r\n845\r\n00:57:19,159 --> 00:57:20,478\r\nI love you very much.\r\n\r\n846\r\n00:57:21,640 --> 00:57:23,961\r\nYour secret will be safe with me.\r\n\r\n847\r\n00:57:24,802 --> 00:57:26,684\r\nFerrari is waiting for our answer.\r\n\r\n848\r\n00:57:27,005 --> 00:57:28,965\r\nFERRARl:\r\nNot more than 50 francs.\r\n\r\n849\r\n00:57:33,608 --> 00:57:35,291\r\nWe've decided, Señor Ferrari.\r\n\r\n850\r\n00:57:35,531 --> 00:57:38,973\r\nFor the present we're Iooking\r\nfor two visas. Thank you very much.\r\n\r\n851\r\n00:57:39,175 --> 00:57:40,815\r\nGood luck, but be careful.\r\n\r\n852\r\n00:57:41,056 --> 00:57:43,697\r\n-You know you're being shadowed?\r\n-It becomes instinct.\r\n\r\n853\r\n00:57:44,178 --> 00:57:46,940\r\nI observe that you, in one respect,\r\nare very fortunate.\r\n\r\n854\r\n00:57:47,262 --> 00:57:49,702\r\nI'll make one suggestion.\r\nWhy, I do not know.\r\n\r\n855\r\n00:57:49,943 --> 00:57:51,864\r\nIt cannot possibly profit me.\r\n\r\n856\r\n00:57:52,066 --> 00:57:54,267\r\nHave you heard\r\nabout the letters of transit?\r\n\r\n857\r\n00:57:55,068 --> 00:57:56,027\r\nYes, something.\r\n\r\n858\r\n00:57:56,268 --> 00:57:58,989\r\nThey were not found on Ugarte\r\nwhen they arrested him.\r\n\r\n859\r\n00:57:59,512 --> 00:58:01,393\r\n-You know where they are?\r\n-Not for sure.\r\n\r\n860\r\n00:58:01,633 --> 00:58:04,555\r\nBut my guess is Ugarte left\r\nthose letters with Rick.\r\n\r\n861\r\n00:58:06,477 --> 00:58:09,359\r\nHe's a difficult man.\r\nOne never knows what he'll do, or why.\r\n\r\n862\r\n00:58:09,640 --> 00:58:11,240\r\nBut it is worth a chance.\r\n\r\n863\r\n00:58:11,761 --> 00:58:14,203\r\nThank you very much.\r\nGood day.\r\n\r\n864\r\n00:58:14,684 --> 00:58:16,365\r\nBye. Thank you for your coffee.\r\n\r\n865\r\n00:58:16,565 --> 00:58:18,245\r\nI shalI miss that when we leave.\r\n\r\n866\r\n00:58:18,488 --> 00:58:21,049\r\nIt was gracious of you\r\nto share it with me.\r\n\r\n867\r\n00:58:21,289 --> 00:58:23,410\r\n-Monsieur.\r\n-Good day.\r\n\r\n868\r\n00:58:30,617 --> 00:58:32,178\r\n(SAM PLAYS PIANO)\r\n\r\n869\r\n00:58:32,499 --> 00:58:34,419\r\n-Here's to you, sir.\r\nMAN: Good Iuck.\r\n\r\n870\r\n00:58:34,701 --> 00:58:36,421\r\n-I'd better be going.\r\nMAN: Check, please.\r\n\r\n871\r\n00:58:36,622 --> 00:58:40,224\r\nI have to warn you. This is\r\na dangerous place, fulI of vultures.\r\n\r\n872\r\n00:58:40,466 --> 00:58:43,066\r\n-Vultures everywhere. Thanks.\r\n-Goodbye.\r\n\r\n873\r\n00:58:43,309 --> 00:58:46,229\r\nIt has been a pleasure to meet you.\r\nI'm sorry.\r\n\r\n874\r\n00:59:02,843 --> 00:59:05,846\r\nYou are getting to be\r\nyour best customer.\r\n\r\n875\r\n00:59:07,328 --> 00:59:09,649\r\nLOUIS: WeIl, drinking!\r\nI'm very pleased with you.\r\n\r\n876\r\n00:59:09,850 --> 00:59:11,571\r\nYou're beginning\r\nto live like a Frenchman.\r\n\r\n877\r\n00:59:11,812 --> 00:59:13,893\r\nThat's some going-over\r\nyour men gave my place.\r\n\r\n878\r\n00:59:14,093 --> 00:59:16,095\r\nWe bareIy got cleaned up\r\nin time to open.\r\n\r\n879\r\n00:59:16,337 --> 00:59:18,216\r\nI toId Strasser\r\nhe wouldn't find the letters.\r\n\r\n880\r\n00:59:18,417 --> 00:59:20,458\r\nBut l told my men to be\r\nespeciaIly destructive.\r\n\r\n881\r\n00:59:20,659 --> 00:59:23,461\r\nYou know how that impresses Germans.\r\n\r\n882\r\n00:59:24,063 --> 00:59:26,302\r\nRick, have you got\r\nthose letters of transit?\r\n\r\n883\r\n00:59:26,545 --> 00:59:28,905\r\nLouis, are you pro-Vichy\r\nor Free French?\r\n\r\n884\r\n00:59:29,147 --> 00:59:33,068\r\nServes me right for asking a direct\r\nquestion. The subject is cIosed.\r\n\r\n885\r\n00:59:33,349 --> 00:59:35,271\r\nIt Iooks Iike you're a Iittle late.\r\n\r\n886\r\n00:59:42,998 --> 00:59:44,639\r\nSo Yvonne's gone over to the enemy.\r\n\r\n887\r\n00:59:44,839 --> 00:59:48,682\r\nWho knows? In her own way, she may\r\nconstitute an entire second front.\r\n\r\n888\r\n00:59:49,123 --> 00:59:52,286\r\nIt's time for me to fIatter Strasser.\r\nI'll see you later.\r\n\r\n889\r\n00:59:52,926 --> 00:59:54,286\r\nSascha!\r\n\r\n890\r\n00:59:54,447 --> 00:59:55,408\r\nGERMAN SOLDlER:\r\nFrench '75.\r\n\r\n891\r\n00:59:55,648 --> 00:59:57,130\r\nPut up the whole row of those.\r\n\r\n892\r\n00:59:57,330 --> 00:59:59,331\r\nStarting here and ending here.\r\n\r\n893\r\n00:59:59,572 --> 01:00:01,733\r\nWe wiIl begin with two.\r\n\r\n894\r\n01:00:01,973 --> 01:00:03,894\r\n(IN FRENCH)\r\n\r\n895\r\n01:00:09,581 --> 01:00:11,580\r\nWhat did you say?\r\nWould you repeat it?\r\n\r\n896\r\n01:00:11,822 --> 01:00:13,344\r\nWhat l said is\r\nnot your business.\r\n\r\n897\r\n01:00:13,544 --> 01:00:14,943\r\nI'll make it my business.\r\n\r\n898\r\n01:00:20,990 --> 01:00:24,512\r\nI don't like disturbances in my place.\r\nLay off politics or get out.\r\n\r\n899\r\n01:00:28,716 --> 01:00:30,196\r\nYou see, captain?\r\n\r\n900\r\n01:00:30,396 --> 01:00:32,358\r\nThe situation is not under control.\r\n\r\n901\r\n01:00:32,559 --> 01:00:34,720\r\nLOUIS: We're trying to cooperate\r\nwith your government.\r\n\r\n902\r\n01:00:34,920 --> 01:00:36,803\r\nWe can't regulate\r\nour peopIe's feeIings.\r\n\r\n903\r\n01:00:37,043 --> 01:00:39,364\r\nAre you certain which side you're on?\r\n\r\n904\r\n01:00:39,724 --> 01:00:41,607\r\nI have no conviction.\r\n\r\n905\r\n01:00:41,807 --> 01:00:43,006\r\nI blow with the wind...\r\n\r\n906\r\n01:00:43,250 --> 01:00:45,410\r\n...and the prevailing wind\r\nis from Vichy.\r\n\r\n907\r\n01:00:45,650 --> 01:00:47,371\r\nAnd if it should change?\r\n\r\n908\r\n01:00:47,732 --> 01:00:49,652\r\nSurely the Reich doesn't admit\r\nthat possibility?\r\n\r\n909\r\n01:00:49,853 --> 01:00:51,775\r\nWe're concerned about more\r\nthan Casablanca.\r\n\r\n910\r\n01:00:51,975 --> 01:00:55,577\r\nEvery French province in Africa\r\nis honeycombed with traitors...\r\n\r\n911\r\n01:00:55,778 --> 01:00:58,460\r\n...waiting for their chance,\r\nwaiting perhaps for a leader.\r\n\r\n912\r\n01:00:58,660 --> 01:01:00,703\r\nA leader? Like Laszlo?\r\n\r\n913\r\n01:01:00,903 --> 01:01:02,263\r\nI have been thinking.\r\n\r\n914\r\n01:01:02,464 --> 01:01:05,426\r\nIt is too dangerous if you\r\nlet him go or let him stay.\r\n\r\n915\r\n01:01:05,627 --> 01:01:06,627\r\nI see what you mean.\r\n\r\n916\r\n01:01:07,268 --> 01:01:09,069\r\n(IN GERMAN)\r\n\r\n917\r\n01:01:12,353 --> 01:01:15,996\r\nThank you, CarI.\r\n\r\n918\r\n01:01:16,675 --> 01:01:18,436\r\nSit down. Have a brandy with us.\r\n\r\n919\r\n01:01:18,679 --> 01:01:21,039\r\nTo celebrate our leaving\r\nfor America tomorrow.\r\n\r\n920\r\n01:01:21,240 --> 01:01:22,361\r\nThank you very much.\r\n\r\n921\r\n01:01:22,561 --> 01:01:25,242\r\nI thought you'd ask me,\r\nso l brought the good brandy...\r\n\r\n922\r\n01:01:25,484 --> 01:01:26,923\r\n...and the dress gIass.\r\n\r\n923\r\n01:01:27,166 --> 01:01:28,845\r\nAt last the day's came!\r\n\r\n924\r\n01:01:29,086 --> 01:01:32,048\r\nWe are speaking nothing\r\nbut English now.\r\n\r\n925\r\n01:01:32,289 --> 01:01:34,931\r\nSo we shouId feel at home\r\nwhen we get to America.\r\n\r\n926\r\n01:01:35,132 --> 01:01:36,852\r\nA very nice idea.\r\n\r\n927\r\n01:01:37,134 --> 01:01:42,216\r\nTo America.\r\n\r\n928\r\n01:01:44,859 --> 01:01:46,781\r\n(IN GERMAN)\r\n\r\n929\r\n01:01:47,181 --> 01:01:48,822\r\nWhat watch?\r\n\r\n930\r\n01:01:49,503 --> 01:01:52,225\r\n-Ten watch.\r\n-Such much?\r\n\r\n931\r\n01:01:53,827 --> 01:01:55,908\r\nYou'll get along\r\nbeautifuIly in America.\r\n\r\n932\r\n01:01:57,031 --> 01:01:58,670\r\nLOUIS:\r\nHow is lady luck treating you?\r\n\r\n933\r\n01:01:58,911 --> 01:02:00,430\r\nOh, too bad.\r\n\r\n934\r\n01:02:01,034 --> 01:02:02,833\r\nYou'll find him over there.\r\n\r\n935\r\n01:02:08,920 --> 01:02:10,280\r\n-Monsieur Rick?\r\n-Yes?\r\n\r\n936\r\n01:02:10,522 --> 01:02:13,283\r\n-Could I speak to you?\r\n-How'd you get in? You're underage.\r\n\r\n937\r\n01:02:13,484 --> 01:02:16,005\r\n-I came with Capt. Renault.\r\n-I should've known.\r\n\r\n938\r\n01:02:16,206 --> 01:02:17,445\r\nMy husband is with me too.\r\n\r\n939\r\n01:02:17,647 --> 01:02:20,129\r\nHe is? Renault's getting\r\nbroad-minded. Sit down.\r\n\r\n940\r\n01:02:20,290 --> 01:02:21,249\r\nHave a drink?\r\n\r\n941\r\n01:02:21,490 --> 01:02:23,651\r\nOf course not.\r\nYou mind if I do?\r\n\r\n942\r\n01:02:24,732 --> 01:02:27,894\r\nMonsieur Rick, what kind of a man\r\nis Capt. Renault?\r\n\r\n943\r\n01:02:28,136 --> 01:02:29,696\r\nLike any other man,\r\nonly more so.\r\n\r\n944\r\n01:02:29,937 --> 01:02:32,979\r\nNo, I mean....\r\nIs he trustworthy? Is his word--\r\n\r\n945\r\n01:02:33,180 --> 01:02:35,061\r\nWho told you to ask me that?\r\n\r\n946\r\n01:02:35,302 --> 01:02:36,862\r\nHe did. Capt. Renault.\r\n\r\n947\r\n01:02:37,062 --> 01:02:39,184\r\nI thought so.\r\nWhere's your husband?\r\n\r\n948\r\n01:02:39,706 --> 01:02:43,508\r\nAt the roulette table, trying\r\nto win enough for our exit visas.\r\n\r\n949\r\n01:02:43,750 --> 01:02:45,390\r\nOf course he's losing.\r\n\r\n950\r\n01:02:45,590 --> 01:02:47,230\r\nHow long have you been married?\r\n\r\n951\r\n01:02:47,432 --> 01:02:48,432\r\nEight weeks.\r\n\r\n952\r\n01:02:49,353 --> 01:02:51,274\r\nWe come from Bulgaria.\r\n\r\n953\r\n01:02:51,675 --> 01:02:53,596\r\nThings are very bad there.\r\n\r\n954\r\n01:02:53,837 --> 01:02:56,118\r\nThe devil has the people\r\nby the throat.\r\n\r\n955\r\n01:02:56,359 --> 01:02:58,840\r\nSo Jan and l, we....\r\n\r\n956\r\n01:02:59,041 --> 01:03:01,523\r\nWe don't want our chiIdren\r\nto grow up there.\r\n\r\n957\r\n01:03:01,725 --> 01:03:03,924\r\n-So you decided to go to America.\r\n-Yes.\r\n\r\n958\r\n01:03:04,125 --> 01:03:06,286\r\nBut we have not much money...\r\n\r\n959\r\n01:03:06,728 --> 01:03:09,089\r\n...and traveling is\r\nso expensive and difficult.\r\n\r\n960\r\n01:03:09,330 --> 01:03:11,491\r\nIt was more than\r\nwe thought to get here.\r\n\r\n961\r\n01:03:11,932 --> 01:03:13,733\r\nThen Capt. Renault sees us.\r\n\r\n962\r\n01:03:13,934 --> 01:03:15,735\r\nHe's so kind.\r\nHe wants to heIp us.\r\n\r\n963\r\n01:03:15,897 --> 01:03:16,856\r\nYes, l'll bet.\r\n\r\n964\r\n01:03:17,257 --> 01:03:19,498\r\nHe tells me he can give us\r\nan exit visa.\r\n\r\n965\r\n01:03:19,700 --> 01:03:21,820\r\nBut we have no money.\r\n\r\n966\r\n01:03:22,022 --> 01:03:23,541\r\n-Does he know that?\r\n-Yes.\r\n\r\n967\r\n01:03:23,783 --> 01:03:25,662\r\nAnd he's still wilIing\r\nto give you a visa?\r\n\r\n968\r\n01:03:26,103 --> 01:03:27,144\r\nYou want to know....\r\n\r\n969\r\n01:03:27,344 --> 01:03:28,945\r\nWiIl he keep his word?\r\n\r\n970\r\n01:03:30,108 --> 01:03:31,067\r\nHe always has.\r\n\r\n971\r\n01:03:34,592 --> 01:03:35,912\r\nMonsieur....\r\n\r\n972\r\n01:03:36,153 --> 01:03:37,713\r\nYou are a man.\r\n\r\n973\r\n01:03:38,275 --> 01:03:40,674\r\nIf someone loved you very much...\r\n\r\n974\r\n01:03:40,876 --> 01:03:44,720\r\n...so that your happiness was the only\r\nthing she wanted in the world...\r\n\r\n975\r\n01:03:45,601 --> 01:03:48,321\r\n...and she did a bad thing\r\nto make certain of it...\r\n\r\n976\r\n01:03:48,923 --> 01:03:50,123\r\n...could you forgive her?\r\n\r\n977\r\n01:03:50,325 --> 01:03:51,684\r\nNobody ever loved me that much.\r\n\r\n978\r\n01:03:51,886 --> 01:03:55,888\r\nAnd he never knew, and the girl kept\r\nthis bad thing locked in her heart...\r\n\r\n979\r\n01:03:56,090 --> 01:03:57,450\r\n...that wouId be all right?\r\n\r\n980\r\n01:03:57,650 --> 01:03:59,971\r\n-You want my advice?\r\n-Yes, please.\r\n\r\n981\r\n01:04:00,213 --> 01:04:01,293\r\nGo back to Bulgaria.\r\n\r\n982\r\n01:04:01,734 --> 01:04:05,656\r\nBut if you knew what it means to us\r\nto leave Europe, to get to America.\r\n\r\n983\r\n01:04:06,938 --> 01:04:08,939\r\nBut if Jan should find out....\r\n\r\n984\r\n01:04:09,141 --> 01:04:10,740\r\nHe is such a boy.\r\n\r\n985\r\n01:04:11,062 --> 01:04:14,064\r\nIn many ways,\r\nI am so much oIder than he is.\r\n\r\n986\r\n01:04:14,264 --> 01:04:16,585\r\nYes, everybody in Casablanca\r\nhas probIems.\r\n\r\n987\r\n01:04:16,827 --> 01:04:19,148\r\nYours may work out.\r\nYou'll excuse me.\r\n\r\n988\r\n01:04:28,236 --> 01:04:29,277\r\nGood evening.\r\n\r\n989\r\n01:04:29,477 --> 01:04:30,477\r\nSee? Here we are again.\r\n\r\n990\r\n01:04:30,638 --> 01:04:32,879\r\nI'll take that as a compliment to Sam.\r\n\r\n991\r\n01:04:33,079 --> 01:04:36,162\r\nI suppose he means to you\r\nParis of happier days.\r\n\r\n992\r\n01:04:36,843 --> 01:04:39,684\r\nHe does. Could we have\r\na table close to him?\r\n\r\n993\r\n01:04:39,926 --> 01:04:42,327\r\nAnd as far away\r\nfrom Strasser as possible.\r\n\r\n994\r\n01:04:42,527 --> 01:04:45,009\r\nThe geography may be\r\ndifficult to arrange.\r\n\r\n995\r\n01:04:45,251 --> 01:04:46,811\r\nPaul, table 30.\r\n\r\n996\r\n01:04:47,051 --> 01:04:48,732\r\nWAITER:\r\nRight this way, if you please.\r\n\r\n997\r\n01:04:48,935 --> 01:04:52,495\r\nI'll have Sam play \"As Time Goes By.\"\r\nI believe that's your favorite.\r\n\r\n998\r\n01:04:52,737 --> 01:04:54,056\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\n999\r\n01:04:59,141 --> 01:05:01,222\r\n(PLAYS \"AS TIME GOES BY\")\r\n\r\n1000\r\n01:05:03,145 --> 01:05:04,587\r\nTwo cognac, please.\r\n\r\n1001\r\n01:05:10,992 --> 01:05:12,952\r\n(IN FRENCH)\r\n\r\n1002\r\n01:05:27,965 --> 01:05:30,046\r\nDo you wish to place\r\nanother bet, sir?\r\n\r\n1003\r\n01:05:30,769 --> 01:05:32,249\r\nNo, I guess not.\r\n\r\n1004\r\n01:05:32,450 --> 01:05:34,331\r\nHave you tried 22 tonight?\r\n\r\n1005\r\n01:05:35,853 --> 01:05:37,172\r\nI said \"22.\"\r\n\r\n1006\r\n01:05:53,028 --> 01:05:54,427\r\nLeave it there.\r\n\r\n1007\r\n01:06:08,520 --> 01:06:10,841\r\nCash it in and don't come back.\r\n\r\n1008\r\n01:06:12,923 --> 01:06:15,244\r\nAre you sure this place is honest?\r\n\r\n1009\r\n01:06:15,444 --> 01:06:18,847\r\nHonest? As honest as the day is long.\r\n\r\n1010\r\n01:06:21,890 --> 01:06:23,171\r\nHow are we doing tonight?\r\n\r\n1011\r\n01:06:23,372 --> 01:06:26,253\r\nA couple of thousand less\r\nthan l thought there would be.\r\n\r\n1012\r\n01:06:29,577 --> 01:06:30,897\r\nMonsieur Rick....\r\n\r\n1013\r\n01:06:36,382 --> 01:06:38,465\r\nHe's just a lucky guy.\r\n\r\n1014\r\n01:06:40,506 --> 01:06:43,269\r\nMonsieur Rick, may I get you\r\na cup of coffee?\r\n\r\n1015\r\n01:06:43,469 --> 01:06:44,870\r\nNo thanks, Carl.\r\n\r\n1016\r\n01:06:48,834 --> 01:06:51,834\r\n-Capt. Renault, may l--\r\n-Not here, please.\r\n\r\n1017\r\n01:06:52,156 --> 01:06:54,078\r\nCome to my office.\r\nWe'll be businesslike.\r\n\r\n1018\r\n01:06:54,318 --> 01:06:57,079\r\n-We'Il be there at six.\r\n-I'lI be there at ten.\r\n\r\n1019\r\n01:06:57,282 --> 01:06:58,881\r\nI'm very happy for both of you.\r\n\r\n1020\r\n01:06:59,083 --> 01:07:01,244\r\nStill, it's very strange\r\nthat you won.\r\n\r\n1021\r\n01:07:01,444 --> 01:07:03,444\r\nWell, maybe not so strange.\r\n\r\n1022\r\n01:07:03,645 --> 01:07:06,047\r\n-I'lI see you in the morning.\r\n-Thank you so much.\r\n\r\n1023\r\n01:07:13,774 --> 01:07:16,296\r\nBoss, you've done a beautiful thing.\r\n\r\n1024\r\n01:07:17,298 --> 01:07:19,218\r\nGo away, you crazy Russian.\r\n\r\n1025\r\n01:07:29,227 --> 01:07:30,468\r\nAs I suspected.\r\n\r\n1026\r\n01:07:30,668 --> 01:07:32,750\r\n-You're a rank sentimentaIist.\r\n-Why?\r\n\r\n1027\r\n01:07:32,951 --> 01:07:34,912\r\nWhy interfere\r\nwith my Iittle romances?\r\n\r\n1028\r\n01:07:35,113 --> 01:07:36,913\r\nPut it down as a gesture to Iove.\r\n\r\n1029\r\n01:07:37,113 --> 01:07:38,554\r\nI forgive you this time.\r\n\r\n1030\r\n01:07:38,795 --> 01:07:41,515\r\nBut l'lI be in tomorrow\r\nwith a breathtaking bIonde.\r\n\r\n1031\r\n01:07:41,717 --> 01:07:44,319\r\nAnd it'll make me\r\nvery happy if she loses.\r\n\r\n1032\r\n01:07:47,803 --> 01:07:49,602\r\nI wonder if I couId talk to you?\r\n\r\n1033\r\n01:07:49,764 --> 01:07:50,724\r\nGo ahead.\r\n\r\n1034\r\n01:07:50,926 --> 01:07:52,525\r\nIsn't there some other place?\r\n\r\n1035\r\n01:07:52,766 --> 01:07:55,169\r\nIt's rather confidential,\r\nwhat I have to say.\r\n\r\n1036\r\n01:07:57,010 --> 01:07:58,771\r\n-In my office.\r\n-Right.\r\n\r\n1037\r\n01:08:00,133 --> 01:08:02,773\r\nYou know it's very important\r\nI get out of CasabIanca.\r\n\r\n1038\r\n01:08:03,017 --> 01:08:05,737\r\nI'm priviIeged to be one\r\nof the leaders of a great movement.\r\n\r\n1039\r\n01:08:05,937 --> 01:08:07,577\r\nYou know what l've been doing.\r\n\r\n1040\r\n01:08:07,820 --> 01:08:11,702\r\nYou know what it means to the work,\r\nto the lives of thousands of peopIe...\r\n\r\n1041\r\n01:08:11,903 --> 01:08:13,784\r\n...that l continue my work.\r\n\r\n1042\r\n01:08:13,986 --> 01:08:15,305\r\nI'm not interested in politics.\r\n\r\n1043\r\n01:08:15,545 --> 01:08:19,188\r\nThe problems of the world are not\r\nin my department. I'm a saloonkeeper.\r\n\r\n1044\r\n01:08:19,630 --> 01:08:22,911\r\nMy friends in the underground tell me\r\nthat you've quite a record.\r\n\r\n1045\r\n01:08:23,112 --> 01:08:24,552\r\nYou ran guns to Ethiopia.\r\n\r\n1046\r\n01:08:24,753 --> 01:08:27,476\r\n-You fought the fascists in Spain.\r\n-What of it?\r\n\r\n1047\r\n01:08:27,716 --> 01:08:30,718\r\nIsn't it strange you always\r\nseem to fight with the underdog?\r\n\r\n1048\r\n01:08:30,998 --> 01:08:32,760\r\nI found that an expensive hobby.\r\n\r\n1049\r\n01:08:32,961 --> 01:08:35,521\r\nBut then I never was\r\nmuch of a businessman.\r\n\r\n1050\r\n01:08:35,722 --> 01:08:38,524\r\nAre you enough of a businessman\r\nto appreciate 1 00,000 francs?\r\n\r\n1051\r\n01:08:38,726 --> 01:08:40,086\r\nI appreciate it,\r\nbut I don't accept it.\r\n\r\n1052\r\n01:08:40,326 --> 01:08:41,447\r\nI'll raise it to 200,000.\r\n\r\n1053\r\n01:08:41,807 --> 01:08:46,091\r\nMake it a million francs or three.\r\nMy answer would stilI be the same.\r\n\r\n1054\r\n01:08:46,291 --> 01:08:48,373\r\nThere's a reason\r\nyou won't let me have them.\r\n\r\n1055\r\n01:08:48,614 --> 01:08:49,694\r\nThere is.\r\n\r\n1056\r\n01:08:50,134 --> 01:08:52,176\r\nI suggest that you ask your wife.\r\n\r\n1057\r\n01:08:52,417 --> 01:08:54,977\r\n-I beg your pardon?\r\n-I said, ask your wife.\r\n\r\n1058\r\n01:08:55,339 --> 01:08:57,580\r\n-My wife?\r\n-Yes.\r\n\r\n1059\r\n01:08:57,821 --> 01:08:59,703\r\n(GERMANS SING \"DAS LIED\r\nDER DEUTSCHEN\")\r\n\r\n1060\r\n01:09:36,494 --> 01:09:38,376\r\nPlay \"La MarseiIlaise.\"\r\nPlay it!\r\n\r\n1061\r\n01:09:42,423 --> 01:09:45,866\r\n(SINGlNG \"LA MARSEILLAlSE\")\r\n\r\n1062\r\n01:10:37,220 --> 01:10:38,862\r\n(PATRONS CHEER)\r\n\r\n1063\r\n01:10:51,520 --> 01:10:55,245\r\nSee? If Laszlo's presence in a cafè\r\ncan inspire this demonstration...\r\n\r\n1064\r\n01:10:55,487 --> 01:10:57,728\r\n...what more wiIl his\r\npresence here bring on?\r\n\r\n1065\r\n01:10:57,929 --> 01:11:00,012\r\nI advise that this place\r\nbe shut up at once.\r\n\r\n1066\r\n01:11:00,214 --> 01:11:02,857\r\n-Everybody's having a good time.\r\n-Much too good a time.\r\n\r\n1067\r\n01:11:03,097 --> 01:11:04,218\r\nThe place is to be cIosed.\r\n\r\n1068\r\n01:11:04,418 --> 01:11:07,143\r\n-But l've no excuse to close it.\r\n-Find one.\r\n\r\n1069\r\n01:11:12,109 --> 01:11:13,712\r\nLOUIS:\r\nEveryone is to leave immediately.\r\n\r\n1070\r\n01:11:13,912 --> 01:11:16,035\r\nThis cafè is closed\r\nuntil further notice.\r\n\r\n1071\r\n01:11:16,236 --> 01:11:18,158\r\nClear the room at once!\r\n\r\n1072\r\n01:11:21,123 --> 01:11:22,204\r\nOn what grounds?\r\n\r\n1073\r\n01:11:22,445 --> 01:11:25,728\r\nI'm shocked to find that\r\ngambling is going on in here.\r\n\r\n1074\r\n01:11:26,170 --> 01:11:27,811\r\n-Your winnings, sir.\r\n-Thank you.\r\n\r\n1075\r\n01:11:28,053 --> 01:11:29,253\r\nEverybody out at once!\r\n\r\n1076\r\n01:11:33,580 --> 01:11:37,425\r\nAfter this disturbance, it's not safe\r\nfor Laszlo to stay in Casablanca.\r\n\r\n1077\r\n01:11:37,667 --> 01:11:40,110\r\nThis morning it wasn't safe\r\nfor him to leave.\r\n\r\n1078\r\n01:11:40,351 --> 01:11:43,233\r\nThat's also true,\r\nexcept to return to occupied France.\r\n\r\n1079\r\n01:11:43,475 --> 01:11:46,158\r\n-Occupied France?\r\n-Under safe conduct from me.\r\n\r\n1080\r\n01:11:46,358 --> 01:11:47,360\r\nOf what value is that?\r\n\r\n1081\r\n01:11:47,601 --> 01:11:50,323\r\nRemember what German guarantees\r\nhave been worth in the past.\r\n\r\n1082\r\n01:11:50,565 --> 01:11:53,649\r\n-There are only two other alternatives.\r\n-What are they?\r\n\r\n1083\r\n01:11:53,850 --> 01:11:57,936\r\nFrench authorities may find a reason to\r\nput him in the concentration camp here.\r\n\r\n1084\r\n01:11:58,136 --> 01:11:59,136\r\nILSA:\r\nThe other alternative?\r\n\r\n1085\r\n01:11:59,377 --> 01:12:03,903\r\nPerhaps you have aIready observed\r\nthat in Casablanca, human life is cheap.\r\n\r\n1086\r\n01:12:04,183 --> 01:12:05,825\r\nGood night, mademoiseIle.\r\n\r\n1087\r\n01:12:15,722 --> 01:12:18,644\r\n-What happened with Rick?\r\n-We'Il discuss it later.\r\n\r\n1088\r\n01:12:41,157 --> 01:12:43,480\r\nOur faithful friend is still there.\r\n\r\n1089\r\n01:12:43,681 --> 01:12:46,083\r\nPlease don't go\r\nto the underground meeting.\r\n\r\n1090\r\n01:12:46,244 --> 01:12:47,205\r\nI must.\r\n\r\n1091\r\n01:12:47,407 --> 01:12:50,530\r\nIt isn't often that a man gets to\r\ndisplay heroics before his wife.\r\n\r\n1092\r\n01:12:50,730 --> 01:12:54,095\r\nDon't joke. After Strasser's\r\nwarning tonight, I'm frightened.\r\n\r\n1093\r\n01:12:54,336 --> 01:12:55,937\r\nI'm frightened too.\r\n\r\n1094\r\n01:12:56,179 --> 01:12:58,541\r\nShall I remain here\r\nin a hotel room, hiding?\r\n\r\n1095\r\n01:12:58,783 --> 01:13:00,383\r\nOr carry on the best l can?\r\n\r\n1096\r\n01:13:00,946 --> 01:13:03,309\r\nWhatever I'd say,\r\nyou would carry on.\r\n\r\n1097\r\n01:13:04,190 --> 01:13:06,953\r\nWhy don't you tell me about Rick?\r\nWhat did you find out?\r\n\r\n1098\r\n01:13:07,154 --> 01:13:09,276\r\n-Apparently he has the letters.\r\n-Yes?\r\n\r\n1099\r\n01:13:09,477 --> 01:13:10,879\r\nBut he won't seIl them.\r\n\r\n1100\r\n01:13:11,080 --> 01:13:13,482\r\nI'd think if sentiment won't\r\npersuade him, money would.\r\n\r\n1101\r\n01:13:14,886 --> 01:13:16,366\r\nDid he give you any reason?\r\n\r\n1102\r\n01:13:16,609 --> 01:13:18,570\r\nHe suggested l ask you.\r\n\r\n1103\r\n01:13:18,771 --> 01:13:19,772\r\nAsk me?\r\n\r\n1104\r\n01:13:20,013 --> 01:13:22,455\r\nYes. He said, \"Ask your wife.\"\r\n\r\n1105\r\n01:13:22,938 --> 01:13:24,938\r\nI don't know why he said that.\r\n\r\n1106\r\n01:13:36,516 --> 01:13:39,560\r\nOur friend outside wilI think\r\nwe've retired by now.\r\n\r\n1107\r\n01:13:40,642 --> 01:13:42,765\r\nI'll be going in a few minutes.\r\n\r\n1108\r\n01:13:44,447 --> 01:13:46,769\r\n-Ilsa, I--\r\n-Yes?\r\n\r\n1109\r\n01:13:48,133 --> 01:13:50,495\r\nWhen I was in the concentration camp...\r\n\r\n1110\r\n01:13:50,736 --> 01:13:52,779\r\n...were you lonely in Paris?\r\n\r\n1111\r\n01:13:54,622 --> 01:13:56,784\r\nYes, Victor. I was.\r\n\r\n1112\r\n01:13:57,466 --> 01:13:59,790\r\nI know how it is to be lonely.\r\n\r\n1113\r\n01:14:01,393 --> 01:14:03,594\r\nIs there anything you wish to telI me?\r\n\r\n1114\r\n01:14:05,558 --> 01:14:07,801\r\nNo, Victor. There isn't.\r\n\r\n1115\r\n01:14:11,967 --> 01:14:13,168\r\nI love you very much.\r\n\r\n1116\r\n01:14:15,772 --> 01:14:16,973\r\nYes.\r\n\r\n1117\r\n01:14:17,616 --> 01:14:19,217\r\nYes, l know.\r\n\r\n1118\r\n01:14:20,260 --> 01:14:22,661\r\nWhatever I do,\r\nwill you believe that l--\r\n\r\n1119\r\n01:14:22,902 --> 01:14:25,225\r\nYou don't even have to say it.\r\n\r\n1120\r\n01:14:25,467 --> 01:14:27,028\r\nI'll beIieve.\r\n\r\n1121\r\n01:14:29,232 --> 01:14:30,633\r\nGood night, dear.\r\n\r\n1122\r\n01:14:32,397 --> 01:14:33,718\r\nGood night.\r\n\r\n1123\r\n01:14:40,327 --> 01:14:41,287\r\nVictor?\r\n\r\n1124\r\n01:14:41,770 --> 01:14:43,052\r\nYes, dear?\r\n\r\n1125\r\n01:14:48,139 --> 01:14:49,540\r\nBe careful.\r\n\r\n1126\r\n01:14:50,942 --> 01:14:52,663\r\nOf course I'll be carefuI.\r\n\r\n1127\r\n01:15:34,204 --> 01:15:37,088\r\nWell, you are in pretty good shape,\r\nHerr Rick.\r\n\r\n1128\r\n01:15:37,289 --> 01:15:39,332\r\nHow long can I afford to stay closed?\r\n\r\n1129\r\n01:15:39,532 --> 01:15:40,934\r\nTwo weeks, maybe three.\r\n\r\n1130\r\n01:15:41,174 --> 01:15:43,176\r\nMaybe I won't have to.\r\nA bribe worked before.\r\n\r\n1131\r\n01:15:43,417 --> 01:15:45,781\r\nIn the meantime,\r\neverybody stays on salary.\r\n\r\n1132\r\n01:15:46,021 --> 01:15:47,062\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\n1133\r\n01:15:47,304 --> 01:15:48,984\r\nSascha wiIl be happy to hear it.\r\n\r\n1134\r\n01:15:49,227 --> 01:15:50,786\r\nI owe him money.\r\n\r\n1135\r\n01:15:51,029 --> 01:15:53,752\r\n-You finish Iocking up, wilI you?\r\n-I will.\r\n\r\n1136\r\n01:15:53,952 --> 01:15:56,916\r\n-Then l'm going to the meeting--\r\n-Don't tell me.\r\n\r\n1137\r\n01:15:57,117 --> 01:15:58,318\r\nI won't.\r\n\r\n1138\r\n01:15:59,401 --> 01:16:00,520\r\nGood night.\r\n\r\n1139\r\n01:16:01,603 --> 01:16:03,085\r\nGood night, Mr. Rick.\r\n\r\n1140\r\n01:16:19,109 --> 01:16:22,193\r\n-How did you get in?\r\n-The stairs from the street.\r\n\r\n1141\r\n01:16:22,393 --> 01:16:25,638\r\nI toId you you'd come around,\r\nbut this is ahead of schedule.\r\n\r\n1142\r\n01:16:25,878 --> 01:16:27,039\r\nWon't you sit down?\r\n\r\n1143\r\n01:16:27,240 --> 01:16:30,645\r\n-Richard, I had to see you.\r\n-\"Richard\" again. We're back in Paris.\r\n\r\n1144\r\n01:16:30,846 --> 01:16:34,330\r\nYour visit isn't connected by any chance\r\nwith the letters of transit?\r\n\r\n1145\r\n01:16:34,531 --> 01:16:36,974\r\nAs Iong as I have them,\r\nI'll never be Ionely.\r\n\r\n1146\r\n01:16:37,175 --> 01:16:39,658\r\nAsk any price,\r\nbut give me those Ietters.\r\n\r\n1147\r\n01:16:39,858 --> 01:16:42,342\r\nI went through that with\r\nyour husband. It's no deal.\r\n\r\n1148\r\n01:16:43,103 --> 01:16:44,466\r\nI know how you feel about me...\r\n\r\n1149\r\n01:16:44,666 --> 01:16:47,268\r\n...but pIease put that aside\r\nfor something important.\r\n\r\n1150\r\n01:16:47,469 --> 01:16:49,631\r\nDo I have to hear again\r\nhow great your husband is...\r\n\r\n1151\r\n01:16:49,873 --> 01:16:51,834\r\n...what an important cause\r\nhe's fighting for?\r\n\r\n1152\r\n01:16:52,036 --> 01:16:53,478\r\nIt was your cause too.\r\n\r\n1153\r\n01:16:53,718 --> 01:16:56,040\r\nIn your way you were fighting\r\nfor the same thing.\r\n\r\n1154\r\n01:16:56,322 --> 01:16:59,085\r\nI'm not fighting for anything anymore,\r\nexcept myself.\r\n\r\n1155\r\n01:16:59,286 --> 01:17:01,288\r\nI'm the only cause l'm interested in.\r\n\r\n1156\r\n01:17:06,216 --> 01:17:07,257\r\nRichard....\r\n\r\n1157\r\n01:17:07,458 --> 01:17:10,902\r\nWe Ioved each other once.\r\nIf those days meant anything at aIl--\r\n\r\n1158\r\n01:17:11,143 --> 01:17:13,665\r\nI wouldn't bring up Paris.\r\nIt's poor saIesmanship.\r\n\r\n1159\r\n01:17:13,868 --> 01:17:17,271\r\nListen. If you knew what really\r\nhappened, if you knew the truth--\r\n\r\n1160\r\n01:17:17,471 --> 01:17:19,314\r\nI wouldn't believe you no matter what.\r\n\r\n1161\r\n01:17:19,515 --> 01:17:21,878\r\nYou'd say anything now\r\nto get what you want.\r\n\r\n1162\r\n01:17:26,525 --> 01:17:28,367\r\nYou want to feeI sorry for yourself?\r\n\r\n1163\r\n01:17:29,449 --> 01:17:32,534\r\nWith so much at stake, alI you can\r\nthink of is your own feeling.\r\n\r\n1164\r\n01:17:32,734 --> 01:17:35,937\r\nOne woman has hurt you, and you\r\ntake revenge on the rest of world.\r\n\r\n1165\r\n01:17:36,179 --> 01:17:39,102\r\nYou're a coward and a weakling!\r\n\r\n1166\r\n01:17:42,468 --> 01:17:43,548\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n1167\r\n01:17:43,791 --> 01:17:45,311\r\nRichard, I'm sorry.\r\n\r\n1168\r\n01:17:46,353 --> 01:17:48,957\r\nI'm sorry, but you--\r\nYou are our last hope.\r\n\r\n1169\r\n01:17:49,158 --> 01:17:51,920\r\nIf you don't help us,\r\nVictor will die in Casablanca.\r\n\r\n1170\r\n01:17:52,081 --> 01:17:53,041\r\nWhat of it?\r\n\r\n1171\r\n01:17:53,243 --> 01:17:55,766\r\nI'm gonna die in CasabIanca.\r\nIt's a good spot for it.\r\n\r\n1172\r\n01:18:02,497 --> 01:18:03,738\r\nNow, if you'lI--\r\n\r\n1173\r\n01:18:06,462 --> 01:18:07,743\r\nAlI right.\r\n\r\n1174\r\n01:18:07,945 --> 01:18:09,826\r\nI tried to reason with you.\r\n\r\n1175\r\n01:18:10,028 --> 01:18:12,028\r\nI tried everything.\r\nI want those letters.\r\n\r\n1176\r\n01:18:12,470 --> 01:18:13,432\r\nGet them for me.\r\n\r\n1177\r\n01:18:13,632 --> 01:18:15,434\r\nI don't have to.\r\nI got them right here.\r\n\r\n1178\r\n01:18:17,238 --> 01:18:18,879\r\nPut them on the table.\r\n\r\n1179\r\n01:18:20,604 --> 01:18:21,563\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n1180\r\n01:18:22,525 --> 01:18:24,607\r\nFor the last time,\r\nput them on the table.\r\n\r\n1181\r\n01:18:26,051 --> 01:18:29,695\r\nIf LaszIo and the cause mean so much\r\nto you, you won't stop at anything.\r\n\r\n1182\r\n01:18:31,137 --> 01:18:33,581\r\nAlI right,\r\nI'll make it easier for you.\r\n\r\n1183\r\n01:18:35,424 --> 01:18:38,226\r\nGo ahead and shoot.\r\nYou'll be doing me a favor.\r\n\r\n1184\r\n01:18:43,716 --> 01:18:45,318\r\nRichard....\r\n\r\n1185\r\n01:18:45,558 --> 01:18:47,600\r\nI tried to stay away.\r\n\r\n1186\r\n01:18:48,241 --> 01:18:50,604\r\nI thought I would never see you again.\r\n\r\n1187\r\n01:18:52,007 --> 01:18:54,009\r\nThat you were out of my Iife.\r\n\r\n1188\r\n01:19:13,719 --> 01:19:16,041\r\nThe day you left Paris...\r\n\r\n1189\r\n01:19:17,284 --> 01:19:19,446\r\n...if you knew what l went through.\r\n\r\n1190\r\n01:19:20,688 --> 01:19:23,370\r\nIf you knew how much I Ioved you.\r\n\r\n1191\r\n01:19:24,334 --> 01:19:26,657\r\nHow much I still Iove you.\r\n\r\n1192\r\n01:19:40,236 --> 01:19:41,197\r\nAnd then?\r\n\r\n1193\r\n01:19:43,241 --> 01:19:47,405\r\nIt wasn't long after we were married\r\nthat Victor went back to CzechosIovakia.\r\n\r\n1194\r\n01:19:47,646 --> 01:19:51,011\r\nThey needed him in Prague.\r\nBut the Gestapo were waiting for him.\r\n\r\n1195\r\n01:19:51,212 --> 01:19:52,492\r\nJust 2 Iines in the paper:\r\n\r\n1196\r\n01:19:52,734 --> 01:19:55,417\r\n\"Victor Laszlo apprehended.\r\nSent to concentration camp.\"\r\n\r\n1197\r\n01:19:56,779 --> 01:19:59,063\r\nI was frantic.\r\nFor months l tried to get word.\r\n\r\n1198\r\n01:19:59,263 --> 01:20:00,504\r\nThen it came.\r\n\r\n1199\r\n01:20:00,706 --> 01:20:03,107\r\nHe was dead.\r\nShot, trying to escape.\r\n\r\n1200\r\n01:20:03,991 --> 01:20:06,912\r\nI was loneIy.\r\nI had nothing, not even hope.\r\n\r\n1201\r\n01:20:07,755 --> 01:20:08,876\r\nThen l met you.\r\n\r\n1202\r\n01:20:09,437 --> 01:20:12,322\r\nWhy weren't you honest?\r\nWhy keep your marriage a secret?\r\n\r\n1203\r\n01:20:12,523 --> 01:20:15,725\r\nIt wasn't my secret, Richard.\r\nVictor wanted it that way.\r\n\r\n1204\r\n01:20:15,967 --> 01:20:18,169\r\nNot even our cIosest friends\r\nknew about it.\r\n\r\n1205\r\n01:20:18,891 --> 01:20:21,333\r\nHe was protecting me.\r\nI knew about his work.\r\n\r\n1206\r\n01:20:21,576 --> 01:20:24,779\r\nIf the Gestapo found out I was his wife,\r\nit'd be dangerous for me...\r\n\r\n1207\r\n01:20:25,021 --> 01:20:26,422\r\n...and for those working with us.\r\n\r\n1208\r\n01:20:27,183 --> 01:20:29,265\r\nWhen did you first find out\r\nhe was alive?\r\n\r\n1209\r\n01:20:30,509 --> 01:20:32,751\r\nJust before you and I\r\nwere to leave Paris.\r\n\r\n1210\r\n01:20:32,952 --> 01:20:35,394\r\nA friend came and told me\r\nthat Victor was alive.\r\n\r\n1211\r\n01:20:35,635 --> 01:20:38,798\r\nThey hid him in a freight car\r\nin the outskirts of Paris.\r\n\r\n1212\r\n01:20:38,999 --> 01:20:40,962\r\nHe was sick. He needed me.\r\n\r\n1213\r\n01:20:42,364 --> 01:20:44,407\r\nI wanted to tell you,\r\nbut I didn't dare.\r\n\r\n1214\r\n01:20:44,649 --> 01:20:49,173\r\nI knew you wouldn't have Ieft and the\r\nGestapo would have caught you, so I....\r\n\r\n1215\r\n01:20:51,939 --> 01:20:53,940\r\nWell, you know the rest.\r\n\r\n1216\r\n01:20:56,265 --> 01:20:58,787\r\nIt's st