90\r\n-Get me the radio tower.\r\n-Put it down!\r\n\r\n1489\r\n01:36:25,738 --> 01:36:27,171\r\nLOUIS:\r\nMaj. Strasser has been shot.\r\n\r\n1490\r\n01:36:31,955 --> 01:36:34,105\r\nRound up the usual suspects.\r\n\r\n1491\r\n01:36:57,063 --> 01:37:00,409\r\nYou're not only a sentimentalist,\r\nbut you've become a patriot.\r\n\r\n1492\r\n01:37:00,608 --> 01:37:02,603\r\nMaybe. It seemed like\r\na good time to start.\r\n\r\n1493\r\n01:37:02,802 --> 01:37:04,793\r\nI think perhaps you're right.\r\n\r\n1494\r\n01:37:28,786 --> 01:37:32,290\r\nIt might be good for you to disappear\r\nfrom CasabIanca for a while.\r\n\r\n1495\r\n01:37:32,492 --> 01:37:34,643\r\nThere's a Free French garrison\r\nat Brazzaville.\r\n\r\n1496\r\n01:37:34,883 --> 01:37:36,436\r\nI could arrange passage.\r\n\r\n1497\r\n01:37:37,075 --> 01:37:38,587\r\nMy Ietter of transit?\r\n\r\n1498\r\n01:37:38,827 --> 01:37:39,943\r\nI could use a trip.\r\n\r\n1499\r\n01:37:40,143 --> 01:37:43,172\r\nBut it doesn't change our bet.\r\nYou still owe me 1 0,000 francs.\r\n\r\n1500\r\n01:37:43,411 --> 01:37:46,280\r\nAnd that 1 0,000 francs\r\nshould pay our expenses.\r\n\r\n1501\r\n01:37:46,479 --> 01:37:48,233\r\nRICK:\r\n\"Our\" expenses?\r\n\r\n1502\r\n01:37:48,473 --> 01:37:49,469\r\nLouis...\r\n\r\n1503\r\n01:37:49,668 --> 01:37:53,214\r\n...l think this is the beginning\r\nof a beautiful friendship.\r\n\r\n","markerStore":{"nextMarkerId":653,"markersById":{"0":{"range":{"start":{"row":59,"column":0},"end":{"row":59,"column":0}},"properties":{"type":"selection","editorId":8,"goalScreenRange":null},"reversed":false,"tailed":false,"valid":true,"invalidate":"never","maintainHistory":true}},"version":2},"history":{"version":3,"nextCheckpointId":1,"undoStack":[],"redoStack":[]},"encoding":"utf8","filePath":"/Users/joegesualdo/Documents/movies/Casablanca (1942)/Casablanca.1942.720.x264.YIFY.srt","digestWhenLastPersisted":"5c59755786b5ea314abb06aee8b63ed2c6b89bdd","preferredLineEnding":null,"deserializer":"TextBuffer","version":2},{"load":true,"text":"﻿1\r\n00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:26,583\r\n[theme song plays]\r\n\r\n2\r\n00:00:30,791 --> 00:00:32,291\r\n♪ Django! ♪\r\n\r\n3\r\n00:00:32,291 --> 00:00:38,083\r\n♪ Django, have you\r\nalways been alone? ♪\r\n\r\n4\r\n00:00:38,083 --> 00:00:39,833\r\n♪ Django! ♪\r\n\r\n5\r\n00:00:39,833 --> 00:00:44,416\r\n♪ Django, have you\r\nnever loved again? ♪\r\n\r\n6\r\n00:00:44,416 --> 00:00:48,250\r\n♪ Love will live on\r\noh oh ♪\r\n\r\n7\r\n00:00:48,250 --> 00:00:52,625\r\n♪ Life must go on\r\noh oh ♪\r\n\r\n8\r\n00:00:52,625 --> 00:00:54,041\r\n♪ For you cannot ♪\r\n\r\n9\r\n00:00:54,041 --> 00:00:58,625\r\n♪ Spend your life regretting ♪\r\n\r\n10\r\n00:01:00,125 --> 00:01:01,875\r\n♪ Django! ♪\r\n\r\n11\r\n00:01:01,875 --> 00:01:07,583\r\n♪ Django, you must\r\nface another day ♪\r\n\r\n12\r\n00:01:07,583 --> 00:01:09,500\r\n♪ Django! ♪\r\n\r\n13\r\n00:01:09,500 --> 00:01:14,375\r\n♪ Django, now your love\r\nhas gone away ♪\r\n\r\n14\r\n00:01:14,375 --> 00:01:18,083\r\n♪ Once you loved her\r\nwhoa-oh ♪\r\n\r\n15\r\n00:01:18,083 --> 00:01:21,583\r\n♪ Now you've lost her\r\nwhoa-oh ♪\r\n\r\n16\r\n00:01:21,583 --> 00:01:26,250\r\n♪ But you've lost\r\nher forever ♪\r\n\r\n17\r\n00:01:26,250 --> 00:01:28,458\r\n♪ Django ♪\r\n\r\n18\r\n00:01:30,875 --> 00:01:33,583\r\n♪ When there are clouds\r\nin the skies ♪\r\n\r\n19\r\n00:01:33,583 --> 00:01:38,250\r\n♪ And they are gray ♪\r\n\r\n20\r\n00:01:38,250 --> 00:01:40,875\r\n♪ You may be sad but remember ♪\r\n\r\n21\r\n00:01:40,875 --> 00:01:44,583\r\n♪ They'll all soon pass away ♪\r\n\r\n22\r\n00:01:44,583 --> 00:01:47,333\r\n♪ Oh Django! ♪\r\n\r\n23\r\n00:01:47,333 --> 00:01:50,208\r\n♪ After the showers ♪\r\n\r\n24\r\n00:01:50,208 --> 00:01:55,708\r\n♪ The sun will be ♪\r\n\r\n25\r\n00:01:55,708 --> 00:01:58,083\r\n♪ Shining ♪\r\n\r\n26\r\n00:02:13,333 --> 00:02:17,166\r\n♪ Once you loved her\r\nwhoa-oh ♪\r\n\r\n27\r\n00:02:17,166 --> 00:02:21,166\r\n♪ Now you've lost her\r\nwhoa-oh ♪\r\n\r\n28\r\n00:02:21,166 --> 00:02:25,125\r\n♪ But you've lost her forever ♪\r\n\r\n29\r\n00:02:25,125 --> 00:02:28,041\r\n♪ Django ♪\r\n\r\n30\r\n00:02:30,041 --> 00:02:32,750\r\n♪ When there are clouds\r\nin the skies ♪\r\n\r\n31\r\n00:02:32,750 --> 00:02:37,250\r\n♪ And they are gray ♪\r\n\r\n32\r\n00:02:37,250 --> 00:02:40,250\r\n♪ You may be sad but remember ♪\r\n\r\n33\r\n00:02:40,250 --> 00:02:43,375\r\n♪ They'll all soon pass away ♪\r\n\r\n34\r\n00:02:43,375 --> 00:02:46,541\r\n♪ Oh Django! ♪\r\n\r\n35\r\n00:02:46,541 --> 00:02:48,958\r\n♪ After the showers ♪\r\n\r\n36\r\n00:02:48,958 --> 00:02:54,750\r\n♪ The sun will be ♪\r\n\r\n37\r\n00:02:54,750 --> 00:02:57,375\r\n♪ Shining ♪\r\n\r\n38\r\n00:02:58,250 --> 00:03:01,166\r\n♪ Django! ♪\r\n\r\n39\r\n00:03:01,166 --> 00:03:04,666\r\n♪ Oh Django! ♪\r\n\r\n40\r\n00:03:04,666 --> 00:03:08,083\r\n♪ You must go on ♪\r\n\r\n41\r\n00:03:08,083 --> 00:03:13,791\r\n♪ Oh Django! ♪\r\n\r\n42\r\n00:03:13,791 --> 00:03:16,458\r\n[chains rattling]\r\n\r\n43\r\n00:03:31,416 --> 00:03:33,291\r\n[man grunting]\r\n\r\n44\r\n00:03:38,625 --> 00:03:40,500\r\n[horse nickering]\r\n\r\n45\r\n00:03:54,416 --> 00:03:57,250\r\n- Whoa.\r\n- [horses snorting]\r\n\r\n46\r\n00:03:57,250 --> 00:04:00,041\r\n[gentle metallic rattling]\r\n\r\n47\r\n00:04:03,416 --> 00:04:04,750\r\nWhoa.\r\n\r\n48\r\n00:04:04,774 --> 00:04:14,774\r\n<font color=\"#00ff00\">Uploaded </font><font color=\"#8000ff\">by</font> [ <font color=\"#1aff8c\">s</font><font color=\"#de01b8\">R</font><font color=\"#13e8f2\">t</font><font color=\"#f09b28\">FeVeR</font> ] <font color=\"#ed0cd7\">new srt source</font>\r\n\r\n49\r\n00:04:18,833 --> 00:04:22,125\r\nWho's that stumblin'\r\naround in the dark?\r\n\r\n50\r\n00:04:22,125 --> 00:04:26,250\r\nState your business\r\nor prepare to get winged!\r\n\r\n51\r\n00:04:26,250 --> 00:04:29,083\r\nCalm yourselves, gentlemen.\r\n\r\n52\r\n00:04:29,083 --> 00:04:31,500\r\nI mean you no harm.\r\n\r\n53\r\n00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:36,583\r\nI'm simply a fellow\r\nweary traveler. Whoa.\r\n\r\n54\r\n00:04:37,708 --> 00:04:39,583\r\nGood cold evening, gentlemen.\r\n\r\n55\r\n00:04:39,583 --> 00:04:42,083\r\nI'm looking for\r\na pair of slave traders\r\n\r\n56\r\n00:04:42,083 --> 00:04:43,875\r\nthat go by the name\r\nof the Speck Brothers.\r\n\r\n57\r\n00:04:43,875 --> 00:04:45,875\r\nMight that be you?\r\n\r\n58\r\n00:04:46,958 --> 00:04:49,958\r\n- Who wants to know?\r\n- Well, I do.\r\n\r\n59\r\n00:04:49,958 --> 00:04:53,083\r\n- I'm Dr. King Schultz.\r\nThis is my horse, Fritz.\r\n- [snorting]\r\n\r\n60\r\n00:04:53,083 --> 00:04:56,875\r\n- What kinda doctor?\r\n- [Schultz] Dentist.\r\n\r\n61\r\n00:04:56,875 --> 00:04:58,750\r\nNow, are you the Speck Brothers?\r\n\r\n62\r\n00:04:58,750 --> 00:05:01,750\r\nAnd did you purchase those men\r\nat the Greenville slave auction?\r\n\r\n63\r\n00:05:01,750 --> 00:05:04,416\r\n- So what?\r\n- So I wish to parley with you.\r\n\r\n64\r\n00:05:04,416 --> 00:05:08,000\r\n- Speak English.\r\n- [chuckles] Oh, I'm sorry.\r\n\r\n65\r\n00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:10,416\r\nPlease forgive me.\r\nIt is a second language.\r\n\r\n66\r\n00:05:10,416 --> 00:05:13,916\r\nNow, amongst your inventory,\r\nI've been led to believe,\r\n\r\n67\r\n00:05:13,916 --> 00:05:16,500\r\nis a specimen\r\nI'm keen to acquire.\r\n\r\n68\r\n00:05:16,500 --> 00:05:18,083\r\nHello, you poor devils!\r\n\r\n69\r\n00:05:19,208 --> 00:05:22,000\r\nIs there one amongst you\r\nwho was formerly a resident\r\n\r\n70\r\n00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:25,083\r\nof the Carrucan plantation?\r\n\r\n71\r\n00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:28,416\r\n[man] I'm from the\r\nCarrucan plantation.\r\n\r\n72\r\n00:05:29,791 --> 00:05:31,416\r\nWho said that?\r\n\r\n73\r\n00:05:38,833 --> 00:05:40,250\r\n[Schultz lighting match]\r\n\r\n74\r\n00:06:18,375 --> 00:06:19,958\r\nWhat's your name?\r\n\r\n75\r\n00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:26,083\r\nDjango.\r\n\r\n76\r\n00:06:26,083 --> 00:06:28,958\r\nThen you are exactly\r\nthe one I'm looking for.\r\n\r\n77\r\n00:06:30,458 --> 00:06:33,083\r\nDo you know who\r\nthe Brittle Brothers are?\r\n\r\n78\r\n00:06:36,416 --> 00:06:37,666\r\nWho are they?\r\n\r\n79\r\n00:06:39,875 --> 00:06:41,791\r\nBig John.\r\n\r\n80\r\n00:06:42,416 --> 00:06:43,791\r\nEllis.\r\n\r\n81\r\n00:06:45,083 --> 00:06:49,208\r\nRoger.\r\nSometime they call him Lil Raj.\r\n\r\n82\r\n00:06:50,416 --> 00:06:52,791\r\nThey was overseers\r\nat the Carrucan plantation.\r\n\r\n83\r\n00:06:52,791 --> 00:06:54,000\r\nNot anymore.\r\n\r\n84\r\n00:06:56,916 --> 00:06:58,583\r\nTell me...\r\n\r\n85\r\n00:06:58,583 --> 00:07:01,416\r\nif you were to see any of\r\nthese three gentlemen again,\r\n\r\n86\r\n00:07:01,416 --> 00:07:04,416\r\n- would you recognize them?\r\n- [man] Hey.\r\n\r\n87\r\n00:07:04,416 --> 00:07:06,916\r\n- Stop talkin' to him like that.\r\n- Like what?\r\n\r\n88\r\n00:07:06,916 --> 00:07:08,708\r\nLike that.\r\n\r\n89\r\n00:07:08,708 --> 00:07:11,083\r\nMy good man, I'm simply\r\ntrying to ascertain...\r\n\r\n90\r\n00:07:11,083 --> 00:07:13,416\r\nSpeak English, goddamn it.\r\n\r\n91\r\n00:07:13,416 --> 00:07:15,333\r\nEverybody calm down.\r\n\r\n92\r\n00:07:15,333 --> 00:07:19,250\r\nI'm simply a customer\r\ntrying to conduct a transaction.\r\n\r\n93\r\n00:07:19,250 --> 00:07:22,250\r\nI don't care. No sale.\r\nNow, off with ya.\r\n\r\n94\r\n00:07:22,250 --> 00:07:25,541\r\n[scoffs] Don't be ridiculous.\r\nOf course they're for sale.\r\n\r\n95\r\n00:07:26,250 --> 00:07:27,833\r\nMove it.\r\n\r\n96\r\n00:07:27,833 --> 00:07:32,875\r\nMy good man, did you simply get\r\ncarried away with your dramatic\r\ngesture\r\n\r\n97\r\n00:07:32,875 --> 00:07:36,833\r\nor are you pointing your weapon\r\nat me with lethal intention?\r\n\r\n98\r\n00:07:37,750 --> 00:07:39,833\r\nLast chance, fancy pants.\r\n\r\n99\r\n00:07:41,083 --> 00:07:43,041\r\nOh, very well.\r\n\r\n100\r\n00:07:44,041 --> 00:07:45,250\r\n[horse whinnying]\r\n\r\n101\r\n00:07:46,750 --> 00:07:49,250\r\n[man screaming]\r\n\r\n102\r\n00:07:53,250 --> 00:07:55,083\r\n[scream echoing]\r\n\r\n103\r\n00:08:07,750 --> 00:08:10,583\r\n[screaming continues]\r\n\r\n104\r\n00:08:11,958 --> 00:08:14,583\r\nI'm sorry to put a bullet\r\nin your beast,\r\n\r\n105\r\n00:08:14,583 --> 00:08:16,750\r\nbut I didn't want you\r\nto do anything rash\r\n\r\n106\r\n00:08:16,750 --> 00:08:19,375\r\nbefore you had a moment\r\nto come to your senses.\r\n\r\n107\r\n00:08:19,375 --> 00:08:22,708\r\nYou goddamn son of a bitch!\r\n\r\n108\r\n00:08:22,708 --> 00:08:25,916\r\n- You shot Roscoe!\r\n- Well...\r\n\r\n109\r\n00:08:25,916 --> 00:08:27,708\r\nAnd you killed Ace!\r\n\r\n110\r\n00:08:27,708 --> 00:08:30,416\r\nI only shot your brother once\r\nhe threatened to shoot me.\r\n\r\n111\r\n00:08:30,416 --> 00:08:33,500\r\nAnd I do believe I have...\r\none, two, three, four...\r\n\r\n112\r\n00:08:33,500 --> 00:08:36,583\r\nfive witnesses\r\nwho can attest to that fact.\r\n\r\n113\r\n00:08:36,583 --> 00:08:39,708\r\n- Damn leg's busted!\r\n- No doubt.\r\n\r\n114\r\n00:08:39,708 --> 00:08:42,416\r\nNow, if you could keep your\r\ncaterwauling down to a minimum,\r\n\r\n115\r\n00:08:42,416 --> 00:08:46,000\r\nI'd like to finish my line\r\nof inquiry with young Django.\r\n\r\n116\r\n00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:48,083\r\n[screaming resumes]\r\n\r\n117\r\n00:08:49,708 --> 00:08:53,083\r\n- [man] God-fuckin'-damn it!\r\n- As I was saying...\r\n\r\n118\r\n00:08:53,083 --> 00:08:57,333\r\nif you were to see the\r\nBrittle Brothers again,\r\nyou could recognize 'em?\r\n\r\n119\r\n00:08:57,916 --> 00:08:59,750\r\nYeah.\r\n\r\n120\r\n00:08:59,750 --> 00:09:01,166\r\nSold American!\r\n\r\n121\r\n00:09:01,166 --> 00:09:05,333\r\nSo, Mr. Speck? Mr. Speck?\r\nHow much for young Django here?\r\n\r\n122\r\n00:09:10,416 --> 00:09:13,250\r\nThat iron is nasty business.\r\n\r\n123\r\n00:09:18,166 --> 00:09:20,541\r\nOh, could you hold this\r\nfor a moment?\r\n\r\n124\r\n00:09:22,541 --> 00:09:24,125\r\nThank you. Django?\r\n\r\n125\r\n00:09:24,125 --> 00:09:26,250\r\nGet up on that horse.\r\n\r\n126\r\n00:09:26,250 --> 00:09:28,208\r\nAlso, if I were you,\r\n\r\n127\r\n00:09:28,208 --> 00:09:32,375\r\nI'd take that winter coat the\r\ndear departed Speck left behind.\r\n\r\n128\r\n00:09:46,375 --> 00:09:50,375\r\nNigger! Don't you touch\r\nmy brother's coat.\r\n\r\n129\r\n00:09:59,166 --> 00:10:00,791\r\n[screaming]\r\n\r\n130\r\n00:10:00,791 --> 00:10:06,000\r\nGoddamn it! Oh!\r\n[moaning]\r\n\r\n131\r\n00:10:07,416 --> 00:10:12,791\r\nOne hundred... ten... 20...\r\n\r\n132\r\n00:10:12,791 --> 00:10:14,791\r\nand five...\r\n\r\n133\r\n00:10:15,791 --> 00:10:17,083\r\nfor young Django here.\r\n\r\n134\r\n00:10:17,083 --> 00:10:19,583\r\nAnd since he won't\r\nbe needing it anymore,\r\n\r\n135\r\n00:10:19,583 --> 00:10:22,000\r\nI'd like to purchase\r\nyour brother's nag.\r\n\r\n136\r\n00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:27,916\r\nAlso, Mr. Speck, I'm afraid\r\nI will require a bill of sale.\r\n\r\n137\r\n00:10:27,916 --> 00:10:29,416\r\nDo you have one?\r\n\r\n138\r\n00:10:29,416 --> 00:10:32,708\r\n- You go to hell, dentist.\r\n- [scoffs]\r\n\r\n139\r\n00:10:32,708 --> 00:10:34,875\r\nI thought not.\r\n\r\n140\r\n00:10:34,875 --> 00:10:38,625\r\nNo worries. I come prepared.\r\n\r\n141\r\n00:10:42,833 --> 00:10:44,541\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\n142\r\n00:10:44,541 --> 00:10:48,250\r\nThis will serve nicely\r\nas a bill of sale.\r\n\r\n143\r\n00:10:53,041 --> 00:10:54,750\r\n[nickering]\r\n\r\n144\r\n00:11:00,416 --> 00:11:01,625\r\nWhoa.\r\n\r\n145\r\n00:11:05,625 --> 00:11:09,083\r\nNow, as to you poor devils.\r\n\r\n146\r\n00:11:09,083 --> 00:11:14,375\r\nSo, as I see it, when it comes\r\nto the subject of what to do\r\nnext,\r\n\r\n147\r\n00:11:14,375 --> 00:11:17,458\r\nyou gentlemen have two choices.\r\n\r\n148\r\n00:11:17,458 --> 00:11:22,875\r\nOne: Once I'm gone, you could\r\nlift that beast off the\r\nremaining Speck,\r\n\r\n149\r\n00:11:22,875 --> 00:11:24,708\r\nthen carry him\r\nto the nearest town.\r\n\r\n150\r\n00:11:24,708 --> 00:11:28,583\r\nWhich would be at least\r\n37 miles back the way you came.\r\n\r\n151\r\n00:11:28,583 --> 00:11:34,458\r\nOr two: You could unshackle\r\nyourselves, take that rifle,\r\n\r\n152\r\n00:11:34,458 --> 00:11:37,083\r\nput a bullet in his head,\r\nbury the two of them deep,\r\n\r\n153\r\n00:11:37,083 --> 00:11:40,875\r\nand then make your way to\r\na more enlightened area\r\nof this country.\r\n\r\n154\r\n00:11:41,791 --> 00:11:43,125\r\nChoice is yours.\r\n\r\n155\r\n00:11:43,125 --> 00:11:44,791\r\nOh, and on the off chance\r\n\r\n156\r\n00:11:44,791 --> 00:11:47,500\r\nthere are any astronomy\r\naficionados amongst you,\r\n\r\n157\r\n00:11:47,500 --> 00:11:51,000\r\nthe North Star is that one.\r\n\r\n158\r\n00:11:52,125 --> 00:11:55,500\r\nTa-ta. [Clucking]\r\n\r\n159\r\n00:12:10,083 --> 00:12:14,291\r\nNow wait a minute, fellas.\r\nLet's talk about this!\r\n\r\n160\r\n00:12:14,291 --> 00:12:17,833\r\n- [lantern crashing]\r\n- [chains rattling]\r\n\r\n161\r\n00:12:17,833 --> 00:12:21,416\r\nYou gotta be reasonable\r\nin a situation like this!\r\n\r\n162\r\n00:12:22,750 --> 00:12:25,916\r\nI'm not a bad guy.\r\nI'm just doin' my job!\r\n\r\n163\r\n00:12:25,916 --> 00:12:29,625\r\nBlueberry, didn't I\r\ngive you my last apple?\r\n\r\n164\r\n00:12:29,625 --> 00:12:32,625\r\nTell you what, boys:\r\nTake me to the doc in El Paso,\r\n\r\n165\r\n00:12:32,625 --> 00:12:34,833\r\n- I'll get you your freedom.\r\n- [gun cocking]\r\n\r\n166\r\n00:12:34,833 --> 00:12:38,833\r\n- No. No, please...\r\n- [gunshot echoing]\r\n\r\n167\r\n00:12:54,458 --> 00:12:56,458\r\n[dogs barking nearby]\r\n\r\n168\r\n00:13:21,083 --> 00:13:24,041\r\n[squeaking]\r\n\r\n169\r\n00:13:24,041 --> 00:13:25,583\r\nAll right, now.\r\n\r\n170\r\n00:13:25,583 --> 00:13:27,791\r\nI'd like you to\r\ntake two of these tonight...\r\n\r\n171\r\n00:13:27,791 --> 00:13:30,208\r\n- [coughing]\r\n- ...and then in the morning...\r\n\r\n172\r\n00:13:32,083 --> 00:13:34,000\r\nThat's a nigger on a horse.\r\n\r\n173\r\n00:13:59,541 --> 00:14:01,458\r\nWhat's everybody staring at?\r\n\r\n174\r\n00:14:01,458 --> 00:14:04,125\r\nThey ain't never seen\r\nno nigger on a horse before.\r\n\r\n175\r\n00:14:05,250 --> 00:14:07,625\r\n[goats bleating]\r\n\r\n176\r\n00:14:16,250 --> 00:14:17,416\r\nWhoa.\r\n\r\n177\r\n00:14:27,333 --> 00:14:29,458\r\nGood morning, innkeeper!\r\n\r\n178\r\n00:14:30,500 --> 00:14:33,250\r\nTwo beers for\r\ntwo weary travelers.\r\n\r\n179\r\n00:14:33,250 --> 00:14:35,083\r\nIt's still a bit early.\r\n\r\n180\r\n00:14:35,083 --> 00:14:37,583\r\nWe won't be open\r\nfor another hour.\r\n\r\n181\r\n00:14:37,583 --> 00:14:39,750\r\nBy then, we'll be\r\nservin' breakfast.\r\n\r\n182\r\n00:14:39,750 --> 00:14:45,166\r\n[gasping] Whoa, whoa, whoa,\r\nwhoa... what the hell you think\r\nyou're doing, boy?\r\n\r\n183\r\n00:14:45,166 --> 00:14:47,666\r\nGet that nigger outta here!\r\n\r\n184\r\n00:14:51,083 --> 00:14:54,958\r\n- [panting] Help! Help!\r\n- Innkeeper!\r\n\r\n185\r\n00:14:54,958 --> 00:14:58,458\r\nRemember, get the sheriff,\r\nnot the marshal.\r\n\r\n186\r\n00:14:58,458 --> 00:15:00,583\r\n[man] Sheriff! Help!\r\n\r\n187\r\n00:15:00,583 --> 00:15:02,291\r\nAlas.\r\n\r\n188\r\n00:15:03,500 --> 00:15:06,291\r\nNow we must act\r\nas our own bartender.\r\n\r\n189\r\n00:15:08,500 --> 00:15:10,500\r\nSit down, my boy.\r\n\r\n190\r\n00:15:19,916 --> 00:15:23,416\r\n- What kind of dentist are you?\r\n- [chortles]\r\n\r\n191\r\n00:15:23,416 --> 00:15:28,416\r\nDespite that cart, I haven't\r\npracticed dentistry in five\r\nyears.\r\n\r\n192\r\n00:15:32,791 --> 00:15:36,333\r\nBut these days,\r\nI practice a new profession...\r\n\r\n193\r\n00:15:38,333 --> 00:15:39,916\r\nbounty hunter.\r\n\r\n194\r\n00:15:46,250 --> 00:15:48,333\r\nDo you know what\r\na bounty hunter is?\r\n\r\n195\r\n00:15:48,916 --> 00:15:50,125\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n196\r\n00:15:50,125 --> 00:15:51,541\r\nWell...\r\n\r\n197\r\n00:15:52,833 --> 00:15:57,041\r\nthe way the slave trade\r\ndeals in human lives for cash,\r\n\r\n198\r\n00:15:57,041 --> 00:15:59,750\r\na bounty hunter\r\ndeals in corpses.\r\n\r\n199\r\n00:15:59,750 --> 00:16:02,125\r\n[tsking] Hat.\r\n\r\n200\r\n00:16:05,625 --> 00:16:07,416\r\nProst.\r\n\r\n201\r\n00:16:15,208 --> 00:16:18,083\r\nThe state places\r\na bounty on a man's head.\r\n\r\n202\r\n00:16:18,083 --> 00:16:20,958\r\nI track that man, I find\r\nthat man, I kill that man.\r\n\r\n203\r\n00:16:20,958 --> 00:16:25,083\r\nAfter I've killed him,\r\nI transport that man's corpse\r\nback to the authorities.\r\n\r\n204\r\n00:16:25,083 --> 00:16:27,750\r\nSometimes that's\r\neasier said than done.\r\n\r\n205\r\n00:16:27,750 --> 00:16:31,000\r\nI show that corpse to the\r\nauthorities, proving yes,\r\nindeed,\r\n\r\n206\r\n00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:32,875\r\nI truly have killed him,\r\n\r\n207\r\n00:16:32,875 --> 00:16:36,083\r\nat which point the authorities\r\npay me the bounty.\r\n\r\n208\r\n00:16:36,083 --> 00:16:39,583\r\nSo, like slavery,\r\nit's a flesh for cash business.\r\n\r\n209\r\n00:16:41,083 --> 00:16:42,208\r\nWhat's a bounty?\r\n\r\n210\r\n00:16:45,833 --> 00:16:47,416\r\nIt's like a reward.\r\n\r\n211\r\n00:16:47,416 --> 00:16:51,041\r\nYou kill people?\r\nAnd they give you a reward?\r\n\r\n212\r\n00:16:51,041 --> 00:16:53,083\r\nCertain people, yeah.\r\n\r\n213\r\n00:16:53,083 --> 00:16:54,416\r\nBad people?\r\n\r\n214\r\n00:16:54,416 --> 00:16:58,500\r\nAh! Badder they are,\r\nbigger the reward.\r\n\r\n215\r\n00:16:58,500 --> 00:17:00,708\r\nWhich brings me to you.\r\n\r\n216\r\n00:17:00,708 --> 00:17:05,000\r\nAnd I must admit, I'm at a bit\r\nof a quandary when it comes to\r\nyou.\r\n\r\n217\r\n00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:07,833\r\nOn one hand, I despise slavery.\r\n\r\n218\r\n00:17:07,833 --> 00:17:11,208\r\nOn the other hand,\r\nI need your help.\r\n\r\n219\r\n00:17:11,208 --> 00:17:15,541\r\nIf you're not in a position\r\nto refuse, all the better.\r\n\r\n220\r\n00:17:15,541 --> 00:17:18,416\r\nSo, for the time being, I'm\r\ngonna make this slavery malarkey\r\n\r\n221\r\n00:17:18,416 --> 00:17:20,750\r\nwork to my benefit.\r\n\r\n222\r\n00:17:20,750 --> 00:17:25,625\r\nStill, having said that,\r\nI feel guilty.\r\n\r\n223\r\n00:17:26,916 --> 00:17:32,541\r\nSo, I would like the two of us\r\nto enter into an agreement.\r\n\r\n224\r\n00:17:39,333 --> 00:17:41,416\r\nI'm looking for\r\nthe Brittle Brothers.\r\n\r\n225\r\n00:17:45,875 --> 00:17:49,458\r\nHowever, at this endeavor,\r\nI'm at a slight disadvantage\r\n\r\n226\r\n00:17:49,458 --> 00:17:52,666\r\ninsofar as I don't know\r\nwhat they look like.\r\n\r\n227\r\n00:17:53,750 --> 00:17:56,875\r\nBut you do. Don't ya?\r\n\r\n228\r\n00:17:56,875 --> 00:17:59,083\r\nI know what they\r\nlook like all right.\r\n\r\n229\r\n00:17:59,083 --> 00:18:02,666\r\nGood. So here's my agreement.\r\n\r\n230\r\n00:18:02,666 --> 00:18:06,458\r\n- You travel with me\r\nuntil we find them.\r\n- Where we goin'?\r\n\r\n231\r\n00:18:06,458 --> 00:18:09,250\r\nI hear at least two of them\r\nare overseeing up in Gatlinburg,\r\n\r\n232\r\n00:18:09,250 --> 00:18:11,250\r\nbut I don't know where.\r\n\r\n233\r\n00:18:11,250 --> 00:18:16,166\r\nThat means we visit every\r\nplantation in Gatlinburg\r\ntill we find 'em.\r\n\r\n234\r\n00:18:16,166 --> 00:18:20,666\r\nAnd when we find them, you point\r\nthem out, and I kill them.\r\n\r\n235\r\n00:18:22,125 --> 00:18:25,916\r\nYou do that, I agree\r\nto give you your freedom,\r\n\r\n236\r\n00:18:25,916 --> 00:18:30,083\r\n$25 per Brittle Brother.\r\nThat's $75.\r\n\r\n237\r\n00:18:30,083 --> 00:18:34,083\r\nAnd, as if on cue,\r\nhere comes the sheriff.\r\n\r\n238\r\n00:18:37,750 --> 00:18:39,083\r\n[scoffs]\r\n\r\n239\r\n00:18:41,583 --> 00:18:47,291\r\nOK, boys. Fun's over.\r\nCome on out.\r\n\r\n240\r\n00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:54,500\r\n- [overlapping chatter]\r\n- All right, folks, calm down.\r\n\r\n241\r\n00:18:55,416 --> 00:18:57,916\r\nGo about your business.\r\n\r\n242\r\n00:18:57,916 --> 00:19:00,541\r\nThese jokers will be gone soon.\r\n\r\n243\r\n00:19:02,250 --> 00:19:07,916\r\nNow, why y'all wanna come\r\ninto my town and start trouble?\r\n\r\n244\r\n00:19:07,916 --> 00:19:11,250\r\nAnd scare all these nice people.\r\n\r\n245\r\n00:19:12,333 --> 00:19:14,916\r\nYou ain't got\r\nnothing better to do\r\n\r\n246\r\n00:19:14,916 --> 00:19:18,541\r\nthan to come into\r\nBill Sharp's town\r\n\r\n247\r\n00:19:18,541 --> 00:19:20,750\r\nand show your ass?\r\n\r\n248\r\n00:19:20,750 --> 00:19:22,625\r\n- [metal springing noise]\r\n- [sheriff screaming]\r\n\r\n249\r\n00:19:22,625 --> 00:19:25,916\r\n- [crowd gasping]\r\n- [groaning]\r\n\r\n250\r\n00:19:25,916 --> 00:19:27,541\r\n[woman screams]\r\n\r\n251\r\n00:19:28,875 --> 00:19:34,458\r\n- What'd you just do\r\nto our sheriff?\r\n- [groaning]\r\n\r\n252\r\n00:19:34,458 --> 00:19:36,458\r\n- [yelling]\r\n- [shot echoing]\r\n\r\n253\r\n00:19:36,458 --> 00:19:37,791\r\n[woman gasps]\r\n\r\n254\r\n00:19:37,791 --> 00:19:39,958\r\n[crowd screaming]\r\n\r\n255\r\n00:19:44,250 --> 00:19:46,750\r\nNow you can get the marshal.\r\n\r\n256\r\n00:19:48,166 --> 00:19:50,666\r\n[man] Marshal! Marshal!\r\n\r\n257\r\n00:19:50,666 --> 00:19:53,083\r\n- Should we wait inside?\r\n- Can we just leave?\r\n\r\n258\r\n00:19:53,083 --> 00:19:54,375\r\nAfter you.\r\n\r\n259\r\n00:19:56,666 --> 00:20:01,000\r\nMove that buckboard a long ways\r\nacross the street from the\r\nsaloon.\r\n\r\n260\r\n00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:04,041\r\nI want six men,\r\nsix rifles behind it.\r\n\r\n261\r\n00:20:04,041 --> 00:20:06,416\r\nI want two men,\r\ntwo rifles up on this roof.\r\n\r\n262\r\n00:20:06,416 --> 00:20:09,000\r\nTwo men, two rifles\r\non that roof.\r\n\r\n263\r\n00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:11,916\r\nAll the barrels aimed\r\nat that front door.\r\n\r\n264\r\n00:20:11,916 --> 00:20:15,291\r\nSomebody get poor Bill\r\noutta the goddamn street.\r\n\r\n265\r\n00:20:16,291 --> 00:20:18,583\r\nYou in the saloon!\r\n\r\n266\r\n00:20:18,583 --> 00:20:22,500\r\nWe got a hundred rifles aimed at\r\nevery way out of that buildin'.\r\n\r\n267\r\n00:20:22,500 --> 00:20:26,000\r\nYou got one chance\r\nto get out of this alive.\r\n\r\n268\r\n00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:29,291\r\nYou and your nigger come out\r\nright now with your hands over\r\nyour head,\r\n\r\n269\r\n00:20:29,291 --> 00:20:31,083\r\nand I mean right now.\r\n\r\n270\r\n00:20:32,416 --> 00:20:36,041\r\n[Schultz] Is this the marshal I\r\nhave the pleasure of addressing?\r\n\r\n271\r\n00:20:36,041 --> 00:20:38,041\r\nYes, it is.\r\n\r\n272\r\n00:20:38,041 --> 00:20:40,250\r\nThis is U.S. Marshal Gill Tatum.\r\n\r\n273\r\n00:20:40,250 --> 00:20:42,541\r\n[Schultz]\r\nNa wunderbar, marshal.\r\n\r\n274\r\n00:20:42,541 --> 00:20:46,833\r\nI have relieved myself\r\nof all weapons,\r\n\r\n275\r\n00:20:46,833 --> 00:20:49,833\r\nand just as you have instructed,\r\n\r\n276\r\n00:20:49,833 --> 00:20:52,625\r\nI am ready to step outside\r\n\r\n277\r\n00:20:52,625 --> 00:20:56,916\r\nwith my hands\r\nraised above my head.\r\n\r\n278\r\n00:20:57,833 --> 00:21:00,416\r\nI trust as a representative\r\n\r\n279\r\n00:21:00,416 --> 00:21:03,750\r\nof the criminal justice system\r\nof the United States of America,\r\n\r\n280\r\n00:21:03,750 --> 00:21:10,083\r\nI shan't be shot down in the\r\nstreet by either you or your\r\ndeputies\r\n\r\n281\r\n00:21:10,083 --> 00:21:12,875\r\nbefore I've had my day in court.\r\n\r\n282\r\n00:21:12,875 --> 00:21:15,291\r\nYou mean like\r\nyou did our sheriff.\r\n\r\n283\r\n00:21:15,291 --> 00:21:17,500\r\nShot him down\r\nlike a dog in the street.\r\n\r\n284\r\n00:21:17,500 --> 00:21:19,958\r\nYes, that's exactly what I mean.\r\n\r\n285\r\n00:21:19,958 --> 00:21:25,875\r\nDo I have your word as a lawman\r\nnot to shoot me down like a dog\r\nin the street?\r\n\r\n286\r\n00:21:28,875 --> 00:21:32,458\r\nWell, much as we'd all enjoy\r\nseeing something like that,\r\n\r\n287\r\n00:21:32,458 --> 00:21:35,583\r\nain't nobody gonna cheat\r\nthe hangman in my town.\r\n\r\n288\r\n00:21:36,500 --> 00:21:39,583\r\nFair enough, marshal.\r\nHere we come.\r\n\r\n289\r\n00:21:41,083 --> 00:21:43,541\r\nThey're a little tense\r\nout there.\r\n\r\n290\r\n00:21:43,541 --> 00:21:47,416\r\nSo don't make any quick\r\nmovements, and let me do\r\nthe talking.\r\n\r\n291\r\n00:21:47,416 --> 00:21:50,208\r\n- [doors squeaking open]\r\n- Come ahead.\r\n\r\n292\r\n00:21:57,083 --> 00:21:58,500\r\nYou unarmed?\r\n\r\n293\r\n00:21:58,500 --> 00:22:00,083\r\n[Schultz] Yes, indeed we are.\r\n\r\n294\r\n00:22:00,083 --> 00:22:04,291\r\nMarshall Tatum, may I address\r\nyou and your deputies,\r\n\r\n295\r\n00:22:04,291 --> 00:22:06,500\r\nand apparently the\r\nentire town of Daughtrey,\r\n\r\n296\r\n00:22:06,500 --> 00:22:09,083\r\nas to the incident\r\nthat just occurred?\r\n\r\n297\r\n00:22:10,125 --> 00:22:12,916\r\n- Go on.\r\n- Thank you.\r\n\r\n298\r\n00:22:12,916 --> 00:22:15,125\r\nMy name is Dr. King Schultz.\r\n\r\n299\r\n00:22:15,125 --> 00:22:18,625\r\nLike yourself, marshal,\r\nI'm a servant of the court.\r\n\r\n300\r\n00:22:18,625 --> 00:22:21,916\r\nThe man lying dead in the dirt,\r\nwho the good people of Daughtrey\r\n\r\n301\r\n00:22:21,916 --> 00:22:26,416\r\nsaw fit to elect as their\r\nsheriff, who went by the\r\nname of Bill Sharp,\r\n\r\n302\r\n00:22:26,416 --> 00:22:31,250\r\nis actually a wanted outlaw\r\nby the name of Willard Peck,\r\n\r\n303\r\n00:22:31,250 --> 00:22:34,041\r\nwith a price\r\non his head of $200.\r\n\r\n304\r\n00:22:34,041 --> 00:22:37,041\r\nNow that's $200, dead or alive.\r\n\r\n305\r\n00:22:37,041 --> 00:22:38,416\r\nThe hell, you say!\r\n\r\n306\r\n00:22:38,416 --> 00:22:42,833\r\nI'm aware this is probably\r\ndisconcerting news.\r\n\r\n307\r\n00:22:42,833 --> 00:22:46,125\r\nBut I'm willing to wager\r\nthis man was elected sheriff\r\n\r\n308\r\n00:22:46,125 --> 00:22:48,833\r\nsometime in the past two years?\r\n\r\n309\r\n00:22:49,583 --> 00:22:50,666\r\nYeah.\r\n\r\n310\r\n00:22:50,666 --> 00:22:53,083\r\n[Schultz] I know this\r\nbecause three years ago,\r\n\r\n311\r\n00:22:53,083 --> 00:22:57,791\r\nhe was rustling cattle from the\r\nB.C. Corrigan Cattle Company of\r\nLubbock, Texas.\r\n\r\n312\r\n00:22:57,791 --> 00:23:02,000\r\nNow, this is a\r\nwarrant made out by.\r\n\r\n313\r\n00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:07,875\r\nCircuit Court Judge Henry Allen\r\nLaudermilk of Austin, Texas.\r\n\r\n314\r\n00:23:07,875 --> 00:23:09,583\r\nYou're encouraged to wire him.\r\n\r\n315\r\n00:23:09,583 --> 00:23:14,875\r\nHe'll back up who I am and who\r\nyour dear departed sheriff was.\r\n\r\n316\r\n00:23:14,875 --> 00:23:18,958\r\n[guns uncocking]\r\n\r\n317\r\n00:23:22,833 --> 00:23:26,916\r\nIn other words, marshal,\r\nyou owe me $200.\r\n\r\n318\r\n00:23:26,916 --> 00:23:30,000\r\n[medium-tempo song plays]\r\n\r\n319\r\n00:23:35,500 --> 00:23:37,000\r\nI'll be damned.\r\n\r\n320\r\n00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:39,416\r\n♪ His name was King ♪\r\n\r\n321\r\n00:23:39,416 --> 00:23:41,708\r\n♪ He had a horse ♪\r\n\r\n322\r\n00:23:41,708 --> 00:23:47,000\r\n♪ Along the countryside\r\nI saw him ride ♪\r\n\r\n323\r\n00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:49,708\r\n♪ He had a gun ♪\r\n\r\n324\r\n00:23:49,708 --> 00:23:51,791\r\n♪ I knew him well ♪\r\n\r\n325\r\n00:23:51,791 --> 00:23:54,416\r\n♪ Oh, I heard him singing ♪\r\n\r\n326\r\n00:23:54,416 --> 00:23:57,625\r\n♪ I knew he loved someone ♪\r\n\r\n327\r\n00:24:05,041 --> 00:24:08,750\r\nAfter this Brittle\r\nbusiness is behind us,\r\n\r\n328\r\n00:24:08,750 --> 00:24:14,416\r\nyou'll be a free man,\r\nwith a horse, $75 in\r\nyour back pocket...\r\n\r\n329\r\n00:24:17,125 --> 00:24:18,625\r\nWhat's your plan after that?\r\n\r\n330\r\n00:24:20,625 --> 00:24:24,750\r\nFind my wife,\r\nand buy her freedom.\r\n\r\n331\r\n00:24:26,833 --> 00:24:32,250\r\nDjango, I had no idea\r\nyou were a married man.\r\n\r\n332\r\n00:24:32,250 --> 00:24:34,666\r\nDo most slaves\r\nbelieve in marriage?\r\n\r\n333\r\n00:24:34,666 --> 00:24:38,458\r\nOh, me and my wife do.\r\n\r\n334\r\n00:24:38,458 --> 00:24:42,750\r\nOld Man Carrucan didn't.\r\nThat's why we, uh... we run off.\r\n\r\n335\r\n00:24:43,875 --> 00:24:45,666\r\n[man] Django.\r\n\r\n336\r\n00:24:46,166 --> 00:24:48,875\r\nDjango, Django.\r\n\r\n337\r\n00:24:48,875 --> 00:24:51,666\r\nYou got sand, Django.\r\n\r\n338\r\n00:24:52,291 --> 00:24:54,250\r\nBoy's got sand.\r\n\r\n339\r\n00:24:55,875 --> 00:24:59,250\r\nI got no use for\r\na nigger with sand.\r\n\r\n340\r\n00:25:00,750 --> 00:25:04,416\r\nI want you to burn a runaway \"r\"\r\nright here on his cheek.\r\n\r\n341\r\n00:25:04,416 --> 00:25:05,583\r\nAnd the girl, too.\r\n\r\n342\r\n00:25:05,583 --> 00:25:07,583\r\n[groaning]\r\n\r\n343\r\n00:25:07,583 --> 00:25:12,583\r\nAnd I want you to take 'em to\r\nthe Greenville auction and sell\r\n'em.\r\n\r\n344\r\n00:25:13,208 --> 00:25:15,291\r\nBoth of 'em.\r\n\r\n345\r\n00:25:15,291 --> 00:25:17,208\r\nSeparately.\r\n\r\n346\r\n00:25:19,541 --> 00:25:21,000\r\nAnd this one...\r\n\r\n347\r\n00:25:23,416 --> 00:25:26,291\r\nyou will sell him cheap.\r\n\r\n348\r\n00:25:28,208 --> 00:25:29,791\r\nIn Greenville...\r\n\r\n349\r\n00:25:32,208 --> 00:25:35,333\r\nthere should be some sort\r\nof a records office.\r\n\r\n350\r\n00:25:42,416 --> 00:25:44,750\r\nYou know when she was sold...\r\n\r\n351\r\n00:25:46,125 --> 00:25:49,166\r\nyou know where she came from,\r\n\r\n352\r\n00:25:49,166 --> 00:25:51,125\r\nand you know her name.\r\n\r\n353\r\n00:25:51,833 --> 00:25:53,541\r\nWhat is her name?\r\n\r\n354\r\n00:25:53,541 --> 00:25:55,333\r\nBroomhilda.\r\n\r\n355\r\n00:25:56,750 --> 00:26:00,125\r\n- What?\r\n- Broom-hilda.\r\n\r\n356\r\n00:26:00,125 --> 00:26:02,333\r\n- Broomhilda?\r\n- Hm-mm.\r\n\r\n357\r\n00:26:04,041 --> 00:26:08,125\r\n- Were her owners German?\r\n- Yeah, how you know?\r\n\r\n358\r\n00:26:08,125 --> 00:26:09,583\r\nShe wasn't born on\r\nthe Carrucan plantation.\r\n\r\n359\r\n00:26:09,583 --> 00:26:12,416\r\nShe was raised by a German\r\nmistress, the Von Shafts.\r\n\r\n360\r\n00:26:12,416 --> 00:26:14,583\r\nShe speak a little German, too.\r\n\r\n361\r\n00:26:14,583 --> 00:26:16,458\r\n- Your wife?\r\n- Hm-mm.\r\n\r\n362\r\n00:26:16,458 --> 00:26:18,583\r\nWhen she was little,\r\nher mistress taught her\r\nso she'd have somebody\r\n\r\n363\r\n00:26:18,583 --> 00:26:20,375\r\nto speak German with.\r\n\r\n364\r\n00:26:21,791 --> 00:26:24,458\r\nWell, let me get this straight.\r\n\r\n365\r\n00:26:24,458 --> 00:26:29,375\r\nYour slave wife speaks German\r\nand her name is Broomhilda\r\nVon Shaft?\r\n\r\n366\r\n00:26:29,375 --> 00:26:30,583\r\nYep.\r\n\r\n367\r\n00:26:34,416 --> 00:26:36,750\r\nThey call me Hildi.\r\n\r\n368\r\n00:26:45,833 --> 00:26:47,916\r\n[rooster crowing nearby]\r\n\r\n369\r\n00:26:53,833 --> 00:26:59,583\r\nWhen we gain access to these\r\nplantations, we'll be putting\r\non an act.\r\n\r\n370\r\n00:27:00,833 --> 00:27:03,708\r\nYou'll be playing a character.\r\n\r\n371\r\n00:27:10,416 --> 00:27:11,708\r\nHm?\r\n\r\n372\r\n00:27:12,291 --> 00:27:13,791\r\nNo?\r\n\r\n373\r\n00:27:20,750 --> 00:27:25,333\r\nDuring the act, you can\r\nnever break character.\r\n\r\n374\r\n00:27:26,250 --> 00:27:28,541\r\nDo you understand?\r\n\r\n375\r\n00:27:28,541 --> 00:27:31,250\r\nYeah. Don't break character.\r\n\r\n376\r\n00:27:33,416 --> 00:27:37,541\r\nAnd your character\r\nis that of The Valet.\r\n\r\n377\r\n00:27:38,125 --> 00:27:39,750\r\nWhat that is?\r\n\r\n378\r\n00:27:40,541 --> 00:27:43,041\r\nThat's a fancy word for servant.\r\n\r\n379\r\n00:27:43,041 --> 00:27:44,416\r\n- Valet?\r\n- Hm-mm.\r\n\r\n380\r\n00:27:44,416 --> 00:27:45,833\r\n[chuckles]\r\n\r\n381\r\n00:27:45,833 --> 00:27:50,458\r\nAnd now, Django, you may choose\r\nyour character's costume.\r\n\r\n382\r\n00:27:52,708 --> 00:27:55,458\r\n- Youse gonna let me\r\npick out my own clothes?\r\n- But of course.\r\n\r\n383\r\n00:27:55,458 --> 00:28:00,083\r\n[medium-tempo song\r\nresumes playing]\r\n\r\n384\r\n00:28:00,083 --> 00:28:02,583\r\n♪ His name was King ♪\r\n\r\n385\r\n00:28:02,583 --> 00:28:05,375\r\n♪ He had a horse ♪\r\n\r\n386\r\n00:28:05,375 --> 00:28:10,666\r\n♪ Along the countryside\r\nI saw him ride ♪\r\n\r\n387\r\n00:28:10,666 --> 00:28:12,958\r\n♪ He had a gun ♪\r\n\r\n388\r\n00:28:12,958 --> 00:28:15,583\r\n♪ Oh, I knew him well ♪\r\n\r\n389\r\n00:28:15,583 --> 00:28:18,083\r\n♪ And when he shot ♪\r\n\r\n390\r\n00:28:18,083 --> 00:28:22,500\r\n♪ Oh, that man\r\nhe never missed ♪\r\n\r\n391\r\n00:28:22,500 --> 00:28:24,916\r\n- ♪ Ride on, King, ride ♪\r\n- Whoa.\r\n\r\n392\r\n00:28:24,916 --> 00:28:28,500\r\n♪ You get your man ♪\r\n\r\n393\r\n00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:33,750\r\nIt's against the law for niggers\r\nto ride horses in this\r\nterritory.\r\n\r\n394\r\n00:28:33,750 --> 00:28:37,291\r\nThis is my valet.\r\nMy valet does not walk.\r\n\r\n395\r\n00:28:37,291 --> 00:28:41,208\r\n- I said niggers on horses...\r\n- [Schultz] His name is Django.\r\n\r\n396\r\n00:28:41,208 --> 00:28:44,291\r\nHe's a free man.\r\nHe can ride what he pleases.\r\n\r\n397\r\n00:28:44,291 --> 00:28:47,708\r\nNot on my property.\r\nNot around my niggers, he can't.\r\n\r\n398\r\n00:28:47,708 --> 00:28:53,500\r\nMy good sir, perhaps we\r\ngot off on the wrong boot.\r\n\r\n399\r\n00:28:53,500 --> 00:28:56,250\r\nAllow me to unring this bell.\r\n\r\n400\r\n00:28:56,250 --> 00:29:00,041\r\nMy name is Dr. King Schultz.\r\nThis is my valet, Django.\r\n\r\n401\r\n00:29:00,041 --> 00:29:02,333\r\nAnd these are our horses,\r\nTony and Fritz.\r\n\r\n402\r\n00:29:02,333 --> 00:29:06,125\r\n- [snorting]\r\n- [women giggling]\r\n\r\n403\r\n00:29:06,125 --> 00:29:12,125\r\nMr. Bennett? I've been led to\r\nbelieve that you are a gentleman\r\nand a businessman.\r\n\r\n404\r\n00:29:12,125 --> 00:29:14,250\r\nAnd it is for these attributes\r\n\r\n405\r\n00:29:14,250 --> 00:29:18,041\r\nwe've ridden from Texas\r\nto Tennessee to parley\r\nwith you now.\r\n\r\n406\r\n00:29:19,166 --> 00:29:22,625\r\nI wish to purchase\r\none of your nigger gals.\r\n\r\n407\r\n00:29:24,750 --> 00:29:28,125\r\nYou and your Jimmie\r\nrode from Texas to Tennessee\r\n\r\n408\r\n00:29:28,125 --> 00:29:30,083\r\nto buy one of my nigger gals?\r\n\r\n409\r\n00:29:30,083 --> 00:29:31,875\r\nNo appointment, no nothin'?\r\n\r\n410\r\n00:29:31,875 --> 00:29:33,750\r\nOh, I'm afraid so.\r\n\r\n411\r\n00:29:33,750 --> 00:29:36,583\r\nWell, what if I was to say\r\nI don't like you?\r\n\r\n412\r\n00:29:36,583 --> 00:29:38,416\r\nOr your fancy-pants nigger?\r\n\r\n413\r\n00:29:38,416 --> 00:29:40,750\r\nAnd I wouldn't sell you\r\na tinker's damn.\r\n\r\n414\r\n00:29:40,750 --> 00:29:42,875\r\nNow what you\r\ngot to say about that?\r\n\r\n415\r\n00:29:46,083 --> 00:29:48,166\r\nMr. Bennett.\r\n\r\n416\r\n00:29:48,166 --> 00:29:51,583\r\nIf you are the businessman I've\r\nbeen led to believe you to be,\r\n\r\n417\r\n00:29:51,583 --> 00:29:56,875\r\nI have 5,000 things I might say\r\nthat could change your mind.\r\n\r\n418\r\n00:29:58,083 --> 00:30:00,791\r\n[chuckles softly]\r\n\r\n419\r\n00:30:00,791 --> 00:30:04,583\r\nWell, come on inside and get\r\nyourself somethin' cool to\r\ndrink.\r\n\r\n420\r\n00:30:06,416 --> 00:30:07,708\r\nHm-mm.\r\n\r\n421\r\n00:30:11,208 --> 00:30:12,416\r\n[chuckles]\r\n\r\n422\r\n00:30:18,916 --> 00:30:20,916\r\nOh, maybe while\r\nwe discuss business,\r\n\r\n423\r\n00:30:20,916 --> 00:30:23,791\r\nyou could provide one of\r\nyour loveliest black creatures\r\n\r\n424\r\n00:30:23,791 --> 00:30:26,291\r\nto escort Django here\r\naround your magnificent grounds.\r\n\r\n425\r\n00:30:26,291 --> 00:30:28,500\r\nOh, well, absolutely!\r\nUh, Betina.\r\n\r\n426\r\n00:30:28,500 --> 00:30:30,583\r\n- Yessir, Big Daddy?\r\n- Uh...\r\n\r\n427\r\n00:30:30,583 --> 00:30:32,416\r\nWhat's your Jimmie's name again?\r\n\r\n428\r\n00:30:32,416 --> 00:30:34,291\r\n- Django.\r\n- Django.\r\n\r\n429\r\n00:30:34,291 --> 00:30:36,625\r\nBetina, sugar, could you\r\ntake Django there\r\n\r\n430\r\n00:30:36,625 --> 00:30:40,041\r\nand take him around the grounds\r\nhere and show him all the pretty\r\nstuff.\r\n\r\n431\r\n00:30:40,041 --> 00:30:41,416\r\nAs you please, Big Daddy.\r\n\r\n432\r\n00:30:41,416 --> 00:30:45,416\r\nOh, Mr. Bennett, I must remind\r\nyou, Django is a free man.\r\n\r\n433\r\n00:30:45,416 --> 00:30:49,041\r\nHe cannot be treated like a\r\nslave. He... within the bounds\r\nof good taste,\r\n\r\n434\r\n00:30:49,041 --> 00:30:51,625\r\nhe must be treated\r\nas an extension of myself.\r\n\r\n435\r\n00:30:51,625 --> 00:30:54,916\r\n- Understood, Schultz.\r\nBetina, sugar?\r\n- Yes'm?\r\n\r\n436\r\n00:30:54,916 --> 00:31:00,916\r\nDjango isn't a slave. Django is\r\na free man, you understand?\r\n\r\n437\r\n00:31:00,916 --> 00:31:03,125\r\nYou can't treat him like any of\r\nthe other niggers around here,\r\n\r\n438\r\n00:31:03,125 --> 00:31:06,125\r\n'cause he ain't like any of\r\nthe other niggers around here.\r\nYou got it?\r\n\r\n439\r\n00:31:06,125 --> 00:31:09,375\r\nYou want I should\r\ntreat him like white folks?\r\n\r\n440\r\n00:31:09,375 --> 00:31:12,666\r\nNo. That's not what I said.\r\n\r\n441\r\n00:31:12,666 --> 00:31:15,500\r\nThen I don't know\r\nwhat you want, Big Daddy.\r\n\r\n442\r\n00:31:15,500 --> 00:31:20,250\r\nYes, I can see that.\r\nUh...\r\n\r\n443\r\n00:31:20,250 --> 00:31:24,750\r\nWhat's the name of that\r\npeckerwood boy from town\r\nthat works with the glass?\r\n\r\n444\r\n00:31:24,750 --> 00:31:27,083\r\nHis mama work over\r\nat the lumberyard.\r\n\r\n445\r\n00:31:27,083 --> 00:31:29,875\r\n- Oh, you mean Jerry.\r\n- That's the boy's name. Jerry!\r\n\r\n446\r\n00:31:29,875 --> 00:31:31,666\r\nYou know Jerry,\r\ndon't you, sugar?\r\n\r\n447\r\n00:31:31,666 --> 00:31:34,875\r\n- Yes'm, Big Daddy.\r\n- Well, that's it, then.\r\n\r\n448\r\n00:31:34,875 --> 00:31:38,083\r\nYou just treat him\r\nlike you would Jerry.\r\n\r\n449\r\n00:31:38,083 --> 00:31:41,583\r\n[playing medium-tempo tune]\r\n\r\n450\r\n00:31:44,708 --> 00:31:47,708\r\nThat house we just left from\r\nis The Big House.\r\n\r\n451\r\n00:31:47,708 --> 00:31:50,916\r\nBig Daddy call it that\r\n'cause it's big.\r\n\r\n452\r\n00:31:51,791 --> 00:31:54,125\r\nThat there is the pantry.\r\n\r\n453\r\n00:31:54,125 --> 00:31:57,791\r\nThat's where Big Daddy\r\nhang all his dead meat.\r\n\r\n454\r\n00:31:57,791 --> 00:32:00,083\r\nPo' little squirrels.\r\n\r\n455\r\n00:32:01,583 --> 00:32:04,208\r\nWhat you do for your massa?\r\n\r\n456\r\n00:32:04,208 --> 00:32:06,083\r\nDidn't you hear him tell you\r\nI ain't no slave?\r\n\r\n457\r\n00:32:06,083 --> 00:32:08,541\r\n- So you really free?\r\n- Yes, I's free.\r\n\r\n458\r\n00:32:08,541 --> 00:32:11,208\r\nYou mean you wanna\r\ndress like that?\r\n\r\n459\r\n00:32:12,916 --> 00:32:15,500\r\n- Betina, I need to ask\r\nyou somethin'.\r\n- What you want?\r\n\r\n460\r\n00:32:15,500 --> 00:32:18,625\r\nI'm lookin' for three white men.\r\nThree brothers. Overseers.\r\n\r\n461\r\n00:32:18,625 --> 00:32:20,416\r\nTheir name is Brittle.\r\nYou know 'em?\r\n\r\n462\r\n00:32:20,416 --> 00:32:22,250\r\n- Brittle?\r\n- Yes, Brittle.\r\n\r\n463\r\n00:32:22,250 --> 00:32:26,916\r\nJohn Brittle, Ellis Brittle,\r\nRoger Brittle, sometime called\r\nLil Raj.\r\n\r\n464\r\n00:32:26,916 --> 00:32:29,250\r\nI don't know them.\r\n\r\n465\r\n00:32:29,250 --> 00:32:31,166\r\nThey could be usin'\r\na different name.\r\n\r\n466\r\n00:32:31,166 --> 00:32:33,750\r\nThey woulda come to the\r\nplantation this past year.\r\n\r\n467\r\n00:32:33,750 --> 00:32:36,333\r\n- You mean the Shaffers?\r\n- Maybe.\r\n\r\n468\r\n00:32:36,333 --> 00:32:38,750\r\n- Three brothers?\r\n- Uh-huh.\r\n\r\n469\r\n00:32:38,750 --> 00:32:40,541\r\n- They here?\r\n- Uh-huh.\r\n\r\n470\r\n00:32:40,541 --> 00:32:42,750\r\nCould you point\r\none of 'em out to me?\r\n\r\n471\r\n00:32:42,750 --> 00:32:45,125\r\nWell, one's over in that field.\r\n\r\n472\r\n00:32:50,875 --> 00:32:53,958\r\n[medium-tempo song plays]\r\n\r\n473\r\n00:32:58,958 --> 00:33: