8:26,791\r\nWe mean no one else any harm.\r\n\r\n544\r\n00:38:26,791 --> 00:38:28,500\r\nWho are you two jokers?\r\n\r\n545\r\n00:38:28,500 --> 00:38:31,708\r\nI am Dr. King Schultz,\r\na legal representative\r\n\r\n546\r\n00:38:31,708 --> 00:38:34,500\r\nof the criminal justice system\r\nof the United States of America.\r\n\r\n547\r\n00:38:34,500 --> 00:38:39,291\r\nThe man to my left is Django\r\nFreeman. He's my deputy.\r\n\r\n548\r\n00:38:39,291 --> 00:38:41,291\r\nIn my pocket is a warrant,\r\n\r\n549\r\n00:38:41,291 --> 00:38:45,583\r\nsigned by Circuit Court Judge\r\nHenry Allen Laudermilk of\r\nAustin, Texas,\r\n\r\n550\r\n00:38:45,583 --> 00:38:49,708\r\nfor the arrest and capture,\r\ndead or alive,\r\n\r\n551\r\n00:38:49,708 --> 00:38:54,791\r\nof John Brittle,\r\nRoger Brittle and Ellis Brittle.\r\n\r\n552\r\n00:38:54,791 --> 00:38:58,333\r\nThey were goin'\r\nby the name Shaffer.\r\n\r\n553\r\n00:38:58,333 --> 00:39:02,750\r\nYou know them by the name of\r\nShaffer, but the butchers' real\r\nname was Brittle.\r\n\r\n554\r\n00:39:02,750 --> 00:39:04,541\r\nThese are wanted men.\r\n\r\n555\r\n00:39:04,541 --> 00:39:06,041\r\nThe law wants 'em for murder.\r\n\r\n556\r\n00:39:06,041 --> 00:39:10,333\r\nNow, I reiterate, the warrant\r\nstates dead or alive,\r\n\r\n557\r\n00:39:10,333 --> 00:39:13,750\r\nso when Mr. Freeman and myself\r\nexecuted these men on sight,\r\n\r\n558\r\n00:39:13,750 --> 00:39:17,416\r\nwe were operating\r\nwithin our legal boundaries.\r\n\r\n559\r\n00:39:18,375 --> 00:39:22,916\r\nI realize passions are high,\r\n\r\n560\r\n00:39:22,916 --> 00:39:27,166\r\nbut I must warn you, the penalty\r\nfor taking deadly force\r\n\r\n561\r\n00:39:27,166 --> 00:39:29,750\r\nagainst an officer of the court\r\nin the performance of his duty\r\n\r\n562\r\n00:39:29,750 --> 00:39:33,750\r\nis you'll be hung by the neck\r\nuntil you're dead.\r\n\r\n563\r\n00:39:36,416 --> 00:39:41,583\r\nNow, may I please remove the\r\nwarrant from my pocket so you\r\nmay examine it?\r\n\r\n564\r\n00:39:43,458 --> 00:39:44,750\r\nGimme.\r\n\r\n565\r\n00:40:01,166 --> 00:40:02,666\r\nSatisfied?\r\n\r\n566\r\n00:40:09,000 --> 00:40:11,500\r\nMay I have that back, please?\r\n\r\n567\r\n00:40:16,791 --> 00:40:20,083\r\n- Get off my land.\r\n- Posthaste.\r\n\r\n568\r\n00:40:20,083 --> 00:40:25,291\r\nLoad up the bodies as quickly\r\nas you can and let's get outta\r\nhere.\r\n\r\n569\r\n00:40:28,250 --> 00:40:30,791\r\n[Schultz whistling indistinctly]\r\n\r\n570\r\n00:40:50,833 --> 00:40:54,625\r\nYeah, that's them\r\nsons-a-bitches.\r\n\r\n571\r\n00:41:02,333 --> 00:41:05,833\r\n[galloping hoofbeats]\r\n\r\n572\r\n00:41:07,541 --> 00:41:12,083\r\n- [dramatic choral music]\r\n- [horses snorting, whinnying]\r\n\r\n573\r\n00:41:19,750 --> 00:41:22,875\r\n[men yelling, whooping]\r\n\r\n574\r\n00:41:34,500 --> 00:41:35,958\r\nCome on, men!\r\n\r\n575\r\n00:41:37,958 --> 00:41:41,666\r\n- [man 1] We're coming for you,\r\nnigger!\r\n- [man 2] Hee-haw!\r\n\r\n576\r\n00:41:50,291 --> 00:41:55,291\r\nNow, unless they start shootin'\r\nfirst, nobody shoot 'em.\r\n\r\n577\r\n00:41:55,291 --> 00:41:58,208\r\nThat's way too simple\r\nfor these jokers.\r\n\r\n578\r\n00:41:58,208 --> 00:42:01,000\r\nWe're gonna whup that\r\nnigger-lover to death.\r\n\r\n579\r\n00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:06,291\r\nAnd I'm gonna personally strip\r\nand clip that garboon myself.\r\n\r\n580\r\n00:42:09,916 --> 00:42:11,291\r\nDamn.\r\n\r\n581\r\n00:42:12,500 --> 00:42:15,291\r\nI can't see fuckin' shit\r\noutta this thing.\r\n\r\n582\r\n00:42:16,125 --> 00:42:17,541\r\nWe ready or what?\r\n\r\n583\r\n00:42:17,541 --> 00:42:19,916\r\n[Big Daddy] Aw, hold on,\r\nI'm fuckin' with my eyeholes.\r\n\r\n584\r\n00:42:19,916 --> 00:42:22,625\r\n- [fabric ripping]\r\n- Oh... Oh, shit.\r\n\r\n585\r\n00:42:22,625 --> 00:42:24,833\r\nI just made it worse.\r\n\r\n586\r\n00:42:24,833 --> 00:42:27,125\r\nWho made this goddamn shit?\r\n\r\n587\r\n00:42:27,125 --> 00:42:30,333\r\n- Willard's wife.\r\n- Well, make your own\r\ngoddamn masks!\r\n\r\n588\r\n00:42:30,333 --> 00:42:34,125\r\nLook, nobody's sayin' they don't\r\nappreciate what Jenny did.\r\n\r\n589\r\n00:42:34,125 --> 00:42:36,750\r\nWell, if all I had to do\r\nwas cut a hole in a bag,\r\n\r\n590\r\n00:42:36,750 --> 00:42:38,333\r\nI coulda cut it\r\nbetter than this!\r\n\r\n591\r\n00:42:38,333 --> 00:42:42,958\r\n- What about you, Robert?\r\nCan you see?\r\n- Not too good.\r\n\r\n592\r\n00:42:42,958 --> 00:42:47,166\r\nI mean, if I don't move my head\r\nI can see you pretty good, more\r\nor less.\r\n\r\n593\r\n00:42:47,166 --> 00:42:51,166\r\nBut when I start ridin',\r\nthe bag's movin' all over,\r\nand I'm ridin' blind.\r\n\r\n594\r\n00:42:51,166 --> 00:42:53,375\r\n- Shit.\r\n- [man] Yeah.\r\n\r\n595\r\n00:42:53,375 --> 00:42:55,666\r\nI just made mine worse.\r\n\r\n596\r\n00:42:56,375 --> 00:42:57,583\r\nOh, God.\r\n\r\n597\r\n00:42:57,583 --> 00:42:59,375\r\nAnybody bring any extra bags?\r\n\r\n598\r\n00:42:59,375 --> 00:43:02,458\r\nNo, nobody brought an extra bag!\r\n\r\n599\r\n00:43:02,458 --> 00:43:04,208\r\nI'm just askin'.\r\n\r\n600\r\n00:43:04,208 --> 00:43:07,458\r\n- Do we have to wear 'em\r\nwhen we ride?\r\n- Oh, well, shitfire!\r\n\r\n601\r\n00:43:07,458 --> 00:43:10,750\r\nIf you don't wear 'em as\r\nyou ride up, that just defeats\r\nthe purpose!\r\n\r\n602\r\n00:43:10,750 --> 00:43:12,875\r\nWell, I can't see\r\nin this fuckin' thing!\r\n\r\n603\r\n00:43:12,875 --> 00:43:15,750\r\nI can't breathe in this fuckin'\r\nthing and I can't ride in this\r\nfuckin' thing!\r\n\r\n604\r\n00:43:15,750 --> 00:43:18,250\r\nWell, fuck all y'all!\r\nI'm goin' home!\r\n\r\n605\r\n00:43:18,250 --> 00:43:21,958\r\nNow, I watched my wife work all\r\nday gettin' 30 bags together\r\n\r\n606\r\n00:43:21,958 --> 00:43:24,500\r\nfor you ungrateful\r\nsons-a-bitches,\r\n\r\n607\r\n00:43:24,500 --> 00:43:28,416\r\nand all I can hear is\r\ncriticize, criticize, criticize!\r\n\r\n608\r\n00:43:28,416 --> 00:43:32,000\r\nFrom now on, don't ask me\r\nor mine for nothin'!\r\n\r\n609\r\n00:43:33,041 --> 00:43:36,000\r\nNow, look, let's not\r\nforget why we're here.\r\n\r\n610\r\n00:43:36,000 --> 00:43:39,208\r\nWe got a killer nigger\r\nover that hill there!\r\n\r\n611\r\n00:43:39,208 --> 00:43:40,625\r\nAnd we gotta make\r\na lesson out of him.\r\n\r\n612\r\n00:43:40,625 --> 00:43:44,791\r\nOK, I'm confused.\r\nAre the bags on or off?\r\n\r\n613\r\n00:43:44,791 --> 00:43:49,708\r\nI think we all think\r\nthe bag was a nice idea.\r\n\r\n614\r\n00:43:49,708 --> 00:43:51,041\r\n- Yeah.\r\n- [mumbling agreements]\r\n\r\n615\r\n00:43:51,041 --> 00:43:53,083\r\nBut, not pointin' any fingers,\r\n\r\n616\r\n00:43:53,083 --> 00:43:55,000\r\nthey coulda been done better.\r\n\r\n617\r\n00:43:55,916 --> 00:43:59,750\r\nSo how 'bout no bags this time,\r\n\r\n618\r\n00:43:59,750 --> 00:44:04,750\r\nbut next time we do the bags\r\nright and then we go full\r\nregalia.\r\n\r\n619\r\n00:44:04,750 --> 00:44:07,041\r\n- I like that idea a lot.\r\n- You get my vote, Robert.\r\n\r\n620\r\n00:44:07,041 --> 00:44:10,541\r\nWait a minute!\r\nI didn't say no bags.\r\n\r\n621\r\n00:44:10,541 --> 00:44:14,041\r\n- But nobody can see.\r\n- So?\r\n\r\n622\r\n00:44:14,041 --> 00:44:16,041\r\nSo it'd be nice to see.\r\n\r\n623\r\n00:44:16,041 --> 00:44:20,750\r\nGoddamn it! This is a raid!\r\nI can't see, you can't see!\r\n\r\n624\r\n00:44:20,750 --> 00:44:26,541\r\nSo what? All that matters is\r\ncan the fuckin' horse see!\r\nThat's a raid!\r\n\r\n625\r\n00:44:26,541 --> 00:44:29,416\r\n- [overlapping shouts]\r\n- [man] Sons of bitches!\r\n\r\n626\r\n00:44:30,166 --> 00:44:31,958\r\nI can't see shit!\r\n\r\n627\r\n00:44:31,958 --> 00:44:36,250\r\n[Big Daddy] There he is!\r\nGet that nigger out\r\nfrom under that wagon!\r\n\r\n628\r\n00:44:36,250 --> 00:44:38,500\r\nAnd get that nigger-lover\r\noutta the wagon!\r\n\r\n629\r\n00:44:38,500 --> 00:44:40,250\r\nThat nigger ain't down here,\r\nBig Daddy!\r\n\r\n630\r\n00:44:40,250 --> 00:44:42,083\r\n- What?\r\n- They tricked us!\r\n\r\n631\r\n00:44:42,083 --> 00:44:43,250\r\nWell, where are they?\r\n\r\n632\r\n00:44:43,250 --> 00:44:44,875\r\nAuf Wiedersehen.\r\n\r\n633\r\n00:44:45,958 --> 00:44:48,583\r\n- [all shouting]\r\n- [horses whinnying]\r\n\r\n634\r\n00:44:50,291 --> 00:44:52,250\r\nOh! [Chuckles]\r\n\r\n635\r\n00:44:52,250 --> 00:44:53,375\r\nBull's-eye.\r\n\r\n636\r\n00:44:53,375 --> 00:44:56,250\r\n- [men yelling]\r\n- [horses whinnying]\r\n\r\n637\r\n00:44:56,250 --> 00:44:59,750\r\n- [Django] Look at 'em run.\r\n- [all shouting]\r\n\r\n638\r\n00:45:02,250 --> 00:45:05,000\r\nYeah, cowards tend to do that.\r\n\r\n639\r\n00:45:05,000 --> 00:45:07,083\r\nGoddamn it!\r\n\r\n640\r\n00:45:13,125 --> 00:45:14,500\r\n[Big Daddy] Goddamn it!\r\n\r\n641\r\n00:45:19,000 --> 00:45:20,916\r\nWould you care to?\r\n\r\n642\r\n00:45:27,541 --> 00:45:29,791\r\nCan't see shit outta this!\r\n\r\n643\r\n00:45:29,791 --> 00:45:32,291\r\n- He's getting away.\r\n- I got him.\r\n\r\n644\r\n00:45:33,916 --> 00:45:35,750\r\n[Schultz]\r\nBig Daddy's getting away.\r\n\r\n645\r\n00:45:35,750 --> 00:45:37,250\r\nI got him.\r\n\r\n646\r\n00:45:41,375 --> 00:45:44,125\r\n- [slow-motion impact sound]\r\n- [Big Daddy grunting]\r\n\r\n647\r\n00:45:52,333 --> 00:45:53,541\r\nGot him.\r\n\r\n648\r\n00:45:58,250 --> 00:46:01,333\r\n[chuckles] The kid's a natural.\r\n\r\n649\r\n00:46:05,333 --> 00:46:07,750\r\n[animal yipping nearby]\r\n\r\n650\r\n00:46:11,750 --> 00:46:15,875\r\nHow you know Broomhilda's\r\nfirst masters was German?\r\n\r\n651\r\n00:46:15,875 --> 00:46:18,250\r\nBroomhilda is a German name.\r\n\r\n652\r\n00:46:18,250 --> 00:46:20,958\r\nIf they named her, it stands\r\nto reason they'd be German.\r\n\r\n653\r\n00:46:20,958 --> 00:46:23,375\r\nLots of gals where\r\nyou're from named Broomhilda?\r\n\r\n654\r\n00:46:24,375 --> 00:46:27,375\r\nBroomhilda is the name\r\nof a character\r\n\r\n655\r\n00:46:27,375 --> 00:46:31,208\r\nin the most popular\r\nof all the German legends.\r\n\r\n656\r\n00:46:31,208 --> 00:46:33,583\r\nThere's a story\r\nabout Broomhilda?\r\n\r\n657\r\n00:46:33,583 --> 00:46:35,375\r\nOh, yes, there is.\r\n\r\n658\r\n00:46:41,250 --> 00:46:45,000\r\n- Do you know it?\r\n- Oh, every German knows\r\nthat story.\r\n\r\n659\r\n00:46:51,208 --> 00:46:52,708\r\nWould you like me to tell you?\r\n\r\n660\r\n00:46:54,083 --> 00:47:00,208\r\nWell, Broomhilda was a princess.\r\n\r\n661\r\n00:47:01,791 --> 00:47:07,000\r\nShe was a daughter of Wotan,\r\ngod of all gods.\r\n\r\n662\r\n00:47:07,000 --> 00:47:10,416\r\nAnyway, her father\r\nis really mad at her.\r\n\r\n663\r\n00:47:10,416 --> 00:47:12,583\r\nWhat she do?\r\n\r\n664\r\n00:47:12,583 --> 00:47:14,208\r\nI can't exactly remember.\r\n\r\n665\r\n00:47:14,208 --> 00:47:17,041\r\nShe disobeys him in some way.\r\n\r\n666\r\n00:47:17,041 --> 00:47:20,416\r\nSo he puts her\r\non top of the mountain.\r\n\r\n667\r\n00:47:20,416 --> 00:47:22,125\r\nBroomhilda's on a mountain?\r\n\r\n668\r\n00:47:22,125 --> 00:47:23,625\r\nIt's a German legend,\r\n\r\n669\r\n00:47:23,625 --> 00:47:26,541\r\nthere's always going to be\r\na mountain in there somewhere.\r\n\r\n670\r\n00:47:26,541 --> 00:47:30,833\r\nAnd he puts a fire-breathing\r\ndragon there to guard the\r\nmountain.\r\n\r\n671\r\n00:47:32,250 --> 00:47:37,541\r\nAnd he surrounds her\r\nin a circle of hellfire.\r\n\r\n672\r\n00:47:38,833 --> 00:47:43,333\r\nAnd there,\r\nBroomhilda shall remain.\r\n\r\n673\r\n00:47:44,625 --> 00:47:47,750\r\nUnless a hero arises\r\n\r\n674\r\n00:47:47,750 --> 00:47:49,916\r\nbrave enough to save her.\r\n\r\n675\r\n00:47:50,875 --> 00:47:52,458\r\nDoes a fella arise?\r\n\r\n676\r\n00:47:52,458 --> 00:47:55,750\r\nYes, Django,\r\nas a matter of fact, he does.\r\n\r\n677\r\n00:47:55,750 --> 00:47:58,583\r\nA fella named Siegfried.\r\n\r\n678\r\n00:47:58,583 --> 00:47:59,666\r\nDoes Siegfried save her?\r\n\r\n679\r\n00:48:01,666 --> 00:48:04,583\r\nQuite spectacularly so.\r\n\r\n680\r\n00:48:04,583 --> 00:48:09,500\r\nHe scales the mountain,\r\nbecause he's not afraid of it.\r\n\r\n681\r\n00:48:09,500 --> 00:48:14,583\r\nHe slays the dragon,\r\nbecause he's not afraid of him.\r\n\r\n682\r\n00:48:14,583 --> 00:48:17,166\r\nAnd he walks through hellfire...\r\n\r\n683\r\n00:48:19,250 --> 00:48:21,875\r\nbecause Broomhilda's\r\nworth it.\r\n\r\n684\r\n00:48:25,791 --> 00:48:27,500\r\nI know how he feel.\r\n\r\n685\r\n00:48:28,791 --> 00:48:32,000\r\nI think I'm just\r\nstarting to realize that.\r\n\r\n686\r\n00:48:37,291 --> 00:48:41,708\r\nNow, look, Django...\r\n\r\n687\r\n00:48:44,500 --> 00:48:49,583\r\nI don't doubt that one day\r\nyou'll save your lady love...\r\n\r\n688\r\n00:48:49,583 --> 00:48:54,208\r\nbut I can't let you go to\r\nGreenville in a good conscience.\r\n\r\n689\r\n00:48:54,208 --> 00:48:58,916\r\nA slave auction town in\r\nMississippi isn't the place\r\nfor you to visit.\r\n\r\n690\r\n00:48:58,916 --> 00:49:01,916\r\nFree or not,\r\nit's just too dangerous.\r\n\r\n691\r\n00:49:04,750 --> 00:49:07,041\r\nBut let me ask you a question.\r\n\r\n692\r\n00:49:14,375 --> 00:49:16,916\r\nHow do you like the\r\nbounty hunting business?\r\n\r\n693\r\n00:49:18,333 --> 00:49:20,833\r\nKill white folks\r\nand they pay you for it?\r\n\r\n694\r\n00:49:21,541 --> 00:49:22,958\r\nWhat's not to like?\r\n\r\n695\r\n00:49:22,958 --> 00:49:25,541\r\nNow, I have to admit,\r\nwe make a good team.\r\n\r\n696\r\n00:49:25,541 --> 00:49:28,541\r\nI thought you was mad at me for\r\nkillin' Big John and Lil Raj.\r\n\r\n697\r\n00:49:28,541 --> 00:49:30,875\r\nYeah, on that occasion\r\nyou were a tad overzealous,\r\n\r\n698\r\n00:49:30,875 --> 00:49:33,583\r\nbut normally,\r\nthat's a good thing.\r\n\r\n699\r\n00:49:33,583 --> 00:49:35,958\r\nHow'd you like to\r\npartner up for the winter?\r\n\r\n700\r\n00:49:35,958 --> 00:49:38,166\r\nWhat you mean \"partner up\"?\r\n\r\n701\r\n00:49:38,166 --> 00:49:42,250\r\nYou work with me through the\r\nwinter till the snow melts...\r\n\r\n702\r\n00:49:43,416 --> 00:49:46,583\r\nI give you\r\na third of my bounties.\r\n\r\n703\r\n00:49:46,583 --> 00:49:50,750\r\nSo we make some money this\r\nwinter, and when the snow melts,\r\n\r\n704\r\n00:49:50,750 --> 00:49:53,791\r\nI'll take you\r\nto Greenville myself\r\n\r\n705\r\n00:49:53,791 --> 00:49:57,166\r\nand we'll find\r\nwhere they sent your wife.\r\n\r\n706\r\n00:50:01,250 --> 00:50:03,166\r\nWhy you care what happen to me?\r\n\r\n707\r\n00:50:04,791 --> 00:50:07,000\r\nWhy you care if I find my wife?\r\n\r\n708\r\n00:50:07,000 --> 00:50:08,500\r\nFrankly...\r\n\r\n709\r\n00:50:09,791 --> 00:50:12,625\r\nI've never given anybody\r\ntheir freedom before.\r\n\r\n710\r\n00:50:12,625 --> 00:50:17,708\r\nAnd now that I have, I feel\r\nvaguely responsible for you.\r\n\r\n711\r\n00:50:17,708 --> 00:50:21,583\r\nPlus, when a German meets a real\r\nlife Siegfried, that's kind of a\r\nbig deal.\r\n\r\n712\r\n00:50:24,000 --> 00:50:27,000\r\nAs a German, I'm obliged\r\nto help you on your quest\r\n\r\n713\r\n00:50:27,000 --> 00:50:29,791\r\nto rescue your\r\nbeloved Broomhilda.\r\n\r\n714\r\n00:50:36,291 --> 00:50:39,750\r\n[medium-tempo song plays]\r\n\r\n715\r\n00:50:42,125 --> 00:50:46,833\r\n♪ Like the pine trees\r\nlinin' the windin' road ♪\r\n\r\n716\r\n00:50:46,833 --> 00:50:49,625\r\n♪ I've got a name ♪\r\n\r\n717\r\n00:50:49,625 --> 00:50:52,125\r\n♪ I've got a name ♪\r\n\r\n718\r\n00:50:53,750 --> 00:50:58,041\r\n♪ Like the singin' bird\r\nand the croakin' toad ♪\r\n\r\n719\r\n00:50:58,041 --> 00:51:00,458\r\n♪ I've got a name ♪\r\n\r\n720\r\n00:51:00,458 --> 00:51:04,416\r\n♪ I've got a name ♪\r\n\r\n721\r\n00:51:04,416 --> 00:51:08,416\r\n♪ And I carry it with me\r\nlike my daddy did ♪\r\n\r\n722\r\n00:51:08,416 --> 00:51:14,666\r\n♪ But I'm livin' the dream\r\nthat he kept hid ♪\r\n\r\n723\r\n00:51:15,916 --> 00:51:18,666\r\n♪ Movin' me down the highway ♪\r\n\r\n724\r\n00:51:18,666 --> 00