\n00:58:16,083 --> 00:58:18,583\r\n[man 1] Move along!\r\n\r\n800\r\n00:58:23,708 --> 00:58:26,000\r\nMove it, boy!\r\n\r\n801\r\n00:58:27,333 --> 00:58:28,916\r\n[man 2] Keep movin'.\r\n\r\n802\r\n00:58:28,916 --> 00:58:32,083\r\nGet on up on that auction block.\r\n\r\n803\r\n00:58:32,083 --> 00:58:34,916\r\nDon't let that mud\r\nslow you down. Keep going.\r\n\r\n804\r\n00:58:51,083 --> 00:58:52,500\r\nKeep goin'!\r\n\r\n805\r\n00:58:54,750 --> 00:58:58,916\r\n[Schultz]\r\n\"Broomhilda Von Shaft. Age 27.\r\n\r\n806\r\n00:58:58,916 --> 00:59:00,541\r\n'R' on right cheek.\"\r\n\r\n807\r\n00:59:02,041 --> 00:59:04,125\r\nCalvin Candie.\r\n\r\n808\r\n00:59:04,125 --> 00:59:08,916\r\nHe owns the fourth biggest\r\ncotton plantation in\r\nMississippi: Candyland.\r\n\r\n809\r\n00:59:08,916 --> 00:59:10,416\r\nCandyland?\r\n\r\n810\r\n00:59:10,416 --> 00:59:11,750\r\nOh, so you've heard of it.\r\n\r\n811\r\n00:59:11,750 --> 00:59:13,916\r\nAin't no slave ain't\r\nheard of Candyland.\r\n\r\n812\r\n00:59:13,916 --> 00:59:16,583\r\nWell, apparently,\r\nthat's where your wife is,\r\n\r\n813\r\n00:59:16,583 --> 00:59:19,250\r\n- and that's the repellant\r\ngentleman who owns her.\r\n- [sighs]\r\n\r\n814\r\n00:59:19,250 --> 00:59:22,375\r\nLet's just hope she works\r\nin the house, not in the field.\r\n\r\n815\r\n00:59:22,375 --> 00:59:24,750\r\nOh, no, she ain't\r\nno field nigger.\r\n\r\n816\r\n00:59:24,750 --> 00:59:27,375\r\nShe... she pretty.\r\n\r\n817\r\n00:59:27,375 --> 00:59:29,416\r\nAnd she talk good, too.\r\n\r\n818\r\n00:59:30,833 --> 00:59:32,750\r\nBut when they tore\r\nher back up and then they...\r\n\r\n819\r\n00:59:33,875 --> 00:59:36,166\r\nburned that runaway \"r\"\r\non her cheek...\r\n\r\n820\r\n00:59:37,458 --> 00:59:38,750\r\nthey goddamned her.\r\n\r\n821\r\n00:59:39,250 --> 00:59:40,458\r\n[yells]\r\n\r\n822\r\n00:59:40,458 --> 00:59:42,250\r\n- [sizzling]\r\n- [screaming]\r\n\r\n823\r\n00:59:43,375 --> 00:59:44,958\r\nShe ain't no field nigger\r\nbut she ain't good enough\r\n\r\n824\r\n00:59:44,958 --> 00:59:47,000\r\nfor the house no more either.\r\n\r\n825\r\n00:59:47,000 --> 00:59:48,583\r\nThey gonna try to\r\nmake her a comfort girl.\r\n\r\n826\r\n00:59:48,583 --> 00:59:50,583\r\nWhat's a comfort...? Oh.\r\n\r\n827\r\n00:59:51,375 --> 00:59:52,750\r\nNot while I got freedom.\r\n\r\n828\r\n00:59:54,166 --> 00:59:56,166\r\nNot while I got my gun.\r\n\r\n829\r\n00:59:59,083 --> 01:00:00,958\r\nSo do we offer to buy her?\r\n\r\n830\r\n01:00:03,375 --> 01:00:05,000\r\nSo...\r\n\r\n831\r\n01:00:06,291 --> 01:00:08,208\r\nsay...\r\n\r\n832\r\n01:00:10,208 --> 01:00:13,500\r\na man wants to buy a horse.\r\n\r\n833\r\n01:00:13,500 --> 01:00:16,416\r\nNeeds to buy a horse.\r\n\r\n834\r\n01:00:16,416 --> 01:00:19,583\r\nHe walks up to the farmer's\r\nfarm, and he knocks on the\r\nfarmer's door\r\n\r\n835\r\n01:00:19,583 --> 01:00:21,291\r\nand asks the farmer\r\nto buy his horse.\r\n\r\n836\r\n01:00:21,291 --> 01:00:23,500\r\nAnd do you know\r\nwhat the farmer says?\r\n\r\n837\r\n01:00:23,500 --> 01:00:25,791\r\nThe farmer says no.\r\n\r\n838\r\n01:00:27,208 --> 01:00:32,291\r\nWell, I say fuck that farmer,\r\nand I'm stealin' that horse.\r\n\r\n839\r\n01:00:32,291 --> 01:00:36,583\r\nFair enough. But now you're\r\na horse thief, and they hang\r\nhorse thieves.\r\n\r\n840\r\n01:00:36,583 --> 01:00:38,833\r\nNot to mention the horse\r\ngoes back to its original owner\r\n\r\n841\r\n01:00:38,833 --> 01:00:40,625\r\nbecause the horse\r\nis still his property.\r\n\r\n842\r\n01:00:40,625 --> 01:00:44,750\r\nWe need her\r\nand we need a bill of sale.\r\n\r\n843\r\n01:00:44,750 --> 01:00:48,125\r\nWell, if we ain't gonna try to\r\nbuy her, then how we gonna get\r\nher?\r\n\r\n844\r\n01:00:48,125 --> 01:00:51,833\r\nMay I offer an\r\nalternative plan of action?\r\n\r\n845\r\n01:00:51,833 --> 01:00:53,458\r\nGo ahead.\r\n\r\n846\r\n01:00:53,458 --> 01:00:58,125\r\nSo... the man walks up\r\nto the farmer's farm,\r\n\r\n847\r\n01:00:58,125 --> 01:01:00,541\r\nhe knocks on\r\nthe farmer's door...\r\n\r\n848\r\n01:01:00,541 --> 01:01:05,625\r\nand asks not to buy\r\nthe horse, but the farm.\r\n\r\n849\r\n01:01:05,625 --> 01:01:09,333\r\nAnd makes an offer\r\nso ridiculous,\r\n\r\n850\r\n01:01:09,333 --> 01:01:12,250\r\nthe farmer is forced to say yes.\r\n\r\n851\r\n01:01:13,083 --> 01:01:14,583\r\nWe gonna offer\r\nto buy Candyland?\r\n\r\n852\r\n01:01:14,583 --> 01:01:16,166\r\nNo, it's far too big.\r\n\r\n853\r\n01:01:16,166 --> 01:01:19,250\r\nBut apparently this farmer\r\nain't all about the farm.\r\n\r\n854\r\n01:01:20,583 --> 01:01:23,750\r\n- How much do you know\r\nabout Mandingo fighting?\r\n- What?\r\n\r\n855\r\n01:01:23,750 --> 01:01:26,875\r\nCan you convincingly\r\nmasquerade as someone\r\n\r\n856\r\n01:01:26,875 --> 01:01:29,875\r\n- who is an expert\r\non Mandingo fighting?\r\n- Why?\r\n\r\n857\r\n01:01:29,875 --> 01:01:33,750\r\n[Schultz] Because my character\r\nis that of a big money buyer\r\nfrom Dusseldorf,\r\n\r\n858\r\n01:01:33,750 --> 01:01:37,458\r\nhere in Greenville to\r\nbuy my way into the Mandingo\r\nfight game.\r\n\r\n859\r\n01:01:37,458 --> 01:01:41,375\r\nAnd your character is a\r\nMandingo expert I hired\r\nto help me do it.\r\n\r\n860\r\n01:01:41,375 --> 01:01:43,750\r\n[Django] They call that\r\n\"One-Eyed Charley.\"\r\n\r\n861\r\n01:01:46,583 --> 01:01:48,291\r\nBonjour.\r\n\r\n862\r\n01:01:48,291 --> 01:01:51,291\r\n[speaks French]\r\n\r\n863\r\n01:01:51,291 --> 01:01:54,208\r\nWe're here to see\r\nMr. Calvin Candie.\r\n\r\n864\r\n01:01:54,208 --> 01:01:55,916\r\nEntr-a.\r\n\r\n865\r\n01:01:58,083 --> 01:01:59,916\r\n- Thank you.\r\n- Hm-mm.\r\n\r\n866\r\n01:02:00,750 --> 01:02:03,416\r\nYou want me to play\r\na black slaver?\r\n\r\n867\r\n01:02:03,416 --> 01:02:06,416\r\nAin't nothin' lower\r\nthan a black slaver.\r\n\r\n868\r\n01:02:06,416 --> 01:02:10,500\r\nA black slaver is lower\r\nthan the head house nigger...\r\n\r\n869\r\n01:02:10,500 --> 01:02:12,791\r\nand, buddy,\r\nthat's pretty fuckin' low.\r\n\r\n870\r\n01:02:13,750 --> 01:02:15,916\r\nThen play him that way.\r\n\r\n871\r\n01:02:15,916 --> 01:02:19,916\r\nGive me your black slaver.\r\n\r\n872\r\n01:02:19,916 --> 01:02:22,416\r\n[people singing\r\nmedium-tempo song]\r\n\r\n873\r\n01:02:22,416 --> 01:02:27,833\r\n♪ Along came the 219\r\nToot! Toot! Peanut butter! ♪\r\n\r\n874\r\n01:02:27,833 --> 01:02:30,333\r\n[singing continues indistinctly]\r\n\r\n875\r\n01:02:31,333 --> 01:02:33,416\r\nDr. Schultz!\r\n\r\n876\r\n01:02:33,416 --> 01:02:36,750\r\n- Good to see you again!\r\n- Mr. Moguy.\r\n\r\n877\r\n01:02:36,750 --> 01:02:39,750\r\nThank you for your assistance\r\nin creating the opportunity\r\n\r\n878\r\n01:02:39,750 --> 01:02:42,750\r\n- for this appointment.\r\n- Nonsense, it's my job.\r\n\r\n879\r\n01:02:42,750 --> 01:02:45,625\r\nSo this is the One-Eyed Charley\r\nI've heard so much about.\r\n\r\n880\r\n01:02:45,625 --> 01:02:48,125\r\nYes, this is Django Freeman.\r\n\r\n881\r\n01:02:48,125 --> 01:02:51,166\r\nDjango, this is Mr. Candie's\r\nlawyer, Leonide Moguy.\r\n\r\n882\r\n01:02:51,166 --> 01:02:53,250\r\nJust call me Leo.\r\n\r\n883\r\n01:02:53,250 --> 01:02:56,583\r\nCalvin's in the Julius Caesar\r\nroom. You all wanna follow me?\r\n\r\n884\r\n01:02:56,583 --> 01:02:59,083\r\n[Schultz] How long have you been\r\nassociated with Mr. Candie?\r\n\r\n885\r\n01:02:59,083 --> 01:03:01,458\r\n[Leo] Oh, Calvin's father and I\r\nwere about 11\r\n\r\n886\r\n01:03:01,458 --> 01:03:03,666\r\nwhen we went to\r\nboarding school together.\r\n\r\n887\r\n01:03:03,666 --> 01:03:06,875\r\nCalvin's father's father\r\nput me through law school.\r\n\r\n888\r\n01:03:06,875 --> 01:03:10,083\r\nOne could almost say I was\r\nraised to be Calvin's lawyer.\r\n\r\n889\r\n01:03:10,083 --> 01:03:11,958\r\nOne could almost say\r\nyouse a nigger.\r\n\r\n890\r\n01:03:12,750 --> 01:03:14,083\r\nWhat did you say?\r\n\r\n891\r\n01:03:14,083 --> 01:03:17,083\r\n- I said...\r\n- Nothing, he's just\r\nbeing cheeky.\r\n\r\n892\r\n01:03:17,083 --> 01:03:21,958\r\nUh, anything else about\r\nMr. Candie that I should\r\nknow before I meet him?\r\n\r\n893\r\n01:03:21,958 --> 01:03:24,208\r\nYes, he is a bit\r\nof a Francophile.\r\n\r\n894\r\n01:03:24,208 --> 01:03:26,291\r\n[chuckles]\r\nWhat civilized people aren't?\r\n\r\n895\r\n01:03:26,291 --> 01:03:28,708\r\nAnd he prefers Monsieur Candie\r\nto Mr. Candie.\r\n\r\n896\r\n01:03:28,708 --> 01:03:31,291\r\n[speaks French]\r\n\r\n897\r\n01:03:31,291 --> 01:03:35,500\r\nHe doesn't speak French.\r\nDon't speak French to him,\r\nit'll embarrass him.\r\n\r\n898\r\n01:03:36,625 --> 01:03:38,208\r\n[men fighting, grunting]\r\n\r\n899\r\n01:03:38,208 --> 01:03:40,708\r\n[man] Get back on top, now!\r\nTurn around!\r\n\r\n900\r\n01:03:40,708 --> 01:03:42,416\r\nThere you go.\r\n\r\n901\r\n01:03:42,416 --> 01:03:44,208\r\nThere you go.\r\n\r\n902\r\n01:03:45,833 --> 01:03:48,291\r\nWhy do you want to get in\r\nthe Mandingo business?\r\n\r\n903\r\n01:03:50,791 --> 01:03:54,583\r\nYou don't intend to allow your\r\nsecond to make the proper\r\nintroductions?\r\n\r\n904\r\n01:03:55,416 --> 01:03:57,500\r\nQuit stalling, now.\r\n\r\n905\r\n01:03:57,500 --> 01:03:59,041\r\nAnswer the question.\r\n\r\n906\r\n01:04:01,541 --> 01:04:04,875\r\nThe awful truth? I'm bored.\r\n\r\n907\r\n01:04:04,875 --> 01:04:07,625\r\nThis seems like\r\na good bit of fun.\r\n\r\n908\r\n01:04:12,333 --> 01:04:14,333\r\nWell, come on over.\r\n\r\n909\r\n01:04:14,333 --> 01:04:17,416\r\nWe got us a fight goin' on\r\nthat's a good bit of fun.\r\n\r\n910\r\n01:04:19,416 --> 01:04:21,250\r\n[man speaks foreign language]\r\n\r\n911\r\n01:04:21,250 --> 01:04:22,875\r\nWon't you accompany me\r\nto the bar?\r\n\r\n912\r\n01:04:22,875 --> 01:04:25,250\r\n[grunting, punches continue]\r\n\r\n913\r\n01:04:32,083 --> 01:04:34,250\r\nYou don't wear a hat\r\nin the house, white man.\r\nEven I know that.\r\n\r\n914\r\n01:04:43,583 --> 01:04:45,166\r\n- Dr. Schultz.\r\n- What a rare pleasure.\r\n\r\n915\r\n01:04:45,166 --> 01:04:46,666\r\nKeep fighting, niggers.\r\n\r\n916\r\n01:04:46,666 --> 01:04:49,708\r\n- And I might add, an honor.\r\n- Honor to meet you.\r\n\r\n917\r\n01:04:49,708 --> 01:04:51,750\r\nPlease have a seat,\r\nthe pleasure's all mine.\r\n\r\n918\r\n01:04:51,750 --> 01:04:55,375\r\nGet free man Django here\r\nwhatever he wants.\r\n\r\n919\r\n01:04:55,375 --> 01:04:57,875\r\nAnd I'll have\r\nsweet tea and bourbon.\r\n\r\n920\r\n01:05:08,291 --> 01:05:11,083\r\n[grunting from fighters\r\ncontinues]\r\n\r\n921\r\n01:05:14,333 --> 01:05:17,333\r\n- [man yelling]\r\n- [grunting]\r\n\r\n922\r\n01:05:17,333 --> 01:05:20,583\r\n[Calvin] Use your weight, boy,\r\nuse your weight! There you go.\r\n\r\n923\r\n01:05:20,583 --> 01:05:23,083\r\nHe's much bigger and stronger!\r\n\r\n924\r\n01:05:23,083 --> 01:05:24,791\r\nCome on, now!\r\n\r\n925\r\n01:05:24,791 --> 01:05:27,416\r\nHe's not doing what I told him,\r\nfor God's sakes.\r\n\r\n926\r\n01:05:27,416 --> 01:05:29,500\r\n[speaking foreign language]\r\n\r\n927\r\n01:05:31,208 --> 01:05:34,083\r\nCome on, now, boy!\r\nIt's a fight to the death!\r\n\r\n928\r\n01:05:34,083 --> 01:05:37,500\r\n- [grunting]\r\n- You either hit him\r\nor are you ain't?\r\n\r\n929\r\n01:05:37,500 --> 01:05:39,125\r\n[yelling]\r\n\r\n930\r\n01:05:41,916 --> 01:05:45,333\r\n[speaking foreign language]\r\n\r\n931\r\n01:05:45,333 --> 01:05:48,750\r\n- Big Fred, come on!\r\n- [grunting]\r\n\r\n932\r\n01:05:48,750 --> 01:05:50,333\r\n[Calvin] Turn him around! Now...\r\n\r\n933\r\n01:05:54,041 --> 01:05:58,541\r\n[Calvin] Use your strength, boy!\r\nCome on, now! Use your strength!\r\n\r\n934\r\n01:05:58,541 --> 01:06:00,416\r\n[man screaming]\r\n\r\n935\r\n01:06:00,416 --> 01:06:02,416\r\n[Calvin] There you go!\r\n\r\n936\r\n01:06:03,541 --> 01:06:06,916\r\nThere you go! Look at that.\r\n\r\n937\r\n01:06:06,916 --> 01:06:10,250\r\nSee, I told you to put\r\nsome more power in there.\r\n\r\n938\r\n01:06:10,250 --> 01:06:12,250\r\nDo what I told you, boy!\r\n\r\n939\r\n01:06:12,250 --> 01:06:14,083\r\n- There you go!\r\n- [bones cracking]\r\n\r\n940\r\n01:06:14,083 --> 01:06:16,458\r\n- No!\r\n- [Calvin] Do what I told ya!\r\n\r\n941\r\n01:06:16,458 --> 01:06:19,750\r\nBlind him black, boy!\r\nBlind him black!\r\n\r\n942\r\n01:06:19,750 --> 01:06:22,000\r\n[man screaming]\r\n\r\n943\r\n01:06:22,000 --> 01:06:24,666\r\n- Oh, no, Luigi.\r\n- [screaming]\r\n\r\n944\r\n01:06:27,666 --> 01:06:31,375\r\n- Whoo! Whoo-hoo-hoo!\r\n- [screaming]\r\n\r\n945\r\n01:06:32,250 --> 01:06:33,458\r\nOh...\r\n\r\n946\r\n01:06:33,458 --> 01:06:36,583\r\n- [panting]\r\n- [man continues screaming]\r\n\r\n947\r\n01:06:40,666 --> 01:06:41,666\r\n[playing pool]\r\n\r\n948\r\n01:06:41,666 --> 01:06:43,958\r\n[screaming continues]\r\n\r\n949\r\n01:06:43,958 --> 01:06:45,416\r\nFinish him.\r\n\r\n950\r\n01:06:49,583 --> 01:06:51,500\r\nGo on, boy, finish him!\r\n\r\n951\r\n01:06:53,000 --> 01:06:54,416\r\n[screaming halts]\r\n\r\n952\r\n01:06:55,625 --> 01:06:57,583\r\nThat's why they\r\ncall him Big Fred.\r\n\r\n953\r\n01:06:57,583 --> 01:07:01,083\r\n- Worth every penny.\r\n- Well, arrivederci, Luigi.\r\n\r\n954\r\n01:07:01,083 --> 01:07:03,583\r\nCome on up, now, boy.\r\nGet yourself a rest.\r\n\r\n955\r\n01:07:03,583 --> 01:07:06,791\r\nYou did a fine job.\r\nA real fine job.\r\n\r\n956\r\n01:07:07,291 --> 01:07:09,208\r\nMercedes.\r\n\r\n957\r\n01:07:30,125 --> 01:07:31,541\r\nTequila.\r\n\r\n958\r\n01:07:41,250 --> 01:07:43,041\r\nWhat's your name?\r\n\r\n959\r\n01:07:45,041 --> 01:07:46,625\r\nDjango.\r\n\r\n960\r\n01:07:48,833 --> 01:07:50,750\r\nCan you spell it?\r\n\r\n961\r\n01:07:52,750 --> 01:07:56,958\r\nD-J-A-N-G-O.\r\n\r\n962\r\n01:07:58,291 --> 01:07:59,958\r\nThe D is silent.\r\n\r\n963\r\n01:07:59,958 --> 01:08:01,666\r\nI know.\r\n\r\n964\r\n01:08:08,250 --> 01:08:09,666\r\n[speaks foreign language]\r\n\r\n965\r\n01:08:09,666 --> 01:08:13,083\r\n[Calvin] Mr. Moguy, want you to\r\ntake care of my new boy here.\r\n\r\n966\r\n01:08:13,083 --> 01:08:15,083\r\nYou find him a room\r\nwith a soft bed,\r\n\r\n967\r\n01:08:15,083 --> 01:08:17,666\r\nthen you bring him up\r\na pony to lick his pole.\r\n\r\n968\r\n01:08:17,666 --> 01:08:20,708\r\nBut you be ready to travel\r\nto Candyland tomorrow morning,\r\nnow, ya hear?\r\n\r\n969\r\n01:08:20,708 --> 01:08:21,958\r\nYessir, Monsieur Candie.\r\n\r\n970\r\n01:08:21,958 --> 01:08:26,083\r\nBefore you go, Roscoe,\r\nget Fred here a tall beer.\r\n\r\n971\r\n01:08:29,583 --> 01:08:32,791\r\nYou enjoy that, boy.\r\nYou've earned it.\r\n\r\n972\r\n01:08:32,791 --> 01:08:34,208\r\nYessir.\r\n\r\n973\r\n01:08:43,500 --> 01:08:47,500\r\n- What's your name, boy?\r\n- His name is Django Freeman.\r\n\r\n974\r\n01:08:47,500 --> 01:08:48,916\r\n[Calvin chuckles]\r\n\r\n975\r\n01:08:50,916 --> 01:08:52,708\r\nWhere'd you dig him up?\r\n\r\n976\r\n01:08:52,708 --> 01:08:56,083\r\nA fortuitous turn of events\r\nbrought Django and myself\r\ntogether.\r\n\r\n977\r\n01:08:57,708 --> 01:09:00,541\r\nI've heard tell about you.\r\n\r\n978\r\n01:09:00,541 --> 01:09:03,333\r\nI heard you been telling\r\neverybody them Mandingos\r\nain't no damn good.\r\n\r\n979\r\n01:09:03,333 --> 01:09:05,625\r\nAin't nothin' nobody\r\nis sellin' is worth buyin'.\r\n\r\n980\r\n01:09:05,625 --> 01:09:10,125\r\nI'm curious... what makes you\r\nsuch a Mandingo expert?\r\n\r\n981\r\n01:09:11,916 --> 01:09:14,541\r\nI'm curious what\r\nmakes you so curious.\r\n\r\n982\r\n01:09:17,625 --> 01:09:19,833\r\n- What did you say, boy?\r\n- Calm down, Butch.\r\n\r\n983\r\n01:09:20,750 --> 01:09:22,250\r\nNo offense given...\r\n\r\n984\r\n01:09:22,833 --> 01:09:24,250\r\nnone taken.\r\n\r\n985\r\n01:09:24,250 --> 01:09:26,041\r\n[Schultz] Monsieur Candie...\r\n\r\n986\r\n01:09:26,041 --> 01:09:29,750\r\nI'd appreciate if you could\r\ndirect your line of inquiry\r\ntoward me.\r\n\r\n987\r\n01:09:29,750 --> 01:09:31,750\r\nOne...\r\n\r\n988\r\n01:09:31,750 --> 01:09:35,208\r\nyou do not have anything\r\nto drink. Can I get you a tasty\r\nrefreshment?\r\n\r\n989\r\n01:09:35,208 --> 01:09:38,083\r\n- Yes! I'll have a beer.\r\n- Wunderbar.\r\n\r\n990\r\n01:09:38,083 --> 01:09:40,208\r\nRoscoe, a beer\r\nfor the man with the beard,\r\n\r\n991\r\n01:09:40,208 --> 01:09:42,166\r\nand I will have a\r\nPolynesian Pearl Diver.\r\n\r\n992\r\n01:09:42,166 --> 01:09:44,458\r\nDo not spare the rum.\r\n\r\n993\r\n01:09:44,458 --> 01:09:48,083\r\nDoc... I am a seasoned slaver.\r\n\r\n994\r\n01:09:48,083 --> 01:09:49,791\r\nYou are, well,\r\nyou are a neophyte.\r\n\r\n995\r\n01:09:49,791 --> 01:09:52,750\r\nI'm simply tryin' to\r\nascertain if this cowboy here\r\n\r\n996\r\n01:09:52,750 --> 01:09:55,375\r\nis takin' advantage of you.\r\n\r\n997\r\n01:09:56,583 --> 01:10:00,375\r\nWith all due respect,\r\nMonsieur Candie...\r\n\r\n998\r\n01:10:00,375 --> 01:10:02,583\r\nI didn't seek you\r\nout for your advice.\r\n\r\n999\r\n01:10:02,583 --> 01:10:04,875\r\nI sought you out to\r\npurchase a fighting nigger\r\n\r\n1000\r\n01:10:04,875 --> 01:10:07,583\r\nat above top-dollar\r\nmarket price.\r\n\r\n1001\r\n01:10:07,583 --> 01:10:10,291\r\nNow I was under the impression,\r\nwhen you granted me an audience,\r\n\r\n1002\r\n01:10:10,291 --> 01:10:12,791\r\nit would be to discuss business.\r\n\r\n1003\r\n01:10:15,291 --> 01:10:18,041\r\nWell, we weren't\r\ntalkin' business yet.\r\n\r\n1004\r\n01:10:18,041 --> 01:10:20,500\r\nWe were discussin' my curiosity.\r\n\r\n1005\r\n01:10:22,583 --> 01:10:23,791\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\n1006\r\n01:10:23,791 --> 01:10:26,708\r\n[Calvin] Roscoe, Coco,\r\ngo outside and play.\r\n\r\n1007\r\n01:10:28,500 --> 01:10:32,041\r\nSheba... you stay right there.\r\n\r\n1008\r\n01:10:32,041 --> 01:10:33,791\r\nI know you didn't mean me.\r\n\r\n1009\r\n01:10:35,208 --> 01:10:38,750\r\n- Prost!\r\n- German.\r\n\r\n1010\r\n01:10:38,750 --> 01:10:42,666\r\nNow, according to Moguy,\r\nif I do business with you,\r\n\r\n1011\r\n01:10:42,666 --> 01:10:44,833\r\nI'm doing business\r\nwith both y'all.\r\n\r\n1012\r\n01:10:44,833 --> 01:10:47,458\r\nHe does the eyeballin',\r\nyou the billfold? Is that it?\r\n\r\n1013\r\n01:10:47,458 --> 01:10:51,541\r\nWell, you don't make it sound\r\ntoo flattering, but more or\r\nless, yeah.\r\n\r\n1014\r\n01:10:51,541 --> 01:10:52,833\r\nHm.\r\n\r\n1015\r\n01:10:54,041 --> 01:10:55,250\r\nSo...\r\n\r\n1016\r\n01:10:55,250 --> 01:10:57,250\r\nBright Boy...\r\n\r\n1017\r\n01:10:57,250 --> 01:10:59,416\r\nMoguy tells me\r\nyou looked over my African flesh\r\n\r\n1018\r\n01:10:59,416 --> 01:11:01,750\r\nand you was\r\nnone too impressed, huh?\r\n\r\n1019\r\n01:11:01,750 --> 01:11:03,416\r\nNot for top dollar.\r\n\r\n1020\r\n01:11:05,125 --> 01:11:07,416\r\nWell, then, we got nothin'\r\nmore to talk about.\r\n\r\n1021\r\n01:11:07,416 --> 01:11:09,833\r\nYou see, you wanna buy\r\na beat-ass nigger from me,\r\n\r\n1022\r\n01:11:09,833 --> 01:11:12,291\r\nthose are the beat-ass niggers\r\nI wanna sell so...\r\n\r\n1023\r\n01:11:12,291 --> 01:11:14,166\r\nHe don't wanna buy\r\nthe niggers you wanna sell.\r\n\r\n1024\r\n01:11:14,166 --> 01:11:18,583\r\nHe wants the nigger\r\nyou don't wanna sell.\r\n\r\n1025\r\n01:11:18,583 --> 01:11:23,083\r\nWell, I don't sell the niggers\r\nI don't wanna sell.\r\n\r\n1026\r\n01:11:25,166 --> 01:11:28,875\r\nWell, you won't sell your best.\r\n\r\n1027\r\n01:11:28,875 --> 01:11:31,458\r\nYou won't even\r\nsell your second best.\r\n\r\n1028\r\n01:11:31,458 --> 01:11:35,291\r\nBut your third best...? You\r\ndon't want to sell him either.\r\n\r\n1029\r\n01:11:35,291 --> 01:11:40,083\r\nBut if I made you an offer\r\nso ridiculous you'd be forced\r\nto consider it...\r\n\r\n1030\r\n01:11:40,083 --> 01:11:42,250\r\n[chortles]\r\n...who knows what could happen?\r\n\r\n1031\r\n01:11:44,291 --> 01:11:46,916\r\nAnd what do you\r\nconsider ridiculous?\r\n\r\n1032\r\n01:11:46,916 --> 01:11:52,000\r\nFor a truly talented specimen,\r\nthe right nigger?\r\n\r\n1033\r\n01:11:53,708 --> 01:11:55,791\r\nHow much would you say, Django?\r\n\r\n1034\r\n01:11:59,083 --> 01:12:00,916\r\nTwelve thousand dollars.\r\n\r\n1035\r\n01:12:01,500 --> 01:12:03,291\r\n[straw slurping]\r\n\r\n1036\r\n01:12:05,208 --> 01:12:09,416\r\nWell, gentlemen,\r\nyou had my curiosity,\r\n\r\n1037\r\n01:12:09,416 --> 01:12:11,500\r\nbut now you have my attention.\r\n\r\n1038\r\n01:12:24,500 --> 01:12:30,291\r\nWillie. Willie.\r\nHold up! Hold up. Ah!\r\n\r\n1039\r\n01:12:30,291 --> 01:12:33,000\r\n- Good morning, gentlemen.\r\n- Good Dr. Schultz.\r\n\r\n1040\r\n01:12:33,000 --> 01:12:37,000\r\n- Beautiful morning, isn't it?\r\n- You couldn't have picked a\r\nbetter one.\r\n\r\n1041\r\n01:12:37,000 --> 01:12:40,208\r\nPlease, won't you take a ride\r\nwith us here in the Victoria.\r\n\r\n1042\r\n01:12:40,208 --> 01:12:41,708\r\n[Schultz]\r\nOh, thank you very much.\r\n\r\n1043\r\n01:12:41,708 --> 01:12:44,208\r\nYou can tie your horse up\r\nback there.\r\n\r\n1044\r\n01:12:52,333 --> 01:12:53,750\r\n[Calvin] Django.\r\n\r\n1045\r\n01:12:58,333 --> 01:13:02,041\r\nWhere I part company from many\r\nof my phrenologist colleagues\r\n\r\n1046\r\n01:13:02,041 --> 01:13:07,416\r\nis I believe there is a level\r\nabove bright, above talented,\r\n\r\n1047\r\n01:13:07,416 --> 01:13:11,750\r\nabove loyal that\r\na nigger can aspire to.\r\n\r\n1048\r\n01:13:11,750 --> 01:13:16,625\r\nSay, one nigger that\r\njust pops up in 10,000.\r\n\r\n1049\r\n01:13:16,625 --> 01:13:18,250\r\nThe exceptional nigger.\r\n\r\n1050\r\n01:13:19,125 --> 01:13:21,333\r\nBright day, huh, Bright Boy?\r\n\r\n1051\r\n01:13:22,250 --> 01:13:23,625\r\nSun is up.\r\n\r\n1052\r\n01:13:24,625 --> 01:13:26,666\r\nShining on all of us.\r\n\r\n1053\r\n01:13:31,166 --> 01:13:34,375\r\n- [Calvin] Have a seat, doc.\r\n- [Schultz] Thank you.\r\n\r\n1054\r\n01:13:34,375 --> 01:13:35,875\r\nQuite an honor.\r\n\r\n1055\r\n01:13:35,875 --> 01:13:37,666\r\n- The honor is all ours.\r\n- Thank you.\r\n\r\n1056\r\n01:13:37,666 --> 01:13:41,250\r\n[Calvin] But I do believe that,\r\ngiven time,\r\n\r\n1057\r\n01:13:41,250 --> 01:13:44,375\r\nexceptional niggers\r\nlike Bright Boy here...\r\n\r\n1058\r\n01:13:45,250 --> 01:13:47,166\r\nbecome if not frequent...\r\n\r\n1059\r\n01:13:48,250 --> 01:13:50,083\r\nmore frequent.\r\n\r\n1060\r\n01:13:51,666 --> 01:13:56,375\r\nBright Boy,\r\nyou are that one in 10,000.\r\n\r\n1061\r\n01:13:56,375 --> 01:13:59,916\r\nThe name of the game is keep up,\r\nnot catch up, nigger.\r\n\r\n1062\r\n01:13:59,916 --> 01:14:02,083\r\n[men laughing]\r\n\r\n1063\r\n01:14:12,083 --> 01:14:14,916\r\n- Whoa!\r\n- [whinnying]\r\n\r\n1064\r\n01:14:14,916 --> 01:14:18,416\r\n- Touch your guns, you die.\r\n- Everybody, calm down!\r\n\r\n1065\r\n01:14:18,416 --> 01:14:20,583\r\nNow I saw the whole thing.\r\nNo harm done.\r\n\r\n1066\r\n01:14:20,583 --> 01:14:23,916\r\n- Are you kidding me?\r\nThis nigger just...\r\n- I said no harm done!\r\n\r\n1067\r\n01:14:23,916 --> 01:14:26,791\r\nNow take your hand\r\noff your pistol!\r\n\r\n1068\r\n01:14:27,708 --> 01:14:30,708\r\nButch, that means you too.\r\n\r\n1069\r\n01:14:31,708 --> 01:14:34,916\r\nEverybody stop\r\nantagonizing my guest.\r\n\r\n1070\r\n01:14:36,250 --> 01:14:39,250\r\nHoot! Get back up on your horse.\r\n\r\n1071\r\n01:14:39,250 --> 01:14:40,916\r\nHe broke my collarbone!\r\n\r\n1072\r\n01:14:40,916 --> 01:14:45,250\r\nFor God's sake, somebody please\r\nhelp Hoot here back up on his\r\ngoddamn horse.\r\n\r\n1073\r\n01:14:45,250 --> 01:14:48,541\r\n- [man] Yessir, boss.\r\n- Oh, now you are\r\none lucky nigger.\r\n\r\n1074\r\n01:14:49,750 --> 01:14:51,333\r\nYou better listen to your boss,\r\nwhite boy.\r\n\r\n1075\r\n01:14:51,333 --> 01:14:53,958\r\nOh, I'm gonna go walking\r\nin the moonlight with you.\r\n\r\n1076\r\n01:14:53,958 --> 01:14:55,916\r\nYou wanna hold my hand?\r\n\r\n1077\r\n01:14:56,541 --> 01:14:58,333\r\n[chuckling]\r\n\r\n1078\r\n01:14:58,333 --> 01:15:00,416\r\n[rap song playing]\r\n\r\n1079\r\n01:15:00,416 --> 01:15:02,250\r\n[clucking]\r\n\r\n1080\r\n01:15:02,250 --> 01:15:05,166\r\nWillie, take us home.\r\n\r\n1081\r\n01:15:07,208 --> 01:15:09,458\r\n[man] Start moving!\r\n\r\n1082\r\n01:15:15,666 --> 01:15:17,083\r\nHead 'em out!\r\n\r\n1083\r\n01:15:25,166 --> 01:15:28,666\r\n♪ I need a hundred black\r\ncoffins for a hundred bad men ♪\r\n\r\n1084\r\n01:15:28,666 --> 01:15:31,750\r\n♪ A hundred black graves\r\nso I can lay they ass in ♪\r\n\r\n1085\r\n01:15:31,750 --> 01:15:35,083\r\n♪ I need a hundred black\r\npreachers with a black sermon\r\nto tell ♪\r\n\r\n1086\r\n01:15:35,083 --> 01:15:38,291\r\n♪ From a hundred black bibles\r\nwhile we send them all\r\nto hell ♪\r\n\r\n1087\r\n01:15:38,291 --> 01:15:42,916\r\n- ♪ I need a hundred\r\nblack coffins ♪\r\n- ♪ Black coffins ♪\r\n\r\n1088\r\n01:15:42,916 --> 01:15:45,208\r\n- ♪ Black coffins ♪\r\n- ♪ Oh, Lord! ♪\r\n\r\n1089\r\n01:15:45,208 --> 01:15:47,833\r\n- ♪ I need a hundred\r\nblack coffins ♪\r\n- ♪ Black coffins ♪\r\n\r\n1090\r\n01:15:47,833 --> 01:15:49,708\r\n- ♪ Black coffins ♪\r\n- ♪ Oh, Lord! ♪\r\n\r\n1091\r\n01:15:49,708 --> 01:15:51,416\r\n- ♪ Oh, Lord! ♪\r\n- ♪ Oh, Lord! ♪\r\n\r\n1092\r\n01:15:51,416 --> 01:15:54,208\r\n- ♪ Black coffins ♪\r\n- ♪ I need a hundred ♪\r\n\r\n1093\r\n01:16:02,500 --> 01:16:04,250\r\nYou got a problem\r\nwith your eyeball, boy?\r\n\r\n1094\r\n01:16:04,250 --> 01:16:05,583\r\nNo, sir.\r\n\r\n1095\r\n01:16:05,583 --> 01:16:07,291\r\nYou want a boot heel in it?\r\n\r\n1096\r\n01:16:08,416 --> 01:16:09,500\r\nNo, sir.\r\n\r\n1097\r\n01:16:09,500 --> 01:16:12,666\r\nThen you keep your\r\ngoddamn eyeballs off me.\r\n\r\n1098\r\n01:16:12,666 --> 01:16:15,916\r\nYou flash that bad look at me\r\nagain, I'll give you a reason\r\nnot to like me.\r\n\r\n1099\r\n01:16:15,916 --> 01:16:18,125\r\nNow move, nigger!\r\n\r\n1100\r\n01:16:18,125 --> 01:16:19,541\r\n[horse snorting]\r\n\r\n1101\r\n01:16:19,541 --> 01:16:21,875\r\nYou niggers are gonna\r\nunderstand something about me.\r\n\r\n1102\r\n01:16:21,875 --> 01:16:23,875\r\nI'm worse than any of these\r\nwhite men here.\r\n\r\n1103\r\n01:16:23,875 --> 01:16:27,750\r\nYou get the molasses out your\r\nass, you keep your goddamn\r\neyeballs off me.\r\n\r\n1104\r\n01:16:27,750 --> 01:16:30,916\r\nHe is a rambunctious sort,\r\nain't he? [Chuckles]\r\n\r\n1105\r\n01:16:30,916 --> 01:16:32,416\r\nIndeed.\r\n\r\n1106\r\n01:16:34,833 --> 01:16:38,333\r\nMay we stop for a moment so I\r\nmay put a word in my man's ear?\r\n\r\n1107\r\n01:16:38,333 --> 01:16:42,250\r\nYou know, I'm expecting to fall\r\nin love once I see the specimens\r\nat Candyland,\r\n\r\n1108\r\n01:16:42,250 --> 01:16:45,458\r\nso before that moment,\r\nit would be good if I could have\r\n\r\n1109\r\n01:16:45,458 --> 01:16:50,083\r\na confidential strategy meeting\r\nwith my confidant.\r\n\r\n1110\r\n01:16:52,875 --> 01:16:54,666\r\nYou mind telling me\r\nwhat the hell you doing?\r\n\r\n1111\r\n01:16:54,666 --> 01:16:57,083\r\nI confirmed that\r\nBroomhilda's at Candyland.\r\n\r\n1112\r\n01:17:00,875 --> 01:17:03,500\r\n- You're sure it's her?\r\n- He didn't call her by name,\r\n\r\n1113\r\n01:17:03,500 --> 01:17:07,166\r\nbut she's a young lady,\r\nwhip marks on her back\r\nand speaks German.\r\n\r\n1114\r\n01:17:07,166 --> 01:17:09,083\r\nNow, while it's\r\nnot wise to assume,\r\n\r\n1115\r\n01:17:09,083 --> 01:17:11,583\r\nin this instance,\r\nI think it's pretty safe.\r\n\r\n1116\r\n01:17:11,583 --> 01:17:16,500\r\nPoint being, don't get\r\nso carried away with your\r\nretribution.\r\n\r\n1117\r\n01:17:16,500 --> 01:17:18,500\r\nYou lose sight\r\nof why we're here.\r\n\r\n1118\r\n01:17:18,500 --> 01:17:20,708\r\n- You think I lost\r\nsight of that?\r\n- Yes, I do.\r\n\r\n1119\r\n01:17:20,708 --> 01:17:23,416\r\nStop antagonizing Candie.\r\n\r\n1120\r\n01:17:23,416 --> 01:17:28,541\r\nYou're going to blow this whole\r\ncharade, or more than likely get\r\nus both killed.\r\n\r\n1121\r\n01:17:28,541 --> 01:17:33,416\r\nAnd I, for one, don't intend\r\nto die in Chickasaw County,\r\nMississippi, USA.\r\n\r\n1122\r\n01:17:33,416 --> 01:17:36,333\r\nI'm not antagonizing him.\r\nI'm intriguing him.\r\n\r\n1123\r\n01:17:36,333 --> 01:17:40,083\r\nYou're yelling abuse\r\nat these poor slaves.\r\n\r\n1124\r\n01:17:40,083 --> 01:17:45,708\r\nI recall the man who had me kill\r\nanother man in front of his son\r\n\r\n1125\r\n01:17:45,708 --> 01:17:47,708\r\nand he didn't bat a eye.\r\n\r\n1126\r\n01:17:48,916 --> 01:17:50,208\r\nYou remember that?\r\n\r\n1127\r\n01:17:52,333 --> 01:17:53,833\r\nYeah, of course I remember.\r\n\r\n1128\r\n01:17:53,833 --> 01:17:58,333\r\nWhat you said was that\r\nthis is my world...\r\n\r\n1129\r\n01:17:58,333 --> 01:18:01,250\r\nand in my world\r\nyou gotta get dirty.\r\n\r\n1130\r\n01:18:01,250 --> 01:18:04,333\r\nSo that's what I'm doing.\r\nI'm gettin' dirty.\r\n\r\n1131\r\n01:18:07,750 --> 01:18:11,125\r\nWell, you're paraphrasing a tad,\r\nbut...\r\n\r\n1132\r\n01:18:12,333 --> 01:18:15,041\r\nthat was the general gist.\r\n\r\n1133\r\n01:18:15,041 --> 01:18:16,333\r\n[sighing]\r\n\r\n1134\r\n01:18:18,125 --> 01:18:19,916\r\nSee you at Candyland.\r\n\r\n1135\r\n01:18:27,416 --> 01:18:30,166\r\n[Django]\r\nAll right, niggers, back at it.\r\n\r\n1136\r\n01:18:31,375 --> 01:18:33,583\r\nThat means you too, Moonlight.\r\n\r\n1137\r\n01:18:42,208 --> 01:18:44,958\r\n[dogs barking nearby]\r\n\r\n1138\r\n01:19:10,250 --> 01:19:12,291\r\n[dogs barking loudly]\r\n\r\n1139\r\n01:19:20,791 --> 01:19:23,791\r\n[Calvin] I'll be. D'Artagnan!\r\n\r\n1140\r\n01:19:23,791 --> 01:19:27,208\r\nNow, boy, why do a\r\nfool thing like run off?\r\n\r\n1141\r\n01:19:27,208 --> 01:19:29,416\r\nI can't fight no more,\r\nMonsieur Candie.\r\n\r\n1142\r\n01:19:29,416 --> 01:19:30,833\r\n[Calvin] Yes, you can.\r\n\r\n1143\r\n01:19:30,833 --> 01:19:34,541\r\nYou might not be able to win,\r\nbut your ass can fight.\r\n\r\n1144\r\n01:19:34,541 --> 01:19:37,250\r\nMr. Stonesipher, would you\r\nplease shut these goddamn dogs\r\nup?\r\n\r\n1145\r\n01:19:37,250 --> 01:19:40,083\r\n- I cannot hear myself think!\r\n- Quiet down, Marsha!\r\n\r\n1146\r\n01:19:40,083 --> 01:19:42,250\r\nMarsha, hush up! Marsha!\r\n\r\n1147\r\n01:19:42,250 --> 01:19:43,875\r\nHush up! Hey!\r\n\r\n1148\r\n01:19:43,875 --> 01:19:46,750\r\nGet these goddamn dogs\r\naway from this nigger!\r\n\r\n1149\r\n01:19:46,750 --> 01:19:49,125\r\n[dogs whining]\r\n\r\n1150\r\n01:19:56,041 --> 01:19:59,750\r\nCome on now, boy...\r\nget on out that tree.\r\n\r\n1151\r\n01:19:59,750 --> 01:20:01,916\r\nYessir.\r\n\r\n1152\r\n01:20:01,916 --> 01:20:03,750\r\n[dogs resume barking]\r\n\r\n1153\r\n01:20:07,875 --> 01:20:09,458\r\n[barking stops]\r\n\r\n1154\r\n01:20:23,916 --> 01:20:26,250\r\nHow long was he loose?\r\n\r\n1155\r\n01:20:26,250 --> 01:20:29,666\r\n[speech slurred]\r\nA night. Day.\r\n\r\n1156\r\n01:20:29,666 --> 01:20:31,458\r\nHalf the other night.\r\n\r\n1157\r\n01:20:32,458 --> 01:20:34,166\r\nHow far he get off the property?\r\n\r\n1158\r\n01:20:34,166 --> 01:20:35,958\r\n'Bout 20 miles off the prop.\r\n\r\n1159\r\n01:20:35,958 --> 01:20:39,291\r\n- Pretty far considering\r\nthat limp he got.\r\n- Hm.\r\n\r\n1160\r\n01:20:40,750 --> 01:20:44,500\r\nMr. Moguy, who was D'Artagnan\r\nsupposed to fight on Friday?\r\n\r\n1161\r\n01:20:44,500 --> 01:20:47,083\r\nOne-a this new lot.\r\n\r\n1162\r\n01:20:47,083 --> 01:20:50,208\r\nWell, way he looks now, a blind\r\nIndian wouldn't bet a bead on\r\nhim.\r\n\r\n1163\r\n01:20:50,208 --> 01:20:52,583\r\n[D'Artagnan weeping] Please,\r\nMonsieur Candie, I ain't got it\r\nin me no more.\r\n\r\n1164\r\n01:20:52,583 --> 01:20:54,500\r\n- Now, now, now, now, now.\r\n- I can't...\r\n\r\n1165\r\n01:20:54,500 --> 01:20:57,083\r\nNow, no beggin'.\r\n\r\n1166\r\n01:20:57,083 --> 01:20:59,708\r\nNo playin' on my soft heart.\r\n\r\n1167\r\n01:21:02,750 --> 01:21:05,708\r\n- You in trouble now, son.\r\n- Yessir.\r\n\r\n1168\r\n01:21:08,416 --> 01:21:12,125\r\nI done paid $500 for you.\r\n\r\n1169\r\n01:21:12,125 --> 01:21:16,916\r\nWhen I pay $500, then I expect\r\nto get five fights out of a\r\nnigger\r\n\r\n1170\r\n01:21:16,916 --> 01:21:19,750\r\n- 'fore he roll over\r\nand play dead.\r\n- Sir.\r\n\r\n1171\r\n01:21:19,750 --> 01:21:23,541\r\nYou have to understand that\r\nI'm runnin' a business here.\r\n\r\n1172\r\n01:21:23,541 --> 01:21:26,750\r\n- You fought three fights.\r\n- But I won every one.\r\n\r\n1173\r\n01:21:26,750 --> 01:21:28,333\r\nYes, you did. Yes, you did.\r\n\r\n1174\r\n01:21:28,333 --> 01:21:31,541\r\nBut that last one, you muddled\r\nthe line between winnin' and\r\nlosin'.\r\n\r\n1175\r\n01:21:31,541 --> 01:21:32,750\r\nYessir.\r\n\r\n1176\r\n01:21:35,250 --> 01:21:37,250\r\nStill, the fact remains:\r\n\r\n1177\r\n01:21:37,250 --> 01:21:41,125\r\nI pay $500,\r\nI want five goddamn fights!\r\n\r\n1178\r\n01:21:41,125 --> 01:21:43,916\r\nSo what about my $500, huh?\r\n\r\n1179\r\n01:21:45,583 --> 01:21:47,750\r\nWhat about my $500?\r\n\r\n1180\r\n01:21:49,166 --> 01:21:50,750\r\nYou gonna reimburse me?\r\n\r\n1181\r\n01:21:56,583 --> 01:21:59,166\r\nYou even know\r\nwhat \"reimburse\" means?\r\n\r\n1182\r\n01:21:59,166 --> 01:22:01,375\r\n- [laughing]\r\n- [Calvin] Huh?\r\n\r\n1183\r\n01:22:02,958 --> 01:22:05,666\r\n[laughter continues]\r\n\r\n1184\r\n01:22:07,583 --> 01:22:09,375\r\nI'll reimburse you!\r\n\r\n1185\r\n01:22:12,875 --> 01:22:14,375\r\nYou will?\r\n\r\n1186\r\n01:22:15,375 --> 01:22:17,083\r\nYep.\r\n\r\n1187\r\n01:22:19,708 --> 01:22:22,500\r\nYou'll pay $500\r\n\r\n1188\r\n01:22:22,500 --> 01:22:26,208\r\nfor practically a one-eyed old\r\nJoe ain't fit to push a broom?\r\n\r\n1189\r\n01:22:26,208 --> 01:22:27,500\r\nNo, he won't.\r\n\r\n1190\r\n01:22:29,583 --> 01:22:31,791\r\nHe just tired of you\r\ntoyin' with him is all.\r\n\r\n1191\r\n01:22:32,583 --> 01:22:34,583\r\nMatter of fact, so am I.\r\n\r\n1192\r\n01:22:34,583 --> 01:22:37,083\r\nBut we ain't payin' a penny\r\nfor that pickaninny.\r\n\r\n1193\r\n01:22:37,083 --> 01:22:39,291\r\nAin't got no use for him.\r\nAin't that right, doc?\r\n\r\n1194\r\n01:22:40,833 --> 01:22:42,208\r\nYou heard him.\r\n\r\n1195\r\n01:22:51,250 --> 01:22:55,041\r\nYou're gonna have to excuse Mr.\r\nStonesipher's slack-jawed gaze.\r\n\r\n1196\r\n01:22:55,041 --> 01:22:59,416\r\nHe ain't never seen a nigger\r\nlike you ever in his life.\r\n\r\n1197\r\n01:22:59,416 --> 01:23:01,833\r\nAin't that right,\r\nMr. Stonesipher?\r\n\r\n1198\r\n01:23:03,833 --> 01:23:05,416\r\nThat right.\r\n\r\n1199\r\n01:23:06,250 --> 01:23:07,833\r\n[Calvin] For that matter...\r\n\r\n1200\r\n01:23:08,916 --> 01:23:10,625\r\nnor have I.\r\n\r\n1201\r\n01:23:16,625 --> 01:23:18,916\r\nNow...\r\n\r\n1202\r\n01:23:18,916 --> 01:23:22,250\r\nseein' as you won't pay\r\na penny for this pickaninny\r\nhere...\r\n\r\n1203\r\n01:23:24,625 --> 01:23:28,083\r\nyou won't mind me handlin'\r\nthis nigger any way I see fit?\r\n\r\n1204\r\n01:23:28,958 --> 01:23:30,750\r\nHe's your nigger.\r\n\r\n1205\r\n01:23:34,375 --> 01:23:37,250\r\nMr. Stonesipher?\r\n\r\n1206\r\n01:23:37,250 --> 01:23:41,250\r\nLet Marsha and her bitches send\r\nD'Artagnan to nigger heaven.\r\n\r\n1207\r\n01:23:41,250 --> 01:23:46,250\r\n- Marsha!\r\nMarsha, hey, get him!\r\n- [barks echoing]\r\n\r\n1208\r\n01:23:47,500 --> 01:23:49,958\r\nGet 'im, get 'im!\r\n\r\n1209\r\n01:23:50,875 --> 01:23:53,583\r\n- Yeah!\r\n- Whoo!\r\n\r\n1210\r\n01:23:53,583 --> 01:23:55,083\r\nWhoo-ee!\r\n\r\n1211\r\n01:24:00,000 --> 01:24:03,000\r\n- [dogs snarling]\r\n- [screaming]\r\n\r\n1212\r\n01:24:23,291 --> 01:24:25,500\r\nYour boss looks a little\r\ngreen around the gills\r\n\r\n1213\r\n01:24:25,500 --> 01:24:27,500\r\nfor a blood sport\r\nlike nigger fighting.\r\n\r\n1214\r\n01:24:27,500 --> 01:24:32,750\r\nNah, he just ain't used to\r\nseein' a man ripped apart\r\nby dogs is all.\r\n\r\n1215\r\n01:24:33,125 --> 01:24:34,541\r\nHm.\r\n\r\n1216\r\n01:24:35,375 --> 01:24:36,916\r\nYou are used to it?\r\n\r\n1217\r\n01:24:36,916 --> 01:24:41,333\r\n- I'm just a little more\r\nused to Americans than he is.\r\n- Hm.\r\n\r\n1218\r\n01:24:41,333 --> 01:24:44,916\r\nNow, Monsieur Candie...\r\n\r\n1219\r\n01:24:44,916 --> 01:24:46,625\r\nwhenever you're ready.\r\n\r\n1220\r\n01:24:46,625 --> 01:24:51,250\r\nWe rode five hours so you could\r\nshow off your stock. Let's get\r\nto it.\r\n\r\n1221\r\n01:24:53,250 --> 01:24:57,750\r\n'Cause as of now, if he's\r\nan example, I ain't impressed.\r\n\r\n1222\r\n01:24:59,750 --> 01:25:01,333\r\nFollow me.\r\n\r\n1223\r\n01:25:13,583 --> 01:25:15,666\r\n[snarling]\r\n\r\n1224\r\n01:25:21,250 --> 01:25:22,958\r\n[clucking]\r\n\r\n1225\r\n01:25:22,958 --> 01:25:24,250\r\n[nickering]\r\n\r\n1226\r\n01:26:58,458 --> 01:27:01,375\r\nLine 'em up to\r\nthe left here now, boy.\r\n\r\n1227\r\n01:27:02,875 --> 01:27:04,375\r\nStand up straight, now!\r\n\r\n1228\r\n01:27:05,250 --> 01:27:06,750\r\nGet up there.\r\n\r\n1229\r\n01:27:06,750 --> 01:27:09,458\r\nGet up there, boy. Come on.\r\n\r\n1230\r\n01:27:09,458 --> 01:27:11,250\r\nGive me a line!\r\nGive me a line!\r\n\r\n1231\r\n01:27:11,250 --> 01:27:13,583\r\nGet in line there!\r\nStraighten up!\r\n\r\n1232\r\n01:28:11,166 --> 01:28:13,125\r\n[indistinct chatter]\r\n\r\n1233\r\n01:28:13,125 --> 01:28:14,750\r\nHello! Stephen, my boy!\r\n\r\n1234\r\n01:28:14,750 --> 01:28:17,625\r\nYeah, yeah, yeah.\r\nHello, my ass.\r\n\r\n1235\r\n01:28:17,625 --> 01:28:20,750\r\nWho this nigger\r\nup on that nag?\r\n\r\n1236\r\n01:28:20,750 --> 01:28:24,250\r\nStephen, you have nails for\r\nbreakfast? What's-a matter?\r\nWhy you so ornery?\r\n\r\n1237\r\n01:28:24,250 --> 01:28:26,958\r\n- You miss me, huh?\r\n- Oh, yessir. [Laughs]\r\n\r\n1238\r\n01:28:26,958 --> 01:28:30,250\r\nI miss you like a hog miss slop!\r\n\r\n1239\r\n01:28:30,250 --> 01:28:34,666\r\n- Like a baby miss mammy's\r\ntitty.\r\n- [all chuckling]\r\n\r\n1240\r\n01:28:34,666 --> 01:28:38,583\r\nI miss you like I misses\r\na rock in my shoe.\r\n\r\n1241\r\n01:28:38,583 --> 01:28:40,791\r\n[laughing]\r\n\r\n1242\r\n01:28:40,791 --> 01:28:45,583\r\nNow, I axed you:\r\nWho this nigger on that nag?\r\n\r\n1243\r\n01:28:45,583 --> 01:28:48,458\r\nHey, Snowball?\r\n\r\n1244\r\n01:28:48,458 --> 01:28:52,166\r\nWanna know my name or the name\r\nof my horse, you ask me.\r\n\r\n1245\r\n01:28:52,166 --> 01:28:54,875\r\nJust who the hell you callin'\r\n\"Snowball,\" horse boy?\r\n\r\n1246\r\n01:28:54,875 --> 01:28:57,583\r\nI'll snatch your black ass\r\noff that nag there and in\r\nthe mud so fast,\r\n\r\n1247\r\n01:28:57,583 --> 01:29:00,833\r\n- make your head spin.\r\n- Whoa, whoa, whoa! Stephen,\r\nStephen, Stephen.\r\n\r\n1248\r\n01:29:00,833 --> 01:29:05,208\r\nLet's keep it funny.\r\nDjango here's a Freeman.\r\n\r\n1249\r\n01:29:05,208 --> 01:29:07,625\r\n- This nigger here?\r\n- That nigger there.\r\n\r\n1250\r\n01:29:07,625 --> 01:29:10,083\r\nLet me at least\r\nintroduce the two of you.\r\n\r\n1251\r\n01:29:10,083 --> 01:29:14,208\r\nDjango, this is another cheeky\r\nblack bugger like yourself,\r\nStephen.\r\n\r\n1252\r\n01:29:14,208 --> 01:29:17,500\r\nStephen, this here's Django.\r\nYou two oughta hate each other.\r\n\r\n1253\r\n01:29:17,500 --> 01:29:21,583\r\nCalvin, just who the hell is\r\nthis nigger you feels the need\r\nto entertain?\r\n\r\n1254\r\n01:29:21,583 --> 01:29:25,583\r\nDjango and his friend\r\nin gray here, Dr. Schultz,\r\nare customers.\r\n\r\n1255\r\n01:29:25,583 --> 01:29:29,583\r\nAnd they are our guests,\r\nStephen. And you, you old\r\ndecrepit bastard,\r\n\r\n1256\r\n01:29:29,583 --> 01:29:31,083\r\noughta show them\r\nevery hospitality.\r\n\r\n1257\r\n01:29:31,083 --> 01:29:33,625\r\n- You understand that?\r\n- Yessir. Him I understand.\r\n\r\n1258\r\n01:29:33,625 --> 01:29:35,416\r\nBut I don't know why I got to\r\ntake lip off this nigger.\r\n\r\n1259\r\n01:29:35,416 --> 01:29:38,333\r\nYou don't have to know why.\r\nDo you understand?\r\n\r\n1260\r\n01:29:39,125 --> 01:29:40,750\r\nYessir. I understand.\r\n\r\n1261\r\n01:29:40,750 --> 01:29:43,333\r\nWell, good.\r\nThey're spendin' the night.\r\n\r\n1262\r\n01:29:43,333 --> 01:29:45,750\r\nGo up in the guest bedrooms\r\nand get two ready.\r\n\r\n1263\r\n01:29:46,750 --> 01:29:48,458\r\nHe gonna stay in The Big House?\r\n\r\n1264\r\n01:29:48,458 --> 01:29:50,625\r\nStephen, he's a slaver.\r\nIt's different.\r\n\r\n1265\r\n01:29:50,625 --> 01:29:53,666\r\n- In The Big House?\r\n- Well, you got a problem\r\nwith that?\r\n\r\n1266\r\n01:29:53,666 --> 01:29:56,125\r\nOh, no.\r\nI ain't got no problem with it,\r\n\r\n1267\r\n01:29:56,125 --> 01:29:58,333\r\nif you ain't got no problem with\r\nburnin' the bed, the sheets,\r\n\r\n1268\r\n01:29:58,333 --> 01:30:00,750\r\nthe pillowcases, everything else\r\nwhen this black-ass\r\nmotherfucker's gone!\r\n\r\n1269\r\n01:30:00,750 --> 01:30:03,250\r\nThat is my problem!\r\nThey are mine to burn!\r\n\r\n1270\r\n01:30:03,250 --> 01:30:05,625\r\nNow your problem right now\r\nis makin' a good impression!\r\n\r\n1271\r\n01:30:05,625 --> 01:30:07,666\r\nAnd I want you to start solvin'\r\nthat problem right now\r\n\r\n1272\r\n01:30:07,666 --> 01:30:09,583\r\nand get them\r\ngoddamn rooms ready!\r\n\r\n1273\r\n01:30:11,500 --> 01:30:13,583\r\nYessir, Monsieur Candie.\r\n\r\n1274\r\n01:30:14,875 --> 01:30:16,375\r\nGo on, now.\r\n\r\n1275\r\n01:30:16,375 --> 01:30:19,583\r\nCan't believe you brought a\r\nnigger to stay in The Big House.\r\n\r\n1276\r\n01:30:19,583 --> 01:30:21,083\r\nYour daddy rollin' over\r\nin his goddamned grave.\r\n\r\n1277\r\n01:30:21,083 --> 01:30:24,750\r\nMan, the lip on him. Whoo!\r\nHe's gettin' worse and worse.\r\n\r\n1278\r\n01:30:24,750 --> 01:30:26,083\r\nNow...\r\n\r\n1279\r\n01:30:26,083 --> 01:30:30,708\r\nWhere is my beautiful sister?!\r\n\r\n1280\r\n01:30:30,708 --> 01:30:33,958\r\nThere she is!\r\nWhoo-hoo-hoo-hoo!\r\n\r\n1281\r\n01:30:33,958 --> 01:30:39,416\r\nDr. Schultz, this attractive\r\nSouthern belle is my widowed\r\nsister.\r\n\r\n1282\r\n01:30:39,416 --> 01:30:43,583\r\nDarlin', you are\r\na tonic for tired eyes.\r\n\r\n1283\r\n01:30:44,708 --> 01:30:48,125\r\nMay I present to you\r\nLara Lee Candie-Fitzwilly.\r\n\r\n1284\r\n01:30:48,125 --> 01:30:51,750\r\nChester, Rodney, Chicken Charly.\r\nY'all get your ass over by that\r\npen.\r\n\r\n1285\r\n01:30:51,750 --> 01:30:54,083\r\n- Come on, Charly. Come on, now!\r\n- Let's go.\r\n\r\n1286\r\n01:30:54,083 --> 01:30:55,208\r\nYou know where it is.\r\n\r\n1287\r\n01:30:55,208 --> 01:30:57,083\r\nLike you on a rope!\r\n\r\n1288\r\n01:30:58,208 --> 01:31:01,500\r\nNiggers don't walk around here,\r\nniggers run!\r\n\r\n1289\r\n01:31:01,500 --> 01:31:04,791\r\n- Monsieur Candie?\r\n- Hm?\r\n\r\n1290\r\n01:31:04,791 --> 01:31:08,750\r\nYeah. About that matter about\r\nthe nigger girl you were talking\r\nabout?\r\n\r\n1291\r\n01:31:08,750 --> 01:31:13,333\r\n- Nigger gal?\r\n- Yeah, I believe you mentioned\r\nshe spoke German.\r\n\r\n1292\r\n01:31:13,333 --> 01:31:15,750\r\nAh, yes! Hildi, what about her?\r\n\r\n1293\r\n01:31:15,750 --> 01:31:20,041\r\nDo you think before the\r\ndemonstration, you could\r\nsend her around to my room?\r\n\r\n1294\r\n01:31:20,041 --> 01:31:24,416\r\n[laughs] You little dickens,\r\nyou. I don't see why not.\r\n\r\n1295\r\n01:31:24,416 --> 01:31:28,041\r\nStephen, when you get through\r\nshowin' them to their rooms,\r\ngo fetch Hildi,\r\n\r\n1296\r\n01:31:28,041 --> 01:31:30,125\r\nget her cleaned up\r\nand smellin' real nice,\r\n\r\n1297\r\n01:31:30,125 --> 01:31:31,750\r\nand sent over to\r\nDr. Schultz's room here.\r\n\r\n1298\r\n01:31:31,750 --> 01:31:33,541\r\nActually, Monsieur Candie, sir,\r\n\r\n1299\r\n01:31:33,541 --> 01:31:36,250\r\nthere's-a somethin'\r\nI ain't told you 'bout yet.\r\n\r\n1300\r\n01:31:36,250 --> 01:31:40,125\r\n- What?\r\n- [stammers] Uh, Hildi\r\nin the Hot Box.\r\n\r\n1301\r\n01:31:41,541 --> 01:31:42,833\r\n[Calvin] What's she doin' there?\r\n\r\n1302\r\n01:31:42,833 --> 01:31:45,750\r\n[Stephen] What you think she\r\ndoin' there in the Hot Box?\r\n\r\n1303\r\n01:31:45,750 --> 01:31:47,375\r\nShe bein' punished.\r\n\r\n1304\r\n01:31:47,375 --> 01:31:49,791\r\n- [Calvin] What she do?\r\n- [Stephen] She run off again.\r\n\r\n1305\r\n01:31:49,791 --> 01:31:52,666\r\nJesus Christ, Stephen, how many\r\npeople ran away while I was\r\ngone?\r\n\r\n1306\r\n01:31:52,666 --> 01:31:55,458\r\n- Two.\r\n- When did she go?\r\n\r\n1307\r\n01:31:55,458 --> 01:31:58,083\r\nLast night. They brung her back\r\nthis morning.\r\n\r\n1308\r\n01:31:58,083 --> 01:32:01,583\r\nHow bad did Stonesipher's dogs\r\ntear her up?\r\n\r\n1309\r\n01:32:01,583 --> 01:32:05,375\r\n[Stephen] Lucky for her, they\r\nwas out chasin' D'Artagnan's\r\nass.\r\n\r\n1310\r\n01:32:05,375 --> 01:32:09,875\r\nBill and Cody went lookin' for\r\nher, found her, brung her back.\r\n\r\n1311\r\n01:32:09,875 --> 01:32:12,958\r\nNow, she a little beat-up.\r\nBut she done that to her own\r\ndamn self\r\n\r\n1312\r\n01:32:12,958 --> 01:32:14,208\r\nrunnin' through them\r\ndamn bushes and shit.\r\n\r\n1313\r\n01:32:14,208 --> 01:32:16,083\r\n[Calvin]\r\nHow long she been in the box?\r\n\r\n1314\r\n01:32:16,083 --> 01:32:19,083\r\n[Stephen] How long you think\r\nshe been in there? All damn day.\r\n\r\n1315\r\n01:32:19,083 --> 01:32:21,833\r\nAnd the little bitch got\r\nten more days to be in there.\r\n\r\n1316\r\n01:32:21,833 --> 01:32:25,208\r\n- Still, take her out.\r\n- Take her out? Why?\r\n\r\n1317\r\n01:32:25,208 --> 01:32:29,250\r\nBecause I said so, that's why.\r\nDr. Schultz is my guest.\r\n\r\n1318\r\n01:32:29,250 --> 01:32:33,583\r\nHildi is my nigger.\r\nSouthern hospitality dictates\r\nI make her available to him.\r\n\r\n1319\r\n01:32:33,583 --> 01:32:36,833\r\n- But, Monsieur Candie,\r\nshe run off.\r\n- Jesus Christ, Stephen.\r\n\r\n1320\r\n01:32:36,833 --> 01:32:39,500\r\nWhat is the point of havin'\r\na nigger that speaks German\r\n\r\n1321\r\n01:32:39,500 --> 01:32:42,291\r\nif you can't wheel 'em out\r\nwhen you have a German guest?\r\n\r\n1322\r\n01:32:42,291 --> 01:32:46,583\r\nNow, I realize it is\r\ninconvenient, but still,\r\nyou take her ass out.\r\n\r\n1323\r\n01:32:46,583 --> 01:32:47,791\r\nYessir.\r\n\r\n1324\r\n01:32:49,041 --> 01:32:51,791\r\n[Calvin] Lara Lee!\r\nWill you and Cora be responsible\r\n\r\n1325\r\n01:32:51,791 --> 01:32:55,416\r\nfor gettin' Hildi cleaned up\r\nand presentable for Dr. Schultz\r\nhere.\r\n\r\n1326\r\n01:32:55,416 --> 01:32:57,041\r\n[Lara Lee] Of course, darlin'.\r\n\r\n1327\r\n01:32:57,041 --> 01:32:58,416\r\nNow, gentlemen, I do apologize,\r\n\r\n1328\r\n01:32:58,416 --> 01:33:01,833\r\nbut I am weary from\r\nour travels beyond words.\r\n\r\n1329\r\n01:33:01,833 --> 01:33:05,041\r\nIt is time for me\r\nto rest my tired eyes.\r\n\r\n1330\r\n01:33:07,250 --> 01:33:09,541\r\n[clucking]\r\n\r\n1331\r\n01:33:09,541 --> 01:33:12,625\r\nY'all done heard the man!\r\nGet her ass up outta there!\r\n\r\n1332\r\n01:33:12,625 --> 01:33:15,041\r\nCora! Come here!\r\n\r\n1333\r\n01:33:15,041 --> 01:33:18,250\r\nGet over there and get her\r\ncleaned up, bring her back\r\nover here to Dr...\r\n\r\n1334\r\n01:33:18,250 --> 01:33:21,041\r\n- What he say your name is?\r\nShoots?\r\n- Schultz.\r\n\r\n1335\r\n01:33:21,041 --> 01:33:23,541\r\nSchultz. Get her back over here.\r\nHurry up, girl.\r\n\r\n1336\r\n01:33:23,541 --> 01:33:27,250\r\n- Yessir.\r\n- [soft guitar music plays]\r\n\r\n1337\r\n01:34:08,000 --> 01:34:10,000\r\n[Hildi screams]\r\n\r\n1338\r\n01:34:10,708 --> 01:34:13,500\r\nCome on, girl. Stand up.\r\n\r\n1339\r\n01:34:14,583 --> 01:34:16,083\r\n[Hildi yelling]\r\n\r\n1340\r\n01:34:16,083 --> 01:34:19,791\r\n[gasping, screaming]\r\n\r\n1341\r\n01:34:20,916 --> 01:34:23,500\r\n[sobbing]\r\n\r\n1342\r\n01:34:43,333 --> 01:34:47,125\r\nIs you comin' with me or is you\r\ngonna sleep in that little box\r\nover yonder?\r\n\r\n1343\r\n01:34:49,333 --> 01:34:52,541\r\n[slow-tempo song plays]\r\n\r\n1344\r\n01:34:55,750 --> 01:34:58,625\r\n[woman sings\r\nin foreign language]\r\n\r\n1345\r\n01:36:14,250 --> 01:36:15,541\r\n[exhales]\r\n\r\n1346\r\n01:36:22,125 --> 01:36:23,750\r\nHello, ladies.\r\n\r\n1347\r\n01:36:23,750 --> 01:36:27,250\r\nDr. Schultz. May I introduce\r\nto you Broomhilda?\r\n\r\n1348\r\n01:36:31,333 --> 01:36:33,916\r\nHildi, this is Dr. Schultz.\r\n\r\n1349\r\n01:36:35,041 --> 01:36:38,333\r\nIt's a pleasure to meet you,\r\nBroomhilda.\r\n\r\n1350\r\n01:36:38,333 --> 01:36:40,666\r\nI've heard a lot of\r\ngood things about you.\r\n\r\n1351\r\n01:36:40,666 --> 01:36:43,625\r\nWell, it's not every nigger\r\nspeaks German, don't ya know.\r\n\r\n1352\r\n01:36:43,625 --> 01:36:45,916\r\n- [chuckles]\r\n- [forced chuckle]\r\n\r\n1353\r\n01:36:46,875 --> 01:36:48,750\r\nAs I look at you now,\r\nBroomhilda,\r\n\r\n1354\r\n01:36:48,750 --> 01:36:54,250\r\nI can see all the passions\r\nyou inspire are completely\r\njustified.\r\n\r\n1355\r\n01:36:57,458 --> 01:36:59,875\r\nThe doctor here speaks German.\r\n\r\n1356\r\n01:37:01,666 --> 01:37:03,875\r\nAnd I've been informed\r\nyou do as well?\r\n\r\n1357\r\n01:37:05,083 --> 01:37:07,583\r\nGo ahead, girl.\r\nSpeak a little German.\r\n\r\n1358\r\n01:37:09,458 --> 01:37:13,250\r\n[speaking German]\r\n\r\n1359\r\n01:37:13,958 --> 01:37:15,666\r\nHa! [Laughs]\r\n\r\n1360\r\n01:37:15,666 --> 01:37:17,875\r\nAstonishing.\r\n\r\n1361\r\n01:37:17,875 --> 01:37:19,666\r\n[speaking German]\r\n\r\n1362\r\n01:37:24,500 --> 01:37:27,083\r\n- And I shall bring you...\r\n- [Schultz] Much obliged.\r\n\r\n1363\r\n01:37:36,416 --> 01:37:37,708\r\nJa.\r\n\r\n1364\r\n01:37:58,250 --> 01:37:59,916\r\n[speaks German]\r\n\r\n1365\r\n01:38:01,041 --> 01:38:02,541\r\nDon't be afraid.\r\n\r\n1366\r\n01:38:40,250 --> 01:38:43,166\r\nHm. Pardon.\r\n\r\n1367\r\n01:38:50,583 --> 01:38:52,083\r\nDanke.\r\n\r\n1368\r\n01:39:35,750 --> 01:39:37,541\r\n[chuckling]\r\n\r\n1369\r\n01:40:37,250 --> 01:40:39,083\r\nHey, Little Trouble Maker.\r\n\r\n1370\r\n01:40:39,500 --> 01:40:41,291\r\n[gasping]\r\n\r\n1371\r\n01:40:43,541 --> 01:40:44,916\r\n[moaning]\r\n\r\n1372\r\n01:40:47,500 --> 01:40:52,083\r\nYou silver-tongued devil, you.\r\n\r\n1373\r\n01:40:52,083 --> 01:40:53,791\r\n- Hurry up, girl.\r\n- These ready, Miss Cora.\r\n\r\n1374\r\n01:40:53,791 --> 01:40:55,500\r\nNo, no, no,\r\nthey drinkin' tonight.\r\n\r\n1375\r\n01:40:55,500 --> 01:40:58,208\r\nGo downstairs, get the big jug\r\nwith the red stuff Monsieur\r\nCandie like, hear?\r\n\r\n1376\r\n01:40:58,208 --> 01:41:01,291\r\n- Get your big pretty ass\r\nout the way.\r\n- You know you like it.\r\n\r\n1377\r\n01:41:01,291 --> 01:41:04,500\r\n- [laughs] That's 'cause\r\nyou knows what I like.\r\n- Ooh!\r\n\r\n1378\r\n01:41:04,500 --> 01:41:06,541\r\nCome on with these biscuits,\r\ngirl.\r\n\r\n1379\r\n01:41:06,541 --> 01:41:12,291\r\nLook, Monsieur Candie, they were\r\nall fine specimens, no doubt\r\nabout it.\r\n\r\n1380\r\n01:41:12,291 --> 01:41:17,125\r\nBut the best three by far\r\nwere Samson...\r\n\r\n1381\r\n01:41:18,250 --> 01:41:19,958\r\n- What's that other one's name?\r\n- Goldie.\r\n\r\n1382\r\n01:41:19,958 --> 01:41:23,250\r\nGoldie. And Eskimo Joe.\r\n\r\n1383\r\n01:41:23,250 --> 01:41:26,333\r\nBy the way, why is\r\nhe called Eskimo Joe?\r\n\r\n1384\r\n01:41:26,333 --> 01:41:29,416\r\n[chuckles] You never know how\r\nthese nigger nicknames get\r\nstarted.\r\n\r\n1385\r\n01:41:29,416 --> 01:41:32,166\r\nHis name was Joe, maybe one day\r\nhe said he was cold. Who knows?\r\n\r\n1386\r\n01:41:32,166 --> 01:41:34,333\r\n[all laugh]\r\n\r\n1387\r\n01:41:35,750 --> 01:41:41,166\r\nWell, regardless, Samson's\r\nyour best. We all know that.\r\n\r\n1388\r\n01:41:41,166 --> 01:41:45,916\r\n- You will never sell him, and\r\nI can see why. He's a champion.\r\n- Hm-hm.\r\n\r\n1389\r\n01:41:46,625 --> 01:41:49,458\r\nAll three are champions.\r\n\r\n1390\r\n01:41:49,458 --> 01:41:51,750\r\nSamson's the champion.\r\n\r\n1391\r\n01:41:51,750 --> 01:41:53,750\r\nThem other two pretty good.\r\n\r\n1392\r\n01:41:54,791 --> 01:41:56,583\r\nCalvin, now what's\r\nthis nigger you let...\r\n\r\n1393\r\n01:41:56,583 --> 01:41:57,791\r\nIt's all right, it's all right.\r\n\r\n1394\r\n01:41:57,791 --> 01:42:00,083\r\nYou have to understand,\r\nMonsieur Candie,\r\n\r\n1395\r\n01:42:00,083 --> 01:42:03,458\r\nwhile admittedly a neophyte\r\nin the nigger fight game,\r\n\r\n1396\r\n01:42:03,458 --> 01:42:07,958\r\nI do have a little bit of a\r\nbackground in the European\r\ntraveling circus.\r\n\r\n1397\r\n01:42:07,958 --> 01:42:13,583\r\n- Is that right?\r\n- Hence, I have big ideas\r\nwhen it comes to presentation.\r\n\r\n1398\r\n01:42:13,583 --> 01:42:17,375\r\n- Hm.\r\n- I need something more\r\nthan just a big nigger.\r\n\r\n1399\r\n01:42:18,958 --> 01:42:21,083\r\nYeah, he needs to have panache.\r\n\r\n1400\r\n01:42:21,083 --> 01:42:24,416\r\n- Need to have what? What?\r\n- Panache. Uh...\r\n\r\n1401\r\n01:42:24,416 --> 01:42:27,416\r\n- A sense of showmanship.\r\n- Showmanship, yes.\r\n\r\n1402\r\n01:42:27,416 --> 01:42:30,916\r\nI want to be able to bill him\r\nas The Black Hercules.\r\n\r\n1403\r\n01:42:30,916 --> 01:42:32,583\r\n[all chuckling]\r\n\r\n1404\r\n01:42:32,583 --> 01:42:35,416\r\n- The Black Hercules,\r\nisn't that clever?\r\n- More like Nigger-les.\r\n\r\n1405\r\n01:42:35,416 --> 01:42:37,583\r\n[laughing]\r\n\r\n1406\r\n01:42:37,583 --> 01:42:43,583\r\nI said, and I quote:\r\n\"I would pay top dollar for...\r\n\r\n1407\r\n01:42:43,583 --> 01:42:46,500\r\n'the right nigger.'\".\r\n\r\n1408\r\n01:42:46,500 --> 01:42:51,000\r\nNow I'm not saying that Eskimo\r\nJoe is the wrong nigger, per se.\r\n\r\n1409\r\n01:42:51,000 --> 01:42:53,833\r\nBut is he right as rain?\r\n\r\n1410\r\n01:42:54,916 --> 01:42:56,541\r\nOh, Dr. Schultz,\r\n\r\n1411\r\n01:42:56,541 --> 01:43:00,458\r\nI will have you know there is\r\nno one in the nigger fight game\r\n\r\n1412\r\n01:43:00,458 --> 01:43:02,416\r\nthat appreciates\r\nthe value of showmanship\r\n\r\n1413\r\n01:43:02,416 --> 01:43:05,625\r\n- more than Monsieur\r\nCalvin J. Candie here.\r\n- Nobody.\r\n\r\n1414\r\n01:43:05,625 --> 01:43:07,541\r\nBut one must not forget\r\nthe most important thing\r\n\r\n1415\r\n01:43:07,541 --> 01:43:09,041\r\n- in the nigger fight game.\r\n- Hm-mm.\r\n\r\n1416\r\n01:43:09,041 --> 01:43:12,625\r\n- And that is a nigger\r\nthat can win fights.\r\n- Hm-mm.\r\n\r\n1417\r\n01:43:12,625 --> 01:43:17,041\r\nNow that should be your first,\r\nsecond, third, fourth, and fifth\r\nconcern.\r\n\r\n1418\r\n01:43:17,041 --> 01:43:19,250\r\nNow, after you have that,\r\nand you know you have that,\r\n\r\n1419\r\n01:43:19,250 --> 01:43:23,416\r\nthen you can start\r\nto implement a grand design.\r\n\r\n1420\r\n01:43:23,416 --> 01:43:26,250\r\nIn other words,\r\nfirst thing is first.\r\n\r\n1421\r\n01:43:26,250 --> 01:43:27,875\r\nFirst thing's first.\r\n\r\n1422\r\n01:43:32,500 --> 01:43:34,250\r\n[whispers in German]\r\n\r\n1423\r\n01:43:35,250 --> 01:43:38,875\r\nOoh! I see you two gettin' on.\r\n\r\n1424\r\n01:43:38,875 --> 01:43:41,458\r\nFamously.\r\n\r\n1425\r\n01:43:41,458 --> 01:43:44,166\r\nOh, Monsieur Candie, you can't\r\nimagine what it's like\r\n\r\n1426\r\n01:43:44,166 --> 01:43:47,666\r\nnot to hear your\r\nnative tongue in four years.\r\n\r\n1427\r\n01:43:47,666 --> 01:43:49,750\r\nWell, hell, I can't imagine\r\ntwo weeks in Boston.\r\n\r\n1428\r\n01:43:49,750 --> 01:43:51,875\r\n[laughing]\r\n\r\n1429\r\n01:43:51,875 --> 01:43:57,250\r\n- Two weeks in Boston!\r\nMonsieur Candie, you a mess!\r\n- [coughing]\r\n\r\n1430\r\n01:43:57,250 --> 01:43:59,083\r\n[Stephen] Two weeks in Boston!\r\n\r\n1431\r\n01:43:59,083 --> 01:44:04,500\r\nI can't express the joy I felt\r\nconversing in my mother tongue.\r\n\r\n1432\r\n01:44:04,500 --> 01:44:08,750\r\nAnd Hildi is a charming\r\nconversation companion.\r\n\r\n1433\r\n01:44:08,750 --> 01:44:10,708\r\n[Calvin] Well, be careful now,\r\nDr. Schultz.\r\n\r\n1434\r\n01:44:10,708 --> 01:44:13,708\r\n- You might-a caught yourself\r\na little dose of nigger love.\r\n- Hm!\r\n\r\n1435\r\n01:44:13,708 --> 01:44:16,291\r\n- [Calvin] Nigger love's\r\na powerful emotion, boy.\r\n- [Stephen] Hm!\r\n\r\n1436\r\n01:44:16,291 --> 01:44:19,916\r\nIt's like a pool of black tar.\r\nOnce it catches your ass,\r\nyou're caught.\r\n\r\n1437\r\n01:44:19,916 --> 01:44:23,083\r\nYessir, you stuck. [Laughs]\r\n\r\n1438\r\n01:44:23,083 --> 01:44:24,750\r\n[Lara Lee] I don't know, doctor.\r\n\r\n1439\r\n01:44:24,750 --> 01:44:27,125\r\nYou can lay on all the\r\nGerman sweet talk you want,\r\n\r\n1440\r\n01:44:27,125 --> 01:44:32,083\r\nbut it looks like this pony's\r\ngot big eyes for Django.\r\n\r\n1441\r\n01:44:32,083 --> 01:44:34,125\r\n[Lara Lee giggles]\r\n\r\n1442\r\n01:44:34,125 --> 01:44:36,750\r\nWell, naturally.\r\n\r\n1443\r\n01:44:36,750 --> 01:44:40,333\r\nIt is the soaring eagle\r\nthat attracts her attention,\r\n\r\n1444\r\n01:44:40,333 --> 01:44:43,416\r\n- not the plucked chicken.\r\n- [all chuckle]\r\n\r\n1445\r\n01:44:43,416 --> 01:44:46,125\r\n[Calvin] Dr. Schultz,\r\ndon't be so down on yourself.\r\n\r\n1446\r\n01:44:46,125 --> 01:44:48,166\r\nYou are quite the dapper\r\nEuropean gentleman.\r\n\r\n1447\r\n01:44:48,166 --> 01:44:49,625\r\n[Cora]\r\nYou got to clean these dishes,\r\n\r\n1448\r\n01:44:49,625 --> 01:44:51,750\r\nyou got to put your elbow\r\nin these dishes, you hear me?\r\n\r\n1449\r\n01:44:51,750 --> 01:44:54,125\r\nYou know that nigger, don't you?\r\n\r\n1450\r\n01:44:54,750 --> 01:44:56,166\r\n- Who?\r\n- \"Who?\"\r\n\r\n1451\r\n01:44:56,166 --> 01:44:59,416\r\nDon't \"who\" me, bitch.\r\nYou know who I'm talkin' about.\r\n\r\n1452\r\n01:45:00,958 --> 01:45:03,125\r\nAt the table?\r\n\r\n1453\r\n01:45:03,125 --> 01:45:04,541\r\nI don't know him.\r\n\r\n1454\r\n01:45:04,541 --> 01:45:07,750\r\n- You don't know him.\r\n- No.\r\n\r\n1455\r\n01:45:07,750 --> 01:45:10,875\r\n- \"No,\" what?\r\n- No, sir.\r\n\r\n1456\r\n01:45:12,791 --> 01:45:13,958\r\n[chuckles]\r\n\r\n1457\r\n01:45:15,375 --> 01:45:17,958\r\nYou wouldn't lie to me, now,\r\nwould you?\r\n\r\n1458\r\n01:45:22,000 --> 01:45:23,375\r\nOK.\r\n\r\n1459\r\n01:45:24,458 --> 01:45:27,750\r\nYeah. If you say so.\r\n\r\n1460\r\n01:45:33,583 --> 01:45:38,791\r\nEskimo Joe's a quality nigger,\r\nno doubt about it.\r\n\r\n1461\r\n01:45:38,791 --> 01:45:44,083\r\nBut if it was my money, I\r\nwouldn't pay no $12,000 for him.\r\n\r\n1462\r\n01:45:44,083 --> 01:45:46,583\r\nWhat would your price be?\r\n\r\n1463\r\n01:45:46,583 --> 01:45:48,791\r\nWell, if I was inclined\r\nto be generous...\r\n\r\n1464\r\n01:45:48,791 --> 01:45:52,416\r\nand I don't know why I would\r\nbe inclined to be generous...\r\n\r\n1465\r\n01:45:53,250 --> 01:45:56,583\r\n9,000. Maybe.\r\n\r\n1466\r\n01:45:57,708 --> 01:46:00,791\r\nDr. Schultz, let me reclarify\r\n\r\n1467\r\n01:46:00,791 --> 01:46:03,583\r\nhow this whole\r\nnegotiation came about.\r\n\r\n1468\r\n01:46:03,583 --> 01:46:05,708\r\nYou see, it wasn't me who\r\ncame to you to sell a nigger.\r\n\r\n1469\r\n01:46:05,708 --> 01:46:08,791\r\n- Sure wasn't.\r\n- It was you who\r\napproached me to buy one.\r\n\r\n1470\r\n01:46:08,791 --> 01:46:11,208\r\n- Sure was.\r\n- Now, that $9,000 figure.\r\n\r\n1471\r\n01:46:11,208 --> 01:46:13,916\r\nBright Boy's been bandyin'\r\nabout, that ain't too far off\r\nfrom right.\r\n\r\n1472\r\n01:46:13,916 --> 01:46:15,750\r\nAnd if I wanted to sell\r\nEskimo Joe for that,\r\n\r\n1473\r\n01:46:15,750 --> 01:46:18,541\r\n- I could do so any day\r\nof the week.\r\n- Any day.\r\n\r\n1474\r\n01:46:18,541 --> 01:46:23,666\r\nBut, like you said in\r\nGreenville, doctor...\r\nI don't want to sell him.\r\n\r\n1475\r\n01:46:23,666 --> 01:46:27,916\r\nIt was only your ridiculous\r\noffer of $12,000\r\n\r\n1476\r\n01:46:27,916 --> 01:46:30,916\r\n- that made me even consider it.\r\n- Hm-mm.\r\n\r\n1477\r\n01:46:35,416 --> 01:46:38,666\r\n[deep inhale]\r\n\r\n1478\r\n01:46:38,666 --> 01:46:43,125\r\nYou know, Monsieur Candie,\r\nyou do possess the power of\r\npersuasion.\r\n\r\n1479\r\n01:46:43,125 --> 01:46:44,625\r\n[chuckles]\r\n\r\n1480\r\n01:46:46,625 --> 01:46:49,250\r\n[slamming table] Why not?\r\nMonsieur Candie, you have\r\na deal.\r\n\r\n1481\r\n01:46:49,250 --> 01:46:53,666\r\n- Eskimo Joe, $12,000.\r\n- [banging table] Hooray,\r\ndoctor. Hooray.\r\n\r\n1482\r\n01:46:53,666 --> 01:46:55,375\r\nAnd a wise decision that is.\r\n\r\n1483\r\n01:46:55,375 --> 01:46:59,083\r\nHowever, that is\r\na tremendous amount of money.\r\n\r\n1484\r\n01:46:59,083 --> 01:47:02,458\r\nAnd the way you have\r\nyour Mr. Moguy, I have a lawyer.\r\n\r\n1485\r\n01:47:02,458 --> 01:47:04,291\r\nPersnickety man named Tuttle.\r\n\r\n1486\r\n01:47:04,291 --> 01:47:07,583\r\nAnd I would need my Mr. Tuttle\r\nto draw up a legal contract\r\n\r\n1487\r\n01:47:07,583 --> 01:47:10,750\r\nbefore I'd feel comfortable\r\nexchanging that amount of money\r\nfor flesh.\r\n\r\n1488\r\n01:47:10,750 --> 01:47:13,750\r\n- Hm-mm.\r\n- Not to mention having\r\nEskimo Joe examined\r\n\r\n1489\r\n01:47:13,750 --> 01:47:16,708\r\n- by a physician of my choosing.\r\n- [Calvin] Naturally.\r\n\r\n1490\r\n01:47:16,708 --> 01:47:21,500\r\nSo, say I return in about...\r\n\r\n1491\r\n01:47:23,333 --> 01:47:25,916\r\n- ...five days time.\r\n- Five days?\r\n\r\n1492\r\n01:47:25,916 --> 01:47:27,291\r\nWith my Mr. Tuttle.\r\n\r\n1493\r\n01:47:27,291 --> 01:47:29,500\r\nAnd then my Mr. Tuttle\r\nand your Mr. Moguy\r\n\r\n1494\r\n01:47:29,500 --> 01:47:33,333\r\ncan hash out the finer\r\ndetails between themselves.\r\n\r\n1495\r\n01:47:33,333 --> 01:47:36,583\r\nI say splendid, doctor.\r\nSplendid.\r\n\r\n1496\r\n01:47:37,083 --> 01:47:38,500\r\nGentlemen...\r\n\r\n1497\r\n01:47:39,291 --> 01:47:41,500\r\nmay I propose a toast.\r\n\r\n1498\r\n01:47:43,708 --> 01:47:48,750\r\nTo Eskimo Joe. Or shall\r\nwe call him The Black Hercules?\r\n\r\n1499\r\n01:47:48,750 --> 01:47:51,583\r\n- [all chuckling]\r\n- To The Black Hercules.\r\n\r\n1500\r\n01:47:51,583 --> 01:47:53,083\r\n[Stephen] The Black Hercules.\r\n\r\n1501\r\n01:47:53,083 --> 01:47:54,750\r\n[speaks low]\r\nTo The Black Hercules.\r\n\r\n1502\r\n01:47:54,750 --> 01:47:58,750\r\nYou was right, doctor.\r\nThat name do have pan-ass.\r\n[chuckles]\r\n\r\n1503\r\n01:47:58,750 --> 01:48:00,333\r\nHm.\r\n\r\n1504\r\n01:48:00,333 --> 01:48:03,750\r\nHildi, top my drink off.\r\n\r\n1505\r\n01:48:06,625 --> 01:48:11,833\r\nSo, Hildi, how you like servin'\r\nat the big table in The Big\r\nHouse, huh?\r\n\r\n1506\r\n01:48:11,833 --> 01:48:14,916\r\nWhen Monsieur Candie\r\ntalk to you, you answers.\r\n\r\n1507\r\n01:48:14,916 --> 01:48:18,125\r\n- I like it a lot,\r\nMonsieur Candie.\r\n- Hm-mm.\r\n\r\n1508\r\n01:48:18,125 --> 01:48:22,541\r\nIt's a lot better than sizzlin'\r\nin that Hot Box or draggin' your\r\nass through a bramble bush.\r\n\r\n1509\r\n01:48:22,541 --> 01:48:25,541\r\nBut maybe it's not quite as much\r\nfun as gettin' to pleasure all\r\nthem Mandingos,\r\n\r\n1510\r\n01:48:25,541 --> 01:48:27,458\r\n- huh, sugar bear?\r\n- Oh, Lord, she like them\r\nniggers.\r\n\r\n1511\r\n01:48:27,458 --> 01:48:28,958\r\n- Sure do.\r\n- Like Samson? Huh?\r\n\r\n1512\r\n01:48:28,958 --> 01:48:32,166\r\n- [Hildi] No, sir.\r\n- You know, Monsieur Candie,\r\n\r\n1513\r\n01:48:32,166 --> 01:48:35,958\r\nthe doctor here might\r\nbe interested in seein'\r\nHildi's peeled back,\r\n\r\n1514\r\n01:48:35,958 --> 01:48:39,000\r\nseein' as how they don't have\r\nmany niggers where he come from.\r\n\r\n1515\r\n01:48:39,000 --> 01:48:41,750\r\nDr. Schultz, when you\r\nwas alone with Hildi, here,\r\n\r\n1516\r\n01:48:41,750 --> 01:48:44,666\r\ndid you just speak German or did\r\nyou get to take her clothes off?\r\n\r\n1517\r\n01:48:44,666 --> 01:48:49,166\r\n- No, we just talked and...\r\n- [Calvin] Oh, so you haven't\r\nseen her back?\r\n\r\n1518\r\n01:48:49,166 --> 01:48:51,250\r\n- I haven't...\r\n- No, no, no, no.\r\n\r\n1519\r\n01:48:51,250 --> 01:48:53,458\r\nStephen's right,\r\nyou might find this interesting.\r\n\r\n1520\r\n01:48:53,458 --> 01:48:56,666\r\nHildi, go on, take off your\r\ndress. Show Dr. Schultz your\r\nback here.\r\n\r\n1521\r\n01:48:56,666 --> 01:48:58,791\r\n- Go on.\r\n- [Lara Lee] Uh, Calvin.\r\n\r\n1522\r\n01:48:58,791 --> 01:49:01,416\r\nI just got her all dressed up\r\nand lookin' nice.\r\n\r\n1523\r\n01:49:01,416 --> 01:49:04,416\r\n[Calvin] But, Lara Lee,\r\nDr. Schultz is from Dusseldorf.\r\n\r\n1524\r\n01:49:04,416 --> 01:49:07,708\r\nThey don't got niggers there.\r\nHe is a man of medicine.\r\n\r\n1525\r\n01:49:07,708 --> 01:49:10,416\r\nI'm sure it would fascinate him,\r\nthe niggers' endurance for pain.\r\n\r\n1526\r\n01:49:10,416 --> 01:49:14,208\r\nThese niggers are tough,\r\nDr. Schultz, no doubt about it.\r\n\r\n1527\r\n01:49:14,208 --> 01:49:16,500\r\nHildi's got somethin'\r\nlike four lashes on her back.\r\n\r\n1528\r\n01:49:16,500 --> 01:49:18,583\r\nLara Lee just get one,\r\nshe'd lose her goddamn mind.\r\n\r\n1529\r\n01:49:18,583 --> 01:49:19,916\r\n- [Stephen] Sure would.\r\n- [Calvin] Look at that, doctor.\r\n\r\n1530\r\n01:49:19,916 --> 01:49:22,916\r\n- It's like a paintin'.\r\nLook at that.\r\n- Calvin!\r\n\r\n1531\r\n01:49:22,916 --> 01:49:26,208\r\nWe are eating. Ain't no one\r\nwanna look at her whipped up\r\nback.\r\n\r\n1532\r\n01:49:27,583 --> 01:49:30,041\r\n- [exhales]\r\n- Fine. Fine, fine, fine, fine.\r\n\r\n1533\r\n01:49:30,041 --> 01:49:33,000\r\nAfter dinner, then, Stephen.\r\nAfter dinner.\r\n\r\n1534\r\n01:49:33,916 --> 01:49:36,041\r\nDuring the brandies,\r\ngentlemen, hm?\r\n\r\n1535\r\n01:49:42,041 --> 01:49:44,041\r\n[Lara Lee]\r\nCora, come get this girl!\r\n\r\n1536\r\n01:49:44,041 --> 01:49:47,041\r\n[approaching footsteps]\r\n\r\n1537\r\n01:49:47,041 --> 01:49:50,541\r\n- [Lara Lee] She a mess.\r\n- Yes, ma'am. [Gasps] Oh!\r\n\r\n1538\r\n01:49:50,541 --> 01:49:53,250\r\nWhy are you all undone?\r\nI just got you done up.\r\n\r\n1539\r\n01:49:53,250 --> 01:49:54,750\r\nCome on in here.\r\n\r\n1540\r\n01:50:00,750 --> 01:50:05,083\r\nBaby, you on Stephen bad side,\r\nand you need to be on his blind\r\nside.\r\n\r\n1541\r\n01:50:05,083 --> 01:50:07,166\r\nYou say you ain't know him.\r\n\r\n1542\r\n01:50:08,166 --> 01:50:09,458\r\nHuh?\r\n\r\n1543\r\n01:50:09,458 --> 01:50:15,166\r\nI said, you said\r\nyou ain't know him.\r\n\r\n1544\r\n01:50:16,083 --> 01:50:19,666\r\n- I don't.\r\n- Yes, you do.\r\n\r\n1545\r\n01:50:21,666 --> 01:50:23,458\r\nMr. Stephen...\r\n\r\n1546\r\n01:50:24,250 --> 01:50:25,500\r\nI don't.\r\n\r\n1547\r\n01:50:25,500 --> 01:50:28,166\r\nWhy is you lying to me?\r\n\r\n1548\r\n01:50:30,458 --> 01:50:31,916\r\nI ain't.\r\n\r\n1549\r\n01:50:31,916 --> 01:50:34,583\r\nThen why is you crying?\r\n\r\n1550\r\n01:50:34,583 --> 01:50:36,666\r\nYou scarin' me.\r\n\r\n1551\r\n01:50:36,666 --> 01:50:42,291\r\n- Why is I'm scaring you?\r\n- Because you scary.\r\n\r\n1552\r\n01:50:42,291 --> 01:50:45,708\r\n[Schultz] To speak German\r\nthis afternoon with Hildi\r\n\r\n1553\r\n01:50:45,708 --> 01:50:48,916\r\nwas positively soul-enriching.\r\n\r\n1554\r\n01:50:48,916 --> 01:50:52,083\r\n[Calvin] Doctor, that warms\r\nmy heart to hear that.\r\n\r\n1555\r\n01:50:52,083 --> 01:50:55,083\r\nYou stay right here.\r\n\r\n1556\r\n01:51:00,208 --> 01:51:04,791\r\n[Schultz] You indicated earlier\r\nyou'd be willing to part with\r\nHildi.\r\n\r\n1557\r\n01:51:04,791 --> 01:51:07,916\r\nWhy, yes.\r\nYessiree bob, I did.\r\n\r\n1558\r\n01:51:09,916 --> 01:51:15,916\r\nIn that case, allow me\r\nto propose another proposition.\r\n\r\n1559\r\n01:51:15,916 --> 01:51:17,416\r\nI'm all ears.\r\n\r\n1560\r\n01:51:17,416 --> 01:51:19,333\r\nHurry up, goddamn it!\r\n\r\n1561\r\n01:51:19,333 --> 01:51:21,416\r\n- Monsieur Candie...\r\n- [Calvin] Stephen!\r\n\r\n1562\r\n01:51:22,375 --> 01:51:25,041\r\nYou just interrupted\r\nDr. Schultz here.\r\n\r\n1563\r\n01:51:25,958 --> 01:51:28,250\r\n[Stephen]\r\nI'm sorry, Dr. Schultz.\r\n\r\n1564\r\n01:51:28,250 --> 01:51:31,125\r\nMy ears ain't\r\nworth a damn these days.\r\n\r\n1565\r\n01:51:31,125 --> 01:51:32,541\r\nExcuse him.\r\n\r\n1566\r\n01:51:32,541 --> 01:51:36,541\r\nMonsieur Candie, could I get\r\na word with you in the kitchen?\r\n\r\n1567\r\n01:51:36,541 --> 01:51:38,416\r\nYou mean get up out of my chair?\r\n\r\n1568\r\n01:51:38,416 --> 01:51:42,041\r\n- If'n you could manage it.\r\n- Why?\r\n\r\n1569\r\n01:51:42,041 --> 01:51:45,916\r\n- It's about dessert.\r\n- What about dessert?\r\n\r\n1570\r\n01:51:45,916 --> 01:51:48,958\r\nI'd rather discuss that\r\nin private.\r\n\r\n1571\r\n01:51:48,958 --> 01:51:50,666\r\nWe're having white cake!\r\n\r\n1572\r\n01:51:50,666 --> 01:51:53,375\r\nWhat sort of melodrama\r\ncould be brewing back there?\r\n\r\n1573\r\n01:51:53,375 --> 01:51:57,958\r\nYou right, Monsieur Candie. You\r\nright. I'll handle it myself.\r\n\r\n1574\r\n01:51:57,958 --> 01:51:59,666\r\n[whispers]\r\nMeet me in the library.\r\n\r\n1575\r\n01:51:59,666 --> 01:52:03,000\r\nI just can't understand why\r\nyou won't come talk to these\r\nniggers.\r\n\r\n1576\r\n01:52:03,000 --> 01:52:04,958\r\nShit get fucked up around here,\r\nyou blame me.\r\n\r\n1577\r\n01:52:04,958 --> 01:52:10,250\r\nFine! Fine. Friend Stephen,\r\nI will be along momentarily.\r\n\r\n1578\r\n01:52:10,250 --> 01:52:12,375\r\nYessir.\r\n\r\n1579\r\n01:52:12,375 --> 01:52:15,958\r\nWell, gentlemen, as you can see,\r\n\r\n1580\r\n01:52:15,958 --> 01:52:17,958\r\ntalented as they are,\r\nno doubt, in the kitchen,\r\n\r\n1581\r\n01:52:17,958 --> 01:52:21,916\r\nfrom time to time,\r\nadult supervision is required.\r\n\r\n1582\r\n01:52:21,916 --> 01:52:23,416\r\n[all chuckle]\r\n\r\n1583\r\n01:52:24,708 --> 01:52:26,708\r\nIf you'll excuse me a moment.\r\n\r\n1584\r\n01:52:32,583 --> 01:52:35,791\r\n[Calvin] You may clear\r\nthe dinner service.\r\n\r\n1585\r\n01:52:35,791 --> 01:52:39,291\r\n[Cora] You heard him. Go on!\r\nGet! Hurry up, girl.\r\n\r\n1586\r\n01:52:39,291 --> 01:52:45,041\r\nSo, Dr. Schultz, why don't you\r\nregale us with a tale of the\r\ncircus.\r\n\r\n1587\r\n01:52:45,041 --> 01:52:47,916\r\n[chuckles] The circus?\r\n\r\n1588\r\n01:52:47,916 --> 01:52:49,583\r\n[fire crackling]\r\n\r\n1589\r\n01:52:54,250 --> 01:52:56,125\r\nWhat is the matter?\r\n\r\n1590\r\n01:53:01,250 --> 01:53:06,458\r\nThem motherfuckers\r\nain't here to buy no Mandingos.\r\n\r\n1591\r\n01:53:06,458 --> 01:53:10,041\r\n- They wants that girl.\r\n- [chuckling]\r\n\r\n1592\r\n01:53:10,041 --> 01:53:13,125\r\nStephen, what the hell\r\nare you talking about? Hm?\r\n\r\n1593\r\n01:53:13,125 --> 01:53:16,333\r\nThey playing your ass for a fool\r\nis what I'm talking about.\r\n\r\n1594\r\n01:53:16,333 --> 01:53:20,333\r\nThey ain't here for\r\nno musclebound Jimmie.\r\n\r\n1595\r\n01:53:20,333 --> 01:53:22,625\r\nThey here for that girl.\r\n\r\n1596\r\n01:53:22,625 --> 01:53:25,250\r\nWh... What girl? Hildi?\r\n\r\n1597\r\n01:53:25,250 --> 01:53:29,250\r\nYeah, Hildi. Her and Django,\r\nthem niggers know each other.\r\n\r\n1598\r\n01:53:30,875 --> 01:53:32,375\r\nHe just bought Eskimo Joe.\r\n\r\n1599\r\n01:53:32,375 --> 01:53:34,958\r\n- Did he give you any money?\r\n- No! Not yet. But...\r\n\r\n1600\r\n01:53:34,958 --> 01:53:37,666\r\nThen he ain't bought diddly.\r\nNot yet, nohow.\r\n\r\n1601\r\n01:53:37,666 --> 01:53:40,083\r\nBut he's just about to buy\r\n\r\n1602\r\n01:53:40,083 --> 01:53:43,458\r\nwho he come here to buy\r\nwhen I interrupted him.\r\n\r\n1603\r\n01:53:43,458 --> 01:53:46,666\r\n\"Thank you, Stephen.\"\r\nYou're welcome, Calvin.\r\n\r\n1604\r\n01:53:51,875 --> 01:53:54,958\r\nWhere you gettin' all this?\r\n\r\n1605\r\n01:53:54,958 --> 01:53:56,916\r\nWhy would they go through\r\nall that trouble for a nigger\r\n\r\n1606\r\n01:53:56,916 --> 01:53:59,666\r\nwith a chewed up back,\r\nain't worth $300?\r\n\r\n1607\r\n01:53:59,666 --> 01:54:04,125\r\nThey doin' it 'cause that nigger\r\nDjango's in love with Hildi.\r\n\r\n1608\r\n01:54:04,125 --> 01:54:06,000\r\nShe probably his wife.\r\n\r\n1609\r\n01:54:06,000 --> 01:54:09,083\r\nNow, why that German\r\ngives a fuck who that\r\nuppity son of a bitch\r\n\r\n1610\r\n01:54:09,083 --> 01:54:12,291\r\nis in love with,\r\nI'm sure I don't know.\r\n\r\n1611\r\n01:54:14,708 --> 01:54:17,291\r\nIf she's who they want...\r\n\r\n1612\r\n01:54:17,291 --> 01:54:21,791\r\nwhy this whole snake oil\r\npitch about Mandingos, then?\r\n\r\n1613\r\n01:54:21,791 --> 01:54:25,416\r\nYou wouldn't pay no\r\nnever mind to no $300.\r\n\r\n1614\r\n01:54:25,416 --> 01:54:31,083\r\nBut that 12,000? That made you\r\nreal friendly, now, didn't it?\r\n\r\n1615\r\n01:54:33,708 --> 01:54:35,541\r\nYes, it did.\r\n\r\n1616\r\n01:54:38,625 --> 01:54:40,416\r\nHis wife, huh?\r\n\r\n1617\r\n01:54:44,041 --> 01:54:47,958\r\nIf it had been a snake,\r\nit would have bit me.\r\n\r\n1618\r\n01:54:47,958 --> 01:54:49,541\r\n[chuckles]\r\n\r\n1619\r\n01:54:51,125 --> 01:54:53,916\r\nThose lying...\r\n\r\n1620\r\n01:54:53,916 --> 01:55:00,125\r\ngoddamn time-wastin'\r\nsons of bitches.\r\n\r\n1621\r\n01:55:02,250 --> 01:55:03,416\r\nSons of bitches!\r\n\r\n1622\r\n01:55:03,416 --> 01:55:05,125\r\n[Lara Lee]\r\n...out of New Orleans,\r\n\r\n1623\r\n01:55:05,125 --> 01:55:09,958\r\nso I have quite a bit of\r\npractice with theater types.\r\n\r\n1624\r\n01:55:09,958 --> 01:55:11,583\r\nOh, there you are.\r\n\r\n1625\r\n01:55:11,583 --> 01:55:14,666\r\nI was beginning to think that\r\nyou and that old crow run off\r\ntogether.\r\n\r\n1626\r\n01:55:14,666 --> 01:55:16,166\r\n[all chuckling]\r\n\r\n1627\r\n01:55:16,166 --> 01:55:18,458\r\nThat'd be a hell of a note,\r\nwouldn't it?\r\n\r\n1628\r\n01:55:18,458 --> 01:55:21,750\r\nLara Lee, I was just\r\nlooking out the big window.\r\n\r\n1629\r\n01:55:21,750 --> 01:55:25,000\r\nBilly Crash is out there\r\ndealing with some shady slaver\r\n\r\n1630\r\n01:55:25,000 --> 01:55:26,250\r\ntrying to sell\r\na passel of ponies.\r\n\r\n1631\r\n01:55:26,250 --> 01:55:27,583\r\nWould you be a dear,\r\ngo out there\r\n\r\n1632\r\n01:55:27,583 --> 01:55:30,375\r\nand give them gals\r\nan eyeball? Hm?\r\n\r\n1633\r\n01:55:30,375 --> 01:55:32,958\r\n- Of course, brother.\r\n- Thank you, darling.\r\n\r\n1634\r\n01:55:45,791 --> 01:55:49,791\r\n- Yeah. Business never sleeps.\r\n- Hm-mm.\r\n\r\n1635\r\n01:55:51,583 --> 01:55:54,708\r\nApropos, before your exit,\r\n\r\n1636\r\n01:55:54,708 --> 01:55:58,916\r\nwe were discussing the\r\npossibility of my purchasing\r\nBroomhilda.\r\n\r\n1637\r\n01:55:58,916 --> 01:56:02,000\r\nAh, yes. Yes, we were, doctor.\r\n\r\n1638\r\n01:56:02,000 --> 01:56:04,208\r\nAnd we will again. In a moment.\r\n\r\n1639\r\n01:56:20,625 --> 01:56:22,833\r\nWho's your little friend?\r\n\r\n1640\r\n01:56:24,916 --> 01:56:26,250\r\n[clearing throat]\r\n\r\n1641\r\n01:56:27,541 --> 01:56:30,250\r\nThis is Ben.\r\n\r\n1642\r\n01:56:30,250 --> 01:56:35,625\r\nHe's a old Joe that lived\r\naround here for a long time.\r\n\r\n1643\r\n01:56:35,625 --> 01:56:37,625\r\nAnd I do mean a long damn time.\r\n\r\n1644\r\n01:56:39,083 --> 01:56:43,041\r\nOld Ben here\r\ntook care of my daddy...\r\n\r\n1645\r\n01:56:43,750 --> 01:56:45,833\r\nand my daddy's daddy.\r\n\r\n1646\r\n01:56:45,833 --> 01:56:48,666\r\nTill he up and\r\nkeeled over one day...\r\n\r\n1647\r\n01:56:51,291 --> 01:56:53,166\r\nOld Ben took care of me.\r\n\r\n1648\r\n01:56:55,666 --> 01:56:59,583\r\nGrowing up the son of a huge\r\nplantation owner in Mississippi\r\n\r\n1649\r\n01:56:59,583 --> 01:57:05,666\r\nputs a white man in contact\r\nwith a whole lotta black faces.\r\n\r\n1650\r\n01:57:06,916 --> 01:57:12,458\r\nI spent my whole life here,\r\nright here in Candyland...\r\n\r\n1651\r\n01:57:13,666 --> 01:57:17,583\r\nsurrounded by black faces.\r\n\r\n1652\r\n01:57:19,458 --> 01:57:22,000\r\nNow, seeing them every day,\r\nday in, day out,\r\n\r\n1653\r\n01:57:22,000 --> 01:57:25,291\r\nI only had one question:\r\n\r\n1654\r\n01:57:28,708 --> 01:57:31,500\r\n- Why don't they kill us?\r\n- [laughs]\r\n\r\n1655\r\n01:57:34,083 --> 01:57:39,500\r\nNow, right out there on that\r\nporch, three times a week\r\nfor 50 years,\r\n\r\n1656\r\n01:57:39,500 --> 01:57:44,708\r\nOld Ben here would shave my\r\ndaddy with a straight razor.\r\n\r\n1657\r\n01:57:44,708 --> 01:57:49,916\r\nNow, if I was Old Ben, I woulda\r\ncut my daddy's goddamn throat\r\n\r\n1658\r\n01:57:49,916 --> 01:57:53,583\r\nand it wouldn't have taken me\r\nno 50 years to do it, neither.\r\n\r\n1659\r\n01:57:55,916 --> 01:57:57,750\r\nBut he never did.\r\n\r\n1660\r\n01:57:59,416 --> 01:58:00,833\r\nWhy not?\r\n\r\n1661\r\n01:58:01,916 --> 01:58:07,041\r\nYou see, the science\r\nof phrenology\r\n\r\n1662\r\n01:58:07,041 --> 01:58:12,250\r\nis crucial to understanding the\r\nseparation of our two species.\r\n\r\n1663\r\n01:58:13,750 --> 01:58:17,625\r\nIn the skull\r\nof the African here,\r\n\r\n1664\r\n01:58:17,625 --> 01:58:20,041\r\nthe area associated\r\nwith submissiveness\r\n\r\n1665\r\n01:58:20,041 --> 01:58:25,750\r\nis larger than any human or any\r\nother subhuman species on planet\r\nEarth.\r\n\r\n1666\r\n01:58:26,750 --> 01:58:28,583\r\n[sawing]\r\n\r\n1667\r\n01:58:41,083 --> 01:58:43,250\r\nIf you examine...\r\n\r\n1668\r\n01:58:44,458 --> 01:58:46,750\r\nthis piece of skull here...\r\n\r\n1669\r\n01:58:52,958 --> 01:58:56,666\r\nyou will notice\r\nthree distinct dimples.\r\n\r\n1670\r\n01:59:00,083 --> 01:59:03,916\r\nHere, here and here.\r\n\r\n1671\r\n01:59:03,916 --> 01:59:05,416\r\nNow...\r\n\r\n1672\r\n01:59:05,416 --> 01:59:10,500\r\nif I was holding the skull\r\nof an Isaac Newton or Galileo,\r\n\r\n1673\r\n01:59:10,500 --> 01:59:13,208\r\nthese three dimples would be\r\nfound in the area of the skull\r\n\r\n1674\r\n01:59:13,208 --> 01:59:17,208\r\nmost associated with...\r\ncreativity.\r\n\r\n1675\r\n01:59:17,208 --> 01:59:19,625\r\nBut this is the skull\r\nof Old Ben.\r\n\r\n1676\r\n01:59:19,625 --> 01:59:22,000\r\nAnd in the skull of Old Ben,\r\n\r\n1677\r\n01:59:22,000 --> 01:59:24,083\r\nunburdened by genius,\r\n\r\n1678\r\n01:59:24,083 --> 01:59:28,791\r\nthese three dimples exist\r\nin the area of the skull\r\nmost associated with...\r\n\r\n1679\r\n01:59:29,791 --> 01:59:31,208\r\nservility.\r\n\r\n1680\r\n01:59:32,000 --> 01:59:34,666\r\nNow, Bright Boy...\r\n\r\n1681\r\n01:59:34,666 --> 01:59:37,125\r\nI will admit\r\nyou are pretty clever.\r\n\r\n1682\r\n01:59:39,250 --> 01:59:41,625\r\nBut if I took\r\nthis hammer here...\r\n\r\n1683\r\n01:59:43,541 --> 01:59:46,916\r\nand I bashed in\r\nyour skull with it...\r\n\r\n1684\r\n01:59:46,916 --> 01:59:52,416\r\nyou would have the same three\r\ndimples in the same place...\r\n\r\n1685\r\n01:59:53,541 --> 01:59:56,125\r\nas Old Ben.\r\n\r\n1686\r\n01:59:56,125 --> 01:59:59,833\r\nHey! Now lay your palms\r\nflat on that tabletop!\r\n\r\n1687\r\n01:59:59,833 --> 02:00:02,750\r\nIf you lift those palms\r\noff that turtle shell tabletop,\r\n\r\n1688\r\n02:00:02,750 --> 02:00:05,541\r\nMr. Pooch is gonna let loose\r\nwith both barrels of that\r\nsawed-off.\r\n\r\n1689\r\n02:00:07,250 --> 02:00:10,583\r\nThere have been a lot of lies\r\nsaid around this dinner table\r\nhere tonight,\r\n\r\n1690\r\n02:00:10,583 --> 02:00:13,166\r\nbut that you can believe!\r\n\r\n1691\r\n02:00:13,166 --> 02:00:15,875\r\nMr. Moguy, would you be\r\nso kind as to collect the pistol\r\n\r\n1692\r\n02:00:15,875 --> 02:00:18,666\r\nhanging off these\r\nboys' hips here?\r\n\r\n1693\r\n02:00:22,958 --> 02:00:25,750\r\n- Thank you ever so much.\r\n- Doctor.\r\n\r\n1694\r\n02:00:30,166 --> 02:00:31,666\r\nWhere were we?\r\n\r\n1695\r\n02:00:36,083 --> 02:00:37,583\r\nJackass.\r\n\r\n1696\r\n02:00:41,500 --> 02:00:43,000\r\nAh, yes.\r\n\r\n1697\r\n02:00:43,000 --> 02:00:46,000\r\nI do believe you were\r\njust getting ready to make me\r\n\r\n1698\r\n02:00:46,000 --> 02:00:48,583\r\na proposition to buy Broomhilda.\r\n\r\n1699\r\n02:00:48,583 --> 02:00:50,208\r\nAm I right?\r\n\r\n1700\r\n02:00:54,000 --> 02:00:55,500\r\nRight.\r\n\r\n1701\r\n02:00:57,791 --> 02:00:59,416\r\nBring out Hildi!\r\n\r\n1702\r\n02:01:02,000 --> 02:01:04,708\r\nGet over there yonder.\r\n\r\n1703\r\n02:01:04,708 --> 02:01:07,416\r\n- [screams]\r\n- Sit your ass in\r\nthat goddamn...\r\n\r\n1704\r\n02:01:07,416 --> 02:01:10,500\r\n- [Stephen] Lay your hand flat\r\non that tabletop.\r\n- [Calvin] Now shut your mouth!\r\n\r\n1705\r\n02:01:14,750 --> 02:01:17,333\r\nDr. Schultz, in Greenville,\r\n\r\n1706\r\n02:01:17,333 --> 02:01:20,250\r\n\"you yourself said that\r\nfor the right nigger\"\r\n\r\n1707\r\n02:01:20,250 --> 02:01:24,833\r\nyou'd be willin' to pay\r\nwhat some may consider\r\nis a ridiculous amount.\r\n\r\n1708\r\n02:01:24,833 --> 02:01:28,125\r\nTo which me myself said,\r\n\"What is your definition\r\nof ridiculous?\"\r\n\r\n1709\r\n02:01:28,125 --> 02:01:32,750\r\nTo which you said, \"$12,000.\"\r\n\r\n1710\r\n02:01:32,750 --> 02:01:36,750\r\n- [yells]\r\n- Now, considering y'all have\r\nridden a whole lot of miles,\r\n\r\n1711\r\n02:01:36,750 --> 02:01:40,916\r\nwent through a whole lot of\r\ntrouble, and done spread a\r\nwhole lot of bull\r\n\r\n1712\r\n02:01:40,916 --> 02:01:43,375\r\nto purchase this\r\nlovely lady right here,\r\n\r\n1713\r\n02:01:43,375 --> 02:01:49,583\r\nit would appear that\r\nBroomhilda is, in fact...\r\nthe right nigger.\r\n\r\n1714\r\n02:01:49,583 --> 02:01:53,666\r\nAnd if y'all want to leave\r\nCandyland with Broomhilda,\r\n\r\n1715\r\n02:01:53,666 --> 02:01:59,208\r\nthe price is $12,000.\r\n\r\n1716\r\n02:01:59,208 --> 02:02:03,375\r\nAnd I take it you prefer the\r\n\"take it or leave it\" style\r\nof negotiation?\r\n\r\n1717\r\n02:02:05,458 --> 02:02:07,750\r\nYes, I do, doctor.\r\n\r\n1718\r\n02:02:07,750 --> 02:02:11,000\r\nYou see, under the laws\r\nof Chickasaw County,\r\n\r\n1719\r\n02:02:11,000 --> 02:02:14,583\r\nBroomhilda here is my property.\r\n\r\n1720\r\n02:02:14,583 --> 02:02:19,958\r\nAnd I can choose to do with my\r\nproperty whatever I so desire!\r\n\r\n1721\r\n02:02:21,000 --> 02:02:23,583\r\nAnd if y'all think my price...\r\n\r\n1722\r\n02:02:23,583 --> 02:02:27,583\r\n- ...for this nigger here\r\nis too steep...\r\n- [grunts]\r\n\r\n1723\r\n02:02:27,583 --> 02:02:30,416\r\nwhat I'm gonna\r\ndesire to do is...\r\n\r\n1724\r\n02:02:34,208 --> 02:02:37,500\r\ntake this goddamn hammer here\r\nand beat her ass to death with\r\nit!\r\n\r\n1725\r\n02:02:37,500 --> 02:02:39,625\r\n- Right in front of both y'all!\r\n- Easy, big fella.\r\n\r\n1726\r\n02:02:39,625 --> 02:02:44,416\r\nThen we can examine the three\r\ndimples inside Broomhilda's\r\nskull!\r\n\r\n1727\r\n02:02:44,416 --> 02:02:48,708\r\nNow, what's it gonna be, doc?\r\nHuh?\r\n\r\n1728\r\n02:02:48,708 --> 02:02:50,208\r\n- [Hildi whimpering]\r\n- What's it gonna be?\r\n\r\n1729\r\n02:02:50,208 --> 02:02:51,916\r\nMay I lift the hands\r\noff the tabletop\r\n\r\n1730\r\n02:02:51,916 --> 02:02:54,583\r\nin order to remove\r\nmy billfold?\r\n\r\n1731\r\n02:02:55,416 --> 02:02:56,833\r\nYes, you may.\r\n\r\n1732\r\n02:03:10,541 --> 02:03:11,833\r\nThat 12.\r\n\r\n1733\r\n02:03:15,625 --> 02:03:17,666\r\n- Sold!\r\n- [screaming]\r\n\r\n1734\r\n02:03:17,666 --> 02:03:20,416\r\nTo the man with\r\nthe exceptional beard\r\n\r\n1735\r\n02:03:20,416 --> 02:03:24,041\r\nand his unexceptional nigger.\r\n\r\n1736\r\n02:03:29,583 --> 02:03:32,083\r\n- Mr. Moguy.\r\n- Yes, Calvin?\r\n\r\n1737\r\n02:03:32,083 --> 02:03:35,958\r\nWill you make these gentlemen\r\na receipt for $12,000, please?\r\n\r\n1738\r\n02:03:35,958 --> 02:03:37,875\r\n$12,000.\r\n\r\n1739\r\n02:03:40,875 --> 02:03:43,166\r\nIt was a pleasure doing\r\nbusiness with y'all.\r\n\r\n1740\r\n02:03:43,875 --> 02:03:45,750\r\nNow, gentlemen...\r\n\r\n1741\r\n02:03:46,875 --> 02:03:49,666\r\nif you care to\r\njoin me in the parlor...\r\n\r\n1742\r\n02:03:49,666 --> 02:03:52,958\r\nwe will be\r\nserving white cake.\r\n\r\n1743\r\n02:03:52,958 --> 02:03:56,083\r\n[Beethoven's \"Fur Elise\"\r\nplayed on harp]\r\n\r\n1744\r\n02:04:51,750 --> 02:04:52,750\r\n- [screaming]\r\n- [dogs snarling]\r\n\r\n1745\r\n02:05:07,916 --> 02:05:09,666\r\n[screaming]\r\n\r\n1746\r\n02:05:20,416 --> 02:05:21,958\r\nWell done, Calvin.\r\n\r\n1747\r\n02:05:24,166 --> 02:05:27,375\r\nExcuse me.\r\nExcuse me, ma'am?\r\n\r\n1748\r\n02:05:28,666 --> 02:05:30,750\r\nCould you please\r\nstop playing Beethoven?\r\n\r\n1749\r\n02:05:30,750 --> 02:05:32,458\r\nTake your hands off\r\nthe harp!\r\n\r\n1750\r\n02:05:36,458 --> 02:05:37,791\r\n[Stephen] Doctor!\r\n\r\n1751\r\n02:05:37,791 --> 02:05:40,583\r\n- Doctor, you can't go in there!\r\n- Stephen, Stephen.\r\n\r\n1752\r\n02:05:40,583 --> 02:05:42,000\r\nHe ain't got no business\r\ngoing in there.\r\n\r\n1753\r\n02:05:42,000 --> 02:05:43,500\r\nLet it be.\r\n\r\n1754\r\n02:05:43,500 --> 02:05:45,583\r\nHe's just a little upset,\r\nthat's all.\r\n\r\n1755\r\n02:05:45,583 --> 02:05:47,208\r\nI'll handle this.\r\n\r\n1756\r\n02:06:12,791 --> 02:06:14,000\r\nWhite cake?\r\n\r\n1757\r\n02:06:14,000 --> 02:06:17,541\r\nI don't go in for sweets,\r\nthank you.\r\n\r\n1758\r\n02:06:18,416 --> 02:06:19,833\r\nHm.\r\n\r\n1759\r\n02:06:24,416 --> 02:06:25,541\r\n[Calvin chuckles softly]\r\n\r\n1760\r\n02:06:27,125 --> 02:06:30,750\r\nYou brooding about me\r\ngetting the best of you, huh?\r\n\r\n1761\r\n02:06:30,750 --> 02:06:35,625\r\nActually, I was thinking of that\r\npoor devil you fed to the dogs\r\ntoday.\r\n\r\n1762\r\n02:06:35,625 --> 02:06:38,250\r\nD'Artagnan.\r\n\r\n1763\r\n02:06:38,250 --> 02:06:42,250\r\nAnd I was wondering what\r\nDumas would make of all this.\r\n\r\n1764\r\n02:06:42,250 --> 02:06:43,833\r\nCome again?\r\n\r\n1765\r\n02:06:46,666 --> 02:06:51,083\r\nAlexandre Dumas.\r\nHe wrote The Three Musketeers.\r\n\r\n1766\r\n02:06:51,083 --> 02:06:52,750\r\nYes, of course, doctor.\r\n\r\n1767\r\n02:06:52,750 --> 02:06:54,458\r\nI figured you\r\nmust be an admirer.\r\n\r\n1768\r\n02:06:54,458 --> 02:06:59,166\r\nYou named your slave after\r\nhis novel's lead character.\r\n\r\n1769\r\n02:06:59,166 --> 02:07:02,875\r\nNow, if Alexandre Dumas\r\nhad been there today,\r\n\r\n1770\r\n02:07:02,875 --> 02:07:05,166\r\nI wonder what\r\nhe would have made of it.\r\n\r\n1771\r\n02:07:07,083 --> 02:07:09,083\r\nYou doubt he'd approve, huh?\r\n\r\n1772\r\n02:07:11,083 --> 02:07:16,458\r\nYes. His approval would be\r\na dubious proposition at best.\r\n\r\n1773\r\n02:07:18,583 --> 02:07:20,458\r\nSoft-hearted Frenchie.\r\n\r\n1774\r\n02:07:22,208 --> 02:07:24,583\r\nAlexandre Dumas is black.\r\n\r\n1775\r\n02:07:28,291 --> 02:07:31,083\r\n- Are these Broomhilda's papers?\r\n- Yes, they are.\r\n\r\n1776\r\n02:07:31,083 --> 02:07:33,000\r\n- May I?\r\n- Of course.\r\n\r\n1777\r\n02:07:33,000 --> 02:07:34,583\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\n1778\r\n02:07:36,416 --> 02:07:39,541\r\nThat is her bill of sale,\r\nher ownership history,\r\n\r\n1779\r\n02:07:39,541 --> 02:07:41,916\r\nand, of course,\r\nher freedom papers, doctor.\r\n\r\n1780\r\n02:07:41,916 --> 02:07:44,416\r\nWould you have\r\nink and pen for me?\r\n\r\n1781\r\n02:07:45,416 --> 02:07:47,500\r\nRight over there\r\non that little table.\r\n\r\n1782\r\n02:07:47,500 --> 02:07:48,916\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\n1783\r\n02:08:09,750 --> 02:08:11,125\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\n1784\r\n02:08:14,541 --> 02:08:16,916\r\nBroomhilda Von Shaft...\r\n\r\n1785\r\n02:08:18,916 --> 02:08:21,541\r\nconsider yourself\r\na free woman.\r\n\r\n1786\r\n02:08:33,375 --> 02:08:35,583\r\nMr. Candie...\r\n\r\n1787\r\n02:08:37,166 --> 02:08:41,166\r\nnormally,\r\nI would say auf Wiedersehen.\r\n\r\n1788\r\n02:08:41,166 --> 02:08:45,791\r\nBut since what auf Wiedersehen\r\nactually means is \"till I see\r\nyou again\"\r\n\r\n1789\r\n02:08:45,791 --> 02:08:48,166\r\nand since I never\r\nwish to see you again,\r\n\r\n1790\r\n02:08:48,166 --> 02:08:53,166\r\nto you, sir...\r\nI say, \"goodbye.\"\r\n\r\n1791\r\n02:08:56,958 --> 02:08:58,375\r\nLet's go.\r\n\r\n1792\r\n02:08:59,208 --> 02:09:00,875\r\nCome on.\r\n\r\n1793\r\n02:09:02,500 --> 02:09:04,708\r\nOne more moment, doctor!\r\n\r\n1794\r\n02:09:06,416 --> 02:09:07,583\r\nWhat?\r\n\r\n1795\r\n02:09:12,208 --> 02:09:14,791\r\nIt's a custom here\r\nin the South...\r\n\r\n1796\r\n02:09:14,791 --> 02:09:20,291\r\nonce a business deal is\r\nconcluded that the two parties\r\nshake hands.\r\n\r\n1797\r\n02:09:21,041 --> 02:09:23,000\r\nIt implies good faith.\r\n\r\n1798\r\n02:09:23,000 --> 02:09:26,416\r\n- I'm not from the South.\r\n- But you are...\r\n\r\n1799\r\n02:09:26,416 --> 02:09:29,500\r\nin my house, doctor.\r\n\r\n1800\r\n02:09:29,500 --> 02:09:32,583\r\n- So I'm afraid I must insist.\r\n- Insist?\r\n\r\n1801\r\n02:09:32,583 --> 02:09:34,583\r\nOn what?\r\nThat I shake your hand?\r\n\r\n1802\r\n02:09:34,583 --> 02:09:38,250\r\nOh, then I'm afraid I must\r\ninsist in the opposite\r\ndirection.\r\n\r\n1803\r\n02:09:38,250 --> 02:09:42,041\r\n- You know what I think you are?\r\n- What you think I am?\r\n\r\n1804\r\n02:09:42,041 --> 02:09:43,916\r\nNo, I don't.\r\n\r\n1805\r\n02:09:45,416 --> 02:09:50,833\r\n- I think you are a bad loser.\r\n- And I think you're an abysmal\r\nwinner.\r\n\r\n1806\r\n02:09:50,833 --> 02:09:55,916\r\nNevertheless, here in Chickasaw\r\nCounty, a deal ain't done\r\n\r\n1807\r\n02:09:55,916 --> 02:09:58,625\r\nuntil the two parties\r\nhave shook hands.\r\n\r\n1808\r\n02:09:58,625 --> 02:10:02,416\r\nEven after all that paper\r\nsignin', don't mean shit...\r\n\r\n1809\r\n02:10:03,250 --> 02:10:07,625\r\nyou don't shake my hand.\r\n\r\n1810\r\n02:10:07,625 --> 02:10:13,583\r\nIf I don't shake your hand,\r\nyou're gonna throw away $12,000?\r\n\r\n1811\r\n02:10:13,583 --> 02:10:15,458\r\nI don't think so.\r\n\r\n1812\r\n02:10:16,250 --> 02:10:17,666\r\nMr. Pooch?\r\n\r\n1813\r\n02:10:19,250 --> 02:10