at real good.\r\n\r\n1980\r\n02:22:13,375 --> 02:22:15,083\r\nThey gonna work ya.\r\n\r\n1981\r\n02:22:15,083 --> 02:22:20,083\r\nAll day, every day,\r\ntill your back give out.\r\n\r\n1982\r\n02:22:20,083 --> 02:22:23,000\r\nThen they're gonna hit you\r\nin the head with a hammer,\r\n\r\n1983\r\n02:22:23,000 --> 02:22:25,416\r\nthrow your ass\r\ndown the nigger hole.\r\n\r\n1984\r\n02:22:25,416 --> 02:22:31,625\r\nAnd that will be\r\nthe story of you, Django.\r\n\r\n1985\r\n02:22:31,625 --> 02:22:34,583\r\n[slow-tempo song plays]\r\n\r\n1986\r\n02:22:43,500 --> 02:22:46,000\r\n♪ There ain't no grave ♪\r\n\r\n1987\r\n02:22:46,000 --> 02:22:49,583\r\n♪ Can hold my body down ♪\r\n\r\n1988\r\n02:22:49,583 --> 02:22:55,000\r\n♪ There ain't no grave\r\ncan hold my body down ♪\r\n\r\n1989\r\n02:23:10,041 --> 02:23:14,916\r\n[man, Australian accent] And\r\nwhat's the golden rule, Frankie,\r\neh? You don't root abos.\r\n\r\n1990\r\n02:23:19,625 --> 02:23:21,125\r\nHey, white boy.\r\n\r\n1991\r\n02:23:22,625 --> 02:23:24,833\r\nI said, hey, white boy.\r\n\r\n1992\r\n02:23:24,833 --> 02:23:28,125\r\nShut up, black. You ain't got\r\nnothing to say I want to hear.\r\n\r\n1993\r\n02:23:28,125 --> 02:23:30,583\r\nHow'd you like to make $11,000?\r\n\r\n1994\r\n02:23:30,583 --> 02:23:31,958\r\nDo what, now?\r\n\r\n1995\r\n02:23:31,958 --> 02:23:37,875\r\nI said how'd you like to make\r\n$11,000? 11,500, actually.\r\n\r\n1996\r\n02:23:37,875 --> 02:23:40,083\r\nWhat the fuck\r\nare you talking about?\r\n\r\n1997\r\n02:23:40,083 --> 02:23:44,875\r\nBack there at that plantation,\r\nCandyland, there was an $11,500\r\nfortune,\r\n\r\n1998\r\n02:23:44,875 --> 02:23:47,666\r\njust sittin' there.\r\nAnd y'all rode right past it.\r\n\r\n1999\r\n02:23:47,666 --> 02:23:50,500\r\nYou be damned, blackie,\r\nwe're not bandits.\r\n\r\n2000\r\n02:23:50,500 --> 02:23:54,916\r\nI ain't saying that. Nice thing\r\nabout this fortune is it ain't\r\nillegal.\r\n\r\n2001\r\n02:23:54,916 --> 02:23:56,500\r\nYou can't steal it.\r\n\r\n2002\r\n02:23:56,500 --> 02:23:59,083\r\nYou got to earn it, white boy.\r\n\r\n2003\r\n02:23:59,083 --> 02:24:01,291\r\nYou got something to say, mate,\r\nyou say it.\r\n\r\n2004\r\n02:24:01,291 --> 02:24:04,708\r\nThe $11,500 fortune waitin'\r\nfor you back at Candyland\r\n\r\n2005\r\n02:24:04,708 --> 02:24:07,000\r\nis in the form of a\r\n\"Wanted Dead or Alive\" bounty\r\n\r\n2006\r\n02:24:07,000 --> 02:24:09,500\r\non Smitty Bacall\r\nand the Bacall Gang.\r\n\r\n2007\r\n02:24:09,500 --> 02:24:11,083\r\nWho the fuck is Smitty Bacall?\r\n\r\n2008\r\n02:24:11,083 --> 02:24:14,708\r\nSmitty Bacall is the leader\r\nof this murderous gang\r\nof stagecoach robbers,\r\n\r\n2009\r\n02:24:14,708 --> 02:24:16,291\r\nthe Bacall Gang.\r\n\r\n2010\r\n02:24:16,291 --> 02:24:19,791\r\nThere's a $7,000 \"Wanted Dead\r\nor Alive\" bounty on him,\r\n\r\n2011\r\n02:24:19,791 --> 02:24:23,291\r\n$1,500 for each\r\nof his three accomplices:\r\n\r\n2012\r\n02:24:23,291 --> 02:24:26,708\r\nDandy Michaels, Gerald Nash,\r\n\r\n2013\r\n02:24:26,708 --> 02:24:29,583\r\nand Crazy Craig Koons.\r\n\r\n2014\r\n02:24:29,583 --> 02:24:31,125\r\nNow, all four of them gentlemen,\r\n\r\n2015\r\n02:24:31,125 --> 02:24:33,500\r\nthey back there at Candyland\r\nlaughing their ass off.\r\n\r\n2016\r\n02:24:33,500 --> 02:24:37,333\r\nYou know why? 'Cause they\r\njust got away with murder.\r\n\r\n2017\r\n02:24:37,333 --> 02:24:39,041\r\nBut it ain't got to be that way.\r\n\r\n2018\r\n02:24:39,041 --> 02:24:40,958\r\nYou and your mates,\r\ny'all can ride back there\r\n\r\n2019\r\n02:24:40,958 --> 02:24:42,416\r\nand y'all can\r\ngo get that money.\r\n\r\n2020\r\n02:24:42,416 --> 02:24:43,750\r\nWhat'd these jokers do again?\r\n\r\n2021\r\n02:24:43,750 --> 02:24:47,125\r\nThese sons of bitches,\r\nthey killed innocent people.\r\n\r\n2022\r\n02:24:47,125 --> 02:24:51,750\r\nStagecoach robbery.\r\nInnocent white people.\r\n\r\n2023\r\n02:24:51,750 --> 02:24:54,916\r\nI got the handbill right here in\r\nmy pocket, if you let me get it.\r\n\r\n2024\r\n02:24:54,916 --> 02:24:56,250\r\nGet it out.\r\n\r\n2025\r\n02:24:57,750 --> 02:25:03,125\r\n[man 1] \"Wanted. Dead or alive.\r\nSmitty Bacall and the Smitty\r\nBacall Gang.\"\r\n\r\n2026\r\n02:25:03,125 --> 02:25:04,541\r\n- [man 2] But you're a slave.\r\n- [man 1] \"For murder...\"\r\n\r\n2027\r\n02:25:04,541 --> 02:25:05,833\r\n[Django]\r\nI ain't no goddamn slave.\r\n\r\n2028\r\n02:25:05,833 --> 02:25:07,333\r\n[man 1]\r\n\"...and stagecoach robbery.\"\r\n\r\n2029\r\n02:25:07,333 --> 02:25:08,750\r\nDo I sound like a fuckin' slave?\r\n\r\n2030\r\n02:25:08,750 --> 02:25:10,458\r\n- [man 1]\r\n\"$7,000 for Smitty Bacall.\"\r\n- Hm?\r\n\r\n2031\r\n02:25:10,458 --> 02:25:13,583\r\n- [man 2] That's a shitload.\r\n- I'm a bounty hunter.\r\n\r\n2032\r\n02:25:14,750 --> 02:25:17,583\r\nYesterday, as a free man,\r\n\r\n2033\r\n02:25:17,583 --> 02:25:22,166\r\nI rode into Candyland on a horse\r\nwith my German white partner,\r\n\r\n2034\r\n02:25:22,166 --> 02:25:23,958\r\nDr. King Schultz.\r\n\r\n2035\r\n02:25:23,958 --> 02:25:28,666\r\nWe tracked the Bacall Gang all\r\nthe way from Texas to Chickasaw\r\nCounty.\r\n\r\n2036\r\n02:25:28,666 --> 02:25:31,958\r\nWe finally found their ass\r\nlayin' low in Candyland.\r\n\r\n2037\r\n02:25:31,958 --> 02:25:35,583\r\nWe went in there to get 'em,\r\nthings went sour,\r\n\r\n2038\r\n02:25:35,583 --> 02:25:38,958\r\nmy partner got killed,\r\nCalvin Candie got shot,\r\n\r\n2039\r\n02:25:38,958 --> 02:25:43,500\r\nthen everybody there decided\r\nto blame me, so here I am.\r\n\r\n2040\r\n02:25:45,291 --> 02:25:47,416\r\nBut y'all know I ain't\r\non that manifest.\r\n\r\n2041\r\n02:25:47,416 --> 02:25:50,416\r\nAnd all y'all know I ain't\r\nsupposed to be on this trip.\r\n\r\n2042\r\n02:25:50,416 --> 02:25:53,916\r\nBut them four men is still back\r\nthere, they're still wanted,\r\n\r\n2043\r\n02:25:53,916 --> 02:25:57,250\r\nand that 11,500 is up for grabs,\r\nand the last thing they'd expect\r\n\r\n2044\r\n02:25:57,250 --> 02:25:59,791\r\nis y'all ridin' back in there\r\nand gettin' it.\r\n\r\n2045\r\n02:25:59,791 --> 02:26:01,708\r\n[man 1] What's the deal?\r\n\r\n2046\r\n02:26:01,708 --> 02:26:05,208\r\nYou tell us who they are\r\nand we turn you loose?\r\n\r\n2047\r\n02:26:05,208 --> 02:26:08,208\r\nNo, no, no, no. I ain't gonna\r\ntell you who they are.\r\n\r\n2048\r\n02:26:08,208 --> 02:26:12,000\r\nBut, you give me a pistol,\r\none of them horses,\r\n\r\n2049\r\n02:26:12,000 --> 02:26:16,750\r\nand $500 of that 11,500,\r\nand I'll point 'em out to you.\r\n\r\n2050\r\n02:26:16,750 --> 02:26:18,750\r\nThis is a real handbill.\r\n\r\n2051\r\n02:26:18,750 --> 02:26:19,916\r\nNow just 'cause\r\nit's a real handbill\r\n\r\n2052\r\n02:26:19,916 --> 02:26:22,083\r\ndoesn't mean that other\r\nbunch of malarkey is.\r\n\r\n2053\r\n02:26:22,083 --> 02:26:28,250\r\nNow why would a slave have a\r\n\"Wanted Dead or Alive\" handbill\r\nin his pocket?\r\n\r\n2054\r\n02:26:32,625 --> 02:26:35,750\r\nDid that black ride\r\ninto Candyland yesterday?\r\n\r\n2055\r\n02:26:41,916 --> 02:26:46,041\r\nAll right,\r\nI'm gonna ask you again.\r\n\r\n2056\r\n02:26:47,083 --> 02:26:50,458\r\nI want you to remember,\r\nI don't like liars.\r\n\r\n2057\r\n02:26:50,458 --> 02:26:52,375\r\nIs he a Candyland slave,\r\n\r\n2058\r\n02:26:52,375 --> 02:26:56,250\r\nor did he ride in with a white\r\nman on a horse yesterday?\r\n\r\n2059\r\n02:26:56,250 --> 02:27:00,083\r\nYeah. They walked us\r\nfrom the Greenville auction,\r\n\r\n2060\r\n02:27:00,083 --> 02:27:02,875\r\nand he rode in on a horse\r\nwith a white man.\r\n\r\n2061\r\n02:27:02,875 --> 02:27:07,750\r\nNow this white man,\r\nwas the black his slave?\r\n\r\n2062\r\n02:27:07,750 --> 02:27:09,375\r\nHe weren't no slave.\r\n\r\n2063\r\n02:27:09,375 --> 02:27:13,458\r\n- You fuckin' sure about that?\r\n- Damn sure.\r\n\r\n2064\r\n02:27:17,166 --> 02:27:20,958\r\n- What happened over in\r\nCandyland