ge>� P@rM!NdeR M@nk�� �\r\n<font color=white>Mobile - +919815899536\r\n<font color=green>EMail - parminder222536@hotmail.com\r\n\r\n26\r\n00:00:36,578 --> 00:00:38,412\r\n(MAN CHATTERING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)\r\n\r\n27\r\n00:01:28,422 --> 00:01:32,341\r\n(SCREAMING)\r\n\r\n28\r\n00:02:15,469 --> 00:02:17,470\r\nThe Hovitos are near.\r\n\r\n29\r\n00:02:17,721 --> 00:02:18,721\r\n(SPITS)\r\n\r\n30\r\n00:02:18,805 --> 00:02:21,057\r\nThe poison is still fresh, three days.\r\n\r\n31\r\n00:02:21,141 --> 00:02:22,808\r\nThey're following us.\r\n\r\n32\r\n00:02:24,144 --> 00:02:27,813\r\nIf they knew we were here, they would've killed us already.\r\n\r\n33\r\n00:02:27,981 --> 00:02:30,024\r\n(ANIMALS CHATTERING)\r\n\r\n34\r\n00:03:14,444 --> 00:03:15,528\r\n(GUN FIRES)\r\n\r\n35\r\n00:03:53,150 --> 00:03:54,859\r\nThis is it.\r\n\r\n36\r\n00:03:54,985 --> 00:03:56,819\r\nThis is where Forrestal cashed in.\r\n\r\n37\r\n00:03:57,154 --> 00:03:59,071\r\n- SATIPO: A friend of yours?\r\n- A competitor.\r\n\r\n38\r\n00:03:59,406 --> 00:04:01,782\r\nHe was good.\r\n\r\n39\r\n00:04:01,908 --> 00:04:03,492\r\nHe was very, very good.\r\n\r\n40\r\n00:04:03,577 --> 00:04:07,413\r\nSe�or, nobody's come out of there alive.\r\n\r\n41\r\n00:04:07,497 --> 00:04:09,498\r\nPlease...\r\n\r\n42\r\n00:04:46,244 --> 00:04:47,453\r\nSe�or.\r\n\r\n43\r\n00:05:00,634 --> 00:05:03,052\r\n(WHIMPERING SOFTLY)\r\n\r\n44\r\n00:05:16,566 --> 00:05:17,691\r\nStop.\r\n\r\n45\r\n00:05:18,527 --> 00:05:19,819\r\nStay out of the light.\r\n\r\n46\r\n00:05:34,876 --> 00:05:36,252\r\n(SCREAMING)\r\n\r\n47\r\n00:05:42,425 --> 00:05:43,884\r\nForrestal.\r\n\r\n48\r\n00:05:44,761 --> 00:05:45,761\r\n(WHIP CRACKS)\r\n\r\n49\r\n00:06:30,599 --> 00:06:31,392\r\nSATIPO: Let us hurry.\r\n\r\n50\r\n00:06:31,418 --> 00:06:32,625\r\nThere is nothing to fear here.\r\n\r\n51\r\n00:06:35,770 --> 00:06:37,146\r\nThat's what scares me.\r\n\r\n52\r\n00:06:56,082 --> 00:06:57,333\r\nStay here.\r\n\r\n53\r\n00:06:57,542 --> 00:06:59,168\r\nIf you insist, se�or.\r\n\r\n54\r\n00:07:13,016 --> 00:07:14,099\r\n(WINCES)\r\n\r\n55\r\n00:08:07,988 --> 00:08:11,490\r\n(RUMBLING)\r\n\r\n56\r\n00:08:17,831 --> 00:08:19,999\r\n(ARROWS WHIZZING)\r\n\r\n57\r\n00:08:25,755 --> 00:08:26,922\r\nGive me the whip.\r\n\r\n58\r\n00:08:27,048 --> 00:08:28,215\r\nThrow me the idol.\r\n\r\n59\r\n00:08:30,719 --> 00:08:31,927\r\nNo time to argue.\r\n\r\n60\r\n00:08:32,095 --> 00:08:33,095\r\nThrow me the idol, I throw you the whip.\r\n\r\n61\r\n00:08:34,431 --> 00:08:35,889\r\nGive me the whip!\r\n\r\n62\r\n00:08:35,974 --> 00:08:37,641\r\nAdi�s, se�or.\r\n\r\n63\r\n00:09:11,551 --> 00:09:12,968\r\n(LOUD RUMBLE)\r\n\r\n64\r\n00:09:14,137 --> 00:09:15,220\r\n(GASPS)\r\n\r\n65\r\n00:09:21,102 --> 00:09:22,478\r\nAdi�s, Satipo.\r\n\r\n66\r\n00:09:22,645 --> 00:09:23,979\r\n(RUMBLING)\r\n\r\n67\r\n00:09:40,872 --> 00:09:41,997\r\n(GRUNTS)\r\n\r\n68\r\n00:10:02,977 --> 00:10:04,478\r\nDr. Jones.\r\n\r\n69\r\n00:10:04,896 --> 00:10:07,356\r\nAgain we see there is nothing you can possess\r\n\r\n70\r\n00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:09,066\r\nwhich I cannot take away.\r\n\r\n71\r\n00:10:09,484 --> 00:10:11,068\r\nAnd you thought I had given up.\r\n\r\n72\r\n00:10:22,664 --> 00:10:24,234\r\nYou chose the wrong friends.\r\n\r\n73\r\n00:10:24,260 --> 00:10:25,941\r\nThis time, it will cost you.\r\n\r\n74\r\n00:10:29,504 --> 00:10:33,841\r\nToo bad the Hovitos don't know you the way I do, Belloq.\r\n\r\n75\r\n00:10:34,384 --> 00:10:35,926\r\nYes, too bad.\r\n\r\n76\r\n00:10:36,761 --> 00:10:40,764\r\nYou could warn them, if only you spoke Hovitos.\r\n\r\n77\r\n00:10:41,724 --> 00:10:43,058\r\n(SPEAKING HOVITOS)\r\n\r\n78\r\n00:10:48,439 --> 00:10:49,648\r\n(MAKES CUTTING SOUNDS)\r\n\r\n79\r\n00:10:49,732 --> 00:10:51,441\r\n(MEN SHOUTING)\r\n\r\n80\r\n00:10:53,570 --> 00:10:54,570\r\n(LAUGHING TRIUMPHANTLY)\r\n\r\n81\r\n00:11:08,626 --> 00:11:09,751\r\n(BIRDS CHIRPING)\r\n\r\n82\r\n00:11:27,812 --> 00:11:29,146\r\nJock! Start the engines!\r\n\r\n83\r\n00:11:29,939 --> 00:11:30,939\r\nGet it up!\r\n\r\n84\r\n00:11:35,069 --> 00:11:36,820\r\nJock, the engines!\r\n\r\n85\r\n00:11:37,655 --> 00:11:39,281\r\nStart the engines, Jock!\r\n\r\n86\r\n00:12:00,470 --> 00:12:01,511\r\n(ARROWS WHIZZING)\r\n\r\n87\r\n00:12:28,790 --> 00:12:31,041\r\nThere's a big snake in the plane, Jock!\r\n\r\n88\r\n00:12:31,834 --> 00:12:34,378\r\nOh, that's just my pet snake Reggie!\r\n\r\n89\r\n00:12:35,255 --> 00:12:37,005\r\nI hate snakes, Jock!\r\n\r\n90\r\n00:12:37,090 --> 00:12:38,215\r\nI hate 'em!\r\n\r\n91\r\n00:12:38,508 --> 00:12:39,050\r\nCome on!\r\n\r\n92\r\n00:12:39,076 --> 00:12:41,243\r\nShow a little backbone, will ya?\r\n\r\n93\r\n00:12:57,986 --> 00:12:59,278\r\n\"Neo,\" meaning \"new\"\r\n\r\n94\r\n00:12:59,362 --> 00:13:03,073\r\nand \"Lithic\"... \"I-T-H\"...\r\n\r\n95\r\n00:13:03,199 --> 00:13:05,993\r\n\"...I-C,\" meaning \"stone.\"\r\n\r\n96\r\n00:13:06,202 --> 00:13:07,786\r\nAll right, let's get back to this site:\r\n\r\n97\r\n00:13:07,870 --> 00:13:09,454\r\nTurkdean Barrow, near Hazelton.\r\n\r\n98\r\n00:13:09,539 --> 00:13:14,334\r\nContains a central passage and three chambers, or cysts...\r\n\r\n99\r\n00:13:19,882 --> 00:13:23,218\r\n...don't confuse that with robbing, in which case we mean\r\n\r\n100\r\n00:13:23,553 --> 00:13:26,305\r\nthe removal of the contents of the barrow.\r\n\r\n101\r\n00:13:26,389 --> 00:13:28,307\r\nThis site also demonstrates...\r\n\r\n102\r\n00:13:31,019 --> 00:13:32,978\r\n...one of the great dangers of archeology,\r\n\r\n103\r\n00:13:33,062 --> 00:13:36,231\r\nnot to life and limb, although that does sometimes take place.\r\n\r\n104\r\n00:13:36,357 --> 00:13:38,650\r\nNo, I'm talking about folklore.\r\n\r\n105\r\n00:13:38,735 --> 00:13:40,444\r\nIn this case, local tradition held\r\n\r\n106\r\n00:13:40,570 --> 00:13:43,989\r\nthat there was a golden coffin buried at the site,\r\n\r\n107\r\n00:13:44,073 --> 00:13:47,326\r\nand this accounts for the holes dug all over the barrow\r\n\r\n108\r\n00:13:47,410 --> 00:13:49,703\r\nand the generally poor condition of the find.\r\n\r\n109\r\n00:13:49,787 --> 00:13:52,706\r\nHowever, chamber three was undisturbed,\r\n\r\n110\r\n00:13:52,790 --> 00:13:54,416\r\nand the undisturbed chamber and the grave goods\r\n\r\n111\r\n00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:55,917\r\nthat were found in another, uh...\r\n\r\n112\r\n00:13:56,419 --> 00:13:58,337\r\nin the area, give us a r...\r\n\r\n113\r\n00:14:00,256 --> 00:14:01,548\r\nUh...\r\n\r\n114\r\n00:14:02,925 --> 00:14:05,969\r\n...reason to da...\r\nto, uh, to-to date this,\r\n\r\n115\r\n00:14:06,054 --> 00:14:07,346\r\nuh, find as we have.\r\n\r\n116\r\n00:14:07,430 --> 00:14:08,597\r\n(BELL RINGING)\r\n\r\n117\r\n00:14:08,890 --> 00:14:10,140\r\nUm... Any questions, then?\r\n\r\n118\r\n00:14:10,933 --> 00:14:12,726\r\nNo? Okay, that's it for the day, then.\r\n\r\n119\r\n00:14:13,770 --> 00:14:15,479\r\nUm, don't forget...\r\n\r\n120\r\n00:14:15,563 --> 00:14:19,358\r\nMichaelson, chapters four and five for next time.\r\n\r\n121\r\n00:14:19,442 --> 00:14:22,152\r\nAnd I will be in my office on Thursday, but not Wednesday.\r\n\r\n122\r\n00:14:32,246 --> 00:14:33,330\r\nI had it, Marcus.\r\n\r\n123\r\n00:14:33,414 --> 00:14:35,707\r\nI had it in my hand.\r\n\r\n124\r\n00:14:35,792 --> 00:14:37,626\r\n- What happened?\r\n- Guess.\r\n\r\n125\r\n00:14:38,503 --> 00:14:39,544\r\n(CHUCKLES)\r\n\r\n126\r\n00:14:39,629 --> 00:14:41,546\r\n- Belloq?\r\n- You want to hear about it?\r\n\r\n127\r\n00:14:41,631 --> 00:14:43,215\r\nNot at all.\r\n\r\n128\r\n00:14:43,299 --> 00:14:45,092\r\nI'm sure everything you do for the museum\r\n\r\n129\r\n00:14:45,176 --> 00:14:48,303\r\nconforms to the International Treaty for the Protection of Antiquities.\r\n\r\n130\r\n00:14:48,429 --> 00:14:49,638\r\nIt's beautiful, Marcus.\r\n\r\n131\r\n00:14:49,722 --> 00:14:50,345\r\nI can get it.\r\n\r\n132\r\n00:14:50,371 --> 00:14:51,665\r\nI got it all figured out.\r\n\r\n133\r\n00:14:51,808 --> 00:14:53,350\r\nThere's only one place he can sell it: Marrakech.\r\n\r\n134\r\n00:14:53,434 --> 00:14:54,726\r\nI need $2,000. Look...\r\n\r\n135\r\n00:14:54,811 --> 00:14:55,894\r\nListen to me, old boy.\r\n\r\n136\r\n00:14:55,978 --> 00:14:57,354\r\nI brought some people to see you.\r\n\r\n137\r\n00:14:57,438 --> 00:14:58,438\r\nLook.\r\n\r\n138\r\n00:14:58,523 --> 00:14:59,606\r\nI got these pieces.\r\n\r\n139\r\n00:14:59,690 --> 00:15:00,941\r\nThey're good pieces, Marcus.\r\n\r\n140\r\n00:15:01,025 --> 00:15:03,068\r\n- Look.\r\n- Indiana...\r\n\r\n141\r\n00:15:03,152 --> 00:15:06,196\r\nYes, the museum will buy them, as usual, no questions asked.\r\n\r\n142\r\n00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:06,870\r\nYes, they are nice.\r\n\r\n143\r\n00:15:06,896 --> 00:15:07,764\r\nThey're worth at least\r\n\r\n144\r\n00:15:07,824 --> 00:15:09,157\r\nthe price of a ticket to Marrakech.\r\n\r\n145\r\n00:15:09,283 --> 00:15:10,492\r\nBut the people I brought are important,\r\n\r\n146\r\n00:15:10,576 --> 00:15:11,300\r\nand they're waiting.\r\n\r\n147\r\n00:15:11,326 --> 00:15:11,977\r\nWhat people?\r\n\r\n148\r\n00:15:12,036 --> 00:15:13,912\r\nArmy Intelligence.\r\n\r\n149\r\n00:15:14,122 --> 00:15:15,622\r\nThey knew you were coming before I did.\r\n\r\n150\r\n00:15:15,915 --> 00:15:17,165\r\nSeem to know everything.\r\n\r\n151\r\n00:15:17,708 --> 00:15:19,251\r\nThey wouldn't tell me what they want.\r\n\r\n152\r\n00:15:19,377 --> 00:15:21,336\r\nWell, what do I want to see them for?\r\n\r\n153\r\n00:15:21,421 --> 00:15:23,338\r\nWhat am I, in trouble?\r\n\r\n154\r\n00:15:23,673 --> 00:15:24,798\r\nEATON: Yes, Dr. Jones,\r\n\r\n155\r\n00:15:24,882 --> 00:15:26,341\r\nwe've heard a great deal about you.\r\n\r\n156\r\n00:15:26,426 --> 00:15:28,135\r\nINDY: Have you?\r\n\r\n157\r\n00:15:28,219 --> 00:15:30,429\r\nUh, professor of archeology,\r\n\r\n158\r\n00:15:30,513 --> 00:15:32,180\r\nexpert on the occult,\r\n\r\n159\r\n00:15:32,265 --> 00:15:33,807\r\nand, uh, how does one say it?\r\n\r\n160\r\n00:15:33,891 --> 00:15:36,560\r\nObtainer of rare antiquities.\r\n\r\n161\r\n00:15:36,686 --> 00:15:37,769\r\nThat's one way of saying it.\r\n\r\n162\r\n00:15:37,854 --> 00:15:38,407\r\nWhy don't you sit down?\r\n\r\n163\r\n00:15:38,433 --> 00:15:39,129\r\nYou'll be more comfortable.\r\n\r\n164\r\n00:15:39,188 --> 00:15:40,689\r\n- Oh, thank you.\r\n- Thank you.\r\n\r\n165\r\n00:15:40,773 --> 00:15:44,067\r\nYes, you're a man of many talents.\r\n\r\n166\r\n00:15:44,277 --> 00:15:46,486\r\nNow, you studied under Professor Ravenwood\r\n\r\n167\r\n00:15:46,612 --> 00:15:48,280\r\nat the University of Chicago.\r\n\r\n168\r\n00:15:48,406 --> 00:15:50,615\r\nYes, I did.\r\n\r\n169\r\n00:15:50,700 --> 00:15:53,243\r\nYou have no idea of his present whereabouts?\r\n\r\n170\r\n00:15:54,495 --> 00:15:56,621\r\nUh... well, just rumors, really.\r\n\r\n171\r\n00:15:56,706 --> 00:15:58,373\r\nSomewhere in Asia, I think.\r\n\r\n172\r\n00:15:58,458 --> 00:16:00,125\r\nI haven't really spoken to him for ten years.\r\n\r\n173\r\n00:16:00,209 --> 00:16:02,794\r\nWe were friends, but, uh...\r\n\r\n174\r\n00:16:02,879 --> 00:16:05,088\r\nhad a bit of a falling out, I'm afraid.\r\n\r\n175\r\n00:16:05,173 --> 00:16:06,339\r\nMmm.\r\n\r\n176\r\n00:16:06,716 --> 00:16:08,967\r\nDr. Jones, now, you must understand\r\n\r\n177\r\n00:16:09,093 --> 00:16:11,761\r\nthat this is all strictly confidential, eh?\r\n\r\n178\r\n00:16:11,846 --> 00:16:12,804\r\nI understand.\r\n\r\n179\r\n00:16:12,889 --> 00:16:15,265\r\nUh... (CLEARS THROAT)\r\n\r\n180\r\n00:16:15,349 --> 00:16:18,894\r\nYesterday afternoon, our European sections\r\n\r\n181\r\n00:16:18,978 --> 00:16:21,730\r\nintercepted a...\r\na German communiqu�\r\n\r\n182\r\n00:16:21,898 --> 00:16:24,232\r\nthat was sent from Cairo to Berlin.\r\n\r\n183\r\n00:16:24,775 --> 00:16:25,351\r\nNow, to Cairo...\r\n\r\n184\r\n00:16:25,377 --> 00:16:26,635\r\nSee, over the last two years,\r\n\r\n185\r\n00:16:26,736 --> 00:16:28,695\r\nthe Nazis have had teams of archeologists\r\n\r\n186\r\n00:16:28,779 --> 00:16:32,741\r\nrunning around the world looking for all kinds of religious artifacts.\r\n\r\n187\r\n00:16:33,034 --> 00:16:34,367\r\nHitler's a nut on the subject.\r\n\r\n188\r\n00:16:34,452 --> 00:16:35,494\r\nHe's crazy.\r\n\r\n189\r\n00:16:35,578 --> 00:16:37,621\r\nHe's obsessed with the occult.\r\n\r\n190\r\n00:16:37,747 --> 00:16:39,331\r\nAnd, right now, apparently,\r\n\r\n191\r\n00:16:39,415 --> 00:16:41,833\r\nthere's some kind of German archeological dig\r\n\r\n192\r\n00:16:41,918 --> 00:16:44,002\r\ngoing on in the desert outside of Cairo.\r\n\r\n193\r\n00:16:44,086 --> 00:16:45,587\r\nNow, we've got some information here,\r\n\r\n194\r\n00:16:45,671 --> 00:16:48,215\r\nbut we can't make anything out of it, and maybe you can.\r\n\r\n195\r\n00:16:49,342 --> 00:16:52,177\r\n\"Tanis development proceeding.\r\n\r\n196\r\n00:16:52,637 --> 00:16:56,473\r\n\"Acquire headpiece, Staff of Ra.\r\n\r\n197\r\n00:16:56,641 --> 00:16:58,725\r\n\"Abner Ravenwood, U.S.\"\r\n\r\n198\r\n00:17:00,102 --> 00:17:02,395\r\nThe Nazis have discovered Tanis.\r\n\r\n199\r\n00:17:02,480 --> 00:17:05,565\r\nEATON: Just what does that mean to you, uh, Tanis?\r\n\r\n200\r\n00:17:05,650 --> 00:17:06,691\r\nWell, it...\r\n\r\n201\r\n00:17:06,776 --> 00:17:09,194\r\nThe city of Tanis is one of the possible resting places of the Lost Ark.\r\n\r\n202\r\n00:17:09,487 --> 00:17:10,946\r\nThe Lost Ark?\r\n\r\n203\r\n00:17:11,072 --> 00:17:12,280\r\nYeah, the Ark of the Covenant.\r\n\r\n204\r\n00:17:12,448 --> 00:17:13,532\r\nThe chest the Hebrews used\r\n\r\n205\r\n00:17:13,616 --> 00:17:14,950\r\nto carry around the Ten Commandments.\r\n\r\n206\r\n00:17:15,034 --> 00:17:16,117\r\nWhat do you mean, \"commandments\"?\r\n\r\n207\r\n00:17:16,202 --> 00:17:17,702\r\nYou talking about the Ten Commandments?\r\n\r\n208\r\n00:17:17,787 --> 00:17:19,871\r\nYes, the actual Ten Commandments.\r\n\r\n209\r\n00:17:19,956 --> 00:17:21,456\r\nThe original stone tablets\r\n\r\n210\r\n00:17:21,541 --> 00:17:23,500\r\nthat Moses brought down out of Mount Horeb and smashed,\r\n\r\n211\r\n00:17:23,626 --> 00:17:25,627\r\nif you believe in that sort of thing.\r\n\r\n212\r\n00:17:26,879 --> 00:17:28,588\r\nAny of you guys ever go to Sunday school?\r\n\r\n213\r\n00:17:28,673 --> 00:17:30,674\r\n- Well, I...\r\n- Oh, look.\r\n\r\n214\r\n00:17:30,758 --> 00:17:32,342\r\nThe Hebrews took the broken pieces\r\n\r\n215\r\n00:17:32,426 --> 00:17:33,482\r\nand put them in the Ark.\r\n\r\n216\r\n00:17:33,508 --> 00:17:34,828\r\nWhen they settled in Canaan,\r\n\r\n217\r\n00:17:35,012 --> 00:17:37,514\r\nthey put the Ark in a place called the Temple of Solomon.\r\n\r\n218\r\n00:17:37,598 --> 00:17:38,640\r\nIn Jerusalem.\r\n\r\n219\r\n00:17:38,724 --> 00:17:40,225\r\nWhere it stayed for many years.\r\n\r\n220\r\n00:17:40,309 --> 00:17:42,394\r\nUntil, all of a sudden, whoosh, it's gone.\r\n\r\n221\r\n00:17:42,478 --> 00:17:43,645\r\nWhere?\r\n\r\n222\r\n00:17:43,729 --> 00:17:45,605\r\nWell, nobody knows where or when.\r\n\r\n223\r\n00:17:45,690 --> 00:17:47,566\r\nHowever, an Egyptian pharaoh...\r\n\r\n224\r\n00:17:47,650 --> 00:17:48,650\r\n- Shishak.\r\n- Yes.\r\n\r\n225\r\n00:17:48,734 --> 00:17:51,486\r\n...invaded the city of Jerusalem right about 980 BC,\r\n\r\n226\r\n00:17:51,571 --> 00:17:54,531\r\nand he may have taken the Ark back to the city of Tanis\r\n\r\n227\r\n00:17:54,615 --> 00:17:56,533\r\nand hidden it in a secret chamber\r\n\r\n228\r\n00:17:56,617 --> 00:17:57,867\r\ncalled the Well of Souls.\r\n\r\n229\r\n00:17:58,452 --> 00:17:59,536\r\nSecret chamber?\r\n\r\n230\r\n00:17:59,620 --> 00:18:01,246\r\nBRODY: However, about a year\r\n\r\n231\r\n00:18:01,330 --> 00:18:03,498\r\nafter the pharaoh would return to Egypt,\r\n\r\n232\r\n00:18:03,666 --> 00:18:06,835\r\nthe city of Tanis was consumed by the desert\r\n\r\n233\r\n00:18:06,961 --> 00:18:10,005\r\nin a sandstorm which lasted a whole year.\r\n\r\n234\r\n00:18:10,172 --> 00:18:12,340\r\nWiped clean by the wrath of God.\r\n\r\n235\r\n00:18:14,677 --> 00:18:16,094\r\nUh-huh.\r\n\r\n236\r\n00:18:16,178 --> 00:18:17,887\r\nObviously, we've come to the right men.\r\n\r\n237\r\n00:18:17,972 --> 00:18:19,514\r\nNow you seem to know, uh,\r\n\r\n238\r\n00:18:19,682 --> 00:18:20,849\r\nall about this Tanis, then.\r\n\r\n239\r\n00:18:21,183 --> 00:18:22,350\r\nNo, no, not really.\r\n\r\n240\r\n00:18:22,435 --> 00:18:24,853\r\nRavenwood is the real expert.\r\n\r\n241\r\n00:18:24,979 --> 00:18:26,938\r\nAbner did the first serious work on Tanis.\r\n\r\n242\r\n00:18:27,064 --> 00:18:29,566\r\nCollected some of its relics.\r\n\r\n243\r\n00:18:29,775 --> 00:18:32,444\r\nIt was his obsession, really.\r\n\r\n244\r\n00:18:32,528 --> 00:18:33,862\r\nBut he never found the city.\r\n\r\n245\r\n00:18:33,946 --> 00:18:37,282\r\nFrankly, we're somewhat suspicious of Mr. Ravenwood.\r\n\r\n246\r\n00:18:37,366 --> 00:18:39,034\r\nAn American being mentioned so prominently\r\n\r\n247\r\n00:18:39,160 --> 00:18:41,286\r\nin a secret Nazi cable.\r\n\r\n248\r\n00:18:41,370 --> 00:18:43,705\r\nOh, rubbish. Ravenwood's no Nazi.\r\n\r\n249\r\n00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:45,540\r\nWell, what do the Nazis want him for, then?\r\n\r\n250\r\n00:18:46,250 --> 00:18:48,084\r\nWell, obviously, the Nazis are looking\r\n\r\n251\r\n00:18:48,169 --> 00:18:49,961\r\nfor the headpiece to the Staff of Ra\r\n\r\n252\r\n00:18:50,212 --> 00:18:52,255\r\nand they think Abner's got it.\r\n\r\n253\r\n00:18:52,340 --> 00:18:55,008\r\nWhat exactly is a headpiece to the Staff of Ra?\r\n\r\n254\r\n00:18:55,217 --> 00:18:56,593\r\nWell, the staff is just a stick...\r\n\r\n255\r\n00:18:56,719 --> 00:18:57,927\r\nI don't know, about this big,\r\n\r\n256\r\n00:18:58,137 --> 00:18:59,763\r\nnobody really knows for sure how high...\r\n\r\n257\r\n00:18:59,847 --> 00:19:02,849\r\nAnd it's... it's, uh...\r\nit's capped\r\n\r\n258\r\n00:19:02,933 --> 00:19:05,435\r\nwith an elaborate headpiece...\r\n\r\n259\r\n00:19:05,519 --> 00:19:08,480\r\nin the shape of the sun, with a crystal in the center.\r\n\r\n260\r\n00:19:08,564 --> 00:19:10,148\r\nAnd what you did was\r\n\r\n261\r\n00:19:10,232 --> 00:19:12,984\r\nyou take the staff to a special room in Tanis...\r\n\r\n262\r\n00:19:13,069 --> 00:19:14,402\r\nA map room with a miniature\r\n\r\n263\r\n00:19:14,487 --> 00:19:15,904\r\nof the city all laid out on the floor,\r\n\r\n264\r\n00:19:16,280 --> 00:19:17,989\r\nand if you put the staff in a certain place,\r\n\r\n265\r\n00:19:18,074 --> 00:19:20,950\r\nat a certain time of day, the sun shone through here\r\n\r\n266\r\n00:19:21,035 --> 00:19:24,788\r\nand made a beam that came down on the floor here...\r\n\r\n267\r\n00:19:24,872 --> 00:19:27,791\r\nand gave you the exact location of the Well of the Souls.\r\n\r\n268\r\n00:19:28,084 --> 00:19:30,293\r\nWhere the Ark of the Covenant was kept, right?\r\n\r\n269\r\n00:19:30,419 --> 00:19:32,629\r\nWhich is exactly what the Nazis are looking for.\r\n\r\n270\r\n00:19:32,713 --> 00:19:34,964\r\nWhat does this Ark look like?\r\n\r\n271\r\n00:19:35,216 --> 00:19:36,383\r\nUh...\r\n\r\n272\r\n00:19:36,884 --> 00:19:38,760\r\nINDY: There's a picture of it right here.\r\n\r\n273\r\n00:19:43,474 --> 00:19:45,266\r\nThat's it.\r\n\r\n274\r\n00:19:51,941 --> 00:19:53,108\r\nEATON: Good God.\r\n\r\n275\r\n00:19:53,275 --> 00:19:55,735\r\nYes, that's just what the Hebrews thought.\r\n\r\n276\r\n00:19:56,028 --> 00:19:57,195\r\nUh...\r\n\r\n277\r\n00:19:57,279 --> 00:19:59,739\r\nnow, what's that supposed to be coming out of there?\r\n\r\n278\r\n00:19:59,824 --> 00:20:01,491\r\nINDY: Lightning...\r\n\r\n279\r\n00:20:01,575 --> 00:20:03,535\r\nfire...\r\n\r\n280\r\n00:20:03,661 --> 00:20:05,787\r\npower of God or something.\r\n\r\n281\r\n00:20:07,623 --> 00:20:08,665\r\nEATON: I'm beginning to understand\r\n\r\n282\r\n00:20:08,749 --> 00:20:10,166\r\nHitler's interest in this.\r\n\r\n283\r\n00:20:10,292 --> 00:20:11,626\r\nBRODY: Oh, yes.\r\n\r\n284\r\n00:20:11,711 --> 00:20:13,878\r\nThe Bible speaks of the Ark leveling mountains,\r\n\r\n285\r\n00:20:13,963 --> 00:20:17,465\r\nand laying waste to entire regions.\r\n\r\n286\r\n00:20:17,550 --> 00:20:21,428\r\nAn army which carries the Ark before it...\r\n\r\n287\r\n00:20:21,512 --> 00:20:22,971\r\nis invincible.\r\n\r\n288\r\n00:20:43,534 --> 00:20:45,535\r\nYou did it, didn't you?\r\n\r\n289\r\n00:20:45,786 --> 00:20:47,245\r\nThey want you to go for it.\r\n\r\n290\r\n00:20:47,329 --> 00:20:49,748\r\n(LAUGHING) Oh, Marcus!\r\n\r\n291\r\n00:20:49,832 --> 00:20:52,542\r\nThey want you to get a hold of the Ark before the Nazis do\r\n\r\n292\r\n00:20:52,626 --> 00:20:54,794\r\nand they're prepared to pay handsomely for it.\r\n\r\n293\r\n00:20:54,879 --> 00:20:56,045\r\nAnd the museum?\r\n\r\n294\r\n00:20:56,130 --> 00:20:57,380\r\nThe museum gets the Ark when we're finished?\r\n\r\n295\r\n00:20:57,465 --> 00:20:58,840\r\nOh, yes.\r\n\r\n296\r\n00:21:00,676 --> 00:21:03,386\r\nOh...\r\n\r\n297\r\n00:21:03,471 --> 00:21:05,513\r\nThe Ark of the Covenant.\r\n\r\n298\r\n00:21:05,598 --> 00:21:08,266\r\nNothing else has come close.\r\n\r\n299\r\n00:21:08,350 --> 00:21:09,559\r\nThat thing represents everything\r\n\r\n300\r\n00:21:09,643 --> 00:21:13,062\r\nwe got into archeology for in the first place.\r\n\r\n301\r\n00:21:13,147 --> 00:21:15,815\r\nMmm!\r\n\r\n302\r\n00:21:16,025 --> 00:21:18,485\r\nYou know, five years ago, I would've gone after it myself.\r\n\r\n303\r\n00:21:18,611 --> 00:21:20,779\r\nI'm really rather envious.\r\n\r\n304\r\n00:21:20,946 --> 00:21:22,947\r\nI've got to locate Abner.\r\n\r\n305\r\n00:21:23,032 --> 00:21:24,699\r\nI think I know where to start.\r\n\r\n306\r\n00:21:29,622 --> 00:21:31,790\r\nSuppose she'll still be with him?\r\n\r\n307\r\n00:21:31,874 --> 00:21:33,792\r\nPossibly, but...\r\n\r\n308\r\n00:21:33,876 --> 00:21:35,919\r\nMarion's the least of your worries right now,\r\n\r\n309\r\n00:21:36,003 --> 00:21:37,629\r\nbelieve me, Indy.\r\n\r\n310\r\n00:21:37,713 --> 00:21:39,672\r\nWhat do you mean?\r\n\r\n311\r\n00:21:39,757 --> 00:21:42,550\r\nWell, I mean that for nearly 3,000 years,\r\n\r\n312\r\n00:21:42,635 --> 00:21:46,763\r\nman has been searching for the Lost Ark.\r\n\r\n313\r\n00:21:46,847 --> 00:21:50,600\r\nNot something to be taken lightly.\r\n\r\n314\r\n00:21:50,684 --> 00:21:54,646\r\nNo one knows its secrets.\r\n\r\n315\r\n00:21:54,730 --> 00:21:58,107\r\nIt's like nothing you've ever gone after before.\r\n\r\n316\r\n00:21:58,567 --> 00:22:00,193\r\n(LAUGHING) Oh, Marcus.\r\n\r\n317\r\n00:22:00,277 --> 00:22:01,778\r\nWhat are you trying to do, scare me?\r\n\r\n318\r\n00:22:01,862 --> 00:22:02,862\r\nYou sound like my mother.\r\n\r\n319\r\n00:22:02,947 --> 00:22:04,322\r\nWe've known each other for a long time.\r\n\r\n320\r\n00:22:04,406 --> 00:22:07,992\r\nI don't believe in magic, a lot of superstitious hocus-pocus.\r\n\r\n321\r\n00:22:08,077 --> 00:22:09,202\r\nI'm going after a find\r\n\r\n322\r\n00:22:09,286 --> 00:22:11,037\r\nof incredible historical significance.\r\n\r\n323\r\n00:22:11,121 --> 00:22:12,997\r\nYou're talking about the bogeyman.\r\n\r\n324\r\n00:22:13,082 --> 00:22:15,667\r\nBesides, you know what a cautious fellow I am.\r\n\r\n325\r\n00:22:26,428 --> 00:22:28,054\r\nNice to see you again, Dr. Jones.\r\n\r\n326\r\n00:22:28,138 --> 00:22:29,138\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\n327\r\n00:23:32,578 --> 00:23:34,329\r\n(ALL CLAMORING)\r\n\r\n328\r\n00:23:42,046 --> 00:23:43,463\r\nShh... shh...\r\n\r\n329\r\n00:23:51,680 --> 00:23:54,933\r\n(MEN CHEERING)\r\n\r\n330\r\n00:24:01,649 --> 00:24:02,649\r\nShh...\r\n\r\n331\r\n00:24:10,532 --> 00:24:12,951\r\n(ALL GROANING)\r\n\r\n332\r\n00:24:15,245 --> 00:24:18,122\r\n(PEOPLE CHATTERING)\r\n\r\n333\r\n00:24:18,207 --> 00:24:19,624\r\n(EXCLAIMS IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)\r\n\r\n334\r\n00:24:20,668 --> 00:24:21,709\r\n(SPEAKS FOREIGN LANGUAGE)\r\n\r\n335\r\n00:24:29,718 --> 00:24:33,012\r\n(ALL CHEERING)\r\n\r\n336\r\n00:24:34,598 --> 00:24:36,307\r\nGive him space!\r\nGive him space!\r\n\r\n337\r\n00:24:36,392 --> 00:24:37,850\r\nGo on, Regan!\r\n\r\n338\r\n00:24:40,104 --> 00:24:42,146\r\nShh! Shh!\r\n\r\n339\r\n00:24:42,231 --> 00:24:43,690\r\nShh! Shh! Shh!\r\n\r\n340\r\n00:24:53,033 --> 00:24:56,953\r\n(ALL CHEERING)\r\n\r\n341\r\n00:24:59,081 --> 00:25:00,123\r\n(THUDS)\r\n\r\n342\r\n00:25:03,002 --> 00:25:07,672\r\n(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)\r\n\r\n343\r\n00:25:28,360 --> 00:25:29,819\r\nINDY: Hello, Marion.\r\n\r\n344\r\n00:25:32,364 --> 00:25:33,698\r\n(GLASS SHATTERING)\r\n\r\n345\r\n00:25:36,618 --> 00:25:38,453\r\nIndiana Jones.\r\n\r\n346\r\n00:25:39,830 --> 00:25:40,872\r\n(EXHALES)\r\n\r\n347\r\n00:25:41,790 --> 00:25:42,999\r\nAlways knew, someday,\r\n\r\n348\r\n00:25:43,083 --> 00:25:45,126\r\nyou'd come walking back through my door.\r\n\r\n349\r\n00:25:45,711 --> 00:25:47,462\r\nI never doubted that.\r\n\r\n350\r\n00:25:47,546 --> 00:25:49,839\r\nSomething made it inevitable.\r\n\r\n351\r\n00:25:49,923 --> 00:25:52,425\r\nSo, what are you doing here in Nepal?\r\n\r\n352\r\n00:25:52,801 --> 00:25:55,428\r\nI need one of the pieces your father collected.\r\n\r\n353\r\n00:25:55,596 --> 00:25:59,891\r\nI learned to hate you in the last ten years.\r\n\r\n354\r\n00:25:59,975 --> 00:26:01,309\r\nI never meant to hurt you.\r\n\r\n355\r\n00:26:01,393 --> 00:26:02,435\r\nI was a child.\r\n\r\n356\r\n00:26:02,519 --> 00:26:03,728\r\nI was in love.\r\n\r\n357\r\n00:26:03,896 --> 00:26:05,480\r\nIt was wrong and you knew it!\r\n\r\n358\r\n00:26:05,606 --> 00:26:06,856\r\nYou knew what you were doing.\r\n\r\n359\r\n00:26:06,940 --> 00:26:08,483\r\nNow I do!\r\nThis is my place.\r\n\r\n360\r\n00:26:08,817 --> 00:26:09,817\r\nGet out!\r\n\r\n361\r\n00:26:09,943 --> 00:26:12,236\r\n(SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)\r\n\r\n362\r\n00:26:13,238 --> 00:26:14,322\r\nI did what I did.\r\n\r\n363\r\n00:26:14,406 --> 00:26:15,490\r\nYou don't have to be happy about it,\r\n\r\n364\r\n00:26:15,574 --> 00:26:17,450\r\nbut maybe we could help each other out now.\r\n\r\n365\r\n00:26:19,411 --> 00:26:21,412\r\nI need one of the pieces your father collected.\r\n\r\n366\r\n00:26:21,497 --> 00:26:22,663\r\nBronze piece, about this size,\r\n\r\n367\r\n00:26:22,748 --> 00:26:24,916\r\nwith a hole in it, off-center, with a crystal.\r\n\r\n368\r\n00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:26,084\r\nYou know the one I mean?\r\n\r\n369\r\n00:26:26,168 --> 00:26:27,794\r\nYeah.\r\n\r\n370\r\n00:26:27,878 --> 00:26:29,087\r\nI know it.\r\n\r\n371\r\n00:26:29,171 --> 00:26:31,214\r\nWhere's Abner?\r\n\r\n372\r\n00:26:31,298 --> 00:26:33,716\r\nWhere's Abner?\r\n\r\n373\r\n00:26:33,801 --> 00:26:35,009\r\nAbner's dead.\r\n\r\n374\r\n00:26:40,224 --> 00:26:43,101\r\nMarion, I'm sorry.\r\n\r\n375\r\n00:26:43,185 --> 00:26:45,603\r\nDo you know what you did to me, to my life?\r\n\r\n376\r\n00:26:45,687 --> 00:26:48,231\r\nI can only say I'm sorry so many times.\r\n\r\n377\r\n00:26:48,315 --> 00:26:50,149\r\nWell, say it again, anyway.\r\n\r\n378\r\n00:26:50,234 --> 00:26:51,275\r\nSorry.\r\n\r\n379\r\n00:26:51,360 --> 00:26:53,486\r\nYeah, everybody's sorry.\r\n\r\n380\r\n00:26:53,570 --> 00:26:55,446\r\nAbner was sorry for dragging me all over this earth\r\n\r\n381\r\n00:26:55,531 --> 00:26:57,198\r\nlooking for his little bits of junk.\r\n\r\n382\r\n00:26:57,282 --> 00:26:59,617\r\nI'm sorry to still be stuck in this dive.\r\n\r\n383\r\n00:27:00,536 --> 00:27:03,079\r\nEverybody's sorry for something.\r\n\r\n384\r\n00:27:03,163 --> 00:27:04,956\r\nINDY: It's a worthless bronze medallion, Marion.\r\n\r\n385\r\n00:27:05,040 --> 00:27:06,082\r\nYou going to give it to me?\r\n\r\n386\r\n00:27:06,166 --> 00:27:07,166\r\nMaybe.\r\n\r\n387\r\n00:27:07,251 --> 00:27:09,001\r\nI don't know where it is.\r\n\r\n388\r\n00:27:09,086 --> 00:27:12,505\r\nWell, maybe you could find it.\r\n\r\n389\r\n00:27:12,589 --> 00:27:15,716\r\n3,000 bucks.\r\n\r\n390\r\n00:27:15,801 --> 00:27:19,762\r\nWell, that will get me back, but not in style.\r\n\r\n391\r\n00:27:19,847 --> 00:27:22,223\r\nI can get you another two when we get to the States.\r\n\r\n392\r\n00:27:22,307 --> 00:27:24,058\r\nIt's important, Marion.\r\n\r\n393\r\n00:27:25,435 --> 00:27:26,686\r\nTrust me.\r\n\r\n394\r\n00:27:28,397 --> 00:27:29,647\r\nYou know the piece I mean?\r\n\r\n395\r\n00:27:29,731 --> 00:27:31,399\r\nDo you know where it is?\r\n\r\n396\r\n00:27:34,862 --> 00:27:35,987\r\nCome back tomorrow.\r\n\r\n397\r\n00:27:37,531 --> 00:27:38,531\r\nWhy?\r\n\r\n398\r\n00:27:38,907 --> 00:27:41,450\r\nBecause I said so, that's why.\r\n\r\n399\r\n00:27:48,750 --> 00:27:49,750\r\nHa!\r\n\r\n400\r\n00:27:49,835 --> 00:27:51,961\r\nSee you tomorrow, Indiana Jones.\r\n\r\n401\r\n00:28:20,115 --> 00:28:21,657\r\n(WIND BLOWS)\r\n\r\n402\r\n00:29:00,155 --> 00:29:02,240\r\nGood evening, Fr�ulein.\r\n\r\n403\r\n00:29:02,324 --> 00:29:03,950\r\nMARION: The bar's closed.\r\n\r\n404\r\n00:29:04,034 --> 00:29:07,078\r\n(CHORTLING) We... We are...\r\n\r\n405\r\n00:29:07,162 --> 00:29:09,080\r\nnot thirsty.\r\n\r\n406\r\n00:29:09,665 --> 00:29:10,873\r\nWhat do you want?\r\n\r\n407\r\n00:29:10,958 --> 00:29:13,751\r\nThe same thing your friend Dr. Jones wanted.\r\n\r\n408\r\n00:29:13,835 --> 00:29:16,128\r\nSurely he told you there would be\r\n\r\n409\r\n00:29:16,213 --> 00:29:18,339\r\nother interested parties.\r\n\r\n410\r\n00:29:18,423 --> 00:29:20,758\r\nMust've slipped his mind.\r\n\r\n411\r\n00:29:20,842 --> 00:29:24,095\r\nThe man is... nefarious.\r\n\r\n412\r\n00:29:25,180 --> 00:29:28,432\r\nI hope, for your sake, he has not yet acquired it.\r\n\r\n413\r\n00:29:28,725 --> 00:29:30,768\r\nWhy, are you willing to offer more?\r\n\r\n414\r\n00:29:31,395 --> 00:29:34,105\r\nOh, almost certainly.\r\n\r\n415\r\n00:29:34,189 --> 00:29:35,815\r\nDo you still have it?\r\n\r\n416\r\n00:29:39,695 --> 00:29:41,153\r\n(COUGHING SOFTLY)\r\n\r\n417\r\n00:29:41,530 --> 00:29:42,822\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n418\r\n00:29:43,824 --> 00:29:45,741\r\nBut I know where it is.\r\n\r\n419\r\n00:29:47,035 --> 00:29:49,620\r\nHey, how about a drink for you and your men?\r\n\r\n420\r\n00:29:49,705 --> 00:29:54,625\r\nYour fire is dying here.\r\n\r\n421\r\n00:29:54,710 --> 00:29:57,461\r\nWhy don't you tell me where the piece is right now?\r\n\r\n422\r\n00:29:57,879 --> 00:30:00,047\r\nListen, Herr Mac...\r\n\r\n423\r\n00:30:01,008 --> 00:30:04,427\r\nI don't know what kind of people you're used to dealing with,\r\n\r\n424\r\n00:30:04,511 --> 00:30:06,929\r\nbut nobody tells me what to do in my place.\r\n\r\n425\r\n00:30:07,014 --> 00:30:10,558\r\nFr�ulein Ravenwood,\r\n\r\n426\r\n00:30:10,642 --> 00:30:14,520\r\nlet me show you what I am used to.\r\n\r\n427\r\n00:30:14,604 --> 00:30:15,646\r\n(BARKS ORDER IN GERMAN)\r\n\r\n428\r\n00:30:16,898 --> 00:30:19,942\r\nMARION: Take your hands off me!\r\n\r\n429\r\n00:30:20,027 --> 00:30:21,235\r\n(MARION GRUNTING)\r\n\r\n430\r\n00:30:21,611 --> 00:30:23,779\r\nTake your lousy hands off!\r\n\r\n431\r\n00:30:24,740 --> 00:30:26,324\r\n(GROANING)\r\n\r\n432\r\n00:30:30,704 --> 00:30:31,746\r\nWait a minute.\r\n\r\n433\r\n00:30:31,830 --> 00:30:33,164\r\nWait, I... I can be reasonable.\r\n\r\n434\r\n00:30:33,248 --> 00:30:34,832\r\nThat time is passed.\r\n\r\n435\r\n00:30:34,916 --> 00:30:36,584\r\nYou don't need that.\r\n\r\n436\r\n00:30:37,169 --> 00:30:38,544\r\n(WHIMPERING)\r\n\r\n437\r\n00:30:38,754 --> 00:30:39,879\r\nWait...\r\n\r\n438\r\n00:30:41,590 --> 00:30:43,758\r\nI'll tell you everything.\r\n\r\n439\r\n00:30:43,842 --> 00:30:46,677\r\n(WHISPERING) Yes, I know you will.\r\n\r\n440\r\n00:30:50,766 --> 00:30:51,807\r\n(WHIP CRACKS)\r\n\r\n441\r\n00:30:53,185 --> 00:30:54,185\r\nLet her go.\r\n\r\n442\r\n00:31:26,593 --> 00:31:29,970\r\n(SCREAMING)\r\n\r\n443\r\n00:31:36,561 --> 00:31:37,561\r\n(INDISTINCT)\r\n\r\n444\r\n00:31:54,704 --> 00:31:55,955\r\n(GROANS)\r\n\r\n445\r\n00:32:09,428 --> 00:32:10,428\r\nWhiskey.\r\n\r\n446\r\n00:32:17,978 --> 00:32:19,437\r\n(CHOKING)\r\n\r\n447\r\n00:32:19,521 --> 00:32:20,646\r\nShoot them.\r\n\r\n448\r\n00:32:21,314 --> 00:32:22,523\r\nShoot them both.\r\n\r\n449\r\n00:32:47,674 --> 00:32:50,384\r\n(SCREAMING)\r\n\r\n450\r\n00:32:58,393 --> 00:32:59,435\r\n(SOBBING)\r\n\r\n451\r\n00:33:00,270 --> 00:33:01,312\r\n(GROANING)\r\n\r\n452\r\n00:33:08,111 --> 00:33:09,153\r\n(GUN FIRES)\r\n\r\n453\r\n00:33:17,704 --> 00:33:18,871\r\nMy medallion!\r\n\r\n454\r\n00:33:26,588 --> 00:33:29,048\r\nMARION: Well, Jones, at least you haven't forgotten\r\n\r\n455\r\n00:33:29,132 --> 00:33:30,925\r\nhow to show a lady a good time!\r\n\r\n456\r\n00:33:31,051 --> 00:33:32,593\r\nBoy, you're something!\r\n\r\n457\r\n00:33:32,677 --> 00:33:33,844\r\nYeah, I'll tell you what.\r\n\r\n458\r\n00:33:33,929 --> 00:33:35,721\r\nUntil I get back my $5,000,\r\n\r\n459\r\n00:33:35,805 --> 00:33:37,890\r\nyou're going to get more than you bargained for.\r\n\r\n460\r\n00:33:37,974 --> 00:33:40,434\r\nI'm your goddamn partner!\r\n\r\n461\r\n00:34:18,473 --> 00:34:20,724\r\nCairo, city of the living.\r\n\r\n462\r\n00:34:20,809 --> 00:34:22,560\r\nA paradise on earth.\r\n\r\n463\r\n00:34:22,686 --> 00:34:24,270\r\n(CHILDREN SHOUTING GLEEFULLY)\r\n\r\n464\r\n00:34:24,354 --> 00:34:25,521\r\nSilence!\r\n\r\n465\r\n00:34:25,605 --> 00:34:27,106\r\nWhy do you forget yourselves?\r\n\r\n466\r\n00:34:27,190 --> 00:34:27,675\r\nWhat is this?\r\n\r\n467\r\n00:34:27,701 --> 00:34:28,632\r\n(MONKEY CHATTERING)\r\n\r\n468\r\n00:34:28,692 --> 00:34:30,484\r\nWhere did this animal come from?\r\n\r\n469\r\n00:34:33,947 --> 00:34:35,114\r\nOh... oh, no.\r\n\r\n470\r\n00:34:35,574 --> 00:34:37,241\r\n(LAUGHING)\r\n\r\n471\r\n00:34:37,325 --> 00:34:38,367\r\n(ALL LAUGH)\r\n\r\n472\r\n00:34:38,451 --> 00:34:39,451\r\nCute.\r\n\r\n473\r\n00:34:39,536 --> 00:34:41,328\r\nWhat an adorable creature.\r\n\r\n474\r\n00:34:43,290 --> 00:34:45,583\r\nThen it shall be welcome in our house.\r\n\r\n475\r\n00:34:45,667 --> 00:34:47,918\r\nOh, well, no, you don't have to keep it here just because of me.\r\n\r\n476\r\n00:34:56,136 --> 00:34:58,721\r\nINDY: I knew the Germans would hire you, Sallah.\r\n\r\n477\r\n00:34:58,805 --> 00:35:00,931\r\nYou're the best digger in Egypt.\r\n\r\n478\r\n00:35:01,016 --> 00:35:04,143\r\nMy services are entirely inconsequential to them.\r\n\r\n479\r\n00:35:04,769 --> 00:35:07,313\r\nThey've hired or shanghaied every digger in Cairo.\r\n\r\n480\r\n00:35:07,397 --> 00:35:09,148\r\nThe excavation is enormous.\r\n\r\n481\r\n00:35:09,441 --> 00:35:14,028\r\nThey hire only strong backs and they pay pennies for them.\r\n\r\n482\r\n00:35:14,112 --> 00:35:16,488\r\nIt's as if the pharaohs had returned.\r\n\r\n483\r\n00:35:16,698 --> 00:35:18,365\r\nWhen did they find the map room?\r\n\r\n484\r\n00:35:18,658 --> 00:35:19,992\r\nThree days ago.\r\n\r\n485\r\n00:35:20,076 --> 00:35:22,328\r\nThey have not one brain among them.\r\n\r\n486\r\n00:35:22,412 --> 00:35:24,371\r\nExcept one.\r\n\r\n487\r\n00:35:24,456 --> 00:35:25,254\r\nHe is very clever.\r\n\r\n488\r\n00:35:25,280 --> 00:35:26,565\r\nHe's a French archeologist.\r\n\r\n489\r\n00:35:29,210 --> 00:35:30,210\r\nWhat's his name?\r\n\r\n490\r\n00:35:30,337 --> 00:35:31,545\r\nThey call him \"Bellosh.\"\r\n\r\n491\r\n00:35:38,386 --> 00:35:40,220\r\nBelloq. Belloq.\r\n\r\n492\r\n00:35:41,389 --> 00:35:44,350\r\nThe Germans have a great advantage over us.\r\n\r\n493\r\n00:35:44,434 --> 00:35:46,727\r\nThey are near to discovering the Well of Souls.\r\n\r\n494\r\n00:35:47,187 --> 00:35:51,565\r\nWell, they're not going to find it without this.\r\n\r\n495\r\n00:35:52,359 --> 00:35:54,610\r\nWho can tell us about these markings?\r\n\r\n496\r\n00:35:56,863 --> 00:35:59,281\r\nPerhaps a man I know can help us.\r\n\r\n497\r\n00:36:01,451 --> 00:36:03,077\r\nIndy...\r\n\r\n498\r\n00:36:04,621 --> 00:36:06,872\r\nthere is something that troubles me.\r\n\r\n499\r\n00:36:07,040 --> 00:36:10,000\r\nWhat is it?\r\n\r\n500\r\n00:36:10,126 --> 00:36:12,127\r\nThe Ark.\r\n\r\n501\r\n00:36:12,212 --> 00:36:14,505\r\nIf it is there, at Tanis,\r\n\r\n502\r\n00:36:14,589 --> 00:36:17,883\r\nthen it is something that man was not meant to disturb.\r\n\r\n503\r\n00:36:18,009 --> 00:36:21,136\r\nDeath has always surrounded it.\r\n\r\n504\r\n00:36:21,221 --> 00:36:23,097\r\nIt is not of this earth.\r\n\r\n505\r\n00:36:23,556 --> 00:36:24,932\r\nDo we need the monkey, huh?\r\n\r\n506\r\n00:36:25,058 --> 00:36:26,517\r\nI'm surprised at you, Jones,\r\n\r\n507\r\n00:36:26,601 --> 00:36:29,228\r\ntalking that way about our baby.\r\n\r\n508\r\n00:36:29,437 --> 00:36:31,021\r\nHe's got your looks, too.\r\n\r\n509\r\n00:36:31,106 --> 00:36:32,106\r\nAnd your brains.\r\n\r\n510\r\n00:36:32,190 --> 00:36:34,024\r\nOops!\r\n\r\n511\r\n00:36:34,109 --> 00:36:35,192\r\nI noticed that.\r\n\r\n512\r\n00:36:35,276 --> 00:36:37,569\r\nShe's a smart little thing.\r\nSmart.\r\n\r\n513\r\n00:36:37,654 --> 00:36:38,696\r\n(YELPS)\r\n\r\n514\r\n00:36:40,323 --> 00:36:41,740\r\n- Hey!\r\n- (MONKEY SCREECHING)\r\n\r\n515\r\n00:36:41,825 --> 00:36:43,033\r\nHey, where you going?\r\n\r\n516\r\n00:36:43,118 --> 00:36:44,172\r\nShe'll be all right.\r\n\r\n517\r\n00:36:44,198 --> 00:36:44,935\r\nHave a date.\r\n\r\n518\r\n00:36:48,832 --> 00:36:49,957\r\nCome on. Come on.\r\n\r\n519\r\n00:36:50,041 --> 00:36:51,959\r\n- Okay...\r\n- Marion.\r\n\r\n520\r\n00:36:52,043 --> 00:36:53,043\r\nWhat's this?\r\n\r\n521\r\n00:36:53,128 --> 00:36:54,461\r\nIt's a date.\r\n\r\n522\r\n00:36:54,546 --> 00:36:55,754\r\nYou eat 'em.\r\n\r\n523\r\n00:37:00,885 --> 00:37:01,927\r\n(CHATTERING)\r\n\r\n524\r\n00:37:09,018 --> 00:37:10,561\r\n(EXCLAIMS IN GERMAN)\r\n\r\n525\r\n00:37:14,399 --> 00:37:16,483\r\n(SPEAKING ARABIC)\r\n\r\n526\r\n00:37:25,577 --> 00:37:26,618\r\n(MONKEY SCREECHES)\r\n\r\n527\r\n00:37:44,804 --> 00:37:47,181\r\nMARION: How come you haven't found\r\nsome nice girl to settle down with,\r\n\r\n528\r\n00:37:47,265 --> 00:37:49,141\r\nraise eight or nine kids, like your friend Sallah?\r\n\r\n529\r\n00:37:49,225 --> 00:37:50,392\r\nINDY: Who says I haven't?\r\n\r\n530\r\n00:37:50,518 --> 00:37:51,560\r\n(SNICKERS)\r\n\r\n531\r\n00:37:52,187 --> 00:37:53,270\r\nI do.\r\n\r\n532\r\n00:37:53,396 --> 00:37:55,189\r\nDad had you figured a long time ago.\r\n\r\n533\r\n00:38:04,699 --> 00:38:06,074\r\nHe said you were a bum.\r\n\r\n534\r\n00:38:06,159 --> 00:38:07,493\r\nOh, he's being generous.\r\n\r\n535\r\n00:38:07,577 --> 00:38:09,578\r\nThe most gifted bum he ever trained.\r\n\r\n536\r\n00:38:09,913 --> 00:38:11,789\r\nYou know, he loved you like a son.\r\n\r\n537\r\n00:38:11,873 --> 00:38:13,415\r\nTook a hell of a lot for you to alienate him.\r\n\r\n538\r\n00:38:13,541 --> 00:38:14,708\r\nNot much, just you.\r\n\r\n539\r\n00:38:32,894 --> 00:38:34,186\r\nMarion, get out of here!\r\n\r\n540\r\n00:38:34,729 --> 00:38:35,729\r\nDuck!\r\n\r\n541\r\n00:38:46,032 --> 00:38:47,074\r\n(SCREAMS)\r\n\r\n542\r\n00:38:56,084 --> 00:38:57,125\r\n(HORSE NEIGHING)\r\n\r\n543\r\n00:39:16,104 --> 00:39:17,771\r\n(LAUGHING MENACINGLY)\r\n\r\n544\r\n00:39:17,856 --> 00:39:19,106\r\nRight.\r\n\r\n545\r\n00:39:26,114 --> 00:39:27,155\r\n(METAL DINGS)\r\n\r\n546\r\n00:39:52,307 --> 00:39:56,226\r\n(SCREECHING)\r\n\r\n547\r\n00:39:58,396 --> 00:39:59,646\r\n(SPEAKING GERMAN)\r\n\r\n548\r\n00:40:01,190 --> 00:40:03,442\r\nShh! Shh!\r\n\r\n549\r\n00:40:09,490 --> 00:40:10,991\r\nMarion!\r\n\r\n550\r\n00:40:17,332 --> 00:40:19,249\r\n(SNICKERING)\r\n\r\n551\r\n00:40:30,970 --> 00:40:32,036\r\nMARION: Help!\r\n\r\n552\r\n00:40:32,062 --> 00:40:33,538\r\nOver here, Indy!\r\n\r\n553\r\n00:40:33,598 --> 00:40:34,640\r\nINDY: Get out of the way!\r\n\r\n554\r\n00:40:34,724 --> 00:40:36,183\r\nMove! Move it!\r\n\r\n555\r\n00:40:37,435 --> 00:40:38,518\r\nMARION: Help me!\r\n\r\n556\r\n00:40:44,233 --> 00:40:45,525\r\nYou can't do this to me!\r\n\r\n557\r\n00:40:45,610 --> 00:40:47,277\r\nI'm an American!\r\n\r\n558\r\n00:40:47,362 --> 00:40:49,696\r\n(SCREAMING) Indy!\r\n\r\n559\r\n00:40:52,533 --> 00:40:54,368\r\nIndiana Jones!\r\n\r\n560\r\n00:40:54,619 --> 00:40:55,953\r\nHelp me, Jones!\r\n\r\n561\r\n00:41:09,384 --> 00:41:13,387\r\n(PEOPLE CLAMORING)\r\n\r\n562\r\n00:41:17,225 --> 00:41:18,392\r\nMARION: (SCREAMING) Jones!\r\n\r\n563\r\n00:41:18,476 --> 00:41:19,476\r\nMarion!\r\n\r\n564\r\n00:41:23,022 --> 00:41:25,190\r\n(SCREAMING) Indy!\r\n\r\n565\r\n00:41:38,746 --> 00:41:41,915\r\n(BEGGARING IN ARABIC)\r\n\r\n566\r\n00:41:42,083 --> 00:41:43,417\r\n(COINS CLINKING)\r\n\r\n567\r\n00:41:43,793 --> 00:41:45,377\r\n(SHOUTING IN GERMAN)\r\n\r\n568\r\n00:41:45,461 --> 00:41:46,586\r\n(MACHINE GUN FIRING)\r\n\r\n569\r\n00:41:54,804 --> 00:41:56,346\r\n(ENGINE REVVING)\r\n\r\n570\r\n00:42:06,941 --> 00:42:08,358\r\nINDY: Marion...\r\n\r\n571\r\n00:42:27,462 --> 00:42:29,212\r\n(MONKEY SCREECHING)\r\n\r\n572\r\n00:42:46,064 --> 00:42:47,147\r\nMAN: Dr. Jones.\r\n\r\n573\r\n00:42:47,231 --> 00:42:49,024\r\n(SPEAKING GERMAN)\r\n\r\n574\r\n00:43:14,383 --> 00:43:15,717\r\nYou looking for me?\r\n\r\n575\r\n00:43:15,843 --> 00:43:19,721\r\n(LAUGHING)\r\n\r\n576\r\n00:43:24,852 --> 00:43:26,061\r\nBelloq.\r\n\r\n577\r\n00:43:26,145 --> 00:43:27,771\r\nGood afternoon, Dr. Jones.\r\n\r\n578\r\n00:43:27,855 --> 00:43:29,731\r\nI ought to kill you right now.\r\n\r\n579\r\n00:43:29,816 --> 00:43:32,442\r\nNot a very private place for a murder.\r\n\r\n580\r\n00:43:33,444 --> 00:43:36,196\r\nWell, these Arabs don't care if we kill each other.\r\n\r\n581\r\n00:43:36,280 --> 00:43:39,491\r\nThey're not going to interfere in our business.\r\n\r\n582\r\n00:43:39,575 --> 00:43:42,119\r\nIt was not I who brought the girl into this business.\r\n\r\n583\r\n00:43:42,245 --> 00:43:44,329\r\nPlease, sit down before you fall down.\r\n\r\n584\r\n00:43:44,413 --> 00:43:47,040\r\nWe can at least behave like civilized people.\r\n\r\n585\r\n00:43:58,386 --> 00:44:00,387\r\nI see your taste in friends remains consistent.\r\n\r\n586\r\n00:44:01,472 --> 00:44:03,390\r\nHow odd that it should end this way for us,\r\n\r\n587\r\n00:44:03,474 --> 00:44:06,393\r\nafter so many stimulating encounters.\r\n\r\n588\r\n00:44:06,561 --> 00:44:08,353\r\nI almost regret it.\r\n\r\n589\r\n00:44:08,563 --> 00:44:09,980\r\nWhere shall I find a new adversary\r\n\r\n590\r\n00:44:10,064 --> 00:44:11,731\r\nso close to my own level?\r\n\r\n591\r\n00:44:11,858 --> 00:44:13,859\r\nTry the local sewer.\r\n\r\n592\r\n00:44:16,445 --> 00:44:19,656\r\nYou and I are very much alike.\r\n\r\n593\r\n00:44:19,740 --> 00:44:22,075\r\nArcheology is our religion,\r\n\r\n594\r\n00:44:22,160 --> 00:44:26,329\r\nyet we have both fallen from the purer faith.\r\n\r\n595\r\n00:44:26,414 --> 00:44:30,000\r\nOur methods have not differed as much as you pretend.\r\n\r\n596\r\n00:44:30,084 --> 00:44:33,253\r\nI am a shadowy reflection of you.\r\n\r\n597\r\n00:44:33,379 --> 00:44:36,464\r\nIt would take only a nudge to make you like me,\r\n\r\n598\r\n00:44:36,549 --> 00:44:38,842\r\nto push you out of the light.\r\n\r\n599\r\n00:44:38,926 --> 00:44:42,345\r\nNow you're getting nasty.\r\n\r\n600\r\n00:44:42,430 --> 00:44:44,389\r\nYou know it's true.\r\n\r\n601\r\n00:44:44,473 --> 00:44:46,433\r\nHow nice.\r\n\r\n602\r\n00:44:46,517 --> 00:44:48,518\r\nLook at this.\r\n\r\n603\r\n00:44:48,603 --> 00:44:50,437\r\nIt's worthless.\r\n\r\n604\r\n00:44:50,521 --> 00:44:52,731\r\nTen dollars from a vendor in the street.\r\n\r\n605\r\n00:44:52,815 --> 00:44:53,940\r\nBut I take it,\r\n\r\n606\r\n00:44:54,025 --> 00:44:55,692\r\nI bury it in the sand for a thousand years,\r\n\r\n607\r\n00:44:55,776 --> 00:44:59,362\r\nit becomes priceless... Like the Ark.\r\n\r\n608\r\n00:44:59,447 --> 00:45:01,323\r\nMen will kill for it.\r\n\r\n609\r\n00:45:01,449 --> 00:45:04,117\r\nMen like you and me.\r\n\r\n610\r\n00:45:04,285 --> 00:45:07,704\r\nWhat about your boss, der F�hrer?\r\n\r\n611\r\n00:45:07,788 --> 00:45:11,208\r\nI thought he was waiting to take possession.\r\n\r\n612\r\n00:45:11,292 --> 00:45:13,835\r\nAll in good time.\r\n\r\n613\r\n00:45:13,920 --> 00:45:15,962\r\nWhen I am finished with it.\r\n\r\n614\r\n00:45:16,047 --> 00:45:19,674\r\nJones, do you realize what the Ark is?\r\n\r\n615\r\n00:45:19,759 --> 00:45:21,635\r\nIt's a transmitter.\r\n\r\n616\r\n00:45:21,719 --> 00:45:24,512\r\nIt's a radio for speaking to God.\r\n\r\n617\r\n00:45:24,639 --> 00:45:26,264\r\nAnd it's within my reach.\r\n\r\n618\r\n00:45:28,184 --> 00:45:31,728\r\nYou want to talk to God?\r\n\r\n619\r\n00:45:31,812 --> 00:45:33,855\r\nLet's go see Him together.\r\n\r\n620\r\n00:45:33,940 --> 00:45:35,565\r\nI've got nothing better to do.\r\n\r\n621\r\n00:45:36,943 --> 00:45:38,777\r\nCHILD: Uncle Indy, come back home now!\r\n\r\n622\r\n00:45:39,445 --> 00:45:40,904\r\n(CHILDREN CHATTERING)\r\n\r\n623\r\n00:45:40,988 --> 00:45:41,988\r\nUncle Indy!\r\n\r\n624\r\n00:45:43,658 --> 00:45:45,116\r\nNext time, Indiana Jones,\r\n\r\n625\r\n00:45:45,243 --> 00:45:47,327\r\nit'll take more than children to save you.\r\n\r\n626\r\n00:45:49,413 --> 00:45:50,580\r\nUncle Indy!\r\n\r\n627\r\n00:46:04,679 --> 00:46:06,263\r\nI thought I would find you there.\r\n\r\n628\r\n00:46:06,347 --> 00:46:08,598\r\nBetter than the United States Marines, eh?\r\n\r\n629\r\n00:46:18,859 --> 00:46:20,026\r\nMarion's dead.\r\n\r\n630\r\n00:46:20,111 --> 00:46:22,529\r\n- Yes, I know.\r\n- And me! And me!\r\n\r\n631\r\n00:46:22,655 --> 00:46:24,239\r\nI'm sorry.\r\n\r\n632\r\n00:46:24,907 --> 00:46:26,908\r\nLife goes on, Indy.\r\n\r\n633\r\n00:46:26,993 --> 00:46:28,368\r\nThere is the proof.\r\n\r\n634\r\n00:46:28,494 --> 00:46:29,536\r\n(GRUNTS)\r\n\r\n635\r\n00:46:30,037 --> 00:46:31,162\r\nUh-oh.\r\n\r\n636\r\n00:46:32,039 --> 00:46:33,915\r\nI have much to tell you.\r\n\r\n637\r\n00:46:34,000 --> 00:46:36,251\r\nFirst we will take them home,\r\n\r\n638\r\n00:46:36,335 --> 00:46:37,627\r\nand then I will take you to the old man.\r\n\r\n639\r\n00:47:28,929 --> 00:47:31,056\r\nINDY: I can't figure out how Belloq did it.\r\n\r\n640\r\n00:47:31,140 --> 00:47:33,558\r\nWhere'd he get a copy of the headpiece?\r\n\r\n641\r\n00:47:33,642 --> 00:47:36,895\r\nThere are no pictures, no duplicates of it anywhere.\r\n\r\n642\r\n00:47:36,979 --> 00:47:39,397\r\nI tell you only what I saw with my own eyes:\r\n\r\n643\r\n00:47:39,482 --> 00:47:41,066\r\nA headpiece like that one,\r\n\r\n644\r\n00:47:41,150 --> 00:47:43,651\r\nexcept round the edges, which were rougher.\r\n\r\n645\r\n00:47:43,736 --> 00:47:45,779\r\nIn the center, the Frenchman had embedded a crystal,\r\n\r\n646\r\n00:47:45,863 --> 00:47:50,283\r\nand... and surrounding the crystal, on one side,\r\n\r\n647\r\n00:47:50,409 --> 00:47:52,452\r\nthere were raised markings, just like that one.\r\n\r\n648\r\n00:47:54,955 --> 00:47:57,207\r\nThey made their calculations in the map room?\r\n\r\n649\r\n00:47:57,291 --> 00:47:58,666\r\nSALLAH: This morning.\r\n\r\n650\r\n00:47:58,751 --> 00:48:01,127\r\nBelloq and the boss German, Dietrich.\r\n\r\n651\r\n00:48:02,463 --> 00:48:03,797\r\nWhen they came out of the map room,\r\n\r\n652\r\n00:48:03,881 --> 00:48:06,132\r\nthey gave us a new spot in which to dig,\r\n\r\n653\r\n00:48:06,217 --> 00:48:08,968\r\nout away from the camp.\r\n\r\n654\r\n00:48:09,303 --> 00:48:11,012\r\nThe Well of the Souls, huh?\r\n\r\n655\r\n00:48:11,097 --> 00:48:14,933\r\nCome, come, look.\r\nLook here... Look.\r\n\r\n656\r\n00:48:15,017 --> 00:48:16,559\r\nSit down.\r\n\r\n657\r\n00:48:16,644 --> 00:48:18,144\r\nCome, sit down.\r\n\r\n658\r\n00:48:18,229 --> 00:48:20,480\r\nWhat is it?\r\n\r\n659\r\n00:48:20,564 --> 00:48:22,399\r\nThis is a warning\r\n\r\n660\r\n00:48:22,483 --> 00:48:24,901\r\nnot to disturb the Ark of the Covenant.\r\n\r\n661\r\n00:48:24,985 --> 00:48:26,820\r\nWhat about the height of the staff, though?\r\n\r\n662\r\n00:48:26,904 --> 00:48:28,071\r\nDid Belloq get it off of here?\r\n\r\n663\r\n00:48:28,155 --> 00:48:30,240\r\nYes. It is here.\r\n\r\n664\r\n00:48:30,324 --> 00:48:32,117\r\nThis were the old way,\r\n\r\n665\r\n00:48:32,201 --> 00:48:34,661\r\nthis mean six kadam high.\r\n\r\n666\r\n00:48:34,745 --> 00:48:35,954\r\n- About 72 inches.\r\n- Wait!\r\n\r\n667\r\n00:48:39,500 --> 00:48:42,335\r\n\"And take back one kadam\r\n\r\n668\r\n00:48:42,420 --> 00:48:46,256\r\nto honor the Hebrew God whose Ark this is.\"\r\n\r\n669\r\n00:48:46,340 --> 00:48:50,176\r\n(WIND CHIMES JINGLING)\r\n\r\n670\r\n00:48:58,519 --> 00:49:00,437\r\nYou said their headpiece only had markings on one side.\r\n\r\n671\r\n00:49:00,521 --> 00:49:02,439\r\nAre you absolutely sure?\r\n\r\n672\r\n00:49:04,108 --> 00:49:05,817\r\nBelloq's staff is too long.\r\n\r\n673\r\n00:49:06,569 --> 00:49:08,570\r\nBOTH: They're digging in the wrong place.\r\n\r\n674\r\n00:49:11,115 --> 00:49:13,783\r\n(SINGING) I am the monarch of the sea\r\n\r\n675\r\n00:49:13,868 --> 00:49:15,743\r\nI am the ruler of the...\r\n\r\n676\r\n00:49:26,630 --> 00:49:28,339\r\nBad dates.\r\n\r\n677\r\n00:49:43,647 --> 00:49:45,607\r\nI told you not to be premature\r\n\r\n678\r\n00:49:45,691 --> 00:49:47,984\r\nin your communiqu� to Berlin.\r\n\r\n679\r\n00:49:48,068 --> 00:49:51,905\r\nArcheology is not an exact science.\r\n\r\n680\r\n00:49:51,989 --> 00:49:54,157\r\nIt does not deal in time schedules.\r\n\r\n681\r\n00:49:54,241 --> 00:49:55,867\r\nThe F�hrer is not a patient man.\r\n\r\n682\r\n00:49:55,951 --> 00:49:59,162\r\nHe demands constant reports, and he expects progress.\r\n\r\n683\r\n00:49:59,246 --> 00:50:00,330\r\nYou led me to believe...\r\n\r\n684\r\n00:50:00,414 --> 00:50:02,207\r\nNothing! I made no promises.\r\n\r\n685\r\n00:50:02,291 --> 00:50:04,501\r\nI only said it looked very favorable.\r\n\r\n686\r\n00:50:04,585 --> 00:50:07,587\r\nBesides, with the information in our possession,\r\n\r\n687\r\n00:50:07,671 --> 00:50:09,255\r\nmy calculations were correct.\r\n\r\n688\r\n00:50:09,673 --> 00:50:11,549\r\nINDY: Boy, they're not kidding, are they?\r\n\r\n689\r\n00:50:13,135 --> 00:50:15,345\r\nWhat time does the sun hit the map room?\r\n\r\n690\r\n00:50:15,429 --> 00:50:17,388\r\nSALLAH: At about 9:00 in the morning.\r\n\r\n691\r\n00:50:17,473 --> 00:50:19,265\r\nINDY: Not much time, then.\r\n\r\n692\r\n00:50:19,350 --> 00:50:21,434\r\nWhere are they digging for the Well of the Souls?\r\n\r\n693\r\n00:50:21,602 --> 00:50:22,907\r\nSALLAH: On that ridge...\r\n\r\n694\r\n00:50:22,933 --> 00:50:24,671\r\nbut the map room's over there.\r\n\r\n695\r\n00:50:24,730 --> 00:50:26,064\r\nINDY: Let's go, come on.\r\n\r\n696\r\n00:50:36,283 --> 00:50:38,284\r\n(MEN SINGING IN ARABIC)\r\n\r\n697\r\n00:51:38,220 --> 00:51:43,850\r\n(BARKING ORDERS IN GERMAN)\r\n\r\n698\r\n00:54:32,436 --> 00:54:34,020\r\nSallah.\r\n\r\n699\r\n00:54:35,355 --> 00:54:37,106\r\nSallah!\r\n\r\n700\r\n00:54:44,990 --> 00:54:46,032\r\nThey're here.\r\n\r\n701\r\n00:54:50,329 --> 00:54:53,498\r\n(SPEAKING GERMAN)\r\n\r\n702\r\n00:54:57,044 --> 00:54:58,252\r\nPlease, my friend, what is the matter?\r\n\r\n703\r\n00:54:58,337 --> 00:55:00,046\r\nI fetch the water. I shall get it for you.\r\n\r\n704\r\n00:55:03,217 --> 00:55:04,383\r\nIf you want water, I will get you water.\r\n\r\n705\r\n00:55:04,468 --> 00:55:05,760\r\nNo problem, no problem.\r\n\r\n706\r\n00:55:16,438 --> 00:55:17,480\r\n(GRUNTS)\r\n\r\n707\r\n00:55:20,567 --> 00:55:22,151\r\nI thought you were dead.\r\n\r\n708\r\n00:55:22,236 --> 00:55:23,736\r\nYou must have switched baskets.\r\n\r\n709\r\n00:55:26,740 --> 00:55:28,115\r\n(MARION LAUGHING)\r\n\r\n710\r\n00:55:28,200 --> 00:55:29,200\r\nAre you hurt?\r\n\r\n711\r\n00:55:29,368 --> 00:55:31,661\r\nNo. You have to get me out of here, quick.\r\n\r\n712\r\n00:55:31,745 --> 00:55:33,704\r\nThey're gonna be back at any minute.\r\n\r\n713\r\n00:55:33,789 --> 00:55:35,289\r\nCut me loose.\r\n\r\n714\r\n00:55:35,374 --> 00:55:36,374\r\nQuick.\r\n\r\n715\r\n00:55:36,458 --> 00:55:38,055\r\nThey keep asking about you.\r\n\r\n716\r\n00:55:38,081 --> 00:55:39,026\r\nWhat you know.\r\n\r\n717\r\n00:55:43,674 --> 00:55:45,007\r\nWhat's wrong?\r\n\r\n718\r\n00:55:45,092 --> 00:55:46,175\r\nCut me loose.\r\n\r\n719\r\n00:55:46,260 --> 00:55:47,593\r\nI know where the Ark is, Marion.\r\n\r\n720\r\n00:55:47,719 --> 00:55:48,761\r\nThe Ark's here?\r\n\r\n721\r\n00:55:49,888 --> 00:55:50,803\r\nI'm coming with you, Jones.\r\n\r\n722\r\n00:55:50,829 --> 00:55:51,539\r\nGet me out of here!\r\n\r\n723\r\n00:55:51,598 --> 00:55:52,043\r\nCut me loose!\r\n\r\n724\r\n00:55:52,069 --> 00:55:52,957\r\nYou can't leave me here!\r\n\r\n725\r\n00:55:53,016 --> 00:55:54,058\r\nIf I take you out of here now,\r\n\r\n726\r\n00:55:54,142 --> 00:55:55,601\r\nthey'll start combing the place for us.\r\n\r\n727\r\n00:55:55,769 --> 00:55:57,186\r\nJones, you've got to get me out of here!\r\n\r\n728\r\n00:55:57,271 --> 00:55:59,647\r\nCome on, Jones, are you crazy?\r\n\r\n729\r\n00:56:00,399 --> 00:56:01,858\r\nMarion, I hate to do this,\r\n\r\n730\r\n00:56:01,942 --> 00:56:04,527\r\nbut if you don't sit still and keep quiet,\r\n\r\n731\r\n00:56:04,611 --> 00:56:06,696\r\nthis whole thing is going to be shot.\r\n\r\n732\r\n00:56:07,948 --> 00:56:09,365\r\nI'll be back to get you.\r\n\r\n733\r\n00:56:09,867 --> 00:56:11,325\r\nJones, what's the matter?\r\n\r\n734\r\n00:56:14,204 --> 00:56:18,916\r\n(MEN CHATTERING IN ARABIC)\r\n\r\n735\r\n00:56:56,997 --> 00:56:58,623\r\nThat's it.\r\n\r\n736\r\n00:56:59,458 --> 00:57:00,458\r\nWho knows?\r\n\r\n737\r\n00:57:00,542 --> 00:57:02,251\r\nPerhaps the Ark is still waiting\r\n\r\n738\r\n00:57:02,336 --> 00:57:05,087\r\nin some antechamber for us to discover.\r\n\r\n739\r\n00:57:05,172 --> 00:57:08,382\r\nPerhaps there's some vital bit of evidence which eludes us.\r\n\r\n740\r\n00:57:08,467 --> 00:57:10,927\r\n- Perhaps... - Perhaps the girl can help us.\r\n\r\n741\r\n00:57:11,053 --> 00:57:12,386\r\nMy feeling exactly.\r\n\r\n742\r\n00:57:12,638 --> 00:57:14,889\r\nShe was in possession of the original piece for years.\r\n\r\n743\r\n00:57:15,015 --> 00:57:17,683\r\nShe may know much, if properly motivated.\r\n\r\n744\r\n00:57:18,477 --> 00:57:20,102\r\nI tell you, the girl knows nothing.\r\n\r\n745\r\n00:57:21,355 --> 00:57:23,064\r\nI'm surprised to find you squeamish.\r\n\r\n746\r\n00:57:23,148 --> 00:57:25,107\r\nThat is not your reputation.\r\n\r\n747\r\n00:57:25,192 --> 00:57:26,484\r\nBut it needn't concern you.\r\n\r\n748\r\n00:57:26,568 --> 00:57:28,778\r\nI have the perfect man for this kind of work.\r\n\r\n749\r\n00:57:34,451 --> 00:57:35,868\r\nHeil Hitler.\r\n\r\n750\r\n00:58:11,279 --> 00:58:12,363\r\n(WHISTLES)\r\n\r\n751\r\n00:58:33,260 --> 00:58:36,470\r\n(MEN SINGING IN ARABIC)\r\n\r\n752\r\n00:58:49,234 --> 00:58:53,070\r\n(WIND HOWLING)\r\n\r\n753\r\n00:58:58,618 --> 00:58:59,869\r\nSALLAH: Indy! Here!\r\n\r\n754\r\n00:58:59,953 --> 00:59:01,328\r\nWe've hit stone!\r\n\r\n755\r\n00:59:05,792 --> 00:59:06,917\r\nINDY: Clear it off.\r\n\r\n756\r\n00:59:07,002 --> 00:59:08,210\r\nCome on, find the edges.\r\n\r\n757\r\n00:59:08,295 --> 00:59:11,547\r\n(SALLAH ORDERING IN ARABIC)\r\n\r\n758\r\n00:59:25,145 --> 00:59:26,771\r\nSALLAH: Good, good, good.\r\n\r\n759\r\n00:59:26,855 --> 00:59:28,147\r\nYou see, Indy? You see?\r\n\r\n760\r\n00:59:28,231 --> 00:59:30,149\r\nOkay, bring the pry bars in.\r\n\r\n761\r\n00:59:30,317 --> 00:59:31,256\r\nAs a team, boys!\r\n\r\n762\r\n00:59:31,282 --> 00:59:31,926\r\nAs a team!\r\n\r\n763\r\n00:59:33,987 --> 00:59:35,112\r\nPush!\r\n\r\n764\r\n00:59:37,407 --> 00:59:39,950\r\n(MEN GRUNTING)\r\n\r\n765\r\n00:59:40,077 --> 00:59:41,159\r\nINDY: Get 'em in there.\r\n\r\n766\r\n00:59:41,185 --> 00:59:41,936\r\nGet 'em under.\r\n\r\n767\r\n00:59:41,995 --> 00:59:43,204\r\nGood, good, that's it.\r\n\r\n768\r\n00:59:43,288 --> 00:59:44,288\r\nWatch your toes.\r\n\r\n769\r\n00:59:44,372 --> 00:59:45,414\r\n(AIR HISSING)\r\n\r\n770\r\n00:59:52,547 --> 00:59:53,756\r\nSALLAH: Carefully, carefully!\r\n\r\n771\r\n01:00:01,932 --> 01:00:03,140\r\n(SCREAMING)\r\n\r\n772\r\n01:00:06,186 --> 01:00:07,812\r\nSorry, Indy.\r\n\r\n773\r\n01:00:09,397 --> 01:00:10,731\r\nIndy...\r\n\r\n774\r\n01:00:11,108 --> 01:00:13,025\r\nwhy does the floor move?\r\n\r\n775\r\n01:00:15,195 --> 01:00:16,821\r\nGive me your torch.\r\n\r\n776\r\n01:00:16,860 --> 01:00:18,382\r\n<font color=\"#8000ff\">�</font> P@rM!NdeR M@nk�� �\r\n\r\n777\r\n01:00:18,383 --> 01:00:19,904\r\n<font color=\"#8000ff\">� </font>P@rM!NdeR M@nk�� �\r\n\r\n778\r\n01:00:19,905 --> 01:00:21,427\r\n<font color=\"#8000ff\">� P</font>@rM!NdeR M@nk�� �\r\n\r\n779\r\n01:00:21,428 --> 01:00:22,949\r\n<font color=\"#8000ff\">� P@</font>rM!NdeR M@nk�� �\r\n\r\n780\r\n01:00:22,950 --> 01:00:24,472\r\n<font color=\"#8000ff\">� P@r</font>M!NdeR M@nk�� �\r\n\r\n781\r\n01:00:24,473 --> 01:00:25,994\r\n<font color=\"#8000ff\">� P@rM</font>!NdeR M@nk�� �\r\n\r\n782\r\n01:00:25,995 --> 01:00:27,517\r\n<font color=\"#8000ff\">� P@rM!</font>NdeR M@nk�� �\r\n\r\n783\r\n01:00:27,518 --> 01:00:29,039\r\n<font color=\"#8000ff\">� P@rM!N</font>deR M@nk�� �\r\n\r\n784\r\n01:00:29,040 --> 01:00:30,562\r\n<font color=\"#8000ff\">� P@rM!Nd</font>eR M@nk�� �\r\n\r\n785\r\n01:00:30,563 --> 01:00:32,084\r\n<font color=\"#8000ff\">� P@rM!Nde</font>R M@nk�� �\r\n\r\n786\r\n01:00:32,085 --> 01:00:33,607\r\n<font color=\"#8000ff\">� P@rM!NdeR</font> M@nk�� �\r\n\r\n787\r\n01:00:33,608 --> 01:00:35,129\r\n<font color=\"#8000ff\">� P@rM!NdeR </font>M@nk�� �\r\n\r\n788\r\n01:00:35,130 --> 01:00:36,652\r\n<font color=\"#8000ff\">� P@rM!NdeR M</font>@nk�� �\r\n\r\n789\r\n01:00:36,653 --> 01:00:38,174\r\n<font color=\"#8000ff\">� P@rM!NdeR M@</font>nk�� �\r\n\r\n790\r\n01:00:38,175 --> 01:00:39,697\r\n<font color=\"#8000ff\">� P@rM!NdeR M@n</font>k�� �\r\n\r\n791\r\n01:00:39,698 --> 01:00:41,219\r\n<font color=\"#8000ff\">� P@rM!NdeR M@nk</font>�� �\r\n\r\n792\r\n01:00:41,220 --> 01:00:42,742\r