9 --> 01:20:59,187\r\nHave it put on the truck.\r\n\r\n1018\r\n01:20:59,271 --> 01:21:01,189\r\nWe'll fly it out of Cairo.\r\n\r\n1019\r\n01:21:01,273 --> 01:21:04,108\r\nAnd Gobler, I want plenty of protection.\r\n\r\n1020\r\n01:21:10,783 --> 01:21:12,492\r\nJones.\r\n\r\n1021\r\n01:21:14,078 --> 01:21:15,286\r\n(INDY WHISTLES)\r\n\r\n1022\r\n01:21:17,790 --> 01:21:19,332\r\nHoly smoke, my friends,\r\n\r\n1023\r\n01:21:19,416 --> 01:21:21,459\r\nI... I'm so pleased you're not dead!\r\n\r\n1024\r\n01:21:23,295 --> 01:21:24,754\r\nIndy, Indy, we have no time.\r\n\r\n1025\r\n01:21:24,838 --> 01:21:26,214\r\nIf you still want the Ark,\r\n\r\n1026\r\n01:21:26,298 --> 01:21:28,674\r\nit is being loaded onto a truck for Cairo.\r\n\r\n1027\r\n01:21:28,759 --> 01:21:30,593\r\nTruck?\r\n\r\n1028\r\n01:21:30,677 --> 01:21:31,928\r\nWhat truck?\r\n\r\n1029\r\n01:21:52,116 --> 01:21:53,157\r\n(MACHINE GUN FIRING)\r\n\r\n1030\r\n01:21:59,540 --> 01:22:00,832\r\nLet's go!\r\n\r\n1031\r\n01:22:09,341 --> 01:22:10,800\r\nGet back to Cairo.\r\n\r\n1032\r\n01:22:10,884 --> 01:22:12,969\r\nGet us some transport to England...\r\n\r\n1033\r\n01:22:13,053 --> 01:22:16,013\r\nboat, plane, anything.\r\n\r\n1034\r\n01:22:16,098 --> 01:22:17,203\r\nMeet me at Omar's.\r\n\r\n1035\r\n01:22:17,229 --> 01:22:18,332\r\nBe ready for me.\r\n\r\n1036\r\n01:22:18,392 --> 01:22:19,475\r\nI'm going after that truck.\r\n\r\n1037\r\n01:22:19,560 --> 01:22:21,102\r\n- How?\r\n- I don't know.\r\n\r\n1038\r\n01:22:21,186 --> 01:22:22,437\r\nI'm making this up as I go.\r\n\r\n1039\r\n01:22:39,913 --> 01:22:43,708\r\n(PEOPLE SHOUTING)\r\n\r\n1040\r\n01:23:13,238 --> 01:23:14,780\r\n(HORSE NEIGHS)\r\n\r\n1041\r\n01:23:15,199 --> 01:23:16,199\r\n(URGES HORSE)\r\n\r\n1042\r\n01:23:25,334 --> 01:23:26,375\r\n(EXCLAIMS IN GERMAN)\r\n\r\n1043\r\n01:23:29,421 --> 01:23:30,838\r\n(MAN SHOUTING)\r\n\r\n1044\r\n01:23:45,187 --> 01:23:46,229\r\n(EXCLAIMS)\r\n\r\n1045\r\n01:24:03,288 --> 01:24:04,330\r\n(SCREAMS)\r\n\r\n1046\r\n01:24:06,542 --> 01:24:08,084\r\n(SCREAMS WARNING IN GERMAN)\r\n\r\n1047\r\n01:25:05,100 --> 01:25:06,142\r\n(CURSES IN GERMAN)\r\n\r\n1048\r\n01:25:25,412 --> 01:25:26,871\r\n(SPEAKING GERMAN)\r\n\r\n1049\r\n01:25:33,920 --> 01:25:35,004\r\n(MACHINE GUN FIRES)\r\n\r\n1050\r\n01:25:37,341 --> 01:25:38,424\r\n(SCREAMING)\r\n\r\n1051\r\n01:25:44,139 --> 01:25:45,598\r\n(BARKS ORDERS IN GERMAN)\r\n\r\n1052\r\n01:26:00,030 --> 01:26:01,238\r\nEw!\r\n\r\n1053\r\n01:26:04,785 --> 01:26:05,910\r\n(SCREAMING)\r\n\r\n1054\r\n01:26:20,133 --> 01:26:21,258\r\n(SCREAMS)\r\n\r\n1055\r\n01:26:28,809 --> 01:26:29,934\r\n(GUN FIRES)\r\n\r\n1056\r\n01:26:44,282 --> 01:26:47,284\r\n(SCREAMING)\r\n\r\n1057\r\n01:26:48,787 --> 01:26:49,829\r\n(CURSES IN GERMAN)\r\n\r\n1058\r\n01:27:37,002 --> 01:27:38,085\r\n(SHOUTING IN GERMAN)\r\n\r\n1059\r\n01:28:23,840 --> 01:28:24,840\r\nHe's there!\r\n\r\n1060\r\n01:28:45,070 --> 01:28:46,153\r\n(SCREAMS)\r\n\r\n1061\r\n01:28:48,907 --> 01:28:50,241\r\n(ENGINE REVVING)\r\n\r\n1062\r\n01:29:16,810 --> 01:29:18,352\r\nIdiot! Idiot!\r\n\r\n1063\r\n01:29:18,436 --> 01:29:19,770\r\n(CURSING IN GERMAN)\r\n\r\n1064\r\n01:29:46,047 --> 01:29:50,759\r\n(DOG BARKING)\r\n\r\n1065\r\n01:29:50,844 --> 01:29:51,886\r\n(DOG WHIMPERS)\r\n\r\n1066\r\n01:29:57,642 --> 01:30:03,314\r\n(ALL SINGING IN ARABIC)\r\n\r\n1067\r\n01:30:04,316 --> 01:30:06,150\r\nEverything at last has been arranged.\r\n\r\n1068\r\n01:30:06,234 --> 01:30:07,776\r\n- The Ark? - Is on board.\r\n\r\n1069\r\n01:30:07,861 --> 01:30:09,528\r\nNothing is lacking, now that you're here.\r\n\r\n1070\r\n01:30:09,654 --> 01:30:10,905\r\nOr what is left of you.\r\n\r\n1071\r\n01:30:10,989 --> 01:30:13,449\r\n- You trust these guys?\r\n- Yes.\r\n\r\n1072\r\n01:30:15,160 --> 01:30:16,911\r\nMr. Katanga.\r\n\r\n1073\r\n01:30:20,415 --> 01:30:22,583\r\nMr. Katanga, these are my friends.\r\n\r\n1074\r\n01:30:23,251 --> 01:30:25,085\r\nThey are my family.\r\n\r\n1075\r\n01:30:25,170 --> 01:30:28,255\r\nI will hear of it if they are not treated well.\r\n\r\n1076\r\n01:30:28,340 --> 01:30:30,758\r\nMy cabin is theirs.\r\n\r\n1077\r\n01:30:30,842 --> 01:30:32,843\r\nMr. Jones...\r\n\r\n1078\r\n01:30:32,928 --> 01:30:35,429\r\nI've heard a lot about you, sir.\r\n\r\n1079\r\n01:30:35,513 --> 01:30:37,890\r\nYour appearance is exactly the way I imagined.\r\n\r\n1080\r\n01:30:38,558 --> 01:30:42,186\r\n(LAUGHING)\r\n\r\n1081\r\n01:30:43,146 --> 01:30:44,855\r\nGood-bye.\r\n\r\n1082\r\n01:30:46,107 --> 01:30:47,107\r\n(GROANING)\r\n\r\n1083\r\n01:30:47,192 --> 01:30:48,984\r\nSALLAH: Look after each other.\r\n\r\n1084\r\n01:30:49,319 --> 01:30:51,111\r\nI am already missing you.\r\n\r\n1085\r\n01:30:53,657 --> 01:30:55,157\r\nYou're my good friend.\r\n\r\n1086\r\n01:30:57,827 --> 01:30:59,244\r\nSallah.\r\n\r\n1087\r\n01:31:02,999 --> 01:31:04,541\r\nThat is for Fayah...\r\n\r\n1088\r\n01:31:06,252 --> 01:31:07,753\r\nthat is for your children...\r\n\r\n1089\r\n01:31:07,837 --> 01:31:10,255\r\nand this is for you.\r\n\r\n1090\r\n01:31:11,007 --> 01:31:13,884\r\n(SHIP'S HORN BLARING)\r\n\r\n1091\r\n01:31:14,886 --> 01:31:16,220\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\n1092\r\n01:31:17,222 --> 01:31:19,765\r\n(SHIP'S HORN BLARING)\r\n\r\n1093\r\n01:31:25,522 --> 01:31:30,734\r\n(SINGING) A British taris a soaring soul\r\n\r\n1094\r\n01:31:30,902 --> 01:31:34,822\r\nAs free as a mountain bird\r\n\r\n1095\r\n01:31:35,198 --> 01:31:39,118\r\nHis energetic fist should be ready to...\r\n\r\n1096\r\n01:31:40,745 --> 01:31:43,205\r\n...a dictator...\r\n\r\n1097\r\n01:31:47,752 --> 01:31:49,211\r\n(WHISTLING)\r\n\r\n1098\r\n01:31:49,963 --> 01:31:51,255\r\nINDY: Where did you go?\r\n\r\n1099\r\n01:31:52,048 --> 01:31:53,132\r\nI'm cleaning up.\r\n\r\n1100\r\n01:31:54,509 --> 01:31:56,427\r\nWhere'd you get that?\r\n\r\n1101\r\n01:31:56,886 --> 01:31:57,970\r\nFrom him.\r\n\r\n1102\r\n01:31:58,054 --> 01:31:59,304\r\nWho him?\r\n\r\n1103\r\n01:31:59,389 --> 01:32:00,431\r\nKatanga.\r\n\r\n1104\r\n01:32:00,515 --> 01:32:01,807\r\nI got a feeling I'm not the first woman\r\n\r\n1105\r\n01:32:01,933 --> 01:32:04,018\r\never to travel with these pirates.\r\n\r\n1106\r\n01:32:04,102 --> 01:32:06,353\r\nIt's lovely.\r\n\r\n1107\r\n01:32:06,438 --> 01:32:07,521\r\nYeah?\r\n\r\n1108\r\n01:32:07,605 --> 01:32:08,605\r\nYeah.\r\n\r\n1109\r\n01:32:08,690 --> 01:32:09,732\r\nReally?\r\n\r\n1110\r\n01:32:09,816 --> 01:32:11,108\r\nYeah.\r\n\r\n1111\r\n01:32:15,321 --> 01:32:16,447\r\n(GROANS)\r\n\r\n1112\r\n01:32:17,949 --> 01:32:18,949\r\n(BANGING)\r\n\r\n1113\r\n01:32:19,075 --> 01:32:20,743\r\n(INDY SCREAMING)\r\n\r\n1114\r\n01:32:22,454 --> 01:32:23,746\r\nWhat'd you say?\r\n\r\n1115\r\n01:32:30,378 --> 01:32:32,421\r\n(GROANS) Wait... I don't need any help.\r\n\r\n1116\r\n01:32:33,256 --> 01:32:35,299\r\nYou know you do.\r\n\r\n1117\r\n01:32:37,302 --> 01:32:39,762\r\nYou're not the man I knew ten years ago.\r\n\r\n1118\r\n01:32:39,846 --> 01:32:43,265\r\nIt's not the years, honey, it's the mileage.\r\n\r\n1119\r\n01:32:48,480 --> 01:32:50,439\r\nYou are...\r\n\r\n1120\r\n01:32:51,483 --> 01:32:53,025\r\nPlease, I don't need a nurse.\r\n\r\n1121\r\n01:32:53,151 --> 01:32:53,771\r\nI just want to sleep.\r\n\r\n1122\r\n01:32:53,797 --> 01:32:54,593\r\nDon't be such a baby.\r\n\r\n1123\r\n01:32:54,652 --> 01:32:55,819\r\nMarion, leave me alone.\r\n\r\n1124\r\n01:32:55,904 --> 01:32:57,029\r\n- What is this here?\r\n- Go away.\r\n\r\n1125\r\n01:32:57,155 --> 01:32:59,615\r\nYes, it hurts.\r\n\r\n1126\r\n01:32:59,699 --> 01:33:00,741\r\nOw!\r\n\r\n1127\r\n01:33:00,825 --> 01:33:04,286\r\nWell, goddamn it, Indy, where doesn't it hurt?\r\n\r\n1128\r\n01:33:04,370 --> 01:33:06,163\r\nHere.\r\n\r\n1129\r\n01:33:12,003 --> 01:33:13,420\r\nHere.\r\n\r\n1130\r\n01:33:22,222 --> 01:33:23,847\r\nThis isn't too bad.\r\n\r\n1131\r\n01:33:33,358 --> 01:33:34,358\r\n(SOFTLY) Here.\r\n\r\n1132\r\n01:33:53,044 --> 01:33:54,545\r\n(SIGHS)\r\n\r\n1133\r\n01:33:55,547 --> 01:33:56,547\r\nJones...\r\n\r\n1134\r\n01:33:57,048 --> 01:33:58,549\r\n(SNORING)\r\n\r\n1135\r\n01:33:59,384 --> 01:34:00,801\r\nJones?\r\n\r\n1136\r\n01:34:03,638 --> 01:34:05,681\r\nWe never seem to get a break, do we?\r\n\r\n1137\r\n01:34:14,774 --> 01:34:17,317\r\n(DEEP WARBLING)\r\n\r\n1138\r\n01:34:17,402 --> 01:34:21,405\r\n(SQUEAKING WEAKLY)\r\n\r\n1139\r\n01:34:34,169 --> 01:34:35,169\r\nWhat is it?\r\n\r\n1140\r\n01:34:35,837 --> 01:34:36,907\r\nEngines have stopped.\r\n\r\n1141\r\n01:34:36,933 --> 01:34:38,155\r\nI'm going to go check.\r\n\r\n1142\r\n01:34:49,434 --> 01:34:49,946\r\nWhat's happening?\r\n\r\n1143\r\n01:34:49,972 --> 01:34:51,084\r\nWe have most important friends.\r\n\r\n1144\r\n01:34:51,144 --> 01:34:52,811\r\nHoly shit.\r\n\r\n1145\r\n01:34:52,896 --> 01:34:54,146\r\n(MAN CHATTERING ON RADIO)\r\n\r\n1146\r\n01:34:54,606 --> 01:34:55,457\r\nI sent my man for you.\r\n\r\n1147\r\n01:34:55,483 --> 01:34:56,798\r\nYou and the girl must disappear.\r\n\r\n1148\r\n01:34:56,858 --> 01:34:57,652\r\nWe have a place in the hold.\r\n\r\n1149\r\n01:34:57,678 --> 01:34:58,300\r\nCome on, go, go, go.\r\n\r\n1150\r\n01:34:58,359 --> 01:34:59,359\r\nCome on, go, my friend, go.\r\n\r\n1151\r\n01:34:59,569 --> 01:35:00,944\r\n(PHONE RINGING)\r\n\r\n1152\r\n01:35:03,781 --> 01:35:06,074\r\n(MAN CHATTERING IN GERMAN OVER MEGAPHONE)\r\n\r\n1153\r\n01:35:13,166 --> 01:35:14,208\r\nMAN: Where is Dr. Jones?\r\n\r\n1154\r\n01:35:14,292 --> 01:35:15,626\r\nMARION: What's the big idea?\r\n\r\n1155\r\n01:35:15,793 --> 01:35:17,127\r\nLet go!\r\n\r\n1156\r\n01:35:17,420 --> 01:35:18,462\r\n(GRUNTS)\r\n\r\n1157\r\n01:35:21,466 --> 01:35:23,300\r\nDon't you touch me.\r\n\r\n1158\r\n01:35:24,302 --> 01:35:25,427\r\n(YELPS)\r\n\r\n1159\r\n01:35:29,599 --> 01:35:32,309\r\n(MEN CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY)\r\n\r\n1160\r\n01:36:03,174 --> 01:36:04,841\r\n(MEN LAUGHING)\r\n\r\n1161\r\n01:36:08,054 --> 01:36:09,680\r\n(BELLOWING) What about Jones?\r\n\r\n1162\r\n01:36:09,847 --> 01:36:11,348\r\nThere's no trace yet, sir.\r\n\r\n1163\r\n01:36:11,432 --> 01:36:12,808\r\nKATANGA: Jones is dead.\r\n\r\n1164\r\n01:36:15,979 --> 01:36:17,187\r\nI killed him.\r\n\r\n1165\r\n01:36:18,356 --> 01:36:19,690\r\nHe was of no use to us.\r\n\r\n1166\r\n01:36:20,441 --> 01:36:23,193\r\nThis girl, however, has certain value where we're headed.\r\n\r\n1167\r\n01:36:23,987 --> 01:36:25,696\r\nShe'll bring a very good price.\r\n\r\n1168\r\n01:36:26,948 --> 01:36:28,031\r\nMmm?\r\n\r\n1169\r\n01:36:28,950 --> 01:36:33,036\r\nHerr Colonel, that cargo you've taken...\r\n\r\n1170\r\n01:36:33,121 --> 01:36:34,705\r\nIf it's your goal, go in peace with it,\r\n\r\n1171\r\n01:36:34,789 --> 01:36:35,789\r\nbut leave us the girl.\r\n\r\n1172\r\n01:36:35,873 --> 01:36:36,957\r\nIt would reduce our loss on this trip.\r\n\r\n1173\r\n01:36:37,041 --> 01:36:39,793\r\nSavage!\r\n\r\n1174\r\n01:36:39,877 --> 01:36:42,462\r\nYou are not in the position to ask for anything.\r\n\r\n1175\r\n01:36:42,547 --> 01:36:44,965\r\nWe will take what we wish.\r\n\r\n1176\r\n01:36:45,049 --> 01:36:46,508\r\nAnd then decide whether or not\r\n\r\n1177\r\n01:36:46,592 --> 01:36:48,510\r\nto blow your ship from the water.\r\n\r\n1178\r\n01:36:50,972 --> 01:36:52,389\r\nThe girl goes with me.\r\n\r\n1179\r\n01:36:53,850 --> 01:36:55,100\r\nShe'll be part of my compensation.\r\n\r\n1180\r\n01:36:55,184 --> 01:36:58,186\r\nI'm sure your F�hrer would approve.\r\n\r\n1181\r\n01:36:58,271 --> 01:36:59,604\r\nIf she fails to please me,\r\n\r\n1182\r\n01:36:59,689 --> 01:37:01,940\r\nyou may do with her as you wish.\r\n\r\n1183\r\n01:37:02,025 --> 01:37:05,027\r\nI will waste no more time with her now.\r\n\r\n1184\r\n01:37:05,111 --> 01:37:06,236\r\nExcuse me.\r\n\r\n1185\r\n01:37:22,337 --> 01:37:23,837\r\nI can't find Mr. Jones, Captain.\r\n\r\n1186\r\n01:37:23,921 --> 01:37:25,505\r\nI've looked everywhere.\r\n\r\n1187\r\n01:37:25,590 --> 01:37:28,008\r\nHe's got to be here somewhere.\r\n\r\n1188\r\n01:37:28,092 --> 01:37:29,259\r\nLook again.\r\n\r\n1189\r\n01:37:31,429 --> 01:37:32,763\r\n- I found him.\r\n- Where?\r\n\r\n1190\r\n01:37:33,056 --> 01:37:34,097\r\nThere.\r\n\r\n1191\r\n01:37:41,522 --> 01:37:42,564\r\n(MEN CHEERING)\r\n\r\n1192\r\n01:37:59,957 --> 01:38:01,708\r\n(SPEAKING GERMAN)\r\n\r\n1193\r\n01:38:01,793 --> 01:38:04,461\r\n(ALARM BLARING)\r\n\r\n1194\r\n01:38:06,798 --> 01:38:08,757\r\n(SPEAKING GERMAN)\r\n\r\n1195\r\n01:38:27,568 --> 01:38:31,488\r\n(MACHINERY WHIRRING)\r\n\r\n1196\r\n01:38:36,828 --> 01:38:39,162\r\n(CHATTERING IN GERMAN)\r\n\r\n1197\r\n01:38:41,582 --> 01:38:44,793\r\n(MAN CHATTERING OVER PA)\r\n\r\n1198\r\n01:39:08,025 --> 01:39:09,025\r\n(SOLDIER GASPS)\r\n\r\n1199\r\n01:39:41,726 --> 01:39:43,226\r\n(GREETS IN GERMAN)\r\n\r\n1200\r\n01:39:48,149 --> 01:39:55,071\r\n(BERATING IN GERMAN)\r\n\r\n1201\r\n01:39:55,156 --> 01:39:56,573\r\n(GRUNTS)\r\n\r\n1202\r\n01:39:56,657 --> 01:39:58,408\r\n(MOANING)\r\n\r\n1203\r\n01:40:00,620 --> 01:40:02,370\r\nThe altar has been prepared in accordance\r\n\r\n1204\r\n01:40:02,455 --> 01:40:03,830\r\nwith your radio instructions, sir.\r\n\r\n1205\r\n01:40:03,915 --> 01:40:04,956\r\nGood.\r\n\r\n1206\r\n01:40:05,082 --> 01:40:06,958\r\nTake the Ark there immediately.\r\n\r\n1207\r\n01:40:09,295 --> 01:40:11,046\r\nMonsieur...\r\n\r\n1208\r\n01:40:12,715 --> 01:40:14,674\r\nI am uncomfortable with the thought\r\n\r\n1209\r\n01:40:14,759 --> 01:40:18,845\r\nof this... Jewish ritual.\r\n\r\n1210\r\n01:40:18,930 --> 01:40:21,473\r\nAre you sure it's necessary?\r\n\r\n1211\r\n01:40:21,557 --> 01:40:23,433\r\nLet me ask you this:\r\n\r\n1212\r\n01:40:23,684 --> 01:40:27,103\r\nWould you be more comfortable opening the Ark in Berlin,\r\n\r\n1213\r\n01:40:27,396 --> 01:40:29,189\r\nfor your F�hrer?\r\n\r\n1214\r\n01:40:29,565 --> 01:40:30,815\r\nFinding out, only then,\r\n\r\n1215\r\n01:40:30,942 --> 01:40:33,652\r\nif the sacred pieces of the Covenant are inside?\r\n\r\n1216\r\n01:40:33,819 --> 01:40:34,861\r\nKnowing, only then,\r\n\r\n1217\r\n01:40:34,946 --> 01:40:36,947\r\nwhether you have accomplished your mission,\r\n\r\n1218\r\n01:40:37,114 --> 01:40:39,908\r\nand obtained the one true Ark?\r\n\r\n1219\r\n01:42:08,706 --> 01:42:09,748\r\nHello!\r\n\r\n1220\r\n01:42:12,543 --> 01:42:13,752\r\nJones.\r\n\r\n1221\r\n01:42:15,046 --> 01:42:16,463\r\nJones!\r\n\r\n1222\r\n01:42:16,589 --> 01:42:18,381\r\nI'm going to blow up the Ark, Ren�.\r\n\r\n1223\r\n01:42:24,972 --> 01:42:27,515\r\nYour persistence surprises even me.\r\n\r\n1224\r\n01:42:29,226 --> 01:42:31,561\r\nYou're going to give mercenaries a bad name.\r\n\r\n1225\r\n01:42:31,729 --> 01:42:33,438\r\nDr. Jones...\r\n\r\n1226\r\n01:42:36,233 --> 01:42:38,777\r\nsurely you don't think you can escape from this island.\r\n\r\n1227\r\n01:42:38,861 --> 01:42:41,237\r\nThat depends on how reasonable we're all willing to be.\r\n\r\n1228\r\n01:42:41,364 --> 01:42:42,739\r\nAll I want is the girl.\r\n\r\n1229\r\n01:42:48,245 --> 01:42:49,788\r\nIf we refuse?\r\n\r\n1230\r\n01:42:50,915 --> 01:42:53,083\r\nThen your F�hrer has no prize.\r\n\r\n1231\r\n01:42:54,251 --> 01:42:55,335\r\nOkay, stand back.\r\n\r\n1232\r\n01:42:55,419 --> 01:42:56,670\r\nAll of you, stand back.\r\n\r\n1233\r\n01:42:56,754 --> 01:42:58,380\r\nStand back.\r\n\r\n1234\r\n01:42:58,547 --> 01:43:00,340\r\nOkay, Jones.\r\n\r\n1235\r\n01:43:00,424 --> 01:43:02,509\r\nYou win!\r\n\r\n1236\r\n01:43:02,593 --> 01:43:03,593\r\nBlow it up.\r\n\r\n1237\r\n01:43:03,719 --> 01:43:04,928\r\n(EXCLAIMS)\r\n\r\n1238\r\n01:43:05,012 --> 01:43:07,097\r\n(SHOUTING IN GERMAN)\r\n\r\n1239\r\n01:43:10,184 --> 01:43:13,478\r\nYes, blow it up!\r\n\r\n1240\r\n01:43:13,562 --> 01:43:15,146\r\nBlow it back to God.\r\n\r\n1241\r\n01:43:16,273 --> 01:43:17,691\r\nAll your life has been spent\r\n\r\n1242\r\n01:43:17,775 --> 01:43:20,360\r\nin pursuit of archeological relics.\r\n\r\n1243\r\n01:43:20,444 --> 01:43:24,114\r\nInside the Ark are treasures beyond your wildest aspirations.\r\n\r\n1244\r\n01:43:25,032 --> 01:43:27,158\r\nYou want to see it open as well as I.\r\n\r\n1245\r\n01:43:29,286 --> 01:43:31,287\r\nIndiana...\r\n\r\n1246\r\n01:43:31,622 --> 01:43:34,124\r\nwe are simply passing through history.\r\n\r\n1247\r\n01:43:35,876 --> 01:43:37,043\r\nThis...\r\n\r\n1248\r\n01:43:39,630 --> 01:43:41,297\r\nThis is history.\r\n\r\n1249\r\n01:43:51,308 --> 01:43:52,976\r\nDo as you will.\r\n\r\n1250\r\n01:44:07,825 --> 01:44:09,242\r\n(THUNDER RUMBLING)\r\n\r\n1251\r\n01:44:30,347 --> 01:44:35,351\r\n(INCANTING IN ANCIENT LANGUAGE)\r\n\r\n1252\r\n01:45:21,398 --> 01:45:23,483\r\n(LAUGHING SOFTLY)\r\n\r\n1253\r\n01:45:23,567 --> 01:45:29,572\r\n(CACKLING)\r\n\r\n1254\r\n01:45:35,120 --> 01:45:39,123\r\n(POWER SURGING)\r\n\r\n1255\r\n01:45:53,973 --> 01:46:00,603\r\n(DEEP WARBLING)\r\n\r\n1256\r\n01:46:01,313 --> 01:46:03,439\r\n(THUNDER RUMBLING)\r\n\r\n1257\r\n01:46:12,283 --> 01:46:14,617\r\n(DISEMBODIED VOICES HISSING)\r\n\r\n1258\r\n01:46:28,632 --> 01:46:30,425\r\nMarion, don't look at it.\r\n\r\n1259\r\n01:46:30,509 --> 01:46:31,634\r\nShut your eyes, Marion.\r\n\r\n1260\r\n01:46:31,719 --> 01:46:33,219\r\nDon't look at it, no matter what happens.\r\n\r\n1261\r\n01:46:44,982 --> 01:46:46,357\r\nAh...\r\n\r\n1262\r\n01:46:49,820 --> 01:46:50,987\r\n(SCREAMING)\r\n\r\n1263\r\n01:47:01,999 --> 01:47:03,666\r\nIt's beautiful!\r\n\r\n1264\r\n01:47:10,341 --> 01:47:11,466\r\n(ROARS)\r\n\r\n1265\r\n01:47:11,550 --> 01:47:12,675\r\n(SCREAMING)\r\n\r\n1266\r\n01:47:14,553 --> 01:47:15,678\r\nIndy?\r\n\r\n1267\r\n01:47:15,763 --> 01:47:16,804\r\nDon't look, Marion!\r\n\r\n1268\r\n01:47:16,889 --> 01:47:18,139\r\nKeep your eyes shut!\r\n\r\n1269\r\n01:47:23,354 --> 01:47:24,854\r\n(SCREAMING)\r\n\r\n1270\r\n01:47:38,327 --> 01:47:40,370\r\n(SCREAMING)\r\n\r\n1271\r\n01:47:54,677 --> 01:47:57,220\r\n(BOTH SCREAMING)\r\n\r\n1272\r\n01:48:25,749 --> 01:48:30,712\r\n(THUNDER CLAPPING)\r\n\r\n1273\r\n01:48:32,047 --> 01:48:33,965\r\n(WIND WHISTLING)\r\n\r\n1274\r\n01:48:36,427 --> 01:48:37,593\r\nMarion.\r\n\r\n1275\r\n01:48:40,264 --> 01:48:41,389\r\n(GASPING)\r\n\r\n1276\r\n01:49:10,252 --> 01:49:13,713\r\nYou've done your country a great service, and we thank you.\r\n\r\n1277\r\n01:49:13,797 --> 01:49:17,550\r\nAnd we trust you found the settlement satisfactory.\r\n\r\n1278\r\n01:49:17,634 --> 01:49:18,718\r\nOh, the money's fine.\r\n\r\n1279\r\n01:49:18,802 --> 01:49:20,470\r\nThe situation's totally unacceptable.\r\n\r\n1280\r\n01:49:20,554 --> 01:49:22,889\r\nWell, gentlemen, I guess that just about wraps it up.\r\n\r\n1281\r\n01:49:22,973 --> 01:49:26,893\r\nWhere is the Ark?\r\n\r\n1282\r\n01:49:26,977 --> 01:49:28,644\r\nI thought we'd settled that.\r\n\r\n1283\r\n01:49:28,812 --> 01:49:31,439\r\nThe Ark is somewhere very safe.\r\n\r\n1284\r\n01:49:31,523 --> 01:49:32,648\r\nFrom whom?\r\n\r\n1285\r\n01:49:32,775 --> 01:49:35,401\r\nThe Ark is a source of unspeakable power\r\n\r\n1286\r\n01:49:35,486 --> 01:49:37,320\r\nand it has to be researched.\r\n\r\n1287\r\n01:49:37,404 --> 01:49:40,615\r\nAnd it will be, I assure you, Dr. Brody,\r\n\r\n1288\r\n01:49:40,699 --> 01:49:42,241\r\nDr. Jones.\r\n\r\n1289\r\n01:49:42,326 --> 01:49:45,953\r\nWe have top men working on it right now.\r\n\r\n1290\r\n01:49:47,039 --> 01:49:48,247\r\nWho?\r\n\r\n1291\r\n01:49:49,792 --> 01:49:52,085\r\nTop men.\r\n\r\n1292\r\n01:49:55,297 --> 01:49:57,548\r\nHey, what happened?\r\n\r\n1293\r\n01:49:57,674 --> 01:49:58,758\r\nYou don't look very happy.\r\n\r\n1294\r\n01:49:58,842 --> 01:50:00,378\r\nFools. Bureaucratic fools.\r\n\r\n1295\r\n01:50:00,404 --> 01:50:01,702\r\nWhat'd they say?\r\n\r\n1296\r\n01:50:02,554 --> 01:50:04,347\r\nThey don't know what they've got there.\r\n\r\n1297\r\n01:50:05,099 --> 01:50:07,058\r\nWell, I know what I've got here.\r\n\r\n1298\r\n01:50:08,435 --> 01:50:09,685\r\nCome on.\r\n\r\n1299\r\n01:50:10,062 --> 01:50:11,104\r\nI'll buy you a drink.\r\n\r\n1300\r\n01:50:11,188 --> 01:50: