t's me, Crowning.\r\n\r\n735\r\n02:08:02,586 --> 02:08:05,338\r\n- Crowning.\r\n- Yeah.\r\n\r\n736\r\n02:08:05,506 --> 02:08:07,173\r\nThat'll do, boys.\r\n\r\n737\r\n02:08:07,341 --> 02:08:09,175\r\nWhat'll do?\r\n\r\n738\r\n02:08:09,343 --> 02:08:12,637\r\nWe almost got the kid\r\nwhere we want him.\r\n\r\n739\r\n02:08:16,475 --> 02:08:19,561\r\nAnd we got the boss where we want him.\r\n\r\n740\r\n02:08:19,728 --> 02:08:21,312\r\nEasy.\r\n\r\n741\r\n02:08:22,356 --> 02:08:24,357\r\nEasy.\r\n\r\n742\r\n02:08:27,695 --> 02:08:30,029\r\nPut them down.\r\n\r\n743\r\n02:08:30,781 --> 02:08:33,366\r\nPut your guns away, boys.\r\n\r\n744\r\n02:08:43,168 --> 02:08:45,253\r\nJust swapping prisoners.\r\n\r\n745\r\n02:08:45,879 --> 02:08:48,506\r\nFair trade, huh, chickenhead?\r\n\r\n746\r\n02:08:55,889 --> 02:08:59,058\r\nUnion boy over here for Mr. Boss Man.\r\n\r\n747\r\n02:08:59,226 --> 02:09:01,769\r\nWell, look who's here. Ha, ha.\r\n\r\n748\r\n02:09:02,521 --> 02:09:05,273\r\nFat Moe's boneyard boys.\r\n\r\n749\r\n02:09:05,441 --> 02:09:07,525\r\nWhich reminds me.\r\n\r\n750\r\n02:09:07,943 --> 02:09:11,696\r\nHow's that cancer in your gut\r\ncoming along, Chicken Joe?\r\n\r\n751\r\n02:09:13,866 --> 02:09:17,660\r\n- Untie him.\r\n- I don't take orders from you.\r\n\r\n752\r\n02:09:17,828 --> 02:09:20,996\r\nWe're not asking you to take orders, Joe.\r\nWe're telling you.\r\n\r\n753\r\n02:09:21,164 --> 02:09:23,332\r\nNow go ahead, untie him.\r\n\r\n754\r\n02:09:23,499 --> 02:09:25,500\r\nUntie him.\r\n\r\n755\r\n02:09:30,381 --> 02:09:31,506\r\nUntie him.\r\n\r\n756\r\n02:10:02,789 --> 02:10:04,790\r\nWho are you?\r\n\r\n757\r\n02:10:05,792 --> 02:10:06,833\r\nWho's paying you?\r\n\r\n758\r\n02:10:08,169 --> 02:10:10,921\r\nI think this is really gonna\r\npiss you off there, Mac.\r\n\r\n759\r\n02:10:11,089 --> 02:10:14,633\r\nI think it's those dirty, dirty\r\npolitician friends of yours.\r\n\r\n760\r\n02:10:14,801 --> 02:10:19,429\r\nYeah? Well, you crawl back and tell\r\nhim we don't want you in with us.\r\n\r\n761\r\n02:10:19,597 --> 02:10:23,350\r\nOur fight's got nothing to do with\r\nliquor and prostitution and dope.\r\n\r\n762\r\n02:10:23,518 --> 02:10:26,395\r\nYou'd better\r\nget used to the idea, pal.\r\n\r\n763\r\n02:10:27,105 --> 02:10:28,980\r\nThis country is still growing up.\r\n\r\n764\r\n02:10:29,148 --> 02:10:33,068\r\nCertain diseases it's better\r\nto have when you're still young.\r\n\r\n765\r\n02:10:34,862 --> 02:10:39,658\r\nYou boys ain't a mild case\r\nof the measles. You're the plague.\r\n\r\n766\r\n02:10:39,826 --> 02:10:41,868\r\nAnd bastards like him are immune.\r\n\r\n767\r\n02:10:42,036 --> 02:10:45,330\r\nThat's the difference\r\nbetween us and them!\r\n\r\n768\r\n02:10:47,166 --> 02:10:49,000\r\nTake it easy.\r\n\r\n769\r\n02:10:49,168 --> 02:10:51,169\r\nThe difference is that\r\nthey're always gonna win...\r\n\r\n770\r\n02:10:51,337 --> 02:10:53,922\r\n...and you're gonna\r\nkeep getting it up the ass.\r\n\r\n771\r\n02:10:54,090 --> 02:10:56,049\r\nSooner than you think.\r\n\r\n772\r\n02:11:13,359 --> 02:11:17,571\r\nChief Aiello, moving policemen into\r\nthe factory came as a surprise to everyone:\r\n\r\n773\r\n02:11:17,739 --> 02:11:20,449\r\nThe press, the unions,\r\nespecially the strikers.\r\n\r\n774\r\n02:11:20,616 --> 02:11:23,201\r\nWell, what did you want, sweetheart,\r\na declaration of war?\r\n\r\n775\r\n02:11:23,369 --> 02:11:25,120\r\nOurs was a peaceable operation.\r\n\r\n776\r\n02:11:25,288 --> 02:11:27,663\r\nWasn't that contrary\r\nto new union laws?\r\n\r\n777\r\n02:11:27,831 --> 02:11:30,040\r\nI'm chief of police,\r\nnot chief of the people.\r\n\r\n778\r\n02:11:30,208 --> 02:11:32,543\r\nWas there any violence by the strikers\r\nto justify...?\r\n\r\n779\r\n02:11:32,711 --> 02:11:36,380\r\nMy motto is:\r\n\"Prevention, not repression.\"\r\n\r\n780\r\n02:11:36,548 --> 02:11:38,632\r\nBut you let scabs move in\r\nand start working.\r\n\r\n781\r\n02:11:38,800 --> 02:11:42,178\r\