2:31:40,324\r\nTo keep from going crazy,\r\nyou have to cut yourself off from the world.\r\n\r\n993\r\n02:31:40,492 --> 02:31:43,118\r\nJust not think about it.\r\nYou have to, uh....\r\n\r\n994\r\n02:31:43,286 --> 02:31:46,580\r\nYou know, years that went by,\r\nit seemed like...\r\n\r\n995\r\n02:31:46,748 --> 02:31:50,042\r\n...no time at all,\r\nbecause you're not doing anything.\r\n\r\n996\r\n02:31:50,210 --> 02:31:53,754\r\nBut there were two things I couldn't\r\nget out of my mind. One was Dominic.\r\n\r\n997\r\n02:31:53,922 --> 02:31:57,466\r\nThe way he said \"I slipped\"\r\njust before he died.\r\n\r\n998\r\n02:31:58,760 --> 02:32:01,011\r\nThe other was you.\r\n\r\n999\r\n02:32:07,227 --> 02:32:11,438\r\nHow you used to read me\r\nyour Song of Songs, remember?\r\n\r\n1000\r\n02:32:13,233 --> 02:32:17,695\r\n<i>How beautiful are your feet</i>\r\n<i>in sandals, O prince's daughter.</i>\r\n\r\n1001\r\n02:32:21,324 --> 02:32:26,495\r\nI used to read the Bible every night.\r\nEvery night I used to think about you.\r\n\r\n1002\r\n02:32:28,748 --> 02:32:33,460\r\n<i>Your navel is a bowl,</i>\r\n<i>well-rounded with no lack of wine.</i>\r\n\r\n1003\r\n02:32:33,628 --> 02:32:37,506\r\n<i>Your belly, a heap of wheat</i>\r\n<i>surrounded with lilies.</i>\r\n\r\n1004\r\n02:32:37,674 --> 02:32:40,092\r\n<i>Your breasts...</i>\r\n\r\n1005\r\n02:32:41,636 --> 02:32:44,095\r\n<i>...clusters of grapes.</i>\r\n\r\n1006\r\n02:32:44,805 --> 02:32:49,142\r\n<i>Your breath, sweet-scented as apples.</i>\r\n\r\n1007\r\n02:32:56,734 --> 02:32:59,819\r\nNobody's gonna love you\r\nthe way I loved you.\r\n\r\n1008\r\n02:33:04,324 --> 02:33:07,827\r\nThere were times I couldn't stand it\r\nanymore. I used to think about you.\r\n\r\n1009\r\n02:33:07,995 --> 02:33:12,081\r\nI'd think, \"Deborah lives.\r\nShe's out there. She exists.\"\r\n\r\n1010\r\n02:33:12,249 --> 02:33:14,751\r\nAnd that would get me through it all.\r\n\r\n1011\r\n02:33:17,296 --> 02:33:19,839\r\nYou know how important\r\nthat was to me?\r\n\r\n1012\r\n02:33:26,096 --> 02:33:28,723\r\nNoodles, I'm leaving tomorrow\r\nto go to Hollywood.\r\n\r\n1013\r\n02:33:28,891 --> 02:33:31,684\r\nI wanted to see you tonight\r\nto tell you.\r\n\r\n1014\r\n02:35:25,798 --> 02:35:27,465\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n1015\r\n02:35:27,925 --> 02:35:29,509\r\nNo! I...\r\n\r\n1016\r\n02:35:30,136 --> 02:35:32,929\r\nNo! No. Ah!\r\n\r\n1017\r\n02:35:36,559 --> 02:35:41,646\r\nNo. Please, no. No, please. No!\r\n\r\n1018\r\n02:35:41,814 --> 02:35:47,110\r\nNo! Oh, no! No, please!\r\n\r\n1019\r\n02:35:47,278 --> 02:35:52,449\r\nNo, no! Please, no, no. No.\r\n\r\n1020\r\n02:35:55,745 --> 02:35:57,495\r\nNo!\r\n\r\n1021\r\n02:37:32,382 --> 02:37:34,049\r\nDeborah. Deborah.\r\n\r\n1022\r\n02:37:34,217 --> 02:37:36,593\r\nGet away! Get away!\r\n\r\n1023\r\n02:37:53,528 --> 02:37:55,487\r\nI'll be right back.\r\n\r\n1024\r\n02:38:27,228 --> 02:38:29,021\r\nTake her home.\r\n\r\n1025\r\n02:38:29,939 --> 02:38:31,774\r\nTake her home.\r\n\r\n1026\r\n02:40:05,033 --> 02:40:07,660\r\nAll aboard!\r\n\r\n1027\r\n02:42:28,342 --> 02:42:29,884\r\nWell...\r\n\r\n1028\r\n02:42:30,553 --> 02:42:32,762\r\n...look who's back.\r\n\r\n1029\r\n02:42:34,056 --> 02:42:35,807\r\nWhat's this?\r\n\r\n1030\r\n02:42:39,312 --> 02:42:41,062\r\nIt's a throne.\r\n\r\n1031\r\n02:42:43,232 --> 02:42:45,609\r\nIt was a gift to a pope.\r\n\r\n1032\r\n02:42:46,485 --> 02:42:50,864\r\n- Cost me 800 bucks.\r\n- It's from the 17th century.\r\n\r\n1033\r\n02:43:00,124 --> 02:43:02,584\r\nSo, what are you doing with it?\r\n\r\n1034\r\n02:43:05,421 --> 02:43:07,297\r\nI'm sitting on it.\r\n\r\n1035\r\n02:43:15,598 --> 02:43:18,767\r\n- You got any coffee around?\r\n- Yeah, sure.\r\n\r\n1036\r\n02:43:30,612 --> 02:43:32,279\r\nThanks.\r\n\r\n1037\r\n02:44:47,188 --> 02:44:48,689\r\nHm.\r\n\r\n1038\r\n02:44:50,191 --> 02:44:54,945\r\nWhile you were on vacation,\r\nwe were working overtime.\r\n\r\n1039\r\n02:45:02,120 --> 02:45:04,246\r\nThe union paid off.\r\n\r\n1040\r\n02:45:07,125 --> 02:45:09,168\r\nThat's your share.\r\n\r\n1041\r\n02:45:10,295 --> 02:45:14,590\r\nYeah. Even that geek.\r\nYou know, Jimmy \"Clean Hands\"...\r\n\r\n1042\r\n02:45:14,758 --> 02:45:20,554\r\n...respects us.\r\nEh, I shed a little blood for the cause.\r\n\r\n1043\r\n02:45:20,722 --> 02:45:23,140\r\nYeah, it's all in the papers.\r\n\r\n1044\r\n02:45:23,308 --> 02:45:27,435\r\n<i>Morning Telegraph</i>, they didn't like it.\r\n\r\n1045\r\n02:45:27,603 --> 02:45:32,440\r\nIt says, \"Underworld joins strikers\r\nin brutal battle.\"\r\n\r\n1046\r\n02:45:32,608 --> 02:45:36,402\r\nBut <i>The Post</i>, they liked it.\r\n\r\n1047\r\n02:45:36,570 --> 02:45:40,281\r\n\"Ends justify means\r\nin decisive gangland encounter.\"\r\n\r\n1048\r\n02:45:40,699 --> 02:45:43,618\r\nAnd they're the ones that kvetched\r\nabout the Atlantic City job.\r\n\r\n1049\r\n02:45:43,786 --> 02:45:47,789\r\nHeh. Newspaper guys never know\r\nwhat the fuck they want.\r\n\r\n1050\r\n02:45:54,713 --> 02:45:58,090\r\n- Well, you could have looked for me.\r\n- We did.\r\n\r\n1051\r\n02:45:59,426 --> 02:46:01,886\r\nCockeye found you at the Chink's.\r\n\r\n1052\r\n02:46:02,054 --> 02:46:04,806\r\nSo fucking doped up\r\nyou didn't even recognize him.\r\n\r\n1053\r\n02:46:05,015 --> 02:46:10,186\r\nYeah, you were. Heh.\r\nYou called me \"Deborah.\" Ha-ha-ha.\r\n\r\n1054\r\n02:46:11,939 --> 02:46:14,273\r\nHey, go fuck yourself.\r\nMind your own business.\r\n\r\n1055\r\n02:46:14,441 --> 02:46:18,736\r\nWe do our business together\r\nand fucking broads do not get in the way...\r\n\r\n1056\r\n02:46:18,904 --> 02:46:20,196\r\n- ...and you know it!\r\n- Yeah?\r\n\r\n1057\r\n02:46:20,364 --> 02:46:22,615\r\n- Yeah.\r\n- Then what's she doing here?\r\n\r\n1058\r\n02:46:23,909 --> 02:46:27,829\r\nToday ain't Saturday. She should be in\r\nDetroit, screwing on the assembly line.\r\n\r\n1059\r\n02:46:27,996 --> 02:46:30,623\r\nWell, she's screwing here now.\r\n\r\n1060\r\n02:46:30,791 --> 02:46:34,502\r\nAnd only with Max.\r\n\r\n1061\r\n02:46:35,128 --> 02:46:37,088\r\nOh, yeah?\r\n\r\n1062\r\n02:46:37,256 --> 02:46:41,843\r\n- With her husband peeping through?\r\n- No, I left him.\r\n\r\n1063\r\n02:46:45,889 --> 02:46:49,642\r\nYou live with her, bring her here,\r\nand you tell me not to mess with broads.\r\n\r\n1064\r\n02:46:49,810 --> 02:46:51,561\r\n- You forget one thing.\r\n- What?\r\n\r\n1065\r\n02:46:51,728 --> 02:46:53,896\r\n- I don't give a fuck about her.\r\n- Max...\r\n\r\n1066\r\n02:46:54,064 --> 02:46:57,316\r\n- Shut up! Shut up! Shh!\r\n- Maxie, tell me something.\r\n\r\n1067\r\n02:46:57,484 --> 02:46:59,318\r\nWhat'll you spend your honeymoon on?\r\n\r\n1068\r\n02:46:59,486 --> 02:47:03,531\r\n- Maxie...\r\n- Shut the fuck up! Shut up!\r\n\r\n1069\r\n02:47:04,825 --> 02:47:06,909\r\nJust shut up!\r\n\r\n1070\r\n02:47:11,373 --> 02:47:13,374\r\nYou want me to dump her?\r\n\r\n1071\r\n02:47:13,834 --> 02:47:15,751\r\nYou want me to kick her\r\nout of here?\r\n\r\n1072\r\n02:47:17,838 --> 02:47:20,172\r\nWant me to kick her ass out or what?\r\n\r\n1073\r\n02:47:20,340 --> 02:47:25,094\r\nYou want me to kick...? Get the fuck out!\r\nGet the fuck out! Get out!\r\n\r\n1074\r\n02:47:32,144 --> 02:47:34,978\r\nYou gonna tell me I don't have\r\na way with women? Ha-ha-ha.\r\n\r\n1075\r\n02:47:47,825 --> 02:47:50,327\r\n- Hello.\r\n<i>- This is Jimmy. Who's this, Max?</i>\r\n\r\n1076\r\n02:47:50,494 --> 02:47:52,537\r\nNo, it's Noodles.\r\n\r\n1077\r\n02:47:54,874 --> 02:47:58,877\r\nOkay, listen.\r\nWe're gonna need you guys today.\r\n\r\n1078\r\n02:47:59,045 --> 02:48:02,297\r\nI'm gonna be making\r\na tough speech, and I think you...\r\n\r\n1079\r\n02:48:12,934 --> 02:48:14,976\r\nGo, go!\r\n\r\n1080\r\n02:48:36,248 --> 02:48:39,501\r\nStart the engine.\r\nI'll be right with you.\r\n\r\n1081\r\n02:48:39,669 --> 02:48:43,922\r\nMr. Gallagher wants you to know\r\nhow much he appreciates what you did.\r\n\r\n1082\r\n02:48:44,090 --> 02:48:46,508\r\nTo show his appreciation....\r\n\r\n1083\r\n02:48:56,936 --> 02:49:00,063\r\nHere's an envelope\r\nfor the both of youse.\r\n\r\n1084\r\n02:49:00,231 --> 02:49:04,943\r\nIf we gotta complete the job,\r\nI'll let you know.\r\n\r\n1085\r\n02:49:41,063 --> 02:49:42,230\r\nWhoa! Whoa!\r\n\r\n1086\r\n02:49:42,647 --> 02:49:44,773\r\nWiped out by a blast of Cordon Rouge.\r\n\r\n1087\r\n02:49:44,941 --> 02:49:47,568\r\nWhat would Crowning\r\nand his bosses say after that, eh?\r\n\r\n1088\r\n02:49:47,736 --> 02:49:50,654\r\nNever be afraid of you, then,\r\nwould they?\r\n\r\n1089\r\n02:49:50,822 --> 02:49:55,576\r\nThey're still not afraid of me.\r\nIt was you boys that scared them off.\r\n\r\n1090\r\n02:49:55,827 --> 02:50:00,205\r\nAnd you didn't want these guys.\r\nAren't you lucky you got party leaders...\r\n\r\n1091\r\n02:50:00,373 --> 02:50:02,666\r\n...like myself who care about the union?\r\n\r\n1092\r\n02:50:02,834 --> 02:50:07,171\r\nHey, the strike is settled. We won.\r\nThat's what counts. Am I right, Jim?\r\n\r\n1093\r\n02:50:07,338 --> 02:50:11,133\r\nIt was tough for Jimmy not to be there\r\nto sign the contract though, huh, Jim?\r\n\r\n1094\r\n02:50:11,301 --> 02:50:12,843\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n1095\r\n02:50:14,512 --> 02:50:19,349\r\nWhat's tough is, you boys did more in\r\na night than I could in two years of talking.\r\n\r\n1096\r\n02:50:19,517 --> 02:50:21,727\r\n- Forget it.\r\n- To the hottest newcomer...\r\n\r\n1097\r\n02:50:21,895 --> 02:50:23,896\r\n- ...in American unions.\r\n- There you go.\r\n\r\n1098\r\n02:50:24,064 --> 02:50:26,148\r\n- Jimmy Conway.\r\n- Now you're talking.\r\n\r\n1099\r\n02:50:26,316 --> 02:50:27,733\r\nRoll out the barrel.\r\n\r\n1100\r\n02:50:27,901 --> 02:50:32,196\r\n- May God bless.\r\n- Drink up. Suck it right down.\r\n\r\n1101\r\n02:50:32,363 --> 02:50:36,158\r\nYou must be crazy giving\r\nhim drinks. We're going to operate.\r\n\r\n1102\r\n02:50:36,326 --> 02:50:41,288\r\nOh, what's the rush? They already told me\r\nI'd be a gimp for the rest of my life.\r\n\r\n1103\r\n02:50:41,456 --> 02:50:46,627\r\nDon't worry, Jimmy, with one leg\r\na little shy, you're gonna take giant steps.\r\n\r\n1104\r\n02:50:46,795 --> 02:50:50,923\r\nYeah. And always one step\r\nright behind you, Sharkey?\r\n\r\n1105\r\n02:50:51,091 --> 02:50:53,801\r\nMake sure they work on\r\nthe right leg, Jim.\r\n\r\n1106\r\n02:50:53,968 --> 02:50:56,261\r\n- It's only blood, huh?\r\n- Mazel.\r\n\r\n1107\r\n02:51:04,145 --> 02:51:09,149\r\nYou boys got yourself a real martyr\r\nfor a friend. Make it work for you.\r\n\r\n1108\r\n02:51:09,317 --> 02:51:12,528\r\nYeah, but what the hell are we\r\ngonna do with a martyr?\r\n\r\n1109\r\n02:51:12,695 --> 02:51:16,907\r\nTimes change. Prohibition ain't gonna\r\nlast much longer. Take it from me...\r\n\r\n1110\r\n02:51:17,075 --> 02:51:23,413\r\n- ...a lot of you guys will be out of work.\r\n- Go on, Mr. Sharkey. We're interested.\r\n\r\n1111\r\n02:51:24,833 --> 02:51:28,377\r\nYou ever think of setting\r\nyourselves up in business?\r\n\r\n1112\r\n02:51:28,753 --> 02:51:33,507\r\nAll those trucks they're using to haul\r\nliquor, soon be selling them for nothing.\r\n\r\n1113\r\n02:51:33,675 --> 02:51:38,929\r\nI'm talking about hundreds of vehicles\r\ncontrolled by a national organization...\r\n\r\n1114\r\n02:51:39,097 --> 02:51:42,683\r\n...and supported by a powerful union\r\nheaded by Jimmy Conway.\r\n\r\n1115\r\n02:51:42,851 --> 02:51:46,937\r\nWhatever you ask,\r\nthere's no way he can turn you down.\r\n\r\n1116\r\n02:51:47,605 --> 02:51:49,648\r\nYou gotta be kidding, Sharkey.\r\n\r\n1117\r\n02:51:51,859 --> 02:51:55,194\r\nJimmy \"Clean Hands\"\r\nin business with us?\r\n\r\n1118\r\n02:51:55,821 --> 02:51:59,323\r\nThey won't be clean for long,\r\nwith the hands he's gonna shake.\r\n\r\n1119\r\n02:51:59,491 --> 02:52:02,118\r\nEverything in good time.\r\n\r\n1120\r\n02:52:16,967 --> 02:52:20,970\r\n- We're not interested.\r\n- What's the matter, you got a problem?\r\n\r\n1121\r\n02:52:21,138 --> 02:52:24,807\r\nWe got plenty of money tucked away.\r\nWhy not invest it? What is the problem?\r\n\r\n1122\r\n02:52:24,975 --> 02:52:29,270\r\nI'll put the party behind you.\r\nAnd I got friends in high places.\r\n\r\n1123\r\n02:52:30,814 --> 02:52:34,066\r\nI'm not interested in your friends,\r\nand I don't trust politicians.\r\n\r\n1124\r\n02:52:34,234 --> 02:52:36,819\r\nYou still think like\r\nsome schmuck from the streets.\r\n\r\n1125\r\n02:52:36,987 --> 02:52:39,947\r\nIf we'd listened to you,\r\nwe'd still be rolling drunks.\r\n\r\n1126\r\n02:52:40,115 --> 02:52:42,450\r\n- Are you broke?\r\n- Don't bust my balls.\r\n\r\n1127\r\n02:52:42,618 --> 02:52:45,661\r\nI am talking about real money.\r\n\r\n1128\r\n02:52:46,163 --> 02:52:51,834\r\nThis is real money to me. It's a lot\r\nof money. You want any of it?\r\n\r\n1129\r\n02:52:52,294 --> 02:52:56,714\r\n- You carry that stink of the streets.\r\n- I like the stink. It makes me feel good.\r\n\r\n1130\r\n02:52:56,882 --> 02:53:00,384\r\nI like the smell of it.\r\nIt opens up my lungs.\r\n\r\n1131\r\n02:53:01,094 --> 02:53:03,179\r\nAnd it gives me a hard-on.\r\n\r\n1132\r\n02:53:03,347 --> 02:53:05,681\r\nYou're carrying dead weight, Maxie.\r\n\r\n1133\r\n02:53:05,849 --> 02:53:09,101\r\nOne of these days,\r\nyou're gonna have to dump it.\r\n\r\n1134\r\n02:53:12,731 --> 02:53:15,524\r\nMaxie. Let me know\r\nwhen you're gonna dump me.\r\n\r\n1135\r\n02:53:15,692 --> 02:53:19,278\r\nMeanwhile, I'll take a vacation in Florida.\r\nI got a yen for the seashore.\r\n\r\n1136\r\n02:53:42,261 --> 02:53:43,970\r\nHey.\r\n\r\n1137\r\n02:53:45,847 --> 02:53:48,724\r\nListen, I was thinking it over and, um....\r\n\r\n1138\r\n02:53:50,060 --> 02:53:54,105\r\nI guess I kind of got a yen\r\nfor the seashore myself.\r\n\r\n1139\r\n02:53:59,735 --> 02:54:01,319\r\nYou wanna go swimming?\r\n\r\n1140\r\n02:54:02,196 --> 02:54:06,366\r\nYeah. Yeah, let's go for a swim.\r\n\r\n1141\r\n02:54:23,175 --> 02:54:26,803\r\nRead all about it! Read all about it!\r\n\r\n1142\r\n02:54:28,764 --> 02:54:31,266\r\nRead all about it!\r\n\r\n1143\r\n02:55:45,841 --> 02:55:47,801\r\nHey, Maxie.\r\n\r\n1144\r\n02:55:48,386 --> 02:55:50,762\r\n- Max.\r\n- Huh?\r\n\r\n1145\r\n02:55:50,930 --> 02:55:53,681\r\nHow much money we got put away?\r\n\r\n1146\r\n02:55:53,933 --> 02:55:55,350\r\nWhy?\r\n\r\n1147\r\n02:55:58,187 --> 02:56:00,605\r\nBecause we're unemployed.\r\n\r\n1148\r\n02:56:15,662 --> 02:56:18,163\r\nAbout a million bucks.\r\n\r\n1149\r\n02:56:18,665 --> 02:56:23,377\r\n- Oh, yeah? Where'd you put it?\r\n- In my underwear.\r\n\r\n1150\r\n02:56:25,505 --> 02:56:29,216\r\n- I'd have found it there.\r\n- Hey.\r\n\r\n1151\r\n02:56:29,551 --> 02:56:31,135\r\nHuh?\r\n\r\n1152\r\n02:56:56,411 --> 02:57:00,956\r\nWe gotta reorganize, Max.\r\nAnd I got a couple of good ideas.\r\n\r\n1153\r\n02:57:02,333 --> 02:57:04,042\r\nMe too.\r\n\r\n1154\r\n02:57:04,335 --> 02:57:07,379\r\nIf I had a million bucks,\r\nI'd take it easy.\r\n\r\n1155\r\n02:57:07,547 --> 02:57:09,923\r\nWe'll take it easy when we got 20.\r\n\r\n1156\r\n02:57:11,301 --> 02:57:14,636\r\n- Fifty.\r\n- Where you gonna get that?\r\n\r\n1157\r\n02:57:17,974 --> 02:57:19,641\r\nRight here.\r\n\r\n1158\r\n02:57:28,985 --> 02:57:30,736\r\nWhat's that?\r\n\r\n1159\r\n02:57:34,157 --> 02:57:36,074\r\nIt's a dream.\r\n\r\n1160\r\n02:57:38,495 --> 02:57:41,246\r\nA dream I've been dreaming\r\nall my life.\r\n\r\n1161\r\n02:57:41,414 --> 02:57:45,542\r\nI swear to God, Noodles, you and me\r\ntogether, we can make it come true.\r\n\r\n1162\r\n02:57:49,464 --> 02:57:50,672\r\nWhat is it?\r\n\r\n1163\r\n02:57:55,970 --> 02:57:57,804\r\nThe Federal Reserve Bank.\r\n\r\n1164\r\n02:58:01,518 --> 02:58:04,978\r\nIt's the biggest step\r\nwe can take, Noodles.\r\n\r\n1165\r\n02:58:28,043 --> 02:58:29,877\r\nYou're really crazy.\r\n\r\n1166\r\n02:58:31,088 --> 02:58:35,758\r\nDon't you ever say that to me.\r\nDon't you ever say that to me again!\r\n\r\n1167\r\n03:00:01,511 --> 03:00:06,390\r\nWhat chance is there that\r\na crazy thing like this might succeed, hm?\r\n\r\n1168\r\n03:00:07,601 --> 03:00:09,518\r\nDon't ask me, ask Max.\r\n\r\n1169\r\n03:00:09,936 --> 03:00:15,775\r\nYou know as well as I do that this is\r\nsuicide, pure and simple, for everyone.\r\n\r\n1170\r\n03:00:16,526 --> 03:00:21,946\r\nYeah, well, don't tell me, tell him.\r\nYou got your own methods.\r\n\r\n1171\r\n03:00:22,573 --> 03:00:24,741\r\nYeah, I tried.\r\n\r\n1172\r\n03:00:25,201 --> 03:00:28,286\r\nHe doesn't want to screw anymore.\r\n\r\n1173\r\n03:00:31,248 --> 03:00:34,584\r\nAll he thinks about is this job.\r\n\r\n1174\r\n03:00:37,088 --> 03:00:40,173\r\nTear gas, hostages,\r\nnow he's gonna do this.\r\n\r\n1175\r\n03:00:40,341 --> 03:00:43,760\r\nHe's gonna do it with or without you.\r\n\r\n1176\r\n03:00:49,016 --> 03:00:52,435\r\nNoodles, we've never liked each other.\r\n\r\n1177\r\n03:00:56,732 --> 03:01:02,362\r\nWe put up with each other for Max's sake.\r\nSo why don't we just get together once...\r\n\r\n1178\r\n03:01:02,530 --> 03:01:05,281\r\n...and do something for him?\r\n\r\n1179\r\n03:01:15,000 --> 03:01:16,960\r\nAnd after that...\r\n\r\n1180\r\n03:01:18,003 --> 03:01:21,172\r\n...we can go back to being enemies.\r\n\r\n1181\r\n03:01:29,682 --> 03:01:34,728\r\nYou know,\r\nif you were all in jail first...\r\n\r\n1182\r\n03:01:34,895 --> 03:01:37,981\r\n...there wouldn't be any bank job.\r\n\r\n1183\r\n03:01:49,535 --> 03:01:52,203\r\nI got the idea from your friend Max.\r\n\r\n1184\r\n03:01:54,039 --> 03:01:55,248\r\nWhat do you mean?\r\n\r\n1185\r\n03:01:58,335 --> 03:02:01,671\r\nHe laughs at you. He makes fun of you.\r\n\r\n1186\r\n03:02:03,507 --> 03:02:06,801\r\nHe says Eve has got you by the balls.\r\n\r\n1187\r\n03:02:06,969 --> 03:02:10,889\r\nEvery time you walk past this place,\r\nyou shit in your pants.\r\n\r\n1188\r\n03:02:11,056 --> 03:02:14,851\r\nYou'd do anything for the cops to pick\r\nyou up so you wouldn't have to do this job.\r\n\r\n1189\r\n03:02:15,019 --> 03:02:17,103\r\nIs that true, huh?\r\n\r\n1190\r\n03:02:29,824 --> 03:02:31,408\r\nWell, then do it.\r\n\r\n1191\r\n03:02:31,576 --> 03:02:34,870\r\nDo it. Put him in jail.\r\nPut him in jail. Not long.\r\n\r\n1192\r\n03:02:35,038 --> 03:02:38,916\r\nJust long enough so he can\r\nget the idea out of his mind.\r\n\r\n1193\r\n03:02:40,710 --> 03:02:45,839\r\nIf you can't stand being away\r\nfrom him, put yourself there too.\r\n\r\n1194\r\n03:02:47,425 --> 03:02:50,344\r\nBetter off than being dead.\r\n\r\n1195\r\n03:02:54,766 --> 03:02:57,059\r\nYou know what to do.\r\n\r\n1196\r\n03:03:00,688 --> 03:03:03,524\r\nAnd if you don't, I will.\r\n\r\n1197\r\n03:03:07,362 --> 03:03:09,571\r\nGet out. Take a cab.\r\n\r\n1198\r\n03:03:09,739 --> 03:03:12,616\r\nI'm busy. I got things to do. Get out.\r\n\r\n1199\r\n03:03:18,164 --> 03:03:19,289\r\nNoodles?\r\n\r\n1200\r\n03:03:20,333 --> 03:03:23,252\r\nMake up your mind fast, huh?\r\n\r\n1201\r\n03:04:47,961 --> 03:04:50,046\r\nWhat's the matter?\r\n\r\n1202\r\n03:04:50,547 --> 03:04:53,049\r\nAren't you having a good time?\r\n\r\n1203\r\n03:04:59,848 --> 03:05:02,433\r\nWhy are you going out tonight?\r\n\r\n1204\r\n03:05:02,976 --> 03:05:06,228\r\nWhy bother now that prohibition\r\nis almost over?\r\n\r\n1205\r\n03:05:08,273 --> 03:05:12,193\r\nEverybody's selling. We got friends who\r\nhave a lot of booze they wanna get rid of...\r\n\r\n1206\r\n03:05:12,361 --> 03:05:16,822\r\n...for practically nothing.\r\nSo we figure, why not?\r\n\r\n1207\r\n03:05:22,996 --> 03:05:25,790\r\nI'm gonna be gone for a while.\r\n\r\n1208\r\n03:05:26,083 --> 03:05:29,001\r\nI'll be waiting at the hotel.\r\n\r\n1209\r\n03:05:29,836 --> 03:05:33,965\r\nI like it when you come home\r\nlate and wake me up.\r\n\r\n1210\r\n03:05:39,554 --> 03:05:41,764\r\nI'm not gonna be home tonight.\r\n\r\n1211\r\n03:05:48,772 --> 03:05:51,357\r\nI'm not gonna be home tomorrow either.\r\n\r\n1212\r\n03:05:51,775 --> 03:05:55,736\r\nI thought these things\r\nonly take a couple of hours.\r\n\r\n1213\r\n03:06:02,119 --> 03:06:08,040\r\nLadies and gents, I drink to the demise\r\nof Fat Moe's speakeasy.\r\n\r\n1214\r\n03:06:08,333 --> 03:06:10,793\r\nWho the hell wants to drink\r\nhere legally anyway?\r\n\r\n1215\r\n03:06:13,130 --> 03:06:16,632\r\nOkay. Come on, Moe, set them up.\r\nGo on, get in there.\r\n\r\n1216\r\n03:06:30,022 --> 03:06:31,480\r\n- Here's another one.\r\n- Ha-ha-ha.\r\n\r\n1217\r\n03:06:31,648 --> 03:06:33,899\r\nHere's mud in your eye.\r\n\r\n1218\r\n03:06:40,574 --> 03:06:42,074\r\nBoys.\r\n\r\n1219\r\n03:06:45,453 --> 03:06:47,579\r\nLet's drink to our last shipment.\r\n\r\n1220\r\n03:06:47,747 --> 03:06:50,582\r\nBecause there's more onboard\r\ntonight than just booze.\r\n\r\n1221\r\n03:06:50,750 --> 03:06:56,171\r\nIt's 10 years of our lives. Ten years\r\nthat were really worth living.\r\n\r\n1222\r\n03:06:56,338 --> 03:06:57,714\r\nYeah.\r\n\r\n1223\r\n03:07:05,890 --> 03:07:07,265\r\nAah.\r\n\r\n1224\r\n03:07:16,192 --> 03:07:18,026\r\nNoodles.\r\n\r\n1225\r\n03:07:19,403 --> 03:07:20,987\r\nNoodles.\r\n\r\n1226\r\n03:07:22,698 --> 03:07:25,283\r\n<i>- L'chaim.</i>\r\n<i>- L'chaim.</i>\r\n\r\n1227\r\n03:07:28,287 --> 03:07:30,872\r\nHow long will I have to wait?\r\n\r\n1228\r\n03:07:34,543 --> 03:07:38,046\r\nA year and a half, more or less.\r\n\r\n1229\r\n03:07:39,423 --> 03:07:41,591\r\nSix months off for good behavior.\r\n\r\n1230\r\n03:07:42,051 --> 03:07:44,886\r\n- What are you gonna do?\r\n- Don't ask.\r\n\r\n1231\r\n03:09:19,647 --> 03:09:21,481\r\n<i>Operator.</i>\r\n\r\n1232\r\n03:09:22,817 --> 03:09:23,984\r\nPolice, please.\r\n\r\n1233\r\n03:09:29,991 --> 03:09:32,242\r\nFifth Precinct. Sergeant Halloran.\r\n\r\n1234\r\n03:09:34,996 --> 03:09:36,538\r\n<i>Hello.</i>\r\n\r\n1235\r\n03:09:37,498 --> 03:09:40,584\r\n<i>Who's speaking? Can I help you?</i>\r\n\r\n1236\r\n03:09:40,752 --> 03:09:42,753\r\n<i>- Hello?</i>\r\n- Yeah.\r\n\r\n1237\r\n03:09:45,340 --> 03:09:47,090\r\nI got a good tip for you.\r\n\r\n1238\r\n03:10:13,576 --> 03:10:17,371\r\n- Yeah, who is it?\r\n- Yeah, it's Max. Open the door.\r\n\r\n1239\r\n03:10:23,253 --> 03:10:27,297\r\n- What's the matter with you? You sick?\r\n- No, I'm fine.\r\n\r\n1240\r\n03:10:27,465 --> 03:10:29,132\r\nYou don't look it.\r\n\r\n1241\r\n03:10:31,261 --> 03:10:34,096\r\nMaybe you'd better\r\nstay home tonight, huh?\r\n\r\n1242\r\n03:10:34,597 --> 03:10:37,516\r\n- Why?\r\n- Heh.\r\n\r\n1243\r\n03:10:39,978 --> 03:10:42,896\r\nYou know, I've been\r\nwatching you all night.\r\n\r\n1244\r\n03:10:44,399 --> 03:10:47,234\r\nAnd you've been drinking like a fish.\r\n\r\n1245\r\n03:10:48,111 --> 03:10:50,529\r\nTrying to get your courage up?\r\n\r\n1246\r\n03:10:54,033 --> 03:10:57,327\r\nWe're only bringing in\r\na shipment of booze.\r\n\r\n1247\r\n03:10:58,870 --> 03:11:02,081\r\nIt's got so you're even\r\nscared to do that.\r\n\r\n1248\r\n03:11:03,834 --> 03:11:06,585\r\nMaybe you just better\r\nstay home tonight.\r\n\r\n1249\r\n03:11:07,629 --> 03:11:09,171\r\nWith Eve. Heh-heh-heh.\r\n\r\n1250\r\n03:11:19,516 --> 03:11:23,936\r\nHey, Maxie, everywhere you go,\r\nI go too. Remember that.\r\n\r\n1251\r\n03:11:33,780 --> 03:11:36,240\r\nMaybe Sharkey was right.\r\n\r\n1252\r\n03:11:36,408 --> 03:11:39,201\r\nMaybe I ought to just dump you.\r\n\r\n1253\r\n03:11:48,337 --> 03:11:49,920\r\nYou're really crazy.\r\n\r\n1254\r\n03:11:50,088 --> 03:11:52,006\r\nNever say that!\r\n\r\n1255\r\n03:11:52,466 --> 03:11:55,634\r\nDon't say it!\r\n\r\n1256\r\n03:12:02,434 --> 03:12:06,604\r\nMax made fools of us, Noodles.\r\nHe wanted to die.\r\n\r\n1257\r\n03:12:06,772 --> 03:12:09,815\r\nDid you know his old man\r\ndied in the nut house?\r\n\r\n1258\r\n03:12:09,983 --> 03:12:12,818\r\nMax didn't want to\r\nend up the same way.\r\n\r\n1259\r\n03:12:13,028 --> 03:12:17,156\r\nSo he put the idea\r\nin our heads to tip off the cops.\r\n\r\n1260\r\n03:12:17,324 --> 03:12:22,203\r\nAnd when they stopped the truck,\r\nMax started shooting first...\r\n\r\n1261\r\n03:12:22,371 --> 03:12:25,664\r\n...just to get himself killed.\r\n\r\n1262\r\n03:12:42,849 --> 03:12:45,184\r\nUh, what is this?\r\n\r\n1263\r\n03:12:48,230 --> 03:12:49,397\r\nOpening night.\r\n\r\n1264\r\n03:12:51,066 --> 03:12:53,776\r\nFifteen years ago.\r\n\r\n1265\r\n03:12:53,944 --> 03:12:56,195\r\nUh, who's this?\r\n\r\n1266\r\n03:12:57,906 --> 03:13:00,908\r\nPatron saint of the place.\r\n\r\n1267\r\n03:13:02,285 --> 03:13:04,537\r\nAnd some actress.\r\n\r\n1268\r\n03:13:05,330 --> 03:13:06,704\r\nDo you know her?\r\n\r\n1269\r\n03:13:08,707 --> 03:13:10,250\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n1270\r\n03:14:03,387 --> 03:14:05,680\r\nHello, Deborah.\r\n\r\n1271\r\n03:14:13,272 --> 03:14:15,940\r\nAren't you gonna say anything?\r\n\r\n1272\r\n03:14:22,698 --> 03:14:26,034\r\nWhat is someone\r\nsupposed to say after...\r\n\r\n1273\r\n03:14:26,660 --> 03:14:29,704\r\n...more than 30 years.\r\n\r\n1274\r\n03:14:34,835 --> 03:14:40,798\r\nWell, how about, \"How you doing?\r\nYou're looking good.\"\r\n\r\n1275\r\n03:14:42,801 --> 03:14:45,970\r\nOr, \"I was hoping I'd never\r\nsee you again.\"\r\n\r\n1276\r\n03:14:48,390 --> 03:14:51,392\r\nI never thought I would.\r\n\r\n1277\r\n03:14:52,478 --> 03:14:54,812\r\nThere's a difference.\r\n\r\n1278\r\n03:14:54,980 --> 03:14:58,650\r\nYeah. At least you recognize me,\r\nthat's something.\r\n\r\n1279\r\n03:14:58,817 --> 03:15:01,819\r\nActresses have good memories.\r\n\r\n1280\r\n03:15:11,580 --> 03:15:13,914\r\nYou want a drink?\r\n\r\n1281\r\n03:15:18,127 --> 03:15:20,546\r\nI'm having one.\r\n\r\n1282\r\n03:15:30,974 --> 03:15:32,015\r\nMargo?\r\n\r\n1283\r\n03:15:33,768 --> 03:15:36,478\r\n- Yes, miss?\r\n- That's all for now. You can go.\r\n\r\n1284\r\n03:15:36,646 --> 03:15:38,855\r\nAll right, miss.\r\n\r\n1285\r\n03:15:43,736 --> 03:15:46,613\r\nShe called you \"miss.\"\r\n\r\n1286\r\n03:15:46,948 --> 03:15:49,366\r\nYou never got married?\r\n\r\n1287\r\n03:15:50,201 --> 03:15:51,827\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n1288\r\n03:15:55,415 --> 03:15:56,957\r\nYou live alone?\r\n\r\n1289\r\n03:16:05,091 --> 03:16:06,592\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n1290\r\n03:16:13,433 --> 03:16:15,767\r\nWhere were you?\r\n\r\n1291\r\n03:16:18,688 --> 03:16:21,106\r\nI was out of town.\r\n\r\n1292\r\n03:16:23,943 --> 03:16:26,737\r\nHave you been back long?\r\n\r\n1293\r\n03:16:27,697 --> 03:16:30,115\r\nA couple of days.\r\n\r\n1294\r\n03:16:30,283 --> 03:16:32,534\r\nAre you staying?\r\n\r\n1295\r\n03:16:44,172 --> 03:16:45,589\r\nThat depends.\r\n\r\n1296\r\n03:16:48,509 --> 03:16:50,594\r\nWhy do you want to see me?\r\n\r\n1297\r\n03:16:52,430 --> 03:16:54,765\r\nTwo reasons.\r\n\r\n1298\r\n03:16:54,932 --> 03:16:58,185\r\nFirst, I wanted to see\r\nif you did the right thing...\r\n\r\n1299\r\n03:16:58,353 --> 03:17:00,437\r\n...turning me down\r\nto become an actress.\r\n\r\n1300\r\n03:17:04,609 --> 03:17:06,193\r\nWell?\r\n\r\n1301\r\n03:17:08,988 --> 03:17:11,239\r\nYou did. You're terrific.\r\n\r\n1302\r\n03:17:27,005 --> 03:17:30,091\r\n\"Age cannot wither her.\"\r\n\r\n1303\r\n03:17:30,300 --> 03:17:33,302\r\nIt's like the play\r\nwas written for you.\r\n\r\n1304\r\n03:17:36,765 --> 03:17:39,225\r\nWhat was the other reason?\r\n\r\n1305\r\n03:17:39,434 --> 03:17:41,727\r\nThe other reason...\r\n\r\n1306\r\n03:17:44,940 --> 03:17:49,276\r\n...is to decide whether I should go\r\nto a party tomorrow night.\r\n\r\n1307\r\n03:17:55,992 --> 03:17:57,535\r\nA party?\r\n\r\n1308\r\n03:18:00,831 --> 03:18:03,332\r\nYeah, on Long Island.\r\n\r\n1309\r\n03:18:04,835 --> 03:18:08,003\r\nA Secretary Bailey.\r\n\r\n1310\r\n03:18:11,842 --> 03:18:14,009\r\nDo you know Secretary Bailey?\r\n\r\n1311\r\n03:18:15,846 --> 03:18:17,054\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n1312\r\n03:18:19,349 --> 03:18:21,809\r\nBut I was invited anyway.\r\n\r\n1313\r\n03:18:30,152 --> 03:18:33,195\r\nBut if you don't know each other,\r\nwhy were you invited?\r\n\r\n1314\r\n03:18:33,363 --> 03:18:34,905\r\nI don't know.\r\n\r\n1315\r\n03:18:36,533 --> 03:18:38,576\r\nI thought you might know why.\r\n\r\n1316\r\n03:18:39,494 --> 03:18:40,995\r\nMe?\r\n\r\n1317\r\n03:18:41,204 --> 03:18:42,830\r\nWhy me?\r\n\r\n1318\r\n03:18:48,253 --> 03:18:50,171\r\nBecause you know him.\r\n\r\n1319\r\n03:18:51,631 --> 03:18:53,090\r\n- Who is it?\r\n- David.\r\n\r\n1320\r\n03:18:53,258 --> 03:18:55,926\r\n- No, David.\r\n- Can I come in?\r\n\r\n1321\r\n03:18:56,136 --> 03:18:58,971\r\nNo, no, no. Just wait outside,\r\nDavid, I'll call you.\r\n\r\n1322\r\n03:18:59,181 --> 03:19:01,557\r\nOkay, I'll be right here.\r\n\r\n1323\r\n03:19:04,352 --> 03:19:08,147\r\n- What does Secretary Bailey want from me?\r\n- You came here to ask me that?\r\n\r\n1324\r\n03:19:08,356 --> 03:19:11,317\r\n- Why did he send me an invitation?\r\n- I don't know. I don't know.\r\n\r\n1325\r\n03:19:11,526 --> 03:19:15,863\r\nWhy should...? Why should I know about\r\nyour invitations? I don't know anything. I...\r\n\r\n1326\r\n03:19:16,072 --> 03:19:20,075\r\nWhat do you want from me? Why did\r\nyou come here? I know nothing, nothing.\r\n\r\n1327\r\n03:19:20,243 --> 03:19:22,912\r\nNow you're a lousy actress.\r\n\r\n1328\r\n03:19:25,749 --> 03:19:28,583\r\nWho is Secretary Bailey?\r\n\r\n1329\r\n03:19:37,343 --> 03:19:40,970\r\nSecretary Bailey is a rich businessman.\r\n\r\n1330\r\n03:19:46,685 --> 03:19:51,272\r\nHe came to the United States as a starving\r\nimmigrant and made a lot of money...\r\n\r\n1331\r\n03:19:51,482 --> 03:19:55,443\r\n...in San Francisco and Los Angeles,\r\nwhere he's lived for 30 years.\r\n\r\n1332\r\n03:19:55,611 --> 03:19:59,614\r\nI know all that. It's all in the papers.\r\nWhat else is there?\r\n\r\n1333\r\n03:20:06,121 --> 03:20:09,123\r\nHe married a very wealthy woman.\r\n\r\n1334\r\n03:20:10,417 --> 03:20:12,752\r\nThey had a child.\r\n\r\n1335\r\n03:20:13,128 --> 03:20:16,172\r\nShe died when the child was born.\r\n\r\n1336\r\n03:20:16,757 --> 03:20:21,302\r\nA few years ago, he went into politics.\r\nMoved here.\r\n\r\n1337\r\n03:20:21,470 --> 03:20:26,099\r\nThat's all past history. I'm not talking\r\nabout that. I'm talking about now.\r\n\r\n1338\r\n03:20:26,684 --> 03:20:29,310\r\nRight now he's in trouble.\r\n\r\n1339\r\n03:20:30,980 --> 03:20:34,357\r\nWhy can't you just tell me you've\r\nbeen living with him all these years...\r\n\r\n1340\r\n03:20:34,525 --> 03:20:36,484\r\n...and that you're his lover?\r\n\r\n1341\r\n03:20:45,327 --> 03:20:48,329\r\nAge can wither me, Noodles.\r\n\r\n1342\r\n03:20:52,042 --> 03:20:54,669\r\nWe're both getting old.\r\n\r\n1343\r\n03:21:00,009 --> 03:21:03,303\r\nAll that we have left now\r\nare our memories.\r\n\r\n1344\r\n03:21:06,223 --> 03:21:12,186\r\nIf you go to that party on Saturday\r\nnight, you won't have those anymore.\r\n\r\n1345\r\n03:21:13,480 --> 03:21:16,024\r\nTear up that invitation.\r\n\r\n1346\r\n03:21:18,319 --> 03:21:21,029\r\nThere's an exit back this way.\r\n\r\n1347\r\n03:21:21,947 --> 03:21:24,866\r\nNoodles, go through it.\r\n\r\n1348\r\n03:21:27,536 --> 03:21:29,412\r\nKeep walking.\r\n\r\n1349\r\n03:21:29,622 --> 03:21:31,873\r\nDon't turn around.\r\n\r\n1350\r\n03:21:33,000 --> 03:21:35,251\r\nPlease, Noodles.\r\n\r\n1351\r\n03:21:35,419 --> 03:21:38,545\r\nI'm begging you. Please.\r\n\r\n1352\r\n03:21:45,011 --> 03:21:48,555\r\nAre you afraid that I'll turn\r\ninto a pillar of salt?\r\n\r\n1353\r\n03:21:52,018 --> 03:21:55,812\r\nIf you go out that door, yes.\r\n\r\n1354\r\n03:22:54,038 --> 03:22:56,999\r\nThis is Secretary Bailey's son.\r\n\r\n1355\r\n03:22:57,208 --> 03:23:00,711\r\nHis name's David, just like yours.\r\n\r\n1356\r\n03:25:52,256 --> 03:25:54,090\r\nPlease go in.\r\n\r\n1357\r\n03:26:08,480 --> 03:26:10,648\r\nWhat are you waiting for?\r\n\r\n1358\r\n03:26:14,486 --> 03:26:16,946\r\nI don't understand, Mr. Bailey.\r\n\r\n1359\r\n03:26:43,641 --> 03:26:45,725\r\nSit down, Noodles.\r\n\r\n1360\r\n03:26:49,980 --> 03:26:51,773\r\nMake yourself comfortable.\r\n\r\n1361\r\n03:27:10,167 --> 03:27:12,877\r\nI'm glad you accepted my invitation.\r\n\r\n1362\r\n03:27:13,045 --> 03:27:15,046\r\nWell, I was curious.\r\n\r\n1363\r\n03:27:18,008 --> 03:27:21,135\r\nSo many important people in one place.\r\n\r\n1364\r\n03:27:21,345 --> 03:27:25,223\r\nYes. Well, the rats usually\r\ndesert a sinking ship.\r\n\r\n1365\r\n03:27:25,683 --> 03:27:29,602\r\nBut in my case, they appear to be\r\nflocking onboard.\r\n\r\n1366\r\n03:27:41,240 --> 03:27:45,076\r\nYeah, well, I read about\r\nyour troubles in the newspapers.\r\n\r\n1367\r\n03:27:46,453 --> 03:27:51,124\r\nBut a man in your position, with all\r\nyour power and all your privileges...\r\n\r\n1368\r\n03:27:51,333 --> 03:27:55,586\r\n...has to assume a certain amount\r\nof responsibility...\r\n\r\n1369\r\n03:27:56,255 --> 03:27:58,715\r\n...a certain amount of risk.\r\n\r\n1370\r\n03:28:06,180 --> 03:28:08,932\r\nWhy'd you ask me\r\nto come here, Mr. Bailey?\r\n\r\n1371\r\n03:28:12,270 --> 03:28:16,773\r\nThat invitation doesn't mean\r\na goddamn thing, and you know it.\r\n\r\n1372\r\n03:28:17,150 --> 03:28:20,694\r\nAll that counts is what\r\nwas in that suitcase.\r\n\r\n1373\r\n03:28:22,363 --> 03:28:25,073\r\nThe money and the contract.\r\n\r\n1374\r\n03:28:27,910 --> 03:28:31,121\r\nIt didn't say who the contract\r\nwas on, though.\r\n\r\n1375\r\n03:28:32,457 --> 03:28:34,875\r\nHaven't you figured that out yet?\r\n\r\n1376\r\n03:28:36,586 --> 03:28:38,128\r\nYou, Mr. Bailey?\r\n\r\n1377\r\n03:28:51,934 --> 03:28:55,645\r\nI haven't had a gun in my hand\r\nfor many, many years.\r\n\r\n1378\r\n03:28:57,273 --> 03:29:02,819\r\nMy eyes aren't too good,\r\neven with my glasses. My hands shake.\r\n\r\n1379\r\n03:29:05,698 --> 03:29:09,701\r\n- And I wouldn't wanna miss, Mr. Bailey.\r\n- Cut the bullshit, Noodles.\r\n\r\n1380\r\n03:29:11,245 --> 03:29:13,997\r\nI'm already a dead man.\r\n\r\n1381\r\n03:29:14,916 --> 03:29:19,336\r\nAt least give me the chance\r\nto settle the debt that I owe to you.\r\n\r\n1382\r\n03:29:20,004 --> 03:29:23,507\r\nI'll never make it before\r\nthe investigating committee.\r\n\r\n1383\r\n03:29:23,674 --> 03:29:27,636\r\nThey're scared to death\r\nI'll implicate the whole bunch of them.\r\n\r\n1384\r\n03:29:28,012 --> 03:29:30,222\r\nThey gotta get rid of me.\r\n\r\n1385\r\n03:29:32,892 --> 03:29:35,852\r\nToday is as good a day as any.\r\n\r\n1386\r\n03:29:38,022 --> 03:29:40,399\r\nYou do it, Noodles.\r\n\r\n1387\r\n03:29:41,359 --> 03:29:44,736\r\nYou're the only person\r\nI can accept it from.\r\n\r\n1388\r\n03:29:51,619 --> 03:29:54,204\r\nYou see, I found out where you were.\r\n\r\n1389\r\n03:29:54,372 --> 03:29:57,457\r\nI brought you back here for this.\r\n\r\n1390\r\n03:29:58,793 --> 03:30:02,003\r\nTo even the score between you and me.\r\n\r\n1391\r\n03:30:04,382 --> 03:30:06,841\r\nYou can get out through there.\r\n\r\n1392\r\n03:30:14,099 --> 03:30:18,644\r\nIt leads right down to the street.\r\nNobody will see you.\r\n\r\n1393\r\n03:30:25,402 --> 03:30:29,780\r\nI don't know what you're talking about,\r\nMr. Bailey. You don't owe me a thing.\r\n\r\n1394\r\n03:30:37,747 --> 03:30:43,878\r\nYour eyes were too full of tears to see\r\nit wasn't me burned up on that street.\r\n\r\n1395\r\n03:30:44,713 --> 03:30:46,589\r\nIt was somebody else.\r\n\r\n1396\r\n03:30:48,175 --> 03:30:53,095\r\nYou were too shocked to realize\r\nthat the cops were in on it too.\r\n\r\n1397\r\n03:30:53,722 --> 03:30:56,932\r\nThat was a syndicate\r\noperation, Noodles.\r\n\r\n1398\r\n03:31:07,235 --> 03:31:09,236\r\nYou're crazy.\r\n\r\n1399\r\n03:31:11,698 --> 03:31:15,951\r\nYou said that to me once before,\r\na long time ago.\r\n\r\n1400\r\n03:31:16,244 --> 03:31:19,705\r\nBut my mind was never as clear\r\nas it was at that moment.\r\n\r\n1401\r\n03:31:20,457 --> 03:31:23,959\r\nI took away your whole life from you.\r\n\r\n1402\r\n03:31:24,169 --> 03:31:27,004\r\nI've been living in your place.\r\n\r\n1403\r\n03:31:28,215 --> 03:31:30,841\r\nI took everything.\r\n\r\n1404\r\n03:31:32,260 --> 03:31:34,428\r\nI took your money.\r\n\r\n1405\r\n03:31:35,055 --> 03:31:37,264\r\nI took your girl.\r\n\r\n1406\r\n03:31:37,974 --> 03:31:42,770\r\nAll I left for you was 35 years of grief\r\nover having killed me.\r\n\r\n1407\r\n03:31:44,356 --> 03:31:45,397\r\nNow, why don't you shoot?\r\n\r\n1408\r\n03:33:21,035 --> 03:33:23,953\r\nIt's true,\r\nI have killed people, Mr. Bailey.\r\n\r\n1409\r\n03:33:24,163 --> 03:33:28,916\r\nSometimes to defend myself,\r\nsometimes for money.\r\n\r\n1410\r\n03:33:29,209 --> 03:33:31,753\r\nAnd many people used to come to us.\r\n\r\n1411\r\n03:33:31,962 --> 03:33:34,881\r\nBusiness partners, rivals...\r\n\r\n1412\r\n03:33:35,257 --> 03:33:37,425\r\n...lovers.\r\n\r\n1413\r\n03:33:37,801 --> 03:33:41,929\r\nSome of the jobs we took\r\nand some we didn't.\r\n\r\n1414\r\n03:33:55,319 --> 03:33:58,279\r\nYours is one we would never touch,\r\nMr. Bailey.\r\n\r\n1415\r\n03:33:59,156 --> 03:34:02,116\r\nIs this your way of getting revenge?\r\n\r\n1416\r\n03:34:06,080 --> 03:34:07,664\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n1417\r\n03:34:11,001 --> 03:34:14,128\r\nIt's just the way I see things.\r\n\r\n1418\r\n03:35:16,816 --> 03:35:19,609\r\nIt's 10:25...\r\n\r\n1419\r\n03:35:20,903 --> 03:35:24,072\r\n...and I've got nothing left to lose.\r\n\r\n1420\r\n03:35:26,200 --> 03:35:30,162\r\nWhen you've been betrayed by a friend,\r\nyou hit back.\r\n\r\n1421\r\n03:35:35,209 --> 03:35:37,043\r\nDo it.\r\n\r\n1422\r\n03:35:59,192 --> 03:36:01,818\r\nYou see, Mr. Secretary...\r\n\r\n1423\r\n03:36:03,821 --> 03:36:05,906\r\n...I have a story also.\r\n\r\n1424\r\n03:36:06,866 --> 03:36:09,409\r\nA little simpler than yours.\r\n\r\n1425\r\n03:36:10,536 --> 03:36:15,248\r\nMany years ago I had a friend,\r\na dear friend.\r\n\r\n1426\r\n03:36:16,876 --> 03:36:20,128\r\nI turned him in to save his life...\r\n\r\n1427\r\n03:36:20,338 --> 03:36:22,631\r\n...but he was killed.\r\n\r\n1428\r\n03:36:23,925 --> 03:36:26,760\r\nBut he wanted it that way.\r\n\r\n1429\r\n03:36:27,804 --> 03:36:30,012\r\nIt was a great friendship.\r\n\r\n1430\r\n03:36:33,099 --> 03:36:37,144\r\nIt went bad for him\r\nand it went bad for me too.\r\n\r\n1431\r\n03:36:42,108 --> 03:36:44,276\r\nGood night, Mr. Bailey.\r\n\r\n1432\r\n03:36:53,453 --> 03:36:57,164\r\nI hope the investigation\r\nturns out to be nothing.\r\n\r\n1433\r\n03:36:59,084 --> 03:37:03,128\r\nIt'd be a shame to see\r\na lifetime of work go to waste.\r\n\r\n1434\r\n03:40:28,630 --> 03:40:33,300\r\n<i>~ God bless America ~</i>\r\n\r\n1435\r\n03:40:33,468 --> 03:40:37,721\r\n<i>~ Land that I love ~</i>\r\n\r\n1436\r\n03:40:37,889 --> 03:40:42,559\r\n<i>~ Stand beside her</i>\r\n<i>And guide her ~</i>\r\n\r\n1437\r\n03:40:42,852 --> 03:40:46,062\r\n<i>~ Through the night</i>\r\n<i>With a light from above ~</i>\r\n\r\n1438\r\n03:40:47,815 --> 03:40:50,372\r\n<i>~ From the mountains ~</i>\r\n\r\n1439\r\n03:40:50,499 --> 03:40:52,625\r\n<i>~ To the prairies ~</i>\r\n\r\n1440\r\n03:40:52,736 --> 03:40:57,115\r\n<i>~ To the oceans white with foam ~</i>\r\n\r\n1441\r\n03:40:58,158 --> 03:41:02,328\r\n<i>~ God bless America ~</i>\r\n\r\n1442\r\n03:41:02,496 --> 03:41:06,666\r\n<i>~ My home sweet home ~</i>\r\n\r\n1443\r\n03:41:08,085 --> 03:41:12,839\r\n<i>~ God bless America ~</i>\r\n\r\n1444\r\n03:41:13,007 --> 03:41:17,051\r\n<i>~ Land that I love ~</i>\r\n\r\n1445\r\n03:41:17,219 --> 03:41:22,098\r\n<i>~ Stand beside her</i>\r\n<i>And guide her... ~</i>\r\n\r\n","markerStore":{"nextMarkerId":133,"markersById":{"0":{"range":{"start":{"row":0,"column":0},"end":{"row":0,"column":0}},"properties":{"type":"selection","editorId":80,"goalScreenRange":null},"reversed":false,"tailed":false,"valid":true,"invalidate":"never","maintainHistory":true}},"version":2},"history":{"version":3,"nextCheckpointId":1,"undoStack":[],"redoStack":[]},"encoding":"utf8","filePath":"/Users/joegesualdo/.Trash/Once.Upon.A.Time.In.America.1