2:45,263\r\nZucker, Helena.\r\n\r\n24\r\n00:02:45,331 --> 00:02:48,129\r\nZucker, Helena.\r\n\r\n25\r\n00:02:48,201 --> 00:02:51,136\r\nHirsch, Salomon?\nMandel, Maria. Hirsch,\nSalomon.\r\n\r\n26\r\n00:02:51,204 --> 00:02:54,731\r\n- Hauptman, Chaim!\n- Weisman! Weisman, Marcus!\r\n\r\n27\r\n00:02:54,807 --> 00:02:57,742\r\n- Feber, Ludwig!\n- Feber, Lufwig.\r\n\r\n28\r\n00:02:57,810 --> 00:03:00,904\r\nElsa Bauman.\r\n\r\n29\r\n00:03:00,980 --> 00:03:03,414\r\n- Josef Klein.\n- Klein.\r\n\r\n30\r\n00:03:03,483 --> 00:03:07,442\r\n- Davidowich, Ignacy.\n- Paula Biffer.\n- Nadel, Rachela.\r\n\r\n31\r\n00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:10,148\r\nSteiner, Gertruda.\nSteiner, Hilda.\r\n\r\n32\r\n00:03:23,336 --> 00:03:27,602\r\n[\"Gloomy Sunday\"]\r\n\r\n33\r\n00:04:24,631 --> 00:04:28,067\r\n[Indistinct Chatter]\r\n\r\n34\r\n00:04:30,803 --> 00:04:33,567\r\n[Whispering]\r\n\r\n35\r\n00:04:40,313 --> 00:04:45,250\r\n[Orchestra Playing]\r\n\r\n36\r\n00:05:09,309 --> 00:05:13,405\r\n[Maitre D'] Jerzy,\nyou know who that man is?\nI fon't know.\r\n\r\n37\r\n00:05:13,479 --> 00:05:16,915\r\n[Woman Laughing]\r\n\r\n38\r\n00:05:16,983 --> 00:05:22,182\r\n[Orchestra Continues]\r\n\r\n39\r\n00:05:30,697 --> 00:05:33,791\r\nLet's get together,\nplease.\r\n\r\n40\r\n00:05:33,866 --> 00:05:36,699\r\nSmile. Good.\r\n\r\n41\r\n00:06:06,632 --> 00:06:09,567\r\nYes, sir.\r\n\r\n42\r\n00:06:09,635 --> 00:06:13,230\r\nBring them over\na round of drinks.\r\n\r\n43\r\n00:06:13,306 --> 00:06:18,744\r\nVery good, sir.\nAnd who shall I say\nth-they are from?\r\n\r\n44\r\n00:06:18,811 --> 00:06:21,871\r\nYou can say\nthey are from me.\r\n\r\n45\r\n00:06:42,001 --> 00:06:45,903\r\nFrom the gentleman.\nWhere?\r\n\r\n46\r\n00:06:51,010 --> 00:06:54,104\r\nDo you know him?\r\n\r\n47\r\n00:06:54,180 --> 00:06:56,614\r\nFind out who he is.\r\n\r\n48\r\n00:06:56,682 --> 00:06:58,582\r\nYes, sir.\r\n\r\n49\r\n00:07:01,421 --> 00:07:03,889\r\nAgnieszka, I would\ngive anything...\r\n\r\n50\r\n00:07:03,956 --> 00:07:06,015\r\nto hear you\nsing tonight.\n[Sighs]\r\n\r\n51\r\n00:07:06,092 --> 00:07:08,458\r\nBut I know you won't.\n[Laughs]\r\n\r\n52\r\n00:07:09,929 --> 00:07:12,796\r\nYou embarrass me.\r\n\r\n53\r\n00:07:21,274 --> 00:07:23,367\r\nWhat's he doing?\r\n\r\n54\r\n00:07:25,778 --> 00:07:27,712\r\nStay here.\r\n\r\n55\r\n00:07:31,284 --> 00:07:33,218\r\nHow are you doing?\r\n\r\n56\r\n00:07:33,286 --> 00:07:37,552\r\nYou'd leave a woman\nalone at the table\nin a place like this?\r\n\r\n57\r\n00:07:37,623 --> 00:07:40,524\r\nSweetheart,\nyou're the picture\nof loneliness.\r\n\r\n58\r\n00:07:40,593 --> 00:07:42,561\r\nOh.\r\n\r\n59\r\n00:07:42,628 --> 00:07:46,064\r\nMmm, what a lovely\nfragrance. You are\nbreaking my heart.\r\n\r\n60\r\n00:07:46,132 --> 00:07:48,726\r\nAn extra chair, please.\nVodka for my friend.\r\n\r\n61\r\n00:07:48,801 --> 00:07:51,361\r\nAnd for the lady?\nPernod.\r\n\r\n62\r\n00:07:51,404 --> 00:07:55,397\r\nIm Grunewald, im Grunewald\nist Holzauktion\r\n\r\n63\r\n00:07:55,475 --> 00:07:58,205\r\n[Men Laughing,\nWhistling]\nIst Holzauktion\r\n\r\n64\r\n00:07:58,277 --> 00:08:01,735\r\nIm Grunewald, im Grunewald\nist Holzauktion\r\n\r\n65\r\n00:08:01,814 --> 00:08:04,681\r\nCome to the table, girls.!\nDrink with us.!\nIst Holzauktion\r\n\r\n66\r\n00:08:04,750 --> 00:08:07,719\r\nLinks um die Ecke 'rum,\nrechts um die Ecke 'rum\r\n\r\n67\r\n00:08:07,787 --> 00:08:10,688\r\nUeberall ist heute\nHolzauktion\r\n\r\n68\r\n00:08:10,756 --> 00:08:13,384\r\nCome to us.!\nMarry us.!\r\n\r\n69\r\n00:08:15,027 --> 00:08:17,222\r\n[Whispering]\r\n\r\n70\r\n00:08:17,296 --> 00:08:20,390\r\nDer ganze Klafter\nSuessholz kostet 'nen Taler\r\n\r\n71\r\n00:08:20,433 --> 00:08:23,698\r\n'Nen Taler, 'nen Taler\r\n\r\n72\r\n00:08:23,769 --> 00:08:26,761\r\nDer ganze Klafter Suessholz\nkostet 'nen Taler\r\n\r\n73\r\n00:08:26,839 --> 00:08:28,431\r\n'Nen Taler...\r\n\r\n74\r\n00:08:30,977 --> 00:08:34,469\r\nThank you.\nI'll tell you what\nI mean by cooperative.\r\n\r\n75\r\n00:08:34,547 --> 00:08:37,914\r\nTwo days after the law\nis passed that allJews\nhave to wear the star,\r\n\r\n76\r\n00:08:37,984 --> 00:08:40,145\r\ntheJewish tailors\nare turning them out\nby the gross...\r\n\r\n77\r\n00:08:40,219 --> 00:08:42,653\r\nin a variety of fabrics\nat three zloty each.\r\n\r\n78\r\n00:08:42,722 --> 00:08:44,656\r\nTell me about\nyour cellar wines.\r\n\r\n79\r\n00:08:44,724 --> 00:08:48,251\r\nI have an excellent\nGerman Riesling. 1937.\nMmm, French.\r\n\r\n80\r\n00:08:48,327 --> 00:08:51,057\r\nA Bordeaux.\nChateau Latour, '28, '29?\nNo, I'm sorry.\r\n\r\n81\r\n00:08:51,130 --> 00:08:53,598\r\nIt's as if they have no idea\nwhat kind of law it is.\r\n\r\n82\r\n00:08:53,666 --> 00:08:56,658\r\nAs if it's the emblem\nof a riding club.\r\n\r\n83\r\n00:08:56,736 --> 00:08:58,829\r\nA Margaux, '29?\nNo, no,\nwe don't have that.\r\n\r\n84\r\n00:08:58,905 --> 00:09:01,237\r\nBurgundy then?\nA Romanee-Conti, '37?\nYes.\r\n\r\n85\r\n00:09:01,307 --> 00:09:04,242\r\nIt's human nature.\n\"We'll do this to avoid that.\"\r\n\r\n86\r\n00:09:04,310 --> 00:09:06,505\r\nThat's what they have done\nsince thousands of years.\r\n\r\n87\r\n00:09:06,579 --> 00:09:08,843\r\nIt's what they do.\nThey weather the storm.\r\n\r\n88\r\n00:09:08,915 --> 00:09:12,942\r\nBut this storm is different.\nThis is not the Romans.\nThis storm is the SS.\r\n\r\n89\r\n00:09:13,019 --> 00:09:16,819\r\nWem Gott will\nrechte Gunst erweisen\r\n\r\n90\r\n00:09:16,889 --> 00:09:20,791\r\nDen schickt er\nin fie weite Welt\r\n\r\n91\r\n00:09:20,860 --> 00:09:24,455\r\nWem Gott will rechte\nGunst erweisen\r\n\r\n92\r\n00:09:24,530 --> 00:09:28,296\r\nDen schickt er in fie\nweite Welt\r\n\r\n93\r\n00:09:28,367 --> 00:09:31,825\r\nFaleri, Falera\r\n\r\n94\r\n00:09:31,904 --> 00:09:35,704\r\nFaleri\nFalera-ha ha ha\r\n\r\n95\r\n00:09:35,775 --> 00:09:39,370\r\nFaleri, Falera\r\n\r\n96\r\n00:09:39,445 --> 00:09:43,882\r\nDen schickt er\nin fie weite Welt\r\n\r\n97\r\n00:09:43,950 --> 00:09:46,043\r\nMartin?\r\n\r\n98\r\n00:09:46,118 --> 00:09:48,211\r\nYes, sir.\r\n\r\n99\r\n00:09:48,287 --> 00:09:50,221\r\nWho is that man?\r\n\r\n100\r\n00:09:50,289 --> 00:09:54,555\r\nThat...\nThat's Oskar Schindler!\r\n\r\n101\r\n00:09:54,627 --> 00:09:57,994\r\nFaleri\nFalera-ha ha ha\r\n\r\n102\r\n00:09:58,064 --> 00:10:01,659\r\nDen schickt er\nin fie weite Welt\r\n\r\n103\r\n00:10:01,734 --> 00:10:04,498\r\nFaleri, Falera\r\n\r\n104\r\n00:10:04,570 --> 00:10:07,733\r\nDen schickt er\nin fie weite Welt\r\n\r\n105\r\n00:10:07,807 --> 00:10:10,901\r\n[All]\nTo Krakow!\r\n\r\n106\r\n00:10:12,545 --> 00:10:16,481\r\n[Singing In German]\r\n\r\n107\r\n00:10:26,959 --> 00:10:29,587\r\n[Soldiers Laughing]\r\n\r\n108\r\n00:10:43,142 --> 00:10:46,168\r\n[Singing Continues]\r\n\r\n109\r\n00:10:48,180 --> 00:10:50,114\r\n[Loufspeaker]\nAn alleJuden!\r\n\r\n110\r\n00:10:50,182 --> 00:10:54,050\r\nAb sofort ist es allen Juden\nuntersagt...\r\n\r\n111\r\n00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:58,250\r\nFleisch aufkoscher Art\nzuzubereiten.\r\n\r\n112\r\n00:10:58,324 --> 00:11:01,623\r\nMelfung an alleJufen.\nAb sofort...\r\n\r\n113\r\n00:11:21,213 --> 00:11:23,272\r\nRabbi...\nPrivate property\ncannot be confiscated.\r\n\r\n114\r\n00:11:23,349 --> 00:11:25,283\r\nHow long are the schools\ngoing to be closed?\nI do not know.\r\n\r\n115\r\n00:11:25,351 --> 00:11:28,616\r\nArticle 47: Pillage\nis formally prohibited.\nYou don't know anything!\r\n\r\n116\r\n00:11:28,688 --> 00:11:30,622\r\nI am familiar with\nthe Hague Convention.\nReligious...\r\n\r\n117\r\n00:11:30,690 --> 00:11:34,956\r\nThey come into our house\nand tell us we don't\nlive there anymore.\r\n\r\n118\r\n00:11:35,027 --> 00:11:37,928\r\nIt now belongs\nto a certain SS officer.\r\n\r\n119\r\n00:11:37,997 --> 00:11:40,124\r\nPlease. I only know\nwhat they tell me.\r\n\r\n120\r\n00:11:40,199 --> 00:11:43,498\r\nAnd what they tell me\nchanges from day to day.\r\n\r\n121\r\n00:11:43,569 --> 00:11:46,629\r\nAren't you supposed\nto be able to help?\r\n\r\n122\r\n00:11:46,706 --> 00:11:49,800\r\nI mean, what if I just\ntook this thing off?\r\n\r\n123\r\n00:11:49,875 --> 00:11:52,639\r\nWhat are they going\nto do about it?\nThey will shoot you.\r\n\r\n124\r\n00:11:52,712 --> 00:11:56,808\r\nWhy don't you stop\nthis silly talk?\nItzhak Stern!\r\n\r\n125\r\n00:11:56,882 --> 00:12:00,147\r\nI'm looking\nfor Itzhak Stern.\r\n\r\n126\r\n00:12:01,987 --> 00:12:04,922\r\n[Schinfler]\nAre you Itzhak Stern\nor not?\r\n\r\n127\r\n00:12:04,990 --> 00:12:08,084\r\nI am.\nWhere can we talk?\r\n\r\n128\r\n00:12:17,670 --> 00:12:21,606\r\nThere's a company\nyou did the books for\non Lipowa Street.\r\n\r\n129\r\n00:12:21,674 --> 00:12:24,108\r\nMade what?\nPots and pans?\r\n\r\n130\r\n00:12:24,176 --> 00:12:27,270\r\nBy law, I have to tell you,\nsir, I'm a Jew.\r\n\r\n131\r\n00:12:27,346 --> 00:12:31,248\r\nWell, I'm a German.\nSo there we are.\r\n\r\n132\r\n00:12:34,019 --> 00:12:37,785\r\nA good company,\nyou think?\nModestly successful.\r\n\r\n133\r\n00:12:37,857 --> 00:12:40,451\r\nI know nothing\nabout enamelware.\nDo you?\r\n\r\n134\r\n00:12:40,526 --> 00:12:42,960\r\nI was just\nthe accountant.\r\n\r\n135\r\n00:12:43,028 --> 00:12:45,462\r\nSimple engineering though,\nwouldn't you think?\r\n\r\n136\r\n00:12:45,531 --> 00:12:46,828\r\nChange the machines around,\nwhatever you do,\r\n\r\n137\r\n00:12:46,866 --> 00:12:49,334\r\nyou could make other\nthings, couldn't you?\r\n\r\n138\r\n00:12:49,368 --> 00:12:53,964\r\nField kits, mess kits.\nArmy contracts.\r\n\r\n139\r\n00:12:55,708 --> 00:12:58,643\r\nOnce the war ends,\nforget it, but for now\nit's great.\r\n\r\n140\r\n00:12:58,711 --> 00:13:00,906\r\nYou can make a fortune,\ndon't you think?\r\n\r\n141\r\n00:13:00,946 --> 00:13:04,382\r\nI think most people right now\nhave other priorities.\r\n\r\n142\r\n00:13:04,450 --> 00:13:07,385\r\nLike what?\n[Sighs]\r\n\r\n143\r\n00:13:07,453 --> 00:13:09,887\r\nI'm sure you'll do just fine\nonce you get the contracts.\r\n\r\n144\r\n00:13:09,955 --> 00:13:12,014\r\nIn fact, the worse things get,\nthe better you'll do.\r\n\r\n145\r\n00:13:12,091 --> 00:13:15,549\r\nOh, well, I can get\nthe signatures I need.\nThat's the easy part.\r\n\r\n146\r\n00:13:15,628 --> 00:13:19,394\r\nFinding the money\nto buy the company,\nthat's hard.\r\n\r\n147\r\n00:13:19,465 --> 00:13:21,399\r\nYou don't have\nany money?\r\n\r\n148\r\n00:13:21,467 --> 00:13:25,563\r\nNot that kind of money.\nYou know anybody?\r\n\r\n149\r\n00:13:25,638 --> 00:13:28,573\r\n[Closes Case]\nJews, yeah.\r\n\r\n150\r\n00:13:28,641 --> 00:13:31,576\r\nInvestors. You must\nhave contacts...\r\n\r\n151\r\n00:13:31,644 --> 00:13:33,578\r\nin theJewish\nbusiness community\nworking here.\r\n\r\n152\r\n00:13:33,646 --> 00:13:36,410\r\nWhat community?\nJews can no longer\nown businesses.\r\n\r\n153\r\n00:13:36,482 --> 00:13:39,576\r\nThat's why this one's\nin receivership.\nBut they\nwouldn't own it.\r\n\r\n154\r\n00:13:39,652 --> 00:13:42,416\r\nI'd own it.\nI'd pay them back in\nproduct... pots and pans.\r\n\r\n155\r\n00:13:42,488 --> 00:13:45,423\r\nPots and pans.\nSomething\nthey can use.\r\n\r\n156\r\n00:13:45,491 --> 00:13:47,425\r\nSomething they can\nfeel in their hands.\r\n\r\n157\r\n00:13:47,493 --> 00:13:49,791\r\nThey can trade it\non the black market,\ndo whatever they want.\r\n\r\n158\r\n00:13:49,862 --> 00:13:52,262\r\nEverybody's happy.\r\n\r\n159\r\n00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:56,768\r\nIf you want, you could\nrun the company for me.\r\n\r\n160\r\n00:14:00,673 --> 00:14:03,073\r\nLet me understand.\r\n\r\n161\r\n00:14:03,142 --> 00:14:05,906\r\nThey'd put up all the money,\nI'd do all the work.\r\n\r\n162\r\n00:14:05,978 --> 00:14:09,243\r\nWhat, if you don't mind\nmy asking, would you do?\r\n\r\n163\r\n00:14:09,315 --> 00:14:11,749\r\nI'd make sure it's known\nthe company's in business.\r\n\r\n164\r\n00:14:11,784 --> 00:14:14,048\r\nI'd see that it had\na certain panache.\r\n\r\n165\r\n00:14:14,119 --> 00:14:17,919\r\nThat's what I'm good at,\nnot the work. Not the work.\r\n\r\n166\r\n00:14:17,990 --> 00:14:20,481\r\nThe presentation.\r\n\r\n167\r\n00:14:38,510 --> 00:14:42,844\r\nI'm sure I don't know anybody\nwho'll be interested in this.\r\n\r\n168\r\n00:14:44,083 --> 00:14:47,280\r\n[Exhales]\nWell, they should be,\nItzhak Stern.\r\n\r\n169\r\n00:14:47,353 --> 00:14:51,187\r\nTell them they should be.\r\n\r\n170\r\n00:15:00,366 --> 00:15:03,199\r\n[Loufspeaker]\nAchtung! Achtung!\r\n\r\n171\r\n00:15:03,269 --> 00:15:09,174\r\nAn alleJuden...\nAb sofort ist es verboten...\r\n\r\n172\r\n00:15:09,241 --> 00:15:13,803\r\n[Priest]\nVere dignum et justum est,\naequum et salutare,\r\n\r\n173\r\n00:15:13,879 --> 00:15:18,373\r\nnos tibi semper et\nubique gratias agere,\r\n\r\n174\r\n00:15:18,450 --> 00:15:21,783\r\nDomine Sancte, Pater Omnipotens,\nAeterne Deus.\r\n\r\n175\r\n00:15:21,854 --> 00:15:25,381\r\nI've got a client\nwho'll sell marks\nfor zloty at 2.45 to 1.\r\n\r\n176\r\n00:15:25,457 --> 00:15:27,721\r\nWool, mink collar.\nIt's a nice coat.\r\n\r\n177\r\n00:15:27,793 --> 00:15:29,727\r\nShe'll trade it\nfor ration coupons.\r\n\r\n178\r\n00:15:29,795 --> 00:15:33,231\r\nWicks, for lamps.\nYou have a truckload\nof wicks?\r\n\r\n179\r\n00:15:33,299 --> 00:15:37,463\r\nWhat am I going to do\nwith a truckload of wicks?\nNine by 12, nine by 14.\r\n\r\n180\r\n00:15:37,536 --> 00:15:40,562\r\nI fon't know.\nBig, beautiful, Persian.\r\n\r\n181\r\n00:15:40,639 --> 00:15:43,574\r\n[Priest Continues]\nLumen aeternum mundo effudit...\r\n\r\n182\r\n00:15:43,642 --> 00:15:46,076\r\nPsst.\nWhat?\r\n\r\n183\r\n00:15:46,111 --> 00:15:48,079\r\nYou don't recognize this?\nIt's shoe polish.\r\n\r\n184\r\n00:15:48,147 --> 00:15:50,581\r\nIn metal containers?\nYou asked\nfor shoe polish.\r\n\r\n185\r\n00:15:50,649 --> 00:15:52,913\r\nIn metal containers.\nThis is glass.\nIn metal containers.\r\n\r\n186\r\n00:15:52,985 --> 00:15:54,919\r\nIt's not what I asked for.\nWhat's\nthe difference?\r\n\r\n187\r\n00:15:54,987 --> 00:15:56,921\r\nWhat's the difference?\nWhat's the difference?\r\n\r\n188\r\n00:15:56,989 --> 00:15:59,082\r\n[Others]\nShh.!\nMy client sold it\nto his client,\r\n\r\n189\r\n00:15:59,158 --> 00:16:01,023\r\nwho sold it\nto the German Army.\r\n\r\n190\r\n00:16:01,226 --> 00:16:05,526\r\nOnly by the time it got there,\nbecause of the freezing cold,\nit broke. All 10,000 units.\r\n\r\n191\r\n00:16:05,597 --> 00:16:07,895\r\nMmm,\nooh, ooh, ooh.\nThis is not my problem.\r\n\r\n192\r\n00:16:07,967 --> 00:16:09,901\r\nThis is not\nhis problem.\nThis is not your problem?\r\n\r\n193\r\n00:16:09,969 --> 00:16:12,563\r\nThis is not\nmy problem.\nAll right.\r\n\r\n194\r\n00:16:12,638 --> 00:16:16,574\r\nThe German Army\nwants to find out\nwhere it came from.\r\n\r\n195\r\n00:16:16,642 --> 00:16:20,009\r\nI am going to make sure\nthey find out.\nNow it's your problem.\r\n\r\n196\r\n00:16:20,079 --> 00:16:23,242\r\nYou be quiet!\n[Chuckles]\r\n\r\n197\r\n00:16:23,315 --> 00:16:26,079\r\nMetal\ncontainers.\r\n\r\n198\r\n00:16:26,151 --> 00:16:28,915\r\nHello.\r\n\r\n199\r\n00:16:28,988 --> 00:16:33,015\r\nPardon me for interfering,\nbut that's a nice shirt.\r\n\r\n200\r\n00:16:33,092 --> 00:16:35,424\r\nNice shirt.\r\n\r\n201\r\n00:16:35,494 --> 00:16:38,793\r\nDo you know where\nI can find a nice\nshirt like that?\r\n\r\n202\r\n00:16:40,766 --> 00:16:44,759\r\n[Priest Continues]\n... laufare, beneficere\net preficare.\r\n\r\n203\r\n00:16:46,505 --> 00:16:48,439\r\nLike this?\r\n\r\n204\r\n00:16:48,507 --> 00:16:51,567\r\nIt's illegal to buy or sell\nanything on the street.\r\n\r\n205\r\n00:16:51,643 --> 00:16:54,942\r\nWe don't do that.\nWe're here to pray.\r\n\r\n206\r\n00:16:57,016 --> 00:16:59,780\r\n[Priest Continues]\nJesum Christum Dominum Nostrum...\r\n\r\n207\r\n00:16:59,852 --> 00:17:04,721\r\nDo you have any idea how much\na shirt like this costs?\nNice things cost money.\r\n\r\n208\r\n00:17:04,790 --> 00:17:09,056\r\n[Priest Continues]\n...adorant Dominationes,\ntremunt Potestates.\r\n\r\n209\r\n00:17:09,128 --> 00:17:14,589\r\nCoeli coelorumque\nvirtutes ac Beata Seraphim...\r\n\r\n210\r\n00:17:14,666 --> 00:17:17,897\r\nsocia exultatione\nconcelebrant...\r\n\r\n211\r\n00:17:17,970 --> 00:17:20,336\r\nHow many?\r\n\r\n212\r\n00:17:20,406 --> 00:17:24,399\r\nI'm going to need\nsome other things, too,\nas things come up.\r\n\r\n213\r\n00:17:24,476 --> 00:17:28,640\r\nThis won't be\na problem.\nFrom time to time.\r\n\r\n214\r\n00:17:28,981 --> 00:17:31,711\r\n[Loufspeaker]\nAchtung! Achtung!\r\n\r\n215\r\n00:18:04,950 --> 00:18:08,113\r\n[Chilfren Crying]\r\n\r\n216\r\n00:18:13,425 --> 00:18:16,826\r\n[Officers]\n- Name? Adresse?\n- Formular ausfuellen!\r\n\r\n217\r\n00:18:16,895 --> 00:18:19,386\r\nWeiter, weiter.!\nNicht fraengeln.!\r\n\r\n218\r\n00:18:19,465 --> 00:18:22,059\r\nKommen Sie hierher.!\nStellen Sie sich foch an.!\r\n\r\n219\r\n00:18:36,448 --> 00:18:39,383\r\n[Silverware Clattering]\r\n\r\n220\r\n00:19:09,281 --> 00:19:12,546\r\n[Loufspeaker]\nAchtung, achtung!\nAlleJuden sind verpflichtet...\r\n\r\n221\r\n00:19:12,618 --> 00:19:16,349\r\nim abgesonderten\njuedischen Bezirk zu wohnen.\r\n\r\n222\r\n00:19:16,421 --> 00:19:20,585\r\nNichteinhaltung der Meldepflicht\nbei der Einwohnerbehoerde...\r\n\r\n223\r\n00:19:20,659 --> 00:19:23,594\r\nverstoesst gegen das Edikt 44/91\nund fuehrt zur Anzeige...\r\n\r\n224\r\n00:19:23,662 --> 00:19:25,254\r\nbeim Militaergericht.\r\n\r\n225\r\n00:19:27,366 --> 00:19:31,132\r\nThis is obviously the right\nplace. How are you doing?\nHerr Schindler.\r\n\r\n226\r\n00:19:31,203 --> 00:19:35,401\r\n[Infistinct Shouting]\r\n\r\n227\r\n00:19:35,474 --> 00:19:39,570\r\nGoof-bye, Jews.!\nGoof-bye, Jews.!\r\n\r\n228\r\n00:19:39,645 --> 00:19:43,604\r\nGood-bye, Jews!\nGood-bye, Jews!\r\n\r\n229\r\n00:19:45,017 --> 00:19:47,918\r\n[Girl Continues Yelling]\nGoof-bye, Jews.!\r\n\r\n230\r\n00:19:47,986 --> 00:19:52,719\r\nGoof-bye, Jews.!\nGoof-bye, Jews.!\r\n\r\n231\r\n00:19:56,161 --> 00:19:58,823\r\nThis iz the vechteka,\nMoyshe.\nOjciec.\r\n\r\n232\r\n00:19:58,897 --> 00:20:01,957\r\nNyne, this kan\nneash zyane.\r\n\r\n233\r\n00:20:09,841 --> 00:20:11,832\r\n[Sighs]\r\n\r\n234\r\n00:20:11,910 --> 00:20:15,778\r\n[Baby Crying, Woman Singing\nPolish Lullaby]\nOh, my God.\r\n\r\n235\r\n00:20:15,847 --> 00:20:19,283\r\nOy, God.\nOh, my God.\r\n\r\n236\r\n00:20:19,351 --> 00:20:22,752\r\n[Crying Continues]\r\n\r\n237\r\n00:20:26,191 --> 00:20:28,921\r\nOh, my God.\r\n\r\n238\r\n00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:37,134\r\nIt could not be better.\r\n\r\n239\r\n00:20:37,202 --> 00:20:40,968\r\nIt could be worse.\nHow? Tell me.\r\n\r\n240\r\n00:20:41,039 --> 00:20:43,974\r\n[Shouting]\nHow on earth could it\npossibly be worse?\r\n\r\n241\r\n00:20:44,042 --> 00:20:46,010\r\n[Slams Down Suitcase]\r\n\r\n242\r\n00:20:46,044 --> 00:20:48,706\r\n[Man]\nDzien dobry.\r\n\r\n243\r\n00:20:48,780 --> 00:20:51,180\r\nDzien fobry.\nDzien fobry.\r\n\r\n244\r\n00:20:51,250 --> 00:20:53,013\r\nDzien fobry.\r\n\r\n245\r\n00:20:53,085 --> 00:20:55,519\r\nDzien fobry.\nDzien fobry.\r\n\r\n246\r\n00:20:55,587 --> 00:20:58,488\r\n[Indistinct German]\r\n\r\n247\r\n00:20:58,557 --> 00:21:00,991\r\nHey, Goldberg.\nPoldek.\r\n\r\n248\r\n00:21:01,059 --> 00:21:05,393\r\nWhat's this?\nUh, the Jufenrat has\nits own police now.\r\n\r\n249\r\n00:21:05,464 --> 00:21:08,228\r\nYou don't say.\nOrfnungsfienst.\r\n\r\n250\r\n00:21:08,300 --> 00:21:10,894\r\nI'm a policeman now,\ncould you believe it?\nIt's hard to believe.\r\n\r\n251\r\n00:21:10,969 --> 00:21:12,903\r\nOh, no,\nit's not hard\nto believe.\r\n\r\n252\r\n00:21:12,971 --> 00:21:15,405\r\nIt's a good racket, Poldek.\nThe only racket here.\r\n\r\n253\r\n00:21:15,474 --> 00:21:18,910\r\nLook, maybe I could\nput in a good word for you\nwith my superiors.\r\n\r\n254\r\n00:21:18,977 --> 00:21:23,243\r\nYour superiors?\nCome on, they are not\nas bad as everyone says.\r\n\r\n255\r\n00:21:23,315 --> 00:21:26,580\r\nWell, they're worse\nthan everyone says,\nbut it's a lot of money.\r\n\r\n256\r\n00:21:26,652 --> 00:21:29,246\r\nA lot of money.\r\n\r\n257\r\n00:21:29,321 --> 00:21:32,085\r\nGive me my\nhousing assignment.\r\n\r\n258\r\n00:21:32,157 --> 00:21:36,594\r\nCome on.\nYou look funny\nin that hat, Goldberg.\r\n\r\n259\r\n00:21:36,662 --> 00:21:40,098\r\n[Laughs]\nYou look like a clown,\nyou know?\r\n\r\n260\r\n00:21:45,003 --> 00:21:47,437\r\n[Stern]\nHe's a very important man.\r\n\r\n261\r\n00:21:47,472 --> 00:21:49,269\r\nJust give him\ntwo minutes of your time.\r\n\r\n262\r\n00:21:49,341 --> 00:21:52,777\r\nSince when did time cost money?\nJust sit down and listen.\r\n\r\n263\r\n00:21:52,844 --> 00:21:55,074\r\nPlease.\nSir?\r\n\r\n264\r\n00:21:58,784 --> 00:22:00,843\r\n[Schinfler]\nFor each thousanf you invest,\nI will repay you with...\r\n\r\n265\r\n00:22:00,886 --> 00:22:03,081\r\nTwo hundred.\n200 kilos\nof enamelware a month,\r\n\r\n266\r\n00:22:03,121 --> 00:22:05,089\r\nto begin in July\nand to continue\nfor one year.\r\n\r\n267\r\n00:22:05,157 --> 00:22:08,923\r\nAfter which time, we're even.\nThat's it. It's very simple.\r\n\r\n268\r\n00:22:08,994 --> 00:22:11,929\r\nNot good enough.\nIt's not\ngood enough.\r\n\r\n269\r\n00:22:11,997 --> 00:22:14,261\r\nNot good enough?\r\n\r\n270\r\n00:22:14,333 --> 00:22:18,429\r\nLook where you're living.\nLook where you've been put.\n\"Not good enough.\"\r\n\r\n271\r\n00:22:18,503 --> 00:22:21,097\r\nA couple of months ago you'd\nbe right, not anymore.\r\n\r\n272\r\n00:22:21,173 --> 00:22:24,267\r\nMoney's still money.\r\n\r\n273\r\n00:22:25,844 --> 00:22:28,108\r\nNo, it is not.\r\n\r\n274\r\n00:22:28,180 --> 00:22:30,273\r\nThat's why we're here.\r\n\r\n275\r\n00:22:30,349 --> 00:22:32,317\r\nTrade goods...\nthat's the only currency...\r\n\r\n276\r\n00:22:32,351 --> 00:22:34,319\r\nthat'll be worth\nanything in the ghetto.\r\n\r\n277\r\n00:22:34,353 --> 00:22:37,789\r\nThings have changed,\nmy friend.\r\n\r\n278\r\n00:22:38,523 --> 00:22:40,957\r\nDid I call\nthis meeting?\r\n\r\n279\r\n00:22:41,026 --> 00:22:43,460\r\nYou told Mr. Stern\nyou wanted to speak to me.\r\n\r\n280\r\n00:22:43,528 --> 00:22:46,122\r\nI'm here.\nI've made you a fair offer.\r\n\r\n281\r\n00:22:46,198 --> 00:22:50,134\r\nFair would be\na percentage in the company.\r\n\r\n282\r\n00:22:50,202 --> 00:22:53,467\r\n[Laughing]\nForget the whole thing.\r\n\r\n283\r\n00:22:53,538 --> 00:22:55,802\r\nGet out.\r\n\r\n284\r\n00:23:00,045 --> 00:23:03,105\r\nHow do we know that you\nwill do what you say?\r\n\r\n285\r\n00:23:03,181 --> 00:23:05,115\r\nBecause I said I would.\r\n\r\n286\r\n00:23:05,183 --> 00:23:07,413\r\nYou want a contract?\nTo be upheld by what court?\r\n\r\n287\r\n00:23:07,486 --> 00:23:10,421\r\nI said what I'll do.\nThat's our contract.\r\n\r\n288\r\n00:23:10,489 --> 00:23:13,822\r\n[Infistinct Polish]\r\n\r\n289\r\n00:23:13,892 --> 00:23:16,019\r\n... mielismy racje.\r\n\r\n290\r\n00:23:27,739 --> 00:23:33,177\r\n[Man]\nPiec, szesc, siedem...\r\n\r\n291\r\n00:23:33,245 --> 00:23:36,840\r\nosiem, fziewiec.\r\n\r\n292\r\n00:23:39,518 --> 00:23:43,420\r\n[Machinery Buzzes]\r\n\r\n293\r\n00:23:45,023 --> 00:23:47,958\r\n[Schindler Clapping]\r\n\r\n294\r\n00:23:48,360 --> 00:23:52,626\r\nThe standard SS rate for\nJewish skilled labor\nis seven marks a day,\r\n\r\n295\r\n00:23:52,697 --> 00:23:55,632\r\nfive for unskilled\nand women.\r\n\r\n296\r\n00:23:55,700 --> 00:23:58,794\r\nThis is what you pay\nthe Reich Economic Office.\r\n\r\n297\r\n00:23:58,870 --> 00:24:01,361\r\nTheJews themselves\nreceive nothing.\r\n\r\n298\r\n00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:05,877\r\nPoles you pay wages.\nGenerally, they get\na little more.\r\n\r\n299\r\n00:24:05,944 --> 00:24:08,538\r\nAre you\nlistening?\nWhat was that about the SS?\r\n\r\n300\r\n00:24:08,613 --> 00:24:10,877\r\nThe rate? The what?\r\n\r\n301\r\n00:24:10,949 --> 00:24:14,544\r\nTheJewish worker's salary...\nyou pay it directly to\nthe SS, not to the worker.\r