o make money.\nFor me.\r\n\r\n459\r\n00:36:15,973 --> 00:36:18,373\r\n[Sighs]\r\n\r\n460\r\n00:36:21,646 --> 00:36:24,877\r\nDoes anyone\nask about me?\r\n\r\n461\r\n00:36:26,317 --> 00:36:29,582\r\nBack home?\nEverybody.\r\n\r\n462\r\n00:36:29,654 --> 00:36:32,589\r\nAll the time.\r\n\r\n463\r\n00:36:32,657 --> 00:36:35,922\r\nHmm.\r\n\r\n464\r\n00:36:35,993 --> 00:36:41,590\r\nThey won't soon forget\nthe name Schindler here,\nI can tell you that.\r\n\r\n465\r\n00:36:43,000 --> 00:36:46,265\r\n\"Oskar Schindler,\"\nthey'll say.\r\n\r\n466\r\n00:36:46,337 --> 00:36:49,773\r\n\"Everybody\nremembers him.\r\n\r\n467\r\n00:36:49,840 --> 00:36:54,277\r\n\"He did something\nextraordinary.\r\n\r\n468\r\n00:36:54,345 --> 00:36:59,442\r\n\"He did something\nno one else did.\r\n\r\n469\r\n00:36:59,517 --> 00:37:02,850\r\n\"He came here\nwith nothing...\r\n\r\n470\r\n00:37:02,920 --> 00:37:05,855\r\n\"a suitcase...\r\n\r\n471\r\n00:37:05,923 --> 00:37:11,520\r\n\"and built a bankrupt\ncompany into a major\nmanufactory.\r\n\r\n472\r\n00:37:11,596 --> 00:37:15,191\r\n\"And left with\na steamer trunk...\r\n\r\n473\r\n00:37:15,266 --> 00:37:19,862\r\n\"Two steamer trunks\nfull of money,\r\n\r\n474\r\n00:37:19,937 --> 00:37:24,203\r\nall the riches\nof the world.\"\r\n\r\n475\r\n00:37:24,275 --> 00:37:26,209\r\nHmm.\r\n\r\n476\r\n00:37:26,277 --> 00:37:29,542\r\nIt's comforting to see\nthat nothing's changed.\r\n\r\n477\r\n00:37:29,614 --> 00:37:33,209\r\nYou're wrong, Emilie.\n[Kissing Sound]\r\n\r\n478\r\n00:37:33,284 --> 00:37:35,718\r\nThere's no way I could have\nknown this before,\r\n\r\n479\r\n00:37:35,786 --> 00:37:39,222\r\nbut there was always\nsomething missing.\r\n\r\n480\r\n00:37:39,290 --> 00:37:43,386\r\nIn every business I tried,\nI can see now, it wasn't me\nthat failed.\r\n\r\n481\r\n00:37:43,461 --> 00:37:46,225\r\nSomething was missing.\r\n\r\n482\r\n00:37:46,297 --> 00:37:49,892\r\nEven if I'd known what it\nwas, there's nothing I could\nhave done about it...\r