t families back home.\r\n\r\n967\r\n01:17:34,016 --> 01:17:37,144\r\nBut it's private infustry\nlike yours that stanfs\nto benefit most...\r\n\r\n968\r\n01:17:37,185 --> 01:17:39,551\r\nby moving insife the wire of\nCommanfant Amon Goeth's camp...\r\n\r\n969\r\n01:17:39,588 --> 01:17:42,455\r\nNo, no, no. Sit, sit.\nJulian, how are you?\r\n\r\n970\r\n01:17:42,524 --> 01:17:44,014\r\nHow are you?\nGood to see you,\nmy friend.\r\n\r\n971\r\n01:17:44,059 --> 01:17:46,857\r\nOskar Schindler.\nLeoJohn.\r\n\r\n972\r\n01:17:46,928 --> 01:17:50,329\r\n[Whispers, Chuckles]\r\n\r\n973\r\n01:17:50,399 --> 01:17:53,698\r\nFranz, good to see you.\nHello, Oskar.\nGlad you could join us.\r\n\r\n974\r\n01:17:53,769 --> 01:17:56,863\r\nMy pleasure. Julius.\nHow are you?\nYou lost weight.\r\n\r\n975\r\n01:17:56,905 --> 01:18:01,001\r\nOnly in the shoulders.\nPlease, everybody, sit down.\r\n\r\n976\r\n01:18:01,076 --> 01:18:03,738\r\nHow are you doing?\nOskar Schindler.\r\n\r\n977\r\n01:18:05,447 --> 01:18:08,883\r\nWe started without you.\nFine.\nI miss anything good?\r\n\r\n978\r\n01:18:08,950 --> 01:18:12,215\r\nI was explaining\nto Herr Bosch\nand Herr Madritsch...\r\n\r\n979\r\n01:18:12,287 --> 01:18:15,154\r\nsome of the benefits\nof moving their\nfactories into Plaszow.\r\n\r\n980\r\n01:18:15,190 --> 01:18:18,125\r\nI meant the food.\n[Chuckles]\r\n\r\n981\r\n01:18:20,262 --> 01:18:24,358\r\nSince your labor is housed\non-site, it's available\nto you at all times.\r\n\r\n982\r\n01:18:24,433 --> 01:18:26,697\r\nYou can work them\nall night if you want.\r\n\r\n983\r\n01:18:26,768 --> 01:18:31,228\r\nYour factory policies, whatever\nthey've been in the past,\nthey'll continue to be.\r\n\r\n984\r\n01:18:31,306 --> 01:18:33,501\r\nThey'll be respectef.\r\n\r\n985\r\n01:18:33,575 --> 01:18:37,841\r\nI have to know, where\ndo you get a suit like that?\nWhat is that? Is that silk?\r\n\r\n986\r\n01:18:37,913 --> 01:18:39,847\r\nOf course.\r\n\r\n987\r\n01:18:39,915 --> 01:18:44,215\r\nJa. It's... It has\na nice sheen about it.\r\n\r\n988\r\n01:18:44,286 --> 01:18:46,220\r\nThank you.\nVery nice.\r\n\r\n989\r\n01:18:46,288 --> 01:18:50,088\r\nI'd say I'd get you one,\nbut the man who made it\nis probably dead.\r\n\r\n990\r\n01:18:50,158 --> 01:18:52,683\r\nI don't know.\r\n\r\n991\r\n01:18:52,761 --> 01:18:56,527\r\n[Schinfler's Voice]\nI go to work the other fay.\r\n\r\n992\r\n01:18:56,598 --> 01:18:58,896\r\nNobofy's there.\r\n\r\n993\r\n01:18:58,967 --> 01:19:02,368\r\nNobofy tells me about this.\nI have to finf out.\nI have to go in.\r\n\r\n994\r\n01:19:02,437 --> 01:19:05,998\r\nEverybody's gone.\r\n\r\n995\r\n01:19:06,074 --> 01:19:09,009\r\nNo.\n[Sighs]\r\n\r\n996\r\n01:19:09,077 --> 01:19:11,170\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n997\r\n01:19:13,915 --> 01:19:16,509\r\nThey're not gone.\nThey're here.\r\n\r\n998\r\n01:19:16,585 --> 01:19:21,545\r\nThey're mine!\nEvery day that goes by,\nI'm losing money.\r\n\r\n999\r\n01:19:21,623 --> 01:19:25,787\r\nEvery worker that is shot\ncosts me money. I have to\nfind somebody else.\r\n\r\n1000\r\n01:19:25,861 --> 01:19:28,489\r\nWe are going to be making\nso much money that none of this\nis going to matter.\r\n\r\n1001\r\n01:19:28,530 --> 01:19:30,088\r\nIt's bad business.\r\n\r\n1002\r\n01:19:33,301 --> 01:19:35,201\r\n[Sniffs]\r\n\r\n1003\r\n01:19:43,111 --> 01:19:45,045\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\n1004\r\n01:19:45,113 --> 01:19:47,638\r\nLeave the bottle.\r\n\r\n1005\r\n01:19:48,884 --> 01:19:51,114\r\nTake that.\r\n\r\n1006\r\n01:19:51,186 --> 01:19:54,781\r\nLena... thank you.\r\n\r\n1007\r\n01:20:04,032 --> 01:20:07,195\r\nScherner told me\nsomething else about you.\r\n\r\n1008\r\n01:20:09,471 --> 01:20:11,837\r\nYeah?\nWhat's that?\r\n\r\n1009\r\n01:20:11,907 --> 01:20:16,606\r\nThat you know the meaning\nof the word \"gratitude.\"\r\n\r\n1010\r\n01:20:16,678 --> 01:20:20,170\r\nThat it's not\nsome vague thing with you...\r\n\r\n1011\r\n01:20:20,248 --> 01:20:23,445\r\nlike it is with others.\r\n\r\n1012\r\n01:20:23,518 --> 01:20:26,976\r\nYou want to stay\nwhere you are.\r\n\r\n1013\r\n01:20:27,055 --> 01:20:30,183\r\nYou've got things\ngoing on the sife.\r\n\r\n1014\r\n01:20:30,258 --> 01:20:32,351\r\nThings are good.\r\n\r\n1015\r\n01:20:32,427 --> 01:20:36,989\r\nYou don't want anybody\ntelling you what to do.\r\n\r\n1016\r\n01:20:37,065 --> 01:20:41,525\r\nI can understand all that,\nyou know. L... I know you.\r\n\r\n1017\r\n01:20:43,672 --> 01:20:48,905\r\nWhat you want...\nis your own sub-camp.\r\n\r\n1018\r\n01:20:54,282 --> 01:20:57,774\r\nDo you have any idea\nwhat is involved?\nThe paperwork alone?\r\n\r\n1019\r\n01:20:57,853 --> 01:21:01,983\r\nYou've got to build the thing.\nGetting those fucking permits\nis enough to drive you crazy.\r\n\r\n1020\r\n01:21:02,023 --> 01:21:06,153\r\nThen the engineers show up,\nthey stand around, they argue\nabout drainage, foundations,\r\n\r\n1021\r\n01:21:06,194 --> 01:21:11,461\r\ncodes, exact specifications,\nfences four kilometers long,\n1,200 kilograms of barbed wire,\r\n\r\n1022\r\n01:21:11,533 --> 01:21:14,832\r\n[Chuckling]\n6,000 kilograms of electrified\nfences, ceramic insulators,\r\n\r\n1023\r\n01:21:14,903 --> 01:21:16,666\r\nthree cubic meters\nof air space per prisoner.\r\n\r\n1024\r\n01:21:16,705 --> 01:21:20,732\r\nI'm telling you,\nyou want to shoot somebody.\nI've been through it. I know.\r\n\r\n1025\r\n01:21:20,775 --> 01:21:24,575\r\nWell, you know.\nYou've been through it.\n[Spits]\r\n\r\n1026\r\n01:21:26,481 --> 01:21:29,575\r\nYou could make things\neasier for me.\r\n\r\n1027\r\n01:21:32,554 --> 01:21:34,715\r\nI'd be grateful.\r\n\r\n1028\r\n01:21:38,226 --> 01:21:40,626\r\nAus fem Weg fa.!\r\n\r\n1029\r\n01:21:48,403 --> 01:21:50,701\r\n[Dogs Barking]\r\n\r\n1030\r\n01:21:50,772 --> 01:21:54,708\r\nWeitergehen.!\nWeitergehen.!\n[Speaking Polish]\r\n\r\n1031\r\n01:21:54,776 --> 01:21:55,902\r\n[Whistle Blows]\r\n\r\n1032\r\n01:21:55,944 --> 01:21:59,380\r\nWlewo zwrot.!\nTrzymac szereg.!\r\n\r\n1033\r\n01:21:59,447 --> 01:22:02,416\r\nWeitergehen.\nNach links.\r\n\r\n1034\r\n01:22:02,484 --> 01:22:05,419\r\n[Dogs Continue Barking]\r\n\r\n1035\r\n01:22:07,122 --> 01:22:09,920\r\n[Whistle Blows]\r\n\r\n1036\r\n01:22:09,991 --> 01:22:11,982\r\nWhere's Stern?\r\n\r\n1037\r\n01:22:15,630 --> 01:22:19,794\r\nGoldberg and Chilowicz...\nmake sure I see my cut...\r\n\r\n1038\r\n01:22:19,868 --> 01:22:23,395\r\nfrom the, uh,\nfactory owners in this camp,\r\n\r\n1039\r\n01:22:23,471 --> 01:22:26,872\r\nleaving you to take care\nof my main account...\r\n\r\n1040\r\n01:22:26,942 --> 01:22:30,275\r\nthe Schindler account.\r\n\r\n1041\r\n01:22:30,345 --> 01:22:34,406\r\nHe wants his independence.\nI gave it to him.\r\n\r\n1042\r\n01:22:34,482 --> 01:22:37,417\r\nBut independence\ncosts money.\r\n\r\n1043\r\n01:22:37,485 --> 01:22:39,885\r\nThis you\nunderstand?\r\n\r\n1044\r\n01:22:44,726 --> 01:22:46,694\r\nLook at me.\r\n\r\n1045\r\n01:22:57,339 --> 01:23:01,503\r\nDon't forget who\nyou are working for now.\r\n\r\n1046\r\n01:23:05,981 --> 01:23:08,916\r\n[Chattering, Shouting]\r\n\r\n1047\r\n01:23:08,984 --> 01:23:10,975\r\n[ Accorfion]\r\n\r\n1048\r\n01:23:11,052 --> 01:23:14,283\r\nJawohl.!\n[Schinfler]\nMake sure he kisses\neach anf every one.!\r\n\r\n1049\r\n01:23:14,356 --> 01:23:17,757\r\nJa. Now, girls,\neveryone.\r\n\r\n1050\r\n01:23:20,695 --> 01:23:23,289\r\nWe need more wine.\nMore wine!\r\n\r\n1051\r\n01:23:23,365 --> 01:23:27,131\r\nStand in my place.\nDon't let him leave.\r\n\r\n1052\r\n01:23:27,202 --> 01:23:29,762\r\n[Laughing, Singing]\r\n\r\n1053\r\n01:23:31,873 --> 01:23:34,933\r\n[Chattering,\nShouting Continue]\r\n\r\n1054\r\n01:23:43,218 --> 01:23:46,619\r\nWas passiert fenn\nin einem Leben\nProst.! Prost.!\r\n\r\n1055\r\n01:23:48,590 --> 01:23:51,320\r\nThank you,\nHerr Direktor.\r\n\r\n1056\r\n01:23:51,393 --> 01:23:53,725\r\nProst,\nHerr Direktor!\r\n\r\n1057\r\n01:23:57,899 --> 01:24:01,357\r\nWhat are you\ndoing?\nWhat?\nScratching my head.\r\n\r\n1058\r\n01:24:01,436 --> 01:24:05,896\r\nMakes them think we have lice.\nHelps them keep their distance.\n[Exhales]\r\n\r\n1059\r\n01:24:05,974 --> 01:24:08,465\r\nDo you have lice?\nDo you have your notebook?\r\n\r\n1060\r\n01:24:08,543 --> 01:24:12,206\r\nThe calendar on my desk has\nthe birthdays of our SS friends'\nwives and children.\r\n\r\n1061\r\n01:24:12,247 --> 01:24:14,841\r\nDon't forget\nto send something.\r\n\r\n1062\r\n01:24:14,916 --> 01:24:18,374\r\nRecord payoffs\nto the Main Administration\nand Economics Office, the Arm...\r\n\r\n1063\r\n01:24:18,453 --> 01:24:22,355\r\nSlower, Stern, slower.\nThe Armaments Board,\nGovernor General's Division...\r\n\r\n1064\r\n01:24:22,424 --> 01:24:25,359\r\nof the Interior\nand Chief of Police as \"fees,\"\r\n\r\n1065\r\n01:24:25,427 --> 01:24:27,520\r\nand make them\non the first of each month,\r\n\r\n1066\r\n01:24:27,595 --> 01:24:29,893\r\nas opposed to individual payoffs\nto our SS contacts.\r\n\r\n1067\r\n01:24:29,931 --> 01:24:35,369\r\nThe list is in the lower drawer\nof my desk, which you...\n\"First of month...\"\r\n\r\n1068\r\n01:24:35,437 --> 01:24:38,372\r\nSS contacts: List,\nlower drawer of my desk,\nwhich you handle...\r\n\r\n1069\r\n01:24:38,440 --> 01:24:42,706\r\nas cash contributions\nto legitimate charities\nsent to each official's office.\r\n\r\n1070\r\n01:24:42,777 --> 01:24:45,837\r\nDealings with\nour black market contacts,\nlisted as suppliers...\r\n\r\n1071\r\n01:24:45,914 --> 01:24:49,577\r\nin the legitimate ledger,\nare more complicated.\nForget it.\r\n\r\n1072\r\n01:24:49,651 --> 01:24:53,587\r\nWhat do you mean, forget it?\nYou can't forget it!\nIt gives me a headache!\r\n\r\n1073\r\n01:24:53,655 --> 01:24:57,250\r\n[Dogs Barking]\r\n\r\n1074\r\n01:24:57,325 --> 01:25:00,260\r\n[Sighs]\r\n\r\n1075\r\n01:25:00,328 --> 01:25:03,729\r\nI couldn't get you\nout of here.\nI'll be all right.\r\n\r\n1076\r\n01:25:03,798 --> 01:25:07,928\r\nAnyway, I'm here\nalmost every week.\nWednesdays, usually.\r\n\r\n1077\r\n01:25:08,002 --> 01:25:11,438\r\nI'll look in on you,\nsee how you're doing.\r\n\r\n1078\r\n01:25:13,608 --> 01:25:17,237\r\nHere, put these\nin your pocket.\r\n\r\n1079\r\n01:25:17,312 --> 01:25:19,337\r\nCome on.\r\n\r\n1080\r\n01:25:22,150 --> 01:25:25,586\r\n[Inhales]\nHerr Direktor,\ndon't let things fall apart.\r\n\r\n1081\r\n01:25:25,653 --> 01:25:27,848\r\nI've worked too hard.\r\n\r\n1082\r\n01:25:36,164 --> 01:25:40,794\r\nThanks for...\nGood luck.\r\n\r\n1083\r\n01:25:40,869 --> 01:25:44,805\r\n[Music, Shouting\nContinue]\r\n\r\n1084\r\n01:26:02,524 --> 01:26:05,015\r\nAchtung, Muetzen ab.!\r\n\r\n1085\r\n01:26:14,869 --> 01:26:17,394\r\n- Work!\n- An fie Arbeit.!\r\n\r\n1086\r\n01:26:31,052 --> 01:26:32,542\r\nWhat are you making?\r\n\r\n1087\r\n01:26:32,921 --> 01:26:35,355\r\nHinges, sir.\r\n\r\n1088\r\n01:26:38,226 --> 01:26:41,855\r\nJa, I've got some workers\ncoming in tomorrow.\nWhere are they from again?\r\n\r\n1089\r\n01:26:41,930 --> 01:26:44,330\r\nYugoslavia,\nHerr Kommanfant.\r\n\r\n1090\r\n01:26:44,399 --> 01:26:46,629\r\nI've got to make room.\r\n\r\n1091\r\n01:26:49,103 --> 01:26:52,368\r\nMake me a hinge.\nYes, sir.\r\n\r\n1092\r\n01:26:57,712 --> 01:27:00,647\r\n[Guarfs Muttering]\r\n\r\n1093\r\n01:27:01,305 --> 01:27:07,764\r\nBest watched using Open Subtitles MKV Player\r\n\r\n","markerStore":{"nextMarkerId":2546,"markersById":{"0":{"range":{"start":{"row":2301,"column":0},"end":{"row":2301,"column":9}},"properties":{"type":"selection","editorId":84,"goalScreenRange":null},"reversed":false,"tailed":true,"valid":true,"invalidate":"never","maintainHistory":true}},"version":2},"history":{"version":3,"nextCheckpointId":1,"undoStack":[],"redoStack":[]},"encoding":"utf8","filePath":"/Users/joegesualdo/.Trash/Schindler's List (1993).en.srt 2.10.45 PM","digestWhenLastPersisted":"d7d1607897e08265c49a72abc6cff908095c24cb","preferredLineEnding":null,"deserializer":"TextBuffer","version":2},{"load":true,"text":"﻿1\r\n00:00:38,833 --> 00:00:42,381\r\nSavree maranun\r\nverabonun verobotay.\r\n\r\n2\r\n00:00:42,381 --> 00:00:45,738\r\nBarooch ata adony\r\nelohaynou melech aholam.\r\n\r\n3\r\n00:00:45,834 --> 00:00:48,519\r\nBorah pree hagafan.\r\n\r\n4\r\n00:00:48,519 --> 00:00:51,972\r\nBarooch ata adony\r\nelohaynou melech aholam.\r\n\r\n5\r\n00:00:52,068 --> 00:00:54,369\r\nAsher kideshano bemitzvotaiv...\r\n\r\n6\r\n00:00:54,466 --> 00:00:56,768\r\nverazha banou veshabat kodsho...\r\n\r\n7\r\n00:00:56,768 --> 00:00:58,877\r\nbehava hencheel lanoe.\r\n\r\n8\r\n00:00:58,877 --> 00:01:02,330\r\nZecaron lemase berashit\r\nke hoe yome...\r\n\r\n9\r\n00:01:02,425 --> 00:01:05,303\r\ntechelah lemekray kodesh...\r\n\r\n10\r\n00:01:05,399 --> 00:01:08,372\r\nzecher letziat mizraim.\r\n\r\n11\r\n00:01:08,468 --> 00:01:11,729\r\nKee banoe bacharta\r\nveotano kedashta mekol hameem.\r\n\r\n12\r\n00:01:11,729 --> 00:01:14,318\r\nVeshabat kodsho\r\nbehavat razone.\r\n\r\n13\r\n00:01:14,414 --> 00:01:15,949\r\nHenchaltanoe.\r\n\r\n14\r\n00:01:16,045 --> 00:01:22,087\r\nBarooch ata adony mekadesh\r\nhasabat.\r\n\r\n15\r\n00:02:15,411 --> 00:02:18,672\r\n- Name?\r\n- Horowitz, Salomon.\r\n\r\n16\r\n00:02:22,796 --> 00:02:25,769\r\nSchneider, Sarah.\r\nBirnbaum, Olga?\r\n\r\n17\r\n00:02:28,838 --> 00:02:31,906\r\nOver there.\r\nOver there!\r\nKommen Sie Doch.\r\n\r\n18\r\n00:02:32,003 --> 00:02:36,127\r\n- Isak Hudes.\r\n- Hudes, Isak.\r\n\r\n19\r\n00:02:36,222 --> 00:02:38,045\r\nZucker, Helena.\r\n\r\n20\r\n00:02:38,140 --> 00:02:40,826\r\nZucker, Helena.\r\n\r\n21\r\n00:02:40,921 --> 00:02:43,703\r\nHirsch, Salomon?\r\nMandel, Maria. Hirsch,\r\nSalomon.\r\n\r\n22\r\n00:02:43,799 --> 00:02:47,155\r\n- Hauptman, Chaim!\r\n- Weisman! Weisman, Marcus!\r\n\r\n23\r\n00:02:47,252 --> 00:02:50,033\r\n- Feber, Ludwig!\r\n- Feber, Ludwig.\r\n\r\n24\r\n00:02:50,128 --> 00:02:53,102\r\nElsa Bauman.\r\n\r\n25\r\n00:02:53,102 --> 00:02:55,500\r\n- Josef Klein.\r\n- Klein.\r\n\r\n26\r\n00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:59,335\r\n- Davidowich, Ignacy.\r\n- Paula Biffer.\r\n- Nadel, Rachela.\r\n\r\n27\r\n00:02:59,432 --> 00:03:01,926\r\nSteiner, Gertruda.\r\nSteiner, Hilda.\r\n\r\n28\r\n00:04:56,246 --> 00:05:00,178\r\nJerzy,\r\nyou know who that man is?\r\nI don't know.\r\n\r\n29\r\n00:05:16,674 --> 00:05:19,647\r\nLet's get together,\r\nplease.\r\n\r\n30\r\n00:05:19,743 --> 00:05:22,428\r\nSmile. Good.\r\n\r\n31\r\n00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:53,981\r\nYes, sir.\r\n\r\n32\r\n00:05:54,078 --> 00:05:57,531\r\nBring them over\r\na round of drinks.\r\n\r\n33\r\n00:05:57,626 --> 00:06:02,806\r\nVery good, sir.\r\nAnd who shall I say\r\nth-they are from?\r\n\r\n34\r\n00:06:02,901 --> 00:06:05,779\r\nYou can say\r\nthey are from me.\r\n\r\n35\r\n00:06:25,152 --> 00:06:28,892\r\nFrom the gentleman.\r\nWhere?\r\n\r\n36\r\n00:06:33,783 --> 00:06:36,756\r\nDo you know him?\r\n\r\n37\r\n00:06:36,756 --> 00:06:39,154\r\nFind out who he is.\r\n\r\n38\r\n00:06:39,154 --> 00:06:40,975\r\nYes, sir.\r\n\r\n39\r\n00:06:43,758 --> 00:06:46,059\r\nAgnieszka, I would\r\ngive anything...\r\n\r\n40\r\n00:06:46,155 --> 00:06:48,169\r\nto hear you\r\nsing tonight.\r\n\r\n41\r\n00:06:48,169 --> 00:06:50,471\r\nBut I know you won't.\r\n\r\n42\r\n00:06:51,909 --> 00:06:54,595\r\nYou embarrass me.\r\n\r\n43\r\n00:07:02,747 --> 00:07:04,761\r\nWhat's he doing?\r\n\r\n44\r\n00:07:07,063 --> 00:07:08,980\r\nStay here.\r\n\r\n45\r\n00:07:12,338 --> 00:07:14,255\r\nHow are you doing?\r\n\r\n46\r\n00:07:14,255 --> 00:07:18,379\r\nYou'd leave a woman\r\nalone at the table\r\nin a place like this?\r\n\r\n47\r\n00:07:18,475 --> 00:07:21,257\r\nSweetheart,\r\nyou're the picture\r\nof loneliness.\r\n\r\n48\r\n00:07:21,257 --> 00:07:23,175\r\nOh.\r\n\r\n49\r\n00:07:23,270 --> 00:07:26,531\r\nMmm, what a lovely\r\nfragrance. You are\r\nbreaking my heart.\r\n\r\n50\r\n00:07:26,628 --> 00:07:29,121\r\nAn extra chair, please.\r\nVodka for my friend.\r\n\r\n51\r\n00:07:29,217 --> 00:07:31,615\r\nAnd for the lady?\r\nPernod.\r\n\r\n52\r\n00:07:41,684 --> 00:07:44,370\r\nCome to the table, girls!\r\nDrink with us!\r\n\r\n53\r\n00:07:50,220 --> 00:07:52,714\r\nCome to us!\r\nMarry us!\r\n\r\n54\r\n00:08:09,594 --> 00:08:12,950\r\nThank you.\r\nI'll tell you what\r\nI mean by cooperative.\r\n\r\n55\r\n00:08:13,047 --> 00:08:16,307\r\nTwo days after the law\r\nis passed that allJews\r\nhave to wear the star,\r\n\r\n56\r\n00:08:16,307 --> 00:08:18,417\r\ntheJewish tailors\r\nare turning them out\r\nby the gross...\r\n\r\n57\r\n00:08:18,513 --> 00:08:20,814\r\nin a variety of fabrics\r\nat three zloty each.\r\n\r\n58\r\n00:08:20,911 --> 00:08:22,733\r\nTell me about\r\nyour cellar wines.\r\n\r\n59\r\n00:08:22,829 --> 00:08:26,186\r\nI have an excellent\r\nGerman Riesling. 1937.\r\nMmm, French.\r\n\r\n60\r\n00:08:26,281 --> 00:08:28,870\r\nA Bordeaux.\r\nChateau Latour, '28, '29?\r\nNo, I'm sorry.\r\n\r\n61\r\n00:08:28,967 --> 00:08:31,269\r\nIt's as if they have no idea\r\nwhat kind of law it is.\r\n\r\n62\r\n00:08:31,364 --> 00:08:34,242\r\nAs if it's the emblem\r\nof a riding club.\r\n\r\n63\r\n00:08:34,337 --> 00:08:36,352\r\nA Margaux, '29?\r\nNo, no,\r\nwe don't have that.\r\n\r\n64\r\n00:08:36,447 --> 00:08:38,653\r\nBurgundy then?\r\nA Romanee-Conti, '37?\r\nYes.\r\n\r\n65\r\n00:08:38,749 --> 00:08:41,530\r\nIt's human nature.\r\n\"We'll do this to avoid that.\"\r\n\r\n66\r\n00:08:41,627 --> 00:08:43,736\r\nThat's what they have done\r\nsince thousands of years.\r\n\r\n67\r\n00:08:43,736 --> 00:08:45,943\r\nIt's what they do.\r\nThey weather the storm.\r\n\r\n68\r\n00:08:46,038 --> 00:08:49,875\r\nBut this storm is different.\r\nThis is not the Romans.\r\nThis storm is the SS.\r\n\r\n69\r\n00:09:19,606 --> 00:09:21,620\r\nMartin?\r\n\r\n70\r\n00:09:21,715 --> 00:09:23,730\r\nYes, sir.\r\n\r\n71\r\n00:09:23,730 --> 00:09:25,647\r\nWho is that man?\r\n\r\n72\r\n00:09:25,647 --> 00:09:29,771\r\nThat--\r\nThat's Oskar Schindler!\r\n\r\n73\r\n00:09:42,527 --> 00:09:45,500\r\nTo Krakow!\r\n\r\n74\r\n00:10:21,177 --> 00:10:23,096\r\nAn alleJuden!\r\n\r\n75\r\n00:10:23,096 --> 00:10:26,836\r\nAb sofort ist es allen Juden\r\nuntersagt...\r\n\r\n76\r\n00:10:26,931 --> 00:10:30,863\r\nFleisch aufkoscher Art\r\nzuzubereiten.\r\n\r\n77\r\n00:10:30,960 --> 00:10:34,125\r\nMeldung an alleJuden.\r\nAb sofort--\r\n\r\n78\r\n00:10:52,922 --> 00:10:54,841\r\nRabbi--\r\nPrivate property\r\ncannot be confiscated.\r\n\r\n79\r\n00:10:54,936 --> 00:10:56,759\r\nHow long are the schools\r\ngoing to be closed?\r\nI do not know.\r\n\r\n80\r\n00:10:56,854 --> 00:11:00,019\r\nPillage\r\nis formally prohibited.\r\nYou don't know anything!\r\n\r\n81\r\n00:11:00,019 --> 00:11:01,937\r\nI am familiar with\r\nthe Hague Convention.\r\nReligious--\r\n\r\n82\r\n00:11:01,937 --> 00:11:06,061\r\nThey come into our house\r\nand tell us we don't\r\nlive there anymore.\r\n\r\n83\r\n00:11:06,158 --> 00:11:08,939\r\nIt now belongs\r\nto a certain SS officer.\r\n\r\n84\r\n00:11:08,939 --> 00:11:11,049\r\nPlease. I only know\r\nwhat they tell me.\r\n\r\n85\r\n00:11:11,049 --> 00:11:14,214\r\nAnd what they tell me\r\nchanges from day to day.\r\n\r\n86\r\n00:11:14,309 --> 00:11:17,283\r\nAren't you supposed\r\nto be able to help?\r\n\r\n87\r\n00:11:17,379 --> 00:11:20,351\r\nI mean, what if I just\r\ntook this thing off?\r\n\r\n88\r\n00:11:20,351 --> 00:11:23,037\r\nWhat are they going\r\nto do about it?\r\nThey will shoot you.\r\n\r\n89\r\n00:11:23,133 --> 00:11:27,066\r\nWhy don't you stop\r\nthis silly talk?\r\nItzhak Stern!\r\n\r\n90\r\n00:11:27,066 --> 00:11:30,230\r\nI'm looking\r\nfor Itzhak Stern.\r\n\r\n91\r\n00:11:31,956 --> 00:11:34,833\r\nAre you Itzhak Stern\r\nor not?\r\n\r\n92\r\n00:11:34,833 --> 00:11:37,806\r\nI am.\r\nWhere can we talk?\r\n\r\n93\r\n00:11:47,013 --> 00:11:50,850\r\nThere's a company\r\nyou did the books for\r\non Lipowa Street.\r\n\r\n94\r\n00:11:50,850 --> 00:11:53,247\r\nMade what?\r\nPots and pans?\r\n\r\n95\r\n00:11:53,247 --> 00:11:56,220\r\nBy law, I have to tell you,\r\nsir, I'm a Jew.\r\n\r\n96\r\n00:11:56,317 --> 00:12:00,057\r\nWell, I'm a German.\r\nSo there we are.\r\n\r\n97\r\n00:12:02,743 --> 00:12:06,291\r\nA good company,\r\nyou think?\r\nModestly successful.\r\n\r\n98\r\n00:12:06,387 --> 00:12:08,880\r\nI know nothing\r\nabout enamelware.\r\nDo you?\r\n\r\n99\r\n00:12:08,977 --> 00:12:11,278\r\nI was just\r\nthe accountant.\r\n\r\n100\r\n00:12:11,374 --> 00:12:13,676\r\nSimple engineering though,\r\nwouldn't you think?\r\n\r\n101\r\n00:12:13,772 --> 00:12:15,018\r\nChange the machines around,\r\nwhatever you do,\r\n\r\n102\r\n00:12:15,018 --> 00:12:17,416\r\nyou could make other\r\nthings, couldn't you?\r\n\r\n103\r\n00:12:17,416 --> 00:12:21,828\r\nField kits, mess kits.\r\nArmy contracts.\r\n\r\n104\r\n00:12:23,554 --> 00:12:26,335\r\nOnce the war ends,\r\nforget it, but for now\r\nit's great.\r\n\r\n105\r\n00:12:26,432 --> 00:12:28,541\r\nYou can make a fortune,\r\ndon't you think?\r\n\r\n106\r\n00:12:28,541 --> 00:12:31,802\r\nI think most people right now\r\nhave other priorities.\r\n\r\n107\r\n00:12:31,898 --> 00:12:34,679\r\nLike what?\r\n\r\n108\r\n00:12:34,775 --> 00:12:37,077\r\nI'm sure you'll do just fine\r\nonce you get the contracts.\r\n\r\n109\r\n00:12:37,172 --> 00:12:39,187\r\nIn fact, the worse things get,\r\nthe better you'll do.\r\n\r\n110\r\n00:12:39,187 --> 00:12:42,544\r\nOh, well, I can get\r\nthe signatures I need.\r\nThat's the easy part.\r\n\r\n111\r\n00:12:42,639 --> 00:12:46,188\r\nFinding the money\r\nto buy the company,\r\nthat's hard.\r\n\r\n112\r\n00:12:46,284 --> 00:12:48,106\r\nYou don't have\r\nany money?\r\n\r\n113\r\n00:12:48,202 --> 00:12:52,134\r\nNot that kind of money.\r\nYou know anybody?\r\n\r\n114\r\n00:12:52,230 --> 00:12:55,012\r\nJews, yeah.\r\n\r\n115\r\n00:12:55,107 --> 00:12:57,888\r\nInvestors. You must\r\nhave contacts...\r\n\r\n116\r\n00:12:57,985 --> 00:12:59,807\r\nin theJewish\r\nbusiness community\r\nworking here.\r\n\r\n117\r\n00:12:59,903 --> 00:13:02,588\r\nWhat community?\r\nJews can no longer\r\nown businesses.\r\n\r\n118\r\n00:13:02,588 --> 00:13:05,562\r\nThat's why this one's\r\nin receivership.\r\nBut they\r\n\r\n119\r\n00:13:05,657 --> 00:13:08,343\r\nI'd own it.\r\nI'd pay them back in\r\nproduct-- pots and pans.\r\n\r\n120\r\n00:13:08,343 --> 00:13:11,219\r\nPots and pans.\r\nSomething\r\nthey can use.\r\n\r\n121\r\n00:13:11,219 --> 00:13:13,138\r\nSomething they can\r\nfeel in their hands.\r\n\r\n122\r\n00:13:13,138 --> 00:13:15,343\r\nThey can trade it\r\non the black market,\r\ndo whatever they want.\r\n\r\n123\r\n00:13:15,440 --> 00:13:17,742\r\nEverybody's happy.\r\n\r\n124\r\n00:13:19,276 --> 00:13:22,057\r\nIf you want, you could\r\nrun the company for me.\r\n\r\n125\r\n00:13:25,798 --> 00:13:28,100\r\nLet me understand.\r\n\r\n126\r\n00:13:28,195 --> 00:13:30,881\r\nThey'd put up all the money,\r\nI'd do all the work.\r\n\r\n127\r\n00:13:30,881 --> 00:13:34,045\r\nWhat, if you don't mind\r\nmy asking, would you do?\r\n\r\n128\r\n00:13:34,141 --> 00:13:36,443\r\nI'd make sure it's known\r\nthe company's in business.\r\n\r\n129\r\n00:13:36,443 --> 00:13:38,648\r\nI'd see that it had\r\na certain panache.\r\n\r\n130\r\n00:13:38,745 --> 00:13:42,390\r\nThat's what I'm good at,\r\nnot the work. Not the work.\r\n\r\n131\r\n00:13:42,390 --> 00:13:44,787\r\nThe presentation.\r\n\r\n132\r\n00:14:02,147 --> 00:14:06,269\r\nI'm sure I don't know anybody\r\nwho'll be interested in this.\r\n\r\n133\r\n00:14:07,420 --> 00:14:10,490\r\nWell, they should be,\r\nItzhak Stern.\r\n\r\n134\r\n00:14:10,586 --> 00:14:14,230\r\nTell them they should be.\r\n\r\n135\r\n00:14:23,053 --> 00:14:25,739\r\nAchtung! Achtung!\r\n\r\n136\r\n00:14:25,834 --> 00:14:31,493\r\nAn alleJuden...\r\nAb sofort ist es verboten--\r\n\r\n137\r\n00:14:31,589 --> 00:14:36,001\r\nVere dignum et justum est,\r\naequum et salutare,\r\n\r\n138\r\n00:14:36,001 --> 00:14:40,316\r\nnos tibi semper et\r\nubique gratias agere,\r\n\r\n139\r\n00:14:40,413 --> 00:14:43,578\r\nDomine Sancte, Pater Omnipotens,\r\nAeterne Deus.\r\n\r\n140\r\n00:14:43,674 --> 00:14:47,031\r\nI've got a client\r\nwho'll sell marks\r\nfor zloty at 2.45 to 1.\r\n\r\n141\r\n00:14:47,126 --> 00:14:49,333\r\nWool, mink collar.\r\nIt's a nice coat.\r\n\r\n142\r\n00:14:49,333 --> 00:14:51,250\r\nShe'll trade it\r\nfor ration coupons.\r\n\r\n143\r\n00:14:51,250 --> 00:14:54,606\r\nWicks, for lamps.\r\nYou have a truckload\r\nof wicks?\r\n\r\n144\r\n00:14:54,606 --> 00:14:58,635\r\nWhat am I going to do\r\nwith a truckload of wicks?\r\nNine by 12, nine by 14.\r\n\r\n145\r\n00:14:58,730 --> 00:15:01,608\r\nI don't know.\r\nBig, beautiful, Persian.\r\n\r\n146\r\n00:15:01,704 --> 00:15:04,485\r\nLumen aeternum mundo effudit--\r\n\r\n147\r\n00:15:04,581 --> 00:15:06,883\r\nPsst.\r\nWhat?\r\n\r\n148\r\n00:15:06,979 --> 00:15:08,801\r\nYou don't recognize this?\r\nIt's shoe polish.\r\n\r\n149\r\n00:15:08,897 --> 00:15:11,199\r\nIn metal containers?\r\nYou asked\r\nfor shoe polish.\r\n\r\n150\r\n00:15:11,295 --> 00:15:13,501\r\nIn metal containers.\r\nThis is glass.\r\nIn metal containers.\r\n\r\n151\r\n00:15:13,501 --> 00:15:15,419\r\nIt's not what I asked for.\r\nWhat's\r\nthe difference?\r\n\r\n152\r\n00:15:15,419 --> 00:15:17,336\r\nWhat's the difference?\r\nWhat's the difference?\r\n\r\n153\r\n00:15:17,336 --> 00:15:19,351\r\nShh!\r\nMy client sold it\r\n\r\n154\r\n00:15:19,446 --> 00:15:21,269\r\nwho sold it\r\nto the German Army.\r\n\r\n155\r\n00:15:21,461 --> 00:15:25,585\r\nOnly by the time it got there,\r\nbecause of the freezing cold,\r\nit broke. All 10,000 units.\r\n\r\n156\r\n00:15:25,585 --> 00:15:27,791\r\nMmm,\r\nooh, ooh, ooh.\r\nThis is not my problem.\r\n\r\n157\r\n00:15:27,886 --> 00:15:29,804\r\nThis is not\r\nhis problem.\r\nThis is not your problem?\r\n\r\n158\r\n00:15:29,804 --> 00:15:32,298\r\nThis is not\r\nmy problem.\r\nAll right.\r\n\r\n159\r\n00:15:32,394 --> 00:15:36,134\r\nThe German Army\r\nwants to find out\r\nwhere it came from.\r\n\r\n160\r\n00:15:36,230 --> 00:15:39,492\r\nI am going to make sure\r\nthey find out.\r\nNow it's your problem.\r\n\r\n161\r\n00:15:39,492 --> 00:15:42,560\r\nYou be quiet!\r\n\r\n162\r\n00:15:42,656 --> 00:15:45,246\r\nMetal\r\ncontainers.\r\n\r\n163\r\n00:15:45,342 --> 00:15:48,027\r\nHello.\r\n\r\n164\r\n00:15:48,027 --> 00:15:51,959\r\nPardon me for interfering,\r\nbut that's a nice shirt.\r\n\r\n165\r\n00:15:51,959 --> 00:15:54,261\r\nNice shirt.\r\n\r\n166\r\n00:15:54,261 --> 00:15:57,425\r\nDo you know where\r\nI can find a nice\r\nshirt like that?\r\n\r\n167\r\n00:15:59,344 --> 00:16:03,180\r\n...laudare, benedicere\r\net predicare.\r\n\r\n168\r\n00:16:04,906 --> 00:16:06,729\r\nLike this?\r\n\r\n169\r\n00:16:06,824 --> 00:16:09,702\r\nIt's illegal to buy or sell\r\nanything on the street.\r\n\r\n170\r\n00:16:09,797 --> 00:16:12,963\r\nWe don't do that.\r\nWe're here to pray.\r\n\r\n171\r\n00:16:14,977 --> 00:16:17,566\r\nJesum Christum Dominum Nostrum--\r\n\r\n172\r\n00:16:17,662 --> 00:16:22,362\r\nDo you have any idea how much\r\na shirt like this costs?\r\nNice things cost money.\r\n\r\n173\r\n00:16:22,362 --> 00:16:26,486\r\n...adorant Dominationes,\r\ntremunt Potestates.\r\n\r\n174\r\n00:16:26,581 --> 00:16:31,761\r\nCoeli coelorumque\r\nvirtutes ac Beata Seraphim...\r\n\r\n175\r\n00:16:31,856 --> 00:16:34,925\r\nsocia exultatione\r\nconcelebrant--\r\n\r\n176\r\n00:16:35,021 --> 00:16:37,323\r\nHow many?\r\n\r\n177\r\n00:16:37,418 --> 00:16:41,160\r\nI'm going to need\r\nsome other things, too,\r\nas things come up.\r\n\r\n178\r\n00:16:41,255 --> 00:16:45,283\r\nThis won't be\r\na problem.\r\nFrom time to time.\r\n\r\n179\r\n00:16:45,571 --> 00:16:48,256\r\nAchtung! Achtung!\r\n\r\n180\r\n00:17:28,249 --> 00:17:31,510\r\n- Name? Adresse?\r\n- Formular ausfuellen!\r\n\r\n181\r\n00:17:31,510 --> 00:17:33,908\r\nWeiter, weiter!\r\nNicht draengeln!\r\n\r\n182\r\n00:17:34,003 --> 00:17:36,497\r\nKommen Sie hierher!\r\nStellen Sie sich doch an!\r\n\r\n183\r\n00:18:21,765 --> 00:18:24,929\r\nAchtung, achtung!\r\nAlleJuden sind verpflichtet...\r\n\r\n184\r\n00:18:25,026 --> 00:18:28,574\r\nim abgesonderten\r\njuedischen Bezirk zu wohnen.\r\n\r\n185\r\n00:18:28,671 --> 00:18:32,603\r\nNichteinhaltung der Meldepflicht\r\nbei der Einwohnerbehoerde...\r\n\r\n186\r\n00:18:32,698 --> 00:18:35,479\r\nverstoesst gegen das Edikt 44l91\r\nund fuehrt zur Anzeige...\r\n\r\n187\r\n00:18:35,576 --> 00:18:37,110\r\nbeim Militaergericht.\r\n\r\n188\r\n00:18:39,124 --> 00:18:42,769\r\nThis is obviously the right\r\nplace. How are you doing?\r\nHerr Schindler.\r\n\r\n189\r\n00:18:46,893 --> 00:18:50,825\r\nGood-bye, Jews!\r\nGood-bye, Jews!\r\n\r\n190\r\n00:18:50,920 --> 00:18:54,757\r\nGood-bye, Jews!\r\nGood-bye, Jews!\r\n\r\n191\r\n00:18:56,100 --> 00:18:58,881\r\nGood-bye, Jews!\r\n\r\n192\r\n00:18:58,881 --> 00:19:03,484\r\nGood-bye, Jews!\r\nGood-bye, Jews!\r\n\r\n193\r\n00:19:06,745 --> 00:19:09,334\r\nThis iz the vechteka,\r\nMoyshe.\r\nOjciec.\r\n\r\n194\r\n00:19:09,334 --> 00:19:12,307\r\nNyne, this kan\r\nneash zyane.\r\n\r\n195\r\n00:19:21,898 --> 00:19:25,543\r\nOh, my God.\r\n\r\n196\r\n00:19:25,639 --> 00:19:28,899\r\nOy, God.\r\nOh, my God.\r\n\r\n197\r\n00:19:35,517 --> 00:19:38,203\r\nOh, my God.\r\n\r\n198\r\n00:19:43,765 --> 00:19:46,067\r\nIt could not be better.\r\n\r\n199\r\n00:19:46,162 --> 00:19:49,712\r\nIt could be worse.\r\nHow? Tell me.\r\n\r\n200\r\n00:19:49,807 --> 00:19:52,588\r\nHow on earth could it\r\npossibly be worse?\r\n\r\n201\r\n00:19:54,602 --> 00:19:57,192\r\nDzien dobry.\r\n\r\n202\r\n00:19:57,192 --> 00:19:59,493\r\nDzien dobry.\r\nDzien dobry.\r\n\r\n203\r\n00:19:59,590 --> 00:20:01,316\r\nDzien dobry.\r\n\r\n204\r\n00:20:01,316 --> 00:20:03,714\r\nDzien dobry.\r\nDzien dobry.\r\n\r\n205\r\n00:20:06,591 --> 00:20:08,892\r\nHey, Goldberg.\r\nPoldek.\r\n\r\n206\r\n00:20:08,989 --> 00:20:13,113\r\nWhat's this?\r\nUh, the Judenrat has\r\nits own police now.\r\n\r\n207\r\n00:20:13,209 --> 00:20:15,894\r\nYou don't say.\r\nOrdnungsdienst.\r\n\r\n208\r\n00:20:15,990 --> 00:20:18,387\r\nI'm a policeman now,\r\ncould you believe it?\r\nIt's hard to believe.\r\n\r\n209\r\n00:20:18,483 --> 00:20:20,401\r\nOh, no,\r\nit's not hard\r\nto believe.\r\n\r\n210\r\n00:20:20,401 --> 00:20:22,800\r\nIt's a good racket, Poldek.\r\nThe only racket here.\r\n\r\n211\r\n00:20:22,800 --> 00:20:26,156\r\nLook, maybe I could\r\nput in a good word for you\r\nwith my superiors.\r\n\r\n212\r\n00:20:26,156 --> 00:20:30,280\r\nYour superiors?\r\nCome on, they are not\r\nas bad as everyone says.\r\n\r\n213\r\n00:20:30,376 --> 00:20:33,445\r\nWell, they're worse\r\nthan everyone says,\r\nbut it's a lot of money.\r\n\r\n214\r\n00:20:33,540 --> 00:20:36,034\r\nA lot of money.\r\n\r\n215\r\n00:20:36,131 --> 00:20:38,720\r\nGive me my\r\nhousing assignment.\r\n\r\n216\r\n00:20:38,815 --> 00:20:43,036\r\nCome on.\r\nYou look funny\r\nin that hat, Goldberg.\r\n\r\n217\r\n00:20:43,131 --> 00:20:46,392\r\nYou look like a clown,\r\nyou know?\r\n\r\n218\r\n00:20:51,187 --> 00:20:53,489\r\nHe's a very important man.\r\n\r\n219\r\n00:20:53,489 --> 00:20:55,215\r\nJust give him\r\ntwo minutes of your time.\r\n\r\n220\r\n00:20:55,312 --> 00:20:58,572\r\nSince when did time cost money?\r\nJust sit down and listen.\r\n\r\n221\r\n00:20:58,668 --> 00:21:00,778\r\nPlease.\r\nSir?\r\n\r\n222\r\n00:21:04,327 --> 00:21:06,341\r\nFor each thousand you invest,\r\nI will repay you with...\r\n\r\n223\r\n00:21:06,341 --> 00:21:08,451\r\nTwo hundred.\r\n200 kilos\r\nof enamelware a month,\r\n\r\n224\r\n00:21:08,546 --> 00:21:10,368\r\nto begin in July\r\nand to continue\r\nfor one year.\r\n\r\n225\r\n00:21:10,465 --> 00:21:14,110\r\nAfter which time, we're even.\r\nThat's it. It's very simple.\r\n\r\n226\r\n00:21:14,110 --> 00:21:16,986\r\nNot good enough.\r\nIt's not\r\ngood enough.\r\n\r\n227\r\n00:21:16,986 --> 00:21:19,193\r\nNot good enough?\r\n\r\n228\r\n00:21:19,288 --> 00:21:23,220\r\nLook where you're living.\r\nLook where you've been put.\r\n\"Not good enough.\"\r\n\r\n229\r\n00:21:23,317 --> 00:21:25,714\r\nA couple of months ago you'd\r\nbe right, not anymore.\r\n\r\n230\r\n00:21:25,809 --> 00:21:28,782\r\nMoney's still money.\r\n\r\n231\r\n00:21:30,317 --> 00:21:32,524\r\nNo, it is not.\r\n\r\n232\r\n00:21:32,524 --> 00:21:34,537\r\nThat's why we're here.\r\n\r\n233\r\n00:21:34,633 --> 00:21:36,551\r\nTrade goods--\r\nthat's the only currency...\r\n\r\n234\r\n00:21:36,551 --> 00:21:38,469\r\nthat'll be worth\r\nanything in the ghetto.\r\n\r\n235\r\n00:21:38,469 --> 00:21:41,731\r\nThings have changed,\r\nmy friend.\r\n\r\n236\r\n00:21:42,498 --> 00:21:44,799\r\nDid I call\r\nthis meeting?\r\n\r\n237\r\n00:21:44,895 --> 00:21:47,196\r\nYou told Mr. Stern\r\nyou wanted to speak to me.\r\n\r\n238\r\n00:21:47,293 --> 00:21:49,787\r\nI'm here.\r\nI've made you a fair offer.\r\n\r\n239\r\n00:21:49,787 --> 00:21:53,622\r\nFair would be\r\na percentage in the company.\r\n\r\n240\r\n00:21:53,719 --> 00:21:56,787\r\nForget the whole thing.\r\n\r\n241\r\n00:21:56,883 --> 00:21:59,089\r\nGet out.\r\n\r\n242\r\n00:22:03,118 --> 00:22:06,090\r\nHow do we know that you\r\nwill do what you say?\r\n\r\n243\r\n00:22:06,090 --> 00:22:08,009\r\nBecause I said I would.\r\n\r\n244\r\n00:22:08,009 --> 00:22:10,214\r\nYou want a contract?\r\nTo be upheld by what court?\r\n\r\n245\r\n00:22:10,214 --> 00:22:13,092\r\nI said what I'll do.\r\nThat's our contract.\r\n\r\n246\r\n00:22:16,352 --> 00:22:18,462\r\n...mielismy racje.\r\n\r\n247\r\n00:22:29,683 --> 00:22:34,862\r\nPiec, szesc, siedem...\r\n\r\n248\r\n00:22:34,958 --> 00:22:38,411\r\nosiem, dziewiec.\r\n\r\n249\r\n00:22:49,440 --> 00:22:53,564\r\nThe standard SS rate for\r\nJewish skilled labor\r\nis seven marks a day,\r\n\r\n250\r\n00:22:53,564 --> 00:22:56,441\r\nfive for unskilled\r\nand women.\r\n\r\n251\r\n00:22:56,538 --> 00:22:59,414\r\nThis is what you pay\r\nthe Reich Economic Office.\r\n\r\n252\r\n00:22:59,511 --> 00:23:01,908\r\nTheJews themselves\r\nreceive nothing.\r\n\r\n253\r\n00:23:02,003 --> 00:23:06,224\r\nPoles you pay wages.\r\nGenerally, they get\r\na little more.\r\n\r\n254\r\n00:23:06,320 --> 00:23:08,813\r\nAre you\r\nlistening?\r\nWhat was that about the SS?\r\n\r\n255\r\n00:23:08,909 --> 00:23:11,020\r\nThe rate? The what?\r\n\r\n256\r\n00:23:11,115 --> 00:23:14,568\r\nTheJewish worker's salary--\r\nyou pay it directly to\r\nthe SS, not to the worker.\r\n\r\n257\r\n00:23:14,663 --> 00:23:16,677\r\nHe gets nothing.\r\nBut it's less.\r\n\r\n258\r\n00:23:16,677 --> 00:23:18,692\r\nIt's less than what\r\nI would pay a Pole.\r\nIt's less.\r\n\r\n259\r\n00:23:18,787 --> 00:23:21,568\r\nThat's the point\r\nI'm trying to make.\r\n\r\n260\r\n00:23:21,665 --> 00:23:24,159\r\nPoles cost more.\r\n\r\n261\r\n00:23:24,254 --> 00:23:28,666\r\nWhy should I hire Poles?\r\n\r\n262\r\n00:23:28,762 --> 00:23:32,502\r\nAn enamelware factory\r\nover at, uh, Lipowa Street.\r\n\r\n263\r\n00:23:32,598 --> 00:23:35,379\r\nIt, uh, it, um--\r\nIt's owned by a German.\r\n\r\n264\r\n00:23:35,475 --> 00:23:38,449\r\nBut it's outside\r\nthe ghetto, so you can\r\nbarter for extra goods--\r\n\r\n265\r\n00:23:38,449 --> 00:23:40,654\r\nfor eggs, I don't know\r\nwhat you need--\r\n\r\n266\r\n00:23:40,750 --> 00:23:42,765\r\nwith the Polish workers.\r\nYou can't get it here.\r\n\r\n267\r\n00:23:42,765 --> 00:23:46,888\r\nAlso, he's asking for ten\r\nhealthy women for the--\r\nI am healthy.\r\n\r\n268\r\n00:23:46,984 --> 00:23:49,861\r\nBring your sister, okay?\r\n\r\n269\r\n00:23:53,985 --> 00:23:56,287\r\nChodz.\r\n\r\n270\r\n00:23:56,383 --> 00:23:59,644\r\nYou need to convince them\r\nyou have a trade, something\r\nvaluable to the war effort.\r\n\r\n271\r\n00:23:59,739 --> 00:24:01,849\r\nLike what?\r\nWhat if you don't?\r\nI'm a musician.\r\n\r\n272\r\n00:24:01,946 --> 00:24:05,398\r\nYour name goes\r\non a list.\r\nAnd they put you on trucks--\r\n\r\n273\r\n00:24:05,494 --> 00:24:07,508\r\nNo, no, no,\r\nthat's not true.\r\nYou're a musician?\r\n\r\n274\r\n00:24:07,603 --> 00:24:10,002\r\nYeah.\r\nI'd fid a good\r\nhiding place if I were you.\r\n\r\n275\r\n00:24:10,097 --> 00:24:14,413\r\nI'm not going to hide\r\nlike some animal.\r\nThere are places to hide.\r\n\r\n276\r\n00:24:18,825 --> 00:24:20,647\r\nDer Naechste!\r\n\r\n277\r\n00:24:20,744 --> 00:24:24,004\r\nI'm a graduate\r\nof the University of Lwow.\r\n\r\n278\r\n00:24:24,004 --> 00:24:27,170\r\nI used to work at the\r\nhydroelectric station\r\nin Roznow--\r\n\r\n279\r\n00:24:27,265 --> 00:24:29,087\r\nBlauschein.\r\n\r\n280\r\n00:24:32,252 --> 00:24:35,993\r\nI'm gonna get the necessary\r\npapers because this card\r\nis no good anymore.\r\n\r\n281\r\n00:24:36,088 --> 00:24:38,390\r\nYou can stay in this line\r\nall day, you'll still get\r\none of these.\r\n\r\n282\r\n00:24:38,486 --> 00:24:42,034\r\nThey are no good.\r\nYou'll have to leave\r\nthe line now,\r\n\r\n283\r\n00:24:42,131 --> 00:24:46,542\r\nthen you'll get a blue card,\r\na Blauschein, to say that\r\nyou are an essential worker.\r\n\r\n284\r\n00:24:46,638 --> 00:24:49,611\r\nI'll get these papers\r\nfor you at Pankiewicz.\r\n\r\n285\r\n00:24:49,611 --> 00:24:51,529\r\nPharmacist.\r\nJust there, look.\r\n\r\n286\r\n00:24:51,625 --> 00:24:53,448\r\nGuess who is here?\r\n\r\n287\r\n00:24:53,543 --> 00:24:56,132\r\nPoldek! Enjoying\r\nthe weather, Poldek?\r\n\r\n288\r\n00:24:56,229 --> 00:24:59,106\r\nEnjoying the lines?\r\nNeed some shoe polish?\r\n\r\n289\r\n00:24:59,106 --> 00:25:01,599\r\nIn a metal container\r\nmaybe?\r\n\r\n290\r\n00:25:01,599 --> 00:25:05,915\r\nNot essential?\r\nI think you misunderstand\r\nthe meaning of the word.\r\n\r\n291\r\n00:25:06,011 --> 00:25:08,792\r\nNo Blauschein, sir.\r\nStand over there.\r\n\r\n292\r\n00:25:08,889 --> 00:25:11,573\r\nMove. Next!\r\n\r\n293\r\n00:25:11,670 --> 00:25:13,780\r\nWhat do you mean,\r\n\"Not essential\"?\r\n\r\n294\r\n00:25:13,875 --> 00:25:19,342\r\nI teach history and literature.\r\nSince when is not essential?\r\n\r\n295\r\n00:25:24,425 --> 00:25:26,727\r\nHe's a metal polisher.\r\n\r\n296\r\n00:25:33,344 --> 00:25:36,030\r\nIt was not right?\r\nIt's very good.\r\nHe's 53 years old.\r\n\r\n297\r\n00:25:36,126 --> 00:25:39,099\r\nIt's too new.\r\nMmm.\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\n298\r\n00:25:46,963 --> 00:25:49,361\r\nYou're crazy.\r\nYou left it\r\nin your drawer.\r\n\r\n299\r\n00:25:49,361 --> 00:25:51,566\r\nHow many times\r\nhave I told you?\r\n\r\n300\r\n00:25:51,663 --> 00:25:54,252\r\nYour work certificate\r\nyou keep in your pocket\r\nat all times.\r\n\r\n301\r\n00:25:54,348 --> 00:25:56,170\r\nAnd you leave everything\r\nin your drawer.\r\n\r\n302\r\n00:25:56,267 --> 00:25:58,568\r\nHow many times I've told you?\r\n\r\n303\r\n00:25:58,664 --> 00:26:01,732\r\nI'm a metal polisher.\r\n\r\n304\r\n00:26:10,173 --> 00:26:12,666\r\nTake the round sheet of tin,\r\n\r\n305\r\n00:26:12,762 --> 00:26:16,503\r\ndip it in soap emulsion.\r\n\r\n306\r\n00:26:16,598 --> 00:26:21,489\r\nThen place it centrally\r\nin the press.\r\n\r\n307\r\n00:26:36,068 --> 00:26:39,328\r\nWe obtain the soup pot.\r\nThe soup pot.\r\n\r\n308\r\n00:26:39,424 --> 00:26:42,684\r\nSoup pot.\r\n\r\n309\r\n00:26:42,781 --> 00:26:45,754\r\nGrosz, Mrs. Grosz,\r\nstay together.\r\n\r\n310\r\n00:26:49,878 --> 00:26:54,865\r\nSir, I have ten work permits\r\nhere for the Deutsche\r\nEmailwarenfabrik,\r\n\r\n311\r\n00:26:54,865 --> 00:26:57,646\r\ncosigned by Mr. Bankier\r\nand myself.\r\n\r\n312\r\n00:26:57,646 --> 00:27:02,154\r\nIf it's carbonized,\r\nclean it with a file.\r\n\r\n313\r\n00:27:02,249 --> 00:27:06,853\r\nBut don't touch\r\nboth the electrodes\r\nat the same time.\r\n\r\n314\r\n00:27:06,853 --> 00:27:09,923\r\nYou'll get electrocuted.\r\nHere, have a try.\r\n\r\n315\r\n00:27:14,142 --> 00:27:16,444\r\nRoll the metal\r\nunder the press,\r\n\r\n316\r\n00:27:16,539 --> 00:27:18,841\r\nbut be very careful\r\nunless you want your fingers...\r\n\r\n317\r\n00:27:18,938 --> 00:27:21,623\r\nto become part\r\nof the teapot.\r\n\r\n318\r\n00:27:23,157 --> 00:27:26,706\r\nOccupation?\r\nI'm a writer.\r\nI play the flute.\r\n\r\n319\r\n00:27:26,706 --> 00:27:30,062\r\nBut Moses is\r\na skilled metalworker.\r\n\r\n320\r\n00:27:30,062 --> 00:27:32,269\r\nHe can make tin pots.\r\nHe can make tanks.\r\n\r\n321\r\n00:27:32,364 --> 00:27:34,187\r\nHe can make whatever\r\nMr. Schindler asks.\r\n\r\n322\r\n00:27:34,283 --> 00:27:36,776\r\nHe's highly skilled.\r\nGive him your card.\r\n\r\n323\r\n00:27:36,776 --> 00:27:39,077\r\nMoses, give him your card.\r\n\r\n324\r\n00:27:41,092 --> 00:27:43,298\r\nNow, dip the basin\r\nwith the tongs...\r\n\r\n325\r\n00:27:43,394 --> 00:27:45,792\r\ninto the enamel solution.\r\n\r\n326\r\n00:27:47,805 --> 00:27:52,026\r\nAnd after swiveling it around,\r\ncarefully place it aside\r\nto drip dry.\r\n\r\n327\r\n00:27:54,902 --> 00:27:58,260\r\nAnd whatever he asks you,\r\nallow me just to represent\r\nyou and speak for you.\r\n\r\n328\r\n00:27:58,355 --> 00:28:00,274\r\nDon't say a word.\r\n\r\n329\r\n00:28:00,369 --> 00:28:03,727\r\nFiling, billing, keeping track\r\nof my appointments, shorthand.\r\n\r\n330\r\n00:28:03,727 --> 00:28:07,849\r\nTyping, obviously.\r\nHow is your typing?\r\nUh, all right.\r\n\r\n331\r\n00:28:07,946 --> 00:28:09,768\r\nPlease.\r\n\r\n332\r\n00:29:00,502 --> 00:29:04,052\r\nYou need a secretary.\r\nPick one.\r\n\r\n333\r\n00:29:04,052 --> 00:29:08,846\r\nI don't know how.\r\nThey're all so...\r\nqualified.\r\n\r\n334\r\n00:29:08,846 --> 00:29:11,724\r\nYou have to choose.\r\n\r\n335\r\n00:29:13,930 --> 00:29:16,615\r\nProsze sie ladnie usmiechac.\r\nBig smile.\r\nBig smile.\r\n\r\n336\r\n00:29:16,615 --> 00:29:18,054\r\nUwaga.\r\n\r\n337\r\n00:29:36,756 --> 00:29:39,537\r\nIf you would,\r\nlook after my guest.\r\n\r\n338\r\n00:29:39,632 --> 00:29:44,715\r\nUm, boxed teas are good.\r\nCoffiee, pate, um...\r\n\r\n339\r\n00:29:44,715 --> 00:29:48,744\r\nkielbasa sausage,\r\ncheeses, Beluga caviar.\r\nYes.\r\n\r\n340\r\n00:29:48,839 --> 00:29:50,566\r\nAnd, of course, who could live\r\nwithout German cigarettes?\r\n\r\n341\r\n00:29:50,662 --> 00:29:52,771\r\nGet me as many\r\nas you can fid.\r\n\r\n342\r\n00:29:52,868 --> 00:29:54,882\r\nAnd some more fresh fruit.\r\n\r\n343\r\n00:29:54,978 --> 00:29:57,663\r\nThe real rarities--\r\noranges, lemons, pineapples.\r\n\r\n344\r\n00:29:57,663 --> 00:30:00,348\r\nI need several boxes\r\nof Cuban cigars. The best.\r\nYes.\r\n\r\n345\r\n00:30:00,348 --> 00:30:03,993\r\nAnd dark, unsweetened chocolate.\r\nNot in the shape ofladyfigers,\r\nthe chunk chocolate.\r\n\r\n346\r\n00:30:04,089 --> 00:30:07,061\r\nYes.\r\nBig as my hand,\r\nyou sample at wine tastings.\r\n\r\n347\r\n00:30:07,158 --> 00:30:10,226\r\nWe're going to need lots\r\nof cognac. The best, Hennessy.\r\n\r\n348\r\n00:30:10,323 --> 00:30:15,501\r\nDom Perignon champagne.\r\nUm, get L 'espadon sardines...\r\n\r\n349\r\n00:30:15,598 --> 00:30:18,475\r\nand, oh,\r\ntry to fid nylon stockings.\r\n\r\n350\r\n00:30:20,872 --> 00:30:23,942\r\nIt is my distinct pleasure\r\nto announce...\r\n\r\n351\r\n00:30:24,037 --> 00:30:29,408\r\nthe fully operational status\r\nof Deutsche Email Fabrik...\r\n\r\n352\r\n00:30:29,504 --> 00:30:30,750\r\nPatrzjakies szmaty!\r\n\r\n353\r\n00:30:30,750 --> 00:30:34,107\r\nManufacturers of superior\r\nenamelware crockery...\r\n\r\n354\r\n00:30:34,107 --> 00:30:39,382\r\nexpressly designed\r\nand crafted for military use.\r\n\r\n355\r\n00:30:39,382 --> 00:30:41,972\r\nUtilizing only\r\nthe most modern equipment,\r\n\r\n356\r\n00:30:42,068 --> 00:30:46,959\r\nD.E.F. 's staffi of\r\nhighly-skilled and experienced\r\nartisans andjourneymen...\r\n\r\n357\r\n00:30:46,959 --> 00:30:50,412\r\ndeliver a product\r\nof unparalleled quality,\r\n\r\n358\r\n00:30:50,507 --> 00:30:54,248\r\nenabling me to proffier,\r\nwith absolute confidence\r\nand pride,\r\n\r\n359\r\n00:30:54,344 --> 00:30:56,838\r\na full line\r\nof field and kitchenware...\r\n\r\n360\r\n00:30:56,933 --> 00:31:00,865\r\nunsurpassable in all respects\r\nby my competitors.\r\n\r\n361\r\n00:31:00,962 --> 00:31:03,455\r\nSee attached list\r\nand available colors.\r\n\r\n362\r\n00:31:03,551 --> 00:31:08,154\r\nAnticipating the enclosed bids\r\nwill meet with your approval.\r\n\r\n363\r\n00:31:08,250 --> 00:31:11,894\r\nMade in Havana, Cuba.\r\nLooking forward to a long and\r\nmutually prosperous association.\r\n\r\n364\r\n00:31:11,991 --> 00:31:15,060\r\nLook at this.\r\nI extend to you in advance\r\nmy sincerest gratitude...\r\n\r\n365\r\n00:31:15,155 --> 00:31:17,936\r\nand very best regards.\r\nOskar Schindler.\r\n\r\n366\r\n00:31:18,033 --> 00:31:21,293\r\nYeah, I need 700 gross\r\nfrom here for next Thursday.\r\n\r\n367\r\n00:31:21,389 --> 00:31:24,075\r\nNine hundred--\r\nNo, make it ten\r\nfor Wednesday.\r\n\r\n368\r\n00:31:24,075 --> 00:31:27,815\r\nAll this stuff here goes\r\nto Madritsch's factory\r\non Tuesday of next week.\r\n\r\n369\r\n00:31:42,968 --> 00:31:46,229\r\nMy father was fond of saying,\r\n\"You need three things in life\r\n\r\n370\r\n00:31:46,325 --> 00:31:50,257\r\n\"a good doctor,\r\na forgiving priest...\r\n\r\n371\r\n00:31:50,353 --> 00:31:53,423\r\nand a clever accountant.\"\r\n\r\n372\r\n00:31:56,683 --> 00:32:00,615\r\nThe first two...\r\nI've never had much use for.\r\n\r\n373\r\n00:32:00,711 --> 00:32:03,971\r\nBut the third--\r\n\r\n374\r\n00:32:09,055 --> 00:32:12,411\r\nJust pretend,\r\nfor Christ's sake.\r\n\r\n375\r\n00:32:15,961 --> 00:32:19,029\r\nIs that all?\r\n\r\n376\r\n00:32:23,633 --> 00:32:26,701\r\nI'm trying to thank you.\r\n\r\n377\r\n00:32:26,798 --> 00:32:30,825\r\nI'm saying I couldn't\r\nhave done this without you.\r\n\r\n378\r\n00:32:33,224 --> 00:32:36,005\r\nThe usual thing would be\r\nto acknowledge my gratitude.\r\n\r\n379\r\n00:32:36,100 --> 00:32:40,801\r\nIt would also, by the way,\r\nbe the courteous thing.\r\n\r\n380\r\n00:32:40,801 --> 00:32:43,582\r\nYou're welcome.\r\n\r\n381\r\n00:32:52,117 --> 00:32:54,227\r\nGet out of here.\r\n\r\n382\r\n00:33:07,079 --> 00:33:10,147\r\nKlonowska, who is it?\r\n\r\n383\r\n00:33:19,067 --> 00:33:21,656\r\nShe's so embarrassed.\r\nLook at her.\r\n\r\n384\r\n00:33:33,165 --> 00:33:35,371\r\nYou know something?\r\nYou would like her.\r\n\r\n385\r\n00:33:35,467 --> 00:33:37,289\r\nOskar, please.\r\nWhat?\r\n\r\n386\r\n00:33:37,384 --> 00:33:39,686\r\nI don't have to like her...\r\njust because you do.\r\nYou would, though.\r\n\r\n387\r\n00:33:39,783 --> 00:33:42,467\r\nIt doesn't\r\nwork that way.\r\n\r\n388\r\n00:33:54,648 --> 00:33:57,429\r\nYou've done well here.\r\n\r\n389\r\n00:33:59,732 --> 00:34:02,224\r\nYou look wonderful.\r\n\r\n390\r\n00:34:05,005 --> 00:34:08,363\r\nBe careful\r\nof the step, miss.\r\nMrs. Schindler, Marek.\r\n\r\n391\r\n00:34:20,543 --> 00:34:24,379\r\nIt's not a charade,\r\nall this?\r\nHow could it\r\n\r\n392\r\n00:34:24,379 --> 00:34:26,777\r\nThe clothes, the car,\r\nthe apartment.\r\nWait a minute.\r\n\r\n393\r\n00:34:26,777 --> 00:34:30,613\r\nTake a guess how many\r\npeople are on my payroll.\r\nOskar.\r\n\r\n394\r\n00:34:30,613 --> 00:34:36,176\r\nMy father, at the height\r\nof his success, had 50.\r\nI've got 350.\r\n\r\n395\r\n00:34:36,176 --> 00:34:40,300\r\n350 workers\r\non the factory floor,\r\nwith one purpose.\r\n\r\n396\r\n00:34:40,395 --> 00:34:42,505\r\nTo make pots and pans?\r\n\r\n397\r\n00:34:42,602 --> 00:34:46,437\r\nTo make money.\r\nFor me.\r\n\r\n398\r\n00:34:51,904 --> 00:34:54,974\r\nDoes anyone\r\nask about me?\r\n\r\n399\r\n00:34:56,412 --> 00:34:59,481\r\nBack home?\r\nEverybody.\r\n\r\n400\r\n00:34:59,577 --> 00:35:02,358\r\nAll the time.\r\n\r\n401\r\n00:35:02,454 --> 00:35:05,619\r\nHmm.\r\n\r\n402\r\n00:35:05,619 --> 00:35:10,989\r\nThey won't soon forget\r\nthe name Schindler here,\r\nI can tell you that.\r\n\r\n403\r\n00:35:12,428 --> 00:35:15,498\r\n\"Oskar Schindler,\"\r\nthey'll say.\r\n\r\n404\r\n00:35:15,593 --> 00:35:18,854\r\n\"Everybody\r\nremembers him.\r\n\r\n405\r\n00:35:18,950 --> 00:35:23,170\r\n\"He did something\r\nextraordinary.\r\n\r\n406\r\n00:35:23,265 --> 00:35:28,157\r\n\"He did something\r\nno one else did.\r\n\r\n407\r\n00:35:28,253 --> 00:35:31,418\r\n\"He came here\r\nwith nothing--\r\n\r\n408\r\n00:35:31,513 --> 00:35:34,294\r\n\"a suitcase--\r\n\r\n409\r\n00:35:34,391 --> 00:35:39,761\r\n\"and built a bankrupt\r\ncompany into a major\r\nmanufactory.\r\n\r\n410\r\n00:35:39,761 --> 00:35:43,214\r\n\"And left with\r\na steamer trunk--\r\n\r\n411\r\n00:35:43,311 --> 00:35:47,722\r\n\"Two steamer trunks\r\nfull of money,\r\n\r\n412\r\n00:35:47,818 --> 00:35:51,942\r\nall the riches\r\nof the world.\"\r\n\r\n413\r\n00:35:51,942 --> 00:35:53,859\r\nHmm.\r\n\r\n414\r\n00:35:53,859 --> 00:35:57,025\r\nIt's comforting to see\r\nthat nothing's changed.\r\n\r\n415\r\n00:35:57,121 --> 00:36:00,574\r\nYou're wrong, Emilie.\r\n\r\n416\r\n00:36:00,574 --> 00:36:02,971\r\nThere's no way I could have\r\nknown this before,\r\n\r\n417\r\n00:36:02,971 --> 00:36:06,328\r\nbut there was always\r\nsomething missing.\r\n\r\n418\r\n00:36:06,328 --> 00:36:10,260\r\nIn every business I tried,\r\nI can see now, it wasn't me\r\nthat failed.\r\n\r\n419\r\n00:36:10,356 --> 00:36:13,041\r\nSomething was missing.\r\n\r\n420\r\n00:36:13,041 --> 00:36:16,494\r\nEven if I'd known what it\r\nwas, there's nothing I could\r\nhave done about it...\r\n\r\n421\r\n00:36:16,589 --> 00:36:21,001\r\nbecause you can't\r\ncreate this thing.\r\n\r\n422\r\n00:36:21,098 --> 00:36:26,180\r\nAnd it makes all\r\nthe difference in the world\r\nbetween success and failure.\r\n\r\n423\r\n00:36:26,180 --> 00:36:28,674\r\nLuck?\r\n\r\n424\r\n00:36:30,976 --> 00:36:33,757\r\nWar.\r\n\r\n425\r\n00:36:56,295 --> 00:36:59,843\r\nShould I stay?\r\n\r\n426\r\n00:36:59,940 --> 00:37:04,543\r\nIt's a beautiful city.\r\n\r\n427\r\n00:37:04,543 --> 00:37:09,338\r\nI asked you\r\nif I should stay.\r\n\r\n428\r\n00:37:09,338 --> 00:37:12,311\r\nIt's up to you.\r\n\r\n429\r\n00:37:16,052 --> 00:37:20,464\r\nPromise me, Oskar,\r\nno doorman or maitre d'\r\nwill ever presume...\r\n\r\n430\r\n00:37:20,559 --> 00:37:25,739\r\nI'm anyone other\r\nthan Mrs. Schindler,\r\nand I'll stay.\r\n\r\n431\r\n00:37:27,848 --> 00:37:30,054\r\nGood-bye, darling.\r\n\r\n432\r\n00:37:45,975 --> 00:37:50,003\r\nI could try to read this\r\nor I could eat my lunch\r\nwhile it's still hot.\r\n\r\n433\r\n00:37:50,099 --> 00:37:52,017\r\nWe're doing well?\r\n\r\n434\r\n00:37:52,112 --> 00:37:53,263\r\nYes.\r\nBetter this month\r\nthan last?\r\n\r\n435\r\n00:37:53,360 --> 00:37:55,565\r\nYes.\r\nAny reason\r\nto think next month\r\n\r\n436\r\n00:37:55,565 --> 00:37:58,730\r\nThe war could end.\r\n\r\n437\r\n00:38:08,225 --> 00:38:10,718\r\nWhat?\r\nThere is a machinist\r\noutside...\r\n\r\n438\r\n00:38:10,718 --> 00:38:13,692\r\nwho'd like to thank you\r\npersonally for giving him a job.\r\n\r\n439\r\n00:38:13,787 --> 00:38:18,295\r\nEvery day he comes.\r\nHe's very grateful.\r\nIt'll just take a minute.\r\n\r\n440\r\n00:38:24,337 --> 00:38:26,639\r\nMr. Lowenstein?\r\n\r\n441\r\n00:38:33,352 --> 00:38:36,325\r\nI want to thank you, sir,\r\n\r\n442\r\n00:38:36,325 --> 00:38:39,011\r\nfor giving me\r\nthe opportunity to work.\r\n\r\n443\r\n00:38:39,106 --> 00:38:41,889\r\nYou're welcome.\r\nI'm sure you're doing\r\na great job.\r\n\r\n444\r\n00:38:41,984 --> 00:38:46,108\r\nThe SS beat me up.\r\nThey would have killed me,\r\n\r\n445\r\n00:38:46,204 --> 00:38:50,712\r\nbut I am essential\r\nto the war effort,\r\nthanks to you.\r\n\r\n446\r\n00:38:50,712 --> 00:38:52,629\r\nThat's great.\r\n\r\n447\r\n00:38:52,629 --> 00:38:55,220\r\nI work hard for you.\r\n\r\n448\r\n00:38:55,220 --> 00:38:59,152\r\nI'm sure you do.\r\nI'll continue\r\nto work hard for you.\r\n\r\n449\r\n00:38:59,247 --> 00:39:01,069\r\nThat's great.\r\nThanks.\r\n\r\n450\r\n00:39:01,165 --> 00:39:03,563\r\nGod bless you, sir.\r\nAll right.\r\n\r\n451\r\n00:39:03,563 --> 00:39:07,208\r\nYou are a good man.\r\n\r\n452\r\n00:39:08,550 --> 00:39:11,523\r\nHe saved my life.\r\nYes, he did.\r\n\r\n453\r\n00:39:11,523 --> 00:39:14,304\r\nGod bless him.\r\nYeah.\r\nCome on.\r\n\r\n454\r\n00:39:16,223 --> 00:39:19,004\r\nGod bless you.\r\n\r\n455\r\n00:39:30,513 --> 00:39:33,294\r\nI'm sorry, Herr Direktor,\r\nbut you're running very late.\r\n\r\n456\r\n00:39:33,389 --> 00:39:36,555\r\nThis is for the\r\nObersturmbannfuehrer, sir.\r\n\r\n457\r\n00:39:36,555 --> 00:39:39,432\r\nAnd this is for his niece,\r\nGreta. It's her birthday.\r\n\r\n458\r\n00:39:39,432 --> 00:39:42,117\r\nGreta as in Garbo.\r\nBy the way, don't ever\r\ndo that to me again.\r\n\r\n459\r\n00:39:42,214 --> 00:39:44,707\r\nGo. Go, go, drive!\r\nDon't bow.\r\n\r\n460\r\n00:39:44,707 --> 00:39:48,543\r\nDid you happen to notice that\r\nthat man had one arm?\r\nWhat? Did he?\r\n\r\n461\r\n00:39:52,092 --> 00:39:54,585\r\nWhat's his use?\r\nVery useful.\r\n\r\n462\r\n00:39:57,175 --> 00:40:00,723\r\nHow?\r\nVery useful! Success!\r\n\r\n463\r\n00:40:27,481 --> 00:40:30,550\r\nBesen und Schaufeln\r\nwerden ausgeladen...\r\n\r\n464\r\n00:40:30,550 --> 00:40:33,140\r\njeder nimmt sich eine und dann\r\nwird die Strasse gereinigt.\r\n\r\n465\r\n00:40:33,235 --> 00:40:35,346\r\nWe'll be late for work.\r\n\r\n466\r\n00:40:47,142 --> 00:40:50,115\r\nYou shouldn't think of them\r\nas yours, Oskar.\r\n\r\n467\r\n00:40:50,115 --> 00:40:52,033\r\nYou need to understand that\r\nsome of the officers here...\r\n\r\n468\r\n00:40:52,033 --> 00:40:54,719\r\ndon't give a damn\r\nabout production.\r\n\r\n469\r\n00:40:54,814 --> 00:40:58,746\r\nTo them, it's a matter of,\r\num, national priority...\r\n\r\n470\r\n00:40:58,746 --> 00:41:01,048\r\nthatJews\r\nbe made to shovel snow.\r\n\r\n471\r\n00:41:01,048 --> 00:41:03,542\r\nIt's got nothing to do\r\nwith reality, Oskar.\r\n\r\n472\r\n00:41:03,542 --> 00:41:05,556\r\nYou know it and I know it.\r\n\r\n473\r\n00:41:05,652 --> 00:41:07,858\r\nJews shoveling snow--\r\n\r\n474\r\n00:41:07,953 --> 00:41:12,462\r\nIt's got a, um,\r\nritual significance.\r\n\r\n475\r\n00:41:13,996 --> 00:41:17,352\r\nCome with me.\r\nI am an essential worker.\r\n\r\n476\r\n00:41:17,449 --> 00:41:20,038\r\nEssential worker?\r\nYes.\r\n\r\n477\r\n00:41:22,819 --> 00:41:26,272\r\nI work for Oskar Schindler.\r\nEssential worker\r\nfor Oskar Schindler.\r\n\r\n478\r\n00:41:26,367 --> 00:41:29,628\r\nA one-armed Jew?\r\nTwice as useless!\r\nYes, yes.\r\n\r\n479\r\n00:41:29,725 --> 00:41:33,561\r\nI lost a day\r\nof production, Rolf.\r\n\r\n480\r\n00:41:33,657 --> 00:41:36,725\r\nI work for Oskar Schindler.\r\n\r\n481\r\n00:41:36,822 --> 00:41:40,657\r\nDanka, look at the snow.\r\nLook at the snow.\r\nLook at the snow!\r\n\r\n482\r\n00:41:43,631 --> 00:41:48,234\r\nI lost a worker.\r\nI expect to be compensated.\r\n\r\n483\r\n00:41:48,331 --> 00:41:51,112\r\nFile a grievance\r\nwith the Economic Office.\r\nIt's your right.\r\n\r\n484\r\n00:41:51,207 --> 00:41:53,798\r\nWould it do\r\nany good?\r\nOf course not.\r\n\r\n485\r\n00:41:56,579 --> 00:42:00,703\r\nA big shot from the SS Budget\r\nand Construction Office\r\ncame to lunch...\r\n\r\n486\r\n00:42:00,703 --> 00:42:04,251\r\nand he told us that to believe\r\ntheJewish skilled worker\r\nhad a place...\r\n\r\n487\r\n00:42:04,251 --> 00:42:08,567\r\nin Reich economics\r\nwas a treasonable idea.\r\n\r\n488\r\n00:42:11,828 --> 00:42:16,527\r\nA one-armed machinist, Oskar?\r\n\r\n489\r\n00:42:16,527 --> 00:42:18,925\r\nHe was\r\na metal press operator.\r\n\r\n490\r\n00:42:22,665 --> 00:42:25,446\r\nQuite skilled.\r\n\r\n491\r\n00:42:53,259 --> 00:42:55,369\r\nHerr Direktor?\r\n\r\n492\r\n00:42:55,369 --> 00:42:57,671\r\nShit.\r\nI don't believe it.\r\n\r\n493\r\n00:42:57,671 --> 00:42:59,877\r\nStern, is that you?\r\n\r\n494\r\n00:42:59,973 --> 00:43:04,001\r\nNo, it's Poldek.\r\nIt's about Stern.\r\n\r\n495\r\n00:43:04,001 --> 00:43:07,741\r\nLeave your luggage\r\non the platform.\r\n\r\n496\r\n00:43:07,741 --> 00:43:09,756\r\nClearly label it.\r\n\r\n497\r\n00:43:09,851 --> 00:43:13,879\r\nGiven name first,\r\nthen your surname.\r\n\r\n498\r\n00:43:13,975 --> 00:43:16,469\r\nDo not bring\r\nyour baggage with you.\r\n\r\n499\r\n00:43:16,564 --> 00:43:19,345\r\nIt will follow you later.\r\n\r\n500\r\n00:43:19,442 --> 00:43:22,511\r\nLeave your luggage\r\non the platform.\r\n\r\n501\r\n00:43:22,606 --> 00:43:24,525\r\nClearly label it.\r\n\r\n502\r\n00:43:24,620 --> 00:43:28,360\r\nLassen Sie Ihr Gepaeck\r\nam Bahnsteig.\r\n\r\n503\r\n00:43:29,224 --> 00:43:31,143\r\nStern?\r\n\r\n504\r\n00:43:33,156 --> 00:43:36,129\r\nHe's on the list.\r\nHe is?\r\n\r\n505\r\n00:43:36,226 --> 00:43:39,007\r\nWell, let's find him.\r\nI'm sorry.\r\nYou can't have him.\r\n\r\n506\r\n00:43:39,102 --> 00:43:41,884\r\nHe's on the list.\r\nIf he were an essential worker,\r\nhe would not be on the list.\r\n\r\n507\r\n00:43:41,980 --> 00:43:44,569\r\nI'm talking to a clerk.\r\nWhat is your name?\r\n\r\n508\r\n00:43:44,665 --> 00:43:47,638\r\nSir, the list\r\nis correct.\r\nI didn't ask you about the list.\r\n\r\n509\r\n00:43:47,735 --> 00:43:51,667\r\nI asked you your name.\r\nKlaus Tauber.\r\n\r\n510\r\n00:43:51,762 --> 00:43:53,872\r\nTauber.\r\n\r\n511\r\n00:43:53,968 --> 00:43:57,708\r\nHauptscharfuehrer,\r\nthis gentleman thinks\r\na mistake's been made.\r\n\r\n512\r\n00:43:57,708 --> 00:44:00,106\r\nMy plant manager is\r\nsomewhere on this train.\r\n\r\n513\r\n00:44:00,202 --> 00:44:02,217\r\nIf it leaves with him on it,\r\nit'll disrupt production...\r\n\r\n514\r\n00:44:02,312 --> 00:44:04,422\r\nand the Armaments Board\r\nwill want to know why.\r\n\r\n515\r\n00:44:04,518 --> 00:44:06,723\r\nAchtung, dieser Zug\r\nfaehrt jetzt ab.\r\n\r\n516\r\n00:44:06,723 --> 00:44:10,752\r\nIs he on the list?\r\nYes, sir.\r\nItzhak Stern.\r\n\r\n517\r\n00:44:10,848 --> 00:44:16,218\r\nWell, the list\r\nis correct, sir.\r\nThere is nothing I can do.\r\n\r\n518\r\n00:44:16,314 --> 00:44:19,191\r\nWhat is your name?\r\nClose and secure all doors.\r\n\r\n519\r\n00:44:19,288 --> 00:44:22,644\r\nMy name?\r\nMy name is Kunder.\r\nThis train is now leaving.\r\n\r\n520\r\n00:44:22,644 --> 00:44:25,042\r\nKunder.\r\nHauptscharfuehrer Kunder.\r\n\r\n521\r\n00:44:25,042 --> 00:44:26,960\r\nK-U-N-D-E-R.\r\nAnd what's yours?\r\n\r\n522\r\n00:44:26,960 --> 00:44:29,070\r\nSchindler.\r\nS-C-H-I-N-D-L-E-R.\r\n\r\n523\r\n00:44:29,166 --> 00:44:31,371\r\nGentlemen,\r\nthank you very much.\r\n\r\n524\r\n00:44:31,468 --> 00:44:33,960\r\nI think I can guarantee you\r\nyou'll both be in...\r\n\r\n525\r\n00:44:34,057 --> 00:44:37,605\r\nSouthern Russia before the\r\nend of the month. Good day.\r\n\r\n526\r\n00:44:37,702 --> 00:44:40,578\r\nZamykac dokladnie drzwi.\r\nDokladnie zamykac drzwi.\r\n\r\n527\r\n00:44:40,578 --> 00:44:42,593\r\nStern!\r\n\r\n528\r\n00:44:42,688 --> 00:44:44,510\r\nStern!\r\nStern!\r\n\r\n529\r\n00:44:44,607 --> 00:44:46,429\r\nItzhak Stern!\r\n\r\n530\r\n00:44:52,567 --> 00:44:55,060\r\nStern!\r\nItzhak Stern!\r\n\r\n531\r\n00:44:55,157 --> 00:44:57,841\r\nStern! Stern!\r\nItzhak Stern!\r\n\r\n532\r\n00:44:59,184 --> 00:45:00,335\r\nStern!\r\n\r\n533\r\n00:45:00,431 --> 00:45:02,253\r\nSir?\r\n\r\n534\r\n00:45:03,596 --> 00:45:06,474\r\nStern!\r\nHerr Direktor.\r\n\r\n535\r\n00:45:06,569 --> 00:45:09,255\r\nMy apologies.\r\n\r\n536\r\n00:45:09,350 --> 00:45:12,131\r\nStop the train!\r\nHe's here!\r\nI apologize.\r\n\r\n537\r\n00:45:12,228 --> 00:45:17,024\r\n- Stop the train!\r\n- Stop the train! Stop it!\r\n\r\n538\r\n00:45:29,012 --> 00:45:32,656\r\nSign here.\r\nInitial there.\r\n\r\n539\r\n00:45:32,752 --> 00:45:36,684\r\nMakes no difference\r\nto us, you understand.\r\nThis one, that one.\r\n\r\n540\r\n00:45:36,684 --> 00:45:39,178\r\nIt's the inconvenience\r\nto the list.\r\n\r\n541\r\n00:45:39,273 --> 00:45:42,918\r\nIt's the paperwork.\r\nI somehow left\r\nmy work card at home.\r\n\r\n542\r\n00:45:42,918 --> 00:45:46,562\r\nI tried to explain them\r\nit was a mistake, but--\r\n\r\n543\r\n00:45:46,658 --> 00:45:50,590\r\nI'm sorry, it was stupid!\r\nWhat if I got here\r\nfive minutes later?\r\n\r\n544\r\n00:45:50,590 --> 00:45:53,276\r\nThen where would I be?\r\n\r\n545\r\n00:47:29,757 --> 00:47:31,197\r\nShechel.\r\n\r\n546\r\n00:47:31,292 --> 00:47:34,073\r\nSacrean,\r\nsacrean end tzukeer.\r\n\r\n547\r\n00:47:34,170 --> 00:47:36,567\r\nTzukeer end sacrean.\r\n\r\n548\r\n00:47:40,115 --> 00:47:42,609\r\nI woke up from a dream\r\nthis morning.\r\n\r\n549\r\n00:47:42,706 --> 00:47:46,733\r\nI was broke and sharing a room\r\nwith 12 people I didn't know,\r\n\r\n550\r\n00:47:46,830 --> 00:47:51,913\r\nonly to discover\r\nI was broke and sharing a room\r\nwith 12 people I didn't know.\r\n\r\n551\r\n00:47:52,871 --> 00:47:55,269\r\nYou laugh about it?\r\nI have to laugh.\r\n\r\n552\r\n00:47:55,269 --> 00:47:58,146\r\nYou are living\r\nbehind walls.\r\n\r\n553\r\n00:47:58,146 --> 00:48:02,750\r\nThe walls I can deal with.\r\nIt's the restrictions\r\nto my life I'm tired of.\r\n\r\n554\r\n00:48:02,845 --> 00:48:05,818\r\nThose walls keep them out.\r\nThat's all I care about.\r\n\r\n555\r\n00:48:05,914 --> 00:48:08,504\r\nI like it here.\r\nThere's a kind of,\r\nI don't know,\r\n\r\n556\r\n00:48:08,600 --> 00:48:10,806\r\nancestral squalor\r\nto it all.\r\n\r\n557\r\n00:48:10,901 --> 00:48:13,011\r\nYou are a slave\r\nto these people.\r\nNo one envies us anymore.\r\n\r\n558\r\n00:48:13,108 --> 00:48:15,122\r\nI'm smart.\r\nOh, yes,\r\nyou're smart.\r\n\r\n559\r\n00:48:15,122 --> 00:48:17,327\r\nYou're\r\na real genius.\r\nYou had your chance.\r\n\r\n560\r\n00:48:17,424 --> 00:48:21,931\r\nToday,\r\ntoday I actually found time\r\nto organize a thought.\r\n\r\n561\r\n00:48:22,027 --> 00:48:24,712\r\nI can't remember\r\nthe last time I did that.\r\n\r\n562\r\n00:48:24,712 --> 00:48:26,631\r\nWhen's the last time\r\nwe did this?\r\n\r\n563\r\n00:48:26,631 --> 00:48:28,933\r\nWhen's the last time\r\nwe stood around and talked?\r\n\r\n564\r\n00:48:29,028 --> 00:48:32,193\r\nNo one ordered me\r\nonto a truck today.\r\n\r\n565\r\n00:48:32,289 --> 00:48:34,495\r\nNo one took my business\r\naway from me.\r\n\r\n566\r\n00:48:34,590 --> 00:48:36,508\r\nYou don't really have\r\na business to take.\r\n\r\n567\r\n00:48:36,605 --> 00:48:38,810\r\nThere's nowhere\r\ndown from here.\r\n\r\n568\r\n00:48:38,810 --> 00:48:41,016\r\nThis is it.\r\nThis is the bottom.\r\n\r\n569\r\n00:48:41,112 --> 00:48:44,661\r\nThe ghetto is... liberty.\r\n\r\n570\r\n00:48:50,607 --> 00:48:53,771\r\nThis street\r\ndivides the ghetto\r\njust about in half.\r\n\r\n571\r\n00:48:53,868 --> 00:48:59,046\r\nRight side, Ghetto A:\r\ncivil employees,\r\n\r\n572\r\n00:48:59,046 --> 00:49:01,924\r\nindustrial workers\r\nand so on.\r\n\r\n573\r\n00:49:01,924 --> 00:49:06,720\r\nLeft side, Ghetto B:\r\nsurplus labor,\r\n\r\n574\r\n00:49:06,815 --> 00:49:09,117\r\nthe elderly\r\nand infirm mostly.\r\n\r\n575\r\n00:49:09,213 --> 00:49:12,090\r\nWhich is where you'll\r\nwant to start, huh?\r\n\r\n576\r\n00:49:12,185 --> 00:49:14,008\r\nDo you have any\r\nquestions, sir?\r\n\r\n577\r\n00:49:14,104 --> 00:49:17,557\r\nJa, why is the top down?\r\nI'm fucking freezing.\r\n\r\n578\r\n00:49:19,667 --> 00:49:22,256\r\nWe expect a labor force\r\nof 25,000 to 30,000.\r\n\r\n579\r\n00:49:22,256 --> 00:49:25,229\r\nSegregated, of course.\r\nThe men in the barracks\r\nnear the quarry.\r\n\r\n580\r\n00:49:25,326 --> 00:49:26,572\r\nThe women on the other\r\nside of the wire.\r\n\r\n581\r\n00:49:26,572 --> 00:49:29,066\r\nMy place is where?\r\nThere, sir.\r\n\r\n582\r\n00:49:29,161 --> 00:49:32,422\r\nThere?\r\nYou call that a villa?\r\nYes, the villa.\r\n\r\n583\r\n00:49:32,518 --> 00:49:34,723\r\nTheir synagogue,\r\ncan you see it?\r\nThat's not a villa.\r\n\r\n584\r\n00:49:34,820 --> 00:49:37,985\r\nWe're planning to turn it\r\ninto the camp stables.\r\nIt's a house.\r\n\r\n585\r\n00:49:38,081 --> 00:49: