\n\r\n681\r\n00:57:32,147 --> 00:57:35,215\r\n'Rueber zum Platz Chodi!\r\nKoffier hierlassen!\r\n\r\n682\r\n00:57:35,312 --> 00:57:38,189\r\nBlauschein.\r\nPlatz Chodi!\r\n\r\n683\r\n00:57:38,189 --> 00:57:40,395\r\nWas soll\r\nder Koffier hier?\r\n\r\n684\r\n00:57:40,490 --> 00:57:43,464\r\nAlles 'rueber\r\nzum Platz Chodi!\r\n\r\n685\r\n00:57:58,521 --> 00:58:00,247\r\nWe're getting out\r\nthrough the sewers.\r\n\r\n686\r\n00:58:00,247 --> 00:58:02,933\r\nI have to check\r\nif they're clear.\r\n\r\n687\r\n00:58:03,028 --> 00:58:05,906\r\nMila, pack some things.\r\nNothing bigger than this.\r\nI can't go in the sewers.\r\n\r\n688\r\n00:58:06,002 --> 00:58:09,167\r\nI told you I won't go\r\nin the sewers.\r\n\r\n689\r\n00:58:12,043 --> 00:58:15,305\r\nYou can go.\r\nYes, you can.\r\n\r\n690\r\n00:58:17,415 --> 00:58:19,428\r\nI won't go in the sewers.\r\n\r\n691\r\n00:58:29,786 --> 00:58:34,007\r\nMove! Over there!\r\nOver there! Move!\r\n\r\n692\r\n00:58:34,102 --> 00:58:36,308\r\nYour card, Jew!\r\n\r\n693\r\n00:58:36,308 --> 00:58:38,706\r\nDeine Papiere,\r\nJude!\r\n\r\n694\r\n00:58:38,706 --> 00:58:41,295\r\nDeine Papiere, Jude!\r\n\r\n695\r\n00:58:42,734 --> 00:58:45,228\r\nThat line.\r\n\r\n696\r\n00:58:45,323 --> 00:58:46,570\r\nDeine Karte!\r\n\r\n697\r\n00:58:46,570 --> 00:58:50,214\r\nIch geh'nicht 'rauf\r\nwegen Deiner verdammten Karte!\r\n\r\n698\r\n00:58:51,270 --> 00:58:53,764\r\nDeine Scheisskarte!\r\n\r\n699\r\n00:59:11,698 --> 00:59:13,903\r\nWas soll denn die Scheisse?\r\nBist du denn verrueckt geworden?\r\n\r\n700\r\n00:59:14,000 --> 00:59:16,397\r\nMit diesem Scheissgewehr\r\nhaettest du mich\r\nerschiessen koennen!\r\n\r\n701\r\n00:59:16,493 --> 00:59:18,411\r\nDu hast so nah an mir\r\nvorbeigeschossen!\r\n\r\n702\r\n00:59:18,507 --> 00:59:20,905\r\nWas heisst hier Entschuldigung.\r\nDu bist wohl verrueckt geworden!\r\n\r\n703\r\n00:59:20,905 --> 00:59:24,069\r\nZurueckbleiben!\r\nZurueckbleiben!\r\n\r\n704\r\n00:59:28,193 --> 00:59:31,838\r\nNicht sprechen, nicht sprechen!\r\nEinfach zu den Lastwagen gehen!\r\n\r\n705\r\n00:59:31,838 --> 00:59:34,332\r\nWeiterlaufen! Weiterlaufen!\r\nNicht sprechen!\r\n\r\n706\r\n00:59:44,210 --> 00:59:45,936\r\nKomm her, du Judensau!\r\n\r\n707\r\n00:59:46,033 --> 00:59:48,142\r\nBleib stehen, hab'ich gesagt.\r\nBleib stehen!\r\n\r\n708\r\n00:59:59,172 --> 01:00:02,145\r\nChodzcie tu szybko!\r\n\r\n709\r\n01:00:43,480 --> 01:00:45,878\r\nShe's good as dead.\r\nLeave her.\r\n\r\n710\r\n01:00:45,974 --> 01:00:49,426\r\nGive me a moment.\r\nJust let me bring her inside.\r\n\r\n711\r\n01:00:54,701 --> 01:00:58,250\r\nYou can join her...\r\nor join the line.\r\n\r\n712\r\n01:01:02,854 --> 01:01:05,156\r\nWomen to the left!\r\nWilhelm!\r\nRose!\r\n\r\n713\r\n01:01:05,156 --> 01:01:07,937\r\nMen to right.\r\nWomen to the left.\r\n\r\n714\r\n01:01:08,032 --> 01:01:10,621\r\nWomen\r\nto the left.\r\nLet me go!\r\n\r\n715\r\n01:01:15,225 --> 01:01:18,678\r\nWomen to the left,\r\nand men to the right.\r\nPromise me, be safe.\r\n\r\n716\r\n01:01:20,500 --> 01:01:23,473\r\nYour government\r\nis in the wrong country!\r\n\r\n717\r\n01:01:29,132 --> 01:01:31,337\r\nMama! Mama!\r\n\r\n718\r\n01:02:17,564 --> 01:02:19,387\r\nMila!\r\n\r\n719\r\n01:02:44,611 --> 01:02:48,063\r\nOh, God, Danka!\r\n\r\n720\r\n01:02:51,899 --> 01:02:54,584\r\nYou have a Blauschein.\r\nBlauschein doesn't\r\nmatter anymore.\r\n\r\n721\r\n01:02:54,584 --> 01:02:57,270\r\nThey are cleaning\r\nout the ghetto.\r\nThere's not enough room for you.\r\n\r\n722\r\n01:02:57,270 --> 01:03:00,818\r\nWhat are you talking about?\r\nWe tried it before.\r\nThere's more than enough room.\r\n\r\n723\r\n01:03:00,915 --> 01:03:03,791\r\n- I changed my mind!\r\n- Mama!\r\n\r\n724\r\n01:03:03,888 --> 01:03:08,108\r\nLook at the space in there.\r\nNow look at me.\r\nYou are just scared.\r\n\r\n725\r\n01:03:08,203 --> 01:03:10,409\r\nI can fit the girl,\r\nbut not you.\r\n\r\n726\r\n01:03:10,409 --> 01:03:12,806\r\n- Mama, I'm coming out!\r\n- Stay where you are.\r\n\r\n727\r\n01:03:12,903 --> 01:03:14,821\r\nI'd rather you be here\r\nthan who knows where.\r\n\r\n728\r\n01:03:14,916 --> 01:03:16,739\r\nMama!\r\n\r\n729\r\n01:03:36,687 --> 01:03:38,318\r\nHerr Kommandant!\r\n\r\n730\r\n01:03:38,414 --> 01:03:40,524\r\nVery good saluting.\r\n\r\n731\r\n01:03:40,524 --> 01:03:44,169\r\nI respectfully report\r\nI've been given orders to clear\r\nthe bundles from the road...\r\n\r\n732\r\n01:03:44,169 --> 01:03:47,237\r\nso there will be no obstructions\r\nto the thoroughfare.\r\n\r\n733\r\n01:03:47,237 --> 01:03:51,649\r\nFinish and join the lines,\r\nlittle Polish clicking soldier.\r\n\r\n734\r\n01:04:13,516 --> 01:04:15,338\r\nMrs. Dresner?\r\n\r\n735\r\n01:04:15,433 --> 01:04:17,256\r\nYes.\r\n\r\n736\r\n01:04:17,352 --> 01:04:19,654\r\nOh, you are a friend\r\nof my son's.\r\n\r\n737\r\n01:04:19,749 --> 01:04:22,051\r\nDon't worry, I'll go quietly.\r\nI'll be no trouble.\r\n\r\n738\r\n01:04:22,148 --> 01:04:26,272\r\nNo, get under the stairs.\r\nThey'll be done searching soon.\r\nYou'll be safe there.\r\n\r\n739\r\n01:04:26,367 --> 01:04:29,532\r\nPlease hide! Please!\r\n...warmed by the sun.\r\n\r\n740\r\n01:04:29,628 --> 01:04:31,930\r\nHide under the stairs.\r\n\r\n741\r\n01:04:34,423 --> 01:04:37,109\r\nI've searched the building.\r\nThere's no one here.\r\n\r\n742\r\n01:04:37,109 --> 01:04:39,986\r\nAlso, gehen wir\r\nzum naechsten Block.\r\nEinverstanden.\r\n\r\n743\r\n01:04:47,083 --> 01:04:49,480\r\nDanka! Ah!\r\nMama!\r\n\r\n744\r\n01:04:54,660 --> 01:04:56,769\r\nHello, Adam.\r\n\r\n745\r\n01:04:56,865 --> 01:04:58,879\r\nH-Hello, Danka.\r\n\r\n746\r\n01:05:04,730 --> 01:05:08,470\r\nCome with me.\r\nI will put you\r\nin the good line.\r\n\r\n747\r\n01:05:10,196 --> 01:05:13,266\r\nDo you know the saying, \"An hour\r\nof life is still life\"?\r\n\r\n748\r\n01:05:13,266 --> 01:05:17,390\r\nYou are not a boy anymore.\r\nI'm saying a blessing for you.\r\n\r\n749\r\n01:06:50,803 --> 01:06:53,487\r\nOh, please, let's go.\r\nLet's go, please.\r\n\r\n750\r\n01:06:53,967 --> 01:06:55,406\r\nCome on.\r\n\r\n751\r\n01:08:01,965 --> 01:08:03,788\r\nMarkieren.\r\n\r\n752\r\n01:08:03,883 --> 01:08:05,897\r\nMarkieren.\r\n\r\n753\r\n01:08:54,906 --> 01:08:57,111\r\nNie!\r\nProsze pana, niech pan--\r\n\r\n754\r\n01:09:03,537 --> 01:09:05,838\r\n...nie znajdziemy!\r\n\r\n755\r\n01:09:29,144 --> 01:09:33,077\r\nWas ist das?\r\nIst das Bach?\r\nNein, nein. Mozart.\r\n\r\n756\r\n01:09:33,172 --> 01:09:35,186\r\nMozart?\r\nJa.\r\n\r\n757\r\n01:09:54,080 --> 01:09:57,437\r\nDas wollen wir heute\r\nnoch schaffien?\r\nNee, schaffien wir nie.\r\n\r\n758\r\n01:09:57,437 --> 01:09:59,834\r\nJemu niedobrze sie robi.\r\n\r\n759\r\n01:10:01,848 --> 01:10:04,246\r\nNee, das schaffien wir nie.\r\n\r\n760\r\n01:10:04,246 --> 01:10:07,314\r\nI wish this fucking\r\nnight were over.\r\n\r\n761\r\n01:10:44,047 --> 01:10:47,596\r\nAppell! Fuenferreihen!\r\n\r\n762\r\n01:10:47,692 --> 01:10:49,993\r\nAntreten!\r\n\r\n763\r\n01:10:51,624 --> 01:10:54,405\r\nHalt, alle anstellen!\r\n\r\n764\r\n01:10:56,515 --> 01:10:59,392\r\nFuenferreihen!\r\n\r\n765\r\n01:10:59,392 --> 01:11:01,310\r\nMuetzen ab!\r\n\r\n766\r\n01:11:03,516 --> 01:11:07,736\r\nNamen verlesen!\r\nWer aufgerufen wird, hebt seine\r\nHand und ein deutliches Jawhol!\r\n\r\n767\r\n01:11:07,736 --> 01:11:11,189\r\nJawohl.\r\n\r\n768\r\n01:11:11,284 --> 01:11:14,737\r\nJawohl.\r\n\r\n769\r\n01:11:14,737 --> 01:11:17,902\r\nKeller, Fanni!\r\nJawohl.\r\n\r\n770\r\n01:11:17,998 --> 01:11:22,218\r\nAdalbert, Hermann!\r\nJawohl.\r\n\r\n771\r\n01:11:22,313 --> 01:11:24,615\r\nFaber, Dorothea!\r\nJawohl.\r\n\r\n772\r\n01:11:24,712 --> 01:11:27,972\r\nGoldstein, Pola!\r\nJawohl.\r\n\r\n773\r\n01:11:28,068 --> 01:11:30,849\r\nWarmberger, Markus!\r\n\r\n774\r\n01:11:30,945 --> 01:11:32,768\r\nJawohl.\r\n\r\n775\r\n01:11:32,863 --> 01:11:35,357\r\nEdelstein, Max!\r\n\r\n776\r\n01:11:52,525 --> 01:11:55,017\r\nAppell\r\nabtreten!\r\n\r\n777\r\n01:11:55,114 --> 01:11:57,032\r\nDo pracy!\r\nDo pracy!\r\n\r\n778\r\n01:11:57,128 --> 01:12:00,772\r\nThe worst is over.\r\nWe are workers now.\r\n\r\n779\r\n01:12:30,312 --> 01:12:33,380\r\nKeine Muedigkeit vorschuetzen!\r\n\r\n780\r\n01:12:37,696 --> 01:12:40,957\r\nOh, God, Amon.\r\n\r\n781\r\n01:12:44,697 --> 01:12:49,493\r\nSofort in der Baracke\r\nzurueckmelden!\r\n\r\n782\r\n01:13:29,390 --> 01:13:32,651\r\nKomm du mal schoen her!\r\nKomm du schoen!\r\n\r\n783\r\n01:13:32,746 --> 01:13:35,048\r\nNa komm!\r\nNa komm!\r\n\r\n784\r\n01:13:38,021 --> 01:13:41,187\r\nAmon, you're such\r\na damned fuckin' child!\r\n\r\n785\r\n01:13:41,187 --> 01:13:43,296\r\nWakey, wakey.\r\n\r\n786\r\n01:13:52,695 --> 01:13:56,148\r\nMake coffiee.\r\nMake it yourself.\r\n\r\n787\r\n01:14:09,959 --> 01:14:11,684\r\nThe SS will manage...\r\n\r\n788\r\n01:14:11,684 --> 01:14:14,658\r\ncertain industries itself\r\ninside Plaszow--\r\n\r\n789\r\n01:14:14,658 --> 01:14:17,343\r\na metalworks,\r\nbrush factory,\r\n\r\n790\r\n01:14:17,343 --> 01:14:19,550\r\nanother for reprocessing\r\nJewish clothing...\r\n\r\n791\r\n01:14:19,550 --> 01:14:23,385\r\nfrom the ghettos for use by\r\nbombed-out families back home.\r\n\r\n792\r\n01:14:23,385 --> 01:14:26,455\r\nBut it's private industry\r\nlike yours that stands\r\nto benefit most...\r\n\r\n793\r\n01:14:26,455 --> 01:14:28,757\r\nby moving inside the wire of\r\nCommandant Amon Goeth's camp--\r\n\r\n794\r\n01:14:28,757 --> 01:14:31,538\r\nNo, no, no. Sit, sit.\r\nJulian, how are you?\r\n\r\n795\r\n01:14:31,633 --> 01:14:32,976\r\nHow are you?\r\nGood to see you,\r\nmy friend.\r\n\r\n796\r\n01:14:33,072 --> 01:14:35,757\r\nOskar Schindler.\r\nLeoJohn.\r\n\r\n797\r\n01:14:39,115 --> 01:14:42,279\r\nFranz, good to see you.\r\nHello, Oskar.\r\nGlad you could join us.\r\n\r\n798\r\n01:14:42,375 --> 01:14:45,348\r\nMy pleasure. Julius.\r\nHow are you?\r\nYou lost weight.\r\n\r\n799\r\n01:14:45,348 --> 01:14:49,280\r\nOnly in the shoulders.\r\nPlease, everybody, sit down.\r\n\r\n800\r\n01:14:49,376 --> 01:14:51,965\r\nHow are you doing?\r\nOskar Schindler.\r\n\r\n801\r\n01:14:53,595 --> 01:14:56,857\r\nWe started without you.\r\nFine.\r\nI miss anything good?\r\n\r\n802\r\n01:14:56,953 --> 01:15:00,021\r\nI was explaining\r\nto Herr Bosch\r\nand Herr Madritsch...\r\n\r\n803\r\n01:15:00,118 --> 01:15:02,899\r\nsome of the benefits\r\nof moving their\r\nfactories into Plaszow.\r\n\r\n804\r\n01:15:02,899 --> 01:15:05,776\r\nI meant the food.\r\n\r\n805\r\n01:15:07,790 --> 01:15:11,722\r\nSince your labor is housed\r\non-site, it's available\r\nto you at all times.\r\n\r\n806\r\n01:15:11,819 --> 01:15:13,928\r\nYou can work them\r\nall night if you want.\r\n\r\n807\r\n01:15:14,024 --> 01:15:18,340\r\nYour factory policies, whatever\r\nthey've been in the past,\r\nthey'll continue to be.\r\n\r\n808\r\n01:15:18,340 --> 01:15:20,450\r\nThey'll be respected.\r\n\r\n809\r\n01:15:20,546 --> 01:15:24,670\r\nI have to know, where\r\ndo you get a suit like that?\r\nWhat is that? Is that silk?\r\n\r\n810\r\n01:15:24,670 --> 01:15:26,588\r\nOf course.\r\n\r\n811\r\n01:15:26,588 --> 01:15:30,712\r\nJa. It's-- It has\r\na nice sheen about it.\r\n\r\n812\r\n01:15:30,807 --> 01:15:32,630\r\nThank you.\r\nVery nice.\r\n\r\n813\r\n01:15:32,726 --> 01:15:36,370\r\nI'd say I'd get you one,\r\nbut the man who made it\r\nis probably dead.\r\n\r\n814\r\n01:15:36,466 --> 01:15:38,864\r\nI don't know.\r\n\r\n815\r\n01:15:38,960 --> 01:15:42,604\r\nI go to work the other day.\r\n\r\n816\r\n01:15:42,604 --> 01:15:44,810\r\nNobody's there.\r\n\r\n817\r\n01:15:44,905 --> 01:15:48,167\r\nNobody tells me about this.\r\nI have to fid out.\r\nI have to go in.\r\n\r\n818\r\n01:15:48,263 --> 01:15:51,620\r\nEverybody's gone.\r\n\r\n819\r\n01:15:51,715 --> 01:15:54,496\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n820\r\n01:15:54,593 --> 01:15:56,606\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n821\r\n01:15:59,196 --> 01:16:01,689\r\nThey're not gone.\r\nThey're here.\r\n\r\n822\r\n01:16:01,786 --> 01:16:06,581\r\nThey're mine!\r\nEvery day that goes by,\r\nI'm losing money.\r\n\r\n823\r\n01:16:06,581 --> 01:16:10,609\r\nEvery worker that is shot\r\ncosts me money. I have to\r\nfind somebody else.\r\n\r\n824\r\n01:16:10,705 --> 01:16:13,198\r\nWe are going to be making\r\nso much money that none of this\r\nis going to matter.\r\n\r\n825\r\n01:16:13,294 --> 01:16:14,733\r\nIt's bad business.\r\n\r\n826\r\n01:16:27,200 --> 01:16:29,119\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\n827\r\n01:16:29,119 --> 01:16:31,612\r\nLeave the bottle.\r\n\r\n828\r\n01:16:32,763 --> 01:16:34,874\r\nTake that.\r\n\r\n829\r\n01:16:34,969 --> 01:16:38,422\r\nLena... thank you.\r\n\r\n830\r\n01:16:47,341 --> 01:16:50,315\r\nScherner told me\r\nsomething else about you.\r\n\r\n831\r\n01:16:52,520 --> 01:16:54,821\r\nYeah?\r\nWhat's that?\r\n\r\n832\r\n01:16:54,821 --> 01:16:59,330\r\nThat you know the meaning\r\nof the word \"gratitude.\"\r\n\r\n833\r\n01:16:59,425 --> 01:17:02,782\r\nThat it's not\r\nsome vague thing with you...\r\n\r\n834\r\n01:17:02,878 --> 01:17:05,947\r\nlike it is with others.\r\n\r\n835\r\n01:17:05,947 --> 01:17:09,303\r\nYou want to stay\r\nwhere you are.\r\n\r\n836\r\n01:17:09,400 --> 01:17:12,373\r\nYou've got things\r\ngoing on the side.\r\n\r\n837\r\n01:17:12,469 --> 01:17:14,483\r\nThings are good.\r\n\r\n838\r\n01:17:14,578 --> 01:17:18,894\r\nYou don't want anybody\r\ntelling you what to do.\r\n\r\n839\r\n01:17:18,990 --> 01:17:23,306\r\nI can understand all that,\r\nyou know. I-- I know you.\r\n\r\n840\r\n01:17:25,320 --> 01:17:30,307\r\nWhat you want...\r\nis your own sub-camp.\r\n\r\n841\r\n01:17:35,486 --> 01:17:38,843\r\nDo you have any idea\r\nwhat is involved?\r\nThe paperwork alone?\r\n\r\n842\r\n01:17:38,939 --> 01:17:42,871\r\nYou've got to build the thing.\r\nGetting those fucking permits\r\nis enough to drive you crazy.\r\n\r\n843\r\n01:17:42,871 --> 01:17:46,900\r\nThen the engineers show up,\r\nthey stand around, they argue\r\nabout drainage, foundations,\r\n\r\n844\r\n01:17:46,900 --> 01:17:51,982\r\ncodes, exact specifications,\r\nfences four kilometers long,\r\n1 ,200 kilograms of barbed wire,\r\n\r\n845\r\n01:17:52,078 --> 01:17:55,243\r\n6,000 kilograms of electrified\r\nfences, ceramic insulators,\r\n\r\n846\r\n01:17:55,243 --> 01:17:56,969\r\nthree cubic meters\r\nof air space per prisoner.\r\n\r\n847\r\n01:17:56,969 --> 01:18:00,901\r\nI'm telling you,\r\nyou want to shoot somebody.\r\nI've been through it. I know.\r\n\r\n848\r\n01:18:00,901 --> 01:18:04,546\r\nWell, you know.\r\nYou've been through it.\r\n\r\n849\r\n01:18:06,368 --> 01:18:09,341\r\nYou could make things\r\neasier for me.\r\n\r\n850\r\n01:18:12,219 --> 01:18:14,232\r\nI'd be grateful.\r\n\r\n851\r\n01:18:17,685 --> 01:18:19,986\r\nAus dem Weg da!\r\n\r\n852\r\n01:18:29,673 --> 01:18:33,414\r\nWeitergehen!\r\nWeitergehen!\r\n\r\n853\r\n01:18:34,660 --> 01:18:37,921\r\nWlewo zwrot!\r\nTrzymac szereg!\r\n\r\n854\r\n01:18:38,018 --> 01:18:40,799\r\nWeitergehen.\r\nNach links.\r\n\r\n855\r\n01:18:48,087 --> 01:18:50,006\r\nWhere's Stern?\r\n\r\n856\r\n01:18:53,554 --> 01:18:57,486\r\nGoldberg and Chilowicz...\r\nmake sure I see my cut...\r\n\r\n857\r\n01:18:57,582 --> 01:19:00,939\r\nfrom the, uh,\r\nfactory owners in this camp,\r\n\r\n858\r\n01:19:01,035 --> 01:19:04,296\r\nleaving you to take care\r\nof my main account--\r\n\r\n859\r\n01:19:04,391 --> 01:19:07,556\r\nthe Schindler account.\r\n\r\n860\r\n01:19:07,652 --> 01:19:11,488\r\nHe wants his independence.\r\nI gave it to him.\r\n\r\n861\r\n01:19:11,585 --> 01:19:14,366\r\nBut independence\r\ncosts money.\r\n\r\n862\r\n01:19:14,462 --> 01:19:16,763\r\nThis you\r\nunderstand?\r\n\r\n863\r\n01:19:21,462 --> 01:19:23,285\r\nLook at me.\r\n\r\n864\r\n01:19:33,547 --> 01:19:37,479\r\nDon't forget who\r\nyou are working for now.\r\n\r\n865\r\n01:19:46,686 --> 01:19:49,755\r\nJawohl!\r\nMake sure he kisses\r\n\r\n866\r\n01:19:49,851 --> 01:19:53,112\r\nJa. Now, girls,\r\neveryone.\r\n\r\n867\r\n01:19:55,893 --> 01:19:58,387\r\nWe need more wine.\r\nMore wine!\r\n\r\n868\r\n01:19:58,482 --> 01:20:02,127\r\nStand in my place.\r\nDon't let him leave.\r\n\r\n869\r\n01:20:17,472 --> 01:20:20,733\r\nProst! Prost!\r\n\r\n870\r\n01:20:22,651 --> 01:20:25,241\r\nThank you,\r\nHerr Direktor.\r\n\r\n871\r\n01:20:25,337 --> 01:20:27,638\r\nProst,\r\nHerr Direktor!\r\n\r\n872\r\n01:20:31,570 --> 01:20:34,928\r\nWhat are you\r\ndoing?\r\nWhat?\r\n\r\n873\r\n01:20:35,023 --> 01:20:39,243\r\nMakes them think we have lice.\r\nHelps them keep their distance.\r\n\r\n874\r\n01:20:39,339 --> 01:20:41,736\r\nDo you have lice?\r\nDo you have your notebook?\r\n\r\n875\r\n01:20:41,833 --> 01:20:45,286\r\nThe calendar on my desk has\r\nthe birthdays of our SS friends'\r\nwives and children.\r\n\r\n876\r\n01:20:45,381 --> 01:20:47,875\r\nDon't forget\r\nto send something.\r\n\r\n877\r\n01:20:47,875 --> 01:20:51,232\r\nRecord payoffs\r\nto the Main Administration\r\nand Economics Office, the Arm--\r\n\r\n878\r\n01:20:51,327 --> 01:20:55,067\r\nSlower, Stern, slower.\r\nThe Armaments Board,\r\nGovernor General's Division...\r\n\r\n879\r\n01:20:55,164 --> 01:20:57,945\r\nof the Interior\r\nand Chief of Police as \"fees,\"\r\n\r\n880\r\n01:20:58,041 --> 01:20:59,958\r\nand make them\r\non the first of each month,\r\n\r\n881\r\n01:21:00,055 --> 01:21:02,260\r\nas opposed to individual payoffs\r\nto our SS contacts.\r\n\r\n882\r\n01:21:02,357 --> 01:21:07,535\r\nThe list is in the lower drawer\r\nof my desk, which you--\r\n\"First of month--\"\r\n\r\n883\r\n01:21:07,632 --> 01:21:10,413\r\nlist,\r\nlower drawer of my desk,\r\nwhich you handle...\r\n\r\n884\r\n01:21:10,508 --> 01:21:14,537\r\nas cash contributions\r\nto legitimate charities\r\nsent to each official's office.\r\n\r\n885\r\n01:21:14,632 --> 01:21:17,606\r\nDealings with\r\nour black market contacts,\r\nlisted as suppliers...\r\n\r\n886\r\n01:21:17,606 --> 01:21:21,155\r\nin the legitimate ledger,\r\nare more complicated.\r\nForget it.\r\n\r\n887\r\n01:21:21,250 --> 01:21:24,990\r\nWhat do you mean, forget it?\r\nYou can't forget it!\r\nIt gives me a headache!\r\n\r\n888\r\n01:21:31,513 --> 01:21:34,773\r\nI couldn't get you\r\nout of here.\r\nI'll be all right.\r\n\r\n889\r\n01:21:34,773 --> 01:21:38,801\r\nAnyway, I'm here\r\nalmost every week.\r\nWednesdays, usually.\r\n\r\n890\r\n01:21:38,801 --> 01:21:42,158\r\nI'll look in on you,\r\nsee how you're doing.\r\n\r\n891\r\n01:21:44,172 --> 01:21:47,720\r\nHere, put these\r\nin your pocket.\r\n\r\n892\r\n01:21:47,720 --> 01:21:49,735\r\nCome on.\r\n\r\n893\r\n01:21:52,419 --> 01:21:55,681\r\nHerr Direktor,\r\ndon't let things fall apart.\r\n\r\n894\r\n01:21:55,776 --> 01:21:57,886\r\nI've worked too hard.\r\n\r\n895\r\n01:22:05,847 --> 01:22:10,258\r\nThanks for--\r\nGood luck.\r\n\r\n896\r\n01:22:31,166 --> 01:22:33,468\r\nAchtung, Muetzen ab!\r\n\r\n897\r\n01:22:42,962 --> 01:22:45,360\r\n- Work!\r\n- An die Arbeit!\r\n\r\n898\r\n01:22:58,500 --> 01:22:59,938\r\nWhat are you making?\r\n\r\n899\r\n01:23:00,226 --> 01:23:02,623\r\nHinges, sir.\r\n\r\n900\r\n01:23:05,405 --> 01:23:08,858\r\nJa, I've got some workers\r\ncoming in tomorrow.\r\nWhere are they from again?\r\n\r\n901\r\n01:23:08,953 --> 01:23:11,255\r\nYugoslavia,\r\nHerr Kommandant.\r\n\r\n902\r\n01:23:11,255 --> 01:23:13,461\r\nI've got to make room.\r\n\r\n903\r\n01:23:15,763 --> 01:23:18,927\r\nMake me a hinge.\r\nYes, sir.\r\n\r\n904\r\n01:23:49,042 --> 01:23:52,112\r\nKeep going,\r\nyou're doing well.\r\n\r\n905\r\n01:23:52,207 --> 01:23:54,221\r\nSays he's\r\ndoing well.\r\n\r\n906\r\n01:24:00,647 --> 01:24:03,236\r\nOh, that's very good.\r\n\r\n907\r\n01:24:03,236 --> 01:24:07,073\r\nBut I'm a bit confused,\r\nand perhaps you can help me.\r\n\r\n908\r\n01:24:07,169 --> 01:24:10,429\r\nWhat I don't understand\r\nis that you've been working...\r\n\r\n909\r\n01:24:10,526 --> 01:24:14,074\r\nsince I think, what,\r\nabout six this morning?\r\n\r\n910\r\n01:24:15,609 --> 01:24:19,828\r\nYet such a small pile\r\nof hinges.\r\n\r\n911\r\n01:24:47,737 --> 01:24:50,518\r\nOh, Christ.\r\nMay I try that, sir?\r\n\r\n912\r\n01:24:50,518 --> 01:24:52,724\r\nCheck the angle-lever.\r\nMaybe it's bent.\r\n\r\n913\r\n01:24:52,724 --> 01:24:56,081\r\nNo, no.\r\nYou wouldn't hear a click\r\nif it was the angle-lever.\r\n\r\n914\r\n01:24:56,177 --> 01:24:58,479\r\nMaybe it's the pin.\r\nMaybe the pin shaft is greasy.\r\nJa, come on.\r\n\r\n915\r\n01:24:58,479 --> 01:25:01,452\r\nWhat did I just say?\r\nHere.\r\n\r\n916\r\n01:25:02,795 --> 01:25:06,247\r\nHerr Kommandant,\r\n\r\n917\r\n01:25:06,343 --> 01:25:10,659\r\nI beg to report\r\nthat my heap ofhinges\r\nwas so unsatisfactory...\r\n\r\n918\r\n01:25:10,754 --> 01:25:14,878\r\nbecause the machines\r\nwere being recalibrated\r\nthis morning.\r\n\r\n919\r\n01:25:14,975 --> 01:25:19,674\r\nI w-was put on\r\nto shoveling coal.\r\n\r\n920\r\n01:25:42,499 --> 01:25:44,514\r\nStrange, huh?\r\n\r\n921\r\n01:25:44,609 --> 01:25:46,431\r\nYeah.\r\n\r\n922\r\n01:25:51,035 --> 01:25:54,105\r\nThank you, Muek.\r\n\r\n923\r\n01:25:54,200 --> 01:25:57,940\r\nAh, Lisiek.\r\nDon't touch the leather,\r\nit's just been oiled.\r\n\r\n924\r\n01:25:58,037 --> 01:25:59,667\r\nRottenfuehrer.\r\nOh, for me?\r\n\r\n925\r\n01:25:59,667 --> 01:26:03,215\r\nOh, thank you very much,\r\nHerr Direktor. Thank you.\r\nHerr Direktor!\r\n\r\n926\r\n01:26:03,312 --> 01:26:05,709\r\nHerr Direktor!\r\n\r\n927\r\n01:26:08,203 --> 01:26:10,696\r\nHerr Direktor!\r\n\r\n928\r\n01:26:11,847 --> 01:26:13,765\r\nHe was making\r\nhinges slowly.\r\n\r\n929\r\n01:26:13,860 --> 01:26:18,561\r\nSo the man can turn out a hinge\r\nin less than a minute.\r\nWhy the long story? Hmm?\r\n\r\n930\r\n01:26:46,469 --> 01:26:49,155\r\nThank you, sir.\r\nYou're welcome.\r\n\r\n931\r\n01:26:52,223 --> 01:26:56,060\r\nNobody knows\r\nwho stole the chicken, hmm?\r\nTell him about the chicken.\r\n\r\n932\r\n01:26:56,060 --> 01:27:00,664\r\nA man walks around\r\nwith a chicken and\r\nnobody notices this.\r\n\r\n933\r\n01:27:00,759 --> 01:27:03,157\r\nSave yourselves.\r\n\r\n934\r\n01:27:03,253 --> 01:27:05,554\r\nTell him\r\nabout the chicken.\r\n\r\n935\r\n01:27:20,612 --> 01:27:22,626\r\nStill nobody knows.\r\n\r\n936\r\n01:27:33,847 --> 01:27:37,492\r\nIt was you.\r\nYou committed this crime.\r\n\r\n937\r\n01:27:37,492 --> 01:27:39,793\r\nNo, sir.\r\nBut you know who, though.\r\n\r\n938\r\n01:27:39,889 --> 01:27:42,095\r\nYes.\r\nWho?\r\n\r\n939\r\n01:27:42,191 --> 01:27:45,068\r\nHim!\r\n\r\n940\r\n01:27:48,424 --> 01:27:52,166\r\nHe's very gifted.\r\nYeah, sure.\r\nBring him over.\r\n\r\n941\r\n01:27:54,850 --> 01:27:58,591\r\nYes, sir.\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\n942\r\n01:28:04,441 --> 01:28:07,222\r\nThank you again,\r\nHerr Direktor.\r\nYou're welcome again.\r\n\r\n943\r\n01:28:07,222 --> 01:28:10,867\r\nIt's an honor to work\r\nfor such a great company.\r\nIt's great to have you.\r\n\r\n944\r\n01:28:10,963 --> 01:28:14,991\r\nI promise to learn everything\r\nabout enamelware production.\r\nThat's great.\r\n\r\n945\r\n01:28:26,979 --> 01:28:31,007\r\nHello?\r\nMiss Elsa Krause is here.\r\nI only need five minutes.\r\n\r\n946\r\n01:28:31,007 --> 01:28:33,693\r\nShe wants to speak\r\nto the Herr Direktor.\r\n\r\n947\r\n01:28:52,394 --> 01:28:54,505\r\nYes.\r\n\r\n948\r\n01:28:58,532 --> 01:29:00,739\r\nHe won't see you.\r\n\r\n949\r\n01:29:30,086 --> 01:29:32,100\r\nPlease, sit down.\r\n\r\n950\r\n01:29:35,169 --> 01:29:37,950\r\nPernod?\r\nCognac?\r\nUh, no.\r\n\r\n951\r\n01:29:39,101 --> 01:29:41,882\r\nSo, what\r\ncan I do for you?\r\n\r\n952\r\n01:29:45,718 --> 01:29:48,692\r\nThey say that no one\r\ndies here.\r\n\r\n953\r\n01:29:48,692 --> 01:29:51,281\r\nThey say your factory\r\nis a haven.\r\n\r\n954\r\n01:29:53,967 --> 01:29:56,173\r\nThey say you are good.\r\n\r\n955\r\n01:29:59,050 --> 01:30:01,159\r\nWho says that?\r\n\r\n956\r\n01:30:01,256 --> 01:30:03,269\r\nEveryone.\r\n\r\n957\r\n01:30:09,407 --> 01:30:12,189\r\nMy name is Regina Perlman,\r\nnot Elsa Krause.\r\n\r\n958\r\n01:30:12,285 --> 01:30:15,354\r\nI've been living in Krakow\r\non false papers since\r\nthe ghetto massacre.\r\n\r\n959\r\n01:30:15,449 --> 01:30:16,889\r\nMy parents are in Plaszow.\r\n\r\n960\r\n01:30:16,984 --> 01:30:21,300\r\nTheir names are\r\nChana and Jakob Perlman.\r\n\r\n961\r\n01:30:21,396 --> 01:30:25,040\r\nThey are older people.\r\nThey are killing older people\r\nnow in Plaszow.\r\n\r\n962\r\n01:30:25,040 --> 01:30:28,877\r\nThey bury them\r\nup in the forest. Look...\r\n\r\n963\r\n01:30:28,972 --> 01:30:31,754\r\nI don't have any money.\r\n\r\n964\r\n01:30:31,850 --> 01:30:34,631\r\nI, I borrowed\r\nthese clothes.\r\n\r\n965\r\n01:30:37,221 --> 01:30:39,235\r\nI'm begging you.\r\n\r\n966\r\n01:30:39,330 --> 01:30:43,070\r\nPlease, please\r\nbring them here.\r\n\r\n967\r\n01:30:43,167 --> 01:30:45,564\r\nI don't do that.\r\n\r\n968\r\n01:30:45,564 --> 01:30:49,401\r\nYou've been misled.\r\nI ask one thing:\r\n\r\n969\r\n01:30:49,401 --> 01:30:52,566\r\nwhether or not a worker\r\nhas certain skills.\r\n\r\n970\r\n01:30:52,566 --> 01:30:55,347\r\nMy father is an importer,\r\nnot a metalworker.\r\n\r\n971\r\n01:30:55,443 --> 01:30:59,183\r\nSuch activities are illegal.\r\nYou will not entrap me!\r\n\r\n972\r\n01:30:59,279 --> 01:31:03,403\r\nCry, and I will\r\nhave you arrested.\r\nI swear to God!\r\n\r\n973\r\n01:31:12,706 --> 01:31:15,295\r\nPeople die.\r\nIt's a fact of life.\r\n\r\n974\r\n01:31:15,391 --> 01:31:19,036\r\nHe wants to kill everybody?\r\nGreat! What am I supposed\r\nto do about it?\r\n\r\n975\r\n01:31:19,132 --> 01:31:21,721\r\nBring everybody over?\r\nIs that what you think?\r\n\r\n976\r\n01:31:21,817 --> 01:31:24,598\r\nSend them over to Schindler.\r\nSend them all!\r\n\r\n977\r\n01:31:24,598 --> 01:31:28,147\r\nHis place is a haven,\r\ndidn't you know?\r\nIt's not a factory.\r\n\r\n978\r\n01:31:28,243 --> 01:31:30,448\r\nIt's not an enterprise\r\nof any kind.\r\n\r\n979\r\n01:31:30,448 --> 01:31:33,229\r\nIt's a haven for rabbis\r\nand orphans...\r\n\r\n980\r\n01:31:33,326 --> 01:31:36,490\r\nand people with\r\nno skills whatsoever!\r\n\r\n981\r\n01:31:37,738 --> 01:31:41,862\r\nYou think I don't know\r\nwhat you're doing?\r\n\r\n982\r\n01:31:41,862 --> 01:31:45,314\r\nYou're so quiet\r\nall the time.\r\nI know, I know!\r\n\r\n983\r\n01:31:45,410 --> 01:31:48,191\r\nAre you losing money?\r\nThat's not the point!\r\n\r\n984\r\n01:31:48,287 --> 01:31:52,028\r\nWhat other point is--\r\nIt's dangerous!\r\nIt's dangerous to me!\r\n\r\n985\r\n01:31:54,359 --> 01:31:57,811\r\nYou have to understand.\r\nGoeth is under enormous\r\npressure.\r\n\r\n986\r\n01:31:57,907 --> 01:32:00,976\r\nYou have to think of it\r\nin his situation.\r\n\r\n987\r\n01:32:01,072 --> 01:32:03,853\r\nHe's got this\r\nwhole place to run.\r\n\r\n988\r\n01:32:03,950 --> 01:32:06,731\r\nHe's responsible\r\nfor everything here,\r\nall these people.\r\n\r\n989\r\n01:32:06,826 --> 01:32:09,704\r\nHe's got a lot of things\r\nto worry about.\r\n\r\n990\r\n01:32:09,704 --> 01:32:13,732\r\nAnd he's got the war\r\nwhich brings out\r\nthe worst in people.\r\n\r\n991\r\n01:32:13,828 --> 01:32:17,089\r\nNever the good,\r\nalways the bad.\r\nAlways the bad.\r\n\r\n992\r\n01:32:19,294 --> 01:32:23,707\r\nBut in normal circumstances\r\nhe wouldn't be like this.\r\nHe'd be all right.\r\n\r\n993\r\n01:32:23,802 --> 01:32:27,159\r\nThere'd just be the good\r\naspects of him which--\r\n\r\n994\r\n01:32:27,159 --> 01:32:30,707\r\nHe's a wonderful crook.\r\n\r\n995\r\n01:32:30,803 --> 01:32:35,023\r\nA man who loves good food,\r\ngood wine, the ladies,\r\nmaking money--\r\n\r\n996\r\n01:32:35,119 --> 01:32:37,325\r\nKilling.\r\n\r\n997\r\n01:32:37,325 --> 01:32:40,010\r\nHe can't enjoy it.\r\n\r\n998\r\n01:32:40,106 --> 01:32:43,079\r\nBejski told me the other day,\r\nsomebody escaped...\r\n\r\n999\r\n01:32:43,175 --> 01:32:45,861\r\nfrom a work detail\r\noutside the wire.\r\n\r\n1000\r\n01:32:45,861 --> 01:32:49,697\r\nGoeth lined up everybody\r\nfrom the missing man's barracks.\r\n\r\n1001\r\n01:32:49,793 --> 01:32:53,725\r\nHe shot the man\r\nto the left of Bejski,\r\nthe man to the right ofhim.\r\n\r\n1002\r\n01:32:53,725 --> 01:32:57,369\r\nHe walked down the line\r\nshooting every other man\r\nwith the pistol.\r\n\r\n1003\r\n01:33:02,260 --> 01:33:04,659\r\nTwenty-five.\r\n\r\n1004\r\n01:33:08,399 --> 01:33:11,947\r\nWhat do you want me\r\nto do about it?\r\nNothing, nothing.\r\n\r\n1005\r\n01:33:12,043 --> 01:33:14,249\r\nWe're just talking.\r\n\r\n1006\r\n01:33:25,470 --> 01:33:27,292\r\n\"Perlman.\"\r\n\r\n1007\r\n01:33:28,923 --> 01:33:30,937\r\nPerlman!\r\n\r\n1008\r\n01:33:30,937 --> 01:33:33,621\r\nHusband and wife.\r\n\r\n1009\r\n01:33:33,718 --> 01:33:37,363\r\nJakob and Chana Perlman!\r\n\r\n1010\r\n01:33:50,022 --> 01:33:53,186\r\nHave Goldberg\r\nbring them over.\r\n\r\n1011\r\n01:33:55,009 --> 01:33:58,269\r\nMuetzen ab!\r\n\r\n1012\r\n01:33:58,366 --> 01:34:00,380\r\nAppell abtreten!\r\n\r\n1013\r\n01:34:46,223 --> 01:34:50,155\r\nI'm sure this will be better\r\nthan those rags, Lisiek.\r\n\r\n1014\r\n01:34:50,251 --> 01:34:53,992\r\nHerr Direktor,\r\nI was just helping Lisiek\r\nto find something...\r\n\r\n1015\r\n01:34:54,087 --> 01:34:56,869\r\nto clean the stains\r\nfrom the Herr Kommandant's\r\nbathtub.\r\n\r\n1016\r\n01:34:56,965 --> 01:34:59,746\r\nGo, please.\r\nPardon me,\r\nHerr Direktor.\r\n\r\n1017\r\n01:35:01,569 --> 01:35:06,076\r\nYou don't have to report\r\nto me, Helen.\r\n\r\n1018\r\n01:35:06,076 --> 01:35:09,241\r\nYou know who I am?\r\nHmm?\r\n\r\n1019\r\n01:35:16,913 --> 01:35:20,174\r\nI'm Schindler.\r\n\r\n1020\r\n01:35:20,270 --> 01:35:23,243\r\nOf course.\r\nI-I have heard and...\r\n\r\n1021\r\n01:35:23,339 --> 01:35:26,217\r\nyou have\r\nbeen here before.\r\n\r\n1022\r\n01:35:28,326 --> 01:35:31,203\r\nHere, why don't you\r\nkeep this someplace?\r\n\r\n1023\r\n01:35:31,300 --> 01:35:34,656\r\nGo on, take it.\r\nI get extra food here.\r\n\r\n1024\r\n01:35:34,752 --> 01:35:39,259\r\nWell, if you don't\r\nwant to eat it, trade it.\r\nOr give it to Lisiek.\r\n\r\n1025\r\n01:35:41,945 --> 01:35:44,151\r\nWhy not\r\nbuild yourself up?\r\n\r\n1026\r\n01:35:48,563 --> 01:35:52,398\r\nMy first day here,\r\nhe beat me...\r\n\r\n1027\r\n01:35:52,495 --> 01:35:56,235\r\nbecause I threw out\r\nthe bones from dinner.\r\n\r\n1028\r\n01:35:59,303 --> 01:36:03,620\r\nHe came down to the basement\r\nat midnight, and he--\r\n\r\n1029\r\n01:36:03,716 --> 01:36:06,305\r\nhe asked me\r\nwhere they were.\r\n\r\n1030\r\n01:36:08,703 --> 01:36:13,114\r\nFor his dogs,\r\nyou understand.\r\n\r\n1031\r\n01:36:15,225 --> 01:36:19,157\r\nI said to him, I--\r\nI don't know how I say this.\r\n\r\n1032\r\n01:36:19,252 --> 01:36:22,610\r\nI never could say it now--\r\nI said to him,\r\n\r\n1033\r\n01:36:22,705 --> 01:36:25,007\r\n\"Why are you beating me?\"\r\n\r\n1034\r\n01:36:28,075 --> 01:36:31,625\r\nHe said, \"The reason\r\nI beat you now...\r\n\r\n1035\r\n01:36:31,720 --> 01:36:35,461\r\nis because you ask\r\nwhy I beat you.\"\r\n\r\n1036\r\n01:36:37,282 --> 01:36:40,065\r\nI know your\r\nsufferings, Helen.\r\n\r\n1037\r\n01:36:42,462 --> 01:36:44,764\r\nIt doesn't matter.\r\n\r\n1038\r\n01:36:46,394 --> 01:36:49,272\r\nI have accepted them.\r\n\r\n1039\r\n01:36:49,272 --> 01:36:51,477\r\nAccepted them?\r\n\r\n1040\r\n01:36:53,204 --> 01:36:55,314\r\nOne day\r\nhe will shoot me.\r\n\r\n1041\r\n01:36:55,409 --> 01:36:57,711\r\nNo, no, no, no,\r\nhe won't shoot you.\r\n\r\n1042\r\n01:36:57,807 --> 01:37:01,355\r\nI know.\r\nI see things.\r\n\r\n1043\r\n01:37:01,451 --> 01:37:04,713\r\nWe were on the roof on Monday,\r\nyoung Lisiek and I,\r\n\r\n1044\r\n01:37:04,808 --> 01:37:08,645\r\nand we saw the Herr Kommandant\r\ncome out of the front door...\r\n\r\n1045\r\n01:37:08,645 --> 01:37:13,344\r\nand down the steps by the patio\r\nright there below us and--\r\n\r\n1046\r\n01:37:13,440 --> 01:37:18,139\r\nand there on the steps\r\nhe drew his gun and he...\r\n\r\n1047\r\n01:37:18,235 --> 01:37:21,016\r\nshot a woman\r\nwho was passing by.\r\n\r\n1048\r\n01:37:22,455 --> 01:37:25,620\r\nA woman carrying a bundle.\r\nThrough the throat.\r\n\r\n1049\r\n01:37:25,716 --> 01:37:29,168\r\nJust-- Just a woman\r\non her way somewhere,\r\nyou know.\r\n\r\n1050\r\n01:37:29,264 --> 01:37:33,005\r\nShe was no fatter\r\nor thinner...\r\n\r\n1051\r\n01:37:33,101 --> 01:37:35,402\r\nor slower or faster\r\nthan anyone else,\r\n\r\n1052\r\n01:37:35,498 --> 01:37:39,047\r\nand I couldn't guess\r\nwhat had she done.\r\n\r\n1053\r\n01:37:43,650 --> 01:37:47,199\r\nThe more you see\r\nof the Herr Kommandant,\r\n\r\n1054\r\n01:37:47,199 --> 01:37:51,994\r\nthe more you see\r\nthere is no set rules\r\nthat you can live by.\r\n\r\n1055\r\n01:37:51,994 --> 01:37:56,694\r\nYou can't say to yourself,\r\n\"If I follow these rules,\r\nI will be safe.\"\r\n\r\n1056\r\n01:38:00,147 --> 01:38:04,270\r\nHe won't shoot you\r\nbecause he enjoys you\r\ntoo much.\r\n\r\n1057\r\n01:38:04,270 --> 01:38:08,203\r\nHe enjoys you so much\r\nhe won't even let you\r\nwear the star.\r\n\r\n1058\r\n01:38:08,298 --> 01:38:10,600\r\nHe doesn't want\r\nanyone else to know...\r\n\r\n1059\r\n01:38:10,696 --> 01:38:12,997\r\nit's a Jew\r\nhe's enjoying.\r\n\r\n1060\r\n01:38:16,259 --> 01:38:19,136\r\nHe shot the woman\r\nfrom the steps...\r\n\r\n1061\r\n01:38:19,136 --> 01:38:22,780\r\nbecause she meant\r\nnothing to him.\r\n\r\n1062\r\n01:38:22,876 --> 01:38:25,177\r\nShe was\r\none of a series,\r\n\r\n1063\r\n01:38:25,274 --> 01:38:27,863\r\nneither offending\r\nor pleasing him.\r\n\r\n1064\r\n01:38:31,603 --> 01:38:33,905\r\nBut you, Helen.\r\n\r\n1065\r\n01:38:38,221 --> 01:38:42,537\r\nIt's all right.\r\nIt's not that kind\r\nof a kiss.\r\n\r\n1066\r\n01:38:46,661 --> 01:38:49,058\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\n1067\r\n01:38:49,058 --> 01:38:51,073\r\nShh.\r\n\r\n1068\r\n01:38:54,141 --> 01:38:55,964\r\nHere.\r\n\r\n1069\r\n01:39:01,910 --> 01:39:04,212\r\nRight. The wine.\r\n\r\n1070\r\n01:39:11,022 --> 01:39:13,898\r\nWonderful party, Amon.\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\n1071\r\n01:39:22,050 --> 01:39:24,832\r\nWhy do you drink\r\nthat motor oil?\r\n\r\n1072\r\n01:39:24,928 --> 01:39:27,901\r\nHmm? I send you\r\ngood stuff all the time.\r\n\r\n1073\r\n01:39:27,901 --> 01:39:31,738\r\nYour liver's\r\ngoing to explode\r\nlike a hand grenade.\r\n\r\n1074\r\n01:39:31,833 --> 01:39:34,614\r\nThe more I look at you--\r\n\r\n1075\r\n01:39:34,710 --> 01:39:36,916\r\nI watch you.\r\n\r\n1076\r\n01:39:38,451 --> 01:39:40,464\r\nYou're never drunk.\r\n\r\n1077\r\n01:39:40,561 --> 01:39:44,397\r\nOh, that's--\r\n\r\n1078\r\n01:39:44,493 --> 01:39:47,466\r\nthat's real control.\r\n\r\n1079\r\n01:39:47,466 --> 01:39:49,576\r\nControl is power.\r\n\r\n1080\r\n01:39:50,534 --> 01:39:52,741\r\nThat's power.\r\n\r\n1081\r\n01:39:56,385 --> 01:40:00,221\r\nIs that why they fear us?\r\n\r\n1082\r\n01:40:00,221 --> 01:40:04,729\r\nWe have the fucking\r\npower to kill, that's\r\nwhy they fear us.\r\n\r\n1083\r\n01:40:04,824 --> 01:40:08,566\r\nThey fear us because\r\nwe have the power\r\nto kill arbitrarily.\r\n\r\n1084\r\n01:40:08,661 --> 01:40:10,771\r\nA man commits a crime,\r\nhe should know better.\r\n\r\n1085\r\n01:40:10,867 --> 01:40:13,360\r\nWe have him killed,\r\nand feel good about it.\r\n\r\n1086\r\n01:40:13,457 --> 01:40:16,333\r\nOr we kill him ourselves\r\nand we feel even better.\r\n\r\n1087\r\n01:40:18,539 --> 01:40:21,513\r\nThat's not power,\r\nthough.\r\n\r\n1088\r\n01:40:21,608 --> 01:40:25,637\r\nThat's justice.\r\nIt's different than power.\r\n\r\n1089\r\n01:40:28,226 --> 01:40:33,117\r\nPower is when we have every\r\njustification to kill...\r\n\r\n1090\r\n01:40:33,213 --> 01:40:35,707\r\nand we don't.\r\n\r\n1091\r\n01:40:35,803 --> 01:40:37,912\r\nYou think that's power?\r\n\r\n1092\r\n01:40:40,502 --> 01:40:43,571\r\nThat's what the emperors had.\r\nA man stole something,\r\n\r\n1093\r\n01:40:43,667 --> 01:40:45,202\r\nhe's brought in\r\nbefore the emperor,\r\n\r\n1094\r\n01:40:45,297 --> 01:40:49,229\r\nhe throws himself\r\ndown on the ground,\r\nhe begs for mercy.\r\n\r\n1095\r\n01:40:49,326 --> 01:40:52,682\r\nHe knows\r\nhe's going to die.\r\n\r\n1096\r\n01:40:54,504 --> 01:40:57,861\r\nAnd the emperor...\r\npardons him.\r\n\r\n1097\r\n01:40:59,108 --> 01:41:02,273\r\nThis worthless man.\r\nHe lets him go.\r\n\r\n1098\r\n01:41:05,246 --> 01:41:07,643\r\nI think you are drunk.\r\n\r\n1099\r\n01:41:09,274 --> 01:41:12,151\r\nThat's power, Amon.\r\n\r\n1100\r\n01:41:12,247 --> 01:41:15,507\r\nThat... is power.\r\n\r\n1101\r\n01:41:22,893 --> 01:41:25,578\r\nAmon the Good.\r\n\r\n1102\r\n01:41:28,456 --> 01:41:31,524\r\nI pardon you.\r\n\r\n1103\r\n01:41:36,895 --> 01:41:39,293\r\nWhat do they want?\r\n\r\n1104\r\n01:41:39,388 --> 01:41:42,649\r\nI don't know,\r\nbut they're in my office now\r\nreviewing our books.\r\n\r\n1105\r\n01:41:42,746 --> 01:41:45,814\r\nAs my accountant, tell me,\r\nshould I be alarmed...\r\n\r\n1106\r\n01:41:45,911 --> 01:41:48,692\r\nthat the auditors\r\nare reviewing my books?\r\nWell--\r\n\r\n1107\r\n01:41:48,787 --> 01:41:51,473\r\nOr have you done\r\nyour job properly?\r\nYou needn't be alarmed.\r\n\r\n1108\r\n01:41:51,569 --> 01:41:53,486\r\nI needn't\r\nbe alarmed.\r\n\r\n1109\r\n01:41:55,980 --> 01:41:58,474\r\nI'm sorry, sir.\r\n\r\n1110\r\n01:41:58,570 --> 01:42:00,584\r\nDo you know how much\r\nthis saddle is worth?\r\n\r\n1111\r\n01:42:00,584 --> 01:42:03,174\r\nDo you know how much\r\nit costs?\r\n\r\n1112\r\n01:42:07,681 --> 01:42:11,230\r\nAll right.\r\n\r\n1113\r\n01:42:11,325 --> 01:42:13,243\r\nAll right.\r\n\r\n1114\r\n01:42:16,505 --> 01:42:19,477\r\nStern, what the hell are you\r\ndoing following me around?\r\n\r\n1115\r\n01:42:28,301 --> 01:42:31,562\r\nBarracken eins, elf,\r\n\r\n1116\r\n01:42:31,657 --> 01:42:34,151\r\nfuenfzehn\r\nund zwounddreissig...\r\n\r\n1117\r\n01:42:34,248 --> 01:42:36,837\r\nam Appellplatz melden.\r\n\r\n1118\r\n01:43:03,402 --> 01:43:06,184\r\nShe was smoking\r\non the job.\r\n\r\n1119\r\n01:43:09,733 --> 01:43:12,706\r\nTell her\r\nnot to do it again.\r\n\r\n1120\r\n01:43:27,667 --> 01:43:30,449\r\nI have to report, sir,\r\n\r\n1121\r\n01:43:30,544 --> 01:43:34,284\r\nI've been unable to remove\r\nthe stains from your bathtub.\r\n\r\n1122\r\n01:43:38,313 --> 01:43:41,957\r\nWhat are you using,\r\nLisiek?\r\nSoap, Commandant.\r\n\r\n1123\r\n01:43:44,259 --> 01:43:46,561\r\nSoap? Not lye?\r\n\r\n1124\r\n01:43:55,384 --> 01:43:59,220\r\nGo ahead, go on, leave.\r\nLeave, I pardon you.\r\n\r\n1125\r\n01:44:20,416 --> 01:44:22,525\r\nI pardon you.\r\n\r\n1126\r\n01:46:09,749 --> 01:46:13,202\r\nAlthough I am not a rabbi,\r\nin these circumstances...\r\n\r\n1127\r\n01:46:13,297 --> 01:46:15,887\r\nI pray to the Almighty\r\nthat you will forgive me...\r\n\r\n1128\r\n01:46:15,983 --> 01:46:18,956\r\nif I intone the blessings.\r\n\r\n1129\r\n01:46:19,052 --> 01:46:21,737\r\nBaruch ata Hsham eloiyni\r\nmelech hoylam...\r\n\r\n1130\r\n01:46:21,737 --> 01:46:24,518\r\nasher ztivonee\r\nal aariuouth.\r\n\r\n1131\r\n01:46:24,615 --> 01:46:28,068\r\nVouser lanou at harosth,\r\nVhesserlanou at hansooes...\r\n\r\n1132\r\n01:46:28,068 --> 01:46:30,944\r\nlanou al yaday cheepah\r\nve kidesheem.\r\n\r\n1133\r\n01:47:09,403 --> 01:47:11,704\r\nSo...\r\n\r\n1134\r\n01:47:11,704 --> 01:47:15,637\r\nthis is where you come\r\nto hide from me.\r\n\r\n1135\r\n01:47:15,733 --> 01:47:18,898\r\nI came to tell you...\r\n\r\n1136\r\n01:47:18,994 --> 01:47:22,830\r\nthat you, um, you really are\r\na wonderful cook...\r\n\r\n1137\r\n01:47:22,830 --> 01:47:25,804\r\nand a well-trained servant.\r\n\r\n1138\r\n01:47:25,899 --> 01:47:30,118\r\nI mean it.\r\nIf you need a reference\r\nafter the war,\r\n\r\n1139\r\n01:47:30,215 --> 01:47:34,819\r\nI'd be-- I'd be happy\r\nto give you one.\r\n\r\n1140\r\n01:47:34,914 --> 01:47:37,216\r\nIt must get lonely\r\ndown here...\r\n\r\n1141\r\n01:47:37,312 --> 01:47:41,532\r\nwhen you're listening\r\nto everyone upstairs\r\nhaving such a good time.\r\n\r\n1142\r\n01:47:48,437 --> 01:47:50,642\r\nDoes it?\r\n\r\n1143\r\n01:47:52,274 --> 01:47:54,191\r\nYou can answer.\r\n\r\n1144\r\n01:47:56,493 --> 01:48:00,713\r\nBut what's the right answer?\r\nThat's what you're thinking.\r\n\r\n1145\r\n01:48:00,809 --> 01:48:03,686\r\nWhat does he want to hear?\r\n\r\n1146\r\n01:48:08,577 --> 01:48:12,606\r\nThe truth, Helen,\r\nis always the right answer.\r\n\r\n1147\r\n01:48:15,195 --> 01:48:17,688\r\nY-Yes, you're right.\r\n\r\n1148\r\n01:48:17,688 --> 01:48:21,046\r\nSometimes\r\nwe're both lonely.\r\n\r\n1149\r\n01:48:21,141 --> 01:48:24,018\r\nYes. I--\r\n\r\n1150\r\n01:48:24,018 --> 01:48:27,470\r\nI mean--\r\n\r\n1151\r\n01:48:34,088 --> 01:48:37,349\r\nI would like so much to...\r\n\r\n1152\r\n01:48:37,445 --> 01:48:41,185\r\nreach out and touch you\r\nin your loneliness.\r\n\r\n1153\r\n01:48:41,282 --> 01:48:44,543\r\nWh-What would that be like,\r\nI wonder? I mean...\r\n\r\n1154\r\n01:48:44,638 --> 01:48:48,187\r\nwhat would be wrong with that?\r\n\r\n1155\r\n01:48:48,283 --> 01:48:52,407\r\nI realize that you're not\r\na-a person in the--\r\n\r\n1156\r\n01:48:52,502 --> 01:48:55,283\r\nthe strictest sense\r\nof the word, but--\r\n\r\n1157\r\n01:48:55,283 --> 01:48:58,641\r\nNo, maybe you're right\r\nabout that too, you know.\r\n\r\n1158\r\n01:48:58,641 --> 01:49:03,436\r\nMaybe what's--\r\nwhat's wrong isn't--\r\n\r\n1159\r\n01:49:03,436 --> 01:49:05,930\r\nIt's not us.\r\n\r\n1160\r\n01:49:06,025 --> 01:49:08,327\r\nIt's no--\r\nIt's this.\r\n\r\n1161\r\n01:49:10,724 --> 01:49:14,848\r\nI mean, when they\r\ncompare you to--\r\n\r\n1162\r\n01:49:14,848 --> 01:49:18,014\r\nto, uh, vermin\r\nand to rodents and to lice...\r\n\r\n1163\r\n01:49:20,028 --> 01:49:22,904\r\nI just, uh--\r\n\r\n1164\r\n01:49:26,262 --> 01:49:29,043\r\nN-No, you-you make\r\na good point.\r\n\r\n1165\r\n01:49:29,138 --> 01:49:31,440\r\nYou make\r\na very good point.\r\n\r\n1166\r\n01:49:39,496 --> 01:49:41,798\r\nIs this the face\r\nof a rat?\r\n\r\n1167\r\n01:49:44,868 --> 01:49:46,977\r\nAre these the eyes\r\nof a rat?\r\n\r\n1168\r\n01:49:49,951 --> 01:49:52,444\r\nHath not a Jew eyes?\r\n\r\n1169\r\n01:50:07,693 --> 01:50:11,241\r\nI feel for you, Helen.\r\n\r\n1170\r\n01:50:27,354 --> 01:50:30,039\r\nNo, I don't think so.\r\n\r\n1171\r\n01:50:31,957 --> 01:50:34,739\r\nYou're a Jewish bitch.\r\n\r\n1172\r\n01:50:36,273 --> 01:50:40,205\r\nYou nearly talked me into it,\r\nHelen, didn't you?\r\n\r\n1173\r\n01:50:45,288 --> 01:50:47,782\r\nBravo.\r\n\r\n1174\r\n01:51:02,743 --> 01:51:06,196\r\nHoch! Hoch! Hoch!\r\n\r\n1175\r\n01:51:08,785 --> 01:51:12,430\r\n- Jawohl!\r\n- Hoch! Hoch!\r\n\r\n1176\r\n01:51:12,526 --> 01:51:15,595\r\nHoch!\r\n\r\n1177\r\n01:51:20,678 --> 01:51:23,172\r\nOn behalf of the--\r\nof the workers, sir,\r\n\r\n1178\r\n01:51:23,267 --> 01:51:26,337\r\nI, I wish for you\r\na happy birthday.\r\n\r\n1179\r\n01:51:26,432 --> 01:51:28,350\r\nHappy birthday.\r\n\r\n1180\r\n01:51:28,447 --> 01:51:30,652\r\nWell, thank\r\nthe staff, please.\r\n\r\n1181\r\n01:51:30,748 --> 01:51:33,434\r\nThank you very much\r\nfor the lovely cake.\r\n\r\n1182\r\n01:51:50,505 --> 01:51:55,109\r\nThank you very much.\r\nTell them thank you from me.\r\n\r\n1183\r\n01:52:09,783 --> 01:52:14,482\r\nThe trains arrived\r\nand the people were\r\ndriven out with clubs.\r\n\r\n1184\r\n01:52:14,482 --> 01:52:18,798\r\nThey were lined up in front\r\nof two big warehouses.\r\n\r\n1185\r\n01:52:18,893 --> 01:52:22,825\r\nOne was marked \"Cloak Room,\"\r\nand the other \"Valuables.\"\r\n\r\n1186\r\n01:52:22,922 --> 01:52:25,224\r\nAnd there they\r\nwere made to undress.\r\n\r\n1187\r\n01:52:25,319 --> 01:52:29,635\r\nAJewish boy handed them\r\npieces of string to tie\r\ntheir shoes together.\r\n\r\n1188\r\n01:52:29,731 --> 01:52:32,320\r\nThey shaved their hair.\r\n\r\n1189\r\n01:52:32,416 --> 01:52:37,115\r\nThey told them it was needed\r\nto make something special\r\nfor U-boat crews.\r\n\r\n1190\r\n01:52:37,212 --> 01:52:41,239\r\nAnd then they were herded\r\ndown a big corridor...\r\n\r\n1191\r\n01:52:41,336 --> 01:52:45,268\r\nto bunkers with\r\nStars of David on the doors,\r\n\r\n1192\r\n01:52:45,363 --> 01:52:49,104\r\nand signs that said\r\n\"Bath and Inhalation Room.\"\r\n\r\n1193\r\n01:52:49,200 --> 01:52:51,310\r\nSS gave them soap.\r\n\r\n1194\r\n01:52:51,405 --> 01:52:56,297\r\nThey told them to\r\nbreathe all the time because\r\nit's good for disinfecting.\r\n\r\n1195\r\n01:52:56,393 --> 01:52:59,079\r\nAnd then they gassed them.\r\n\r\n1196\r\n01:53:00,325 --> 01:53:02,819\r\nMila, why soaps?\r\n\r\n1197\r\n01:53:02,914 --> 01:53:05,408\r\nSo that they would agree\r\nto go in, I think.\r\n\r\n1198\r\n01:53:05,408 --> 01:53:09,052\r\nCome on, Mila, stop it.\r\nYour bedtime stories\r\nare scaring everyone.\r\n\r\n1199\r\n01:53:09,052 --> 01:53:11,450\r\nI just don't believe it.\r\nJa. You know\r\nit's ridiculous.\r\n\r\n1200\r\n01:53:11,546 --> 01:53:13,464\r\nI don't believe it\r\neither.\r\nI cannot believe it.\r\n\r\n1201\r\n01:53:13,561 --> 01:53:16,054\r\nI didn't say I believed it.\r\nI said I heard it.\r\n\r\n1202\r\n01:53:16,150 --> 01:53:19,315\r\nFrom who?\r\nFrom somebody who heard it\r\nfrom someone who was there.\r\n\r\n1203\r\n01:53:19,315 --> 01:53:21,809\r\nYou know,\r\nif they were there,\r\n\r\n1204\r\n01:53:21,904 --> 01:53:24,110\r\nthey would\r\nhave been gassed.\r\n\r\n1205\r\n01:53:24,110 --> 01:53:27,466\r\nYes.\r\nIt doesn't\r\nmake any sense.\r\n\r\n1206\r\n01:53:27,563 --> 01:53:29,481\r\nWe're their work force.\r\n\r\n1207\r\n01:53:29,576 --> 01:53:33,221\r\nWhat sense does it make\r\nto kill your own work force?\r\n\r\n1208\r\n01:53:33,317 --> 01:53:38,016\r\nTo go to all this trouble\r\nof assembling a work force\r\nonly to--\r\n\r\n1209\r\n01:53:38,112 --> 01:53:41,277\r\nNo, it can't be true.\r\n\r\n1210\r\n01:53:41,277 --> 01:53:44,155\r\nWe are very, very\r\nimportant for them.\r\n\r\n1211\r\n01:53:44,155 --> 01:53:47,415\r\nJa, we do now.\r\nGood night.\r\n\r\n1212\r\n01:53:47,511 --> 01:53:50,389\r\nGood night.\r\nGood night.\r\nSweet dreams.\r\n\r\n1213\r\n01:53:58,520 --> 01:54:01,013\r\nAttention, attention.\r\n\r\n1214\r\n01:54:01,109 --> 01:54:03,411\r\nEveryone who is alive...\r\n\r\n1215\r\n01:54:03,507 --> 01:54:06,863\r\nis to come\r\nto the Appellplatz.\r\n\r\n1216\r\n01:54:06,960 --> 01:54:11,276\r\nAttention, attention.\r\nCome, we have to go\r\nto the Appellplatz.\r\n\r\n1217\r\n01:54:11,276 --> 01:54:12,427\r\nEveryone who is alive...\r\nThe listmakers are here.\r\n\r\n1218\r\n01:54:12,522 --> 01:54:15,400\r\nIs to come to the Appellplatz.\r\nThere is going\r\nto be a selection.\r\n\r\n1219\r\n01:54:15,495 --> 01:54:19,907\r\nAttention, attention.\r\nEveryone who is alive...\r\n\r\n1220\r\n01:54:20,003 --> 01:54:23,743\r\nis to come\r\nto the Appellplatz.\r\n\r\n1221\r\n01:54:36,978 --> 01:54:38,897\r\nMeine Herren.\r\n\r\n1222\r\n01:54:38,897 --> 01:54:40,815\r\nRaz!\r\nDwa!\r\n\r\n1223\r\n01:54:40,815 --> 01:54:43,021\r\nRaz!\r\nDwa!\r\n\r\n1224\r\n01:54:43,021 --> 01:54:45,131\r\n...die Hunderttausend\r\nUngarn kommen...\r\n\r\n1225\r\n01:54:47,144 --> 01:54:50,885\r\nAlle in einer\r\nEinzelreihe aufstellen!\r\n\r\n1226\r\n01:54:50,981 --> 01:54:54,913\r\nYou could afford\r\nto lose some weight, Amon.\r\n\r\n1227\r\n01:54:55,009 --> 01:54:57,503\r\nAnd you've got to\r\ncut down on the cognac.\r\n\r\n1228\r\n01:54:57,503 --> 01:55:00,380\r\nMorning.\r\nWhat's going on?\r\n\r\n1229\r\n01:55:00,380 --> 01:55:03,257\r\nIt's another\r\nsemiannual physical.\r\n\r\n1230\r\n01:55:05,078 --> 01:55:09,682\r\nThere.\r\nOh, I've, um, got another\r\nshipment coming in of, uh--\r\n\r\n1231\r\n01:55:09,682 --> 01:55:11,793\r\nWhat are they this time?\r\n\r\n1232\r\n01:55:11,888 --> 01:55:13,711\r\nHungarians.\r\nOh, ja, Hungarians.\r\n\r\n1233\r\n01:55:13,711 --> 01:55:17,259\r\nWe've got to separate\r\nthe sick from the healthy\r\nto make room.\r\n\r\n1234\r\n01:55:17,259 --> 01:55:21,095\r\nTeraz! Teraz!\r\n\r\n1235\r\n01:55:37,784 --> 01:55:41,236\r\nDas darf nicht\r\nbis zum Abend dauern!\r\n\r\n1236\r\n01:55:51,498 --> 01:55:53,896\r\nLet me help you.\r\n\r\n1237\r\n01:55:57,444 --> 01:56:00,225\r\nZack, zack, zack!\r\n\r\n1238\r\n01:56:03,870 --> 01:56:08,186\r\nWe've got to go out there.\r\n\r\n1239\r\n01:56:10,391 --> 01:56:12,980\r\nDon't go.\r\n\r\n1240\r\n01:56:12,980 --> 01:56:14,995\r\nLook alive, Rebeka.\r\n\r\n1241\r\n01:56:15,091 --> 01:56:17,296\r\nSchneller!\r\n\r\n1242\r\n01:56:17,296 --> 01:56:21,325\r\nNaokolo!\r\nPredzej! Predzej!\r\n\r\n1243\r\n01:56:21,325 --> 01:56:23,722\r\nNaokolo!\r\nNaokolo!\r\n\r\n1244\r\n01:56:37,053 --> 01:56:39,739\r\nThat's my mechanic.\r\n\r\n1245\r\n01:56:39,834 --> 01:56:43,095\r\nWhose bright idea was it\r\nto get rid of him?\r\n\r\n1246\r\n01:56:48,946 --> 01:56:52,399\r\nRuszaj sie!\r\nNaokolo!\r\n\r\n1247\r\n01:56:53,837 --> 01:56:57,769\r\nSzybciej! Szybciej!\r\nTrzymaj ubrania!\r\n\r\n1248\r\n01:57:00,358 --> 01:57:04,290\r\nRuszac sie!\r\nRuszac sie!\r\n\r\n1249\r\n01:57:06,497 --> 01:57:09,182\r\nNaokolo!\r\nNaokolo!\r\n\r\n1250\r\n01:57:09,278 --> 01:57:12,156\r\nOtworz usta.\r\nZajrzymy do gardla.\r\n\r\n1251\r\n01:57:12,251 --> 01:57:15,896\r\nWez gleboki oddech.\r\nJeszcze. Jeszcze.\r\n\r\n1252\r\n01:57:22,896 --> 01:57:27,308\r\nUnies ramiona.\r\nObroc sie. Przykucnij.\r\n\r\n1253\r\n01:57:34,118 --> 01:57:36,707\r\nFormowac kolmune!\r\n\r\n1254\r\n01:57:43,420 --> 01:57:46,202\r\nNo, no, no.\r\nWait, go away.\r\nShe can work.\r\n\r\n1255\r\n01:57:46,298 --> 01:57:49,943\r\nCome here. Look,\r\nseparate the sick\r\nfrom the healthy.\r\n\r\n1256\r\n01:57:50,038 --> 01:57:52,436\r\nThose who can work\r\nand those who can't.\r\nShe can work.\r\n\r\n1257\r\n01:57:52,436 --> 01:57:56,560\r\nYou can work,\r\nyou can come.\r\n\r\n1258\r\n01:57:56,751 --> 01:57:59,053\r\nRuszac sie!\r\nSzybciej!\r\n\r\n1259\r\n01:58:33,771 --> 01:58:36,170\r\nStehenbleiben!\r\nStehenbleiben!\r\n\r\n1260\r\n01:59:18,560 --> 01:59:23,356\r\nThose not selected\r\nfor transport,\r\nput your clothes back on.\r\n\r\n1261\r\n01:59:23,451 --> 01:59:27,863\r\nMen, go back to the barracks.\r\nReturn to the barracks.\r\n\r\n1262\r\n01:59:32,466 --> 01:59:35,631\r\nGo back to the barracks.\r\n\r\n1263\r\n01:59:38,988 --> 01:59:41,482\r\nOh, my God!\r\n\r\n1264\r\n02:00:02,581 --> 02:00:06,897\r\nOlek? Olek?\r\nDanka?\r\n\r\n1265\r\n02:00:06,897 --> 02:00:11,692\r\nOlek? Olek?\r\n\r\n1266\r\n02:00:11,788 --> 02:00:15,049\r\nOlek! Olek!\r\n\r\n1267\r\n02:00:21,091 --> 02:00:23,873\r\nOlek?\r\nDanka?\r\n\r\n1268\r\n02:00:23,968 --> 02:00:25,790\r\nDanka?\r\nOlek?\r\n\r\n1269\r\n02:00:25,886 --> 02:00:28,764\r\nAb in die Barracke!\r\nIn die Barracke mit euch!\r\n\r\n1270\r\n02:00:28,859 --> 02:00:32,791\r\nI didn't see him!\r\nThey're hiding.\r\nI'm telling you, they're hiding.\r\n\r\n1271\r\n02:00:32,791 --> 02:00:36,244\r\nI know Danka.\r\nShe took them to a good place.\r\nShe took all of them together.\r\n\r\n1272\r\n02:00:36,244 --> 02:00:38,930\r\nZurueck in die Barracken!\r\n\r\n1273\r\n02:00:57,631 --> 02:01:03,098\r\nFind your own hiding place.\r\nThere's no room for you here.\r\nGo away, quick!\r\n\r\n1274\r\n02:01:25,636 --> 02:01:28,514\r\nGet out. This is our place.\r\nGet out!\r\n\r\n1275\r\n02:01:51,339 --> 02:01:54,505\r\nOskar!\r\nAmon. Gentlemen.\r\n\r\n1276\r\n02:01:54,600 --> 02:01:57,765\r\nWhy didn't you call me?\r\nI tried to call you.\r\nHere, Hujar, move.\r\n\r\n1277\r\n02:01:57,861 --> 02:02:00,546\r\nQuite a picnic, huh?\r\nMadritsch.\r\nOskar.\r\n\r\n1278\r\n02:02:00,642 --> 02:02:03,328\r\nI'm running a little late.\r\nThis is taking longer\r\nthan I thought.\r\n\r\n1279\r\n02:02:03,423 --> 02:02:06,493\r\nA drink?\r\nSomething cold.\r\nBowle.\r\n\r\n1280\r\n02:02:06,588 --> 02:02:08,698\r\nThe Bowle.\r\n\r\n1281\r\n02:02:10,328 --> 02:02:13,398\r\nOh, another\r\nbeautiful day.\r\n\r\n1282\r\n02:02:16,083 --> 02:02:18,289\r\nCisza! Spokoj!\r\n\r\n1283\r\n02:02:25,961 --> 02:02:28,167\r\nDie Beladung der Transportwagen\r\nist beendet.\r\n\r\n1284\r\n02:02:28,263 --> 02:02:30,661\r\nWir sind abfahrbereit.\r\n\r\n1285\r\n02:02:30,757 --> 02:02:33,154\r\nWody!\r\nWody!\r\n\r\n1286\r\n02:02:33,154 --> 02:02:36,127\r\nWasser... wasser.\r\n\r\n1287\r\n02:02:42,170 --> 02:02:46,005\r\nWohlsein.\r\nOh, thank you.\r\n\r\n1288\r\n02:02:51,569 --> 02:02:56,652\r\nWhat do you say we get your\r\nfire hoses out here and hose\r\ndown the cars? Thank you.\r\n\r\n1289\r\n02:02:58,665 --> 02:03:00,967\r\nIndulge me.\r\n\r\n1290\r\n02:03:02,406 --> 02:03:04,516\r\nHujar.\r\nYes, sir.\r\n\r\n1291\r\n02:03:04,612 --> 02:03:08,064\r\n- Go bring the fire hoses.\r\n- Where's the fire?\r\n\r\n1292\r\n02:03:11,517 --> 02:03:15,066\r\nIn the windows.\r\nThat's it, that's it.\r\n\r\n1293\r\n02:03:15,161 --> 02:03:19,093\r\nOn the roof.\r\nThat's it, good, good.\r\nIn the window, in the window.\r\n\r\n1294\r\n02:03:21,875 --> 02:03:25,615\r\nCome on. Come on.\r\n\r\n1295\r\n02:03:25,615 --> 02:03:27,534\r\nThat's it, more, more.\r\n\r\n1296\r\n02:03:31,561 --> 02:03:35,302\r\nThat's it, that's it.\r\nMore, more.\r\n\r\n1297\r\n02:03:35,398 --> 02:03:38,850\r\nThis is really cruel, Oskar.\r\nYou are giving them hope.\r\n\r\n1298\r\n02:03:38,850 --> 02:03:42,590\r\nYou shouldn't do that.\r\nThat's cruel!\r\n\r\n1299\r\n02:03:42,687 --> 02:03:46,043\r\nCome on, try and\r\nreach the far end.\r\nLook out--\r\n\r\n1300\r\n02:03:46,140 --> 02:03:49,016\r\nWater! More water!\r\n\r\n1301\r\n02:03:51,223 --> 02:03:54,963\r\nI've got some 200-meter\r\nhoses back at Emalia.\r\n\r\n1302\r\n02:03:55,058 --> 02:03:56,880\r\nI have 20 meters\r\nat home in my garden.\r\n\r\n1303\r\n02:03:56,977 --> 02:03:59,087\r\nWe can reach\r\nthe cars at the end.\r\n\r\n1304\r\n02:03:59,087 --> 02:04:01,484\r\nWhat? What?\r\n\r\n1305\r\n02:04:01,581 --> 02:04:05,705\r\nHuh?\r\n\r\n1306\r\n02:04:05,800 --> 02:04:08,006\r\nHujar.\r\nYeah, sure.\r\n\r\n1307\r\n02:04:25,844 --> 02:04:28,338\r\nDon't forget\r\nthe roof.\r\n\r\n1308\r\n02:04:28,434 --> 02:04:31,119\r\nOn the roof\r\non the other side.\r\n\r\n1309\r\n02:04:31,216 --> 02:04:35,339\r\nWater!\r\n\r\n1310\r\n02:04:37,641 --> 02:04:40,039\r\nScharfuehrer,\r\nevery time the train stops,\r\n\r\n1311\r\n02:04:40,039 --> 02:04:42,436\r\nyou open the doors,\r\nyou give them water, ja?\r\n\r\n1312\r\n02:04:42,436 --> 02:04:45,314\r\nJawohl.\r\nJa. This car!\r\nThis car!\r\n\r\n1313\r\n02:05:08,811 --> 02:05:11,976\r\nI'm not saying you'll\r\nregret it, but you might.\r\n\r\n1314\r\n02:05:12,071 --> 02:05:16,675\r\nYou should be\r\naware of that.\r\nWe will have to risk regret.\r\n\r\n1315\r\n02:05:16,770 --> 02:05:20,415\r\nAll right, sure.\r\nIt's a nice day. I'll go\r\nfor a drive with you.\r\n\r\n1316\r\n02:05:53,982 --> 02:05:56,284\r\nWhat about you?\r\n\r\n1317\r\n02:05:56,381 --> 02:06:00,408\r\nI violated the\r\n\"Race and Resettlement Act.\"\r\n\r\n1318\r\n02:06:00,505 --> 02:06:04,340\r\nThough I doubt\r\nanyone can point out\r\nthe actual provision to me.\r\n\r\n1319\r\n02:06:04,437 --> 02:06:07,601\r\nI kissed a Jewish girl.\r\n\r\n1320\r\n02:06:11,150 --> 02:06:13,931\r\nDid your prick fall off?\r\n\r\n1321\r\n02:06:31,769 --> 02:06:34,743\r\nHe likes women.\r\n\r\n1322\r\n02:06:35,702 --> 02:06:38,771\r\nHe likes\r\ngood-looking women.\r\n\r\n1323\r\n02:06:40,305 --> 02:06:44,429\r\nHe sees a beautiful woman,\r\nhe doesn't think.\r\n\r\n1324\r\n02:06:44,526 --> 02:06:47,210\r\nI mean,\r\n\r\n1325\r\n02:06:47,307 --> 02:06:49,896\r\nhe has so many women.\r\n\r\n1326\r\n02:06:49,896 --> 02:06:52,006\r\nAnd they love him.\r\n\r\n1327\r\n02:06:52,006 --> 02:06:54,979\r\nJa, they love him.\r\nI mean, he is married,\r\nja, but he's--\r\n\r\n1328\r\n02:06:54,979 --> 02:06:59,967\r\nAll right, it's not--\r\nShe was Jewish.\r\nHe shouldn't have done it.\r\n\r\n1329\r\n02:07:00,062 --> 02:07:03,611\r\nBut, you didn't see this girl.\r\n\r\n1330\r\n02:07:03,707 --> 02:07:06,967\r\nI saw this girl.\r\nThis girl was, woof--\r\n\r\n1331\r\n02:07:07,064 --> 02:07:09,174\r\nShe was very good-looking.\r\n\r\n1332\r\n02:07:12,434 --> 02:07:15,120\r\nThey cast a spell on you,\r\nyou know, theJews.\r\n\r\n1333\r\n02:07:15,215 --> 02:07:17,709\r\nWhen you work closely with them,\r\nlike I do, you see this.\r\n\r\n1334\r\n02:07:17,805 --> 02:07:21,546\r\nThey have this power.\r\nIt's like a virus. Some of my men\r\nare infected with this virus.\r\n\r\n1335\r\n02:07:21,546 --> 02:07:23,847\r\nThey should be\r\npitied, not punished.\r\nThey should receive treatment.\r\n\r\n1336\r\n02:07:23,847 --> 02:07:26,821\r\nThis is as real as typhus.\r\nI see this all the time.\r\n\r\n1337\r\n02:07:26,821 --> 02:07:29,794\r\nIt's a matter of money?\r\nHmm?\r\n\r\n1338\r\n02:07:29,889 --> 02:07:32,479\r\nYou're offering me\r\na bribe?\r\n\r\n1339\r\n02:07:34,301 --> 02:07:39,096\r\nA bribe? No. No, please.\r\nIt's a gratuity.\r\n\r\n1340\r\n02:07:39,192 --> 02:07:41,014\r\nHeil Hitler!\r\n\r\n1341\r\n02:07:45,235 --> 02:07:47,440\r\nHello, Amon.\r\n\r\n1342\r\n02:07:49,934 --> 02:07:51,851\r\nSit down.\r\n\r\n1343\r\n02:07:54,537 --> 02:07:58,085\r\nWe give you Jewish girls\r\nat five marks a day, Oskar.\r\n\r\n1344\r\n02:07:58,182 --> 02:08:00,100\r\nYou should kiss us,\r\nnot them.\r\n\r\n1345\r\n02:08:00,196 --> 02:08:04,128\r\nGod forbid you ever get\r\na real taste forJewish skirt.\r\n\r\n1346\r\n02:08:04,224 --> 02:08:07,484\r\nThere's no future in it.\r\nThey don't have a future.\r\n\r\n1347\r\n02:08:07,581 --> 02:08:12,280\r\nThat's not just good,\r\nold-fashioned, Jew-hating talk.\r\n\r\n1348\r\n02:08:12,280 --> 02:08:15,061\r\nIt's policy now.\r\n\r\n1349\r\n02:08:16,297 --> 02:08:20,037\r\nJa, schoen gefangen! Gut!\r\n\r\n1350\r\n02:08:25,504 --> 02:08:29,532\r\nNochmal, ja! Schoen!\r\n\r\n1351\r\n02:08:58,304 --> 02:09:00,798\r\nAlso los! Bewegung!\r\n\r\n1352\r\n02:09:00,894 --> 02:09:04,634\r\nSchneller hier!\r\nZack, zack, zack!\r\n\r\n1353\r\n02:09:04,730 --> 02:09:06,935\r\nBeweg deinen Arsch!\r\n\r\n1354\r\n02:09:07,032 --> 02:09:09,526\r\nDas geht\r\nauch schneller!\r\n\r\n1355\r\n02:09:09,621 --> 02:09:12,498\r\nBewegt euch!\r\nSchlaft nicht ein!\r\n\r\n1356\r\n02:09:21,322 --> 02:09:23,240\r\nWas ist denn hier los?\r\n\r\n1357\r\n02:09:23,336 --> 02:09:25,925\r\nKomm, das kannst du mit\r\nden Haenden machen,\r\nfass da vorn an!\r\n\r\n1358\r\n02:09:25,925 --> 02:09:27,459\r\nHier!\r\n\r\n1359\r\n02:09:27,556 --> 02:09:30,241\r\nLos, raus mit den Fetzen!\r\nDie Kleinteile lass liegen!\r\n\r\n1360\r\n02:09:39,160 --> 02:09:42,805\r\nJetzt macht aber schnell,\r\nverdammt noch mal!\r\nWeg mit den Scheissdingern!\r\n\r\n1361\r\n02:09:51,148 --> 02:09:54,601\r\nSo ist es! Walhalla!\r\nWalhalla laeuft hier!\r\n\r\n1362\r\n02:09:59,684 --> 02:10:01,890\r\nCan you believe this?\r\n\r\n1363\r\n02:10:01,985 --> 02:10:05,151\r\nAs if I don't have enough to do,\r\nthey come up with this?\r\n\r\n1364\r\n02:10:05,247 --> 02:10:09,083\r\nI have to find every rag\r\nburied up here and burn it.\r\n\r\n1365\r\n02:10:09,083 --> 02:10:13,686\r\nThe party's over, Oskar.\r\nThey're closing us down,\r\nsending everybody to Auschwitz.\r\n\r\n1366\r\n02:10:13,783 --> 02:10:16,085\r\nWhen?\r\nI don't know. As soon as\r\nI can arrange the shipments.\r\n\r\n1367\r\n02:10:16,180 --> 02:10:19,825\r\nMaybe 30, 40 days.\r\nThat ought to be fun.\r\n\r\n1368\r\n02:10:39,198 --> 02:10:42,363\r\nI've been talking to Goeth.\r\nI know the destination.\r\n\r\n1369\r\n02:10:42,458 --> 02:10:45,239\r\nThese are\r\nthe evacuation orders.\r\n\r\n1370\r\n02:10:45,336 --> 02:10:48,022\r\nI'm to help organize\r\nthe shipments, put myself\r\non the last train.\r\n\r\n1371\r\n02:10:48,022 --> 02:10:51,090\r\nThat's not what\r\nI was going to say.\r\n\r\n1372\r\n02:10:51,186 --> 02:10:54,830\r\nI made Goeth promise me\r\nhe'd put in a good word for you.\r\n\r\n1373\r\n02:10:54,927 --> 02:10:58,188\r\nNothing bad is going to happen\r\nto you there. You'll receive\r\nspecial treatment.\r\n\r\n1374\r\n02:10:58,283 --> 02:11:02,120\r\nThe directives coming in\r\nfrom Berlin mention \"Special Treatment\"\r\nmore and more often.\r\n\r\n1375\r\n02:11:02,215 --> 02:11:05,860\r\nI'd like to think\r\nthat's not what you mean.\r\nPreferential treatment.\r\n\r\n1376\r\n02:11:05,955 --> 02:11:11,230\r\n- Do we have to invent\r\na whole new language?\r\n- I think so.\r\n\r\n1377\r\n02:11:12,573 --> 02:11:15,067\r\nYou're staying,\r\nI take it.\r\n\r\n1378\r\n02:11:18,903 --> 02:11:23,123\r\nIn Krakow? What on earth for?\r\nWhat for?\r\nYou have a business to run.\r\n\r\n1379\r\n02:11:23,123 --> 02:11:26,768\r\nOf course, you'll have\r\nto hire new workers.\r\nPoles, I guess.\r\n\r\n1380\r\n02:11:26,863 --> 02:11:30,412\r\nThey cost\r\na little more, but--\r\n\r\n1381\r\n02:11:31,371 --> 02:11:33,673\r\nWhat are you going to do?\r\n\r\n1382\r\n02:11:37,413 --> 02:11:40,386\r\nYou run my business.\r\n\r\n1383\r\n02:11:42,496 --> 02:11:44,798\r\nNo, I'm going home.\r\n\r\n1384\r\n02:11:44,894 --> 02:11:50,169\r\nI've done what I came here for.\r\nI've got more money than any man\r\ncould spend in a lifetime.\r\n\r\n1385\r\n02:12:00,527 --> 02:12:05,418\r\nSomeday, this is all\r\ngoing to end, you know.\r\n\r\n1386\r\n02:12:09,253 --> 02:12:11,939\r\nI was going to say\r\nwe'll have a drink then.\r\n\r\n1387\r\n02:12:15,968 --> 02:12:19,420\r\nI think I better\r\nhave it now.\r\n\r\n1388\r\n02:13:50,819 --> 02:13:54,847\r\nI don't understand.\r\nI mean, you want these people?\r\n\r\n1389\r\n02:13:54,943 --> 02:13:57,437\r\n\"These people\"?\r\nMy people,\r\nI want my people.\r\n\r\n1390\r\n02:13:57,532 --> 02:14:00,410\r\nWho are you, Moses?\r\nCome on, what is this?\r\n\r\n1391\r\n02:14:00,506 --> 02:14:03,287\r\nWhere's the money in this?\r\nWhere's the scam?\r\nIt's good business.\r\n\r\n1392\r\n02:14:03,382 --> 02:14:05,589\r\nIt's good business\r\nin your opinion.\r\n\r\n1393\r\n02:14:05,684 --> 02:14:09,617\r\nYou've got to move them,\r\nthe equipment, everything\r\nto Czechoslovakia.\r\n\r\n1394\r\n02:14:09,713 --> 02:14:12,781\r\nPay for all that\r\nand build another camp.\r\nDoesn't make any sense.\r\n\r\n1395\r\n02:14:12,878 --> 02:14:15,946\r\nLook, Amon--\r\nIt's good for me.\r\nYou're not telling me something.\r\n\r\n1396\r\n02:14:16,042 --> 02:14:18,728\r\nI know them.\r\nI'm familiar with them.\r\nI don't have to train them.\r\n\r\n1397\r\n02:14:18,824 --> 02:14:20,550\r\nYou're not telling me something.\r\nIt's good for you.\r\nI'll compensate you.\r\n\r\n1398\r\n02:14:20,550 --> 02:14:23,331\r\nThat's right.\r\nIt's good for the Army.\r\n\r\n1399\r\n02:14:23,428 --> 02:14:25,825\r\nYou know what\r\nI'm going to make?\r\nWhat?\r\n\r\n1400\r\n02:14:25,920 --> 02:14:28,127\r\nArtillery shells.\r\nEveryone is!\r\n\r\n1401\r\n02:14:28,222 --> 02:14:30,044\r\nTank shells,\r\nthey need that.\r\nTanks shells, ja.\r\n\r\n1402\r\n02:14:30,141 --> 02:14:32,538\r\nEverybody's happy.\r\nExcept me.\r\n\r\n1403\r\n02:14:32,635 --> 02:14:35,511\r\nYou're probably\r\nscamming me somehow.\r\n\r\n1404\r\n02:14:35,607 --> 02:14:38,485\r\nIf I'm making 100,\r\nyou've got to be making 300.\r\n\r\n1405\r\n02:14:38,580 --> 02:14:41,842\r\nIf you admit to 300,\r\nthen it's 400 actually.\r\nBut how?\r\n\r\n1406\r\n02:14:41,842 --> 02:14:45,485\r\nI just told you.\r\nYou did, but you didn't.\r\n\r\n1407\r\n02:14:46,733 --> 02:14:49,609\r\nAh, ja, all right,\r\ndon't tell me.\r\n\r\n1408\r\n02:14:49,609 --> 02:14:53,733\r\nI'll go along with it.\r\nIt's just irritating\r\nI can't work it out.\r\n\r\n1409\r\n02:14:53,830 --> 02:14:58,337\r\nLook, all you have\r\nto do is tell me\r\nwhat it's worth to you.\r\n\r\n1410\r\n02:14:58,434 --> 02:15:01,023\r\nWhat's a person\r\nworth to you?\r\nNo, no, no, no.\r\n\r\n1411\r\n02:15:01,118 --> 02:15:03,996\r\nWhat's one worth to you?\r\n\r\n1412\r\n02:15:11,573 --> 02:15:15,025\r\nPoldek Pfefferberg.\r\nMila Pfefferberg.\r\n\r\n1413\r\n02:15:15,121 --> 02:15:18,381\r\nAnd, uh--\r\n\r\n1414\r\n02:15:18,381 --> 02:15:20,300\r\nUh, Stagel, Stagel--\r\n\r\n1415\r\n02:15:20,396 --> 02:15:22,313\r\nPaul.\r\nPaul Stagel.\r\n\r\n1416\r\n02:15:22,313 --> 02:15:24,904\r\nDoctor.\r\n\r\n1417\r\n02:15:24,904 --> 02:15:29,699\r\nThe investors.\r\nI want all of them.\r\nYes, sir.\r\n\r\n1418\r\n02:15:29,699 --> 02:15:32,288\r\nUh, Fischer.\r\nIsmail Fischer.\r\n\r\n1419\r\n02:15:32,384 --> 02:15:35,454\r\nFischer, Ismail.\r\n\r\n1420\r\n02:15:35,549 --> 02:15:38,426\r\nJosef Scharf.\r\nOne moment, sir.\r\nI'm sorry, sir.\r\n\r\n1421\r\n02:15:38,522 --> 02:15:40,440\r\nCome on, Stern.\r\nScharf, Scharf.\r\n\r\n1422\r\n02:15:43,413 --> 02:15:47,345\r\nThe children.\r\nAll the children.\r\n\r\n1423\r\n02:15:51,469 --> 02:15:53,292\r\nHerbert Stier.\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\n1424\r\n02:15:53,387 --> 02:15:57,416\r\nHow many?\r\nFour hundred, 450.\r\n\r\n1425\r\n02:15:59,909 --> 02:16:01,827\r\nMore, more.\r\n\r\n1426\r\n02:16:06,910 --> 02:16:09,404\r\nGood morning.\r\n\r\n1427\r\n02:16:24,749 --> 02:16:29,928\r\nThink of Feigenbaum, Jakob.\r\nWolf. Wolf Wein.\r\n\r\n1428\r\n02:16:33,956 --> 02:16:37,792\r\nLutek, Jakob,\r\nNacha. Yes? Nacha.\r\n\r\n1429\r\n02:16:37,792 --> 02:16:39,711\r\nNacha, that's right.\r\n\r\n1430\r\n02:16:39,711 --> 02:16:42,300\r\nAnd Wolf.\r\n\r\n1431\r\n02:16:42,395 --> 02:16:44,794\r\nHow many?\r\n\r\n1432\r\n02:16:46,327 --> 02:16:49,589\r\nSix hundred.\r\nMore.\r\n\r\n1433\r\n02:16:49,589 --> 02:16:52,274\r\nYou can do\r\nthe same thing I'm doing.\r\n\r\n1434\r\n02:16:52,274 --> 02:16:54,960\r\nYou might even\r\nmake money at it.\r\nI don't know.\r\n\r\n1435\r\n02:16:54,960 --> 02:16:57,645\r\nCome on, Julius, I know\r\nabout the extra food\r\nand clothes you give them.\r\n\r\n1436\r\n02:16:57,741 --> 02:17:00,714\r\nPaid for out of your own pocket.\r\nIf we make a combined approach,\r\n\r\n1437\r\n02:17:00,809 --> 02:17:03,208\r\nwe could get more than\r\n4,000 out, mine and yours.\r\nOskar--\r\n\r\n1438\r\n02:17:03,208 --> 02:17:06,468\r\nWe could relocate them\r\nin something like safety,\r\nin Moravia.\r\n\r\n1439\r\n02:17:06,564 --> 02:17:08,962\r\nI don't know.\r\n\r\n1440\r\n02:17:11,072 --> 02:17:14,812\r\nHow many cigarettes\r\nhave you smoked tonight?\r\nToo many.\r\n\r\n1441\r\n02:17:14,908 --> 02:17:19,320\r\nFor every one--\r\nyou smoke, I smoke half.\r\n\r\n1442\r\n02:17:19,415 --> 02:17:21,909\r\nI've done all I can.\r\nI will not accept that.\r\n\r\n1443\r\n02:17:21,909 --> 02:17:25,074\r\nNo, Oskar,\r\nI can't do anymore.\r\nI will not accept that.\r\n\r\n1444\r\n02:17:25,170 --> 02:17:26,800\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n1445\r\n02:17:36,391 --> 02:17:38,980\r\nHow many? How many?\r\nEight hundred and fifty,\r\ngive or take.\r\n\r\n1446\r\n02:17:39,077 --> 02:17:42,817\r\nGive or take what, Stern?\r\nCount them. How many?\r\n\r\n1447\r\n02:17:52,983 --> 02:17:56,435\r\nThat's it.\r\nYou can finish that page.\r\n\r\n1448\r\n02:18:01,039 --> 02:18:04,779\r\nWhat... did... Goeth...\r\nsay about this?\r\n\r\n1449\r\n02:18:04,779 --> 02:18:08,520\r\nYou just told him how\r\nmany people you needed and--\r\n\r\n1450\r\n02:18:11,493 --> 02:18:13,699\r\nYou're not buying them.\r\n\r\n1451\r\n02:18:16,000 --> 02:18:18,974\r\nYou're buying them?\r\nYou're paying him\r\nfor each of these names?\r\n\r\n1452\r\n02:18:19,069 --> 02:18:22,331\r\nIf you were still working\r\nfor me, I'd expect you\r\nto talk me out of it.\r\n\r\n1453\r\n02:18:22,426 --> 02:18:25,687\r\nIt's costing me\r\na fortune.\r\n\r\n1454\r\n02:18:25,687 --> 02:18:29,619\r\nFinish the page and leave\r\none space at the bottom.\r\n\r\n1455\r\n02:18:50,814 --> 02:18:52,925\r\nLook.\r\n\r\n1456\r\n02:18:58,295 --> 02:19:02,323\r\nThe list is\r\nan absolute good.\r\n\r\n1457\r\n02:19:02,420 --> 02:19:05,105\r\nThe list... is life.\r\n\r\n1458\r\n02:19:06,639 --> 02:19:11,819\r\nAll around its margins\r\nlies the gulf.\r\n\r\n1459\r\n02:19:11,914 --> 02:19:15,654\r\nOskar, there's\r\na clerical error here\r\nat the bottom of the last page.\r\n\r\n1460\r\n02:19:15,751 --> 02:19:18,340\r\nNo, there's one more name\r\nI want to put there.\r\n\r\n1461\r\n02:19:18,435 --> 02:19:22,751\r\nI'll never fid a maid as well\r\ntrained as her at Brinnlitz.\r\nThey are all country girls.\r\n\r\n1462\r\n02:19:22,848 --> 02:19:24,766\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n1463\r\n02:19:34,068 --> 02:19:35,890\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n1464\r\n02:19:35,987 --> 02:19:38,000\r\nOne hand of 21.\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n1465\r\n02:19:38,000 --> 02:19:40,878\r\nIf you win, I pay you\r\n7,400 Reichsmark.\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n1466\r\n02:19:40,973 --> 02:19:44,235\r\nHit a natural,\r\nI make it 14,800.\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n1467\r\n02:19:44,331 --> 02:19:47,112\r\nIf I win,\r\nthe girl goes on my list.\r\n\r\n1468\r\n02:19:47,207 --> 02:19:50,948\r\nI can't wager Helen\r\nin a card game.\r\nWhy not?\r\n\r\n1469\r\n02:19:51,044 --> 02:19:53,922\r\nWouldn't be right.\r\nShe's just going to Auschwitz\r\non Number Two anyway.\r\n\r\n1470\r\n02:19:54,017 --> 02:19:56,511\r\nWhat difference\r\ndoes it make?\r\nShe's not going to Auschwitz.\r\n\r\n1471\r\n02:19:56,606 --> 02:20:00,251\r\nI'd never do that to her.\r\nNo, I want her to come back\r\nto Vienna with me.\r\n\r\n1472\r\n02:20:00,347 --> 02:20:03,224\r\nI want her to come\r\nto work for me there.\r\n\r\n1473\r\n02:20:03,319 --> 02:20:07,636\r\nI want to grow old\r\nwith her.\r\nAre you mad?\r\n\r\n1474\r\n02:20:07,732 --> 02:20:13,102\r\nAmon, you can't take her\r\nto Vienna with you.\r\nNo, of course I can't.\r\n\r\n1475\r\n02:20:13,102 --> 02:20:16,651\r\nThat's what I'd like to do.\r\n\r\n1476\r\n02:20:16,651 --> 02:20:21,830\r\nWhat I can do, if I'm\r\nany sort of a man, is the\r\nnext most merciful thing.\r\n\r\n1477\r\n02:20:21,925 --> 02:20:26,529\r\nI should take her into the woods\r\nand shoot her painlessly\r\nin the back of the head.\r\n\r\n1478\r\n02:20:36,025 --> 02:20:39,477\r\nWhat was it you said\r\nfor a natural 21?\r\n\r\n1479\r\n02:20:39,573 --> 02:20:42,738\r\nWas it 14,800?\r\n\r\n1480\r\n02:20:42,833 --> 02:20:45,040\r\nSchindlerjuden to these tables!\r\nSay your names clearly.\r\n\r\n1481\r\n02:20:45,998 --> 02:20:49,451\r\nWe are the family Dresner.\r\nJuda, Jonas,\r\n\r\n1482\r\n02:20:49,451 --> 02:20:51,753\r\nDonata and Chaja.\r\n\r\n1483\r\n02:20:51,848 --> 02:20:55,301\r\nWe are Rosners.\r\nHenry, Manci--\r\nAnd Leo.\r\n\r\n1484\r\n02:20:55,398 --> 02:20:57,412\r\nAnd our son.\r\nI am Olek.\r\n\r\n1485\r\n02:20:58,274 --> 02:21:00,096\r\nMaria Mischel.\r\n\r\n1486\r\n02:21:00,193 --> 02:21:02,878\r\nChaim Nowak.\r\n\r\n1487\r\n02:21:02,878 --> 02:21:05,084\r\nWulkan, Markus.\r\n\r\n1488\r\n02:21:05,179 --> 02:21:07,002\r\nMichael Lemper.\r\n\r\n1489\r\n02:21:08,537 --> 02:21:10,454\r\nItzhak Stern.\r\n\r\n1490\r\n02:21:10,551 --> 02:21:13,907\r\nRebeka and Josef Bau.\r\n\r\n1491\r\n02:21:13,907 --> 02:21:16,593\r\nRosalia Nussbaum.\r\nWilhelm Nussbaum.\r\n\r\n1492\r\n02:21:16,593 --> 02:21:19,278\r\nJakob Levartov.\r\n\r\n1493\r\n02:21:19,374 --> 02:21:22,060\r\nFarber, Rosa.\r\nFarber, Arje.\r\n\r\n1494\r\n02:21:22,060 --> 02:21:25,224\r\n...Sara.\r\nFriehof, Fischel.\r\n\r\n1495\r\n02:21:25,320 --> 02:21:27,910\r\nMietek Pemper.\r\n\r\n1496\r\n02:21:28,005 --> 02:21:30,691\r\nPoldek and Mila Pfefferberg.\r\n\r\n1497\r\n02:21:30,691 --> 02:21:33,376\r\nHorowitz, Dolek.\r\n\r\n1498\r\n02:21:33,376 --> 02:21:35,774\r\nAdam Levy.\r\n\r\n1499\r\n02:21:35,870 --> 02:21:38,172\r\nMarcel Goldberg.\r\n\r\n1500\r\n02:21:38,267 --> 02:21:41,241\r\nKlipstein, Isak David.\r\n\r\n1501\r\n02:21:41,241 --> 02:21:43,542\r\nAltmann, Eduard.\r\n\r\n1502\r\n02:21:43,542 --> 02:21:45,557\r\nGrunberg, Miriam.\r\n\r\n1503\r\n02:21:45,652 --> 02:21:47,666\r\nLuftig, Eliasz.\r\n\r\n1504\r\n02:21:47,762 --> 02:21:49,681\r\nHilmann, Eduard.\r\n\r\n1505\r\n02:21:49,776 --> 02:21:51,694\r\nErna Rothberg.\r\n\r\n1506\r\n02:21:51,694 --> 02:21:54,476\r\nZuckermann, Jetti.\r\n\r\n1507\r\n02:21:54,572 --> 02:21:56,778\r\nHelen Hirsch.\r\n\r\n1508\r\n02:21:58,888 --> 02:22:02,628\r\nThe worst is over.\r\n\r\n1509\r\n02:22:02,723 --> 02:22:06,464\r\nMen to this transport\r\nand women to this transport.\r\n\r\n1510\r\n02:22:06,560 --> 02:22:11,259\r\nBe careful.\r\nMen to this transport and\r\nwomen to this transport.\r\n\r\n1511\r\n02:22:11,355 --> 02:22:15,479\r\nWatch your step.\r\nMen to this transport\r\nand women to this transport.\r\n\r\n1512\r\n02:22:52,308 --> 02:22:56,335\r\nWonderful, Olek, wonderful.\r\n\r\n1513\r\n02:22:56,335 --> 02:23:00,556\r\nYou know how we make\r\nice into water?\r\n\r\n1514\r\n02:23:00,651 --> 02:23:03,816\r\nOlek, get another one!\r\n\r\n1515\r\n02:23:40,548 --> 02:23:43,234\r\nAlle in eine Einzelreihe\r\naufstellen!\r\n\r\n1516\r\n02:23:43,330 --> 02:23:48,413\r\nYou'll be pleased with\r\nthe level of efficiency\r\nI get from these workers.\r\n\r\n1517\r\n02:23:50,043 --> 02:23:52,345\r\nBudzyn, under my command,\r\n\r\n1518\r\n02:23:52,345 --> 02:23:55,414\r\nwas the envy\r\nof every other commandant\r\nin the labor camp system.\r\n\r\n1519\r\n02:23:55,509 --> 02:23:56,469\r\nThe prisoners,\r\nhowever--\r\nExcuse me.\r\n\r\n1520\r\n02:23:56,565 --> 02:23:59,250\r\nThey would have rather\r\nbeen somewhere else.\r\n\r\n1521\r\n02:24:12,772 --> 02:24:16,609\r\nThe train with the women\r\nhas already left Plaszow...\r\n\r\n1522\r\n02:24:16,706 --> 02:24:20,062\r\nand will be arriving\r\nhere very shortly.\r\n\r\n1523\r\n02:24:20,158 --> 02:24:22,747\r\nI know you've had\r\na long journey.\r\n\r\n1524\r\n02:24:22,747 --> 02:24:25,913\r\nBut it's only a short walk\r\nfurther to the factory...\r\n\r\n1525\r\n02:24:26,008 --> 02:24:31,186\r\nwhere hot soup and bread\r\nis waiting for you.\r\n\r\n1526\r\n02:24:31,283 --> 02:24:33,297\r\nWelcome to Brinnlitz!\r\n\r\n1527\r\n02:24:42,504 --> 02:24:45,957\r\nBeans in tsunt?\r\nBeans are the best.\r\n\r\n1528\r\n02:24:45,957 --> 02:24:47,970\r\nI don't like beans.\r\n\r\n1529\r\n02:24:48,067 --> 02:24:51,807\r\nBeans and meat\r\nand potatoes and bread.\r\n\r\n1530\r\n02:24:51,807 --> 02:24:53,917\r\nThat's not the way\r\nyou make tsunt.\r\n\r\n1531\r\n02:24:57,466 --> 02:25:00,726\r\nEggs in tsunt?\r\nYes!\r\n\r\n1532\r\n02:25:03,316 --> 02:25:06,097\r\nI don't like tsunt.\r\nNo, you don't.\r\n\r\n1533\r\n02:25:06,097 --> 02:25:11,084\r\nWhat do you like?\r\nI like caviar.\r\n\r\n1534\r\n02:25:11,180 --> 02:25:13,578\r\nOne day on the fire.\r\n\r\n1535\r\n02:26:16,684 --> 02:26:18,986\r\nAlle vorm Wagen\r\nin Position bleiben.\r\n\r\n1536\r\n02:26:20,424 --> 02:26:23,685\r\nAlle in der Gruppe\r\nzusammenbleiben.\r\n\r\n1537\r\n02:26:23,685 --> 02:26:27,809\r\nWegbleiben vom Wagen!\r\nWegbleiben vom Wagen!\r\n\r\n1538\r\n02:26:27,906 --> 02:26:30,207\r\nWegbleiben vom Wagen,\r\nhab ich gesagt!\r\n\r\n1539\r\n02:26:32,317 --> 02:26:34,619\r\nBagaze zostawic!\r\n\r\n1540\r\n02:26:36,057 --> 02:26:38,838\r\nSchneller!\r\nDalli, dalli, dalli!\r\n\r\n1541\r\n02:26:38,935 --> 02:26:41,045\r\nWas ist da hinten los!\r\n\r\n1542\r\n02:26:43,538 --> 02:26:45,456\r\nSchnell!\r\n\r\n1543\r\n02:26:49,964 --> 02:26:54,087\r\nLos, 'raus mit euch.\r\nZack, zack, zack! 'Raus!\r\n\r\n1544\r\n02:26:54,184 --> 02:26:59,746\r\nDreissig, fuenfunddreissig,\r\nvierzig, fuenfundvierzig.\r\n\r\n1545\r\n02:26:59,842 --> 02:27:01,664\r\nAussteigen!\r\n\r\n1546\r\n02:27:01,761 --> 02:27:04,062\r\n'Rausgehen!\r\n'Rausgehen!\r\n\r\n1547\r\n02:27:04,158 --> 02:27:06,939\r\nSchneller!\r\n'Rausgehen!\r\n\r\n1548\r\n02:27:10,104 --> 02:27:12,790\r\nAlle 'raus!\r\n\r\n1549\r\n02:27:12,790 --> 02:27:16,434\r\nWhere are the listmakers?\r\nWhere are the tables?\r\n\r\n1550\r\n02:27:19,216 --> 02:27:21,900\r\nMove the line!\r\n\r\n1551\r\n02:27:21,997 --> 02:27:24,299\r\n'Raus mit euch!\r\n\r\n1552\r\n02:27:24,394 --> 02:27:26,696\r\nHopp, hopp!\r\n\r\n1553\r\n02:27:26,792 --> 02:27:28,806\r\n...bagaze w wagonach!\r\n\r\n1554\r\n02:27:28,902 --> 02:27:32,163\r\n- Dalli! 'Rausgehen!\r\n- Schneller!\r\n\r\n1555\r\n02:27:32,163 --> 02:27:34,560\r\nZostawcie bagaze w wagonach!\r\n\r\n1556\r\n02:27:34,560 --> 02:27:36,958\r\nSchneller!\r\n\r\n1557\r\n02:27:36,958 --> 02:27:38,781\r\nLos, ein bisschen\r\nschneller!\r\n\r\n1558\r\n02:27:38,876 --> 02:27:41,657\r\nMama, where are we?\r\n\r\n1559\r\n02:27:42,329 --> 02:27:45,877\r\nSeventeen, 18, 20--\r\nThey're in Auschwitz.\r\n\r\n1560\r\n02:27:45,973 --> 02:27:49,138\r\nThe train was\r\nnever routed here.\r\nApaperwork mistake.\r\n\r\n1561\r\n02:27:56,139 --> 02:27:57,674\r\nSzybciej! Szybko!\r\n\r\n1562\r\n02:27:57,769 --> 02:28:00,071\r\nDie Schuhe werfen!\r\n\r\n1563\r\n02:28:12,539 --> 02:28:15,320\r\nSchneller!\r\nSchneller!\r\nUbrania skladac!\r\n\r\n1564\r\n02:28:17,431 --> 02:28:20,020\r\nPod prysznic!\r\nZieht euch aus!\r\nBewegung!\r\n\r\n1565\r\n02:28:20,116 --> 02:28:22,706\r\nBewegt euch!\r\nStellt euch auf\r\nund zieht euch aus!\r\n\r\n1566\r\n02:28:22,801 --> 02:28:25,775\r\nRozbierac sie tam szybciej!\r\nSchneller!\r\n\r\n1567\r\n02:28:27,117 --> 02:28:29,899\r\nSzybko sie rozbierac.\r\n\r\n1568\r\n02:28:29,994 --> 02:28:34,023\r\nDostaniecie mydlo\r\ni recznik i pojdziecie\r\npod prysznic do dezynfeckji!\r\n\r\n1569\r\n02:28:34,118 --> 02:28:36,420\r\nSzybko sie rozbierac!\r\n\r\n1570\r\n02:28:39,969 --> 02:28:42,846\r\nSchneller!\r\nZabierajcie to\r\nmydlo i szybko!\r\n\r\n1571\r\n02:28:42,846 --> 02:28:46,011\r\nZieht euch schneller aus!\r\nBewegung!\r\n\r\n1572\r\n02:28:51,094 --> 02:28:54,450\r\nSzybko!\r\nSzybko!\r\nSofort hinein!\r\n\r\n1573\r\n02:28:54,546 --> 02:28:57,136\r\nPojdziecie pod prysznic!\r\nSzybko!\r\n\r\n1574\r\n02:28:57,232 --> 02:28:59,053\r\nSchneller!\r\n\r\n1575\r\n02:28:59,150 --> 02:29:01,836\r\nHineim zum Bad!\r\nSchneller!\r\n\r\n1576\r\n02:29:03,849 --> 02:29:07,878\r\nSchneller!\r\nSchneller!\r\n\r\n1577\r\n02:29:07,878 --> 02:29:10,659\r\nSzybko!\r\nSzybko!\r\n\r\n1578\r\n02:29:10,754 --> 02:29:12,673\r\nTu wchodzic!\r\n\r\n1579\r\n02:31:31,737 --> 02:31:33,655\r\nBlick hinunter!\r\n\r\n1580\r\n02:31:36,341 --> 02:31:39,027\r\nDie Hand auf\r\ndie Schulter!\r\n\r\n1581\r\n02:31:39,122 --> 02:31:42,000\r\nHow old are you, Mother?\r\nSixty-eight.\r\n\r\n1582\r\n02:31:42,095 --> 02:31:46,986\r\nCough for me, Mother.\r\nThey say to fall against\r\nthe fence is a kindness.\r\n\r\n1583\r\n02:31:47,083 --> 02:31:50,056\r\nDon't kill yourself\r\nagainst the fence, Clara.\r\n\r\n1584\r\n02:31:50,151 --> 02:31:53,891\r\nIf you do, you'll never\r\nknow what happened to you.\r\n\r\n1585\r\n02:31:53,988 --> 02:31:58,112\r\nHow old are you,\r\nMother?\r\nSixty-six, sir.\r\n\r\n1586\r\n02:31:58,112 --> 02:32:00,317\r\nSir?\r\nGood morning.\r\n\r\n1587\r\n02:32:00,317 --> 02:32:03,195\r\nA mistake has been made.\r\nWe are not supposed\r\nto be here.\r\n\r\n1588\r\n02:32:03,290 --> 02:32:06,838\r\nWe work for Oskar Schindler.\r\nWe are SchindlerJews.\r\n\r\n1589\r\n02:32:06,935 --> 02:32:10,291\r\nWho is Oskar Schindler?\r\nHe had a factory\r\nin Krakow.\r\n\r\n1590\r\n02:32:10,388 --> 02:32:14,607\r\nEnamelware.\r\nA potmaker.\r\n\r\n1591\r\n02:32:14,607 --> 02:32:16,717\r\nHow old are you, Mother?\r\n\r\n1592\r\n02:32:21,130 --> 02:32:25,444\r\nYou are not\r\nthe only industrialist\r\nwho needs labor,\r\n\r\n1593\r\n02:32:25,541 --> 02:32:29,089\r\nHerr Schindler.\r\n\r\n1594\r\n02:32:29,186 --> 02:32:31,967\r\nI remember\r\nearlier this year,\r\nI.G. Farben ordered...\r\n\r\n1595\r\n02:32:32,062 --> 02:32:37,625\r\na trainload of Hungarians\r\nfor his chemical factory.\r\n\r\n1596\r\n02:32:37,721 --> 02:32:41,461\r\nThe train came in\r\nthrough the archway,\r\n\r\n1597\r\n02:32:41,557 --> 02:32:46,544\r\nand the officer in charge\r\nof the selection went\r\nimmediately to work...\r\n\r\n1598\r\n02:32:46,640 --> 02:32:49,997\r\nand sent 2,000\r\nof them...\r\n\r\n1599\r\n02:32:50,092 --> 02:32:53,066\r\nstraightaway\r\nto Special Treatment.\r\n\r\n1600\r\n02:32:53,162 --> 02:32:58,148\r\nIt is not my task\r\nto interfere with the processes\r\nthat take place down here.\r\n\r\n1601\r\n02:32:59,875 --> 02:33:05,150\r\nWhy do you think I can\r\nhelp you if I can't\r\nhelp I.G. Farben?\r\n\r\n1602\r\n02:33:05,150 --> 02:33:07,452\r\nAllow me to express\r\nthe reason.\r\n\r\n1603\r\n02:33:16,467 --> 02:33:19,632\r\nI'm not making\r\nany judgment about you.\r\n\r\n1604\r\n02:33:19,728 --> 02:33:23,277\r\nIt's just that I know\r\nthat in the coming months...\r\n\r\n1605\r\n02:33:23,372 --> 02:33:27,401\r\nwe're all going\r\nto need portable wealth.\r\n\r\n1606\r\n02:33:28,455 --> 02:33:31,045\r\nI could have you arrested.\r\n\r\n1607\r\n02:33:31,141 --> 02:33:35,457\r\nI'm protected\r\nby powerful friends.\r\nYou should know that.\r\n\r\n1608\r\n02:33:38,526 --> 02:33:42,362\r\nI do not say\r\nI am accepting them.\r\n\r\n1609\r\n02:33:42,458 --> 02:33:47,061\r\nAll I say is,\r\nI'm not comfortable\r\nwith them on the table.\r\n\r\n1610\r\n02:34:00,392 --> 02:34:03,558\r\nI have a shipment\r\ncoming in tomorrow.\r\n\r\n1611\r\n02:34:03,653 --> 02:34:05,955\r\nI'll cut you\r\n300 units from it.\r\n\r\n1612\r\n02:34:05,955 --> 02:34:09,791\r\nNew ones.\r\nThese are fresh.\r\n\r\n1613\r\n02:34:13,340 --> 02:34:16,600\r\nThe train comes,\r\nwe turn it around.\r\nMmm, yes, yes.\r\n\r\n1614\r\n02:34:16,600 --> 02:34:18,806\r\nIt's yours.\r\nI understand.\r\n\r\n1615\r\n02:34:18,902 --> 02:34:21,396\r\nI want these.\r\n\r\n1616\r\n02:34:23,697 --> 02:34:26,479\r\nYou shouldn't\r\nget stuck on names.\r\n\r\n1617\r\n02:34:33,960 --> 02:34:38,084\r\nThat's right. It creates\r\na lot of paperwork.\r\n\r\n1618\r\n02:34:38,563 --> 02:34:42,208\r\nZoldinger, Ernestina!\r\nWaldergrun, Hilda!\r\n\r\n1619\r\n02:34:42,303 --> 02:34:44,413\r\nWaldergrun, Leonora!\r\n\r\n1620\r\n02:34:44,510 --> 02:34:47,770\r\nLaast, Anna!\r\nPfefferberg, Mila!\r\n\r\n1621\r\n02:34:47,866 --> 02:34:51,223\r\nDresner, Chaja!\r\nDresner, Danka!\r\n\r\n1622\r\n02:34:51,318 --> 02:34:54,868\r\nNussbaum, Sidonia!\r\nRosner, Manci!\r\n\r\n1623\r\n02:34:54,963 --> 02:34:59,951\r\nHirsch, Helen!\r\nGrosz, Chaja Sara!\r\nSeelenfreund, Estella!\r\n\r\n1624\r\n02:35:12,898 --> 02:35:17,022\r\nSchneller laufen!\r\nSchneller laufen! Schneller!\r\n\r\n1625\r\n02:35:17,117 --> 02:35:21,049\r\nSchneller!\r\nSchneller!\r\nMach schon! Voran!\r\n\r\n1626\r\n02:35:23,064 --> 02:35:25,845\r\nLos, los, los!\r\nSchneller!\r\n\r\n1627\r\n02:35:27,572 --> 02:35:31,504\r\n- Schneller!\r\n- Bewegt euch!\r\n\r\n1628\r\n02:35:31,599 --> 02:35:34,572\r\nBojcie sie!\r\nBojcie sie!\r\n\r\n1629\r\n02:35:38,312 --> 02:35:42,437\r\nNo! No! No!\r\n\r\n1630\r\n02:35:46,753 --> 02:35:50,493\r\nMaedchen, los jetzt aber!\r\nJetzt aber Tempo!\r\n\r\n1631\r\n02:35:56,247 --> 02:35:59,796\r\nNo! No! No!\r\n\r\n1632\r\n02:35:59,892 --> 02:36:03,249\r\nDanka! Danka! Danka!\r\n\r\n1633\r\n02:36:03,344 --> 02:36:05,551\r\nNo! No! No!\r\n\r\n1634\r\n02:36:07,565 --> 02:36:10,921\r\nHey! Hey! Hey!\r\nWhat are you doing?\r\n\r\n1635\r\n02:36:11,018 --> 02:36:16,101\r\nThese are mine!\r\nThese are my workers!\r\nThey should be on my train!\r\n\r\n1636\r\n02:36:16,101 --> 02:36:18,690\r\nThey're skilled\r\nmunitions workers!\r\nThey're essential!\r\n\r\n1637\r\n02:36:18,690 --> 02:36:22,430\r\nEssential girls!\r\n\r\n1638\r\n02:36:22,526 --> 02:36:27,609\r\nTheir fingers polish the insides\r\nof shell metal casings.\r\n\r\n1639\r\n02:36:27,705 --> 02:36:31,445\r\nHow else am I\r\nto polish the inside of\r\na .45 millimeter shell casing?\r\n\r\n1640\r\n02:36:31,541 --> 02:36:35,186\r\nYou tell me.\r\nYou tell me!\r\n\r\n1641\r\n02:36:35,281 --> 02:36:39,885\r\nBack on the train!\r\nBack on the train!\r\n\r\n1642\r\n02:38:30,082 --> 02:38:34,301\r\nUnder Department \"W\"\r\nprovisions,\r\n\r\n1643\r\n02:38:34,301 --> 02:38:38,521\r\nit is unlawful to kill\r\na worker without just cause.\r\n\r\n1644\r\n02:38:38,617 --> 02:38:41,494\r\nUnder the Businesses\r\nCompensation Fund,\r\n\r\n1645\r\n02:38:41,591 --> 02:38:45,715\r\nI am entitled to file\r\ndamage claims for such deaths.\r\n\r\n1646\r\n02:38:45,810 --> 02:38:48,591\r\nIf you shoot\r\nwithout thinking,\r\n\r\n1647\r\n02:38:48,688 --> 02:38:52,236\r\nyou go to prison,\r\nI get paid.\r\n\r\n1648\r\n02:38:52,331 --> 02:38:54,922\r\nThat's how it works.\r\n\r\n1649\r\n02:38:54,922 --> 02:38:59,141\r\nSo, there will be no\r\nsummary executions here.\r\n\r\n1650\r\n02:39:00,868 --> 02:39:05,472\r\nThere will be no\r\ninterference of any kind\r\nwith production.\r\n\r\n1651\r\n02:39:05,567 --> 02:39:10,362\r\nIn hopes of ensuring that,\r\nguards will no longer be\r\nallowed on the factory floor...\r\n\r\n1652\r\n02:39:10,458 --> 02:39:13,815\r\nwithout my authorization.\r\n\r\n1653\r\n02:39:18,611 --> 02:39:22,638\r\nFor your cooperation,\r\nyou have my gratitude.\r\n\r\n1654\r\n02:39:23,694 --> 02:39:25,899\r\nCome on, come.\r\n\r\n1655\r\n02:39:25,995 --> 02:39:28,297\r\nMensch, seitJahren hab' ich\r\nso etwas nicht mehr gesehen.\r\n\r\n1656\r\n02:39:28,393 --> 02:39:31,942\r\nCome on, boys, come.\r\nGuck dir mal die Buddeln an!\r\n\r\n1657\r\n02:39:32,325 --> 02:39:36,736\r\nEt dimitte nobis debita nostra,\r\n\r\n1658\r\n02:39:36,833 --> 02:39:40,573\r\nsicut et nos dimittimus...\r\n\r\n1659\r\n02:39:40,669 --> 02:39:45,081\r\n...quotidianum da nobis hodie,\r\n\r\n1660\r\n02:39:45,081 --> 02:39:49,588\r\net dimitte nobis\r\ndebita nostra...\r\n\r\n1661\r\n02:39:49,588 --> 02:39:52,945\r\nsicut et nos dimittimus...\r\n\r\n1662\r\n02:39:53,040 --> 02:39:55,822\r\ndebitoribus nostris--\r\n\r\n1663\r\n02:39:55,918 --> 02:40:01,097\r\nNo doorman or maitre d'\r\nwill ever mistake you again.\r\n\r\n1664\r\n02:40:01,193 --> 02:40:03,590\r\nI promise.\r\n\r\n1665\r\n02:40:03,687 --> 02:40:05,797\r\n...sed libera nos a malo.\r\n\r\n1666\r\n02:40:07,427 --> 02:40:10,304\r\nItzhak.\r\n\r\n1667\r\n02:40:10,400 --> 02:40:14,045\r\nThis is Itzhak Stern,\r\nmy accountant. Itzhak--\r\nYou must be Mrs. Schindler.\r\n\r\n1668\r\n02:40:14,140 --> 02:40:16,537\r\nIt's a pleasure.\r\nEmilie has volunteered\r\nto work in the clinic.\r\n\r\n1669\r\n02:40:16,634 --> 02:40:18,456\r\nVery generous\r\nof you.\r\nI know.\r\n\r\n1670\r\n02:40:18,552 --> 02:40:21,141\r\nWe need to talk\r\nwhen you have a moment.\r\n\r\n1671\r\n02:40:21,141 --> 02:40:23,635\r\nThis is my wife, Stern.\r\nI don't keep any secrets\r\nfrom my spouse.\r\n\r\n1672\r\n02:40:23,731 --> 02:40:26,704\r\nOskar, please, attend\r\nto business. It's much\r\nmore attractive.\r\n\r\n1673\r\n02:40:26,800 --> 02:40:28,622\r\nMadam.\r\nHello.\r\n\r\n1674\r\n02:40:28,718 --> 02:40:31,211\r\nWhat is it?\r\nWe received an angry complaint\r\nfrom the Armaments Board.\r\n\r\n1675\r\n02:40:31,308 --> 02:40:33,418\r\nThe artillery shells,\r\ntank shells, rocket casings--\r\n\r\n1676\r\n02:40:33,418 --> 02:40:36,774\r\nApparently all of them have\r\nfailed quality control tests.\r\nThat's to be expected.\r\n\r\n1677\r\n02:40:36,870 --> 02:40:40,226\r\nStart-up problems.\r\nThis isn't pots and pans.\r\nThis is a precise business.\r\n\r\n1678\r\n02:40:40,226 --> 02:40:41,761\r\nI'll write them\r\na letter.\r\nThey're withholding payment.\r\n\r\n1679\r\n02:40:41,857 --> 02:40:45,885\r\nSure, so would I, so would you.\r\nI wouldn't worry. We'll get it\r\nright one of these days.\r\n\r\n1680\r\n02:40:45,885 --> 02:40:49,817\r\nThere's a rumor\r\nyou've been going around\r\nmiscalibrating the machines.\r\n\r\n1681\r\n02:40:50,489 --> 02:40:54,900\r\nThey could shut us down,\r\nsend us back to Auschwitz.\r\n\r\n1682\r\n02:40:55,572 --> 02:40:58,450\r\nI'll call around, find out\r\nwhere we can buy shells.\r\n\r\n1683\r\n02:40:58,545 --> 02:41:01,422\r\nPass them off as ours.\r\nI don't see the difference\r\nwhether they're made here--\r\n\r\n1684\r\n02:41:01,518 --> 02:41:04,299\r\nYou don't see a difference?\r\nI see a difference.\r\nYou lose a lot of money.\r\n\r\n1685\r\n02:41:04,395 --> 02:41:07,560\r\nFewer shells will be made.\r\nStern, if this factory\r\never produces...\r\n\r\n1686\r\n02:41:07,657 --> 02:41:12,835\r\na shell that can\r\nactually be fired,\r\nI'll be very unhappy.\r\n\r\n1687\r\n02:41:12,835 --> 02:41:15,713\r\nHello, madam.\r\nHow do you do?\r\n\r\n1688\r\n02:41:28,660 --> 02:41:32,976\r\nHow are you doing,\r\nRabbi? Rabbi!\r\n\r\n1689\r\n02:41:35,086 --> 02:41:36,908\r\nGood, Herr Direktor.\r\n\r\n1690\r\n02:41:38,634 --> 02:41:41,032\r\nSun's going down.\r\n\r\n1691\r\n02:41:43,045 --> 02:41:45,539\r\nYes, it is.\r\n\r\n1692\r\n02:41:45,635 --> 02:41:49,184\r\nWhat day is this?\r\nFriday?\r\nIt is Friday, isn't it?\r\n\r\n1693\r\n02:41:49,279 --> 02:41:51,293\r\nIs it?\r\n\r\n1694\r\n02:41:55,417 --> 02:42:00,308\r\nWhat's the matter with you?\r\nYou should be preparing\r\nfor the Sabbath.\r\n\r\n1695\r\n02:42:00,308 --> 02:42:03,378\r\nShouldn't you?\r\n\r\n1696\r\n02:42:08,844 --> 02:42:13,447\r\nI've got some wine.\r\nIn my office. Come.\r\n\r\n1697\r\n02:42:16,709 --> 02:42:20,545\r\nSavree maranun\r\nverbanun verabuty...\r\n\r\n1698\r\n02:42:22,175 --> 02:42:28,985\r\nBaruch ata adoshem,\r\nElokynou melach hoyleam...\r\n\r\n1699\r\n02:42:28,985 --> 02:42:32,533\r\nboyrah paree hagofan.\r\n\r\n1700\r\n02:42:32,533 --> 02:42:35,411\r\nAmen.\r\n\r\n1701\r\n02:42:35,411 --> 02:42:38,576\r\nBaruch ata adoshem elokynou\r\nmelach hoyleam.\r\n\r\n1702\r\n02:42:38,671 --> 02:42:41,549\r\nAsher kideshanou\r\nbamezvoytaiv veratzah banou...\r\n\r\n1703\r\n02:42:41,644 --> 02:42:47,111\r\nve shabath kodshoy beahava ve\r\nrazoun hencheelanou...\r\n\r\n1704\r\n02:42:47,207 --> 02:42:50,275\r\nzicarone lemahsa barashit...\r\n\r\n1705\r\n02:42:50,372 --> 02:42:55,168\r\nyhom techelah lemikrahy kodesh\r\nzecher letzeat Mitzraim.\r\n\r\n1706\r\n02:42:55,263 --> 02:43:01,593\r\nKee banou bachartah veotanou\r\nkedashtah mekol ahameem.\r\n\r\n1707\r\n02:43:01,689 --> 02:43:06,772\r\nVe Shabath kodshou beahava\r\nve razoun hencheltanou...\r\n\r\n1708\r\n02:43:06,868 --> 02:43:12,814\r\nBarooch ata adoshem\r\nmekadesh hashabat.\r\n\r\n1709\r\n02:43:12,910 --> 02:43:14,732\r\nGeet Shabath.\r\n\r\n1710\r\n02:43:14,828 --> 02:43:16,938\r\nGeet Shabath.\r\n\r\n1711\r\n02:43:25,378 --> 02:43:28,351\r\nWhat?\r\n\r\n1712\r\n02:43:28,351 --> 02:43:33,147\r\nDo you have any money,\r\nuh, hidden away someplace...\r\n\r\n1713\r\n02:43:33,147 --> 02:43:35,831\r\nthat I don't know about?\r\n\r\n1714\r\n02:43:39,093 --> 02:43:41,490\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n1715\r\n02:43:45,710 --> 02:43:49,451\r\nWhy? Am I broke?\r\n\r\n1716\r\n02:43:49,546 --> 02:43:52,327\r\nUh--\r\n\r\n1717\r\n02:43:52,423 --> 02:43:55,205\r\nWell--\r\n\r\n1718\r\n02:43:55,301 --> 02:44:00,768\r\nYesterday morning, at 241 a.m.,\r\n\r\n1719\r\n02:44:00,863 --> 02:44:05,275\r\nat General Eisenhower's\r\nheadquarters,\r\n\r\n1720\r\n02:44:05,371 --> 02:44:07,960\r\nGeneral Jodl...\r\n\r\n1721\r\n02:44:08,056 --> 02:44:11,508\r\nsigned the \"Act of\r\nUnconditional Surrender\"...\r\n\r\n1722\r\n02:44:11,508 --> 02:44:14,002\r\nof all German land,\r\n\r\n1723\r\n02:44:14,099 --> 02:44:17,839\r\nsea and air forces\r\nin Europe...\r\n\r\n1724\r\n02:44:17,934 --> 02:44:21,771\r\nto the Allied\r\nExpeditionary Force,\r\n\r\n1725\r\n02:44:21,771 --> 02:44:25,895\r\nand simultaneously\r\nto the Soviet High Command.\r\n\r\n1726\r\n02:44:25,990 --> 02:44:30,211\r\nThe German war is,\r\ntherefore, at an end.\r\n\r\n1727\r\n02:44:30,306 --> 02:44:32,224\r\nBut let us not forget\r\nfor a moment--\r\n\r\n1728\r\n02:44:32,224 --> 02:44:36,348\r\nI think it's time the guards\r\ncame into the factory.\r\n\r\n1729\r\n02:44:36,445 --> 02:44:39,513\r\nJapan, with all\r\nher treachery and greed--\r\n\r\n1730\r\n02:44:39,513 --> 02:44:44,788\r\nThe unconditional surrender of\r\nGermany has just been announced.\r\n\r\n1731\r\n02:44:44,884 --> 02:44:48,720\r\nAt midnight tonight,\r\nthe war is over.\r\n\r\n1732\r\n02:44:50,735 --> 02:44:53,421\r\nTomorrow you'll\r\nbegin the process...\r\n\r\n1733\r\n02:44:53,516 --> 02:44:56,681\r\nof looking for survivors\r\nof your families.\r\n\r\n1734\r\n02:44:59,462 --> 02:45:04,066\r\nIn most cases,\r\nyou won't find them.\r\n\r\n1735\r\n02:45:05,217 --> 02:45:08,573\r\nAfter six long years\r\nof murder,\r\n\r\n1736\r\n02:45:08,669 --> 02:45:13,848\r\nvictims are being mourned\r\nthroughout the world.\r\n\r\n1737\r\n02:45:13,944 --> 02:45:16,917\r\nWe've survived.\r\n\r\n1738\r\n02:45:16,917 --> 02:45:20,945\r\nMany of you have come up\r\nto me and thanked me.\r\n\r\n1739\r\n02:45:22,863 --> 02:45:24,974\r\nThank yourselves.\r\n\r\n1740\r\n02:45:26,125 --> 02:45:28,522\r\nThank your fearless Stern...\r\n\r\n1741\r\n02:45:28,617 --> 02:45:31,879\r\nand others among you\r\nwho worried about you...\r\n\r\n1742\r\n02:45:31,879 --> 02:45:35,619\r\nand faced death\r\nat every moment.\r\n\r\n1743\r\n02:45:38,305 --> 02:45:40,989\r\nI'm a member\r\nof the Nazi party.\r\n\r\n1744\r\n02:45:40,989 --> 02:45:43,963\r\nI'm a munitions\r\nmanufacturer.\r\n\r\n1745\r\n02:45:43,963 --> 02:45:46,552\r\nI'm a profiteer\r\nof slave labor.\r\n\r\n1746\r\n02:45:46,648 --> 02:45:50,196\r\nI am a criminal.\r\n\r\n1747\r\n02:45:50,293 --> 02:45:55,663\r\nAt midnight you'll be free,\r\nand I'll be hunted.\r\n\r\n1748\r\n02:45:55,759 --> 02:45:59,021\r\nI shall remain with you until\r\nfive minutes after midnight.\r\n\r\n1749\r\n02:45:59,116 --> 02:46:02,281\r\nAfter which time,\r\nand I hope you'll forgive me,\r\n\r\n1750\r\n02:46:02,377 --> 02:46:04,295\r\nI have to flee.\r\n\r\n1751\r\n02:46:06,885 --> 02:46:10,625\r\nI know you have received orders\r\nfrom our Commandant,\r\n\r\n1752\r\n02:46:10,625 --> 02:46:14,941\r\nwhich he has received\r\nfrom his superiors, to dispose\r\nof the population of this camp.\r\n\r\n1753\r\n02:46:15,036 --> 02:46:18,106\r\nNow would be\r\nthe time to do it.\r\n\r\n1754\r\n02:46:18,201 --> 02:46:23,476\r\nHere they are, they're all here.\r\nThis is your opportunity.\r\n\r\n1755\r\n02:46:27,696 --> 02:46:30,190\r\nOr you could leave,\r\n\r\n1756\r\n02:46:30,285 --> 02:46:33,642\r\nand return to\r\nyour families as men...\r\n\r\n1757\r\n02:46:33,738 --> 02:46:37,287\r\ninstead of murderers.\r\n\r\n1758\r\n02:47:15,553 --> 02:47:19,582\r\nIn memory of the countless\r\nvictims among your people,\r\n\r\n1759\r\n02:47:19,582 --> 02:47:23,514\r\nI ask us to observe\r\nthree minutes of silence.\r\n\r\n1760\r\n02:47:30,419 --> 02:47:35,406\r\nYetkadal veytkadosh shamy raboo.\r\n\r\n1761\r\n02:47:35,502 --> 02:47:38,858\r\nVealmah Devyrsah\r\nveyamlich malchootay.\r\n\r\n1762\r\n02:47:38,955 --> 02:47:43,174\r\nVysmach Palkoney\r\nbekoor meshchay.\r\n\r\n1763\r\n02:47:43,271 --> 02:47:48,162\r\nVchyachoon ovyomachoon\r\novachaye bechol bayeth ysrael.\r\n\r\n1764\r\n02:47:48,162 --> 02:47:51,518\r\nBahgoola ovzman Kariv veemree.\r\nAmen.\r\n\r\n1765\r\n02:47:51,518 --> 02:47:53,437\r\nAmen.\r\n\r\n1766\r\n02:47:53,437 --> 02:47:57,272\r\nYahee Shmay Rabah Mevoorach\r\nleolame oleomlay olmaya.\r\n\r\n1767\r\n02:47:57,369 --> 02:48:00,534\r\nYetbarach veyeshtabach\r\nveytpaehar veytromam.\r\n\r\n1768\r\n02:48:00,534 --> 02:48:03,890\r\nVeytnasah veytader\r\nveytalah veythalel.\r\n\r\n1769\r\n02:48:03,987 --> 02:48:07,343\r\nSchmy dekodsha breech hoe.\r\n\r\n1770\r\n02:48:07,439 --> 02:48:10,413\r\nYehee shalama Rabah\r\nMean shamaya...\r\n\r\n1771\r\n02:48:10,508 --> 02:48:13,961\r\nvechayeem toveem alayno veal\r\nkol israel. Vemree. Amen.\r\n\r\n1772\r\n02:48:13,961 --> 02:48:16,167\r\nAmen.\r\n\r\n1773\r\n02:48:16,646 --> 02:48:19,236\r\nThank you, Mr.Jereth.\r\nThank you,\r\nMr.Jereth.\r\n\r\n1774\r\n02:48:19,236 --> 02:48:21,633\r\nThank you,\r\nMr.Jereth.\r\nThank you, Mr.Jereth.\r\n\r\n1775\r\n02:48:21,633 --> 02:48:23,934\r\nOpen wide.\r\n\r\n1776\r\n02:48:25,374 --> 02:48:27,195\r\nThank you, Mr.Jereth.\r\n\r\n1777\r\n02:48:44,747 --> 02:48:47,528\r\nThank you,\r\nMr.Jereth.\r\n\r\n1778\r\n02:49:10,641 --> 02:49:14,478\r\nAs soon as peace occurs,\r\nI want...\r\n\r\n1779\r\n02:49:14,573 --> 02:49:18,314\r\num, I want that cloth\r\ndistributed to the workers.\r\n\r\n1780\r\n02:49:18,410 --> 02:49:20,999\r\nTwo and a half meters each.\r\n\r\n1781\r\n02:49:21,095 --> 02:49:24,069\r\nAlso, each person is\r\nto get a bottle of vodka.\r\n\r\n1782\r\n02:49:24,164 --> 02:49:26,945\r\nThey won't drink it.\r\nThey know its value.\r\n\r\n1783\r\n02:49:27,042 --> 02:49:30,398\r\nLikewise for those\r\nEgipshi cigarettes\r\nwe organized.\r\n\r\n1784\r\n02:49:30,495 --> 02:49:34,235\r\nIt'll be done.\r\nEverything you ask.\r\n\r\n1785\r\n02:49:52,936 --> 02:49:56,484\r\nWe've written a letter,\r\ntrying to explain things...\r\n\r\n1786\r\n02:49:56,581 --> 02:49:58,786\r\nin case\r\nyou are captured.\r\n\r\n1787\r\n02:50:01,376 --> 02:50:04,349\r\nEvery worker\r\nhas signed it.\r\n\r\n1788\r\n02:50:14,228 --> 02:50:16,049\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\n1789\r\n02:50:41,560 --> 02:50:44,246\r\nIt is Hebrew,\r\nfrom the Talmud.\r\n\r\n1790\r\n02:50:44,342 --> 02:50:49,808\r\nIt says,\r\n\"Whoever saves one life,\r\nsaves the world entire.\"\r\n\r\n1791\r\n02:51:27,116 --> 02:51:29,418\r\nI could have got more out.\r\n\r\n1792\r\n02:51:31,624 --> 02:51:34,310\r\nI could have got more.\r\nI don't know.\r\n\r\n1793\r\n02:51:34,310 --> 02:51:36,707\r\nIf I just--\r\n\r\n1794\r\n02:51:36,707 --> 02:51:39,104\r\nI could have got more.\r\n\r\n1795\r\n02:51:39,104 --> 02:51:44,187\r\nOskar, there are 1 ,100 people\r\nwho are alive because of you.\r\nLook at them.\r\n\r\n1796\r\n02:51:44,187 --> 02:51:46,873\r\nIf I'd made more money.\r\n\r\n1797\r\n02:51:50,326 --> 02:51:55,408\r\nI threw away so much money.\r\n\r\n1798\r\n02:51:55,505 --> 02:51:58,861\r\nYou have no idea.\r\n\r\n1799\r\n02:51:58,958 --> 02:52:00,971\r\nIf I had just--\r\n\r\n1800\r\n02:52:01,067 --> 02:52:05,287\r\nThere will be generations\r\nbecause of what you did.\r\n\r\n1801\r\n02:52:05,384 --> 02:52:08,260\r\nI didn't do enough.\r\n\r\n1802\r\n02:52:08,357 --> 02:52:11,617\r\nYou did so much.\r\n\r\n1803\r\n02:52:14,686 --> 02:52:16,796\r\nThis car.\r\n\r\n1804\r\n02:52:16,892 --> 02:52:19,097\r\nGoeth would've\r\nbought this car.\r\n\r\n1805\r\n02:52:19,097 --> 02:52:23,030\r\nWhy did I keep the car?\r\nTen people right there.\r\n\r\n1806\r\n02:52:26,195 --> 02:52:28,689\r\nTen people.\r\n\r\n1807\r\n02:52:28,689 --> 02:52:30,703\r\nTen more people.\r\n\r\n1808\r\n02:52:33,676 --> 02:52:35,881\r\nThis pin.\r\n\r\n1809\r\n02:52:35,881 --> 02:52:39,526\r\nTwo people.\r\n\r\n1810\r\n02:52:39,621 --> 02:52:41,636\r\nThis is gold.\r\n\r\n1811\r\n02:52:41,636 --> 02:52:43,553\r\nTwo more people.\r\n\r\n1812\r\n02:52:43,553 --> 02:52:46,239\r\nHe would have given me\r\ntwo for it; at least one.\r\n\r\n1813\r\n02:52:46,336 --> 02:52:49,596\r\nHe would have given me one,\r\none more.\r\n\r\n1814\r\n02:52:51,898 --> 02:52:55,734\r\nOne more person.\r\n\r\n1815\r\n02:52:55,734 --> 02:52:59,091\r\nA person, Stern.\r\n\r\n1816\r\n02:52:59,091 --> 02:53:01,777\r\nFor this.\r\n\r\n1817\r\n02:53:03,599 --> 02:53:07,339\r\nI could have gotten...\r\n\r\n1818\r\n02:53:07,434 --> 02:53:11,846\r\none more person\r\nand I didn't.\r\n\r\n1819\r\n02:53:11,942 --> 02:53:15,778\r\nAnd I-I didn't!\r\n\r\n1820\r\n02:54:40,081 --> 02:54:43,054\r\nYou have been liberated...\r\n\r\n1821\r\n02:54:43,149 --> 02:54:46,602\r\nby the Soviet Army!\r\n\r\n1822\r\n02:54:53,220 --> 02:54:55,234\r\nHave you been\r\nin Poland?\r\n\r\n1823\r\n02:54:55,329 --> 02:54:58,782\r\nI just came from Poland.\r\n\r\n1824\r\n02:54:58,782 --> 02:55:01,755\r\nAre there\r\nanyJews left?\r\n\r\n1825\r\n02:55:07,030 --> 02:55:09,427\r\nWhere should we go?\r\n\r\n1826\r\n02:55:09,524 --> 02:55:11,729\r\nDon't go east, that's for sure.\r\n\r\n1827\r\n02:55:11,826 --> 02:55:14,894\r\nThey hate you there.\r\n\r\n1828\r\n02:55:14,991 --> 02:55:18,539\r\nI wouldn't go west either,\r\nif I were you.\r\n\r\n1829\r\n02:55:18,634 --> 02:55:22,566\r\nWe could use some food.\r\n\r\n1830\r\n02:55:22,663 --> 02:55:27,651\r\nIsn't that a town\r\nover there?\r\n","markerStore":{"nextMarkerId":