Detective Mills.\r\n\r\n19\r\n00:01:52,403 --> 00:01:55,395\r\nI get in town 20 minutes ago,\nthey dump me here.\r\n\r\n20\r\n00:01:55,603 --> 00:01:56,353\r\nLook...\r\n\r\n21\r\n00:01:57,283 --> 00:01:57,920\r\nMills?\r\n\r\n22\r\n00:01:58,443 --> 00:02:01,003\r\nLet's find a bar,\nsit and talk...\r\n\r\n23\r\n00:02:01,243 --> 00:02:03,074\r\nI'd like to get to the precinct.\r\n\r\n24\r\n00:02:03,323 --> 00:02:05,757\r\nNot much time for\nthis transition thing.\r\n\r\n25\r\n00:02:07,243 --> 00:02:09,962\r\nI had a question,\nwhen we spoke on the phone.\r\n\r\n26\r\n00:02:10,163 --> 00:02:10,640\r\nYeah?\r\n\r\n27\r\n00:02:12,524 --> 00:02:15,084\r\n- Why here?\n- I don't follow.\r\n\r\n28\r\n00:02:16,004 --> 00:02:18,472\r\nAll this effort\nto get transferred.\r\n\r\n29\r\n00:02:19,764 --> 00:02:22,198\r\nIt's the first question\nthat popped into my head.\r\n\r\n30\r\n00:02:22,764 --> 00:02:24,117\r\nSame reasons as you,\r\n\r\n31\r\n00:02:24,404 --> 00:02:27,237\r\nor the reasons you had\nbefore you decided to quit.\r\n\r\n32\r\n00:02:29,684 --> 00:02:31,117\r\nYou just met me.\r\n\r\n33\r\n00:02:32,364 --> 00:02:34,435\r\nMaybe I don't understand\nthe question.\r\n\r\n34\r\n00:02:35,805 --> 00:02:36,874\r\nIt's very simple.\r\n\r\n35\r\n00:02:37,925 --> 00:02:41,315\r\nYou actually fought\nto get reassigned here.\r\n\r\n36\r\n00:02:42,285 --> 00:02:45,755\r\n- I never saw it done that way.\n- Thought I'd do some good.\r\n\r\n37\r\n00:02:46,005 --> 00:02:49,964\r\nBe great if we didn't start out\nkicking each other in the balls.\r\n\r\n38\r\n00:02:51,925 --> 00:02:54,075\r\n- You're calling the shots.\n- Yes.\r\n\r\n39\r\n00:02:55,565 --> 00:02:58,524\r\nI want you to look\nand listen, okay?\r\n\r\n40\r\n00:02:58,806 --> 00:03:02,640\r\nI wasn't guarding a Taco Bell.\nI worked homicide 5 years.\r\n\r\n41\r\n00:03:02,886 --> 00:03:04,604\r\n- Not here.\n- I understand.\r\n\r\n42\r\n00:03:04,846 --> 00:03:08,600\r\nOver the next 7 days,\ndo me a favor and remember 