8,789 --> 01:54:40,958\r\nWhat the hell is going on?\r\n\r\n1453\r\n01:54:41,125 --> 01:54:43,919\r\n<i>– What are you doing here?</i>\r\n– I'm delivering a package.\r\n\r\n1454\r\n01:54:44,086 --> 01:54:45,796\r\nI got this package for this guy, David.\r\n\r\n1455\r\n01:54:45,963 --> 01:54:49,258\r\nUh, Detective David Mills.\r\n\r\n1456\r\n01:54:56,223 --> 01:54:58,559\r\nGet it. Slowly.\r\n\r\n1457\r\n01:54:59,435 --> 01:55:01,979\r\n<i>Stay alert. He's opening the back of the van.</i>\r\n\r\n1458\r\n01:55:02,146 --> 01:55:03,814\r\n<i>We've got him in sight.</i>\r\n\r\n1459\r\n01:55:10,071 --> 01:55:13,324\r\nThis guy paid me 500 bucks\r\nto bring it out here, man.\r\n\r\n1460\r\n01:55:13,491 --> 01:55:15,576\r\nHe said he wanted it here at exactly 7:00.\r\n\r\n1461\r\n01:55:16,327 --> 01:55:17,828\r\nPut it down.\r\n\r\n1462\r\n01:55:18,454 --> 01:55:19,789\r\n<i>We got a box.</i>\r\n\r\n1463\r\n01:55:19,955 --> 01:55:24,251\r\nWe got a box. Call the bomb squad.\r\nI need a bomb squad. We got a box.\r\n\r\n1464\r\n01:55:24,710 --> 01:55:26,420\r\nFace the van.\r\n\r\n1465\r\n01:55:26,796 --> 01:55:28,255\r\nHands up.\r\n\r\n1466\r\n01:55:35,679 --> 01:55:37,306\r\nTurn around.\r\n\r\n1467\r\n01:55:38,182 --> 01:55:40,101\r\nOkay. Go. Off you go. Go.\r\n\r\n1468\r\n01:55:40,267 --> 01:55:42,394\r\n<i>Do you want us to pick this guy up?</i>\r\n\r\n1469\r\n01:55:43,312 --> 01:55:45,314\r\nI'm sending the driver out on foot.\r\n\r\n1470\r\n01:55:48,192 --> 01:55:52,154\r\n<i>– Got the driver in sight.</i>\r\n– He's headed north. Have him picked up.\r\n\r\n1471\r\n01:56:01,413 --> 01:56:03,332\r\nOh, I don't know.\r\n\r\n1472\r\n01:56:09,547 --> 01:56:11,048\r\nI'm gonna open it.\r\n\r\n1473\r\n01:56:11,215 --> 01:56:15,094\r\nWhen I said I admired you,\r\nI meant what I said.\r\n\r\n1474\r\n01:56:33,737 --> 01:56:34,822\r\nIt's blood.\r\n\r\n1475\r\n01:56:34,989 --> 01:56:36,740\r\nYou've made quite a life for yourself.\r\n\r\n1476\r\n01:56:36,907 --> 01:56:37,950\r\nHmm.\r\n\r\n1477\r\n01:56:38,117 --> 01:56:41,245\r\n– You should be very proud.\r\n– Shut the fuck up, you piece of shit.\r\n\r\n1478\r\n01:56:54,925 --> 01:56:56,343\r\n<i>Someone lost contact, copy.</i>\r\n\r\n1479\r\n01:57:08,939 --> 01:57:10,399\r\nCalifornia, stay away from here.\r\n\r\n1480\r\n01:57:10,566 --> 01:57:13,027\r\nStay away from here, now.\r\nDon't come in here.\r\n\r\n1481\r\n01:57:13,485 --> 01:57:15,195\r\n<i>Whatever you hear, stay away.</i>\r\n\r\n1482\r\n01:57:16,405 --> 01:57:19,491\r\nJohn Doe has the upper hand. Mills!\r\n\r\n1483\r\n01:57:19,909 --> 01:57:21,035\r\nHere he comes.\r\n\r\n1484\r\n01:57:21,201 --> 01:57:23,078\r\n– Throw your gun down!\r\n– What?\r\n\r\n1485\r\n01:57:23,245 --> 01:57:25,456\r\n– I wish I could've lived like you.\r\n– Shut up.\r\n\r\n1486\r\n01:57:25,623 --> 01:57:28,417\r\n– What the fuck you talking about?\r\n– Go away!\r\n\r\n1487\r\n01:57:28,584 --> 01:57:29,877\r\nDo you hear me, detective?\r\n\r\n1488\r\n01:57:30,044 --> 01:57:34,381\r\nI'm trying to tell you how much\r\nI admire you and your pretty wife.\r\n\r\n1489\r\n01:57:35,466 --> 01:57:37,301\r\n– What?\r\n– Tracy.\r\n\r\n1490\r\n01:57:37,468 --> 01:57:38,677\r\nMills!\r\n\r\n1491\r\n01:57:38,844 --> 01:57:39,929\r\nWhat'd you fucking say?\r\n\r\n1492\r\n01:57:40,095 --> 01:57:44,183\r\nIt's disturbing how easily a member\r\nof the press can purchase information…\r\n\r\n1493\r\n01:57:44,350 --> 01:57:46,060\r\n…from the men in your precinct.\r\n\r\n1494\r\n01:57:46,560 --> 01:57:48,062\r\nWhat the fuck?\r\n\r\n1495\r\n01:57:48,479 --> 01:57:50,356\r\n<i>Throw your gun down!</i>\r\n\r\n1496\r\n01:57:50,522 --> 01:57:52,566\r\nI visited your home this morning…\r\n\r\n1497\r\n01:57:53,567 --> 01:57:55,361\r\nAfter you'd left.\r\n\r\n1498\r\n01:57:55,527 --> 01:57:57,655\r\n– Mills!\r\n– I tried to play husband.\r\n\r\n1499\r\n01:57:58,322 --> 01:58:01,575\r\nI tried to taste the life of a simple man.\r\n\r\n1500\r\n01:58:01,784 --> 01:58:03,035\r\nThrow it away!\r\n\r\n1501\r\n01:58:03,202 --> 01:58:05,496\r\nTsk, it didn't work out.\r\n\r\n1502\r\n01:58:05,663 --> 01:58:07,331\r\nSo…\r\n\r\n1503\r\n01:58:07,498 --> 01:58:09,416\r\nI took a souvenir.\r\n\r\n1504\r\n01:58:11,043 --> 01:58:12,753\r\nHer pretty head.\r\n\r\n1505\r\n01:58:12,920 --> 01:58:14,505\r\nMills.\r\n\r\n1506\r\n01:58:15,047 --> 01:58:16,674\r\nMills.\r\n\r\n1507\r\n01:58:17,675 --> 01:58:18,842\r\nWhat's he talking about?\r\n\r\n1508\r\n01:58:19,009 --> 01:58:21,387\r\n– Give me your gun.\r\n– What's going on over there?\r\n\r\n1509\r\n01:58:21,553 --> 01:58:22,846\r\nPut the, ugh-- Put the gun down.\r\n\r\n1510\r\n01:58:23,013 --> 01:58:25,015\r\nI saw you with a box.\r\nWhat was in the box?\r\n\r\n1511\r\n01:58:25,182 --> 01:58:28,102\r\n– Because I envy your normal life.\r\n– Put the gun down, David.\r\n\r\n1512\r\n01:58:28,268 --> 01:58:31,230\r\n– It seems that envy is my sin.\r\n– Oh, what's in the box?\r\n\r\n1513\r\n01:58:31,397 --> 01:58:33,732\r\n– Not until you give me the gun.\r\n– What's in the box?\r\n\r\n1514\r\n01:58:33,899 --> 01:58:35,651\r\n– Give me the gun.\r\n– He just told you.\r\n\r\n1515\r\n01:58:35,818 --> 01:58:39,446\r\n– You lie. You're a fucking liar, shut up.\r\n– David.\r\n\r\n1516\r\n01:58:39,613 --> 01:58:42,366\r\nThat's what he wants.\r\nHe wants you to shoot him.\r\n\r\n1517\r\n01:58:42,533 --> 01:58:45,661\r\nNo! No.\r\n\r\n1518\r\n01:58:46,036 --> 01:58:47,830\r\nYou tell me that's not true.\r\n\r\n1519\r\n01:58:47,997 --> 01:58:50,124\r\n– That's not true.\r\n– Become vengeance, David.\r\n\r\n1520\r\n01:58:50,291 --> 01:58:53,168\r\n– Oh, she's all right. You tell me.\r\n– Become…\r\n\r\n1521\r\n01:58:53,335 --> 01:58:55,838\r\n– …wrath.\r\n– Tell me she's all right!\r\n\r\n1522\r\n01:58:56,005 --> 01:58:58,132\r\n– If you murder a suspect, David--\r\n– No.\r\n\r\n1523\r\n01:58:58,299 --> 01:59:00,050\r\nYou throw it all away, he knows it.\r\n\r\n1524\r\n01:59:00,217 --> 01:59:01,218\r\nNo!\r\n\r\n1525\r\n01:59:01,385 --> 01:59:03,387\r\n– She begged for her life.\r\n– Shut up.\r\n\r\n1526\r\n01:59:03,554 --> 01:59:07,224\r\nShe begged for her life\r\nand for the life of the baby inside of her.\r\n\r\n1527\r\n01:59:23,282 --> 01:59:24,658\r\nOh.\r\n\r\n1528\r\n01:59:26,577 --> 01:59:27,786\r\nHe didn't know.\r\n\r\n1529\r\n01:59:41,759 --> 01:59:43,719\r\nGive me the gun, David.\r\n\r\n1530\r\n01:59:48,682 --> 01:59:50,184\r\nDavid.\r\n\r\n1531\r\n01:59:51,477 --> 01:59:52,895\r\nIf you kill him…\r\n\r\n1532\r\n01:59:54,396 --> 01:59:56,148\r\n…he will win.\r\n\r\n1533\r\n01:59:59,860 --> 02:00:01,695\r\nOh, God.\r\n\r\n1534\r\n02:00:01,862 --> 02:00:04,073\r\nOh, God.\r\n\r\n1535\r\n02:00:04,782 --> 02:00:05,949\r\nOh!\r\n\r\n1536\r\n02:00:19,380 --> 02:00:21,131\r\nOh, fuck, he shot him.\r\n\r\n1537\r\n02:00:43,237 --> 02:00:45,823\r\n<i>Set it down somewhere.</i>\r\n\r\n1538\r\n02:00:47,032 --> 02:00:49,326\r\n<i>Come on, set us down.</i>\r\n\r\n1539\r\n02:00:51,745 --> 02:00:55,541\r\n<i>Holy Christ. Somebody call somebody.</i>\r\n\r\n1540\r\n02:00:55,707 --> 02:00:57,543\r\n<i>Call somebody.</i>\r\n\r\n1541\r\n02:01:12,015 --> 02:01:15,060\r\nWell, we'll take care of him.\r\n\r\n1542\r\n02:01:23,735 --> 02:01:25,779\r\nWhatever he needs.\r\n\r\n1543\r\n02:01:26,697 --> 02:01:28,198\r\nWhere are you gonna be?\r\n\r\n1544\r\n02:01:30,909 --> 02:01:32,286\r\nAround.\r\n\r\n1545\r\n02:01:36,623 --> 02:01:38,542\r\nI'll be around.\r\n\r\n1546\r\n02:01:42,421 --> 02:01:44,673\r\n<i>Ernest Hemingway once wrote:</i>\r\n\r\n1547\r\n02:01:44,840 --> 02:01:49,261\r\n<i>«The world is a fine place\r\nand worth fighting for.»</i>\r\n\r\n1548\r\n02:01:50,095 --> 02:01:52,681\r\n<i>I agree with the second part.</i>\r\n\r\n","markerStore":{"nextMarkerId":33,"markersById":{"0":{"range":{"start":{"row":0,"column":0},"end":{"row":0,"column":0}},"properties":{"type":"selection","editorId":100,"goalScreenRange":null},"reversed":false,"tailed":false,"valid":true,"invalidate":"never","maintainHistory":true}},"version":2},"history":{"version":3,"nextCheckpointId":1,"undoStack":[],"redoStack":[]},"encoding":"utf8","filePath":"/Users/joegesualdo/Downloads/se7en.(1995).eng.1cd.(4834505)/Se7en.1995.Remastered.HDRip.Eng.srt","digestWhenLastPersisted":"eb7237f6436487ef8ff8766350c95514377e995e","preferredLineEnding":null,"deserializer":"TextBuffer","version":2},{"load":true,"text":"1\r\n00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:07,074\r\nSubtitles downloaded from www.OpenSubtitles.org\r\n\r\n2\r\n00:00:31,050 --> 00:00:32,710\r\nMy name is Turkish.\r\n\r\n3\r\n00:00:33,010 --> 00:00:35,086\r\nFunny name for an Englishman, I know.\r\n\r\n4\r\n00:00:35,346 --> 00:00:38,796\r\nMy parents were on the same plane\nwhen it crashed. That's how they met.\r\n\r\n5\r\n00:00:40,224 --> 00:00:42,347\r\nThey named me after the plane.\r\n\r\n6\r\n00:00:42,601 --> 00:00:45,092\r\nNot many people are\nnamed after a plane crash.\r\n\r\n7\r\n00:00:45,896 --> 00:00:47,307\r\nThat's Tommy.\r\n\r\n8\r\n00:00:47,606 --> 00:00:49,764\r\nHe tells people\nhe was named after a gun.\r\n\r\n9\r\n00:00:50,317 --> 00:00:55,024\r\nBut I know he was really named after\na famous 19th century ballet dancer.\r\n\r\n10\r\n00:00:55,571 --> 00:00:59,189\r\nKnown him for as long as I can\nremember. He's my partner.\r\n\r\n11\r\n00:00:59,533 --> 00:01:02,154\r\nDoesn't mean we hold hands\nor take walks.\r\n\r\n12\r\n00:01:02,452 --> 00:01:06,744\r\nIt means I try to keep him out of\nas much trouble as he inflicts on me.\r\n\r\n13\r\n00:01:06,997 --> 00:01:09,867\r\nI give him a hard time.\nKeeps him in check.\r\n\r\n14\r\n00:01:10,166 --> 00:01:12,622\r\nBut really, he's like my brother.\r\n\r\n15\r\n00:01:13,336 --> 00:01:16,954\r\nWhat do I know about diamonds?\nI'm a boxing promoter.\r\n\r\n16\r\n00:01:17,256 --> 00:01:20,838\r\nI was a happy boxing promoter\nuntil a week ago, and then:\r\n\r\n17\r\n00:01:21,134 --> 00:01:23,292\r\nWhat do I know about diamonds?\r\n\r\n18\r\n00:01:24,137 --> 00:01:26,213\r\nDon't they come from Antwerp?\r\n\r\n19\r\n00:01:27,181 --> 00:01:30,431\r\n- Himy, would you listen to this?\n- Do we have a choice?\r\n\r\n20\r\n00:01:30,726 --> 00:01:34,390\r\nIt wasn't meant to be taken literally.\r\n\r\n21\r\n00:01:34,687 --> 00:01:37,439\r\nIt's a nice story, Adam and Eve.\r\n\r\n22\r\n00:01:37,690 --> 00:01:39,729\r\nIt's bound with moral fibre...\r\n\r\n23\r\n00:01:40,025 --> 00:01:43,608\r\n... but asking a grown man\nto believe it?\r\n\r\n24\r\n00:01:44,612 --> 00:01:45,857\r\nWhat is it?\r\n\r\n25\r\n00:01:48,115 --> 00:01:49,609\r\nWell, what is it?\r\n\r\n26\r\n00:01:51,285 --> 00:01:54,617\r\nWhat you want I should do,\ndrop my pants?\r\n\r\n27\r\n00:01:54,912 --> 00:01:56,490\r\nOkay, go through.\r\n\r\n28\r\n00:01:57,872 --> 00:01:59,912\r\nIt's a nice story.\r\n\r\n29\r\n00:02:00,625 --> 00:02:03,579\r\nIt's just that. Just a story.\r\n\r\n30\r\n00:02:03,878 --> 00:02:07,246\r\nCatholic religion is based\non a mistranslation.\r\n\r\n31\r\n00:02:07,548 --> 00:02:09,955\r\nEnough already. Ruben, say something.\r\n\r\n32\r\n00:02:10,259 --> 00:02:12,795\r\nListen. Are you busy?\nI'll tell you the whole story.\r\n\r\n33\r\n00:02:13,052 --> 00:02:17,263\r\nThe Septuagint scholars mistranslated\nthe Hebrew word for \"young woman\"...\r\n\r\n34\r\n00:02:17,556 --> 00:02:19,679\r\n... into the Greek word for \"virgin.\"\r\n\r\n35\r\n00:02:19,933 --> 00:02:22,341\r\nIt was an easy mistake to make...\r\n\r\n36\r\n00:02:22,602 --> 00:02:27,144\r\n... because there was only a subtle\ndifference in the spelling.\r\n\r\n37\r\n00:02:37,115 --> 00:02:39,272\r\nSo, they came up with a prophecy:\r\n\r\n38\r\n00:02:39,574 --> 00:02:43,738\r\n\"Behold, the virgin shall conceive\nand bear us a son. \"\r\n\r\n39\r\n00:02:43,995 --> 00:02:48,040\r\nYou understand? It was \"virgin\"\nthat caught people's attention.\r\n\r\n40\r\n00:02:48,333 --> 00:02:52,495\r\nIt's not everyday a virgin conceives\nand bears a son.\r\n\r\n41\r\n00:03:08,599 --> 00