 Yeah. Don't go to England.\r\n\r\n1217\r\n01:25:09,766 --> 01:25:13,597\r\nThat dog is gonna go back\nto the campsite. It always does.\r\n\r\n1218\r\n01:25:13,894 --> 01:25:15,934\r\nHow's the dog gonna find the campsite?\r\n\r\n1219\r\n01:25:16,230 --> 01:25:18,436\r\nHave you smelled the campsite, Sol?\r\n\r\n1220\r\n01:25:18,732 --> 01:25:21,649\r\nAll right. But we have\nto wait until it gets light.\r\n\r\n1221\r\n01:25:21,902 --> 01:25:23,811\r\nAnd we have to get rid\nof these bodies.\r\n\r\n1222\r\n01:25:24,070 --> 01:25:27,356\r\nThat one with the tea cosy\non his head's starting to stink.\r\n\r\n1223\r\n01:25:27,657 --> 01:25:32,734\r\nRight. Let's stick them in the car,\nand then go and look for a pig farm.\r\n\r\n1224\r\n01:25:35,957 --> 01:25:37,285\r\nMickey.\r\n\r\n1225\r\n01:25:39,376 --> 01:25:40,491\r\nMickey!\r\n\r\n1226\r\n01:25:43,172 --> 01:25:44,998\r\nYou feeling all right, Mickey?\r\n\r\n1227\r\n01:25:47,884 --> 01:25:48,999\r\nNeed a drink.\r\n\r\n1228\r\n01:25:51,763 --> 01:25:53,138\r\nYou can't give him a drink!\r\n\r\n1229\r\n01:25:53,431 --> 01:25:55,388\r\nIt's not for him. It's for me.\r\n\r\n1230\r\n01:26:01,021 --> 01:26:03,014\r\nAh, mates. Amen.\r\n\r\n1231\r\n01:26:09,988 --> 01:26:14,448\r\nHe's a hard bastard, this Good Night\nAnderson, so pay attention.\r\n\r\n1232\r\n01:26:15,452 --> 01:26:16,827\r\nAll right, Mickey?\r\n\r\n1233\r\n01:26:17,578 --> 01:26:18,907\r\nMickey!\r\n\r\n1234\r\n01:26:23,376 --> 01:26:25,167\r\nNeed to have a shite!\r\n\r\n1235\r\n01:26:26,337 --> 01:26:31,082\r\nIf you see the pikey, Turkish or\nhis girlfriend come out before me...\r\n\r\n1236\r\n01:26:31,341 --> 01:26:33,417\r\n...shoot the bastards.\r\n\r\n1237\r\n01:26:35,637 --> 01:26:38,210\r\nWell, come on.\nWe got a fight to go to.\r\n\r\n1238\r\n01:26:45,313 --> 01:26:46,688\r\nAll right, Tom.\r\n\r\n1239\r\n01:26:47,648 --> 01:26:51,776\r\n- Hope we get a better show this time.\n- This will make up for it.\r\n\r\n1240\r\n01:26:52,027 --> 01:26:54,316\r\nMickey's going down in the fourth.\r\n\r\n1241\r\n01:26:54,571 --> 01:26:57,062\r\nTerry over there is in charge\nof the bets.\r\n\r\n1242\r\n01:26:57,365 --> 01:26:58,990\r\nNow, you have to forgive me.\r\n\r\n1243\r\n01:26:59,284 --> 01:27:01,857\r\nI'll forgive you\nif he goes down this time.\r\n\r\n1244\r\n01:27:05,123 --> 01:27:08,076\r\n- Our lads at the campsite?\n- They're over there now.\r\n\r\n1245\r\n01:27:11,378 --> 01:27:13,620\r\nI fucking hate pikeys.\r\n\r\n1246\r\n01:27:15,632 --> 01:27:19,677\r\n- How long have we gotta stay here?\n- As long as it takes. Now, shut up.\r\n\r\n1247\r\n01:27:20,762 --> 01:27:22,719\r\nFucking hate pikeys.\r\n\r\n1248\r\n01:27:23,890 --> 01:27:25,847\r\nIs he fucking stoned?\r\n\r\n1249\r\n01:27:26,351 --> 01:27:28,343\r\nHe's like that before a fight.\r\n\r\n1250\r\n01:27:28,644 --> 01:27:30,969\r\nDo you know when you're going down?\r\n\r\n1251\r\n01:27:31,230 --> 01:27:33,768\r\nOf course he knows\nwhen he's going down.\r\n\r\n1252\r\n01:27:34,024 --> 01:27:38,271\r\nFuck-face, who's speaking to you?\nHe asked him, didn't he?\r\n\r\n1253\r\n01:27:38,570 --> 01:27:41,144\r\nFuck-face? I like that one, Errol.\r\n\r\n1254\r\n01:27:41,406 --> 01:27:43,778\r\nI'll remember that next time\nI climb off your mum.\r\n\r\n1255\r\n01:27:44,034 --> 01:27:47,367\r\n- Not now.\n- Gonna be a tragedy of a fight.\r\n\r\n1256\r\n01:27:47,579 --> 01:27:50,449\r\nBe a nice one.\nHell of a way to be a war.\r\n\r\n1257\r\n01:27:50,707 --> 01:27:52,165\r\nAnd there none a yours.\r\n\r\n1258\r\n01:27:53,501 --> 01:27:57,368\r\nThere's a camp full of pikeys\nthat might not think you're so funny.\r\n\r\n1259\r\n01:27:57,630 --> 01:28:00,915\r\nNot when they're putting out flames\non their children's backs.\r\n\r\n1260\r\n01:28:02,467 --> 01:28:04,341\r\nNow get up and have a fucking fight.\r\n\r\n1261\r\n01:28:10,391 --> 01:28:13,843\r\nThree rounds and you're a vegetable,\naren't you, pikey!\r\n\r\n1262\r\n01:29:04,357 --> 01:29:07,393\r\nI'm in charge here.\nNo fucking about, no eye-gouging.\r\n\r\n1263\r\n01:29:07,652 --> 01:29:09,810\r\nDo your worst. Let's get it on!\r\n\r\n1264\r\n01:29:41,308 --> 01:29:44,095\r\nWhat the fuck's going on?\nYou gonna finish him or what?\r\n\r\n1265\r\n01:30:26,392 --> 01:30:28,016\r\nTalk about saved by the bell.\r\n\r\n1266\r\n01:30:28,560 --> 01:30:32,143\r\nDo you understand the consequences\nof knocking that man out?\r\n\r\n1267\r\n01:30:32,439 --> 01:30:34,681\r\nDo not knock him out, Mickey.\r\n\r\n1268\r\n01:30:41,322 --> 01:30:43,030\r\nAll right, let's break it up.\r\n\r\n1269\r\n01:31:17,064 --> 01:31:18,474\r\nWhat, is he fucking deaf?\r\n\r\n1270\r\n01:31:19,941 --> 01:31:21,685\r\nWhat is he doing?\r\n\r\n1271\r\n01:31:37,458 --> 01:31:38,786\r\nCome on and sit.\r\n\r\n1272\r\n01:31:41,628 --> 01:31:43,585\r\nWhat the fuck are you doing, Mickey?\r\n\r\n1273\r\n01:31:43,839 --> 01:31:45,914\r\nYou're dancing like a fairy.\r\n\r\n1274\r\n01:31:46,216 --> 01:31:48,837\r\nThey'll hang us\nif they think it's rigged.\r\n\r\n1275\r\n01:31:49,636 --> 01:31:51,758\r\nGet out there and hurt him.\r\n\r\n1276\r\n01:31:53,181 --> 01:31:58,056\r\nBut for fuck's sake,\ndo not knock him out.\r\n\r\n1277\r\n01:33:18,384 --> 01:33:21,254\r\nAll he's got to do is stay down.\r\n\r\n1278\r\n01:33:25,849 --> 01:33:28,007\r\nNow, we are fucked.\r\n\r\n1279\r\n01:33:36,317 --> 01:33:37,266\r\nHe can't stand up.\r\n\r\n1280\r\n01:33:37,526 --> 01:33:38,273\r\nWe're out of here.\r\n\r\n1281\r\n01:33:38,569 --> 01:33:43,646\r\nStupid pikey knows Brick Top's got\nkeen-to-kill monkeys with shotguns...\r\n\r\n1282\r\n01:33:43,907 --> 01:33:46,363\r\n... sitting outside his campsite.\r\n\r\n1283\r\n01:33:46,702 --> 01:33:51,577\r\nOnce the campsite's wiped out,\nI know it's gonna be the same for us.\r\n\r\n1284\r\n01:33:54,250 --> 01:33:56,077\r\nEver cross the road\nand look the wrong way?\r\n\r\n1285\r\n01:33:56,336 --> 01:33:57,794\r\nGive me that fucking shooter!\r\n\r\n1286\r\n01:33:58,087 --> 01:34:00,708\r\nAnd, hey, presto,\nthere's a car nearly on you.\r\n\r\n1287\r\n01:34:01,007 --> 01:34:02,121\r\nSo, what do you do?\r\n\r\n1288\r\n01:34:02,758 --> 01:34:04,834\r\nSomething very silly.\r\n\r\n1289\r\n01:34:05,219 --> 01:34:08,089\r\nYou freeze. And your life\ndoesn't flash before you...\r\n\r\n1290\r\n01:34:08,347 --> 01:34:10,837\r\n... because you're too scared\nto think.\r\n\r\n1291\r\n01:34:11,141 --> 01:34:14,177\r\nYou just freeze\nand pull a stupid face.\r\n\r\n1292\r\n01:34:14,477 --> 01:34:16,684\r\nBut the pikey didn't. Why?\r\n\r\n1293\r\n01:34:16,938 --> 01:34:19,725\r\nBecause he had plans\non running the car over.\r\n\r\n1294\r\n01:34:22,151 --> 01:34:24,227\r\nIt had previously occurred to me...\r\n\r\n1295\r\n01:34:24,528 --> 01:34:27,778\r\n... that he'd taken the demise\nof his mother rather lightly.\r\n\r\n1296\r\n01:34:30,993 --> 01:34:33,697\r\nFor every action,\nthere is a reaction.\r\n\r\n1297\r\n01:34:33,995 --> 01:34:35,869\r\nAnd a pikey reaction...\r\n\r\n1298\r\n01:34:36,581 --> 01:34:37,909\r\n... is quite a fucking thing.\r\n\r\n1299\r\n01:35:19,955 --> 01:35:21,994\r\nPete, talk to me.\r\n\r\n1300\r\n01:35:22,249 --> 01:35:25,831\r\nIf you want your friend to hear you,\ntalk a lot louder than that.\r\n\r\n1301\r\n01:35:34,844 --> 01:35:38,378\r\n- Give me that fucking shooter.\n- I'll give you your shooter, you cunt.\r\n\r\n1302\r\n01:35:46,438 --> 01:35:50,056\r\nThat is when I thought the pikey\nhad money riding on himself.\r\n\r\n1303\r\n01:35:51,108 --> 01:35:54,607\r\nThat's why the bastard never\ngoes down when he's supposed to.\r\n\r\n1304\r\n01:35:56,404 --> 01:35:58,148\r\nWe've been tucked up...\r\n\r\n1305\r\n01:35:59,824 --> 01:36:01,402\r\n... while he's been cleaning up.\r\n\r\n1306\r\n01:36:03,578 --> 01:36:06,151\r\nWe're worse off now than\nwhen we started.\r\n\r\n1307\r\n01:36:11,668 --> 01:36:14,076\r\nThe next day we went\nto the campsite...\r\n\r\n1308\r\n01:36:14,379 --> 01:36:17,499\r\n... but the gypsies had disappeared\nduring the night.\r\n\r\n1309\r\n01:36:17,757 --> 01:36:19,714\r\nWhich was probably a good thing...\r\n\r\n1310\r\n01:36:20,009 --> 01:36:24,386\r\n... considering they'd just buried\n12 people somewhere in the area.\r\n\r\n1311\r\n01:36:24,722 --> 01:36:26,051\r\nWhere is he?\r\n\r\n1312\r\n01:36:26,349 --> 01:36:28,425\r\nHe ain't fucking here,\nthat's for sure.\r\n\r\n1313\r\n01:36:29,268 --> 01:36:32,767\r\nWe can't ask a man to fight for us\nif we can't find him, can we?\r\n\r\n1314\r\n01:36:33,022 --> 01:36:36,271\r\nYou won't find a pikey that\ndoesn't want to be found.\r\n\r\n1315\r\n01:36:38,485 --> 01:36:41,688\r\nHe could be in a campsite\nin Kampu-fucking-chea by now.\r\n\r\n1316\r\n01:36:43,281 --> 01:36:45,072\r\nBollocks! Come on.\r\n\r\n1317\r\n01:36:50,371 --> 01:36:53,158\r\n- What you doing here?\n- What's it got to do with you?\r\n\r\n1318\r\n01:36:57,086 --> 01:36:59,208\r\nSo, what you doing here?\r\n\r\n1319\r\n01:37:06,845 --> 01:37:09,680\r\nI'm taking the dog for a walk.\nWhat's the problem?\r\n\r\n1320\r\n01:37:11,390 --> 01:37:12,256\r\nWhat's in the car?\r\n\r\n1321\r\n01:37:12,975 --> 01:37:14,469\r\nSeats and a steering wheel.\r\n\r\n1322\r\n01:37:15,644 --> 01:37:17,436\r\nWhat do you know about gypsies?\r\n\r\n1323\r\n01:37:19,231 --> 01:37:21,188\r\nI know they're not to be trusted.\r\n\r\n1324\r\n01:37:23,277 --> 01:37:25,946\r\nAll right, get your dog. On your way.\r\n\r\n1325\r\n01:37:26,821 --> 01:37:28,316\r\nGet the dog, Tommy.\r\n\r\n1326\r\n01:37:30,200 --> 01:37:31,445\r\nThe dog.\r\n\r\n1327\r\n01:37:33,036 --> 01:37:37,496\r\nAll right, boy. Come on.\nCome on, Daisy. No, Daisy!\r\n\r\n1328\r\n01:37:38,249 --> 01:37:39,909\r\nHe loves that dog.\r\n\r\n1329\r\n01:37:40,292 --> 01:37:42,000\r\nAlways playing silly games.\r\n\r\n1330\r\n01:37:42,252 --> 01:37:45,621\r\nStop messing about\nand get it in the car. Tommy!\r\n\r\n1331\r\n01:37:47,507 --> 01:37:52,252\r\nGood boy. Good boy.\nGood boy, Daisy, good boy.\r\n\r\n1332\r\n01:38:03,063 --> 01:38:04,558\r\nCould you tell me...\r\n\r\n1333\r\n01:38:04,857 --> 01:38:08,060\r\n...why you got a dead man\nwith an arm missing in your boot?\r\n\r\n1334\r\n01:38:08,694 --> 01:38:09,689\r\nHey, George...\r\n\r\n1335\r\n01:38:11,113 --> 01:38:13,271\r\n...is that a tea cosy on his head?\r\n\r\n1336\r\n01:38:16,701 --> 01:38:19,109\r\nOh, you love a dog, don't you, Tommy?\r\n\r\n1337\r\n01:38:29,046 --> 01:38:31,584\r\nTommy persuaded me to keep the dog.\r\n\r\n1338\r\n01:38:31,840 --> 01:38:35,458\r\nI eventually agreed,\nas long as he took it to a vet.\r\n\r\n1339\r\n01:38:35,719 --> 01:38:38,174\r\nI couldn't stand\nthat squeaking anymore.\r\n\r\n1340\r\n01:38:38,471 --> 01:38:41,805\r\nThe vet found half an undigested\nshoe, a squeaky toy...\r\n\r\n1341\r\n01:38:42,058 --> 01:38:45,343\r\n... and an 84-carat diamond\nlodged in its stomach.\r\n\r\n1342\r\n01:38:45,978 --> 01:38:48,469\r\nIt's quite amazing what can happen\nin a week.\r\n\r\n1343\r\n01:38:48,898 --> 01:38:50,855\r\nStill didn't shut it up, though.\r\n\r\n1344\r\n01:38:51,775 --> 01:38:53,602\r\nSo, what do you do?\r\n\r\n1345\r\n01:38:53,902 --> 01:38:56,773\r\nYou go see the man that knows\nabout these sort of things.\r\n\r\n1346\r\n01:38:57,030 --> 01:38:58,572\r\nSo, what do you think?\r\n\r\n1347\r\n01:39:00,367 --> 01:39:02,525\r\nDo you know anyone\nwho'd be interested?\r\n\r\n1348\r\n01:39:07,457 --> 01:39:08,286\r\nI might.\r\n\r\n1349\r\n01:39:09,305 --> 01:39:15,254\r\nBest watched using Open Subtitles MKV Player\r\n\r\n","markerStore":{"nextMarkerId":142,"markersById":{"0":{"range":{"start":{"row":758,"column":0},"end":{"row":758,"column":9}},"properties":{"type":"selection","editorId":104,"goalScreenRange":null},"reversed":false,"tailed":true,"valid":true,"invalidate":"never","maintainHistory":true}},"version":2},"history":{"version":3,"nextCheckpointId":1,"undoStack":[],"redoStack":[]},"encoding":"utf8","filePath":"/Users/joegesualdo/.Trash/Snatch (2000).en.srt 3.08.06 PM","digestWhenLastPersisted":"6b78a20bfc8d6448b5ff4b32d5263180450cc31d","preferredLineEnding":null,"deserializer":"TextBuffer","version":2},{"load":true,"text":"1\r\n00:00:33,050 --> 00:00:34,710\r\n<i>My name is Turkish.</i>\r\n\r\n2\r\n00:00:35,010 --> 00:00:37,086\r\n<i>Funny name for an Englishman, I know.</i>\r\n\r\n3\r\n00:00:37,346 --> 00:00:40,796\r\n<i>My parents were on the same plane\r\nwhen it crashed. That's how they met.</i>\r\n\r\n4\r\n00:00:42,224 --> 00:00:44,347\r\n<i>They named me after the plane.</i>\r\n\r\n5\r\n00:00:44,601 --> 00:00:47,092\r\n<i>Not many people are\r\nnamed after a plane crash.</i>\r\n\r\n6\r\n00:00:47,896 --> 00:00:49,307\r\n<i>That's Tommy.</i>\r\n\r\n7\r\n00:00:49,606 --> 00:00:51,764\r\n<i>He tells people\r\nhe was named after a gun.</i>\r\n\r\n8\r\n00:00:52,317 --> 00:00:57,024\r\n<i>But I know he was really named after\r\na famous 19th century ballet dancer.</i>\r\n\r\n9\r\n00:00:57,571 --> 00:01:01,189\r\n<i>Known him for as long as I can\r\nremember. He's my partner.</i>\r\n\r\n10\r\n00:01:01,533 --> 00:01:04,154\r\n<i>Doesn't mean we hold hands\r\nor take walks.</i>\r\n\r\n11\r\n00:01:04,452 --> 00:01:08,744\r\n<i>It means I try to keep him out of\r\nas much trouble as he inflicts on me.</i>\r\n\r\n12\r\n00:01:08,997 --> 00:01:11,867\r\n<i>I give him a hard time.\r\nKeeps him in check.</i>\r\n\r\n13\r\n00:01:12,166 --> 00:01:14,622\r\n<i>But really, he's like my brother.</i>\r\n\r\n14\r\n00:01:15,336 --> 00:01:18,954\r\n<i>What do I know about diamonds?\r\nI'm a boxing promoter.</i>\r\n\r\n15\r\n00:01:19,256 --> 00:01:22,838\r\n<i>I was a happy boxing promoter\r\nuntil a week ago, and then:</i>\r\n\r\n16\r\n00:01:23,134 --> 00:01:25,292\r\n<i>What do I know about diamonds?</i>\r\n\r\n17\r\n00:01:26,137 --> 00:01:28,213\r\n<i>Don't they come from Antwerp?</i>\r\n\r\n18\r\n00:01:29,181 --> 00:01:32,431\r\n<i>- Himy, would you listen to this?\r\n- Do we have a choice?</i>\r\n\r\n19\r\n00:01:32,726 --> 00:01:36,390\r\n<i>It wasn't meant to be taken literally.</i>\r\n\r\n20\r\n00:01:36,687 --> 00:01:39,439\r\n<i>It's a nice story, Adam and Eve.</i>\r\n\r\n21\r\n00:01:39,690 --> 00:01:41,729\r\n<i>It's bound with moral fibre...</i>\r\n\r\n22\r\n00:01:42,025 --> 00:01:45,608\r\n<i>... but asking a grown man\r\nto believe it?</i>\r\n\r\n23\r\n00:01:46,612 --> 00:01:47,857\r\n<i>What is it?</i>\r\n\r\n24\r\n00:01:50,115 --> 00:01:51,609\r\n<i>Well, what is it?</i>\r\n\r\n25\r\n00:01:53,285 --> 00:01:56,617\r\n<i>What you want I should do,\r\ndrop my pants?</i>\r\n\r\n26\r\n00:01:56,912 --> 00:01:58,490\r\n<i>Okay, go through.</i>\r\n\r\n27\r\n00:01:59,872 --> 00:02:01,912\r\n<i>It's a nice story.</i>\r\n\r\n28\r\n00:02:02,625 --> 00:02:05,579\r\n<i>It's just that. Just a story.</i>\r\n\r\n29\r\n00:02:05,878 --> 00:02:09,246\r\n<i>Catholic religion is based\r\non a mistranslation.</i>\r\n\r\n30\r\n00:02:09,548 --> 00:02:11,955\r\n<i>Enough already. Ruben, say something.</i>\r\n\r\n31\r\n00:02:12,259 --> 00:02:14,795\r\n<i>Listen. Are you busy?\r\nI'll tell you the whole story.</i>\r\n\r\n32\r\n00:02:15,052 --> 00:02:19,263\r\n<i>The Septuagint scholars mistranslated\r\nthe Hebrew word for \"young woman\"...</i>\r\n\r\n33\r\n00:02:19,556 --> 00:02:21,679\r\n<i>... into the Greek word for \"virgin.\"</i>\r\n\r\n34\r\n00:02:21,933 --> 00:02:24,341\r\n<i>It was an easy mistake to make...</i>\r\n\r\n35\r\n00:02:24,602 --> 00:02:29,144\r\n<i>... because there was only a subtle\r\ndifference in the spelling.</i>\r\n\r\n36\r\n00:02:39,115 --> 00:02:41,272\r\n<i>So, they came up with a prophecy:</i>\r\n\r\n37\r\n00:02:41,574 --> 00:02:45,738\r\n<i>\"Behold, the virgin shall conceive\r\nand bear us a son. \"</i>\r\n\r\n38\r\n00:02:45,995 --> 00:02:50,040\r\n<i>You understand? It was \"virgin\"\r\nthat caught people's attention.</i>\r\n\r\n39\r\n00:02:50,333 --> 00:02:54,495\r\n<i>It's not everyday a virgin conceives\r\nand bears a son.</i>\r\n\r\n40\r\n00:03:10,599 --> 00:03:14,810\r\n<i>But leave that for a couple\r\nof hundred years to stew...</i>\r\n\r\n41\r\n00:03:15,103 --> 00:03:18,638\r\n<i>... and next thing you know you have\r\nthe Holy Catholic Church.</i>\r\n\r\n42\r\n00:03:18,940 --> 00:03:22,023\r\n<i>Oy vay, what are you saying?</i>\r\n\r\n43\r\n00:03:22,276 --> 00:03:24,849\r\n<i>I'm saying, just because\r\nit's written...</i>\r\n\r\n44\r\n00:03:25,153 --> 00:03:26,647\r\n<i>... doesn't make it so.</i>\r\n\r\n45\r\n00:03:26,947 --> 00:03:30,814\r\n<i>Gives them hope. It's not important\r\nwhether it's fact or fiction.</i>\r\n\r\n46\r\n00:03:31,117 --> 00:03:33,488\r\n<i>- People like to believe.\r\n- I don't want to hear anymore.</i>\r\n\r\n47\r\n00:03:33,744 --> 00:03:36,994\r\n<i>Anyway, who is it that we're seeing?</i>\r\n\r\n48\r\n00:03:37,664 --> 00:03:39,288\r\n<i>- Michael.\r\n- Hello?</i>\r\n\r\n49\r\n00:03:41,042 --> 00:03:42,240\r\n<i>Mutti.</i>\r\n\r\n50\r\n00:03:42,543 --> 00:03:46,161\r\nRudy! Rud, Rud, let them in, please.\r\n\r\n51\r\n00:03:48,965 --> 00:03:52,168\r\nRud, it's okay, let them through.\r\n\r\n52\r\n00:03:52,427 --> 00:03:53,422\r\n- Michael.\r\n- Mutti.\r\n\r\n53\r\n00:03:53,678 --> 00:03:58,339\r\nYou've kept us waiting for half an hour.\r\nAre you trying to give me heartburn?\r\n\r\n54\r\n00:04:04,854 --> 00:04:06,312\r\nLie down on the floor.\r\n\r\n55\r\n00:04:08,857 --> 00:04:10,055\r\nGet on the floor!\r\n\r\n56\r\n00:04:10,818 --> 00:04:12,016\r\nLie on the floor!\r\n\r\n57\r\n00:04:12,319 --> 00:04:13,978\r\nGet on the fucking floor!\r\n\r\n58\r\n00:04:14,987 --> 00:04:17,608\r\n- Get down!\r\n- Get fucking down!\r\n\r\n59\r\n00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:20,114\r\nDown on the floor! Get down!\r\n\r\n60\r\n00:04:20,409 --> 00:04:21,607\r\nOn the ground!\r\n\r\n61\r\n00:04:25,997 --> 00:04:27,621\r\nGet down, I say!\r\n\r\n62\r\n00:04:27,915 --> 00:04:29,907\r\n- Time.\r\n- Seven minutes!\r\n\r\n63\r\n00:04:33,712 --> 00:04:34,910\r\nWhere is the stone?\r\n\r\n64\r\n00:04:38,550 --> 00:04:40,256\r\nWhere is the stone?\r\n\r\n65\r\n00:04:41,802 --> 00:04:44,423\r\nWhere is the stone?\r\n\r\n66\r\n00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:51,178\r\nMichael, where is the stone?\r\n\r\n67\r\n00:06:17,340 --> 00:06:19,416\r\nWhen does your plane leave?\r\n\r\n68\r\n00:06:19,968 --> 00:06:21,711\r\nTwenty minutes.\r\n\r\n69\r\n00:06:22,470 --> 00:06:24,012\r\nGive me your gun.\r\n\r\n70\r\n00:06:35,564 --> 00:06:37,557\r\nWhen you get to London...\r\n\r\n71\r\n00:06:37,817 --> 00:06:39,643\r\n...if you want a gun...\r\n\r\n72\r\n00:06:40,443 --> 00:06:41,771\r\n...call this number.\r\n\r\n73\r\n00:06:46,282 --> 00:06:48,570\r\n- Boris.\r\n- Boris.\r\n\r\n74\r\n00:06:49,285 --> 00:06:51,989\r\nHe can get you anything you need.\r\n\r\n75\r\n00:06:59,126 --> 00:07:01,000\r\nIs he allowed to do that?\r\n\r\n76\r\n00:07:01,336 --> 00:07:05,583\r\nIt's an unlicensed boxing match.\r\nIt's not a tickling competition.\r\n\r\n77\r\n00:07:05,882 --> 00:07:07,921\r\nThese lads are out\r\nto hurt each other.\r\n\r\n78\r\n00:07:08,634 --> 00:07:10,507\r\nWhat's with those sausages,\r\nCharlie?\r\n\r\n79\r\n00:07:10,802 --> 00:07:12,380\r\nTwo minutes, Turkish.\r\n\r\n80\r\n00:07:14,097 --> 00:07:17,797\r\nLook at it. How am I supposed\r\nto run this thing from that?\r\n\r\n81\r\n00:07:18,101 --> 00:07:19,559\r\nWe'll need a proper office.\r\n\r\n82\r\n00:07:19,852 --> 00:07:22,769\r\nI want a new one.\r\nYou're going to buy it for me.\r\n\r\n83\r\n00:07:23,063 --> 00:07:24,605\r\nWhy me?\r\n\r\n84\r\n00:07:25,357 --> 00:07:27,230\r\nWell, you know about caravans.\r\n\r\n85\r\n00:07:27,483 --> 00:07:28,894\r\nHow's that?\r\n\r\n86\r\n00:07:29,235 --> 00:07:32,568\r\nYou spent a summer in one.\r\nWhich means you know more than me.\r\n\r\n87\r\n00:07:32,863 --> 00:07:36,029\r\nAnd I don't want to have me pants\r\npulled down over the price.\r\n\r\n88\r\n00:07:36,324 --> 00:07:37,604\r\nWhat's wrong with this one?\r\n\r\n89\r\n00:07:39,410 --> 00:07:4