rds earlier.\r\n\r\n745\r\n01:08:00,680 --> 01:08:04,639\r\nIt was nothin' serious.\r\nYou might call it a lovers' quarrel.\r\n\r\n746\r\n01:08:05,600 --> 01:08:08,398\r\nSo you went right out\r\nand picked yourself up another dame.\r\n\r\n747\r\n01:08:08,520 --> 01:08:13,116\r\n- Something like that.\r\n- You know, Baxter, you're a real cutie pie.\r\n\r\n748\r\n01:08:13,240 --> 01:08:14,719\r\nYes, you are.\r\n\r\n749\r\n01:08:22,560 --> 01:08:27,475\r\nIf you'd come home half an hour later,\r\nyou'd have had quite a Christmas present.\r\n\r\n750\r\n01:08:45,520 --> 01:08:47,476\r\nGet the coffee.\r\n\r\n751\r\n01:09:10,120 --> 01:09:12,839\r\nLet's get some air in here.\r\nOpen the windows.\r\n\r\n752\r\n01:09:27,520 --> 01:09:29,476\r\nWhat's her name?\r\n\r\n753\r\n01:09:29,600 --> 01:09:32,194\r\nMiss Kubelik. Fran.\r\n\r\n754\r\n01:09:35,440 --> 01:09:40,468\r\nFran, I'm a doctor. I'm here because\r\nyou took too many sleeping pills.\r\n\r\n755\r\n01:09:40,600 --> 01:09:42,716\r\nDo you understand what I'm saying?\r\n\r\n756\r\n01:09:44,400 --> 01:09:47,710\r\nFran, I'm Dr Dreyfuss.\r\nI'm here to help you.\r\n\r\n757\r\n01:09:47,840 --> 01:09:50,638\r\nYou took all those sleeping pills.\r\nRemember?\r\n\r\n758\r\n01:09:51,800 --> 01:09:55,270\r\n- Sleeping pills.\r\n- That's right, Fran. And I'm a doctor.\r\n\r\n759\r\n01:09:56,080 --> 01:09:58,799\r\n- Doctor?\r\n- Dr Dreyfuss.\r\n\r\n760\r\n01:10:01,200 --> 01:10:02,713\r\nDreyfuss.\r\n\r\n761\r\n01:10:02,840 --> 01:10:04,796\r\nGet more coffee.\r\n\r\n762\r\n01:10:05,680 --> 01:10:08,035\r\nNow tell me again. What's my name?\r\n\r\n763\r\n01:10:11,120 --> 01:10:13,395\r\nDr... Dreyfuss.\r\n\r\n764\r\n01:10:13,520 --> 01:10:15,476\r\nAnd what happened to you?\r\n\r\n765\r\n01:10:16,040 --> 01:10:17,040\r\nI...\r\n\r\n766\r\n01:10:17,800 --> 01:10:19,756\r\nI took sleeping pills.\r\n\r\n767\r\n01:10:20,320 --> 01:10:22,675\r\nDo you know where you are?\r\n\r\n768\r\n01:10:24,600 --> 01:10:27,751\r\n- No.\r\n- Yes, you do, Fran. Now concentrate!\r\n\r\n769\r\n01:10:29,600 --> 01:10:31,556\r\nI don't know.\r\n\r\n770\r\n01:10:32,440 --> 01:10:34,396\r\nDo you know who that is?\r\n\r\n771\r\n01:10:40,880 --> 01:10:42,836\r\nLook at him.\r\n\r\n772\r\n01:10:43,880 --> 01:10:46,633\r\nMr Baxter. 19th floor.\r\n\r\n773\r\n01:10:47,320 --> 01:10:49,276\r\nHello, Miss Kubelik.\r\n\r\n774\r\n01:10:49,720 --> 01:10:52,154\r\nMr? Miss? Such politeness!\r\n\r\n775\r\n01:10:53,400 --> 01:10:57,234\r\nWe work in the same building.\r\nWe try to keep it quiet.\r\n\r\n776\r\n01:10:58,840 --> 01:11:01,400\r\nWhat are you doing here?\r\n\r\n777\r\n01:11:02,920 --> 01:11:06,515\r\nDon't you remember\r\nwe were together at the office party?\r\n\r\n778\r\n01:11:06,640 --> 01:11:08,949\r\nOh, yes. The office party.\r\n\r\n779\r\n01:11:09,080 --> 01:11:11,548\r\n- Miss Olsen.\r\n- That's right.\r\n\r\n780\r\n01:11:11,680 --> 01:11:14,513\r\nI told you we had a fight.\r\nThat was what it was about.\r\n\r\n781\r\n01:11:14,640 --> 01:11:17,837\r\nMiss Olsen. That girl\r\nthat was here earlier.\r\n\r\n782\r\n01:11:19,360 --> 01:11:21,954\r\nI don't understand.\r\n\r\n783\r\n01:11:22,080 --> 01:11:27,234\r\nThe main thing is I got here in time and\r\nyou're gonna be all right. Isn't she, Doc?\r\n\r\n784\r\n01:11:28,120 --> 01:11:30,315\r\nI'm so tired.\r\n\r\n785\r\n01:11:30,440 --> 01:11:32,396\r\nCome on. Drink this.\r\n\r\n786\r\n01:11:32,760 --> 01:11:35,354\r\nPlease... just let me sleep.\r\n\r\n787\r\n01:11:35,480 --> 01:11:39,109\r\nNo, you can't sleep! Fran, open your eyes!\r\n\r\n788\r\n01:11:39,760 --> 01:11:41,716\r\nLet's get her walking.\r\n\r\n789\r\n01:11:44,280 --> 01:11:48,717\r\nWe've got to keep her awake for the next\r\nfew hours. Now come on, Fran, walk!\r\n\r\n790\r\n01:11:48,840 --> 01:11:51,308\r\nOne, two, three, four!\r\n\r\n791\r\n01:11:51,440 --> 01:11:53,635\r\nOne, two, three, four!\r\n\r\n792\r\n01:11:53,760 --> 01:11:55,876\r\nLeft, right, left, right...\r\n\r\n793\r\n01:11:56,000 --> 01:11:58,150\r\n...left, right and return!\r\n\r\n794\r\n01:11:58,280 --> 01:12:01,352\r\nAnd... one, two, three, four!\r\n\r\n795\r\n01:12:01,480 --> 01:12:04,756\r\nNow you've got it! One, two, three, four!\r\n\r\n796\r\n01:12:04,880 --> 01:12:07,997\r\nWalk, Fran! One, two, three, four!\r\n\r\n797\r\n01:12:08,120 --> 01:12:10,680\r\nOne, two... And return again.\r\n\r\n798\r\n01:12:10,800 --> 01:12:13,792\r\nAnd... left, right, left, right.\r\n\r\n799\r\n01:12:20,720 --> 01:12:23,917\r\nShe'll sleep on and off\r\nfor the next 24 hours.\r\n\r\n800\r\n01:12:24,040 --> 01:12:27,589\r\nOf course, she'll have\r\na dandy hangover when she wakes up.\r\n\r\n801\r\n01:12:27,720 --> 01:12:29,676\r\nJust as long as she's OK.\r\n\r\n802\r\n01:12:29,800 --> 01:12:35,079\r\nThese cases are harder on the doctor than\r\nthe patient. I oughta charge by the mile.\r\n\r\n803\r\n01:12:35,200 --> 01:12:38,158\r\n- Any of that coffee left?\r\n- Yeah, sure.\r\n\r\n804\r\n01:12:39,120 --> 01:12:41,475\r\nHow do you spell her last name?\r\n\r\n805\r\n01:12:41,600 --> 01:12:43,989\r\nKubelik. Two k's.\r\n\r\n806\r\n01:12:44,120 --> 01:12:46,076\r\nWhat's her address?\r\n\r\n807\r\n01:12:46,800 --> 01:12:48,756\r\nWhere does she live?\r\n\r\n808\r\n01:12:49,720 --> 01:12:52,075\r\nWhy do you wanna know, Doc?\r\n\r\n809\r\n01:12:53,120 --> 01:12:56,157\r\n- You don't have to report this, do you?\r\n- It's regulations.\r\n\r\n810\r\n01:12:56,280 --> 01:13:01,070\r\nBut it was an accident. She had too much\r\nto drink, didn't know what she was doing.\r\n\r\n811\r\n01:13:01,200 --> 01:13:03,270\r\nThere was no suicide note or anything.\r\n\r\n812\r\n01:13:03,400 --> 01:13:06,392\r\n- I'm not thinkin' about myself.\r\n- Aren't you?\r\n\r\n813\r\n01:13:06,520 --> 01:13:09,876\r\nShe's got a family,\r\nand there's the people at the office.\r\n\r\n814\r\n01:13:10,000 --> 01:13:13,754\r\nCan't you forget you're a doctor,\r\njust say you're here as a neighbour?\r\n\r\n815\r\n01:13:13,880 --> 01:13:16,633\r\nWell, as a doctor, I can't prove\r\nit wasn't an accident.\r\n\r\n816\r\n01:13:16,760 --> 01:13:19,832\r\nBut as your neighbour,\r\nI'd like to kick you around the block.\r\n\r\n817\r\n01:13:19,960 --> 01:13:22,394\r\n- Mind if I cool this off?\r\n- Help yourself.\r\n\r\n818\r\n01:13:22,520 --> 01:13:24,829\r\nI don't know what you did to that girl...\r\n\r\n819\r\n01:13:24,960 --> 01:13:27,394\r\n...but it was bound to happen,\r\nthe way you carry on.\r\n\r\n820\r\n01:13:27,520 --> 01:13:29,875\r\nLive now, pay later. Diners Club!\r\n\r\n821\r\n01:13:31,760 --> 01:13:34,593\r\nWhy don't you grow up, Baxter?\r\nBe a <i>mensch.</i>\r\n\r\n822\r\n01:13:34,720 --> 01:13:37,029\r\n- You know what that means?\r\n- I'm not sure.\r\n\r\n823\r\n01:13:37,160 --> 01:13:39,116\r\nA <i>mensch!</i> A human being!\r\n\r\n824\r\n01:13:40,080 --> 01:13:42,992\r\nSo you got off easy this time.\r\nSo you were lucky.\r\n\r\n825\r\n01:13:43,120 --> 01:13:47,591\r\nBut you're not out of the woods yet,\r\nbecause most of 'em try it again.\r\n\r\n826\r\n01:13:48,600 --> 01:13:51,068\r\nWell, you know where I am\r\nif you need me.\r\n\r\n827\r\n01:15:00,120 --> 01:15:02,793\r\nMr Baxter! Open up already.\r\n\r\n828\r\n01:15:05,920 --> 01:15:06,920\r\nOh.\r\n\r\n829\r\n01:15:07,960 --> 01:15:11,236\r\n- Mrs Lieberman.\r\n- Who did you think it was? Kriss Kringle?\r\n\r\n830\r\n01:15:11,360 --> 01:15:13,396\r\nWhat was going on here last night?\r\n\r\n831\r\n01:15:13,520 --> 01:15:16,751\r\n- Last night?\r\n- All that marching! Tramp, tramp, tramp!\r\n\r\n832\r\n01:15:16,880 --> 01:15:20,156\r\n- Army manoeuvres maybe?\r\n- I'll never invite those people again.\r\n\r\n833\r\n01:15:20,280 --> 01:15:24,319\r\nWhat you get from renting to bachelors.\r\nAll night I didn't sleep ten minutes.\r\n\r\n834\r\n01:15:24,440 --> 01:15:29,719\r\n- And I'm sure you woke up Dr Dreyfuss.\r\n- Don't worry. He was out on a case.\r\n\r\n835\r\n01:15:29,840 --> 01:15:34,755\r\nI'm warning you, Mr Baxter. This is\r\na respectable house, not a honky-tonky.\r\n\r\n836\r\n01:15:34,880 --> 01:15:36,836\r\nCome on, Oscar.\r\n\r\n837\r\n01:16:02,720 --> 01:16:07,191\r\nOperator, I want White Plains,\r\nNew York. Mr JD Sheldrake.\r\n\r\n838\r\n01:16:07,320 --> 01:16:09,276\r\nMake that person-to-person.\r\n\r\n839\r\n01:16:13,880 --> 01:16:16,792\r\nFive, four, three, two, one...\r\n\r\n840\r\n01:16:16,920 --> 01:16:19,320\r\nLet her rip!\r\n\r\n841\r\n01:16:19,520 --> 01:16:21,078\r\nI'll get the phone.\r\n\r\n842\r\n01:16:21,200 --> 01:16:24,033\r\nHey, Dad, why don't we\r\nput a fly in the nose cone?\r\n\r\n843\r\n01:16:24,160 --> 01:16:26,958\r\n- See if we can bring it back alive.\r\n- That's a thought.\r\n\r\n844\r\n01:16:27,080 --> 01:16:30,993\r\nMaybe we should put in two flies\r\nand see if they'll propagate in orbit.\r\n\r\n845\r\n01:16:31,120 --> 01:16:35,113\r\n- See if they'll what?\r\n- Propagate. You know. Multiply.\r\n\r\n846\r\n01:16:35,240 --> 01:16:38,789\r\n- Baby flies?\r\n- Oh. Oh!\r\n\r\n847\r\n01:16:39,600 --> 01:16:42,068\r\n- It's for you, Dad.\r\n- Thanks, Jeff.\r\n\r\n848\r\n01:16:42,200 --> 01:16:45,272\r\nA Mr Baxter. Person-to-person.\r\n\r\n849\r\n01:16:45,400 --> 01:16:47,914\r\nCome on. Help me round up some flies.\r\n\r\n850\r\n01:16:48,040 --> 01:16:52,591\r\n- Hello? What's on your mind, Baxter?\r\n- Something came up that's important.\r\n\r\n851\r\n01:16:52,720 --> 01:16:56,156\r\nI think you should see me\r\nat the apartment as soon as possible.\r\n\r\n852\r\n01:16:56,280 --> 01:16:59,875\r\n- What's this all about?\r\n- I didn't wanna tell you over the phone.\r\n\r\n853\r\n01:17:00,000 --> 01:17:04,915\r\nBut that certain party... You know\r\nwho I mean. I found her here last night.\r\n\r\n854\r\n01:17:05,040 --> 01:17:08,032\r\n- She took an overdose of sleeping pills.\r\n- What?!\r\n\r\n855\r\n01:17:09,360 --> 01:17:13,194\r\n- What is it, Jeff? Who's on the phone?\r\n- One of our employees had an accident.\r\n\r\n856\r\n01:17:13,320 --> 01:17:16,596\r\nI don't know why they bother me\r\nwith these things on Christmas Day.\r\n\r\n857\r\n01:17:16,720 --> 01:17:18,472\r\nYes, Baxter.\r\n\r\n858\r\n01:17:18,600 --> 01:17:20,556\r\nJust how serious is it?\r\n\r\n859\r\n01:17:20,680 --> 01:17:24,195\r\nIt was touch and go there for a while,\r\nbut she's sleeping it off now.\r\n\r\n860\r\n01:17:24,320 --> 01:17:27,198\r\nI thought maybe you'd like to\r\nbe here when she wakes up.\r\n\r\n861\r\n01:17:28,240 --> 01:17:32,518\r\nThat's impossible. You'll have to\r\nhandle the situation yourself, Baxter.\r\n\r\n862\r\n01:17:32,640 --> 01:17:36,872\r\n- As a matter of fact, I'm counting on you.\r\n- Yes, sir. I understand.\r\n\r\n863\r\n01:17:37,000 --> 01:17:41,198\r\nShe left a letter. Would you like me\r\nto open it and read it to you?\r\n\r\n864\r\n01:17:41,320 --> 01:17:43,959\r\nWell, it was just a suggestion.\r\n\r\n865\r\n01:17:44,080 --> 01:17:47,834\r\nNo, don't worry. I kept your name\r\nout of it, so there'll be no trouble...\r\n\r\n866\r\n01:17:47,960 --> 01:17:50,315\r\n...policewise or newspaperwise.\r\n\r\n867\r\n01:17:51,520 --> 01:17:55,718\r\nYou see, the doctor is a friend of mine,\r\nso we were very lucky in that respect.\r\n\r\n868\r\n01:17:55,840 --> 01:17:58,195\r\nActually, he thinks she's my girl.\r\n\r\n869\r\n01:17:59,040 --> 01:18:01,190\r\nNo, he just jumped to the conclusion.\r\n\r\n870\r\n01:18:01,320 --> 01:18:04,039\r\nAround here I'm known as\r\nquite a ladies' man.\r\n\r\n871\r\n01:18:04,160 --> 01:18:08,233\r\nOf course, we're not out of the woods yet.\r\nSometimes they try it again.\r\n\r\n872\r\n01:18:08,360 --> 01:18:12,114\r\nYes, sir. I'll do my best. It'll take her\r\na couple of days to fully recover...\r\n\r\n873\r\n01:18:12,240 --> 01:18:15,391\r\n...and I may have a little problem\r\nwith the landlady.\r\n\r\n874\r\n01:18:16,080 --> 01:18:19,390\r\nOK, Mr Sheldrake. I'll keep her\r\nin the apartment as long as I can.\r\n\r\n875\r\n01:18:19,520 --> 01:18:22,910\r\nIsn't there some sort of message\r\nyou want me to give her?\r\n\r\n876\r\n01:18:23,360 --> 01:18:25,476\r\nWell, I'll... think of something.\r\n\r\n877\r\n01:18:26,040 --> 01:18:28,076\r\nYes, sir. Goodbye, Mr Sheldrake.\r\n\r\n878\r\n01:18:30,840 --> 01:18:32,796\r\nI'm sorry.\r\n\r\n879\r\n01:18:33,520 --> 01:18:36,990\r\n- I'm sorry, Mr Baxter.\r\n- What are you doing out of bed?\r\n\r\n880\r\n01:18:37,120 --> 01:18:40,192\r\nI didn't know. I had no idea\r\nthis was your apartment.\r\n\r\n881\r\n01:18:40,320 --> 01:18:42,914\r\nHere. Let me help you.\r\n\r\n882\r\n01:18:43,400 --> 01:18:45,356\r\nOh, I'm so ashamed.\r\n\r\n883\r\n01:18:45,480 --> 01:18:47,436\r\nWhy didn't you just let me die?\r\n\r\n884\r\n01:18:47,560 --> 01:18:52,918\r\nWhat kind of talk is that? You got\r\na little overemotional, but you're fine now.\r\n\r\n885\r\n01:18:53,040 --> 01:18:54,040\r\nOh!\r\n\r\n886\r\n01:18:54,560 --> 01:18:58,712\r\nOh, my head! It feels just like\r\na big wad of chewing gum.\r\n\r\n887\r\n01:18:58,840 --> 01:19:01,479\r\n- What time is it?\r\n- Two o'clock.\r\n\r\n888\r\n01:19:01,600 --> 01:19:03,750\r\nOh, my dress. I have to go home.\r\n\r\n889\r\n01:19:03,880 --> 01:19:06,235\r\nYou're in no shape\r\nto go anywhere but back to bed.\r\n\r\n890\r\n01:19:06,360 --> 01:19:08,749\r\n- You don't want me here.\r\n- Sure I do. I...\r\n\r\n891\r\n01:19:08,880 --> 01:19:11,872\r\nIt's always nice\r\nto have company for Christmas.\r\n\r\n892\r\n01:19:12,000 --> 01:19:15,390\r\n- I'm stronger than you are.\r\n- I just wanna brush my teeth.\r\n\r\n893\r\n01:19:15,520 --> 01:19:18,910\r\nOh. Of course. I think I can find\r\na new toothbrush somewhere.\r\n\r\n894\r\n01:19:19,040 --> 01:19:21,600\r\nHere. Put that on.\r\n\r\n895\r\n01:19:49,120 --> 01:19:52,715\r\n- How about some breakfast?\r\n- No. I don't want anything.\r\n\r\n896\r\n01:19:52,840 --> 01:19:54,796\r\nI'll fix you some coffee.\r\n\r\n897\r\n01:19:54,920 --> 01:19:59,072\r\nOh! We're all out of coffee.\r\nYou had quite a lot last night.\r\n\r\n898\r\n01:19:59,200 --> 01:20:01,156\r\nBack in a minute.\r\n\r\n899\r\n01:20:10,200 --> 01:20:12,430\r\nMrs Dreyfuss,\r\ncould I borrow some coffee?\r\n\r\n900\r\n01:20:12,560 --> 01:20:16,189\r\n- And an orange and a couple of eggs?\r\n- Eggs, he asks me for! Oranges!\r\n\r\n901\r\n01:20:16,320 --> 01:20:20,632\r\nWhat you need is a good horsewhipping!\r\nFrom me the doctor has no secrets.\r\n\r\n902\r\n01:20:20,760 --> 01:20:22,910\r\nPoor girl. How could you do such a thing?\r\n\r\n903\r\n01:20:23,040 --> 01:20:25,873\r\nI didn't do anything. Honest. It's just...\r\n\r\n904\r\n01:20:26,720 --> 01:20:31,999\r\nYou take a girl out just for laughs and\r\nshe thinks you're serious marriagewise.\r\n\r\n905\r\n01:20:32,120 --> 01:20:35,476\r\nBig shot! For you, I wouldn't lift a finger!\r\n\r\n906\r\n01:20:35,600 --> 01:20:38,558\r\nBut for her, I'll fix a little something to eat.\r\n\r\n907\r\n01:20:46,760 --> 01:20:48,432\r\nWho are you calling?\r\n\r\n908\r\n01:20:48,560 --> 01:20:50,596\r\nMy sister, to tell her\r\nwhat happened to me.\r\n\r\n909\r\n01:20:50,720 --> 01:20:55,475\r\nWait a minute! Let's talk it over first.\r\nJust what are you gonna tell her?\r\n\r\n910\r\n01:20:56,240 --> 01:21:00,028\r\n- I haven't figured it out exactly.\r\n- Well, you'd better figure it out exactly.\r\n\r\n911\r\n01:21:00,160 --> 01:21:03,118\r\nSuppose she asks you why\r\nyou didn't come home last night.\r\n\r\n912\r\n01:21:03,240 --> 01:21:05,117\r\nI'll say I spent the night with a friend.\r\n\r\n913\r\n01:21:05,240 --> 01:21:07,196\r\n- Who?\r\n- Someone from the office.\r\n\r\n914\r\n01:21:07,320 --> 01:21:09,072\r\n- Where are you now?\r\n- In his apartment.\r\n\r\n915\r\n01:21:09,200 --> 01:21:11,475\r\n- In <i>his</i> apartment?\r\n- In <i>her</i> apartment.\r\n\r\n916\r\n01:21:11,600 --> 01:21:13,716\r\n- What's your friend's name?\r\n- Baxter.\r\n\r\n917\r\n01:21:13,840 --> 01:21:16,798\r\n- What's her first name?\r\n- Miss.\r\n\r\n918\r\n01:21:16,920 --> 01:21:19,639\r\n- When are you comin' home?\r\n- As soon as I can walk.\r\n\r\n919\r\n01:21:19,760 --> 01:21:21,716\r\n- Your legs hurt?\r\n- No, my stomach.\r\n\r\n920\r\n01:21:21,840 --> 01:21:24,513\r\n- Your stomach?\r\n- They had to pump it out!\r\n\r\n921\r\n01:21:24,640 --> 01:21:29,350\r\nYou shouldn't call anybody. Not till you\r\nget the chewing gum out of your head.\r\n\r\n922\r\n01:21:29,480 --> 01:21:32,517\r\nThey'll be worried about me.\r\nThey might call the police.\r\n\r\n923\r\n01:21:32,640 --> 01:21:35,712\r\nWe have to be careful.\r\nWe don't wanna involve anybody.\r\n\r\n924\r\n01:21:35,840 --> 01:21:38,798\r\nAfter all, Mr Sheldrake's a married man.\r\n\r\n925\r\n01:21:39,600 --> 01:21:41,556\r\nThanks for reminding me\r\n\r\n926\r\n01:21:45,200 --> 01:21:47,156\r\nI didn't mean it that way.\r\n\r\n927\r\n01:21:47,280 --> 01:21:51,239\r\nI was just talking to him on the phone.\r\nHe's very concerned about you.\r\n\r\n928\r\n01:21:51,360 --> 01:21:53,999\r\nHe doesn't give a damn about me.\r\n\r\n929\r\n01:21:54,120 --> 01:21:57,715\r\n- You're wrong. He told me...\r\n- He's a liar.\r\n\r\n930\r\n01:21:57,840 --> 01:21:59,990\r\nBut that's not the worst part.\r\n\r\n931\r\n01:22:00,120 --> 01:22:02,395\r\nThe worst part is I still love him.\r\n\r\n932\r\n01:22:06,280 --> 01:22:08,396\r\nOh. That must be Mrs Dreyfuss.\r\n\r\n933\r\n01:22:08,520 --> 01:22:11,830\r\nRemember the doctor from last night?\r\nThat's his wife.\r\n\r\n934\r\n01:22:13,480 --> 01:22:15,436\r\nSo where's the victim?\r\n\r\n935\r\n01:22:16,440 --> 01:22:18,396\r\nMax the Knife!\r\n\r\n936\r\n01:22:20,920 --> 01:22:24,993\r\n<i>- Nu,</i> little lady, how are we feeling today?\r\n- I don't know. Kind of dizzy.\r\n\r\n937\r\n01:22:25,120 --> 01:22:30,274\r\nThe best thing for dizzy is noodle soup\r\nwith chicken white meat and a glass tea.\r\n\r\n938\r\n01:22:30,400 --> 01:22:34,678\r\n- No, thank you. I'm really not hungry.\r\n- Go ahead, eat. Enjoy.\r\n\r\n939\r\n01:22:34,800 --> 01:22:37,598\r\nYou wouldn't have such a thing\r\nas a napkin, would you?\r\n\r\n940\r\n01:22:37,720 --> 01:22:40,792\r\n- I have some paper towels.\r\n- Beatnik.\r\n\r\n941\r\n01:22:40,920 --> 01:22:44,276\r\nIn my kitchen, third drawer,\r\nunder the good silver, are napkins.\r\n\r\n942\r\n01:22:44,400 --> 01:22:45,719\r\nYes, Mrs Dreyfuss.\r\n\r\n943\r\n01:22:45,840 --> 01:22:48,354\r\nSo, what are you waiting for?\r\nA singing commercial?\r\n\r\n944\r\n01:22:48,480 --> 01:22:50,436\r\n- I can't eat.\r\n- You must eat.\r\n\r\n945\r\n01:22:50,560 --> 01:22:53,597\r\nAnd you must get healthy\r\nand you must forget him.\r\n\r\n946\r\n01:22:53,720 --> 01:22:56,871\r\nSuch a fine boy he seemed\r\nwhen he first moved in here.\r\n\r\n947\r\n01:22:57,000 --> 01:22:59,878\r\nClean and cut, a regular Ivy Leaguer.\r\n\r\n948\r\n01:23:00,000 --> 01:23:04,278\r\nTurns out he's King Farouk,\r\nwith the drinking, with the cha-cha.\r\n\r\n949\r\n01:23:04,400 --> 01:23:06,356\r\nWith the no napkins.\r\n\r\n950\r\n01:23:06,480 --> 01:23:10,359\r\nA girl like you, for the rest of your life\r\nyou wanna cry in your noodle soup?\r\n\r\n951\r\n01:23:10,480 --> 01:23:12,948\r\nWho needs it? Now you listen to me.\r\n\r\n952\r\n01:23:13,080 --> 01:23:17,073\r\nYou'll find yourself a nice,\r\nsubstantial man - a widower, maybe -\r\n\r\n953\r\n01:23:17,200 --> 01:23:20,715\r\nand settle down, instead of\r\n<i>noshing</i> all those sleeping pills.\r\n\r\n954\r\n01:23:20,840 --> 01:23:23,877\r\nFor what? For whom?\r\nFor some good-time Charlie?\r\n\r\n955\r\n01:23:24,000 --> 01:23:25,000\r\nShh.\r\n\r\n956\r\n01:23:25,960 --> 01:23:29,839\r\nOne napkin comin' up. Wish we had\r\nsome champagne to wrap it around.\r\n\r\n957\r\n01:23:29,960 --> 01:23:32,997\r\n- What did I tell you?\r\n- Mrs Dreyfuss, you don't have to wait.\r\n\r\n958\r\n01:23:33,120 --> 01:23:36,908\r\n- I'll wash the dishes.\r\n- You'd break 'em. I'll come back for them.\r\n\r\n959\r\n01:23:37,040 --> 01:23:39,429\r\nIf he makes trouble, give me a yell.\r\n\r\n960\r\n01:23:40,720 --> 01:23:44,395\r\n- She doesn't seem to like you very much.\r\n- Oh, I don't mind.\r\n\r\n961\r\n01:23:44,520 --> 01:23:46,988\r\nAs a matter of fact, I'm sort of flattered.\r\n\r\n962\r\n01:23:47,120 --> 01:23:52,069\r\nThat anybody'd think a girl like you would\r\ndo a thing like this over a guy like me.\r\n\r\n963\r\n01:23:53,240 --> 01:23:56,198\r\nDid you find something here?\r\nAn envelope?\r\n\r\n964\r\n01:23:56,320 --> 01:23:57,833\r\nYes. I've got it.\r\n\r\n965\r\n01:23:57,960 --> 01:24:02,158\r\nDon't you think we'd better destroy it\r\nso it won't fall in the wrong hands?\r\n\r\n966\r\n01:24:02,280 --> 01:24:03,880\r\nOpen it.\r\n\r\n967\r\n01:24:07,760 --> 01:24:10,228\r\nThere's nothing here but a $100 bill.\r\n\r\n968\r\n01:24:10,360 --> 01:24:13,591\r\nThat's right. Will you see\r\nthat Mr Sheldrake gets it?\r\n\r\n969\r\n01:24:14,720 --> 01:24:15,720\r\nSure.\r\n\r\n970\r\n01:24:18,120 --> 01:24:20,076\r\nTake this away, will you?\r\n\r\n971\r\n01:24:20,760 --> 01:24:23,513\r\nWould you like me to move\r\nthe television set in here?\r\n\r\n972\r\n01:24:23,640 --> 01:24:26,279\r\n- You play gin rummy?\r\n- I'm not very good at it.\r\n\r\n973\r\n01:24:26,400 --> 01:24:30,234\r\n- I am. Let me get the cards.\r\n- You don't have to entertain me.\r\n\r\n974\r\n01:24:30,360 --> 01:24:33,955\r\nThere's nothing I'd like better.\r\nYou know. Togetherness.\r\n\r\n975\r\n01:24:34,080 --> 01:24:38,596\r\nGuess what I did last Christmas. Had\r\ndinner at the automat, went to the zoo...\r\n\r\n976\r\n01:24:38,720 --> 01:24:41,393\r\n...then came home and cleaned up\r\nafter Mr Eichelberger.\r\n\r\n977\r\n01:24:41,520 --> 01:24:43,795\r\nHe had a little eggnog party here.\r\n\r\n978\r\n01:24:43,920 --> 01:24:46,115\r\nSo I'm way ahead this year.\r\n\r\n979\r\n01:24:46,240 --> 01:24:48,879\r\nThree across. Spades double?\r\n\r\n980\r\n01:24:49,000 --> 01:24:50,956\r\nHigh deals.\r\n\r\n981\r\n01:24:51,600 --> 01:24:53,556\r\nSix? Eight.\r\n\r\n982\r\n01:25:01,240 --> 01:25:03,993\r\nI think I'm gonna give it all up.\r\n\r\n983\r\n01:25:05,200 --> 01:25:06,872\r\nGive what up?\r\n\r\n984\r\n01:25:09,800 --> 01:25:12,678\r\nWhy do people have to\r\nlove people, anyway?\r\n\r\n985\r\n01:25:14,040 --> 01:25:15,996\r\nI know what you mean.\r\n\r\n986\r\n01:25:19,120 --> 01:25:20,320\r\nQueen.\r\n\r\n987\r\n01:25:23,720 --> 01:25:26,075\r\n- I don't want it.\r\n- Pick a card.\r\n\r\n988\r\n01:25:30,720 --> 01:25:34,918\r\nWhat do you call it when somebody keeps\r\ngettin' smashed up in car accidents?\r\n\r\n989\r\n01:25:35,040 --> 01:25:38,191\r\n- Bad insurance risk?\r\n- That's me with men.\r\n\r\n990\r\n01:25:39,800 --> 01:25:44,396\r\nI was jinxed from the word go. First time\r\nI was ever kissed was in a cemetery.\r\n\r\n991\r\n01:25:44,520 --> 01:25:46,556\r\nA cemetery?\r\n\r\n992\r\n01:25:46,680 --> 01:25:49,319\r\nI was 15. We used to go there to smoke.\r\n\r\n993\r\n01:25:49,440 --> 01:25:53,399\r\nHis name was George and\r\nhe threw me over for a drum majorette.\r\n\r\n994\r\n01:25:54,800 --> 01:25:56,400\r\nUh, gin.\r\n\r\n995\r\n01:26:00,040 --> 01:26:05,114\r\nThat's 10, 20... 36.\r\nAnd 25 makes 61 and two boxes.\r\n\r\n996\r\n01:26:05,240 --> 01:26:07,231\r\nI have this talent for falling in love...\r\n\r\n997\r\n01:26:07,360 --> 01:26:10,670\r\n...with the wrong guy\r\nin the wrong place at the wrong time.\r\n\r\n998\r\n01:26:11,400 --> 01:26:13,470\r\nWell, how many guys were there?\r\n\r\n999\r\n01:26:14,640 --> 01:26:15,840\r\nThree.\r\n\r\n1000\r\n01:26:16,520 --> 01:26:20,308\r\nThe last one was the manager of a finance\r\ncompany back home in Pittsburgh.\r\n\r\n1001\r\n01:26:20,440 --> 01:26:22,396\r\nThey found a shortage in his accounts.\r\n\r\n1002\r\n01:26:22,520 --> 01:26:26,115\r\nHe asked me to wait for him.\r\nHe'll be out in 1965.\r\n\r\n1003\r\n01:26:27,600 --> 01:26:28,600\r\nCut.\r\n\r\n1004\r\n01:26:30,200 --> 01:26:35,069\r\nSo I came to New York and moved in with\r\nmy sister and her husband, a cab driver.\r\n\r\n1005\r\n01:26:35,200 --> 01:26:39,876\r\nThey sent me to secretarial school and\r\nthen I applied for a job at Consolidated.\r\n\r\n1006\r\n01:26:40,000 --> 01:26:42,116\r\nBut I flunked the typing test.\r\n\r\n1007\r\n01:26:42,240 --> 01:26:44,913\r\n- Too slow?\r\n- No. I can type up a storm.\r\n\r\n1008\r\n01:26:45,040 --> 01:26:46,996\r\nI just can't spell.\r\n\r\n1009\r\n01:26:48,000 --> 01:26:52,869\r\nSo they gave me a pair of white gloves\r\nand stuck me in an elevator.\r\n\r\n1010\r\n01:26:53,000 --> 01:26:55,355\r\nAnd that's how I met Jeff.\r\n\r\n1011\r\n01:26:56,520 --> 01:26:59,080\r\nOh God, I'm so fouled up.\r\n\r\n1012\r\n01:26:59,200 --> 01:27:01,509\r\nWhat am I gonna do now?\r\n\r\n1013\r\n01:27:03,640 --> 01:27:05,756\r\nBetter win a hand. You're on a blitz.\r\n\r\n1014\r\n01:27:07,320 --> 01:27:10,073\r\nWas he very upset when you told him?\r\n\r\n1015\r\n01:27:10,200 --> 01:27:12,156\r\nMr Sheldrake? Yeah, very.\r\n\r\n1016\r\n01:27:13,400 --> 01:27:16,949\r\nMaybe he does love me, only he doesn't\r\nhave the nerve to tell his wife.\r\n\r\n1017\r\n01:27:17,080 --> 01:27:18,479\r\nI'm sure that's it.\r\n\r\n1018\r\n01:27:18,600 --> 01:27:21,831\r\n- You really think so?\r\n- No doubt about it.\r\n\r\n1019\r\n01:27:23,200 --> 01:27:25,395\r\nWould you hand me that pad and pencil?\r\n\r\n1020\r\n01:27:25,520 --> 01:27:28,432\r\n- What for?\r\n- I'm gonna write to Mrs Sheldrake.\r\n\r\n1021\r\n01:27:28,560 --> 01:27:30,790\r\n- You what?\r\n- As one woman to another.\r\n\r\n1022\r\n01:27:30,920 --> 01:27:34,708\r\n- I'm sure she'll understand.\r\n- I don't think that's a very good idea.\r\n\r\n1023\r\n01:27:34,840 --> 01:27:38,116\r\n- Why not?\r\n- For one thing, you can't spell.\r\n\r\n1024\r\n01:27:38,240 --> 01:27:42,199\r\nSecondly, if you did something\r\nlike that, you'd hate yourself.\r\n\r\n1025\r\n01:27:43,320 --> 01:27:45,880\r\nI don't like myself very much anyway.\r\n\r\n1026\r\n01:27:47,760 --> 01:27:50,069\r\nPick up the cards. Let's go.\r\n\r\n1027\r\n01:27:50,200 --> 01:27:53,158\r\n- Do I have to?\r\n- You bet. I got a terrific hand.\r\n\r\n1028\r\n01:27:59,640 --> 01:28:02,393\r\n- You really wanna discard that?\r\n- Sure.\r\n\r\n1029\r\n01:28:02,520 --> 01:28:03,520\r\nGin.\r\n\r\n1030\r\n01:28:08,440 --> 01:28:13,195\r\n10, 20, 40, 52 and 25... 77.\r\n\r\n1031\r\n01:28:13,920 --> 01:28:17,230\r\nSpades are double... 154.\r\n\r\n1032\r\n01:28:22,200 --> 01:28:24,156\r\nBlitzed. Two games.\r\n\r\n1033\r\n01:29:50,640 --> 01:29:53,791\r\nAll right, all right, Mrs Dreyfuss.\r\n\r\n1034\r\n01:30:01,000 --> 01:30:02,752\r\n- Hi, Baxter.\r\n- What do <i>you</i> want?\r\n\r\n1035\r\n01:30:02,880 --> 01:30:04,836\r\nWhat do I want? Just a minute.\r\n\r\n1036\r\n01:30:04,960 --> 01:30:07,520\r\n- You can't come in!\r\n- What's the matter with you?\r\n\r\n1037\r\n01:30:07,640 --> 01:30:09,631\r\nI made a reservation for four o'clock.\r\n\r\n1038\r\n01:30:09,760 --> 01:30:11,990\r\nYou can't stay.\r\nTake your champagne and go.\r\n\r\n1039\r\n01:30:12,120 --> 01:30:15,510\r\nI don't wanna pull rank on you,\r\nbut I told the little lady it was all set.\r\n\r\n1040\r\n01:30:15,640 --> 01:30:19,189\r\nAre you gonna leave, Mr Kirkeby,\r\nor do I have to throw you out?\r\n\r\n1041\r\n01:30:20,120 --> 01:30:22,759\r\nBuddy-boy,\r\nwhy didn't you say so?\r\n\r\n1042\r\n01:30:22,880 --> 01:30:26,111\r\n- Got yourself a little playmate, huh?\r\n- Now will you get out?\r\n\r\n1043\r\n01:30:31,520 --> 01:30:34,751\r\nHey, come on! What are we waiting for?\r\nOpen up, will you?\r\n\r\n1044\r\n01:30:34,880 --> 01:30:36,480\r\nMildred!\r\n\r\n1045\r\n01:30:38,360 --> 01:30:42,638\r\n- What's holding things up?\r\n- Say, let's have a party, the four of us.\r\n\r\n1046\r\n01:30:42,760 --> 01:30:43,760\r\nNo!\r\n\r\n1047\r\n01:30:48,760 --> 01:30:50,990\r\nWell, I don't blame you.\r\n\r\n1048\r\n01:30:51,120 --> 01:30:53,998\r\nSo you hit the jackpot, eh, kid?\r\nI mean Kubelikwise.\r\n\r\n1049\r\n01:30:54,120 --> 01:30:56,475\r\nDon't worry.\r\nI won't say a word to anybody.\r\n\r\n1050\r\n01:30:56,840 --> 01:30:58,796\r\nStay with it, Buddy-boy.\r\n\r\n1051\r\n01:31:13,280 --> 01:31:15,236\r\nWho was that?\r\n\r\n1052\r\n01:31:15,920 --> 01:31:19,276\r\nJust somebody delivering\r\na bottle of champagne. Like some?\r\n\r\n1053\r\n01:31:20,120 --> 01:31:22,680\r\nWould you mind opening that window?\r\n\r\n1054\r\n01:31:25,360 --> 01:31:30,480\r\n- Now don't get any ideas, Miss Kubelik.\r\n- I just want some fresh air.\r\n\r\n1055\r\n01:31:30,600 --> 01:31:33,831\r\nIt's only one storey down.\r\nThe best you could do is break a leg.\r\n\r\n1056\r\n01:31:33,960 --> 01:31:36,554\r\nSo they'll shoot me, like a horse.\r\n\r\n1057\r\n01:31:36,880 --> 01:31:40,111\r\nPlease, you gotta promise me\r\nyou won't do anything foolish.\r\n\r\n1058\r\n01:31:40,240 --> 01:31:42,595\r\n- Who'd care?\r\n- I would.\r\n\r\n1059\r\n01:31:48,120 --> 01:31:51,874\r\nWhy can't I ever fall in love\r\nwith somebody nice like you?\r\n\r\n1060\r\n01:31:52,760 --> 01:31:54,716\r\nYeah. Well...\r\n\r\n1061\r\n01:31:55,360 --> 01:31:58,193\r\nThat's the way it crumbles, cookiewise.\r\n\r\n1062\r\n01:31:59,520 --> 01:32:01,875\r\nGo to sleep.\r\n\r\n1063\r\n01:32:34,640 --> 01:32:39,191\r\n- Good morning, Mr Sheldrake.\r\n- Miss Olsen, come into my office, please.\r\n\r\n1064\r\n01:32:48,240 --> 01:32:52,028\r\n- Did you have a nice Christmas?\r\n- Lovely. You were a great help\r\n\r\n1065\r\n01:32:52,160 --> 01:32:54,720\r\nYour pep talk to Miss Kubelik\r\nat the office party.\r\n\r\n1066\r\n01:32:54,840 --> 01:32:59,277\r\n- Sorry, Jeff. I never could hold my liquor.\r\n- I thought you could hold your tongue.\r\n\r\n1067\r\n01:32:59,400 --> 01:33:01,834\r\n- It won't happen again.\r\n- You bet it won't.\r\n\r\n1068\r\n01:33:01,960 --> 01:33:04,793\r\nI'll arrange for you to get\r\na month's severance pay.\r\n\r\n1069\r\n01:33:04,920 --> 01:33:07,798\r\nThat's right, Miss Olsen.\r\nI'm letting you go.\r\n\r\n1070\r\n01:33:08,520 --> 01:33:10,988\r\nYou let me go four years ago, Jeff.\r\n\r\n1071\r\n01:33:11,120 --> 01:33:15,352\r\nAnd were cruel enough to make me sit out\r\nthere and watch the new models pass by.\r\n\r\n1072\r\n01:33:15,480 --> 01:33:18,517\r\nI'd appreciate it if you'd be\r\nout of here as soon as you can.\r\n\r\n1073\r\n01:33:18,640 --> 01:33:20,596\r\nYes, Mr Sheldrake.\r\n\r\n1074\r\n01:33:29,040 --> 01:33:33,079\r\nOperator, this is Mr Sheldrake. I'd like\r\nMr Baxter's home telephone number.\r\n\r\n1075\r\n01:33:33,200 --> 01:33:35,953\r\nHe's in Ordinary Premium Accounting.\r\n\r\n1076\r\n01:33:50,720 --> 01:33:54,156\r\n<i>- Hello?</i>\r\n<i>- Hello. Jeff Sheldrake. Can you talk?</i>\r\n\r\n1077\r\n01:33:54,880 --> 01:33:56,632\r\nYes. She's in the shower.\r\n\r\n1078\r\n01:33:56,760 --> 01:33:59,354\r\n- She's coming along fine, considering.\r\n- Good.\r\n\r\n1079\r\n01:33:59,480 --> 01:34:02,995\r\n- Is there anything you need? Money?\r\n- No, thank you, Mr Sheldrake.\r\n\r\n1080\r\n01:34:03,120 --> 01:34:06,157\r\nAs a matter of fact, I have\r\nsome money for you. $100.\r\n\r\n1081\r\n01:34:06,280 --> 01:34:07,280\r\nOh.\r\n\r\n1082\r\n01:34:07,760 --> 01:34:11,435\r\n- If there's anything I can do for you...\r\n- For me? I don't think so.\r\n\r\n1083\r\n01:34:11,560 --> 01:34:14,199\r\nBut I was hoping maybe\r\nyou could do something for <i>her.</i>\r\n\r\n1084\r\n01:34:14,480 --> 01:34:17,711\r\nLike what? Put yourself\r\nin my place, Baxter.\r\n\r\n1085\r\n01:34:17,840 --> 01:34:19,956\r\nHow can I help her? My hands are tied.\r\n\r\n1086\r\n01:34:21,200 --> 01:34:23,555\r\nWell... at least you can talk to her.\r\n\r\n1087\r\n01:34:24,640 --> 01:34:28,076\r\nLet me put her on. And please, be gentle.\r\n\r\n1088\r\n01:34:28,760 --> 01:34:31,149\r\nThere's a call for you!\r\n\r\n1089\r\n01:34:31,280 --> 01:34:33,635\r\n- For me?\r\n- Yeah. Mr Sheldrake.\r\n\r\n1090\r\n01:34:35,520 --> 01:34:37,476\r\nI don't wanna talk to him.\r\n\r\n1091\r\n01:34:37,600 --> 01:34:39,477\r\nI think you should.\r\n\r\n1092\r\n01:34:39,600 --> 01:34:44,720\r\nI gotta run down to the grocery anyway.\r\nThere's nothing left here but frozen pizza.\r\n\r\n1093\r\n01:34:45,520 --> 01:34:47,476\r\nI'll be right back. OK?\r\n\r\n1094\r\n01:35:07,120 --> 01:35:09,076\r\nHello, Jeff.\r\n\r\n1095\r\n01:35:10,480 --> 01:35:13,517\r\n- Yes, I'm all right.\r\n- Why did you do it, Fran?\r\n\r\n1096\r\n01:35:13,640 --> 01:35:16,029\r\nIt's so childish,\r\nand it never solves anything.\r\n\r\n1097\r\n01:35:16,160 --> 01:35:18,720\r\nI oughta be very angry with you,\r\nscaring me that way.\r\n\r\n1098\r\n01:35:18,840 --> 01:35:23,436\r\nBut let's forget the whole thing, pretend\r\nit never happened. What do you say?\r\n\r\n1099\r\n01:35:23,560 --> 01:35:24,560\r\nFran?\r\n\r\n1100\r\n01:35:25,960 --> 01:35:28,394\r\n<i>Are you there, Fran?</i>\r\n\r\n1101\r\n01:35:29,840 --> 01:35:34,152\r\nOf course I'm not here, because\r\nthe whole thing never happened.\r\n\r\n1102\r\n01:35:34,280 --> 01:35:37,989\r\nI never took those pills,\r\nI never loved you...\r\n\r\n1103\r\n01:35:38,120 --> 01:35:40,270\r\n...we never even met.\r\n\r\n1104\r\n01:35:41,400 --> 01:35:45,279\r\n- Isn't that the way you want it, Jeff?\r\n- You know I didn't mean it that way.\r\n\r\n1105\r\n01:35:45,400 --> 01:35:48,119\r\nYou just get well.\r\nDo what the nurse says. I mean Baxter.\r\n\r\n1106\r\n01:35:48,240 --> 01:35:51,198\r\nI'll see you as soon as I can.\r\nGoodbye, Fran.\r\n\r\n1107\r\n01:36:08,800 --> 01:36:11,268\r\nHello, Mrs Sheldrake. This is Miss Olsen.\r\n\r\n1108\r\n01:36:11,400 --> 01:36:15,393\r\nFine, thank you. I was wondering\r\nif we could have lunch together.\r\n\r\n1109\r\n01:36:16,240 --> 01:36:19,789\r\nI don't know how important it is,\r\nbut you might find it educational.\r\n\r\n1110\r\n01:36:19,920 --> 01:36:22,514\r\nIt concerns your husband.\r\n\r\n1111\r\n01:36:22,640 --> 01:36:26,189\r\nAll right. One o'clock,\r\nLongchamps, Madison and 59th.\r\n\r\n1112\r\n01:36:32,240 --> 01:36:34,390\r\nDon't worry. I'm on my way.\r\n\r\n1113\r\n01:36:34,520 --> 01:36:36,476\r\nJust making a personal call.\r\n\r\n1114\r\n01:36:38,120 --> 01:36:40,076\r\nHere's a dime.\r\n\r\n1115\r\n01:36:42,760 --> 01:36:44,239\r\nGoing down.\r\n\r\n1116\r\n01:36:56,120 --> 01:36:58,634\r\nOh, Mr Baxter! I'm glad you're here.\r\n\r\n1117\r\n01:36:58,760 --> 01:37:01,274\r\n- I was just going to get the passkey.\r\n- What for?\r\n\r\n1118\r\n01:37:01,400 --> 01:37:04,119\r\nI thought I smelled gas\r\ncoming from your apartment.\r\n\r\n1119\r\n01:37:04,240 --> 01:37:05,240\r\nGas?!\r\n\r\n1120\r\n01:37:14,920 --> 01:37:16,876\r\nMiss Kubelik?\r\n\r\n1121\r\n01:37:18,680 --> 01:37:20,636\r\nMiss Kubelik!\r\n\r\n1122\r\n01:37:23,240 --> 01:37:25,196\r\n- You all right?\r\n- Sure!\r\n\r\n1123\r\n01:37:26,080 --> 01:37:29,117\r\n- What's that funny smell?\r\n- Gas! Didn't you turn it on?\r\n\r\n1124\r\n01:37:29,240 --> 01:37:32,118\r\nYes, to boil water to get\r\nthe coffee stains out of my dress.\r\n\r\n1125\r\n01:37:32,240 --> 01:37:35,516\r\n- You turned it on but you didn't light it.\r\n- Are you supposed to?\r\n\r\n1126\r\n01:37:35,640 --> 01:37:39,315\r\nIn this house you're supposed to.\r\nHey, what are you doing with that?\r\n\r\n1127\r\n01:37:39,440 --> 01:37:42,750\r\nI was washing my stockings,\r\nso I thought I'd wash your socks too.\r\n\r\n1128\r\n01:37:42,880 --> 01:37:46,873\r\n- Oh. Thank you.\r\n- Very curious. I could only find 3 1/2 pair.\r\n\r\n1129\r\n01:37:47,000 --> 01:37:49,389\r\nThings are a little disorganised\r\naround here.\r\n\r\n1130\r\n01:37:49,520 --> 01:37:53,229\r\nI'd say. What's a tennis racket\r\ndoing in the kitchen?\r\n\r\n1131\r\n01:37:53,360 --> 01:37:58,070\r\nTennis racket? Oh, I remember.\r\nI was cooking myself an Italian dinner.\r\n\r\n1132\r\n01:37:58,200 --> 01:38:00,839\r\nI used it to strain the spaghetti.\r\n\r\n1133\r\n01:38:00,960 --> 01:38:03,428\r\n- Why not?\r\n- In fact, I'm a pretty good cook.\r\n\r\n1134\r\n01:38:03,560 --> 01:38:06,233\r\n- Only I'm a lousy housekeeper.\r\n- Yes, you are.\r\n\r\n1135\r\n01:38:06,360 --> 01:38:10,592\r\nWhen I was straightening up the couch,\r\nI found six hairpins, a lipstick...\r\n\r\n1136\r\n01:38:10,720 --> 01:38:14,235\r\n...a pair of false eyelashes and\r\na swizzle stick from the Stork Club.\r\n\r\n1137\r\n01:38:14,360 --> 01:38:17,557\r\nIt's just that I'm the kind of guy\r\nwho can't say no.\r\n\r\n1138\r\n01:38:17,680 --> 01:38:21,593\r\n- I don't mean to girls. I mean...\r\n- To someone like Mr Sheldrake.\r\n\r\n1139\r\n01:38:21,720 --> 01:38:24,678\r\n- I guess so.\r\n- I know so.\r\n\r\n1140\r\n01:38:26,320 --> 01:38:28,675\r\n- He's a taker.\r\n- What?\r\n\r\n1141\r\n01:38:29,240 --> 01:38:31,390\r\nSome people take, some people get took.\r\n\r\n1142\r\n01:38:31,520 --> 01:38:35,399\r\nAnd they know they're gettin' took\r\nand there's nothin' they can do about it.\r\n\r\n1143\r\n01:38:35,520 --> 01:38:37,476\r\nI wouldn't say that.\r\n\r\n1144\r\n01:38:38,200 --> 01:38:40,156\r\nWhat would you like for dinner, huh?\r\n\r\n1145\r\n01:38:40,280 --> 01:38:43,352\r\nHey. Onion soup, and canned asparagus...\r\n\r\n1146\r\n01:38:43,480 --> 01:38:45,436\r\nI really should be getting home.\r\n\r\n1147\r\n01:38:45,560 --> 01:38:48,438\r\n- My family'll be flipping by now.\r\n- You can't leave yet.\r\n\r\n1148\r\n01:38:48,560 --> 01:38:52,758\r\nThe doctor said it takes 48 hours\r\nto get that stuff out of your system.\r\n\r\n1149\r\n01:38:53,800 --> 01:38:57,918\r\nHow long does it take to get someone\r\nyou're stuck on out of your system?\r\n\r\n1150\r\n01:38:58,040 --> 01:39:00,873\r\nIf only they'd invent\r\nsome kind of pump for that.\r\n\r\n1151\r\n01:39:01,000 --> 01:39:06,393\r\nI know how you feel, Miss Kubelik. You\r\nthink it's the end of the world. But it's not.\r\n\r\n1152\r\n01:39:06,520 --> 01:39:08,988\r\nI went through exactly\r\nthe same thing myself.\r\n\r\n1153\r\n01:39:09,120 --> 01:39:10,997\r\n- You did?\r\n- Well, not exactly the same.\r\n\r\n1154\r\n01:39:11,120 --> 01:39:12,792\r\nI tried to do it with a gun.\r\n\r\n1155\r\n01:39:12,920 --> 01:39:15,912\r\n- Over a girl?\r\n- Worse. It was the wife of my best friend.\r\n\r\n1156\r\n01:39:16,040 --> 01:39:20,875\r\nAnd I was mad about her. But I knew\r\nit was hopeless and I decided to end it all.\r\n\r\n1157\r\n01:39:21,000 --> 01:39:24,959\r\nI went to a pawnshop and I bought a.45\r\nautomatic and I drove up to Eden Park...\r\n\r\n1158\r\n01:39:25,080 --> 01:39:27,116\r\n- Do you know Cincinnati?\r\n- No, I don't.\r\n\r\n1159\r\n01:39:27,240 --> 01:39:29,800\r\nAnyway, I parked the car\r\nand I loaded that gun...\r\n\r\n1160\r\n01:39:29,920 --> 01:39:34,118\r\nYou read in the papers that people shoot\r\nthemselves. Believe me, it's not that easy.\r\n\r\n1161\r\n01:39:34,240 --> 01:39:37,710\r\nI mean, how do you do it?\r\nHere? Here? Here?\r\n\r\n1162\r\n01:39:39,040 --> 01:39:41,600\r\n- Know where I finally shot myself?\r\n- Where?\r\n\r\n1163\r\n01:39:41,720 --> 01:39:43,551\r\n- Here.\r\n- In the knee?!\r\n\r\n1164\r\n01:39:43,680 --> 01:39:46,114\r\nYeah! I was sittin' there, tryin' to decide.\r\n\r\n1165\r\n01:39:46,240 --> 01:39:48,515\r\nA cop came up because\r\nI was illegally parked.\r\n\r\n1166\r\n01:39:48,640 --> 01:39:51,871\r\nI tried to hide the gun\r\nunder the seat and it went off.\r\n\r\n1167\r\n01:39:52,000 --> 01:39:55,515\r\n- That's terrible!\r\n- It was a year till I could bend the knee.\r\n\r\n1168\r\n01:39:55,640 --> 01:39:58,632\r\nBut I got over the girl in three weeks.\r\n\r\n1169\r\n01:40:00,120 --> 01:40:03,749\r\nStill lives in Cincinnati.\r\nHas four kids and gained 20 pounds.\r\n\r\n1170\r\n01:40:03,880 --> 01:40:06,189\r\nSends me a fruitcake every Christmas.\r\n\r\n1171\r\n01:40:06,320 --> 01:40:08,675\r\nAre you just making this up\r\nto make me feel better?\r\n\r\n1172\r\n01:40:08,800 --> 01:40:10,756\r\nOf course not! Here's the fruitcake.\r\n\r\n1173\r\n01:40:10,880 --> 01:40:12,996\r\n- Do you wanna see my knee?\r\n- No, thank you.\r\n\r\n1174\r\n01:40:13,120 --> 01:40:16,271\r\nThe fellas in the office might\r\nget the wrong idea how I found out.\r\n\r\n1175\r\n01:40:16,400 --> 01:40:20,359\r\nLet 'em! Look, I'm gonna cook dinner\r\nfor us. We'll have fruitcake for dessert.\r\n\r\n1176\r\n01:40:20,480 --> 01:40:23,597\r\nYou just sit there and rest.\r\nYou've done enough for today.\r\n\r\n1177\r\n01:40:23,720 --> 01:40:25,920\r\nYes, Nurse.\r\n\r\n1178\r\n01:40:40,400 --> 01:40:43,517\r\n- Can I help you?\r\n- I'm lookin' for Miss Kubelik.\r\n\r\n1179\r\n01:40:43,640 --> 01:40:48,634\r\n- So am I. She didn't report this morning.\r\n- She didn't? Who's in charge here?\r\n\r\n1180\r\n01:40:48,760 --> 01:40:52,958\r\nThat comes under General Office\r\nAdministration. Mr Dobisch, 21st floor.\r\n\r\n1181\r\n01:40:53,080 --> 01:40:54,480\r\nThanks.\r\n\r\n1182\r\n01:40:57,160 --> 01:41:01,472\r\nSo I take Sylvia up to the apartment, and\r\nguess who he's stashed in the bedroom.\r\n\r\n1183\r\n01:41:01,600 --> 01:41:02,828\r\n- Who?\r\n- Kubelik.\r\n\r\n1184\r\n01:41:02,960 --> 01:41:05,952\r\nNo kiddin'? Buddy-boy and Kubelik\r\nhaving a little toot?\r\n\r\n1185\r\n01:41:06,080 --> 01:41:10,392\r\nToot? More like a lost weekend.\r\nNeither of 'em showed up for work today.\r\n\r\n1186\r\n01:41:10,520 --> 01:41:12,112\r\nAWOL, hm?\r\n\r\n1187\r\n01:41:12,240 --> 01:41:14,708\r\nWhat gripes me is\r\nthey guzzled my champagne...\r\n\r\n1188\r\n01:41:14,840 --> 01:41:18,230\r\n...while Sylvia and I wound up\r\nat the Guggenheim Museum.\r\n\r\n1189\r\n01:41:19,840 --> 01:41:21,796\r\n- Mr Dobisch?\r\n- Yeah.\r\n\r\n1190\r\n01:41:22,800 --> 01:41:26,839\r\nI'm Karl Matuschka. My sister-in-law\r\nruns one of the elevators. Fran Kubelik.\r\n\r\n1191\r\n01:41:26,960 --> 01:41:28,393\r\n- Miss Kubelik?\r\n- You know her?\r\n\r\n1192\r\n01:41:28,520 --> 01:41:32,229\r\nOf course. We have a lot of employees,\r\nbut we're one big, happy family.\r\n\r\n1193\r\n01:41:32,360 --> 01:41:37,275\r\nShe lives with us, and my wife's nervous\r\ncos Fran hasn't been home for two days.\r\n\r\n1194\r\n01:41:37,400 --> 01:41:38,719\r\nThat so?\r\n\r\n1195\r\n01:41:38,840 --> 01:41:41,798\r\nSo we wondered if somebody here\r\nknew what happened to her.\r\n\r\n1196\r\n01:41:41,920 --> 01:41:43,120\r\nI see.\r\n\r\n1197\r\n01:41:43,440 --> 01:41:46,910\r\nWhat do you think, Al?\r\nCan we help the man?\r\n\r\n1198\r\n01:41:47,040 --> 01:41:50,316\r\nWhy not? We don't owe\r\nBuddy-boy anything.\r\n\r\n1199\r\n01:41:50,440 --> 01:41:53,796\r\nYeah. What's Buddy-boy\r\ndone for us lately?\r\n\r\n1200\r\n01:41:55,880 --> 01:41:58,155\r\nWho is Buddy-boy?\r\n\r\n1201\r\n01:42:21,360 --> 01:42:25,069\r\n- Are we dressing for dinner?\r\n- No. Just come as you are.\r\n\r\n1202\r\n01:42:25,200 --> 01:42:29,159\r\n- You're pretty good with that racket.\r\n- You should see my backhand.\r\n\r\n1203\r\n01:42:31,120 --> 01:42:33,998\r\nWait till you see me serve the meatballs.\r\n\r\n1204\r\n01:42:34,120 --> 01:42:38,033\r\n- Shall I light the candles?\r\n- It's a must, gracious livingwise.\r\n\r\n1205\r\n01:42:41,120 --> 01:42:42,473\r\n<i>~ Meatball ~</i>\r\n\r\n1206\r\n01:42:46,080 --> 01:42:47,638\r\n<i>~ Meatball ~</i>\r\n\r\n1207\r\n01:42:56,320 --> 01:42:59,198\r\n- You bought some napkins.\r\n- Might as well go all the way.\r\n\r\n1208\r\n01:43:02,480 --> 01:43:04,789\r\nYou know, I used to live\r\nlike Robinson Crusoe.\r\n\r\n1209\r\n01:43:04,920 --> 01:43:07,070\r\nShipwrecked, among eight million people.\r\n\r\n1210\r\n01:43:07,200 --> 01:43:10,237\r\nAnd then one day I saw\r\na footprint in the sand...\r\n\r\n1211\r\n01:43:10,360 --> 01:43:12,316\r\n...and there you were.\r\n\r\n1212\r\n01:43:13,200 --> 01:43:15,350\r\nIt's a wonderful thing, dinner for two.\r\n\r\n1213\r\n01:43:15,480 --> 01:43:19,189\r\n- Do you usually eat alone?\r\n- No. Sometimes I eat with Ed Sullivan.\r\n\r\n1214\r\n01:43:19,320 --> 01:43:22,039\r\nOr sometimes Dinah Shore\r\nor Perry Como.\r\n\r\n1215\r\n01:43:22,160 --> 01:43:25,994\r\nThe other night it was Mae West.\r\nShe was much younger then. Cheers.\r\n\r\n1216\r\n01:43:26,120 --> 01:43:28,839\r\n- Cheers.\r\n- Know what we're gonna do after dinner?\r\n\r\n1217\r\n01:43:29,000 --> 01:43:30,991\r\n- The dishes.\r\n- I mean after that.\r\n\r\n1218\r\n01:43:31,120 --> 01:43:33,315\r\n- What?\r\n- You don't have to if you don't want to.\r\n\r\n1219\r\n01:43:33,440 --> 01:43:35,749\r\n- Oh, I don't?\r\n- We're gonna finish the gin game.\r\n\r\n1220\r\n01:43:35,880 --> 01:43:38,440\r\nSo keep a clear head.\r\n\r\n1221\r\n01:43:39,240 --> 01:43:43,119\r\nCos I don't wanna take advantage of you,\r\nthe way I did yesterday in bed.\r\n\r\n1222\r\n01:43:43,240 --> 01:43:45,276\r\n- Baxter?\r\n- Yes.\r\n\r\n1223\r\n01:43:54,040 --> 01:43:56,634\r\nWhat's with you, Fran?\r\nDid you forget where you live?\r\n\r\n1224\r\n01:43:56,760 --> 01:44:00,309\r\n- My brother-in-law, Karl Matuschka.\r\n- Oh! How do you do, Mr Matusch...\r\n\r\n1225\r\n01:44:00,440 --> 01:44:04,672\r\n- Get dressed. I got the cab downstairs.\r\n- Wait. I know what you're thinking, but...\r\n\r\n1226\r\n01:44:04,800 --> 01:44:07,473\r\nIt's none of my business\r\nwhat you do. You're over 21.\r\n\r\n1227\r\n01:44:07,600 --> 01:44:11,070\r\n- But your sister thinks you're a lady.\r\n- All we were gonna do was eat!\r\n\r\n1228\r\n01:44:11,200 --> 01:44:13,589\r\nIf there wasn't a lady present,\r\nI'd clobber you.\r\n\r\n1229\r\n01:44:13,720 --> 01:44:16,473\r\nAll right, Karl! I'll get dressed.\r\n\r\n1230\r\n01:44:25,320 --> 01:44:27,276\r\nWant a martini?\r\n\r\n1231\r\n01:44:31,120 --> 01:44:34,829\r\nHow about some spaghetti\r\nwith meat sauce that I cooked myself?\r\n\r\n1232\r\n01:44:40,120 --> 01:44:42,793\r\nYour sister-in-law sure is terrific.\r\n\r\n1233\r\n01:44:45,920 --> 01:44:50,277\r\nIt must be murder drivin' a cab\r\nin New York with the cross-town traffic.\r\n\r\n1234\r\n01:44:54,560 --> 01:44:56,516\r\nHi, Baxter. How's the patient?\r\n\r\n1235\r\n01:44:56,640 --> 01:44:58,551\r\nOh, uh... I'm fine, Doc.\r\n\r\n1236\r\n01:44:58,680 --> 01:45:00,636\r\nNot you. Miss Kubelik.\r\n\r\n1237\r\n01:45:01,360 --> 01:45:06,115\r\n- What's the matter with Miss Kubelik?\r\n- This is Mr Matuschka. He's... got a cab.\r\n\r\n1238\r\n01:45:06,240 --> 01:45:08,595\r\n- Fran been sick?\r\n- No. Just a little accident.\r\n\r\n1239\r\n01:45:08,720 --> 01:45:12,508\r\n- What does he mean, accident?\r\n- Well... these things happen all the time.\r\n\r\n1240\r\n01:45:12,640 --> 01:45:14,710\r\nWhat things? What kind\r\nof a doctor are you?\r\n\r\n1241\r\n01:45:14,840 --> 01:45:17,912\r\nNot that kind! He just gave her\r\na shot, pumped out her stomach.\r\n\r\n1242\r\n01:45:18,040 --> 01:45:21,112\r\n- What for?\r\n- I took sleeping pills. But I'm fine now.\r\n\r\n1243\r\n01:45:21,240 --> 01:45:23,708\r\n- Why'd you take sleeping pills?\r\n- On account of me.\r\n\r\n1244\r\n01:45:23,840 --> 01:45:24,840\r\nYou?\r\n\r\n1245\r\n01:45:25,920 --> 01:45:27,638\r\nWho else?\r\n\r\n1246\r\n01:45:32,320 --> 01:45:34,276\r\nLeave him alone!\r\n\r\n1247\r\n01:45:36,560 --> 01:45:39,711\r\nOh, you fool. You damn fool.\r\n\r\n1248\r\n01:45:41,760 --> 01:45:44,718\r\n- Come on, Fran.\r\n- Goodbye, Mr Baxter.\r\n\r\n1249\r\n01:45:50,440 --> 01:45:52,396\r\nGoodbye, Doctor.\r\n\r\n1250\r\n01:45:54,240 --> 01:45:58,791\r\nWell, I don't wanna gloat, but\r\njust between us, you had it coming to you.\r\n\r\n1251\r\n01:46:01,000 --> 01:46:03,798\r\nYou're gonna have a shiner tomorrow.\r\n\r\n1252\r\n01:46:03,920 --> 01:46:05,672\r\nLet me get my bag.\r\n\r\n1253\r\n01:46:07,720 --> 01:46:09,676\r\nDon't bother, Doc.\r\n\r\n1254\r\n01:46:09,800 --> 01:46:11,756\r\nIt doesn't hurt a bit.\r\n\r\n1255\r\n01:46:32,680 --> 01:46:34,910\r\nMr Sheldrake's office? This is CC Baxter.\r\n\r\n1256\r\n01:46:35,040 --> 01:46:38,157\r\nPlease tell him I'd like to\r\ncome up and see him. It's important.\r\n\r\n1257\r\n01:46:38,280 --> 01:46:40,236\r\nWill you call me back, please?\r\n\r\n1258\r\n01:46:42,920 --> 01:46:45,832\r\nMr Sheldrake, I've got good news for you.\r\n\r\n1259\r\n01:46:47,000 --> 01:46:48,956\r\nAll your troubles are over.\r\n\r\n1260\r\n01:46:50,120 --> 01:46:52,839\r\nI'm gonna take Miss Kubelik\r\noff your hands.\r\n\r\n1261\r\n01:46:53,640 --> 01:46:55,995\r\nThe plain fact is, I love her.\r\n\r\n1262\r\n01:46:56,880 --> 01:46:59,348\r\nI thought you should be the first to know.\r\n\r\n1263\r\n01:46:59,480 --> 01:47:02,278\r\nAfter all, you don't really\r\nwant her, and I do.\r\n\r\n1264\r\n01:47:02,400 --> 01:47:06,359\r\nAnd though it may sound presumptuous,\r\nshe needs somebody like me.\r\n\r\n1265\r\n01:47:06,480 --> 01:47:09,790\r\nSo I think it would be best all around.\r\n\r\n1266\r\n01:47:09,920 --> 01:47:11,319\r\nSolutionwise.\r\n\r\n1267\r\n01:47:11,440 --> 01:47:12,440\r\nYes?\r\n\r\n1268\r\n01:47:12,800 --> 01:47:14,870\r\nI'll be right up.\r\n\r\n1269\r\n01:47:15,000 --> 01:47:18,231\r\nMr Sheldrake, I've got good news for you.\r\n\r\n1270\r\n01:47:18,360 --> 01:47:20,316\r\nAll your troubles are over.\r\n\r\n1271\r\n01:47:24,440 --> 01:47:25,440\r\n19.\r\n\r\n1272\r\n01:47:26,720 --> 01:47:30,269\r\n- Hi, Buddy-boy. What happened to you?\r\n- Hit by a swinging door?\r\n\r\n1273\r\n01:47:30,400 --> 01:47:33,198\r\n- Or a yellow cab?\r\n- That guy really must've belted him.\r\n\r\n1274\r\n01:47:33,320 --> 01:47:36,392\r\nYeah. He's punchy. Talking to himself.\r\n\r\n1275\r\n01:47:36,640 --> 01:47:37,640\r\n27.\r\n\r\n1276\r\n01:47:38,080 --> 01:47:40,435\r\nThose two days\r\nshe spent in the apartment...\r\n\r\n1277\r\n01:47:40,560 --> 01:47:43,438\r\n...made me realise\r\nhow lonely I'd been before.\r\n\r\n1278\r\n01:47:43,560 --> 01:47:46,950\r\nBut, thanks to you, I'm\r\nin a financial position to marry her.\r\n\r\n1279\r\n01:47:47,080 --> 01:47:49,992\r\nIf I can ever square things with her family.\r\n\r\n1280\r\n01:47:50,120 --> 01:47:52,429\r\nGood morning. CC Baxter.\r\n\r\n1281\r\n01:47:56,240 --> 01:47:58,196\r\n- <i>Mr Baxter is here.</i>\r\n- Send him in.\r\n\r\n1282\r\n01:48:00,360 --> 01:48:03,158\r\nMr Sheldrake, I've got good news for you.\r\n\r\n1283\r\n01:48:03,280 --> 01:48:05,316\r\nAnd I've got good news for <i>you,</i> Baxter.\r\n\r\n1284\r\n01:48:05,440 --> 01:48:07,635\r\n- All your troubles are over.\r\n- Sir?\r\n\r\n1285\r\n01:48:07,960 --> 01:48:11,032\r\nI know how worried you were\r\nabout Miss Kubelik. Stop worrying.\r\n\r\n1286\r\n01:48:11,160 --> 01:48:13,913\r\nI'm going to take her off your hands.\r\n\r\n1287\r\n01:48:14,040 --> 01:48:16,838\r\n- You're gonna take her off <i>my</i> hands?\r\n- That's right.\r\n\r\n1288\r\n01:48:16,960 --> 01:48:19,315\r\nI've moved out of the house.\r\n\r\n1289\r\n01:48:20,240 --> 01:48:23,118\r\nI'm gonna be staying in town,\r\nat the Athletic Club.\r\n\r\n1290\r\n01:48:23,240 --> 01:48:26,118\r\n- You left your wife.\r\n- If you must know, I fired my secretary.\r\n\r\n1291\r\n01:48:26,240 --> 01:48:30,870\r\nMy secretary got to my wife, and my wife\r\nfired me. Ain't that a kick in the head?\r\n\r\n1292\r\n01:48:31,000 --> 01:48:32,000\r\nYeah.\r\n\r\n1293\r\n01:48:32,600 --> 01:48:34,431\r\nNow what's your news, Baxter?\r\n\r\n1294\r\n01:48:36,520 --> 01:48:40,115\r\nIt's about Miss Kubelik. She's feeling\r\nall right again so she went home.\r\n\r\n1295\r\n01:48:40,240 --> 01:48:43,198\r\nSwell. And don't think\r\nI've forgotten what you did for me.\r\n\r\n1296\r\n01:48:43,320 --> 01:48:45,276\r\nThis way, Baxter.\r\n\r\n1297\r\n01:48:48,560 --> 01:48:50,835\r\nSit down. Try it on for size.\r\n\r\n1298\r\n01:48:51,840 --> 01:48:54,274\r\n- You like? It's all yours.\r\n- Mine?\r\n\r\n1299\r\n01:48:54,400 --> 01:48:59,394\r\nMy assistant has been shifted to the\r\nDenver office and you're taking his place.\r\n\r\n1300\r\n01:48:59,520 --> 01:49:01,875\r\nWhat's the matter?\r\nYou don't seem very excited.\r\n\r\n1301\r\n01:49:02,000 --> 01:49:06,073\r\nWell, it's just that so many things\r\nhave been happening so fast.\r\n\r\n1302\r\n01:49:06,200 --> 01:49:08,873\r\nI'm very pleased.\r\nEspecially for Miss Kubelik.\r\n\r\n1303\r\n01:49:09,000 --> 01:49:13,790\r\nI think she's the kind of girl that definitely\r\nought to be married to... someone.\r\n\r\n1304\r\n01:49:13,920 --> 01:49:19,199\r\nSure, sure. But first the property has to be\r\nsettled. Then it takes six weeks in Reno.\r\n\r\n1305\r\n01:49:19,320 --> 01:49:22,118\r\nMeanwhile I'm going to enjoy\r\nbeing a bachelor for a while.\r\n\r\n1306\r\n01:49:22,240 --> 01:49:25,550\r\nOh, Baxter, you now can have lunch\r\nin the executive dining room.\r\n\r\n1307\r\n01:49:25,680 --> 01:49:28,240\r\nThat's one of the privileges\r\nthat goes with this job.\r\n\r\n1308\r\n01:49:28,360 --> 01:49:32,797\r\nYou also get a nice little expense account,\r\nuse of the executive washroom...\r\n\r\n1309\r\n01:49:32,920 --> 01:49:35,229\r\nSay, what happened to you, Baxter?\r\n\r\n1310\r\n01:49:35,360 --> 01:49:37,954\r\n- I got kicked in the head too.\r\n- Oh?\r\n\r\n1311\r\n01:49:58,200 --> 01:50:00,236\r\nGood evening, Mr Baxter.\r\n\r\n1312\r\n01:50:00,360 --> 01:50:01,360\r\nOh.\r\n\r\n1313\r\n01:50:01,920 --> 01:50:04,593\r\nMiss Kubelik. How are you feeling?\r\n\r\n1314\r\n01:50:04,720 --> 01:50:07,314\r\n- I feel fine. How's your eye?\r\n- Oh, fine.\r\n\r\n1315\r\n01:50:07,440 --> 01:50:10,159\r\n- How are things at the apartment?\r\n- Nothing's changed.\r\n\r\n1316\r\n01:50:10,280 --> 01:50:13,113\r\n- We never did finish that gin game.\r\n- I know.\r\n\r\n1317\r\n01:50:14,760 --> 01:50:17,035\r\nI suppose you heard about Mr Sheldrake.\r\n\r\n1318\r\n01:50:17,160 --> 01:50:19,628\r\nLeaving his wife? Yeah.\r\nI'm very happy for you.\r\n\r\n1319\r\n01:50:19,760 --> 01:50:22,228\r\n- I never thought he'd do it.\r\n- I told you all along.\r\n\r\n1320\r\n01:50:22,360 --> 01:50:25,750\r\n- You were wrong about Mr Sheldrake.\r\n- I guess so.\r\n\r\n1321\r\n01:50:25,880 --> 01:50:27,836\r\nYou were wrong about me too.\r\n\r\n1322\r\n01:50:27,960 --> 01:50:30,997\r\nWhat you said about those who take\r\nand those who get took.\r\n\r\n1323\r\n01:50:31,120 --> 01:50:34,192\r\nMr Sheldrake wasn't using me.\r\nI was using <i>him.</i> See?\r\n\r\n1324\r\n01:50:34,320 --> 01:50:38,632\r\nLast month I was at desk 861 on\r\nthe 19th floor. Now I'm on the 27th floor.\r\n\r\n1325\r\n01:50:38,760 --> 01:50:40,716\r\nA panelled office, three windows.\r\n\r\n1326\r\n01:50:40,840 --> 01:50:43,752\r\nSo it all worked out fine.\r\nWe're both getting what we wanted.\r\n\r\n1327\r\n01:50:43,880 --> 01:50:46,678\r\nYes. Will you walk me to the subway?\r\n\r\n1328\r\n01:50:46,800 --> 01:50:52,238\r\nNo, thank you. Well, I... To tell you the\r\ntruth, I have this heavy date for tonight.\r\n\r\n1329\r\n01:50:55,600 --> 01:50:58,831\r\n- Aren't you meeting Mr Sheldrake?\r\n- No. You know how people talk.\r\n\r\n1330\r\n01:50:58,960 --> 01:51:04,034\r\nI decided it was best not to see each other\r\nuntil everything was settled, divorcewise.\r\n\r\n1331\r\n01:51:04,160 --> 01:51:06,116\r\nThat's very wise.\r\n\r\n1332\r\n01:51:07,200 --> 01:51:09,555\r\n- Good night, Mr Baxter.\r\n- Good night.\r\n\r\n1333\r\n01:51:44,120 --> 01:51:47,351\r\n- Baxter, could you step in here a minute?\r\n- <i>Yes, Mr Sheldrake.</i>\r\n\r\n1334\r\n01:51:47,480 --> 01:51:49,436\r\n- There you are.\r\n- Much obliged.\r\n\r\n1335\r\n01:51:51,240 --> 01:51:56,837\r\nHere are the figures on staff turnover. 37%\r\nof females leave to get married and 22%...\r\n\r\n1336\r\n01:51:56,960 --> 01:51:59,793\r\nBaxter, you work too hard.\r\nIt's New Year's Eve. Relax!\r\n\r\n1337\r\n01:51:59,920 --> 01:52:02,798\r\n- Yes, sir.\r\n- I suppose you'll be celebrating tonight.\r\n\r\n1338\r\n01:52:02,920 --> 01:52:04,956\r\n- Naturally.\r\n- I'm taking Miss Kubelik out.\r\n\r\n1339\r\n01:52:05,120 --> 01:52:07,111\r\n- I finally talked her into it.\r\n- I see.\r\n\r\n1340\r\n01:52:07,240 --> 01:52:11,438\r\nThe only thing is, I'm staying at the\r\nAthletic Club and it's strictly stag, so...\r\n\r\n1341\r\n01:52:11,560 --> 01:52:13,596\r\nIf you don't mind?\r\n\r\n1342\r\n01:52:14,360 --> 01:52:17,750\r\n- Don't mind what?\r\n- You know my key to your apartment?\r\n\r\n1343\r\n01:52:17,880 --> 01:52:20,997\r\nWhen we had that little scare\r\nabout Miss Kubelik...\r\n\r\n1344\r\n01:52:21,120 --> 01:52:24,954\r\n...I threw it out the window of the train.\r\n- Very clever.\r\n\r\n1345\r\n01:52:25,080 --> 01:52:27,275\r\nSo now I'll have to borrow your key.\r\n\r\n1346\r\n01:52:28,720 --> 01:52:31,439\r\n- Sorry, Mr Sheldrake.\r\n- What do you mean, sorry?\r\n\r\n1347\r\n01:52:31,560 --> 01:52:33,869\r\nYou're not bringing anybody\r\nto my apartment.\r\n\r\n1348\r\n01:52:34,000 --> 01:52:38,198\r\n- It's not just anybody. It's Miss Kubelik.\r\n- Especially not Miss Kubelik.\r\n\r\n1349\r\n01:52:38,320 --> 01:52:41,392\r\n- How's that again?\r\n- No key.\r\n\r\n1350\r\n01:52:43,200 --> 01:52:47,637\r\nBaxter, I picked you for my team because\r\nI thought you were a bright young man.\r\n\r\n1351\r\n01:52:47,760 --> 01:52:51,070\r\nDo you realise what you're doing?\r\nNot to me, but to yourself?\r\n\r\n1352\r\n01:52:51,200 --> 01:52:54,431\r\nNormally it takes years\r\nto work your way up to the 27th floor.\r\n\r\n1353\r\n01:52:54,560 --> 01:52:57,472\r\nBut it only takes 30 seconds\r\nto be out on the street again.\r\n\r\n1354\r\n01:52:57,600 --> 01:53:00,068\r\n- You dig?\r\n- I dig.\r\n\r\n1355\r\n01:53:01,200 --> 01:53:03,156\r\nSo what's it going to be?\r\n\r\n1356\r\n01:53:09,680 --> 01:53:12,638\r\n- Now you're being bright.\r\n- Thank you, sir.\r\n\r\n1357\r\n01:53:29,360 --> 01:53:31,954\r\n- Baxter, you gave me the wrong key.\r\n- No, I didn't.\r\n\r\n1358\r\n01:53:32,080 --> 01:53:34,640\r\nBut this is the key\r\nto the executive washroom.\r\n\r\n1359\r\n01:53:34,760 --> 01:53:38,389\r\nThat's right. I won't be needing it\r\nbecause I'm all washed up around here.\r\n\r\n1360\r\n01:53:38,520 --> 01:53:41,796\r\n- What's gotten into you?\r\n- Just following doctor's orders.\r\n\r\n1361\r\n01:53:41,920 --> 01:53:45,993\r\nI've decided to become a <i>mensch.</i>\r\nKnow what that means? A human being.\r\n\r\n1362\r\n01:53:46,120 --> 01:53:49,908\r\n- Now hold on, Baxter.\r\n- The old payola won't work any more.\r\n\r\n1363\r\n01:53:50,040 --> 01:53:51,996\r\nGoodbye, Mr Sheldrake.\r\n\r\n1364\r\n01:54:26,160 --> 01:54:29,948\r\n- We're having a party and ran out of ice.\r\n- Sure, Doc.\r\n\r\n1365\r\n01:54:30,080 --> 01:54:32,116\r\nHow come you're alone\r\non New Year's Eve?\r\n\r\n1366\r\n01:54:32,240 --> 01:54:34,117\r\nWell, I got things to do.\r\n\r\n1367\r\n01:54:34,240 --> 01:54:38,279\r\n- What's this? You're packing?\r\n- Yeah. I'm giving up the apartment.\r\n\r\n1368\r\n01:54:38,400 --> 01:54:40,197\r\nWhere are you moving to?\r\n\r\n1369\r\n01:54:40,320 --> 01:54:43,232\r\nI don't know. All I know is\r\nI gotta get outta this place.\r\n\r\n1370\r\n01:54:43,360 --> 01:54:45,316\r\nSorry to lose you, Baxter.\r\n\r\n1371\r\n01:54:45,440 --> 01:54:49,991\r\nMe? Oh, my body. Don't worry, it'll go to\r\nthe university, Doc. I'll put it in writing.\r\n\r\n1372\r\n01:54:50,120 --> 01:54:53,192\r\n- Could you use some champagne?\r\n- Booze we don't need.\r\n\r\n1373\r\n01:54:53,320 --> 01:54:55,072\r\nSay, why don't you join us?\r\n\r\n1374\r\n01:54:55,200 --> 01:54:59,990\r\nWe got two brain surgeons, a proctologist\r\nand three nurses from Bellevue.\r\n\r\n1375\r\n01:55:00,120 --> 01:55:01,997\r\nNo, thanks. I don't feel like it.\r\n\r\n1376\r\n01:55:02,120 --> 01:55:06,193\r\nIn case I don't see you again, how much\r\ndo I owe you for taking care of that girl?\r\n\r\n1377\r\n01:55:06,320 --> 01:55:10,029\r\nForget it. I didn't do it as a doctor.\r\nI did it as a neighbour.\r\n\r\n1378\r\n01:55:10,160 --> 01:55:12,720\r\nBy the way, whatever happened to her?\r\n\r\n1379\r\n01:55:13,960 --> 01:55:16,838\r\nYou know me with girls.\r\nEasy come, easy go.\r\n\r\n1380\r\n01:55:16,960 --> 01:55:19,520\r\n- Goodbye, Doc.\r\n- Happy New Year.\r\n\r\n1381\r\n01:56:01,080 --> 01:56:03,435\r\nSorry I took so long\r\non the phone. We're all set.\r\n\r\n1382\r\n01:56:03,560 --> 01:56:05,869\r\n- For what?\r\n- I rented a car. It'll be here at one.\r\n\r\n1383\r\n01:56:06,000 --> 01:56:08,753\r\n- We're driving to Atlantic City.\r\n- Atlantic City?\r\n\r\n1384\r\n01:56:08,880 --> 01:56:13,237\r\nI know it's a drag, but you can't find\r\na hotel room in town on New Year's Eve.\r\n\r\n1385\r\n01:56:14,240 --> 01:56:16,993\r\nRing out the old year, ring in the new.\r\n\r\n1386\r\n01:56:17,120 --> 01:56:19,236\r\nRing-a-ding-ding.\r\n\r\n1387\r\n01:56:19,720 --> 01:56:22,951\r\nI didn't plan it this way. It's Baxter's fault.\r\n\r\n1388\r\n01:56:23,080 --> 01:56:24,070\r\nBaxter?\r\n\r\n1389\r\n01:56:24,170 --> 01:56:27,550\r\nHe wouldn't give me\r\nthe key to the apartment.\r\n\r\n1390\r\n01:56:27,680 --> 01:56:30,148\r\n- He wouldn't?\r\n- No. He just walked out on me. Quit.\r\n\r\n1391\r\n01:56:30,280 --> 01:56:33,192\r\nThrew that big, fat job right in my face.\r\n\r\n1392\r\n01:56:34,560 --> 01:56:38,473\r\n- The nerve.\r\n- The little punk. After all I did for him.\r\n\r\n1393\r\n01:56:38,600 --> 01:56:42,798\r\nSaid I couldn't bring anybody to the\r\napartment, especially not Miss Kubelik.\r\n\r\n1394\r\n01:56:42,920 --> 01:56:45,593\r\nWhat's he got against you, anyway?\r\n\r\n1395\r\n01:56:45,720 --> 01:56:51,352\r\nI don't know. I guess that's the way\r\nit crumbles, cookiewise.\r\n\r\n1396\r\n01:56:53,320 --> 01:56:55,675\r\nWhat are you talking about?\r\n\r\n1397\r\n01:56:56,640 --> 01:56:59,916\r\nI'd spell it out for you, only I can't spell.\r\n\r\n1398\r\n01:57:04,720 --> 01:57:09,589\r\n<i>~ Should auld acquaintance be forgot ~</i>\r\n\r\n1399\r\n01:57:09,720 --> 01:57:14,430\r\n<i>~ And never brought to mind... ~</i>\r\n\r\n1400\r\n01:57:15,720 --> 01:57:17,676\r\nHappy New Year, Fran.\r\n\r\n1401\r\n01:57:19,680 --> 01:57:23,878\r\n<i>~ And days of auld lang syne ~</i>\r\n\r\n1402\r\n01:57:24,720 --> 01:57:29,669\r\n<i>~ For auld lang syne, my dear ~</i>\r\n\r\n1403\r\n01:57:29,800 --> 01:57:35,130\r\n<i>~ For auld lang syne ~</i>\r\n\r\n1404\r\n01:57:35,230 --> 01:57:39,709\r\n<i>~ We'll drink a cup of kindness yet ~</i>\r\n\r\n1405\r\n01:57:39,920 --> 01:57:45,720\r\n<i>~ For auld lang syne ~</i>\r\n\r\n1406\r\n01:57:56,560 --> 01:57:57,560\r\nFran?\r\n\r\n1407\r\n01:57:59,760 --> 01:58:01,716\r\nWhere are you, Fran?\r\n\r\n1408\r\n01:58:19,120 --> 01:58:21,076\r\nMr Baxter!\r\n\r\n1409\r\n01:58:21,360 --> 01:58:22,475\r\nMr Baxter!\r\n\r\n1410\r\n01:58:22,840 --> 01:58:25,718\r\nMr Baxter! Mr Baxter!\r\n\r\n1411\r\n01:58:28,600 --> 01:58:29,600\r\nOh!\r\n\r\n1412\r\n01:58:30,000 --> 01:58:32,992\r\n- Are you all right?\r\n- I'm fine.\r\n\r\n1413\r\n01:58:33,120 --> 01:58:35,475\r\nAre you sure? How's your knee?\r\n\r\n1414\r\n01:58:36,200 --> 01:58:38,156\r\nI'm fine all over.\r\n\r\n1415\r\n01:58:40,120 --> 01:58:43,396\r\n- Mind if I come in?\r\n- Of course not.\r\n\r\n1416\r\n01:58:47,000 --> 01:58:48,956\r\nLet me get another glass.\r\n\r\n1417\r\n01:58:51,800 --> 01:58:53,836\r\n- Where are you going?\r\n- Who knows?\r\n\r\n1418\r\n01:58:53,960 --> 01:58:57,157\r\nAnother neighbourhood,\r\nanother town, another job.\r\n\r\n1419\r\n01:58:57,280 --> 01:58:59,510\r\nI'm on my own.\r\n\r\n1420\r\n01:58:59,640 --> 01:59:01,596\r\nThat's funny. So am I.\r\n\r\n1421\r\n01:59:02,760 --> 01:59:04,955\r\nWhat'd you do with the cards?\r\n\r\n1422\r\n01:59:05,080 --> 01:59:06,880\r\nIn there.\r\n\r\n1423\r\n01:59:17,920 --> 01:59:19,876\r\nWhat about Mr Sheldrake?\r\n\r\n1424\r\n01:59:20,000 --> 01:59:22,958\r\nI'm gonna send him\r\na fruitcake every Christmas.\r\n\r\n1425\r\n01:59:25,320 --> 01:59:26,320\r\nCut.\r\n\r\n1426\r\n01:59:28,880 --> 01:59:30,836\r\nI love you, Miss Kubelik.\r\n\r\n1427\r\n01:59:31,360 --> 01:59:32,560\r\nThree.\r\n\r\n1428\r\n01:59:33,240 --> 01:59:34,389\r\nQueen.\r\n\r\n1429\r\n01:59:34,520 --> 01:59:38,354\r\nDid you hear what I said, Miss Kubelik?\r\nI absolutely adore you.\r\n\r\n1430\r\n01:59:40,920 --> 01:59:42,876\r\nShut up and deal.\r\n\r\n1431\r\n01:59:57,240 --> 02:00:00,198\r\nVisiontext Subtitles:\r\nDoreen Trenerry\r\n\r\n","markerStore":{"nextMarkerId":331,"markersById":{"0":{"range":{"start":{"row":1682,"column":24},"end":{"row":1682,"column":24}},"properties":{"type":"selection","editorId":140,"goalScreenRange":null},"reversed":false,"tailed":false,"valid":true,"invalidate":"never","maintainHistory":true}},"version":2},"history":{"version":3,"nextCheckpointId":1,"undoStack":[],"redoStack":[]},"encoding":"utf8","filePath":"/Users/joegesualdo/.Trash/the apartment english dvd.srt 3.08.07 PM","digestWhenLastPersisted":"7d3d8a3f27e7af9a7732c7ac5fc9a8fca67c559c","preferredLineEnding":null,"deserializer":"TextBuffer","version":2},{"load":true,"text":"1\r\n00:03:11,305 --> 00:03:13,671\r\nHi. I've got an appointment\r\nwith Mr. Ullman.\r\n\r\n2\r\n00:03:13,874 --> 00:03:15,808\r\nMy name is Jack Torrance.\r\n\r\n3\r\n00:03:16,009 --> 00:03:18,534\r\nHis office is the first door\r\non the left.\r\n\r\n4\r\n00:03:18,745 --> 00:03:19,973\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\n5\r\n00:03:36,029 --> 00:03:37,018\r\n<font color=\"#ff00ff\">[KNOCKS]</font>\r\n\r\n6\r\n00:03:37,197 --> 00:03:38,391\r\n- Mr. Ullman?\r\n- Yes.\r\n\r\n7\r\n00:03:38,565 --> 00:03:41,830\r\n- I'm Jack Torrance.\r\n- Oh, come on in, Jack.\r\n\r\n8\r\n00:03:42,936 --> 00:03:45,461\r\n- Very nice to meet you.\r\n- Nice to meet you.\r\n\r\n9\r\n00:03:45,672 --> 00:03:47,697\r\n- This is my secretary, Susie.\r\n- Hello.\r\n\r\n10\r\n00:03:47,875 --> 00:03:50,105\r\n- Susie, how do you do?\r\n- Any trouble finding us?\r\n\r\n11\r\n00:03:50,310 --> 00:03:53,143\r\nNo problem at all.\r\nI made the trip in 3 1/2 hours.\r\n\r\n12\r\n00:03:53,347 --> 00:03:55,247\r\nThat's very good time.\r\n\r\n13\r\n00:03:55,582 --> 00:03:57,174\r\nSit down a minute, Jack.\r\n\r\n14\r\n00:03:57,417 --> 00:03:59,180\r\nJust make yourself at home.\r\n\r\n15\r\n00:03:59,386 --> 00:04:00,648\r\nLike some coffee?\r\n\r\n16\r\n00:04:00,854 --> 00:04:03,345\r\nIf you're having some,\r\nI wouldn't mind. Thanks.\r\n\r\n17\r\n00:04:03,557 --> 00:04:04,546\r\n- Susie.\r\n- Sure.\r\n\r\n18\r\n00:04:04,758 --> 00:04:06,487\r\nAnd ask Bill Watson to join us.\r\n\r\n19\r\n00:04:06,693 --> 00:04:08,126\r\nYes, I will.\r\n\r\n20\r\n00:04:16,837 --> 00:04:18,668\r\n<font color=\"#ff00ff\">[MUSIC PLAYS ON TV]</font>\r\n\r\n21\r\n00:04:19,006 --> 00:04:20,132\r\nMom?\r\n\r\n22\r\n00:04:21,008 --> 00:04:22,168\r\nYeah?\r\n\r\n23\r\n00:04:22,576 --> 00:04:26,205\r\nDo you really want to go and live\r\nin that hotel for the winter?\r\n\r\n24\r\n00:04:26,813 --> 00:04:28,178\r\nSure I do.\r\n\r\n25\r\n00:04:28,382 --> 00:04:30,316\r\nIt'll be lots of fun.\r\n\r\n26\r\n00:04:32,185 --> 00:04:34,278\r\nYeah. I guess so.\r\n\r\n27\r\n00:04:34,488 --> 00:04:38,652\r\nAnyway, there's hardly anybody\r\nto play with around here.\r\n\r\n28\r\n00:04:39,459 --> 00:04:43,088\r\nI know. It always takes\r\na little time to make new friends.\r\n\r\n29\r\n00:04:44,564 --> 00:04:46,862\r\nYeah, I guess so.\r\n\r\n30\r\n00:04:47,634 --> 00:04:48,658\r\nWhat about Tony?\r\n\r\n31\r\n00:04:48,869 --> 00:04:51,269\r\nHe's looking forward\r\nto the hotel, I bet.\r\n\r\n32\r\n00:04:51,805 --> 00:04:54,171\r\n<font color=\"#ff00ff\">[IN TONY'S VOICE]</font>\r\n<i>No, I ain't, Mrs. Torrance.</i>\r\n\r\n33\r\n00:04:54,574 --> 00:04:57,008\r\nNow, come on, Tony.\r\nDon't be silly.\r\n\r\n34\r\n00:04:57,411 --> 00:04:59,402\r\n<i>I don't want to go there.</i>\r\n\r\n35\r\n00:04:59,880 --> 00:05:01,905\r\nHow come you don't want to go?\r\n\r\n36\r\n00:05:02,149 --> 00:05:04,242\r\n<i>I just don't.</i>\r\n\r\n37\r\n00:05:04,685 --> 00:05:07,245\r\nLet's just wait and see.\r\n\r\n38\r\n00:05:07,521 --> 00:05:10,217\r\nWe're all going to have\r\na real good time.\r\n\r\n39\r\n00:05:11,591 --> 00:05:14,059\r\nBill, I'd like you\r\nto meet Jack Torrance.\r\n\r\n40\r\n00:05:14,261 --> 00:05:15,694\r\nHow do you do, Bill?\r\n\r\n41\r\n00:05:15,896 --> 00:05:17,864\r\n- Nice to meet you.\r\n- Nice to meet you.\r\n\r\n\r\n42\r\n00:05:18,065 --> 00:05:19,999\r\nGrab a chair, Bill. Join in.\r\n\r\n43\r\n00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:24,330\r\nJack is going to take care of\r\nthe Overlook for us this winter.\r\n\r\n44\r\n00:05:24,571 --> 00:05:27,506\r\nI'd like you to take him around\r\nsoon as we're through.\r\n\r\n45\r\n00:05:27,674 --> 00:05:28,663\r\nFine.\r\n\r\n46\r\n00:05:29,309 --> 00:05:30,833\r\nJack is a schoolteacher.\r\n\r\n47\r\n00:05:31,011 --> 00:05:33,445\r\nUh, formerly a schoolteacher.\r\n\r\n48\r\n00:05:33,647 --> 00:05:35,342\r\n<font color=\"#FF55M1\">BILL:</font>\r\nWhat line of work are you in now?\r\n\r\n49\r\n00:05:35,549 --> 00:05:37,141\r\nI'm a writer.\r\n\r\n50\r\n00:05:37,384 --> 00:05:41,013\r\nTeaching's been more or less\r\na way of making ends meet.\r\n\r\n51\r\n00:05:41,221 --> 00:05:43,189\r\nThis ought to be\r\nquite a change for you.\r\n\r\n52\r\n00:05:43,390 --> 00:05:45,915\r\nWell, I'm looking for a change.\r\n\r\n53\r\n00:05:46,126 --> 00:05:49,721\r\nOur people in Denver recommended\r\nJack very highly, and for once...\r\n\r\n54\r\n00:05:49,930 --> 00:05:51,522\r\n...I agree with them.\r\n\r\n55\r\n00:05:52,165 --> 00:05:53,962\r\nLet's see, where were we?\r\n\r\n56\r\n00:05:54,167 --> 00:05:56,761\r\nI was about to explain that...\r\n\r\n57\r\n00:05:57,004 --> 00:06:01,168\r\n...our season here runs from\r\nMay 15th to October 30th.\r\n\r\n58\r\n00:06:01,375 --> 00:06:04,833\r\nThen we close down completely\r\nuntil the following May.\r\n\r\n59\r\n00:06:05,045 --> 00:06:07,843\r\nDo you mind if I ask why you do that?\r\n\r\n60\r\n00:06:08,048 --> 00:06:11,506\r\nIt seems to me that the skiing\r\nup here would be fantastic.\r\n\r\n61\r\n00:06:11,718 --> 00:06:14,312\r\nIt would be. The problem is\r\nthe enormous cost...\r\n\r\n62\r\n00:06:14,521 --> 00:06:17,081\r\n...it would be to keep\r\nthe road to Sidewinder open.\r\n\r\n63\r\n00:06:17,724 --> 00:06:19,453\r\nIt's a 25-mile stretch of road.\r\n\r\n64\r\n00:06:19,659 --> 00:06:22,025\r\nIt gets 20 feet of snow\r\nduring the winter.\r\n\r\n65\r\n00:06:22,229 --> 00:06:25,460\r\nThere's just no way to make it\r\neconomically feasible to...\r\n\r\n66\r\n00:06:25,665 --> 00:06:27,599\r\n...keep it clear.\r\n\r\n67\r\n00:06:27,801 --> 00:06:30,167\r\nWhen the place was built in 1907...\r\n\r\n68\r\n00:06:30,370 --> 00:06:32,930\r\n...there was very little interest\r\nin winter sports.\r\n\r\n69\r\n00:06:33,140 --> 00:06:38,009\r\nThis site was chosen for its\r\nseclusion and scenic beauty.\r\n\r\n70\r\n00:06:38,245 --> 00:06:40,770\r\nIt's certainly got plenty of that.\r\n\r\n71\r\n00:06:40,981 --> 00:06:42,175\r\nThat's right.\r\n\r\n72\r\n00:06:42,883 --> 00:06:45,716\r\nDid they give you any idea in Denver about...\r\n\r\n73\r\n00:06:45,919 --> 00:06:47,580\r\n...what the job entails?\r\n\r\n74\r\n00:06:47,788 --> 00:06:49,881\r\nOnly in a very general way.\r\n\r\n75\r\n00:06:50,690 --> 00:06:52,123\r\nWell...\r\n\r\n76\r\n00:06:52,526 --> 00:06:54,960\r\n...the winters can be fantastically cruel.\r\n\r\n77\r\n00:06:55,162 --> 00:06:58,620\r\nThe basic idea is to cope\r\nwith the very costly damage...\r\n\r\n78\r\n00:06:58,832 --> 00:07:00,823\r\n...and depreciation\r\nwhich can occur.\r\n\r\n79\r\n00:07:01,034 --> 00:07:03,468\r\nThis consists mainly\r\nof running the boiler...\r\n\r\n80\r\n00:07:03,670 --> 00:07:07,629\r\n...heating different parts of the\r\nhotel on a daily rotating basis...\r\n\r\n81\r\n00:07:07,841 --> 00:07:09,904\r\n...repairing damage as it occurs...\r\n\r\n82\r\n00:07:09,904 --> 00:07:13,577\r\n...and doing repairs so the\r\nelements can't get a foothold.\r\n\r\n83\r\n00:07:14,648 --> 00:07:16,878\r\nThat sounds fine to me.\r\n\r\n84\r\n00:07:17,284 --> 00:07:20,253\r\nPhysically, it's not\r\na very demanding job.\r\n\r\n85\r\n00:07:20,454 --> 00:07:23,617\r\nThe only thing that can get a bit\r\ntrying here during the winter is...\r\n\r\n86\r\n00:07:23,824 --> 00:07:26,452\r\n...a tremendous sense\r\nof isolation.\r\n\r\n87\r\n00:07:27,594 --> 00:07:32,156\r\nThat just happens to be\r\nexactly what I'm looking for.\r\n\r\n88\r\n00:07:32,499 --> 00:07:35,627\r\nI'm outlining a new writing project.\r\n\r\n89\r\n00:07:36,036 --> 00:07:39,335\r\nFive months of peace\r\nis just what I want.\r\n\r\n90\r\n00:07:40,107 --> 00:07:41,836\r\nThat's very good, Jack.\r\n\r\n91\r\n00:07:42,142 --> 00:07:45,305\r\nBecause, for some people...\r\n\r\n92\r\n00:07:45,512 --> 00:07:47,275\r\n...solitude...\r\n\r\n93\r\n00:07:47,481 --> 00:07:49,108\r\n...and isolation...\r\n\r\n94\r\n00:07:49,282 --> 00:07:52,251\r\n...can, of itself, become a problem.\r\n\r\n95\r\n00:07:53,053 --> 00:07:54,645\r\nNot for me.\r\n\r\n96\r\n00:07:55,188 --> 00:07:58,419\r\nHow about your wife and son?\r\nDo you think they'll take to it?\r\n\r\n97\r\n00:08:00,227 --> 00:08:01,387\r\nThey'll love it.\r\n\r\n98\r\n00:08:01,595 --> 00:08:02,789\r\nGreat.\r\n\r\n99\r\n00:08:04,264 --> 00:08:08,928\r\nWell, before I turn you over to Bill...\r\n\r\n100\r\n00:08:09,136 --> 00:08:12,628\r\n...there's one other thing I think\r\nwe should talk about.\r\n\r\n101\r\n00:08:12,839 --> 00:08:14,272\r\nNot to sound melodramatic...\r\n\r\n102\r\n00:08:14,474 --> 00:08:17,034\r\n...but it's been known to\r\ngive a few people...\r\n\r\n103\r\n00:08:17,244 --> 00:08:19,439\r\n...second thoughts about the job.\r\n\r\n104\r\n00:08:20,147 --> 00:08:21,808\r\nI'm intrigued.\r\n\r\n105\r\n00:08:22,015 --> 00:08:24,347\r\nI don't suppose they tell you\r\nabout anything in Denver...\r\n\r\n106\r\n00:08:24,551 --> 00:08:28,510\r\n...about the tragedy we had up here\r\nduring the winter of 1970.\r\n\r\n107\r\n00:08:29,122 --> 00:08:31,113\r\nI don't believe they did.\r\n\r\n108\r\n00:08:32,058 --> 00:08:33,616\r\n<font color=\"#FF55M1\">ULLMAN:</font>\r\nWell....\r\n\r\n109\r\n00:08:34,060 --> 00:08:36,153\r\nMy predecessor in this job...\r\n\r\n110\r\n00:08:36,329 --> 00:08:39,355\r\n...hired a man named Charles Grady\r\nas the winter caretaker.\r\n\r\n111\r\n00:08:39,566 --> 00:08:43,093\r\nHe came up with his wife and\r\ntwo little girls of about 8 and 10.\r\n\r\n112\r\n00:08:43,303 --> 00:08:46,295\r\nHe had a good employment record,\r\ngood references.\r\n\r\n113\r\n00:08:46,506 --> 00:08:48,770\r\nAnd from what I've been told,\r\nhe seemed like...\r\n\r\n114\r\n00:08:48,975 --> 00:08:51,671\r\n...a completely\r\nnormal individual.\r\n\r\n115\r\n00:08:51,878 --> 00:08:54,244\r\nBut at some point during the winter...\r\n\r\n116\r\n00:08:54,447 --> 00:08:58,076\r\n...he must have suffered some kind\r\nof a complete mental breakdown.\r\n\r\n117\r\n00:08:58,285 --> 00:09:00,651\r\nHe ran amuck and...\r\n\r\n118\r\n00:09:04,057 --> 00:09:06,252\r\n...killed his family\r\nwith an ax.\r\n\r\n119\r\n00:09:07,527 --> 00:09:12,157\r\nStacked them neatly in a room\r\nin the west wing, and then...\r\n\r\n120\r\n00:09:12,966 --> 00:09:16,663\r\n...he put both barrels\r\nof his shotgun in his mouth.\r\n\r\n121\r\n00:09:17,904 --> 00:09:19,701\r\nThe police...\r\n\r\n122\r\n00:09:19,906 --> 00:09:23,967\r\n...thought that it was what the\r\nold-timers used to call cabin fever.\r\n\r\n123\r\n00:09:24,177 --> 00:09:27,203\r\nA kind of claustrophobic reaction\r\nwhich can occur...\r\n\r\n124\r\n00:09:27,414 --> 00:09:31,544\r\n...when people are shut in together\r\nover long periods of time.\r\n\r\n125\r\n00:09:33,687 --> 00:09:35,177\r\nWow.\r\n\r\n126\r\n00:09:36,623 --> 00:09:38,056\r\nThat is...\r\n\r\n127\r\n00:09:38,258 --> 00:09:39,782\r\n...quite a story.\r\n\r\n128\r\n00:09:41,094 --> 00:09:42,561\r\nYeah, it is.\r\n\r\n129\r\n00:09:43,663 --> 00:09:46,962\r\nIt's still hard for me to believe\r\nit actually happened here.\r\n\r\n130\r\n00:09:47,300 --> 00:09:48,995\r\nBut it did.\r\n\r\n131\r\n00:09:49,202 --> 00:09:50,601\r\nAnd, uh...\r\n\r\n132\r\n00:09:50,770 --> 00:09:54,797\r\n...I think you can appreciate\r\nwhy I wanted to tell you about it.\r\n\r\n133\r\n00:09:55,342 --> 00:09:57,833\r\nI certainly can.\r\n\r\n134\r\n00:09:58,345 --> 00:10:00,905\r\nI also understand\r\nwhy your people in Denver...\r\n\r\n135\r\n00:10:01,114 --> 00:10:03,378\r\n...left it for you to tell me.\r\n\r\n136\r\n00:10:04,584 --> 00:10:07,280\r\nObviously, some people\r\ncan be put off...\r\n\r\n137\r\n00:10:07,487 --> 00:10:11,583\r\n...from staying in a place where\r\nsomething like that happened.\r\n\r\n138\r\n00:10:11,791 --> 00:10:16,694\r\nYou can rest assured that's not\r\ngoing to happen with me.\r\n\r\n139\r\n00:10:16,896 --> 00:10:20,559\r\nAnd as far as my wife\r\nis concerned...\r\n\r\n140\r\n00:10:20,767 --> 00:10:24,601\r\n...I'm sure she'll be absolutely\r\nfascinated when I tell her about it.\r\n\r\n141\r\n00:10:24,804 --> 00:10:27,637\r\nShe's a confirmed ghost story...\r\n\r\n142\r\n00:10:27,841 --> 00:10:30,275\r\n...and horror film addict.\r\n\r\n143\r\n00:10:35,115 --> 00:10:38,812\r\nTony, do you think Dad'll get the job?\r\n\r\n144\r\n00:10:40,220 --> 00:10:42,415\r\n<i>He already did.</i>\r\n\r\n145\r\n00:10:42,856 --> 00:10:46,587\r\n<i>He's going to phone Wendy up\r\nin a few minutes to tell her.</i>\r\n\r\n146\r\n00:10:54,501 --> 00:10:56,264\r\n<font color=\"#ff00ff\">[PHONE RINGING]</font>\r\n\r\n147\r\n00:10:59,906 --> 00:11:01,066\r\nHello.\r\n\r\n148\r\n00:11:01,308 --> 00:11:03,970\r\n- Hi, babe.\r\n-<i>Hi, hon. How's it going?</i>\r\n\r\n149\r\n00:11:04,177 --> 00:11:07,772\r\nGreat. I'm at the hotel and\r\nI still have a lot to go through.\r\n\r\n150\r\n00:11:07,981 --> 00:11:11,109\r\nI don't think I can get home\r\nbefore 9:00 or 10:00.\r\n\r\n151\r\n00:11:11,318 --> 00:11:12,808\r\nSounds like you got the job.\r\n\r\n152\r\n00:11:13,019 --> 00:11:15,715\r\nRight. It's a beautiful place.\r\n\r\n153\r\n00:11:15,922 --> 00:11:18,049\r\nYou and Danny are going to love it.\r\n\r\n154\r\n00:11:19,526 --> 00:11:22,427\r\nTony, why don't you want to go\r\nto the hotel?\r\n\r\n155\r\n00:11:22,696 --> 00:11:24,425\r\n<i>I don't know.</i>\r\n\r\n156\r\n00:11:25,498 --> 00:11:29,025\r\nYou do too know.\r\nNow come on, tell me.\r\n\r\n157\r\n00:11:29,602 --> 00:11:31,661\r\n<i>I don't want to.</i>\r\n\r\n158\r\n00:11:32,372 --> 00:11:33,634\r\nPlease.\r\n\r\n159\r\n00:11:34,874 --> 00:11:36,000\r\n<i>No.</i>\r\n\r\n160\r\n00:11:36,309 --> 00:11:38,402\r\nNow, Tony, tell me.\r\n\r\n161\r\n00:12:08,308 --> 00:12:11,038\r\n<font color=\"#FF55M1\">DOCTOR:</font> <i>Now, hold your eyes still\r\nso I can see.</i>\r\n\r\n162\r\n00:12:15,515 --> 00:12:17,745\r\nThat's good. Now the other one.\r\n\r\n163\r\n00:12:19,152 --> 00:12:20,619\r\nGood boy.\r\n\r\n164\r\n00:12:27,961 --> 00:12:29,326\r\nNow, Danny...\r\n\r\n165\r\n00:12:29,796 --> 00:12:31,821\r\n...when you were brushing\r\nyour teeth...\r\n\r\n166\r\n00:12:32,031 --> 00:12:35,023\r\n...do you remember if you\r\nsmelled anything funny...\r\n\r\n167\r\n00:12:35,235 --> 00:12:40,002\r\n...or saw any bright, flashing\r\nlights or anything at all strange?\r\n\r\n168\r\n00:12:42,842 --> 00:12:44,002\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n169\r\n00:12:45,078 --> 00:12:47,569\r\n<font color=\"#FF55M1\">DOCTOR:</font> Do you remember\r\nwhen you were brushing your teeth?\r\n\r\n170\r\n00:12:48,148 --> 00:12:49,445\r\nYes.\r\n\r\n171\r\n00:12:50,583 --> 00:12:54,212\r\nWhat's the next thing you remember\r\nafter you were brushing your teeth?\r\n\r\n172\r\n00:12:58,425 --> 00:13:02,555\r\nMy mom was saying, \"Wake up.\r\nWake up, Danny, wake up.\"\r\n\r\n173\r\n00:13:03,296 --> 00:13:07,494\r\nNow, Danny, can you remember\r\nwhat you were doing...\r\n\r\n174\r\n00:13:07,700 --> 00:13:10,635\r\n...just before you started\r\nbrushing your teeth?\r\n\r\n175\r\n00:13:13,139 --> 00:13:14,902\r\nTalking to Tony.\r\n\r\n176\r\n00:13:15,575 --> 00:13:17,941\r\nIs Tony one of your animals?\r\n\r\n177\r\n00:13:18,812 --> 00:13:21,747\r\nNo. He's a little boy\r\nthat lives in my mouth.\r\n\r\n178\r\n00:13:22,048 --> 00:13:24,448\r\nTony's his imaginary friend.\r\n\r\n179\r\n00:13:24,851 --> 00:13:26,284\r\n<font color=\"#FF55M1\">DOCTOR:</font>\r\nOh.\r\n\r\n180\r\n00:13:27,387 --> 00:13:30,788\r\nIf you were to open your mouth now,\r\ncould I see Tony?\r\n\r\n181\r\n00:13:31,558 --> 00:13:32,991\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n182\r\n00:13:33,460 --> 00:13:34,688\r\nWhy not?\r\n\r\n183\r\n00:13:35,962 --> 00:13:37,793\r\nBecause he hides.\r\n\r\n184\r\n00:13:38,531 --> 00:13:40,192\r\nWhere does he go?\r\n\r\n185\r\n00:13:41,301 --> 00:13:43,098\r\nTo my stomach.\r\n\r\n186\r\n00:13:45,138 --> 00:13:48,039\r\nDoes Tony ever tell you\r\nto do things?\r\n\r\n187\r\n00:13:52,111 --> 00:13:54,773\r\nI don't want to talk\r\nabout Tony anymore.\r\n\r\n188\r\n00:13:55,582 --> 00:13:57,243\r\nOkay.\r\n\r\n189\r\n00:13:57,417 --> 00:13:58,850\r\nThat's fine.\r\n\r\n190\r\n00:13:59,619 --> 00:14:01,416\r\nAll right, Danny.\r\n\r\n191\r\n00:14:02,222 --> 00:14:05,020\r\nI'm going to ask you\r\nto do me a favor...\r\n\r\n192\r\n00:14:05,225 --> 00:14:08,592\r\n...and stay quietly in bed\r\nfor the rest of the day. Okay?\r\n\r\n193\r\n00:14:08,795 --> 00:14:09,921\r\nDo I have to?\r\n\r\n194\r\n00:14:10,129 --> 00:14:12,393\r\nYes. I'd like you to.\r\n\r\n195\r\n00:14:12,599 --> 00:14:15,363\r\nWe're going in the other room\r\nfor a few minutes and talk.\r\n\r\n196\r\n00:14:15,568 --> 00:14:17,934\r\nI'll come back and check on you.\r\nOkay?\r\n\r\n197\r\n00:14:17,934 --> 00:14:19,969\r\n- Okay.\r\n- Bye.\r\n\r\n198\r\n00:14:26,212 --> 00:14:28,612\r\n- Shall we go into the living room?\r\n- Yes.\r\n\r\n199\r\n00:14:32,318 --> 00:14:34,183\r\n- Please.\r\n- Thank you.\r\n\r\n200\r\n00:14:38,057 --> 00:14:42,426\r\nMrs. Torrance, I don't think\r\nyou have anything to worry about.\r\n\r\n201\r\n00:14:42,629 --> 00:14:46,656\r\nI'm quite sure there's nothing\r\nphysically wrong with Danny.\r\n\r\n202\r\n00:14:47,367 --> 00:14:48,834\r\nYeah?\r\n\r\n203\r\n00:14:49,302 --> 00:14:50,826\r\nOh.\r\n\r\n204\r\n00:14:51,404 --> 00:14:54,498\r\nHe seems absolutely fine now.\r\n\r\n205\r\n00:14:54,674 --> 00:14:55,732\r\nBut you should've seen him.\r\n\r\n206\r\n00:14:56,409 --> 00:14:57,433\r\nI know.\r\n\r\n207\r\n00:14:57,644 --> 00:14:59,339\r\nKids can scare you to death.\r\n\r\n208\r\n00:14:59,546 --> 00:15:02,413\r\nBut believe me, these episodes\r\nare not at all uncommon.\r\n\r\n209\r\n00:15:02,615 --> 00:15:05,175\r\nAnd they look much worse\r\nthan they are.\r\n\r\n210\r\n00:15:05,718 --> 00:15:08,380\r\nBut what was the matter with him?\r\n\r\n211\r\n00:15:08,588 --> 00:15:12,684\r\nMost of the time, these episodes\r\nwith kids are never explained.\r\n\r\n212\r\n00:15:12,892 --> 00:15:17,761\r\nThey're brought on by emotional\r\nfactors and rarely occur again.\r\n\r\n213\r\n00:15:18,565 --> 00:15:21,534\r\nThey're more akin\r\nto autohypnosis...\r\n\r\n214\r\n00:15:21,734 --> 00:15:24,703\r\n...a kind of self-induced trance.\r\n\r\n215\r\n00:15:24,904 --> 00:15:26,895\r\nIf it reoccurs, which I doubt...\r\n\r\n216\r\n00:15:27,774 --> 00:15:30,868\r\n...we can always think about\r\nhaving some tests done.\r\n\r\n217\r\n00:15:31,344 --> 00:15:32,811\r\nNo, thank you.\r\n\r\n218\r\n00:15:33,479 --> 00:15:35,743\r\nI'm sure you're right.\r\n\r\n219\r\n00:15:37,383 --> 00:15:40,079\r\nHave you been in Boulder long?\r\n\r\n220\r\n00:15:40,887 --> 00:15:42,184\r\nOnly about three months.\r\n\r\n221\r\n00:15:42,388 --> 00:15:45,755\r\nWe're from Vermont. My husband\r\nwas teaching school there.\r\n\r\n222\r\n00:15:47,760 --> 00:15:51,560\r\nDid the appearance\r\nof Danny's imaginary friend....\r\n\r\n223\r\n00:15:51,831 --> 00:15:52,820\r\nTony.\r\n\r\n224\r\n00:15:53,032 --> 00:15:56,991\r\nDid Tony's first appearance happen\r\nto coincide with your arrival here?\r\n\r\n225\r\n00:15:58,204 --> 00:15:59,933\r\nNo, um....\r\n\r\n226\r\n00:16:00,106 --> 00:16:01,437\r\nLet's see....\r\n\r\n227\r\n00:16:02,141 --> 00:16:04,701\r\nI guess Danny started\r\ntalking to Tony about...\r\n\r\n228\r\n00:16:04,911 --> 00:16:07,607\r\n...the time we put him\r\nin nursery school.\r\n\r\n229\r\n00:16:08,014 --> 00:16:10,312\r\nDid he adjust well to school?\r\n\r\n230\r\n00:16:11,184 --> 00:16:12,344\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n231\r\n00:16:12,518 --> 00:16:14,452\r\nHe didn't like it too much at first.\r\n\r\n232\r\n00:16:14,654 --> 00:16:17,953\r\nThen he had an injury, so we kept\r\nhim out for a while and....\r\n\r\n233\r\n00:16:18,658 --> 00:16:23,254\r\nYeah, I guess that's about when I first\r\nnoticed he was talking to Tony.\r\n\r\n234\r\n00:16:24,263 --> 00:16:26,663\r\nWhat sort of injury did he have?\r\n\r\n235\r\n00:16:27,333 --> 00:16:29,494\r\nHe dislocated his shoulder.\r\n\r\n236\r\n00:16:29,969 --> 00:16:32,233\r\nHow did he manage to do that?\r\n\r\n237\r\n00:16:35,675 --> 00:16:38,735\r\nIt was just one of\r\nthose things, you know.\r\n\r\n238\r\n00:16:38,945 --> 00:16:40,936\r\nPurely an accident.\r\n\r\n239\r\n00:16:41,914 --> 00:16:44,712\r\nMy husband had been drinking...\r\n\r\n240\r\n00:16:44,917 --> 00:16:48,250\r\n...and he came home\r\nabout three hours late.\r\n\r\n241\r\n00:16:48,554 --> 00:16:53,116\r\nSo he wasn't exactly\r\nin the greatest mood that night.\r\n\r\n242\r\n00:16:53,860 --> 00:16:58,627\r\nAnd Danny had scattered some of his\r\nschool papers all over the room and...\r\n\r\n243\r\n00:16:58,831 --> 00:17:03,131\r\n...my husband grabbed his arm\r\nto pull him away from them.\r\n\r\n244\r\n00:17:03,336 --> 00:17:06,396\r\nIt's just the sort of thing you do\r\n100 times with a child you know,...\r\n\r\n245\r\n00:17:06,606 --> 00:17:08,631\r\n...in a park or in the street.\r\n\r\n246\r\n00:17:09,742 --> 00:17:12,370\r\nBut on this particular occasion...\r\n\r\n247\r\n00:17:12,578 --> 00:17:15,206\r\n...my husband just used\r\ntoo much strength...\r\n\r\n248\r\n00:17:15,415 --> 00:17:18,009\r\n...and he injured Danny's arm.\r\n\r\n249\r\n00:17:21,054 --> 00:17:25,582\r\nAnyway, something good did come out\r\nof it all because he said:\r\n\r\n250\r\n00:17:25,825 --> 00:17:28,385\r\n\"Wendy, I'm never going to\r\ntouch another drop.\r\n\r\n251\r\n00:17:28,594 --> 00:17:30,528\r\nAnd if I do, you can leave me.\"\r\n\r\n252\r\n00:17:30,730 --> 00:17:32,061\r\nAnd he didn't.\r\n\r\n253\r\n00:17:32,265 --> 00:17:36,759\r\nHe hasn't had any alcohol in 5 months.\r\n\r\n254\r\n00:18:02,061 --> 00:18:03,528\r\nBoy.\r\n\r\n255\r\n00:18:03,696 --> 00:18:07,860\r\nWe must really be high up.\r\nThe air feels so different.\r\n\r\n256\r\n00:18:09,102 --> 00:18:10,535\r\nMm-hm.\r\n\r\n257\r\n00:18:13,506 --> 00:18:14,734\r\nDad?\r\n\r\n258\r\n00:18:15,308 --> 00:18:16,866\r\nYes?\r\n\r\n259\r\n00:18:17,543 --> 00:18:19,238\r\nI'm hungry.\r\n\r\n260\r\n00:18:21,080 --> 00:18:23,810\r\nYou should've eaten your breakfast.\r\n\r\n261\r\n00:18:24,650 --> 00:18:27,551\r\nWe'll get you something\r\nas soon as we get to the hotel.\r\n\r\n262\r\n00:18:27,754 --> 00:18:29,381\r\nOkay, Mom.\r\n\r\n263\r\n00:18:30,823 --> 00:18:34,953\r\nWasn't it around here that\r\nthe Donner party got snowbound?\r\n\r\n264\r\n00:18:36,696 --> 00:18:40,029\r\nI think that was farther west,\r\nin the Sierras.\r\n\r\n265\r\n00:18:40,199 --> 00:18:41,496\r\nOh.\r\n\r\n266\r\n00:18:41,667 --> 00:18:44,101\r\nWhat was the Donner party?\r\n\r\n267\r\n00:18:46,038 --> 00:18:50,304\r\nThey were a party of settlers\r\nin covered wagon times.\r\n\r\n268\r\n00:18:50,543 --> 00:18:53,808\r\nThey got snowbound one winter\r\nin the mountains.\r\n\r\n269\r\n00:18:54,013 --> 00:18:58,211\r\nThey had to resort to cannibalism\r\nin order to stay alive.\r\n\r\n270\r\n00:18:59,352 --> 00:19:02,253\r\nYou mean they ate each other up?\r\n\r\n271\r\n00:19:02,455 --> 00:19:05,549\r\nThey had to in order to survive.\r\n\r\n272\r\n00:19:05,758 --> 00:19:06,986\r\nJack.\r\n\r\n273\r\n00:19:07,193 --> 00:19:08,285\r\nDon't worry, Mom.\r\n\r\n274\r\n00:19:08,494 --> 00:19:12,828\r\nI know all about cannibalism.\r\nI saw it on TV.\r\n\r\n275\r\n00:19:13,032 --> 00:19:15,660\r\nSee, it's okay.\r\n\r\n276\r\n00:19:15,868 --> 00:19:18,302\r\nHe saw it on the television.\r\n\r\n277\r\n00:19:49,001 --> 00:19:50,832\r\n- What time does the plane leave?\r\n- 8:30.\r\n\r\n278\r\n00:19:51,037 --> 00:19:53,801\r\nThat gives us plenty of time\r\nto go over everything.\r\n\r\n279\r\n00:19:54,006 --> 00:19:55,940\r\n- Goodbye, Mr. Ullman.\r\n- Bye.\r\n\r\n280\r\n00:19:56,142 --> 00:19:59,270\r\nGood morning. I hope you\r\nhaven't been waiting too long.\r\n\r\n281\r\n00:19:59,478 --> 00:20:02,106\r\nNo problem. We had time\r\nto grab a bite to eat.\r\n\r\n282\r\n00:20:02,315 --> 00:20:05,216\r\nGood. Glad you made it\r\nbefore they shut down the kitchen.\r\n\r\n283\r\n00:20:05,418 --> 00:20:07,147\r\n- Hi.\r\n- Is your family having a look around?\r\n\r\n284\r\n00:20:07,353 --> 00:20:10,720\r\nNo, my son's\r\ndiscovered the games room.\r\n\r\n285\r\n00:20:10,923 --> 00:20:13,050\r\n- Has your luggage been brought in?\r\n- Right there.\r\n\r\n286\r\n00:20:13,226 --> 00:20:14,454\r\nOh, fine.\r\n\r\n287\r\n00:20:14,627 --> 00:20:16,561\r\nIn view of all we have to cover today...\r\n\r\n288\r\n00:20:16,762 --> 00:20:20,425\r\n...I suggest we have a quick look\r\nat your apartment and get started.\r\n\r\n289\r\n00:20:20,633 --> 00:20:23,124\r\nHave the Torrances' things\r\nbrought to their apartment.\r\n\r\n290\r\n00:20:23,302 --> 00:20:25,532\r\n- Fine.\r\n- I'd better collect my family first.\r\n\r\n291\r\n00:20:25,705 --> 00:20:26,933\r\nOh, yes.\r\n\r\n292\r\n00:20:34,447 --> 00:20:36,813\r\nThis is our Colorado Lounge.\r\n\r\n293\r\n00:20:37,016 --> 00:20:39,450\r\nIt's beautiful.\r\n\r\n294\r\n00:20:39,852 --> 00:20:41,717\r\nMy God!\r\n\r\n295\r\n00:20:41,921 --> 00:20:44,481\r\nThis place is fantastic, Isn it, hon?\r\n\r\n296\r\n00:20:44,690 --> 00:20:46,021\r\nIt sure is.\r\n\r\n297\r\n00:20:46,225 --> 00:20:49,023\r\nI've never seen anything\r\nlike this before.\r\n\r\n298\r\n00:20:50,663 --> 00:20:52,631\r\nAre all these\r\nIndian designs authentic?\r\n\r\n299\r\n00:20:52,832 --> 00:20:54,265\r\nI believe they're based...\r\n\r\n300\r\n00:20:54,467 --> 00:20:57,664\r\n...mainly on Navajo and Apache motifs.\r\n\r\n301\r\n00:20:57,870 --> 00:20:59,838\r\nThey're really gorgeous.\r\n\r\n302\r\n00:21:00,039 --> 00:21:04,368\r\nAs a matter of fact this is probably the\r\nmost gorgeous hotel I've ever seen.\r\n\r\n304\r\n00:21:04,777 --> 00:21:07,746\r\nThis old place has had\r\nan illustrious past.\r\n\r\n305\r\n00:21:07,947 --> 00:21:11,041\r\nIn its heyday, it was a stopping\r\nplace for the jet setters...\r\n\r\n306\r\n00:21:11,250 --> 00:21:14,219\r\n...even before anybody knew\r\nwhat a jet set was.\r\n\r\n307\r\n00:21:14,420 --> 00:21:17,480\r\nWe had four presidents\r\nwho stayed here.\r\n\r\n308\r\n00:21:17,757 --> 00:21:19,019\r\nLots of movie stars.\r\n\r\n309\r\n00:21:19,225 --> 00:21:20,783\r\nRoyalty?\r\n\r\n310\r\n00:21:21,160 --> 00:21:22,559\r\nAll the best people.\r\n\r\n311\r\n00:22:15,681 --> 00:22:18,241\r\nThis is the staff wing of the hotel.\r\n\r\n312\r\n00:22:19,218 --> 00:22:22,551\r\nNone of the other bedrooms\r\nare heated during the winter.\r\n\r\n313\r\n00:22:22,788 --> 00:22:25,689\r\n- Goodbye, Mr. Ullman.\r\n- Goodbye, girls.\r\n\r\n314\r\n00:22:25,925 --> 00:22:27,916\r\n<font color=\"#FF55M1\">ULLMAN:</font>\r\nAnd here are your quarters.\r\n\r\n315\r\n00:22:28,327 --> 00:22:30,921\r\nLiving room, bedroom, bathroom.\r\n\r\n316\r\n00:22:31,130 --> 00:22:33,621\r\nAnd a small bedroom for your son.\r\n\r\n317\r\n00:22:37,236 --> 00:22:38,999\r\nPerfect for a child.\r\n\r\n318\r\n00:22:39,171 --> 00:22:40,866\r\n- Yeah.\r\n- Yes.\r\n\r\n319\r\n00:22:46,479 --> 00:22:49,937\r\n<font color=\"#FF55M1\">ULLMAN:</font> Well, then. Place is\r\nvery nicely self-contained.\r\n\r\n320\r\n00:22:50,149 --> 00:22:51,707\r\nEasy to keep.\r\n\r\n321\r\n00:22:54,487 --> 00:22:55,545\r\nCozy.\r\n\r\n322\r\n00:22:55,755 --> 00:22:58,019\r\n<font color=\"#FF55M1\">ULLMAN:</font>\r\nYes, very cozy for a family.\r\n\r\n323\r\n00:22:58,257 --> 00:22:59,918\r\nIf you feel like spreading out...\r\n\r\n324\r\n00:23:00,126 --> 00:23:02,788\r\n...you have the rest of the hotel\r\nto move around in.\r\n\r\n325\r\n00:23:04,430 --> 00:23:06,921\r\nWell, it's very...\r\n\r\n326\r\n00:23:07,466 --> 00:23:08,763\r\n...homey.\r\n\r\n327\r\n00:23:09,001 --> 00:23:10,127\r\nYeah.\r\n\r\n328\r\n00:23:11,670 --> 00:23:13,934\r\nThis is our famous hedge maze.\r\n\r\n329\r\n00:23:14,140 --> 00:23:18,440\r\nIt's quite an attraction here.\r\nThe walls are 13 feet high...\r\n\r\n330\r\n00:23:18,644 --> 00:23:20,942\r\n...and the hedge is as old\r\nas the hotel itself.\r\n\r\n331\r\n00:23:21,147 --> 00:23:23,575\r\nA lot of fun, but I wouldn't\r\nwant to go in there...\r\n\r\n332\r\n00:23:23,575 --> 00:23:26,975\r\n...unless I had an hour\r\nto spare to find my way out.\r\n\r\n333\r\n00:23:28,387 --> 00:23:30,480\r\n<font color=\"#FF55M1\">WENDY:</font>\r\nWhen was the Overlook built?\r\n\r\n334\r\n00:23:31,490 --> 00:23:33,720\r\nConstruction started in 1907.\r\n\r\n335\r\n00:23:33,926 --> 00:23:35,894\r\nIt was finished in 1909.\r\n\r\n336\r\n00:23:36,095 --> 00:23:38,757\r\nThe site's supposed to be\r\non an Indian burial ground.\r\n\r\n337\r\n00:23:38,964 --> 00:23:40,800\r\nThey actually had to repel...\r\n\r\n338\r\n00:23:40,800 --> 00:23:43,701\r\n...a few Indian attacks as they\r\nwere building it.\r\n\r\n339\r\n00:23:44,303 --> 00:23:46,203\r\nThat's our Snowcat.\r\n\r\n340\r\n00:23:46,906 --> 00:23:48,203\r\nCan you both drive a car?\r\n\r\n341\r\n00:23:48,374 --> 00:23:49,363\r\n<font color=\"#FF55M1\">BOTH:</font>\r\nYes.\r\n\r\n342\r\n00:23:49,542 --> 00:23:53,034\r\n<font color=\"#FF55M1\">ULLMAN:</font> That's fine. Basically\r\nthe Snowcat operates very much like a car.\r\n\r\n343\r\n00:23:53,245 --> 00:23:55,805\r\nIt won't take you long\r\nto get the hang of it.\r\n\r\n344\r\n00:23:57,016 --> 00:24:00,486\r\nAs a matter of fact, we brought\r\na decorator in from Chicago...\r\n\r\n345\r\n00:24:00,486 --> 00:24:03,111\r\n...just last year to refurbish\r\nthis part of the hotel.\r\n\r\n346\r\n00:24:03,289 --> 00:24:05,883\r\nOh. He sure did a beautiful job.\r\n\r\n347\r\n00:24:06,092 --> 00:24:08,424\r\nPink and gold are my favorite colors.\r\n\r\n348\r\n00:24:09,228 --> 00:24:11,594\r\nWell, this is our Gold Ballroom.\r\n\r\n349\r\n00:24:12,331 --> 00:24:14,424\r\nOh, I'll say!\r\n\r\n350\r\n00:24:14,633 --> 00:24:18,399\r\nWe can accommodate up to\r\n300 people here very comfortably.\r\n\r\n351\r\n00:24:18,938 --> 00:24:21,805\r\nBoy, we could really have\r\na good party in this room.\r\n\r\n352\r\n00:24:22,007 --> 00:24:25,807\r\nI'm afraid you won't do too well\r\nhere unless you brought supplies.\r\n\r\n353\r\n00:24:26,011 --> 00:24:29,071\r\nWe remove the booze from\r\nthe premises when we shut down.\r\n\r\n354\r\n00:24:29,281 --> 00:24:32,341\r\nThat reduces the insurance\r\nwe normally have to carry.\r\n\r\n355\r\n00:24:32,518 --> 00:24:33,507\r\nWe don't drink.\r\n\r\n356\r\n00:24:33,719 --> 00:24:35,152\r\nThen you're in luck.\r\n\r\n357\r\n00:24:35,354 --> 00:24:39,586\r\nDick, come on over and say hello\r\nto Mr. and Mrs. Torrance.\r\n\r\n358\r\n00:24:39,792 --> 00:24:41,919\r\nThis is Dick Hallorann,\r\nour head chef.\r\n\r\n359\r\n00:24:42,128 --> 00:24:44,858\r\nMr. Hallorann, I'm Jack.\r\nThis is my wife, Winifred.\r\n\r\n360\r\n00:24:45,064 --> 00:24:46,258\r\nGlad to meet you.\r\n\r\n361\r\n00:24:46,465 --> 00:24:49,332\r\nThe Torrances will take care\r\nof the Overlook this winter.\r\n\r\n362\r\n00:24:49,535 --> 00:24:53,266\r\nThat's just great. How do you\r\nfolks like our hotel so far?\r\n\r\n363\r\n00:24:53,472 --> 00:24:55,337\r\nIt's just wonderful.\r\n\r\n364\r\n00:24:55,541 --> 00:24:57,065\r\nHi, Danny!\r\n\r\n365\r\n00:24:58,277 --> 00:25:00,677\r\nI found him outside looking for you.\r\n\r\n366\r\n00:25:00,913 --> 00:25:04,576\r\nDan, did you get tired\r\nof bombing the universe?\r\n\r\n367\r\n00:25:04,750 --> 00:25:05,978\r\nYeah.\r\n\r\n368\r\n00:25:06,152 --> 00:25:07,278\r\nCome on over here.\r\n\r\n369\r\n00:25:07,453 --> 00:25:09,011\r\n- Thanks.\r\n- Thank you, Susie.\r\n\r\n370\r\n00:25:09,221 --> 00:25:13,325\r\nI think it'd be good if you could\r\nshow Mrs. Torrance the kitchen...\r\n\r\n371\r\n00:25:13,325 --> 00:25:15,290\r\n...while I continue on with Jack.\r\n\r\n372\r\n00:25:15,494 --> 00:25:18,128\r\nIt would be a pleasure. Right this way.\r\n\r\n373\r\n00:25:18,130 --> 00:25:19,688\r\nGreat. See you later, hon.\r\n\r\n374\r\n00:25:19,899 --> 00:25:21,264\r\nBye, darling.\r\n\r\n375\r\n00:25:23,636 --> 00:25:26,969\r\nMrs. Torrance, your husband\r\nintroduced you as Winifred.\r\n\r\n376\r\n00:25:27,173 --> 00:25:29,698\r\nNow, are you a \"Winnie,\"\r\nor a \"Freddie\"?\r\n\r\n377\r\n00:25:29,909 --> 00:25:30,898\r\nI'm a Wendy.\r\n\r\n378\r\n00:25:31,076 --> 00:25:34,568\r\nOh, Wendy. That's nice.\r\nThat's the prettiest.\r\n\r\n379\r\n00:25:34,780 --> 00:25:36,407\r\nThis is the kitchen, huh?\r\n\r\n380\r\n00:25:36,615 --> 00:25:38,207\r\nThis is it.\r\n\r\n381\r\n00:25:38,417 --> 00:25:40,885\r\nHow do you like it, Danny?\r\nIs it big enough for you?\r\n\r\n382\r\n00:25:41,053 --> 00:25:44,386\r\nYeah. It's the biggest place I ever seen.\r\n\r\n383\r\n00:25:44,623 --> 00:25:46,955\r\nThis whole place\r\nis such an enormous maze.\r\n\r\n384\r\n00:25:47,159 --> 00:25:50,720\r\nI'll have to leave a trail of\r\nbreadcrumbs every time I come in.\r\n\r\n385\r\n00:25:51,630 --> 00:25:53,495\r\nDon't let it get you down.\r\n\r\n386\r\n00:25:53,699 --> 00:25:56,190\r\nIt's big, but it ain't\r\nnothing but a kitchen.\r\n\r\n387\r\n00:25:56,402 --> 00:25:58,597\r\nA lot of this stuff\r\nyou'll never have to touch.\r\n\r\n388\r\n00:25:58,804 --> 00:26:01,034\r\nI wouldn't know\r\nwhat to do with it if I did.\r\n\r\n389\r\n00:26:01,240 --> 00:26:04,368\r\nOne thing for sure, you don't\r\nhave to worry about food.\r\n\r\n390\r\n00:26:04,577 --> 00:26:09,241\r\nYou folks could eat here for a year\r\nand never have the same menu twice.\r\n\r\n391\r\n00:26:09,448 --> 00:26:12,542\r\nRight here is our walk-in freezer.\r\n\r\n392\r\n00:26:13,686 --> 00:26:16,746\r\nThis is where we keep\r\nall of our meat.\r\n\r\n393\r\n00:26:16,956 --> 00:26:18,947\r\nYou got 15 rib roasts...\r\n\r\n394\r\n00:26:19,158 --> 00:26:21,285\r\n...30 ten-pound bags of hamburger.\r\n\r\n395\r\n00:26:21,493 --> 00:26:24,553\r\nWe got 12 turkeys,\r\nabout 40 chickens...\r\n\r\n396\r\n00:26:24,763 --> 00:26:27,857\r\n...50 sirloin steaks,\r\ntwo dozen of pork roast...\r\n\r\n397\r\n00:26:28,067 --> 00:26:31,036\r\n...and 20 legs of lamb.\r\nDo you like lamb, Doc?\r\n\r\n398\r\n00:26:31,203 --> 00:26:32,898\r\n- No.\r\n- You don't?\r\n\r\n399\r\n00:26:33,072 --> 00:26:34,630\r\nWhat's your favorite food, then?\r\n\r\n400\r\n00:26:34,840 --> 00:26:36,705\r\nFrench fries and ketchup.\r\n\r\n401\r\n00:26:37,443 --> 00:26:39,434\r\nI think we can\r\nmanage that too, Doc.\r\n\r\n402\r\n00:26:39,645 --> 00:26:41,374\r\nCome along, now.\r\nWatch your step.\r\n\r\n403\r\n00:26:45,084 --> 00:26:47,143\r\nMr. Hallorann...\r\n\r\n404\r\n00:26:48,120 --> 00:26:49,678\r\n...how'd you know we call him Doc?\r\n\r\n405\r\n00:26:49,888 --> 00:26:53,915\r\n- Beg your pardon?\r\n- Doc. You called Danny \"Doc\" twice.\r\n\r\n406\r\n00:26:54,126 --> 00:26:56,151\r\n- I did?\r\n- Yeah.\r\n\r\n407\r\n00:26:56,328 --> 00:26:59,456\r\nWe call him Doc sometimes,\r\nlike in the Bugs Bunny cartoons.\r\n\r\n408\r\n00:26:59,665 --> 00:27:00,927\r\nBut how did you know?\r\n\r\n409\r\n00:27:01,133 --> 00:27:03,658\r\nI guess I probably\r\nheard you call him that.\r\n\r\n410\r\n00:27:03,869 --> 00:27:06,238\r\nIt's possible.\r\nBut I honestly don't remember...\r\n\r\n411\r\n00:27:06,238 --> 00:27:08,533\r\n...calling him that\r\nsince we've been with you.\r\n\r\n412\r\n00:27:08,741 --> 00:27:10,936\r\nAnyway, he looks\r\nlike a Doc, doesn't he?\r\n\r\n413\r\n00:27:11,143 --> 00:27:13,805\r\n<font color=\"#ff00ff\">[IMITATES BUGS BUNNY]</font>\r\nEh, what's up, Doc?\r\n\r\n414\r\n00:27:15,648 --> 00:27:17,843\r\nNow, this is the storeroom.\r\n\r\n415\r\n00:27:19,585 --> 00:27:21,416\r\nIn here is where we keep...\r\n\r\n416\r\n00:27:21,620 --> 00:27:24,418\r\n...all the dried goods\r\nand the canned goods.\r\n\r\n417\r\n00:27:24,623 --> 00:27:27,057\r\nWe got canned fruits\r\nand vegetables...\r\n\r\n418\r\n00:27:27,259 --> 00:27:31,059\r\n...canned fish and meats,\r\nhot and cold cereals.\r\n\r\n419\r\n00:27:31,263 --> 00:27:34,460\r\nPost Toasties, Corn Flakes,\r\nSugar Puffs...\r\n\r\n420\r\n00:27:34,667 --> 00:27:38,694\r\n...Rice Krispies, oatmeal,\r\nWheatena and Cream of Wheat.\r\n\r\n421\r\n00:27:38,937 --> 00:27:41,371\r\nYou got a dozen jugs\r\nof black molasses.\r\n\r\n422\r\n00:27:41,573 --> 00:27:44,770\r\nWe got 60 boxes of dried milk....\r\n\r\n423\r\n00:27:48,414 --> 00:27:50,006\r\n<font color=\"#ff00ff\">[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]</font>\r\n\r\n424\r\n00:27:52,418 --> 00:27:54,886\r\n<font color=\"#FF55M1\">DICK'S VOICE:</font>\r\n<i>How'd you like some ice cream, Doc?</i>\r\n\r\n425\r\n00:27:57,289 --> 00:27:59,280\r\n<font color=\"#FF55M1\">DICK:</font>\r\nSociables, finger rolls...\r\n\r\n426\r\n00:27:59,491 --> 00:28:01,015\r\n...and 7 kinds of what have you.\r\n\r\n427\r\n00:28:01,226 --> 00:28:04,753\r\nNow, we've got dried peaches,\r\ndried apricots...\r\n\r\n428\r\n00:28:04,963 --> 00:28:07,857\r\n...dried raisins and dried prunes.\r\n\r\n429\r\n00:28:07,857 --> 00:28:12,567\r\nYou know, you got to keep regular\r\nif you want to be happy.\r\n\r\n430\r\n00:28:14,106 --> 00:28:15,474\r\n- Hi.\r\n<font color=\"#FF55M1\">- WENDY:</font> Hi.\r\n\r\n431\r\n00:28:15,474 --> 00:28:17,101\r\n- How're you getting on?\r\n- Just fine.\r\n\r\n432\r\n00:28:17,309 --> 00:28:20,870\r\nCan we borrow Mrs. Torrance?\r\nWe're on our way to the basement.\r\n\r\n433\r\n00:28:21,080 --> 00:28:23,014\r\nI promise we won't\r\nkeep her very long.\r\n\r\n434\r\n00:28:23,215 --> 00:28:26,412\r\nNo problem, Mr. Ullman. I was just\r\ngetting to the ice cream.\r\n\r\n435\r\n00:28:26,618 --> 00:28:29,143\r\n- You like ice cream, Doc?\r\n- Yeah.\r\n\r\n436\r\n00:28:29,321 --> 00:28:30,310\r\nI thought you did.\r\n\r\n437\r\n00:28:30,522 --> 00:28:33,582\r\nYou folks mind if I give Danny\r\nsome ice cream while we wait?\r\n\r\n438\r\n00:28:33,792 --> 00:28:35,623\r\n- Not at all.\r\n- We don't mind.\r\n\r\n439\r\n00:28:35,828 --> 00:28:37,489\r\n- Good.\r\n- Sound good to you, Doc?\r\n\r\n440\r\n00:28:37,663 --> 00:28:40,291\r\n<font color=\"#FF55M1\">- DANNY:</font> Yeah.\r\n- Okay, you behave yourself.\r\n\r\n441\r\n00:28:43,302 --> 00:28:45,167\r\nWhat kind of ice cream do you like?\r\n\r\n442\r\n00:28:45,371 --> 00:28:46,395\r\nChocolate.\r\n\r\n443\r\n00:28:46,572 --> 00:28:49,439\r\nChocolate it shall be.\r\nCome on, son.\r\n\r\n444\r\n00:28:54,012 --> 00:28:56,003\r\nIt's amazing, all this activity today.\r\n\r\n445\r\n00:28:56,215 --> 00:28:59,013\r\nThe guests and some staff\r\nleft yesterday, but the...\r\n\r\n446\r\n00:28:59,218 --> 00:29:00,851\r\n...last day's always hectic.\r\n\r\n447\r\n00:29:00,853 --> 00:29:03,913\r\nEverybody wants to be on their way\r\nas early as possible.\r\n\r\n448\r\n00:29:04,123 --> 00:29:08,150\r\nBy 5:00 tonight, you'll never\r\nknow anybody was ever here.\r\n\r\n449\r\n00:29:08,360 --> 00:29:10,419\r\n<font color=\"#FF55M1\">- WENDY:</font> Just like a ghost ship, huh?\r\n- Yes.\r\n\r\n450\r\n00:29:16,101 --> 00:29:19,070\r\nDo you know how I knew\r\nyour name was Doc?\r\n\r\n451\r\n00:29:25,644 --> 00:29:28,044\r\nYou know what I'm talking about,\r\ndon't you?\r\n\r\n452\r\n00:29:35,020 --> 00:29:38,512\r\nI can remember when I was\r\na little boy...\r\n\r\n453\r\n00:29:38,924 --> 00:29:41,660\r\n...my grandmother and I\r\ncould hold conversations...\r\n\r\n454\r\n00:29:41,660 --> 00:29:45,494\r\n...entirely without ever\r\nopening our mouths.\r\n\r\n455\r\n00:29:46,565 --> 00:29:48,863\r\nShe called it \"shining.\"\r\n\r\n456\r\n00:29:50,369 --> 00:29:53,305\r\nAnd for a long time I thought\r\nit was just the two of us...\r\n\r\n457\r\n00:29:53,305 --> 00:29:55,933\r\n...that had \"the shine\" to us.\r\n\r\n458\r\n00:29:56,542 --> 00:29:59,534\r\nJust like you probably thought\r\nyou was the only one.\r\n\r\n459\r\n00:30:00,212 --> 00:30:02,077\r\nBut there are other folks...\r\n\r\n460\r\n00:30:02,281 --> 00:30:06,012\r\n...though mostly they don't\r\nknow it, or don't believe it.\r\n\r\n461\r\n00:30:10,689 --> 00:30:13,123\r\nHow long have you\r\nbeen able to do it?\r\n\r\n462\r\n00:30:18,330 --> 00:30:20,730\r\nWhy don't you want to talk about it?\r\n\r\n463\r\n00:30:25,971 --> 00:30:28,030\r\nI'm not supposed to.\r\n\r\n464\r\n00:30:29,608 --> 00:30:32,133\r\nWho says you ain't supposed to?\r\n\r\n465\r\n00:30:35,581 --> 00:30:36,980\r\nTony.\r\n\r\n466\r\n00:30:38,951 --> 00:30:40,612\r\nWho's Tony?\r\n\r\n467\r\n00:30:43,088 --> 00:30:46,489\r\nTony's the little boy\r\nthat lives in my mouth.\r\n\r\n468\r\n00:30:48,427 --> 00:30:50,452\r\nIs Tony the one that...\r\n\r\n469\r\n00:30:50,662 --> 00:30:52,220\r\n...tells you things?\r\n\r\n470\r\n00:30:53,765 --> 00:30:55,357\r\nYes.\r\n\r\n471\r\n00:30:56,768 --> 00:30:59,134\r\nHow does he tell you things?\r\n\r\n472\r\n00:31:00,973 --> 00:31:05,273\r\nIt's like I go to sleep,\r\nand he shows me things.\r\n\r\n473\r\n00:31:05,477 --> 00:31:09,573\r\nBut when I wake up,\r\nI can't remember everything.\r\n\r\n474\r\n00:31:11,416 --> 00:31:15,113\r\nDoes your mom and dad\r\nknow about Tony?\r\n\r\n475\r\n00:31:16,388 --> 00:31:17,616\r\nYes.\r\n\r\n476\r\n00:31:18,423 --> 00:31:20,983\r\nDo they know he tells you things?\r\n\r\n477\r\n00:31:21,860 --> 00:31:24,795\r\nTony told me never to tell them.\r\n\r\n478\r\n00:31:26,932 --> 00:31:30,299\r\nHas Tony ever told you\r\nanything about this place?\r\n\r\n479\r\n00:31:30,502 --> 00:31:33,062\r\nAbout the Overlook Hotel?\r\n\r\n480\r\n00:31:36,341 --> 00:31:37,899\r\nI don't know.\r\n\r\n481\r\n00:31:38,810 --> 00:31:41,176\r\nNow think real hard, Doc.\r\n\r\n482\r\n00:31:41,346 --> 00:31:42,836\r\nThink.\r\n\r\n483\r\n00:31:45,951 --> 00:31:48,681\r\nMaybe he showed me something.\r\n\r\n484\r\n00:31:49,621 --> 00:31:52,249\r\nTry to think of what it was.\r\n\r\n485\r\n00:31:55,260 --> 00:31:58,559\r\nMr. Hallorann, are you scared\r\nof this place?\r\n\r\n486\r\n00:32:00,065 --> 00:32:01,498\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n487\r\n00:32:01,667 --> 00:32:03,897\r\nScared of nothing here.\r\n\r\n488\r\n00:32:04,369 --> 00:32:05,859\r\nIt's just that...\r\n\r\n489\r\n00:32:06,605 --> 00:32:09,438\r\n...you know, some places\r\nare like people.\r\n\r\n490\r\n00:32:10,275 --> 00:32:11,970\r\nSome shine...\r\n\r\n491\r\n00:32:12,177 --> 00:32:13,576\r\n...and some don't.\r\n\r\n492\r\n00:32:14,813 --> 00:32:16,940\r\nI guess you could say\r\nthe Overlook Hotel...\r\n\r\n493\r\n00:32:17,149 --> 00:32:20,448\r\n...has something about it\r\nthat's like shining.\r\n\r\n494\r\n00:32:23,488 --> 00:32:25,888\r\nIs there something bad here?\r\n\r\n495\r\n00:32:33,966 --> 00:32:35,593\r\nWell...\r\n\r\n496\r\n00:32:37,502 --> 00:32:39,936\r\n...you know, Doc,\r\nwhen something happens...\r\n\r\n497\r\n00:32:39,938 --> 00:32:43,767\r\n...it can leave a trace\r\nof itself behind.\r\n\r\n498\r\n00:32:44,543 --> 00:32:46,101\r\nSay, like...\r\n\r\n499\r\n00:32:46,311 --> 00:32:49,371\r\n...if someone burns toast.\r\n\r\n500\r\n00:32:50,082 --> 00:32:51,310\r\nWell....\r\n\r\n501\r\n00:32:51,483 --> 00:32:56,147\r\nMaybe things that happen\r\nleave other kind of traces behind.\r\n\r\n502\r\n00:32:57,322 --> 00:33:00,758\r\nNot things that anyone can notice.\r\n\r\n503\r\n00:33:00,959 --> 00:33:05,760\r\nBut things that people\r\nwho shine can see.\r\n\r\n504\r\n00:33:06,865 --> 00:33:10,164\r\nJust like they can see things\r\nthat haven't happened yet...\r\n\r\n505\r\n00:33:10,502 --> 00:33:11,992\r\n...well...\r\n\r\n506\r\n00:33:12,437 --> 00:33:16,601\r\n...sometimes they can see things\r\nthat happened a long time ago.\r\n\r\n507\r\n00:33:18,143 --> 00:33:21,010\r\nI think a lot of things\r\nhappened right here...\r\n\r\n508\r\n00:33:21,213 --> 00:33:24,910\r\n...in this particular hotel\r\nover the years.\r\n\r\n509\r\n00:33:25,450 --> 00:33:27,850\r\nAnd not all of them was good.\r\n\r\n510\r\n00:33:31,156 --> 00:33:33,784\r\nWhat about room 237?\r\n\r\n511\r\n00:33:37,129 --> 00:33:39,324\r\nRoom 237?\r\n\r\n512\r\n00:33:40,632 --> 00:33:43,726\r\nYou're scared of room 237, ain't you?\r\n\r\n513\r\n00:33:45,504 --> 00:33:46,971\r\nNo, I ain't.\r\n\r\n514\r\n00:33:48,473 --> 00:33:52,307\r\nMr. Hallorann, what is in room 237?\r\n\r\n515\r\n00:33:53,645 --> 00:33:55,010\r\nNothing.\r\n\r\n516\r\n00:33:55,447 --> 00:33:58,678\r\nThere ain't nothing in room 237.\r\n\r\n517\r\n00:33:58,884 --> 00:34:02,115\r\nBut you ain't got no business\r\ngoing in there anyway.\r\n\r\n518\r\n00:34:02,320 --> 00:34:04,447\r\nSo stay out.\r\n\r\n519\r\n00:34:04,656 --> 00:34:07,147\r\nYou understand? Stay out!\r\n\r\n520\r\n00:34:12,998 --> 00:34:15,023\r\n<font color=\"#ff00ff\">[WOLF HOWLS]</font>\r\n\r\n521\r\n00:35:31,209 --> 00:35:32,642\r\n<font color=\"#ff00ff\">[KNOCKING]</font>\r\n\r\n522\r\n00:35:46,691 --> 00:35:48,420\r\nGood morning, hon.\r\n\r\n523\r\n00:35:50,428 --> 00:35:52,191\r\nYour breakfast is ready.\r\n\r\n524\r\n00:35:52,964 --> 00:35:54,591\r\nWhat time is it?\r\n\r\n525\r\n00:35:54,800 --> 00:35:56,665\r\nIt's about 11:30.\r\n\r\n526\r\n00:35:57,102 --> 00:36:00,162\r\nEleven-thirty, Jesus.\r\n\r\n527\r\n00:36:01,106 --> 00:36:03,540\r\nI guess we've been\r\nstaying up too late.\r\n\r\n528\r\n00:36:03,842 --> 00:36:05,275\r\nI know it.\r\n\r\n529\r\n00:36:06,578 --> 00:36:09,445\r\nI made them just the way\r\nyou like them, sunny-side up.\r\n\r\n530\r\n00:36:09,748 --> 00:36:11,306\r\nNice.\r\n\r\n531\r\n00:36:13,585 --> 00:36:15,382\r\nIt's really pretty outside.\r\n\r\n532\r\n00:36:15,587 --> 00:36:18,818\r\nHow about taking me for a walk\r\nafter you finish your breakfast?\r\n\r\n533\r\n00:36:19,424 --> 00:36:23,758\r\nI suppose I ought to try\r\nto do some writing first.\r\n\r\n534\r\n00:36:25,197 --> 00:36:26,858\r\nAny ideas yet?\r\n\r\n535\r\n00:36:27,866 --> 00:36:29,527\r\nLots of ideas.\r\n\r\n536\r\n00:36:29,734 --> 00:36:31,258\r\nNo good ones.\r\n\r\n537\r\n00:36:31,736 --> 00:36:34,204\r\nSomething will come.\r\n\r\n538\r\n00:36:34,706 --> 00:36:38,642\r\nIt's just a matter of settling into\r\nthe habit of writing every day.\r\n\r\n539\r\n00:36:39,244 --> 00:36:41,906\r\nYep. That's all it is.\r\n\r\n540\r\n00:36:44,015 --> 00:36:46,313\r\nIt's really nice up here, Isn it?\r\n\r\n541\r\n00:36:46,718 --> 00:36:48,151\r\nI love it.\r\n\r\n542\r\n00:36:48,653 --> 00:36:50,245\r\nI really do.\r\n\r\n543\r\n00:36:51,156 --> 00:36:54,182\r\nI've never been this happy\r\nor comfortable anywhere.\r\n\r\n544\r\n00:36:54,392 --> 00:36:58,158\r\nIt's amazing how fast you get\r\nused to such a big place.\r\n\r\n545\r\n00:36:58,363 --> 00:37:01,264\r\nI tell you, when we first\r\ncame up here...\r\n\r\n546\r\n00:37:01,264 --> 00:37:03,525\r\n...I thought it was kind of scary.\r\n\r\n547\r\n00:37:03,969 --> 00:37:06,529\r\nI fell in love with it right away.\r\n\r\n548\r\n00:37:07,205 --> 00:37:10,003\r\nWhen I came up here\r\nfor my interview...\r\n\r\n549\r\n00:37:10,375 --> 00:37:14,209\r\n...it was as though\r\nI'd been here before.\r\n\r\n550\r\n00:37:14,412 --> 00:37:17,040\r\nI mean, we all have moments\r\nof deja vu...\r\n\r\n551\r\n00:37:17,249 --> 00:37:19,444\r\n...but this was ridiculous.\r\n\r\n552\r\n00:37:20,185 --> 00:37:22,050\r\nIt was almost as though I knew...\r\n\r\n553\r\n00:37:22,254 --> 00:37:25,712\r\n...what was going to be\r\naround every corner.\r\n\r\n554\r\n00:37:25,891 --> 00:37:28,519\r\nOoh-woo-ooh.\r\n\r\n555\r\n00:37:29,961 --> 00:37:32,088\r\n<font color=\"#ff00ff\">[THUDDING]</font>\r\n\r\n556\r\n00:37:59,124 --> 00:38:02,321\r\nThe loser has to keep\r\nAmerica clean. How's that?\r\n\r\n557\r\n00:38:02,527 --> 00:38:05,087\r\n- All right.\r\n- And you're going to lose.\r\n\r\n558\r\n00:38:05,297 --> 00:38:08,425\r\nAnd I'm going to get you.\r\nYou'd better run fast!\r\n\r\n559\r\n00:38:08,600 --> 00:38:11,364\r\n<font color=\"#ff00ff\">[WENDY HUMS]</font>\r\n\r\n560\r\n00:38:13,438 --> 00:38:14,564\r\nLook out!\r\n\r\n561\r\n00:38:14,773 --> 00:38:16,638\r\nI'm coming in close.\r\n\r\n562\r\n00:38:16,841 --> 00:38:19,071\r\n<font color=\"#FF55M1\">DANNY:</font>\r\nLoser has to keep America clean.\r\n\r\n563\r\n00:38:19,244 --> 00:38:21,212\r\n<font color=\"#FF55M1\">- WENDY:</font> Oh, no!\r\n<font color=\"#FF55M1\">- DANNY:</font> Keep America clean.\r\n\r\n564\r\n00:38:21,379 --> 00:38:23,677\r\nOkay. Danny, you win.\r\n\r\n565\r\n00:38:24,015 --> 00:38:26,347\r\nLet's take the rest of this walking.\r\n\r\n566\r\n00:38:26,518 --> 00:38:28,543\r\n- Okay.\r\n- Whew.\r\n\r\n567\r\n00:38:28,887 --> 00:38:30,286\r\nGive me your hand.\r\n\r\n568\r\n00:38:32,924 --> 00:38:34,721\r\nIsn it beautiful?\r\n\r\n569\r\n00:38:34,960 --> 00:38:35,949\r\nYeah.\r\n\r\n570\r\n00:38:52,477 --> 00:38:53,842\r\n<font color=\"#FF55M1\">DANNY:</font>\r\nDead end.\r\n\r\n571\r\n00:39:50,802 --> 00:39:52,929\r\n<font color=\"#FF55M1\">WENDY:</font>\r\nWoo, we made it.\r\n\r\n572\r\n00:39:53,438 --> 00:39:55,736\r\n- Isn it beautiful?\r\n<font color=\"#FF55M1\">- DANNY:</font> Yeah.\r\n\r\n573\r\n00:40:16,361 --> 00:40:18,192\r\nIt's so pretty.\r\n\r\n574\r\n00:40:18,530 --> 00:40:19,963\r\nYeah.\r\n\r\n575\r\n00:40:22,767 --> 00:40:25,497\r\nI didn't think it was\r\ngoing to be this big. Did you?\r\n\r\n576\r\n00:40:25,670 --> 00:40:26,932\r\nNope.\r\n\r\n577\r\n00:40:37,015 --> 00:40:38,615\r\n<font color=\"#FF55M1\">WOMAN</font> <font color=\"#ff00ff\">[ON TV]:</font>\r\n<i>Rutherford was serving a life sentence...</i>\r\n\r\n578\r\n00:40:38,615 --> 00:40:41,380\r\n<i>...for a disfection 1968 shooting.</i>\r\n\r\n579\r\n00:40:41,586 --> 00:40:45,454\r\n<i>And the search continues\r\nfor that missing Aspen woman.</i>\r\n\r\n580\r\n00:40:45,657 --> 00:40:49,024\r\n<i>Twenty-four-year-old Susan Robertson\r\nhas been missing 10 days.</i>\r\n\r\n581\r\n00:40:49,227 --> 00:40:51,957\r\n<i>She disappeared on a hunting trip\r\nwith her husband.</i>\r\n\r\n582\r\n00:40:52,163 --> 00:40:54,961\r\n<i>They may have to\r\ncall off the search...</i>\r\n\r\n583\r\n00:40:54,966 --> 00:40:57,691\r\n<i>...if a predicted snowstorm\r\nmoves in tomorrow.</i>\r\n\r\n584\r\n00:40:57,691 --> 00:40:59,767\r\n<i>It's so beautiful\r\nin Denver today...</i>\r\n\r\n585\r\n00:40:59,971 --> 00:41:02,098\r\n<i>...it's hard to believe\r\na snowstorm could be close.</i>\r\n\r\n586\r\n00:41:02,307 --> 00:41:04,537\r\n<i>I want to go outside\r\nand lie in the sun...</i>\r\n\r\n587\r\n00:41:04,742 --> 00:41:08,872\r\n<i>...yet to our north, to our west,\r\nit is snowing and cold.</i>\r\n\r\n588\r\n00:41:08,880 --> 00:41:10,274\r\n<i>And it's moving...</i>\r\n\r\n589\r\n00:41:10,482 --> 00:41:13,645\r\n<i>...right here towards Colorado\r\nas we talk. It's incredible.</i>\r\n\r\n590\r\n00:43:03,995 --> 00:43:05,986\r\n<font color=\"#ff00ff\">[TYPEWRITER KEYS CLACKING]</font>\r\n\r\n591\r\n00:43:42,267 --> 00:43:43,700\r\nHi, hon.\r\n\r\n592\r\n00:43:47,305 --> 00:43:48,704\r\nHow's it going?\r\n\r\n593\r\n00:43:51,276 --> 00:43:52,436\r\nFine.\r\n\r\n594\r\n00:43:54,545 --> 00:43:56,103\r\nGet a lot written today?\r\n\r\n595\r\n00:43:58,416 --> 00:44:00,008\r\nYes.\r\n\r\n596\r\n00:44:01,986 --> 00:44:05,717\r\nHey, the weather forecast\r\nsaid it's going to snow tonight.\r\n\r\n597\r\n00:44:10,928 --> 00:44:13,260\r\nWhat do you want me to do about it?\r\n\r\n598\r\n00:44:15,433 --> 00:44:17,594\r\nCome on, hon.\r\n\r\n599\r\n00:44:17,935 --> 00:44:19,960\r\nDon't be so grouchy.\r\n\r\n600\r\n00:44:20,371 --> 00:44:21,702\r\nI'm not...\r\n\r\n601\r\n00:44:22,073 --> 00:44:23,267\r\n...being grouchy.\r\n\r\n602\r\n00:44:23,474 --> 00:44:26,272\r\nI just want to finish my work.\r\n\r\n603\r\n00:44:29,781 --> 00:44:32,181\r\nOkay. I understand.\r\n\r\n604\r\n00:44:32,417 --> 00:44:35,011\r\nI'll come back later with a\r\ncouple of sandwiches for you.\r\n\r\n605\r\n00:44:35,219 --> 00:44:37,687\r\nMaybe you'll let me\r\nread something then.\r\n\r\n606\r\n00:44:40,892 --> 00:44:41,984\r\nWendy...\r\n\r\n607\r\n00:44:42,193 --> 00:44:44,787\r\n...let me explain something to you.\r\n\r\n608\r\n00:44:45,697 --> 00:44:49,767\r\nWhen you come in and interrupt,\r\nyou're breaking my concentration.\r\n\r\n609\r\n00:44:49,767 --> 00:44:51,200\r\nYou're distracting me...\r\n\r\n610\r\n00:44:51,402 --> 00:44:54,838\r\n...and it will then take me time\r\nto get back to where I was.\r\n\r\n611\r\n00:44:55,039 --> 00:44:56,472\r\nUnderstand?\r\n\r\n612\r\n00:44:58,276 --> 00:44:59,470\r\nYeah.\r\n\r\n613\r\n00:44:59,944 --> 00:45:01,104\r\nFine.\r\n\r\n614\r\n00:45:02,280 --> 00:45:04,009\r\nWe're going to make a new rule:\r\n\r\n615\r\n00:45:04,215 --> 00:45:05,648\r\nWhenever I'm in here...\r\n\r\n616\r\n00:45:05,850 --> 00:45:07,408\r\n...and you hear me typing...\r\n\r\n617\r\n00:45:07,585 --> 00:45:09,075\r\n<font color=\"#ff00ff\">[PUNCHES KEYS]</font>\r\n\r\n618\r\n00:45:09,921 --> 00:45:12,856\r\n...or whatever the fuck\r\nyou hear me doing in here...\r\n\r\n619\r\n00:45:13,057 --> 00:45:15,355\r\n...when I'm in here,\r\nthat means I am working.\r\n\r\n620\r\n00:45:15,560 --> 00:45:17,790\r\nThat means don't come in.\r\n\r\n621\r\n00:45:17,995 --> 00:45:20,259\r\nNow, do you think\r\nyou can h