re...?\r\n\r\n1517\r\n02:17:55,333 --> 02:17:57,324\r\n<font color=\"#ff00ff\">[GROANING]</font>\r\n\r\n1518\r\n02:17:58,336 --> 02:18:00,099\r\n<font color=\"#ff00ff\">[SNOWCAT ENGINE SPUTTERING]</font>\r\n\r\n1519\r\n02:18:07,845 --> 02:18:09,574\r\n<font color=\"#ff00ff\">[ENGINE ROARS]</font>\r\n\r\n1520\r\n02:18:21,826 --> 02:18:24,454\r\n<font color=\"#ff00ff\">[YELLING INCOHERENTLY]</font>\r\n\r\n1521\r\n02:19:43,541 --> 02:19:46,533\r\n<font color=\"#ff00ff\">[BALLROOM MUSIC PLAYING]</font>\r\n\r\n1522\r\n02:23:41,879 --> 02:23:43,870\r\n<font color=\"#ff00ff\">[ENGLISH SDH]</font>\r\n\r\n<!-- Eng. Sub2Srt: PgDn 2008/07/04 -->","markerStore":{"nextMarkerId":142,"markersById":{"0":{"range":{"start":{"row":390,"column":0},"end":{"row":390,"column":7}},"properties":{"type":"selection","editorId":144,"goalScreenRange":null},"reversed":false,"tailed":true,"valid":true,"invalidate":"never","maintainHistory":true}},"version":2},"history":{"version":3,"nextCheckpointId":1,"undoStack":[],"redoStack":[]},"encoding":"utf8","filePath":"/Users/joegesualdo/code/node/modules/subtitle-hero/srt/The Shining (1980) 23.976 fps - 143.45 min version-must do half sec delayed-Hi.srt","digestWhenLastPersisted":"0ccfa30f5b55b9e214cfd9074032fc045ed7710e","preferredLineEnding":null,"deserializer":"TextBuffer","version":2},{"load":true,"text":"﻿1\r\n00:03:12,570 --> 00:03:14,936\r\nHi. I've got an appointment\r\nwith Mr. Ullman.\r\n\r\n2\r\n00:03:15,139 --> 00:03:17,073\r\nMy name is Jack Torrance.\r\n\r\n3\r\n00:03:17,274 --> 00:03:19,799\r\nHis office is the first door\r\non the left.\r\n\r\n4\r\n00:03:20,010 --> 00:03:21,238\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\n5\r\n00:03:38,596 --> 00:03:39,460\r\nMr. Ullman?\r\n\r\n6\r\n00:03:39,663 --> 00:03:40,925\r\nI'm Jack Torrance.\r\n\r\n7\r\n00:03:41,132 --> 00:03:43,100\r\nCome on in, Jack.\r\n\r\n8\r\n00:03:44,201 --> 00:03:46,726\r\n-Very nice to meet you.\r\n-Nice to meet you.\r\n\r\n9\r\n00:03:46,937 --> 00:03:48,461\r\nThis is my secretary, Susie.\r\n\r\n10\r\n00:03:48,873 --> 00:03:51,364\r\n-Susie, how do you do?\r\n-Any trouble finding us?\r\n\r\n11\r\n00:03:51,575 --> 00:03:54,408\r\nNo problem at all.\r\nI made the trip in 3 1/2 hours.\r\n\r\n12\r\n00:03:54,612 --> 00:03:56,512\r\nThat's very good time.\r\n\r\n13\r\n00:03:56,847 --> 00:03:58,439\r\nSit down a minute, Jack.\r\n\r\n14\r\n00:03:58,682 --> 00:04:00,445\r\nJust make yourself at home.\r\n\r\n15\r\n00:04:00,651 --> 00:04:01,913\r\nLike some coffee?\r\n\r\n16\r\n00:04:02,119 --> 00:04:04,610\r\nIf you're having some,\r\nI wouldn't mind. Thanks.\r\n\r\n17\r\n00:04:04,822 --> 00:04:05,811\r\n-Susie.\r\n-Sure.\r\n\r\n18\r\n00:04:06,023 --> 00:04:07,752\r\nAnd ask Bill Watson to join us.\r\n\r\n19\r\n00:04:07,958 --> 00:04:09,391\r\nYes, I will.\r\n\r\n20\r\n00:04:20,271 --> 00:04:21,397\r\nMom?\r\n\r\n21\r\n00:04:22,273 --> 00:04:23,433\r\nYeah?\r\n\r\n22\r\n00:04:23,841 --> 00:04:27,470\r\nDo you really want to go and live\r\nin that hotel for the winter?\r\n\r\n23\r\n00:04:28,078 --> 00:04:29,443\r\nSure I do.\r\n\r\n24\r\n00:04:29,647 --> 00:04:31,581\r\nIt'll be lots of fun.\r\n\r\n25\r\n00:04:33,450 --> 00:04:35,543\r\nYeah. I guess so.\r\n\r\n26\r\n00:04:35,753 --> 00:04:39,917\r\nAnyway, there's hardly anybody\r\nto play with around here.\r\n\r\n27\r\n00:04:40,724 --> 00:04:44,353\r\nI know. It always takes\r\na little time to make new friends.\r\n\r\n28\r\n00:04:45,830 --> 00:04:48,128\r\nYeah, I guess so.\r\n\r\n29\r\n00:04:48,899 --> 00:04:49,923\r\nWhat about Tony?\r\n\r\n30\r\n00:04:50,134 --> 00:04:52,534\r\nHe's looking forward\r\nto the hotel, I bet.\r\n\r\n31\r\n00:04:53,070 --> 00:04:55,436\r\nNo, I ain't, Mrs. Torrance.\r\n\r\n32\r\n00:04:55,840 --> 00:04:58,274\r\nNow, come on, Tony.\r\nDon't be silly.\r\n\r\n33\r\n00:04:58,676 --> 00:05:00,667\r\nI don't want to go there.\r\n\r\n34\r\n00:05:01,145 --> 00:05:03,170\r\nHow come you don't want to go?\r\n\r\n35\r\n00:05:03,414 --> 00:05:05,507\r\nI just don't.\r\n\r\n36\r\n00:05:06,116 --> 00:05:08,516\r\nLet's just wait and see.\r\n\r\n37\r\n00:05:08,786 --> 00:05:11,482\r\nWe're all going to have\r\na real good time.\r\n\r\n38\r\n00:05:12,857 --> 00:05:15,325\r\nBill, I'd like you\r\nto meet Jack Torrance.\r\n\r\n39\r\n00:05:15,526 --> 00:05:16,959\r\nHow do you do, Bill?\r\n\r\n40\r\n00:05:17,161 --> 00:05:19,129\r\n-Nice to meet you.\r\n-Pleasure to meet you.\r\n\r\n41\r\n00:05:19,330 --> 00:05:21,264\r\nGrab a chair, Bill. Join in.\r\n\r\n42\r\n00:05:21,465 --> 00:05:25,595\r\nJack is going to take care of\r\nthe Overlook for us this winter.\r\n\r\n43\r\n00:05:25,836 --> 00:05:28,805\r\nI'd like you to take him around\r\nsoon as we're through.\r\n\r\n44\r\n00:05:29,006 --> 00:05:29,938\r\nFine.\r\n\r\n45\r\n00:05:30,574 --> 00:05:32,474\r\nJack is a schoolteacher.\r\n\r\n46\r\n00:05:32,743 --> 00:05:34,711\r\nFormerly a schoolteacher.\r\n\r\n47\r\n00:05:34,912 --> 00:05:36,607\r\nWhat line of work are you in now?\r\n\r\n48\r\n00:05:36,814 --> 00:05:38,406\r\nI'm a writer.\r\n\r\n49\r\n00:05:38,649 --> 00:05:42,278\r\nTeaching's been more or less\r\na way of making ends meet.\r\n\r\n50\r\n00:05:42,486 --> 00:05:44,454\r\nThis ought to be\r\nquite a change for you.\r\n\r\n51\r\n00:05:45,389 --> 00:05:47,186\r\nI'm looking for a change.\r\n\r\n52\r\n00:05:47,391 --> 00:05:50,986\r\nOur people in Denver recommended\r\nJack very highly, and for once...\r\n\r\n53\r\n00:05:51,195 --> 00:05:52,787\r\n...I agree with them.\r\n\r\n54\r\n00:05:53,430 --> 00:05:55,227\r\nLet's see, where were we?\r\n\r\n55\r\n00:05:55,432 --> 00:05:58,026\r\nI was about to explain...\r\n\r\n56\r\n00:05:58,269 --> 00:06:02,433\r\n...that our season here runs from\r\nMay 15th to October 30th.\r\n\r\n57\r\n00:06:02,640 --> 00:06:06,098\r\nThen we close down completely\r\nuntil the following May.\r\n\r\n58\r\n00:06:06,310 --> 00:06:09,108\r\nDo you mind if I ask\r\nwhy you do that?\r\n\r\n59\r\n00:06:09,313 --> 00:06:12,771\r\nIt seems to me that the skiing\r\nup here would be fantastic.\r\n\r\n60\r\n00:06:12,983 --> 00:06:15,577\r\nIt would be. The problem is\r\nthe enormous cost...\r\n\r\n61\r\n00:06:15,786 --> 00:06:18,346\r\n...it would be to keep\r\nthe road to Sidewinder open.\r\n\r\n62\r\n00:06:18,989 --> 00:06:20,718\r\nIt's a 25-mile stretch of road.\r\n\r\n63\r\n00:06:20,925 --> 00:06:23,291\r\nIt gets 20 feet of snow\r\nduring the winter.\r\n\r\n64\r\n00:06:23,494 --> 00:06:26,725\r\nThere's just no way to make it\r\neconomically feasible...\r\n\r\n65\r\n00:06:26,931 --> 00:06:28,865\r\n...to keep it clear.\r\n\r\n66\r\n00:06:29,066 --> 00:06:31,432\r\nWhen the place was built in 1907...\r\n\r\n67\r\n00:06:31,635 --> 00:06:34,195\r\n...there was very little interest\r\nin winter sports.\r\n\r\n68\r\n00:06:34,405 --> 00:06:39,274\r\nThis site was chosen for its\r\nseclusion and scenic beauty.\r\n\r\n69\r\n00:06:39,510 --> 00:06:42,035\r\nIt's certainly got\r\nplenty of that.\r\n\r\n70\r\n00:06:42,246 --> 00:06:43,440\r\nThat's right.\r\n\r\n71\r\n00:06:44,148 --> 00:06:46,981\r\nDid they give you\r\nany idea in Denver...\r\n\r\n72\r\n00:06:47,184 --> 00:06:48,845\r\n...about what the job entails?\r\n\r\n73\r\n00:06:49,053 --> 00:06:51,146\r\nOnly in a very general way.\r\n\r\n74\r\n00:06:53,624 --> 00:06:56,218\r\nThe winters can be\r\nfantastically cruel.\r\n\r\n75\r\n00:06:56,427 --> 00:06:59,885\r\nThe basic idea is to cope\r\nwith the very costly damage...\r\n\r\n76\r\n00:07:00,097 --> 00:07:02,088\r\n...and depreciation\r\nwhich can occur.\r\n\r\n77\r\n00:07:02,299 --> 00:07:04,733\r\nThis consists mainly\r\nof running the boiler...\r\n\r\n78\r\n00:07:04,935 --> 00:07:08,894\r\n...heating different parts of the\r\nhotel on a daily rotating basis...\r\n\r\n79\r\n00:07:09,106 --> 00:07:11,802\r\n...repairing damage as it occurs...\r\n\r\n80\r\n00:07:12,009 --> 00:07:14,842\r\n...and doing repairs so the\r\nelements can't get a foothold.\r\n\r\n81\r\n00:07:15,913 --> 00:07:18,143\r\nThat sounds fine to me.\r\n\r\n82\r\n00:07:18,549 --> 00:07:21,518\r\nPhysically, it's not\r\na very demanding job.\r\n\r\n83\r\n00:07:21,719 --> 00:07:24,882\r\nThe only thing that can get a bit\r\ntrying here during the winter...\r\n\r\n84\r\n00:07:25,089 --> 00:07:27,717\r\n...is a tremendous sense\r\nof isolation.\r\n\r\n85\r\n00:07:28,859 --> 00:07:33,421\r\nThat just happens to be\r\nexactly what I'm looking for.\r\n\r\n86\r\n00:07:33,764 --> 00:07:36,892\r\nI'm outlining a new\r\nwriting project.\r\n\r\n87\r\n00:07:37,301 --> 00:07:40,600\r\nFive months of peace\r\nis just what I want.\r\n\r\n88\r\n00:07:41,372 --> 00:07:43,101\r\nThat's very good, Jack.\r\n\r\n89\r\n00:07:43,407 --> 00:07:46,570\r\nBecause, for some people...\r\n\r\n90\r\n00:07:46,777 --> 00:07:48,540\r\n...solitude...\r\n\r\n91\r\n00:07:48,746 --> 00:07:50,373\r\n...and isolation...\r\n\r\n92\r\n00:07:51,248 --> 00:07:53,512\r\n...can, of itself, become a problem.\r\n\r\n93\r\n00:07:54,318 --> 00:07:55,910\r\nNot for me.\r\n\r\n94\r\n00:07:56,453 --> 00:07:59,684\r\nHow about your wife and son?\r\nDo you think they'll take to it?\r\n\r\n95\r\n00:08:01,492 --> 00:08:02,652\r\nThey'll love it.\r\n\r\n96\r\n00:08:02,860 --> 00:08:04,054\r\nGreat.\r\n\r\n97\r\n00:08:06,964 --> 00:08:10,195\r\nBefore I turn you over to Bill...\r\n\r\n98\r\n00:08:10,401 --> 00:08:13,893\r\n...there's one other thing I think\r\nwe should talk about.\r\n\r\n99\r\n00:08:14,104 --> 00:08:15,537\r\nNot to sound melodramatic...\r\n\r\n100\r\n00:08:15,739 --> 00:08:18,299\r\n...but it's been known to\r\ngive a few people...\r\n\r\n101\r\n00:08:18,509 --> 00:08:20,704\r\n...second thoughts about the job.\r\n\r\n102\r\n00:08:21,412 --> 00:08:23,073\r\nI'm intrigued.\r\n\r\n103\r\n00:08:23,280 --> 00:08:25,612\r\nI don't suppose they\r\nsaid anything in Denver...\r\n\r\n104\r\n00:08:25,816 --> 00:08:29,775\r\n...about the tragedy we had up here\r\nduring the winter of 1970.\r\n\r\n105\r\n00:08:30,387 --> 00:08:32,378\r\nI don't believe they did.\r\n\r\n106\r\n00:08:34,958 --> 00:08:36,653\r\nMy predecessor in this job...\r\n\r\n107\r\n00:08:37,394 --> 00:08:40,625\r\n...hired a man named Charles Grady\r\nas the winter caretaker.\r\n\r\n108\r\n00:08:40,831 --> 00:08:44,358\r\nHe came up with his wife and\r\n2 little girls of about 8 and 10.\r\n\r\n109\r\n00:08:44,568 --> 00:08:47,560\r\nHe had a good employment record,\r\ngood references.\r\n\r\n110\r\n00:08:47,771 --> 00:08:50,035\r\nAnd from what I've been told,\r\nhe seemed...\r\n\r\n111\r\n00:08:50,240 --> 00:08:52,936\r\n...like a completely\r\nnormal individual.\r\n\r\n112\r\n00:08:53,143 --> 00:08:55,509\r\nBut at some point\r\nduring the winter...\r\n\r\n113\r\n00:08:55,712 --> 00:08:59,341\r\n...he must have suffered some kind\r\nof a complete mental breakdown.\r\n\r\n114\r\n00:08:59,550 --> 00:09:01,916\r\nHe ran amuck...\r\n\r\n115\r\n00:09:05,322 --> 00:09:07,517\r\n...and killed his family\r\nwith an ax.\r\n\r\n116\r\n00:09:08,792 --> 00:09:13,422\r\nStacked them neatly in a room\r\nin the west wing, and then...\r\n\r\n117\r\n00:09:14,231 --> 00:09:17,928\r\n...he put both barrels\r\nof his shotgun in his mouth.\r\n\r\n118\r\n00:09:19,169 --> 00:09:20,966\r\nThe police thought...\r\n\r\n119\r\n00:09:21,171 --> 00:09:25,232\r\n...that it was what the old-timers\r\nused to call cabin fever.\r\n\r\n120\r\n00:09:25,442 --> 00:09:28,468\r\nA kind of claustrophobic reaction\r\nwhich can occur...\r\n\r\n121\r\n00:09:28,679 --> 00:09:32,809\r\n...when people are shut in together\r\nover long periods of time.\r\n\r\n122\r\n00:09:37,888 --> 00:09:39,321\r\nThat is...\r\n\r\n123\r\n00:09:39,523 --> 00:09:41,047\r\n...quite a story.\r\n\r\n124\r\n00:09:42,359 --> 00:09:43,826\r\nYeah, it is.\r\n\r\n125\r\n00:09:44,928 --> 00:09:48,227\r\nIt's still hard for me to believe\r\nit actually happened here.\r\n\r\n126\r\n00:09:48,565 --> 00:09:50,260\r\nBut it did.\r\n\r\n127\r\n00:09:52,035 --> 00:09:56,062\r\nI think you can appreciate\r\nwhy I wanted to tell you about it.\r\n\r\n128\r\n00:09:56,607 --> 00:09:59,098\r\nI certainly can.\r\n\r\n129\r\n00:09:59,610 --> 00:10:02,170\r\nI also understand\r\nwhy your people in Denver...\r\n\r\n130\r\n00:10:02,379 --> 00:10:04,643\r\n...left it for you to tell me.\r\n\r\n131\r\n00:10:05,849 --> 00:10:08,545\r\nObviously, some people\r\ncan be put off...\r\n\r\n132\r\n00:10:08,752 --> 00:10:12,848\r\n...from staying in a place where\r\nsomething like that happened.\r\n\r\n133\r\n00:10:13,056 --> 00:10:17,959\r\nYou can rest assured that's not\r\ngoing to happen with me.\r\n\r\n134\r\n00:10:18,162 --> 00:10:21,825\r\nAnd as far as my wife\r\nis concerned...\r\n\r\n135\r\n00:10:22,032 --> 00:10:25,866\r\n...I'm sure she'll be absolutely\r\nfascinated when I tell her.\r\n\r\n136\r\n00:10:26,069 --> 00:10:28,902\r\nShe's a confirmed ghost story...\r\n\r\n137\r\n00:10:29,106 --> 00:10:31,540\r\n...and horror film addict.\r\n\r\n138\r\n00:10:36,380 --> 00:10:40,077\r\nTony, do you think\r\nDad'll get the job?\r\n\r\n139\r\n00:10:41,485 --> 00:10:43,680\r\nHe already did.\r\n\r\n140\r\n00:10:44,121 --> 00:10:47,852\r\nHe's going to phone Wendy up\r\nin a few minutes to tell her.\r\n\r\n141\r\n00:11:02,573 --> 00:11:05,235\r\n-Hi, babe.\r\n-Hi, hon. How's it going?\r\n\r\n142\r\n00:11:05,442 --> 00:11:09,037\r\nGreat. I'm at the hotel and\r\nI still have a lot to go through.\r\n\r\n143\r\n00:11:09,246 --> 00:11:12,374\r\nI don't think I can get home\r\nbefore 9:00 or 10:00.\r\n\r\n144\r\n00:11:12,583 --> 00:11:14,073\r\nSounds like you got the job.\r\n\r\n145\r\n00:11:14,284 --> 00:11:16,980\r\nRight. It's a beautiful place.\r\n\r\n146\r\n00:11:17,187 --> 00:11:19,314\r\nYou and Danny are going to love it.\r\n\r\n147\r\n00:11:20,791 --> 00:11:23,692\r\nTony, why don't you want to go\r\nto the hotel?\r\n\r\n148\r\n00:11:23,961 --> 00:11:25,690\r\nI don't know.\r\n\r\n149\r\n00:11:26,763 --> 00:11:30,290\r\nYou do too know.\r\nNow come on, tell me.\r\n\r\n150\r\n00:11:30,867 --> 00:11:32,926\r\nI don't want to.\r\n\r\n151\r\n00:11:33,637 --> 00:11:34,899\r\nPlease.\r\n\r\n152\r\n00:11:36,139 --> 00:11:37,265\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n153\r\n00:11:37,574 --> 00:11:39,667\r\nNow, Tony, tell me.\r\n\r\n154\r\n00:12:09,573 --> 00:12:12,303\r\nNow, hold your eyes still\r\nso I can see.\r\n\r\n155\r\n00:12:16,780 --> 00:12:19,010\r\nThat's good. Now the other one.\r\n\r\n156\r\n00:12:20,417 --> 00:12:21,884\r\nGood boy.\r\n\r\n157\r\n00:12:29,226 --> 00:12:30,591\r\nNow, Danny...\r\n\r\n158\r\n00:12:31,061 --> 00:12:33,086\r\n...when you were brushing\r\nyour teeth...\r\n\r\n159\r\n00:12:33,297 --> 00:12:36,289\r\n...do you remember if you\r\nsmelled anything funny...\r\n\r\n160\r\n00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:41,267\r\n...or saw any bright, flashing\r\nlights or anything at all strange?\r\n\r\n161\r\n00:12:44,107 --> 00:12:45,267\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n162\r\n00:12:46,343 --> 00:12:48,834\r\nDo you remember when you were\r\nbrushing your teeth?\r\n\r\n163\r\n00:12:49,413 --> 00:12:50,710\r\nYes.\r\n\r\n164\r\n00:12:51,848 --> 00:12:55,477\r\nWhat's the next thing you remember\r\nafter you were brushing your teeth?\r\n\r\n165\r\n00:12:59,690 --> 00:13:02,318\r\nMy mom was saying, \"Wake up.\r\nWake up, Danny, wake up.\"\r\n\r\n166\r\n00:13:06,530 --> 00:13:08,760\r\nCan you remember\r\nwhat you were doing...\r\n\r\n167\r\n00:13:08,965 --> 00:13:11,900\r\n...just before you started\r\nbrushing your teeth?\r\n\r\n168\r\n00:13:14,404 --> 00:13:16,167\r\nTalking to Tony.\r\n\r\n169\r\n00:13:16,840 --> 00:13:19,206\r\nIs Tony one of your animals?\r\n\r\n170\r\n00:13:20,077 --> 00:13:23,012\r\nNo. He's a little boy\r\nthat lives in my mouth.\r\n\r\n171\r\n00:13:23,313 --> 00:13:25,713\r\nTony's his imaginary friend.\r\n\r\n172\r\n00:13:28,652 --> 00:13:32,053\r\nIf you were to open your mouth now,\r\ncould I see Tony?\r\n\r\n173\r\n00:13:34,725 --> 00:13:35,953\r\nWhy not?\r\n\r\n174\r\n00:13:37,227 --> 00:13:39,058\r\nBecause he hides.\r\n\r\n175\r\n00:13:39,796 --> 00:13:41,457\r\nWhere does he go?\r\n\r\n176\r\n00:13:42,566 --> 00:13:44,363\r\nTo my stomach.\r\n\r\n177\r\n00:13:46,403 --> 00:13:49,304\r\nDoes Tony ever tell you\r\nto do things?\r\n\r\n178\r\n00:13:53,377 --> 00:13:56,039\r\nI don't want to talk\r\nabout Tony anymore.\r\n\r\n179\r\n00:13:58,682 --> 00:14:00,115\r\nThat's fine.\r\n\r\n180\r\n00:14:00,884 --> 00:14:02,681\r\nAll right, Danny.\r\n\r\n181\r\n00:14:03,487 --> 00:14:06,285\r\nI'm going to ask you\r\nto do me a favor...\r\n\r\n182\r\n00:14:06,490 --> 00:14:09,857\r\n...and stay quietly in bed\r\nfor the rest of the day. Okay?\r\n\r\n183\r\n00:14:10,060 --> 00:14:11,186\r\nDo I have to?\r\n\r\n184\r\n00:14:11,395 --> 00:14:13,659\r\nYes. I'd like you to.\r\n\r\n185\r\n00:14:13,864 --> 00:14:16,628\r\nWe're going in the other room\r\nfor a few minutes and talk.\r\n\r\n186\r\n00:14:16,833 --> 00:14:18,960\r\nI'll come back and check on you.\r\n\r\n187\r\n00:14:27,477 --> 00:14:29,877\r\n-Shall we go into the living room?\r\n-Yes.\r\n\r\n188\r\n00:14:33,583 --> 00:14:35,448\r\n-Please.\r\n-Thank you.\r\n\r\n189\r\n00:14:39,322 --> 00:14:43,691\r\nMrs. Torrance, I don't think\r\nyou have anything to worry about.\r\n\r\n190\r\n00:14:43,894 --> 00:14:47,921\r\nI'm quite sure there's nothing\r\nphysically wrong with Danny.\r\n\r\n191\r\n00:14:52,669 --> 00:14:55,797\r\nHe seems absolutely fine now.\r\n\r\n192\r\n00:14:56,006 --> 00:14:56,995\r\nBut you should've seen him.\r\n\r\n193\r\n00:14:57,674 --> 00:14:58,698\r\nI know.\r\n\r\n194\r\n00:14:58,909 --> 00:15:00,604\r\nIKids can scare you to death.\r\n\r\n195\r\n00:15:00,811 --> 00:15:03,678\r\nBut believe me, these episodes\r\nare not at all uncommon.\r\n\r\n196\r\n00:15:03,880 --> 00:15:06,440\r\nAnd they look much worse\r\nthan they are.\r\n\r\n197\r\n00:15:06,983 --> 00:15:09,645\r\nBut what was the matter with him?\r\n\r\n198\r\n00:15:09,853 --> 00:15:13,949\r\nMost of the time, these episodes\r\nwith kids are never explained.\r\n\r\n199\r\n00:15:14,157 --> 00:15:19,026\r\nThey're brought on by emotional\r\nfactors and rarely occur again.\r\n\r\n200\r\n00:15:19,830 --> 00:15:22,799\r\nThey're more akin\r\nto autohypnosis...\r\n\r\n201\r\n00:15:22,999 --> 00:15:25,968\r\n...a kind of self-induced trance.\r\n\r\n202\r\n00:15:26,169 --> 00:15:28,160\r\nIf it reoccurs, which I doubt...\r\n\r\n203\r\n00:15:29,039 --> 00:15:32,133\r\n...we can always think about\r\nhaving some tests done.\r\n\r\n204\r\n00:15:34,744 --> 00:15:37,008\r\nI'm sure you're right.\r\n\r\n205\r\n00:15:38,648 --> 00:15:41,344\r\nHave you been in Boulder long?\r\n\r\n206\r\n00:15:42,152 --> 00:15:43,449\r\nOnly about three months.\r\n\r\n207\r\n00:15:43,653 --> 00:15:47,020\r\nWe're from Vermont. My husband\r\nwas teaching school there.\r\n\r\n208\r\n00:15:49,025 --> 00:15:52,825\r\nDid the appearance\r\nof Danny's imaginary friend....\r\n\r\n209\r\n00:15:53,263 --> 00:15:54,093\r\nTony.\r\n\r\n210\r\n00:15:54,297 --> 00:15:58,256\r\nDid Tony's first appearance happen\r\nto coincide with your arrival here?\r\n\r\n211\r\n00:16:01,371 --> 00:16:02,702\r\nLet's see....\r\n\r\n212\r\n00:16:03,406 --> 00:16:05,966\r\nI guess Danny started\r\ntalking to Tony...\r\n\r\n213\r\n00:16:06,176 --> 00:16:08,872\r\n...about the time we put him\r\nin nursery school.\r\n\r\n214\r\n00:16:09,279 --> 00:16:11,577\r\nDid he adjust well to school?\r\n\r\n215\r\n00:16:13,783 --> 00:16:15,717\r\nHe didn't like it too much\r\nat first.\r\n\r\n216\r\n00:16:15,919 --> 00:16:19,218\r\nThen he had an injury, so we kept\r\nhim out for a while and....\r\n\r\n217\r\n00:16:20,624 --> 00:16:24,526\r\nI guess that's about when I first\r\nnoticed he was talking to Tony.\r\n\r\n218\r\n00:16:25,529 --> 00:16:27,929\r\nWhat sort of injury did he have?\r\n\r\n219\r\n00:16:28,598 --> 00:16:30,759\r\nHe dislocated his shoulder.\r\n\r\n220\r\n00:16:31,234 --> 00:16:33,498\r\nHow did he manage to do that?\r\n\r\n221\r\n00:16:36,940 --> 00:16:40,000\r\nIt was just one of\r\nthose things, you know.\r\n\r\n222\r\n00:16:40,210 --> 00:16:42,201\r\nPurely an accident.\r\n\r\n223\r\n00:16:43,179 --> 00:16:45,977\r\nMy husband had been drinking...\r\n\r\n224\r\n00:16:46,182 --> 00:16:49,515\r\n...and he came home\r\nabout three hours late.\r\n\r\n225\r\n00:16:49,819 --> 00:16:54,381\r\nSo he wasn't exactly\r\nin the greatest mood that night.\r\n\r\n226\r\n00:16:55,125 --> 00:16:59,892\r\nAnd Danny had scattered some of his\r\nschool papers all over the room...\r\n\r\n227\r\n00:17:00,096 --> 00:17:04,396\r\n...and my husband grabbed his arm\r\nto pull him away from them.\r\n\r\n228\r\n00:17:04,601 --> 00:17:07,661\r\nIt's just the sort of thing you do\r\n100 times with a child...\r\n\r\n229\r\n00:17:07,871 --> 00:17:09,896\r\n...you know, in a park\r\nor in the street.\r\n\r\n230\r\n00:17:11,007 --> 00:17:13,635\r\nBut on this particular occasion...\r\n\r\n231\r\n00:17:13,843 --> 00:17:16,471\r\n...my husband just used\r\ntoo much strength...\r\n\r\n232\r\n00:17:16,680 --> 00:17:19,274\r\n...and he injured Danny's arm.\r\n\r\n233\r\n00:17:22,319 --> 00:17:26,847\r\nAnyway, something good did come out\r\nof it all because he said...\r\n\r\n234\r\n00:17:27,090 --> 00:17:29,650\r\n...\"Wendy, I'm never going to\r\ntouch another drop.\r\n\r\n235\r\n00:17:29,859 --> 00:17:31,793\r\nAnd if I do, you can leave me.\"\r\n\r\n236\r\n00:17:31,995 --> 00:17:33,326\r\nAnd he didn't.\r\n\r\n237\r\n00:17:33,530 --> 00:17:38,024\r\nHe hasn't had any\r\nalcohol in 5 months.\r\n\r\n238\r\n00:18:04,894 --> 00:18:09,058\r\nWe must really be high up.\r\nThe air feels so different.\r\n\r\n239\r\n00:18:14,704 --> 00:18:15,932\r\nDad?\r\n\r\n240\r\n00:18:18,742 --> 00:18:20,437\r\nI'm hungry.\r\n\r\n241\r\n00:18:22,278 --> 00:18:25,008\r\nYou should've eaten your breakfast.\r\n\r\n242\r\n00:18:25,849 --> 00:18:28,750\r\nWe'll get you something\r\nas soon as we get to the hotel.\r\n\r\n243\r\n00:18:28,952 --> 00:18:30,579\r\nOkay, Mom.\r\n\r\n244\r\n00:18:32,022 --> 00:18:36,152\r\nWasn't it around here that\r\nthe Donner party got snowbound?\r\n\r\n245\r\n00:18:37,894 --> 00:18:41,386\r\nI think that was farther west,\r\nin the Sierras.\r\n\r\n246\r\n00:18:42,866 --> 00:18:45,300\r\nWhat was the Donner party?\r\n\r\n247\r\n00:18:47,237 --> 00:18:51,503\r\nThey were a party of settlers\r\nin covered wagon times.\r\n\r\n248\r\n00:18:51,741 --> 00:18:55,006\r\nThey got snowbound one winter\r\nin the mountains.\r\n\r\n249\r\n00:18:55,211 --> 00:18:59,409\r\nThey had to resort to cannibalism\r\nin order to stay alive.\r\n\r\n250\r\n00:19:00,550 --> 00:19:03,451\r\nYou mean they ate each other up?\r\n\r\n251\r\n00:19:03,653 --> 00:19:06,747\r\nThey had to in order to survive.\r\n\r\n252\r\n00:19:06,956 --> 00:19:08,184\r\nJack.\r\n\r\n253\r\n00:19:08,391 --> 00:19:09,483\r\nDon't worry, Mom.\r\n\r\n254\r\n00:19:09,693 --> 00:19:14,027\r\nI know all about cannibalism.\r\nI saw it on TV.\r\n\r\n255\r\n00:19:14,230 --> 00:19:16,858\r\nSee, it's okay.\r\n\r\n256\r\n00:19:17,067 --> 00:19:19,501\r\nHe saw it all on the television.\r\n\r\n257\r\n00:19:50,200 --> 00:19:52,031\r\n-What time does the plane leave?\r\n-8:30.\r\n\r\n258\r\n00:19:52,235 --> 00:19:54,999\r\nThat gives us plenty of time\r\nto go over everything.\r\n\r\n259\r\n00:19:55,205 --> 00:19:57,139\r\n-Goodbye, Mr. Ullman.\r\n-Bye.\r\n\r\n260\r\n00:19:57,340 --> 00:20:00,468\r\nGood morning. I hope you\r\nhaven't been waiting too long.\r\n\r\n261\r\n00:20:00,677 --> 00:20:03,305\r\nNo problem. We had time\r\nto grab a bite to eat.\r\n\r\n262\r\n00:20:03,513 --> 00:20:06,414\r\nGood. Glad you made it\r\nbefore they shut down the kitchen.\r\n\r\n263\r\n00:20:06,616 --> 00:20:08,345\r\nIs your family\r\nhaving a look around?\r\n\r\n264\r\n00:20:08,551 --> 00:20:11,918\r\nNo, my son's\r\ndiscovered the games room.\r\n\r\n265\r\n00:20:12,122 --> 00:20:15,216\r\n-Has your luggage been brought in?\r\n-Right there.\r\n\r\n266\r\n00:20:15,792 --> 00:20:17,760\r\nIn view of all we have\r\nto cover today...\r\n\r\n267\r\n00:20:17,961 --> 00:20:21,624\r\n...I suggest we have a quick look\r\nat your apartment and get started.\r\n\r\n268\r\n00:20:21,831 --> 00:20:24,595\r\nHave the Torrances' things\r\nbrought to their apartment.\r\n\r\n269\r\n00:20:24,801 --> 00:20:27,497\r\nI'd better collect my family first.\r\n\r\n270\r\n00:20:35,645 --> 00:20:38,011\r\nThis is our Colorado Lounge.\r\n\r\n271\r\n00:20:38,214 --> 00:20:40,648\r\nIt's beautiful.\r\n\r\n272\r\n00:20:41,050 --> 00:20:42,915\r\nMy God!\r\n\r\n273\r\n00:20:43,119 --> 00:20:45,679\r\nThis place is fantastic,\r\nisn't it, hon?\r\n\r\n274\r\n00:20:45,889 --> 00:20:47,220\r\nIt sure is.\r\n\r\n275\r\n00:20:47,423 --> 00:20:50,221\r\nI've never seen anything\r\nlike this before.\r\n\r\n276\r\n00:20:51,861 --> 00:20:53,829\r\nAre all these\r\nIndian designs authentic?\r\n\r\n277\r\n00:20:54,030 --> 00:20:55,463\r\nI believe they're based...\r\n\r\n278\r\n00:20:55,665 --> 00:20:58,862\r\n...mainly on Navajo and Apache motifs.\r\n\r\n279\r\n00:20:59,068 --> 00:21:01,036\r\nThey're really gorgeous.\r\n\r\n280\r\n00:21:01,237 --> 00:21:02,261\r\nAs a matter of fact...\r\n\r\n281\r\n00:21:02,472 --> 00:21:05,566\r\n...this is probably the most\r\ngorgeous hotel I've ever seen.\r\n\r\n282\r\n00:21:05,975 --> 00:21:08,944\r\nThis old place has had\r\nan illustrious past.\r\n\r\n283\r\n00:21:09,145 --> 00:21:12,239\r\nIn its heyday, it was a stopping\r\nplace for the jet setters...\r\n\r\n284\r\n00:21:12,448 --> 00:21:15,417\r\n...even before anybody knew\r\nwhat a jet set was.\r\n\r\n285\r\n00:21:15,618 --> 00:21:18,678\r\nWe had four presidents\r\nwho stayed here.\r\n\r\n286\r\n00:21:18,955 --> 00:21:20,217\r\nLots of movie stars.\r\n\r\n287\r\n00:21:20,423 --> 00:21:21,981\r\nRoyalty?\r\n\r\n288\r\n00:21:22,358 --> 00:21:23,757\r\nAll the best people.\r\n\r\n289\r\n00:22:16,880 --> 00:22:19,440\r\nThis is the staff wing\r\nof the hotel.\r\n\r\n290\r\n00:22:20,416 --> 00:22:23,749\r\nNone of the other bedrooms\r\nare heated during the winter.\r\n\r\n291\r\n00:22:23,987 --> 00:22:26,888\r\n-Goodbye, Mr. Ullman.\r\n-Goodbye, girls.\r\n\r\n292\r\n00:22:27,123 --> 00:22:29,114\r\nAnd here are your quarters.\r\n\r\n293\r\n00:22:29,525 --> 00:22:32,119\r\nLiving room, bedroom, bathroom.\r\n\r\n294\r\n00:22:32,328 --> 00:22:34,819\r\nAnd a small bedroom for your son.\r\n\r\n295\r\n00:22:38,434 --> 00:22:40,459\r\nPerfect for a child.\r\n\r\n296\r\n00:22:47,677 --> 00:22:51,135\r\nWell, then. Place is\r\nvery nicely self-contained.\r\n\r\n297\r\n00:22:51,347 --> 00:22:52,905\r\nEasy to keep.\r\n\r\n298\r\n00:22:55,685 --> 00:22:56,743\r\nCozy.\r\n\r\n299\r\n00:22:56,953 --> 00:22:59,217\r\nYes, very cozy for a family.\r\n\r\n300\r\n00:22:59,455 --> 00:23:01,116\r\nIf you feel like spreading out...\r\n\r\n301\r\n00:23:01,324 --> 00:23:03,986\r\n...you have the rest of the hotel\r\nto move around in.\r\n\r\n302\r\n00:23:05,628 --> 00:23:08,119\r\nWell, it's very...\r\n\r\n303\r\n00:23:08,665 --> 00:23:09,962\r\n...homey.\r\n\r\n304\r\n00:23:12,869 --> 00:23:15,133\r\nThis is our famous hedge maze.\r\n\r\n305\r\n00:23:15,338 --> 00:23:19,638\r\nIt's quite an attraction here.\r\nThe walls are 13 feet high...\r\n\r\n306\r\n00:23:19,842 --> 00:23:22,140\r\n...and the hedge is as old\r\nas the hotel itself.\r\n\r\n307\r\n00:23:22,345 --> 00:23:24,973\r\nA lot of fun, but I wouldn't\r\nwant to go in there...\r\n\r\n308\r\n00:23:25,181 --> 00:23:28,173\r\n...unless I had an hour\r\nto spare to find my way out.\r\n\r\n309\r\n00:23:29,585 --> 00:23:31,678\r\nWhen was the Overlook built?\r\n\r\n310\r\n00:23:32,689 --> 00:23:34,919\r\nConstruction started in 1907.\r\n\r\n311\r\n00:23:35,124 --> 00:23:37,092\r\nIt was finished in 1909.\r\n\r\n312\r\n00:23:37,293 --> 00:23:39,955\r\nThe site's supposed to be\r\non an Indian burial ground.\r\n\r\n313\r\n00:23:40,163 --> 00:23:41,790\r\nThey actually had to repel...\r\n\r\n314\r\n00:23:41,998 --> 00:23:44,899\r\n...a few Indian attacks as they\r\nwere building it.\r\n\r\n315\r\n00:23:45,501 --> 00:23:47,401\r\nThat's our Snowcat.\r\n\r\n316\r\n00:23:48,104 --> 00:23:50,129\r\nCan you both drive a car?\r\n\r\n317\r\n00:23:50,673 --> 00:23:54,234\r\nThat's fine. Basically the Snowcat\r\noperates very much like a car.\r\n\r\n318\r\n00:23:54,444 --> 00:23:57,004\r\nIt won't take you long\r\nto get the hang of it.\r\n\r\n319\r\n00:23:58,214 --> 00:24:01,581\r\nAs a matter of fact, we brought\r\na decorator in from Chicago...\r\n\r\n320\r\n00:24:01,784 --> 00:24:04,912\r\n...just last year to refurbish\r\nthis part of the hotel.\r\n\r\n321\r\n00:24:05,121 --> 00:24:07,089\r\nHe sure did a beautiful job.\r\n\r\n322\r\n00:24:07,290 --> 00:24:09,622\r\nPink and gold\r\nare my favorite colors.\r\n\r\n323\r\n00:24:10,426 --> 00:24:12,792\r\nThis is our Gold Ballroom.\r\n\r\n324\r\n00:24:14,364 --> 00:24:15,626\r\nI'll say!\r\n\r\n325\r\n00:24:15,832 --> 00:24:19,598\r\nWe can accommodate up to\r\n300 people here very comfortably.\r\n\r\n326\r\n00:24:20,136 --> 00:24:23,003\r\nBoy, we could really have\r\na good party in this room.\r\n\r\n327\r\n00:24:23,206 --> 00:24:27,006\r\nI'm afraid you won't do too well\r\nhere unless you brought supplies.\r\n\r\n328\r\n00:24:27,210 --> 00:24:30,270\r\nWe remove the booze from\r\nthe premises when we shut down.\r\n\r\n329\r\n00:24:30,480 --> 00:24:33,540\r\nThat reduces the insurance\r\nwe normally have to carry.\r\n\r\n330\r\n00:24:33,750 --> 00:24:34,717\r\nWe don't drink.\r\n\r\n331\r\n00:24:34,917 --> 00:24:36,350\r\nThen you're in luck.\r\n\r\n332\r\n00:24:36,552 --> 00:24:40,784\r\nDick, come on over and say hello\r\nto Mr. and Mrs. Torrance.\r\n\r\n333\r\n00:24:40,990 --> 00:24:43,117\r\nThis is Dick Hallorann,\r\nour head chef.\r\n\r\n334\r\n00:24:43,326 --> 00:24:46,056\r\nMr. Hallorann, I'm Jack.\r\nThis is my wife, Winifred.\r\n\r\n335\r\n00:24:46,262 --> 00:24:47,456\r\nGlad to meet you.\r\n\r\n336\r\n00:24:47,663 --> 00:24:50,530\r\nThe Torrances will take care\r\nof the Overlook this winter.\r\n\r\n337\r\n00:24:50,733 --> 00:24:54,464\r\nThat's just great. How do you\r\nfolks like our hotel so far?\r\n\r\n338\r\n00:24:54,670 --> 00:24:56,535\r\nIt's just wonderful.\r\n\r\n339\r\n00:24:56,739 --> 00:24:58,263\r\nHi, Danny!\r\n\r\n340\r\n00:24:59,575 --> 00:25:01,873\r\nI found him outside\r\nlooking for you.\r\n\r\n341\r\n00:25:03,079 --> 00:25:05,946\r\nDid you get tired\r\nof bombing the universe?\r\n\r\n342\r\n00:25:07,350 --> 00:25:08,840\r\nCome on over here.\r\n\r\n343\r\n00:25:09,052 --> 00:25:10,212\r\nThank you, Susie.\r\n\r\n344\r\n00:25:10,420 --> 00:25:14,413\r\nI think it'd be good if you could\r\nshow Mrs. Torrance the kitchen...\r\n\r\n345\r\n00:25:14,624 --> 00:25:16,489\r\n...while I continue on with Jack.\r\n\r\n346\r\n00:25:16,692 --> 00:25:19,126\r\nIt would be a pleasure.\r\nRight this way.\r\n\r\n347\r\n00:25:19,328 --> 00:25:20,886\r\nGreat. See you later, hon.\r\n\r\n348\r\n00:25:21,097 --> 00:25:22,462\r\nBye, darling.\r\n\r\n349\r\n00:25:24,834 --> 00:25:28,167\r\nMrs. Torrance, your husband\r\nintroduced you as Winifred.\r\n\r\n350\r\n00:25:28,371 --> 00:25:30,896\r\nNow, are you a \"Winnie,\"\r\nor a \"Freddie\"?\r\n\r\n351\r\n00:25:31,107 --> 00:25:32,369\r\nI'm a Wendy.\r\n\r\n352\r\n00:25:32,575 --> 00:25:35,772\r\nWendy. That's nice.\r\nThat's the prettiest.\r\n\r\n353\r\n00:25:35,978 --> 00:25:37,605\r\nThis is the kitchen, huh?\r\n\r\n354\r\n00:25:37,814 --> 00:25:39,406\r\nThis is it.\r\n\r\n355\r\n00:25:39,615 --> 00:25:42,550\r\nHow do you like it, Danny?\r\nIs it big enough for you?\r\n\r\n356\r\n00:25:43,386 --> 00:25:45,581\r\nIt's the biggest place I ever seen.\r\n\r\n357\r\n00:25:45,822 --> 00:25:48,154\r\nThis whole place\r\nis such an enormous maze.\r\n\r\n358\r\n00:25:48,357 --> 00:25:51,918\r\nI'll have to leave a trail of\r\nbreadcrumbs every time I come in.\r\n\r\n359\r\n00:25:52,829 --> 00:25:54,694\r\nDon't let it get you down.\r\n\r\n360\r\n00:25:54,897 --> 00:25:57,388\r\nIt's big, but it ain't\r\nnothing but a kitchen.\r\n\r\n361\r\n00:25:57,600 --> 00:25:59,795\r\nA lot of this stuff\r\nyou'll never have to touch.\r\n\r\n362\r\n00:26:00,002 --> 00:26:02,232\r\nI wouldn't know\r\nwhat to do with it if I did.\r\n\r\n363\r\n00:26:02,438 --> 00:26:05,566\r\nOne thing for sure, you don't\r\nhave to worry about food.\r\n\r\n364\r\n00:26:05,775 --> 00:26:10,439\r\nYou folks could eat here for a year\r\nand never have the same menu twice.\r\n\r\n365\r\n00:26:10,646 --> 00:26:13,740\r\nRight here is\r\nour walk-in freezer.\r\n\r\n366\r\n00:26:14,884 --> 00:26:17,944\r\nThis is where we keep\r\nall of our meat.\r\n\r\n367\r\n00:26:18,154 --> 00:26:20,145\r\nYou got 15 rib roasts...\r\n\r\n368\r\n00:26:20,356 --> 00:26:22,483\r\n...30 ten-pound bags of hamburger.\r\n\r\n369\r\n00:26:22,692 --> 00:26:25,752\r\nWe got 12 turkeys,\r\nabout 40 chickens...\r\n\r\n370\r\n00:26:25,962 --> 00:26:29,056\r\n...50 sirloin steaks,\r\ntwo dozen of pork roast...\r\n\r\n371\r\n00:26:29,265 --> 00:26:32,234\r\n...and 20 legs of lamb.\r\nDo you like lamb, Doc?\r\n\r\n372\r\n00:26:33,469 --> 00:26:35,835\r\nYou don't?\r\nWhat's your favorite food, then?\r\n\r\n373\r\n00:26:36,038 --> 00:26:37,903\r\nFrench fries and ketchup.\r\n\r\n374\r\n00:26:38,641 --> 00:26:40,632\r\nI think we can\r\nmanage that too, Doc.\r\n\r\n375\r\n00:26:40,843 --> 00:26:42,572\r\nCome along, now.\r\nWatch your step.\r\n\r\n376\r\n00:26:49,318 --> 00:26:50,876\r\nHow'd you know we call him Doc?\r\n\r\n377\r\n00:26:51,087 --> 00:26:55,114\r\n-Beg your pardon?\r\n-Doc. You called Danny \"Doc\" twice.\r\n\r\n378\r\n00:26:55,324 --> 00:26:56,723\r\nI did?\r\n\r\n379\r\n00:26:57,527 --> 00:27:00,655\r\nWe call him Doc sometimes,\r\nlike in the Bugs Bunny cartoons.\r\n\r\n380\r\n00:27:00,863 --> 00:27:02,125\r\nBut how did you know?\r\n\r\n381\r\n00:27:02,331 --> 00:27:04,856\r\nI guess I probably\r\nheard you call him that.\r\n\r\n382\r\n00:27:05,067 --> 00:27:07,331\r\nIt's possible.\r\nBut I honestly don't remember...\r\n\r\n383\r\n00:27:07,537 --> 00:27:09,732\r\n...calling him that\r\nsince we've been with you.\r\n\r\n384\r\n00:27:09,939 --> 00:27:12,134\r\nAnyway, he looks\r\nlike a Doc, doesn't he?\r\n\r\n385\r\n00:27:13,576 --> 00:27:15,009\r\nWhat's up, Doc?\r\n\r\n386\r\n00:27:16,846 --> 00:27:19,041\r\nNow, this is the storeroom.\r\n\r\n387\r\n00:27:20,783 --> 00:27:22,614\r\nIn here is where we keep...\r\n\r\n388\r\n00:27:22,818 --> 00:27:25,616\r\n...all the dried goods\r\nand the canned goods.\r\n\r\n389\r\n00:27:25,821 --> 00:27:28,255\r\nWe got canned fruits\r\nand vegetables...\r\n\r\n390\r\n00:27:28,457 --> 00:27:32,257\r\n...canned fish and meats,\r\nhot and cold cereals.\r\n\r\n391\r\n00:27:32,461 --> 00:27:35,658\r\nPost Toasties, Corn Flakes,\r\nSugar Puffs...\r\n\r\n392\r\n00:27:35,865 --> 00:27:39,892\r\n...Rice IKrispies, oatmeal,\r\nWheatena and Cream of Wheat.\r\n\r\n393\r\n00:27:40,136 --> 00:27:42,570\r\nYou got a dozen jugs\r\nof black molasses.\r\n\r\n394\r\n00:27:42,772 --> 00:27:45,969\r\nWe got 60 boxes of dried milk...\r\n\r\n395\r\n00:27:53,616 --> 00:27:56,084\r\nHow'd you like some ice cream, Doc?\r\n\r\n396\r\n00:27:58,487 --> 00:28:00,478\r\nSociables, finger rolls...\r\n\r\n397\r\n00:28:00,690 --> 00:28:02,214\r\n...and 7 kinds of what have you.\r\n\r\n398\r\n00:28:02,425 --> 00:28:05,952\r\nNow, we've got dried peaches,\r\ndried apricots...\r\n\r\n399\r\n00:28:06,162 --> 00:28:09,256\r\n...dried raisins and dried prunes.\r\n\r\n400\r\n00:28:09,465 --> 00:28:13,765\r\nYou know, you got to keep regular\r\nif you want to be happy.\r\n\r\n401\r\n00:28:16,672 --> 00:28:18,299\r\n-How're you getting on?\r\n-Fine.\r\n\r\n402\r\n00:28:18,507 --> 00:28:22,068\r\nCan we borrow Mrs. Torrance?\r\nWe're on our way to the basement.\r\n\r\n403\r\n00:28:22,278 --> 00:28:24,212\r\nI promise we won't\r\nkeep her very long.\r\n\r\n404\r\n00:28:24,413 --> 00:28:27,610\r\nNo problem, Mr. Ullman. I was just\r\ngetting to the ice cream.\r\n\r\n405\r\n00:28:27,817 --> 00:28:29,682\r\nYou like ice cream, Doc?\r\n\r\n406\r\n00:28:30,553 --> 00:28:31,520\r\nI thought you did.\r\n\r\n407\r\n00:28:31,721 --> 00:28:34,781\r\nYou folks mind if I give Danny\r\nsome ice cream while we wait?\r\n\r\n408\r\n00:28:34,991 --> 00:28:36,822\r\n-Not at all.\r\n-We don't mind.\r\n\r\n409\r\n00:28:37,026 --> 00:28:39,221\r\n-Good.\r\n-Sound good to you, Doc?\r\n\r\n410\r\n00:28:39,428 --> 00:28:41,487\r\nOkay, you behave yourself.\r\n\r\n411\r\n00:28:44,500 --> 00:28:46,365\r\nWhat kind of ice cream\r\ndo you like?\r\n\r\n412\r\n00:28:46,569 --> 00:28:47,467\r\nChocolate.\r\n\r\n413\r\n00:28:47,670 --> 00:28:50,639\r\nChocolate it shall be.\r\nCome on, son.\r\n\r\n414\r\n00:28:55,211 --> 00:28:57,202\r\nIt's amazing, all this\r\nactivity today.\r\n\r\n415\r\n00:28:57,413 --> 00:29:00,211\r\nThe guests and some staff\r\nleft yesterday, but the...\r\n\r\n416\r\n00:29:00,416 --> 00:29:01,849\r\n...last day's always hectic.\r\n\r\n417\r\n00:29:02,051 --> 00:29:05,111\r\nEverybody wants to be on their way\r\nas early as possible.\r\n\r\n418\r\n00:29:05,321 --> 00:29:09,348\r\nBy 5:00 tonight, you'll never\r\nknow anybody was ever here.\r\n\r\n419\r\n00:29:09,558 --> 00:29:11,617\r\nJust like a ghost ship, huh?\r\n\r\n420\r\n00:29:17,300 --> 00:29:20,269\r\nDo you know how I knew\r\nyour name was Doc?\r\n\r\n421\r\n00:29:26,842 --> 00:29:29,242\r\nYou know what I'm\r\ntalking about, don't you?\r\n\r\n422\r\n00:29:36,218 --> 00:29:39,710\r\nI can remember when I was\r\na little boy...\r\n\r\n423\r\n00:29:40,122 --> 00:29:42,647\r\n...my grandmother and I\r\ncould hold conversations...\r\n\r\n424\r\n00:29:42,858 --> 00:29:46,692\r\n...entirely without ever\r\nopening our mouths.\r\n\r\n425\r\n00:29:47,763 --> 00:29:50,061\r\nShe called it \"shining.\"\r\n\r\n426\r\n00:29:51,567 --> 00:29:54,297\r\nAnd for a long time I thought\r\nit was just the two of us...\r\n\r\n427\r\n00:29:54,503 --> 00:29:57,131\r\n...that had \"the shine\" to us.\r\n\r\n428\r\n00:29:57,740 --> 00:30:00,732\r\nJust like you probably thought\r\nyou was the only one.\r\n\r\n429\r\n00:30:01,410 --> 00:30:03,275\r\nBut there are other folks...\r\n\r\n430\r\n00:30:03,479 --> 00:30:07,210\r\n...though mostly they don't\r\nknow it, or don't believe it.\r\n\r\n431\r\n00:30:11,887 --> 00:30:14,321\r\nHow long have you\r\nbeen able to do it?\r\n\r\n432\r\n00:30:19,528 --> 00:30:21,928\r\nWhy don't you want\r\nto talk about it?\r\n\r\n433\r\n00:30:27,169 --> 00:30:29,228\r\nI'm not supposed to.\r\n\r\n434\r\n00:30:30,806 --> 00:30:33,331\r\nWho says you ain't supposed to?\r\n\r\n435\r\n00:30:36,779 --> 00:30:38,178\r\nTony.\r\n\r\n436\r\n00:30:40,149 --> 00:30:41,810\r\nWho's Tony?\r\n\r\n437\r\n00:30:44,286 --> 00:30:47,687\r\nTony's the little boy\r\nthat lives in my mouth.\r\n\r\n438\r\n00:30:49,625 --> 00:30:51,650\r\nIs Tony the one\r\nthat...\r\n\r\n439\r\n00:30:51,861 --> 00:30:53,419\r\n...tells you things?\r\n\r\n440\r\n00:30:57,967 --> 00:31:00,333\r\nHow does he tell you things?\r\n\r\n441\r\n00:31:02,171 --> 00:31:06,471\r\nIt's like I go to sleep,\r\nand he shows me things.\r\n\r\n442\r\n00:31:06,675 --> 00:31:10,771\r\nBut when I wake up,\r\nI can't remember everything.\r\n\r\n443\r\n00:31:12,615 --> 00:31:16,312\r\nDoes your mom and dad\r\nknow about Tony?\r\n\r\n444\r\n00:31:19,622 --> 00:31:22,182\r\nDo they know he tells you things?\r\n\r\n445\r\n00:31:23,058 --> 00:31:25,993\r\nTony told me never to tell them.\r\n\r\n446\r\n00:31:28,130 --> 00:31:31,497\r\nHas Tony ever told you\r\nanything about this place?\r\n\r\n447\r\n00:31:31,700 --> 00:31:34,260\r\nAbout the Overlook Hotel?\r\n\r\n448\r\n00:31:37,540 --> 00:31:39,098\r\nI don't know.\r\n\r\n449\r\n00:31:40,009 --> 00:31:42,807\r\nNow think real hard, Doc.\r\n\r\n450\r\n00:31:43,012 --> 00:31:44,036\r\nThink.\r\n\r\n451\r\n00:31:47,149 --> 00:31:49,879\r\nMaybe he showed me something.\r\n\r\n452\r\n00:31:50,820 --> 00:31:53,448\r\nTry to think of what it was.\r\n\r\n453\r\n00:31:56,459 --> 00:31:59,758\r\nMr. Hallorann, are you scared\r\nof this place?\r\n\r\n454\r\n00:32:02,865 --> 00:32:05,095\r\nScared of nothing here.\r\n\r\n455\r\n00:32:05,568 --> 00:32:07,058\r\nIt's just that...\r\n\r\n456\r\n00:32:07,803 --> 00:32:10,636\r\n...you know, some places\r\nare like people.\r\n\r\n457\r\n00:32:11,474 --> 00:32:13,169\r\nSome shine...\r\n\r\n458\r\n00:32:13,375 --> 00:32:14,774\r\n...and some don't.\r\n\r\n459\r\n00:32:16,011 --> 00:32:18,138\r\nI guess you could say\r\nthe Overlook Hotel...\r\n\r\n460\r\n00:32:18,347 --> 00:32:21,646\r\n...has something about it\r\nthat's like shining.\r\n\r\n461\r\n00:32:24,687 --> 00:32:27,087\r\nIs there something bad here?\r\n\r\n462\r\n00:32:38,701 --> 00:32:41,135\r\nYou know, Doc,\r\nwhen something happens...\r\n\r\n463\r\n00:32:41,337 --> 00:32:44,966\r\n...it can leave a trace\r\nof itself behind.\r\n\r\n464\r\n00:32:45,741 --> 00:32:47,299\r\nSay, like...\r\n\r\n465\r\n00:32:47,510 --> 00:32:50,570\r\n...if someone burns toast.\r\n\r\n466\r\n00:32:52,681 --> 00:32:57,345\r\nMaybe things that happen\r\nleave other kind of traces behind.\r\n\r\n467\r\n00:32:58,521 --> 00:33:01,957\r\nNot things that anyone\r\ncan notice.\r\n\r\n468\r\n00:33:02,157 --> 00:33:06,958\r\nBut things that people\r\nwho shine can see.\r\n\r\n469\r\n00:33:08,063 --> 00:33:11,362\r\nJust like they can see things\r\nthat haven't happened yet...\r\n\r\n470\r\n00:33:13,636 --> 00:33:17,800\r\n...sometimes they can see things\r\nthat happened a long time ago.\r\n\r\n471\r\n00:33:19,341 --> 00:33:22,208\r\nI think a lot of things\r\nhappened right here...\r\n\r\n472\r\n00:33:22,411 --> 00:33:26,108\r\n...in this particular hotel\r\nover the years.\r\n\r\n473\r\n00:33:26,649 --> 00:33:29,049\r\nAnd not all of them\r\nwas good.\r\n\r\n474\r\n00:33:32,354 --> 00:33:34,982\r\nWhat about room 237?\r\n\r\n475\r\n00:33:38,327 --> 00:33:40,522\r\nRoom 237?\r\n\r\n476\r\n00:33:41,830 --> 00:33:44,924\r\nYou're scared of room 237,\r\nain't you?\r\n\r\n477\r\n00:33:46,702 --> 00:33:48,169\r\nNo, I ain't.\r\n\r\n478\r\n00:33:49,672 --> 00:33:53,506\r\nMr. Hallorann, what is in room 237?\r\n\r\n479\r\n00:33:54,843 --> 00:33:56,208\r\nNothing.\r\n\r\n480\r\n00:33:56,645 --> 00:33:59,876\r\nThere ain't nothing in room 237.\r\n\r\n481\r\n00:34:00,082 --> 00:34:03,313\r\nBut you ain't got no business\r\ngoing in there anyway.\r\n\r\n482\r\n00:34:03,519 --> 00:34:05,646\r\nSo stay out.\r\n\r\n483\r\n00:34:05,854 --> 00:34:08,345\r\nYou understand? Stay out!\r\n\r\n484\r\n00:35:47,723 --> 00:35:49,452\r\nGood morning, hon.\r\n\r\n485\r\n00:35:51,460 --> 00:35:53,223\r\nYour breakfast is ready.\r\n\r\n486\r\n00:35:53,996 --> 00:35:55,623\r\nWhat time is it?\r\n\r\n487\r\n00:35:55,831 --> 00:35:57,696\r\nIt's about 11:30.\r\n\r\n488\r\n00:35:59,601 --> 00:36:01,193\r\nJesus.\r\n\r\n489\r\n00:36:02,137 --> 00:36:04,571\r\nI guess we've been\r\nstaying up too late.\r\n\r\n490\r\n00:36:04,873 --> 00:36:06,306\r\nI know it.\r\n\r\n491\r\n00:36:07,609 --> 00:36:10,476\r\nI made them just the way\r\nyou like them, sunny-side up.\r\n\r\n492\r\n00:36:10,779 --> 00:36:12,337\r\nNice.\r\n\r\n493\r\n00:36:14,616 --> 00:36:16,413\r\nIt's really pretty outside.\r\n\r\n494\r\n00:36:16,618 --> 00:36:19,849\r\nHow about taking me for a walk\r\nafter you finish your breakfast?\r\n\r\n495\r\n00:36:20,456 --> 00:36:24,790\r\nI suppose I ought to try\r\nto do some writing first.\r\n\r\n496\r\n00:36:26,228 --> 00:36:27,889\r\nAny ideas yet?\r\n\r\n497\r\n00:36:28,897 --> 00:36:30,558\r\nLots of ideas.\r\n\r\n498\r\n00:36:30,766 --> 00:36:32,290\r\nNo good ones.\r\n\r\n499\r\n00:36:32,768 --> 00:36:35,236\r\nSomething will come.\r\n\r\n500\r\n00:36:35,738 --> 00:36:39,674\r\nIt's just a matter of settling into\r\nthe habit of writing every day.\r\n\r\n501\r\n00:36:41,243 --> 00:36:42,938\r\nThat's all it is.\r\n\r\n502\r\n00:36:45,047 --> 00:36:47,345\r\nIt's really nice up here,\r\nisn't it?\r\n\r\n503\r\n00:36:47,750 --> 00:36:49,183\r\nI love it.\r\n\r\n504\r\n00:36:49,685 --> 00:36:51,277\r\nI really do.\r\n\r\n505\r\n00:36:52,187 --> 00:36:55,213\r\nI've never been this happy\r\nor comfortable anywhere.\r\n\r\n506\r\n00:36:55,424 --> 00:36:59,190\r\nIt's amazing how fast you get\r\nused to such a big place.\r\n\r\n507\r\n00:36:59,394 --> 00:37:02,295\r\nI tell you, when we first\r\ncame up here...\r\n\r\n508\r\n00:37:02,598 --> 00:37:04,657\r\n...I thought it was kind of scary.\r\n\r\n509\r\n00:37:05,100 --> 00:37:07,660\r\nI fell in love with it right away.\r\n\r\n510\r\n00:37:08,337 --> 00:37:11,135\r\nWhen I came up here\r\nfor my interview...\r\n\r\n511\r\n00:37:11,507 --> 00:37:15,341\r\n...it was as though\r\nI'd been here before.\r\n\r\n512\r\n00:37:15,544 --> 00:37:18,172\r\nI mean, we all have moments\r\nof déjà vu...\r\n\r\n513\r\n00:37:18,380 --> 00:37:20,575\r\n...but this was ridiculous.\r\n\r\n514\r\n00:37:21,316 --> 00:37:23,181\r\nIt was almost as though I knew...\r\n\r\n515\r\n00:37:23,385 --> 00:37:27,116\r\n...what was going to be\r\naround every corner.\r\n\r\n516\r\n00:38:00,255 --> 00:38:03,452\r\nThe loser has to keep\r\nAmerica clean. How's that?\r\n\r\n517\r\n00:38:03,659 --> 00:38:06,219\r\n-All right.\r\n-And you're going to lose.\r\n\r\n518\r\n00:38:06,428 --> 00:38:09,556\r\nAnd I'm going to get you.\r\nYou'd better run fast!\r\n\r\n519\r\n00:38:14,570 --> 00:38:15,696\r\nLook out!\r\n\r\n520\r\n00:38:15,904 --> 00:38:17,769\r\nI'm coming in close.\r\n\r\n521\r\n00:38:17,973 --> 00:38:20,464\r\nLoser has to keep America clean.\r\n\r\n522\r\n00:38:20,709 --> 00:38:22,336\r\nIKeep America clean.\r\n\r\n523\r\n00:38:23,345 --> 00:38:24,812\r\nDanny, you win.\r\n\r\n524\r\n00:38:25,147 --> 00:38:27,479\r\nLet's take the rest\r\nof this walking.\r\n\r\n525\r\n00:38:30,018 --> 00:38:31,417\r\nGive me your hand.\r\n\r\n526\r\n00:38:34,056 --> 00:38:35,853\r\nIsn't it beautiful?\r\n\r\n527\r\n00:38:53,609 --> 00:38:54,974\r\nDead end.\r\n\r\n528\r\n00:39:52,434 --> 00:39:54,061\r\nWe made it.\r\n\r\n529\r\n00:39:54,569 --> 00:39:55,797\r\nIsn't it beautiful?\r\n\r\n530\r\n00:40:17,492 --> 00:40:19,323\r\nIt's so pretty.\r\n\r\n531\r\n00:40:24,066 --> 00:40:27,035\r\nI didn't think it was\r\ngoing to be this big. Did you?\r\n\r\n532\r\n00:40:38,180 --> 00:40:40,580\r\nRutherford was serving\r\na life sentence...\r\n\r\n533\r\n00:40:40,782 --> 00:40:42,545\r\n...for a 1968 shooting.\r\n\r\n534\r\n00:40:42,751 --> 00:40:46,619\r\nAnd the search continues\r\nfor that missing Aspen woman.\r\n\r\n535\r\n00:40:46,822 --> 00:40:50,189\r\n24-year-old Susan Robertson\r\nhas been missing 10 days.\r\n\r\n536\r\n00:40:50,392 --> 00:40:53,122\r\nShe disappeared on a hunting\r\ntrip with her husband.\r\n\r\n537\r\n00:40:53,328 --> 00:40:56,126\r\nThey may have to\r\ncall off the search...\r\n\r\n538\r\n00:40:56,331 --> 00:40:58,856\r\n...if a predicted snowstorm\r\nmoves in tomorrow.\r\n\r\n539\r\n00:40:59,067 --> 00:41:00,932\r\nIt's so beautiful\r\nin Denver today...\r\n\r\n540\r\n00:41:01,136 --> 00:41:03,263\r\n...it's hard to believe\r\na snowstorm could be close.\r\n\r\n541\r\n00:41:03,472 --> 00:41:05,702\r\nI want to go outside\r\nand lie in the sun...\r\n\r\n542\r\n00:41:05,907 --> 00:41:10,037\r\n...yet to our north, to our west,\r\nit is snowing and cold.\r\n\r\n543\r\n00:41:10,245 --> 00:41:11,439\r\nAnd it's moving...\r\n\r\n544\r\n00:41:11,646 --> 00:41:14,809\r\n...right here towards Colorado\r\nas we talk. It's incredible.\r\n\r\n545\r\n00:43:43,431 --> 00:43:44,864\r\nHi, hon.\r\n\r\n546\r\n00:43:48,470 --> 00:43:49,869\r\nHow's it going?\r\n\r\n547\r\n00:43:52,440 --> 00:43:53,600\r\nFine.\r\n\r\n548\r\n00:43:55,710 --> 00:43:57,268\r\nGet a lot written today?\r\n\r\n549\r\n00:44:04,319 --> 00:44:06,879\r\nThe weather forecast\r\nsaid it's going to snow tonight.\r\n\r\n550\r\n00:44:12,093 --> 00:44:14,425\r\nWhat do you want me\r\nto do about it?\r\n\r\n551\r\n00:44:16,565 --> 00:44:18,726\r\nCome on, hon.\r\n\r\n552\r\n00:44:19,067 --> 00:44:21,092\r\nDon't be so grouchy.\r\n\r\n553\r\n00:44:21,503 --> 00:44:22,834\r\nI'm not...\r\n\r\n554\r\n00:44:23,205 --> 00:44:24,399\r\n...being grouchy.\r\n\r\n555\r\n00:44:24,606 --> 00:44:27,404\r\nI just want to finish my work.\r\n\r\n556\r\n00:44:30,912 --> 00:44:33,312\r\nOkay. I understand.\r\n\r\n557\r\n00:44:33,548 --> 00:44:36,142\r\nI'll come back later\r\nwith a couple of sandwiches.\r\n\r\n558\r\n00:44:36,518 --> 00:44:38,986\r\nMaybe you'll let me\r\nread something then.\r\n\r\n559\r\n00:44:42,190 --> 00:44:43,282\r\nWendy...\r\n\r\n560\r\n00:44:43,491 --> 00:44:46,085\r\n...let me explain something to you.\r\n\r\n561\r\n00:44:46,995 --> 00:44:50,863\r\nWhen you come in and interrupt,\r\nyou're breaking my concentration.\r\n\r\n562\r\n00:44:51,066 --> 00:44:52,499\r\nYou're distracting me...\r\n\r\n563\r\n00:44:52,701 --> 00:44:56,137\r\n...and it will then take me time\r\nto get back to where I was.\r\n\r\n564\r\n00:44:56,338 --> 00:44:57,669\r\nUnderstand?\r\n\r\n565\r\n00:45:01,243 --> 00:45:02,403\r\nFine.\r\n\r\n566\r\n00:45:03,578 --> 00:45:05,307\r\nWe're going to make a new rule:\r\n\r\n567\r\n00:45:05,513 --> 00:45:06,946\r\nWhenever I'm in here...\r\n\r\n568\r\n00:45:07,148 --> 00:45:09,412\r\n...and you hear me typing...\r\n\r\n569\r\n00:45:11,219 --> 00:45:14,154\r\n...or whatever the fuck\r\nyou hear me doing in here...\r\n\r\n570\r\n00:45:14,356 --> 00:45:16,654\r\n...when I'm in here,\r\nthat means I am working.\r\n\r\n571\r\n00:45:16,858 --> 00:45:19,088\r\nThat means don't come in.\r\n\r\n572\r\n00:45:19,294 --> 00:45:21,558\r\nNow, do you think\r\nyou can handle that?\r\n\r\n573\r\n00:45:26,201 --> 00:45:27,327\r\nFine.\r\n\r\n574\r\n00:45:28,370 --> 00:45:31,669\r\nWhy don't you start right now\r\nand get the fuck out of here?\r\n\r\n575\r\n00:46:07,509 --> 00:46:08,874\r\nAll right, you!\r\n\r\n576\r\n00:46:10,312 --> 00:46:12,109\r\nI know you've got more.\r\n\r\n577\r\n00:46:14,215 --> 00:46:15,273\r\nMissed!\r\n\r\n578\r\n00:46:20,855 --> 00:46:21,685\r\nDon't have!\r\n\r\n579\r\n00:46:21,923 --> 00:46:23,652\r\nNo fair anymore.\r\n\r\n580\r\n00:47:31,326 --> 00:47:32,623\r\nI knew it.\r\n\r\n581\r\n00:48:02,891 --> 00:48:06,383\r\nThis is IKDIK 12 calling IKDIK 1 .\r\n\r\n582\r\n00:48:08,897 --> 00:48:12,594\r\nKDK 12 to KDK 1.\r\n\r\n583\r\n00:48:12,801 --> 00:48:15,929\r\nThis is IKDIK 1 .\r\nWe're receiving you. Over.\r\n\r\n584\r\n00:48:16,304 --> 00:48:19,432\r\nHi, this is Wendy Torrance\r\nat the Overlook Hotel.\r\n\r\n585\r\n00:48:20,008 --> 00:48:22,806\r\nHi, how are you folks\r\ngetting on up there? Over.\r\n\r\n586\r\n00:48:23,077 --> 00:48:24,408\r\nWe're just fine.\r\n\r\n587\r\n00:48:24,612 --> 00:48:27,080\r\nBut our telephones\r\naren't doing too well.\r\n\r\n588\r\n00:48:27,282 --> 00:48:30,308\r\nAre the lines down,\r\nby any chance? Over.\r\n\r\n589\r\n00:48:30,952 --> 00:48:34,752\r\nYes, quite a few of them are down\r\ndue to the storm. Over.\r\n\r\n590\r\n00:48:35,056 --> 00:48:38,253\r\nAny chance of them\r\nbeing repaired soon? Over.\r\n\r\n591\r\n00:48:38,460 --> 00:48:39,620\r\nWell, I wouldn't like to say.\r\n\r\n592\r\n00:48:39,828 --> 00:48:43,264\r\nMost winters they stay that way\r\nuntil spring. Over.\r\n\r\n593\r\n00:48:43,765 --> 00:48:47,166\r\nBoy, this storm is really something,\r\nisn't it? Over.\r\n\r\n594\r\n00:48:47,635 --> 00:48:50,536\r\nYes. It's one of the worst we've\r\nhad for years.\r\n\r\n595\r\n00:48:51,105 --> 00:48:54,302\r\nIs there anything else we can\r\ndo for you, Mrs. Torrance?\r\n\r\n596\r\n00:48:54,776 --> 00:48:56,937\r\nI suppose not. Over.\r\n\r\n597\r\n00:48:57,545 --> 00:49:00,844\r\nIf you folks have any problems\r\nup there, just give us a call.\r\n\r\n598\r\n00:49:01,049 --> 00:49:02,346\r\nAnd, Mrs. Torrance?\r\n\r\n599\r\n00:49:02,550 --> 00:49:06,748\r\nIt might be a good idea if you\r\nleave your radio on all the time.\r\n\r\n600\r\n00:49:07,589 --> 00:49:09,079\r\nOkay. We'll do that.\r\n\r\n601\r\n0