rite my own ticket\r\nif I went back now, couldn't I?\r\n\r\n864\r\n01:20:04,328 --> 01:20:08,059\r\nShoveling out driveways,\r\nwork in a car wash.\r\n\r\n865\r\n01:20:08,265 --> 01:20:10,358\r\nAny of that appeal to you?\r\n\r\n866\r\n01:20:11,568 --> 01:20:14,264\r\nI have let you fuck up my life\r\nso far...\r\n\r\n867\r\n01:20:14,471 --> 01:20:18,100\r\n...but I am not going to let you\r\nfuck this up.\r\n\r\n868\r\n01:21:36,019 --> 01:21:38,317\r\nGood evening. Forest Service.\r\n\r\n869\r\n01:21:38,889 --> 01:21:40,322\r\nMy name is Dick Hallorann.\r\n\r\n870\r\n01:21:40,524 --> 01:21:42,958\r\nI'm the head chef at\r\nthe Overlook Hotel.\r\n\r\n871\r\n01:21:43,160 --> 01:21:45,287\r\nGood evening.\r\nWhat can I do for you?\r\n\r\n872\r\n01:21:45,495 --> 01:21:49,056\r\nI've been trying to make\r\nan urgent phone call up there...\r\n\r\n873\r\n01:21:49,266 --> 01:21:52,565\r\n...but the operator said\r\nthat the phone lines are down.\r\n\r\n874\r\n01:21:52,769 --> 01:21:56,364\r\nA lot of lines around here\r\nare down due to the storm.\r\n\r\n875\r\n01:21:56,573 --> 01:21:59,235\r\nI hate to put you through\r\nany trouble...\r\n\r\n876\r\n01:21:59,443 --> 01:22:02,674\r\n...but there's a family up there\r\nall by themselves with a young kid.\r\n\r\n877\r\n01:22:02,879 --> 01:22:04,540\r\nAnd with this storm\r\nand everything...\r\n\r\n878\r\n01:22:04,748 --> 01:22:07,649\r\n...I'd appreciate it if you'd give\r\nthem a call on your radio...\r\n\r\n879\r\n01:22:07,851 --> 01:22:09,842\r\n...just to see if\r\neverything's okay.\r\n\r\n880\r\n01:22:10,353 --> 01:22:11,650\r\nI'll be glad to do that.\r\n\r\n881\r\n01:22:11,855 --> 01:22:14,653\r\nWhy don't you call me back\r\nin about 20 minutes?\r\n\r\n882\r\n01:22:14,858 --> 01:22:16,883\r\nThank you very much.\r\nI'll do that.\r\n\r\n883\r\n01:22:17,094 --> 01:22:18,527\r\nAll right, sir.\r\n\r\n884\r\n01:22:38,849 --> 01:22:40,817\r\nGood evening, Mr. Torrance.\r\n\r\n885\r\n01:22:41,017 --> 01:22:42,484\r\nGood evening.\r\n\r\n886\r\n01:23:07,043 --> 01:23:08,510\r\nHi, Lloyd.\r\n\r\n887\r\n01:23:08,712 --> 01:23:10,577\r\nBeen away, but now I'm back.\r\n\r\n888\r\n01:23:10,847 --> 01:23:12,576\r\nGood evening, Mr. Torrance.\r\n\r\n889\r\n01:23:13,250 --> 01:23:14,239\r\nIt's good to see you.\r\n\r\n890\r\n01:23:14,451 --> 01:23:17,113\r\nIt's good to be back, Lloyd.\r\n\r\n891\r\n01:23:17,754 --> 01:23:19,483\r\nWhat'll it be, sir?\r\n\r\n892\r\n01:23:20,290 --> 01:23:22,554\r\nHair of the dog that bit me.\r\n\r\n893\r\n01:23:23,960 --> 01:23:25,621\r\nBourbon on the rocks.\r\n\r\n894\r\n01:23:26,463 --> 01:23:27,862\r\nThat'll do her.\r\n\r\n895\r\n01:23:41,378 --> 01:23:43,642\r\nNo charge to you, Mr. Torrance.\r\n\r\n896\r\n01:23:45,081 --> 01:23:47,049\r\nNo charge?\r\n\r\n897\r\n01:23:47,684 --> 01:23:49,675\r\nYour money's no good here.\r\n\r\n898\r\n01:23:55,325 --> 01:23:57,054\r\nOrders from the house.\r\n\r\n899\r\n01:24:00,263 --> 01:24:02,754\r\nOrders from the house.\r\n\r\n900\r\n01:24:06,002 --> 01:24:07,993\r\nDrink up, Mr. Torrance.\r\n\r\n901\r\n01:24:10,207 --> 01:24:14,735\r\nI'm the kind of man likes to know\r\nwho's buying their drinks, Lloyd.\r\n\r\n902\r\n01:24:17,047 --> 01:24:19,982\r\nIt's not a matter that concerns you,\r\nMr. Torrance.\r\n\r\n903\r\n01:24:20,183 --> 01:24:22,117\r\nAt least, not at this point.\r\n\r\n904\r\n01:24:26,923 --> 01:24:29,323\r\nAnything you say, Lloyd.\r\n\r\n905\r\n01:24:29,759 --> 01:24:31,750\r\nAnything you say.\r\n\r\n906\r\n01:24:44,841 --> 01:24:47,309\r\nOh, dear! I'm so sorry, sir.\r\n\r\n907\r\n01:24:48,411 --> 01:24:49,878\r\nOh, dear. Oh, dear.\r\n\r\n908\r\n01:24:50,080 --> 01:24:52,640\r\nI've made an awful mess\r\nof your jacket, sir.\r\n\r\n909\r\n01:24:53,883 --> 01:24:57,512\r\nThat's all right.\r\nI've got plenty of jackets.\r\n\r\n910\r\n01:24:57,721 --> 01:25:00,519\r\nI'm afraid it's advocaat, sir.\r\nIt tends to stain.\r\n\r\n911\r\n01:25:00,724 --> 01:25:01,850\r\nAdvocaat, is it?\r\n\r\n912\r\n01:25:02,058 --> 01:25:04,219\r\nYes, sir.\r\nI think the best thing...\r\n\r\n913\r\n01:25:04,427 --> 01:25:06,622\r\n...is to come along\r\nto the gentlemen's room...\r\n\r\n914\r\n01:25:06,830 --> 01:25:09,355\r\n...and we'll get\r\nsome water to it, sir.\r\n\r\n915\r\n01:25:10,200 --> 01:25:13,499\r\nLooks like you might have got a\r\nspot of it on yourself...\r\n\r\n916\r\n01:25:13,703 --> 01:25:14,692\r\n...Jeevesy old boy.\r\n\r\n917\r\n01:25:14,904 --> 01:25:18,067\r\nThat doesn't matter, sir.\r\nYou're the important one.\r\n\r\n918\r\n01:25:18,375 --> 01:25:20,775\r\nAwfully nice of you to say.\r\n\r\n919\r\n01:25:21,211 --> 01:25:24,078\r\nOf course, I intended to change\r\nmy jacket this evening...\r\n\r\n920\r\n01:25:24,281 --> 01:25:26,545\r\n...before the fish and\r\ngoose soiree.\r\n\r\n921\r\n01:25:26,750 --> 01:25:28,775\r\nVery wise, sir. Very wise.\r\n\r\n922\r\n01:25:28,985 --> 01:25:30,009\r\nHere. I'll just...\r\n\r\n923\r\n01:25:31,121 --> 01:25:33,385\r\n...hold this for you there,\r\nJeevesy.\r\n\r\n924\r\n01:25:33,590 --> 01:25:35,387\r\nThank you, sir. Thank you.\r\n\r\n925\r\n01:25:36,426 --> 01:25:40,055\r\nLet's see if we can improve this\r\nwith a little water, sir.\r\n\r\n926\r\n01:25:40,263 --> 01:25:41,525\r\nAll right. I'll just...\r\n\r\n927\r\n01:25:41,731 --> 01:25:45,929\r\n...set my bourbon and advocaat\r\ndown right there.\r\n\r\n928\r\n01:25:46,503 --> 01:25:47,936\r\nWon't keep you a moment.\r\n\r\n929\r\n01:25:48,138 --> 01:25:49,537\r\nFine.\r\n\r\n930\r\n01:25:52,609 --> 01:25:54,270\r\nWhat do they call you,\r\nJeevesy?\r\n\r\n931\r\n01:25:54,477 --> 01:25:57,037\r\nGrady, sir. Delbert Grady.\r\n\r\n932\r\n01:26:01,818 --> 01:26:02,648\r\nGrady?\r\n\r\n933\r\n01:26:02,852 --> 01:26:04,183\r\nYes, sir.\r\n\r\n934\r\n01:26:05,355 --> 01:26:06,686\r\nDelbert Grady.\r\n\r\n935\r\n01:26:06,890 --> 01:26:08,414\r\nThat's right, sir.\r\n\r\n936\r\n01:26:17,133 --> 01:26:18,566\r\nMr. Grady...\r\n\r\n937\r\n01:26:19,336 --> 01:26:21,429\r\n...haven't I seen you\r\nsomewhere before?\r\n\r\n938\r\n01:26:21,638 --> 01:26:24,334\r\nWhy, no, sir. I don't believe so.\r\n\r\n939\r\n01:26:31,381 --> 01:26:33,212\r\nIt's coming off now, sir.\r\n\r\n940\r\n01:26:38,154 --> 01:26:39,712\r\nMr. Grady...\r\n\r\n941\r\n01:26:41,224 --> 01:26:43,692\r\n...weren't you once\r\nthe caretaker here?\r\n\r\n942\r\n01:26:43,893 --> 01:26:46,691\r\nWhy, no, sir. I don't believe so.\r\n\r\n943\r\n01:26:49,733 --> 01:26:53,066\r\nYou a married man, are you,\r\nMr. Grady?\r\n\r\n944\r\n01:26:53,269 --> 01:26:54,099\r\nYes, sir.\r\n\r\n945\r\n01:26:54,304 --> 01:26:57,569\r\nI have a wife and\r\ntwo daughters, sir.\r\n\r\n946\r\n01:26:58,608 --> 01:27:00,132\r\nAnd...\r\n\r\n947\r\n01:27:01,811 --> 01:27:03,073\r\n...where are they now?\r\n\r\n948\r\n01:27:03,279 --> 01:27:07,340\r\nThey're somewhere around.\r\nI'm not quite sure at the moment.\r\n\r\n949\r\n01:27:18,027 --> 01:27:20,427\r\nYou were the caretaker here.\r\n\r\n950\r\n01:27:21,898 --> 01:27:23,889\r\nI recognize you.\r\n\r\n951\r\n01:27:25,268 --> 01:27:28,328\r\nI saw your picture\r\nin the newspapers.\r\n\r\n952\r\n01:27:28,772 --> 01:27:30,535\r\nYou...\r\n\r\n953\r\n01:27:31,007 --> 01:27:34,534\r\n...chopped your wife and daughter\r\nup into little bits.\r\n\r\n954\r\n01:27:35,044 --> 01:27:36,443\r\nAnd...\r\n\r\n955\r\n01:27:37,080 --> 01:27:39,014\r\n...then you blew your brains out.\r\n\r\n956\r\n01:27:48,925 --> 01:27:50,688\r\nThat's strange, sir.\r\n\r\n957\r\n01:27:51,694 --> 01:27:54,424\r\nI don't have any recollection\r\nof that at all.\r\n\r\n958\r\n01:27:58,101 --> 01:27:59,966\r\nMr. Grady...\r\n\r\n959\r\n01:28:00,403 --> 01:28:03,736\r\n...you were the caretaker here.\r\n\r\n960\r\n01:28:11,548 --> 01:28:14,312\r\nI'm sorry to differ with you, sir.\r\n\r\n961\r\n01:28:16,186 --> 01:28:17,915\r\nBut you...\r\n\r\n962\r\n01:28:18,655 --> 01:28:20,486\r\n...are the caretaker.\r\n\r\n963\r\n01:28:22,759 --> 01:28:25,660\r\nYou've always been the caretaker.\r\n\r\n964\r\n01:28:28,565 --> 01:28:30,396\r\nI should know, sir.\r\n\r\n965\r\n01:28:31,835 --> 01:28:34,429\r\nI've always been here.\r\n\r\n966\r\n01:28:52,655 --> 01:28:54,850\r\nDid you know, Mr. Torrance...\r\n\r\n967\r\n01:28:55,091 --> 01:28:56,854\r\n...that your son...\r\n\r\n968\r\n01:28:57,260 --> 01:28:59,956\r\n...is attempting to bring\r\nan outside party...\r\n\r\n969\r\n01:29:00,163 --> 01:29:02,358\r\n...into this situation?\r\n\r\n970\r\n01:29:04,934 --> 01:29:06,629\r\nDid you know that?\r\n\r\n971\r\n01:29:12,876 --> 01:29:14,969\r\nHe is, Mr. Torrance.\r\n\r\n972\r\n01:29:17,313 --> 01:29:18,473\r\nWho?\r\n\r\n973\r\n01:29:20,717 --> 01:29:22,344\r\nA nigger.\r\n\r\n974\r\n01:29:26,422 --> 01:29:27,821\r\nA nigger?\r\n\r\n975\r\n01:29:30,560 --> 01:29:31,993\r\nA nigger...\r\n\r\n976\r\n01:29:32,195 --> 01:29:33,287\r\n...cook.\r\n\r\n977\r\n01:29:39,802 --> 01:29:41,064\r\nHow?\r\n\r\n978\r\n01:29:43,339 --> 01:29:45,102\r\nYour son...\r\n\r\n979\r\n01:29:45,542 --> 01:29:48,340\r\n...has a very great talent.\r\n\r\n980\r\n01:29:49,312 --> 01:29:52,804\r\nI don't think you are aware\r\nhow great it is.\r\n\r\n981\r\n01:29:53,550 --> 01:29:56,781\r\nBut he is attempting to use\r\nthat very talent...\r\n\r\n982\r\n01:29:56,986 --> 01:29:58,954\r\n...against your will.\r\n\r\n983\r\n01:30:07,497 --> 01:30:08,759\r\nWell...\r\n\r\n984\r\n01:30:11,534 --> 01:30:14,594\r\n...he is a very willful boy.\r\n\r\n985\r\n01:30:17,006 --> 01:30:19,406\r\nIndeed he is, Mr. Torrance.\r\n\r\n986\r\n01:30:19,609 --> 01:30:22,510\r\nA very willful boy.\r\n\r\n987\r\n01:30:22,712 --> 01:30:24,043\r\nA rather...\r\n\r\n988\r\n01:30:24,247 --> 01:30:25,771\r\n...naughty boy...\r\n\r\n989\r\n01:30:25,982 --> 01:30:29,179\r\n...if I may be so bold, sir.\r\n\r\n990\r\n01:30:36,426 --> 01:30:38,189\r\nIt's his mother.\r\n\r\n991\r\n01:30:40,330 --> 01:30:41,797\r\nShe...\r\n\r\n992\r\n01:30:41,998 --> 01:30:43,989\r\n...interferes.\r\n\r\n993\r\n01:30:47,103 --> 01:30:50,197\r\nPerhaps they need a good...\r\n\r\n994\r\n01:30:50,406 --> 01:30:51,998\r\n...talking-to.\r\n\r\n995\r\n01:30:52,442 --> 01:30:53,272\r\nlf...\r\n\r\n996\r\n01:30:53,476 --> 01:30:56,240\r\n...you don't mind my saying so.\r\n\r\n997\r\n01:30:57,046 --> 01:30:58,673\r\nPerhaps...\r\n\r\n998\r\n01:30:59,215 --> 01:31:00,910\r\n...a bit more.\r\n\r\n999\r\n01:31:04,120 --> 01:31:05,348\r\nMy girls, sir...\r\n\r\n1000\r\n01:31:05,555 --> 01:31:09,355\r\n...they didn't care for\r\nthe Overlook at first.\r\n\r\n1001\r\n01:31:10,026 --> 01:31:13,928\r\nOne of them actually stole\r\na pack of matches...\r\n\r\n1002\r\n01:31:14,130 --> 01:31:16,792\r\n...and tried to burn it down.\r\n\r\n1003\r\n01:31:17,867 --> 01:31:19,528\r\nBut I...\r\n\r\n1004\r\n01:31:19,736 --> 01:31:21,704\r\n...corrected them, sir.\r\n\r\n1005\r\n01:31:23,039 --> 01:31:27,169\r\nAnd when my wife tried to prevent me\r\nfrom doing my duty...\r\n\r\n1006\r\n01:31:27,377 --> 01:31:28,639\r\n...I...\r\n\r\n1007\r\n01:31:29,646 --> 01:31:31,739\r\n...corrected her.\r\n\r\n1008\r\n01:31:45,995 --> 01:31:47,929\r\nWe have the Snowcat.\r\n\r\n1009\r\n01:31:51,334 --> 01:31:53,097\r\nIf the weather breaks...\r\n\r\n1010\r\n01:31:53,302 --> 01:31:55,065\r\n...we might just be able...\r\n\r\n1011\r\n01:31:55,271 --> 01:31:57,136\r\n...to get down the mountain.\r\n\r\n1012\r\n01:32:00,009 --> 01:32:02,978\r\nI could call\r\nthe forest rangers first...\r\n\r\n1013\r\n01:32:03,179 --> 01:32:04,476\r\n...and...\r\n\r\n1014\r\n01:32:04,814 --> 01:32:06,679\r\n...tell them that we're coming...\r\n\r\n1015\r\n01:32:07,050 --> 01:32:08,210\r\n....so that...\r\n\r\n1016\r\n01:32:08,418 --> 01:32:12,514\r\n...they could start searching\r\nfor us in case we didn't make it.\r\n\r\n1017\r\n01:32:16,292 --> 01:32:18,453\r\nAnd if Jack won't come with us...\r\n\r\n1018\r\n01:32:20,930 --> 01:32:24,661\r\n...I'll just have to tell him that\r\nwe're going by ourselves.\r\n\r\n1019\r\n01:32:24,867 --> 01:32:26,835\r\nThat's all there is to it.\r\n\r\n1020\r\n01:32:28,204 --> 01:32:29,694\r\nRedrum.\r\n\r\n1021\r\n01:32:30,673 --> 01:32:32,334\r\nRedrum.\r\n\r\n1022\r\n01:32:43,586 --> 01:32:44,746\r\nWhat's the matter, hon?\r\n\r\n1023\r\n01:32:44,954 --> 01:32:45,852\r\nRedrum!\r\n\r\n1024\r\n01:32:46,055 --> 01:32:48,114\r\nAre you having a bad dream?\r\n\r\n1025\r\n01:32:54,063 --> 01:32:55,291\r\nHon?\r\n\r\n1026\r\n01:33:01,104 --> 01:33:05,006\r\nDanny's not here, Mrs. Torrance.\r\n\r\n1027\r\n01:33:10,012 --> 01:33:11,536\r\nCome on, hon.\r\n\r\n1028\r\n01:33:12,515 --> 01:33:13,948\r\nWake up.\r\n\r\n1029\r\n01:33:14,884 --> 01:33:17,148\r\nYou just had a bad dream.\r\n\r\n1030\r\n01:33:18,554 --> 01:33:20,681\r\nEverything's okay.\r\n\r\n1031\r\n01:33:24,761 --> 01:33:28,629\r\nDanny can't wake up, Mrs. Torrance.\r\n\r\n1032\r\n01:33:38,107 --> 01:33:39,904\r\nWake up!\r\n\r\n1033\r\n01:33:41,077 --> 01:33:42,408\r\nCome on.\r\n\r\n1034\r\n01:33:42,612 --> 01:33:44,136\r\nRight now.\r\n\r\n1035\r\n01:33:44,614 --> 01:33:45,979\r\nWake up!\r\n\r\n1036\r\n01:33:50,019 --> 01:33:54,046\r\nDanny's gone away, Mrs. Torrance.\r\n\r\n1037\r\n01:34:04,367 --> 01:34:07,029\r\nThis is KDK 1 calling\r\nKDK 12.\r\n\r\n1038\r\n01:34:07,236 --> 01:34:10,171\r\nKDK 1 calling KDK 12.\r\n\r\n1039\r\n01:34:10,473 --> 01:34:12,236\r\nAre you receiving me?\r\n\r\n1040\r\n01:34:15,444 --> 01:34:18,902\r\nThis is KDK 1 calling\r\nKDK 12.\r\n\r\n1041\r\n01:34:19,248 --> 01:34:22,046\r\nKDK 1 calling KDK 12.\r\n\r\n1042\r\n01:34:22,251 --> 01:34:23,912\r\nDo you read me?\r\n\r\n1043\r\n01:34:28,291 --> 01:34:31,317\r\nThis is KDK 1 calling\r\nKDK 12.\r\n\r\n1044\r\n01:34:31,527 --> 01:34:34,087\r\nKDK 1 calling KDK 12.\r\n\r\n1045\r\n01:34:34,297 --> 01:34:36,060\r\nAre you receiving me?\r\n\r\n1046\r\n01:35:12,501 --> 01:35:14,366\r\nGood evening. Forest service.\r\n\r\n1047\r\n01:35:14,570 --> 01:35:16,800\r\nThis is Dick Hallorann again.\r\n\r\n1048\r\n01:35:17,006 --> 01:35:20,100\r\nI called a while ago about\r\nthe folks at the Overlook Hotel.\r\n\r\n1049\r\n01:35:21,344 --> 01:35:25,144\r\nWe tried to contact them several\r\ntimes but they didn't answer.\r\n\r\n1050\r\n01:35:25,348 --> 01:35:28,943\r\nMaybe they got their radio\r\nturned off or they can't hear it.\r\n\r\n1051\r\n01:35:29,151 --> 01:35:32,052\r\nIf you'd like, I'd be glad\r\nto try again later on.\r\n\r\n1052\r\n01:35:32,555 --> 01:35:34,682\r\nThat's very nice of you.\r\n\r\n1053\r\n01:35:34,891 --> 01:35:36,654\r\nI'll call you back later.\r\n\r\n1054\r\n01:35:36,859 --> 01:35:37,883\r\nBye.\r\n\r\n1055\r\n01:36:24,974 --> 01:36:28,000\r\nPardon me, miss.\r\nWhat time will we get to Denver?\r\n\r\n1056\r\n01:36:28,210 --> 01:36:30,371\r\nWe're due to arrive at 8:20, sir.\r\n\r\n1057\r\n01:36:30,579 --> 01:36:32,171\r\nThank you very much.\r\n\r\n1058\r\n01:37:36,078 --> 01:37:37,010\r\nDurkin's Garage.\r\n\r\n1059\r\n01:37:37,213 --> 01:37:38,339\r\nCan I speak to Larry?\r\n\r\n1060\r\n01:37:38,547 --> 01:37:39,514\r\nSpeaking.\r\n\r\n1061\r\n01:37:39,815 --> 01:37:42,306\r\nHi, Larry. This is Dick.\r\nDick Hallorann.\r\n\r\n1062\r\n01:37:42,585 --> 01:37:44,246\r\nDick! How you doing?\r\n\r\n1063\r\n01:37:44,453 --> 01:37:45,818\r\nHow's the weather down there?\r\n\r\n1064\r\n01:37:46,022 --> 01:37:49,185\r\nI'm not in Florida.\r\nI'm calling from Stapleton Airport.\r\n\r\n1065\r\n01:37:49,558 --> 01:37:51,150\r\nWhat are you doing there?\r\n\r\n1066\r\n01:37:51,594 --> 01:37:55,030\r\nI just got in from Miami.\r\nI got to get to the Overlook today.\r\n\r\n1067\r\n01:37:55,231 --> 01:37:56,858\r\nWhat's the weather like there?\r\n\r\n1068\r\n01:37:57,500 --> 01:38:00,367\r\nThe snowplows are keeping things\r\nmoving in town...\r\n\r\n1069\r\n01:38:00,569 --> 01:38:02,503\r\n...but the mountain roads\r\nare blocked.\r\n\r\n1070\r\n01:38:03,039 --> 01:38:05,735\r\nThen I'm going to need a Snowcat\r\nto get up there.\r\n\r\n1071\r\n01:38:05,941 --> 01:3